name: Rocket Pack
description: Allows flight via highly volatile rockets strapped to one's back.

name: Claw Hammer
description: An ordinary household hammer.

name: Perfectly Generic Object
description: A medium-sized green cube. It is entirely generic in every way.
effects: SHUNT::Your Alchemiter is now a Perfectly Generic Alchemiter. Which is to say, it\'s exactly the same as a regular Alchemiter.

name: Pogo Hammer
description: A bouncy hammer. Charge it up by bouncing it on either side of yourself and go nuts!

name: Shitty sword
description: A shitty sword.

name: Picture of Hella Jeff
description: It's a picture of one of the characters from Sweet Bro and Hella Jeff. You would do well to heed his warnings regarding stairs.

name: SORD.....
description: This thing is so unspeakably shitty you are having a hard time even holding it.

name: Fountain Pen
description: They say the pen is mightier than the 0I0Y5nML. You don't really know what that means, though.

name: Fruit Gushers - Hellacious Blue Phlegm Aneurysm flavour
description: Hellacious Blue Phlegm Aneurysm flavoured Fruit Gushers, formed from some kind of ectoplasmic slime. They have potent restorative properties when consumed, although you're not sure what the mercury has to do with that.

name: Blue Ecto-Slime
description: Some funny-looking ectoplasmic slime. This blue stuff is supposedly restorative in some way.

name: Fruit Gushers - Massive Tropical Brain Hemorrhage flavour
description: Delicious, sugary candy.

name: Bottle of Ink
description: A normal bottle of ink. The words "Squid Pro Quo" are written on it for some reason.

name: Fruit Gushers - Bodacious Black Liquid Sorrow flavour
description: Bodacious Black Liquid Sorrow flavoured Fruit Gushers. Highly poisonous, consumption of these candies is not recommended.

name: Gothic Sorrow Livejournal Poetry Pen
description: Write about the infinite blackness of your rainy soul miasma with this pen designed for two things: Deeply sad emotional poetry, and slowly draining the life from your enemies. For added sadness, try both at the same time!

name: Green Slime Ghost Pogo
description: Some sort of nostalgic childhood ride. You're not entirely sure why you have one.

name: Spatula
description: This common spatula is useful for few things other than flipping burgers, omelettes and other food items to ensure equal doneness. Though in the right hands, it becomes a tool for serving up heaping dishes of pain.

name: PEN FIFTEEN
description: Luridly coloured and highly offensive, the PEN FIFTEEN is the height of weaponry for the shitty jpeg penkind user.

name: Kringlefucker
description: This thing is so unspeakably shitty you are having a hard time getting rid of it. But why would you want to? It's the prettiest christmas tree you've ever seen.

name: Gardening Gloves
description: A pair of gardening gloves. The padding allows you to strike harder than you could otherwise.

name: Hair Shears
description: A pair of shears for grooming hair. Much like knitting needles, this seemingly domestic weapon is highly effective against the early enemies within the Medium.

name: Laptop
description: A laptop computer. An essential basic device for running Sburb on the go.

name: Netbook
description: A netbook computer. It runs Sburb slowly due to lower processing power, but it's a fair bit more portable.

name: Drawing Tablet
description: A drawing tablet. Links up to computing devices to let you interface with them and draw things!

name: Sketchbook
description: A book designed for sketching. Essential equipment for the budding artist, and not a bad bludgeoning tool besides.

name: Tripod
description: A standard scientific tool, the tripod is generally used to hold items steady during experiments, often in concert with a Bunsen burner. It's also a reasonably sized hunk of metal. Just sayin'

name: Slytherin Pin
description: A decorative pin bearing the emblem of Slytherin house. It has no practical use. Magic isn't real, after all.

name: Madoka Pins
description: A pair of pins inspired by the show "Puella Magi Madoka Magica". One is a Grief Seed, and the other one appears to be a blue Soul Gem. Pretty sweet merch, on the whole.

name: Paper Shears
description: A pair of shears for cutting paper. Despite the name, of no use against rocks.

name: Sewing Shears
description: Shears for use for sewing applications. Bonus damage against enemy clothing, which conveniently translates to no actual combat effect.

name: Inflatable Crayon
description: A jumbo-sized inflatable crayon. It is not incredibly useful as a weapon as is, but it sure is hilarious.

name: Rapier
description: A Rapier that was used back in the 16th century. Your possession of it is either an indicator of Weird Time Shit, or you're just a huge nerd that collects this sort of stuff. <!-- You found the first! -->

name: Rapiern of Scribing
description: A pen in the shape of a Rapier. Unfortunately not designed with strife in mind, but it makes for a pretty badass writing implement.

name: Strife Rapiern
description: A rapier with a fountain pen head for a tip. The metal that makes up the rapier's blade is semi-transparent, so you can see the Ink sloshing around inside. Unfortunately it has a habit of slicing paper to ribbons when you attempt to write with it.

name: SledgeHu
description: An erhu with the strength of a SLEDGEHAMMER. Now you can make amazing music, AND KICK ASS!

name: Serpent Blade
description: A green blade with a snake pattern on the hilt. Wielding it makes you feel a little like you possess the proverbial forked tongue.

name: Edwardian Executioners
description: These scissor-hands are made for cutting, and that's just what they'll do. Unless wielded by an uncommonly gentle man, of course. Do not aim at face.

name: Basic Spellbook
description: This book seems to have some magic powers. Saying the simple words in it make simple spells  come out of it. Awesome. Unfortunately, Fireball is 3rd-level, so this spellbook doesn't allow you to cast it. The cover appears to be studded with gemstones, which is typical of pretentious wizards.

name: Triple Pogo Hammer
description: Like an ordinary Pogo Hammer, but with three springy whacky things attached, which gives it better coverage and makes you less likely to fall flat on your face when bouncing. Pogo a go go go!

name: Shitty replica mutant claws
description: Pretty cool looking, but not very effective as an actual weapon. Made with a mutant healing factor in mind. Oh, you don't have one of those? Sucks to be you then.

name: Poisoned Shears
description: Gardening shears tainted by a highly venomous candy-based unction, turning makeshift weapon into a tool of slow death.

name: Basilisk Fang
description: Not a literal basilisk fang, but a sword reminiscent of it in both reptilian motif and the fact that it's highly venomous.

name: The Mightier Sword
description: You know what they say about the pen being mightier than the sword? This thing kicks both their butts.

name: Faygo - Red Pop flavour
description: The original Faygo flavour, supposedly. Tastes kind of funny, but you'll get used to it. Probably.

name: Tektroxcaliburn
description: A powerful writing tool and weapon. Using it will boost your diplomatic skills to high levels. But it looks slightly...off?

name: Fedora
description: A plain fedora. It looks like it could be rather Hard-Boiled.

name: Candy Corn
description: Some pieces of Candy Corn. They look pretty tasty.

name: Sweet Bounty
description: A detective's hard-earned bounty. It's a hat with some candy corn under it.

name: Tectrixcalibur
description: The ultimate Diplomatic Weapon. This Sword/Quill can dish out the sickest of officially notarized burns, and you don't even have to pull it out of some shitty stone first or get it distributed to you by a strange woman lying in a pond!

name: Fingers of Blight
description: Claws that are prefered by spooks and assassains. Quick, very sharp, highly poisonous, but try to defend yourself and you risk self-inflicted wounds.

name: Pointy Anime Shades
description: A pair of pointed, easily recognizable sunglasses. Makes you want to fight the power.

name: Unbreakable Katana
description: A real hard sword for a real hard dude

name: Faygo - Blitzin\' Blue Raspberry flavour
description: A sweet drink with a weird name and healing capabilities. Unfortunately, the healing process gives it a strange chalky aftertaste.

name: Skateboard
description: Your basic "fuckin' wheelie" tool, it also finds many important applications in the field of ollie-ing outie.

name: Magical Blade
description: A +1 magical sword. Whoaaa! +1 to what, you ask? EVERYTHING!

name: Hard-boiled Revolver
description: Does the name refer to the fact that this gun is commonly used by hard-boiled detectives, or to some obscure manufacturing process involving boiling the gun itself? We may never know.

name: Confection\'s Malice
description: A hard-boiled way to gun down the enemy with fruit snack laden lead. Just make sure not to mistake the ammunition for actual fruit snacks or you may end up with lead poisoning. Or fruit poisoning.

name: Dark Souls
description: A really hard video game about knights and getting murdered by everything. It's hard to tell if it\'s the spiritual successor to Demon's Souls or Dwarf Fortress.

name: Uchigatana
description: A beautifully crafted blade from the far east, fabricated from the realms of fantasy. Cuts cleanly, with good range, but has a brittle blade.

name: Judgment Rapier
description: A rapier blessed by Velka, Goddess of Judgement, and wielded by her faithful clerics, the Pardoners, near inhuman swordsman who fight with finesse beyond imagining. Of course, you are not a Pardoner. But, hey, you can pretend, right?

name: Royal Rapier
description: The jeweled rapier of the Undead prince, Ricard. Sharp and classy, suitable for royalty.

name: Claymore
description: A featherweight among greatswords. It's still bloody heavy, though!

name: Hand-Shaped Poison Faygo Bottle
description: A bottle of Faygo in the shape of a hand. The liquid inside also appears to have poisonous properties. You...you GUESS this could be useful?

name: Fear No Anvil
description: The hammer of the Denizen Hephaestus. Despite the incredible power it possesses, everyone nearby is still drawn to slap the user when they attempt to make any joke regarding hammertime. (Get it? 'cause the hammer stops time! Wait, I forgot to mention that, didn't I. Shit)

name: Inflatable Boxing Gloves
description: They may not be fists of steel, but they pack enough of a wallop to knock the wind out of your enemies.

name: Blow-Up Doll
description: It's a doll that blows up. Why, what were you expecting?

name: Ahab\'s Crosshairs
description: Legendary piece of shit only wielded by the most desperate of wwhalers.

name: Kingdom Hearts Collection
description: In your hands is a box containing the entire Kingdom Hearts series of games. Goodbye, Paradox Space. Hello, Gummi Space!

name: Shield
description: An ordinary-looking wooden shield. Not a particularly threatening weapon, but excellent for defending yourself.

name: Rescue the Elderly Male Royalty
description: A lapis blue shield adorned with fancy silver designs and an image of a crown. Surprisingly effective as a straight-up weapon.

name: Staff
description: It seems to have some sort of hidden power. Then again, given that it appears outwardly to be entirely mundane, this may be wishful thinking.

name: Rescue the Elderly Female Royalty
description: An azure blue staff, topped with gold filigree and an immense sky-blue gem. It seems a little bit...ducky, for some reason.

name: Lonesome Sock
description: The other one got lost in the wash. This one's looking a bit crusty though, perhaps you should re-unite them. On the other hand, maybe you can weaponize that stench...

name: Midnight Crew Poster
description: A poster featuring MS Paint Adventures characters the Midnight Crew. Early to bed and you'll miss all the fun...

name: Felt Poster
description: Not an actual poster made out of felt, of course, but rather a poster portraying the Midnight Crew's primary antagonists, the Felt.

name: Lighter
description: This little lighter is technically classified as a flamethrower, but as a weapon it is beyond lame.

name: Flame Tome
description: A spellbook with an emphasis on immolation, incineration, evaporation, conflagration, and all the other major -ations. Except exsanguination. That one's in the tome of blood.

name: Nike Greatsword
description: This weapon forged from athletic footwear slices through enemies as fast as the shoes from which it get...wait, no. Apparently the name comes from a group known as the "Knights Berenike". My bad.

name: Black Knight Sword
description: NONE SHALL PASS. A powerful weapon designed for demon slaying. The original wielders use it as a regular blade, but there's no hope of that for you.

name: Bone
description: A part of the framework of a once living creature; now it's been liberated, it makes a decent club. You hope it wasn't human...

name: Archaeologist\'s Whip
description: A whip favoured by archaeologists. What's that? Archaeologists don't need whips? Quiet, or they'll whip you!

name: Black Inches
description: A whip famous for inflicting red cheeks on opponents. Unfortunately, it is hampered by use of the clearly inferior imperial system of measurement.

name: Three-handled Pogo Hammer
description: It's just like the pogo hammer, except it has three handles going in different directions. Seems very unwieldy and pretty hard to hold, but you bet you could set up a Bunsen burner under it with no trouble.

name: Leather Jacket
description: A leather jacket, The epitome of biker fashion.

name: Studded Biker Gloves
description: Studded leather gloves. An excellent reserve weapon if you can't find a tire iron or chain to hit things with.

name: Necrotomeicon
description: Summon forth legions of shambling undead with this powerful tome of completely original name. Listen closely to the book and you can hear the whispers of spirits, most of them attempting to converse with you about the weather.

name: Horse Poster
description: Magneighficent

name: STRONG gloves
description: You don't know why, but when you put these on you feel incredibly powerful. And sweaty.

name: Rocket Hammer
description: If the last hammers you made weren't dangerous enough, then this is the hammer for you. Favourite weapon of penguin royalty everywhere! It makes a really strange sound for some reason, though.

name: Jousting Lance
description: A massive lance intended for jousting. Good luck trying to use it on the ground!

name: Spear
description: A pretty ordinary spear consisting of a pointy end and a non-pointy end. Being able to tell the two apart is the mark of someone not about to have themselves a nasty accident.

name: Pistol
description: A basic sidearm. Pew pew!

name: Rifle
description: A firearm with more power than a pistol, although it does take up both your hands. Don't forget to aim!

name: Machine Gun
description: A ranged weapon that makes up for weaker firepower with rapid fire. This being the base model, it produces quite the modest amount of dakka.

name: Wrench
description: A wrench commonly used for engineering jobs. Curiously, the primary function of repairing complicated machinery is performed in the same way the combat usage is: whack the object in question as hard as you can.

name: Hatchet
description: A very small and simple hand-axe, designed for use in a wilderness survival situation. Doubles as a fairly respectable weapon.

name: Yo-yo
description: A wooden toy yo-yo. Not an ideal weapon, but it'd do in a pinch.

name: Medieval Mace
description: A long, flanged blunt weapon from times of early warfare. This replica weapon isn't as impressive as the real thing, but it's a lump of metal on a stick at the very worst so you can still brain some imps with it.

name: Violin
description: A lovely string instrument, capable of producing great music. Or bashing in some minion skulls. It's up to you, really.

name: Hardboiled Staff
description: It's like a normal staff, but imbued with the hardboiledness of FEDORAS. You could probably summon hats with this, or something.

name: Dual Knives
description: A pair of sharp knives, well-balanced for relentless dual wielding.

name: Tarot Deck
description: The Homestuck tarot deck! No Seer should be without one.

name: Tommy Gun/Key Ring
description: You pick up your gun and unlock the door. No, not by shooting at it, what are you-

name: Mounted Machine Gun
description: Three legs for stability, three barrels for lethality. Also recoil.

name: Palmtops
description: Now your computer will always be at hand! These incredible computing devices can be used for manner of tas-...aaaaaaand you're just going to punch imps with them, aren't you. Seriously. Don't blame me if you break them....

name: Technomancer\'s Tome
description: The world's best resource for any budding young fuser of the electronic and arcane. Which is to say, the only resource. Technomancy isn't too popular these days, probably something to do with all the soul-stealing toasters.

name: Detective\'s Diplomat
description: You're here to reference webcomics and present your foes with well-worded offerings of peace, and you're all out of webcomics. Which is a shame, because you really liked that Homestuck thing.

name: Wristwatch
description: A digital timekeeping device worn around the wrist. Well, if you want to be boring about it and NOT headbutt some time into your enemies, anyway.

name: Tiro Finale
description: A three gun salute, strong enough to finish off whatever creatures are still left. Wield two and you'll end up with a six-gun salute from your six-guns! That sort of exponential firepower cannot be easily ignored.

name: Pool Cue
description: An ordinary pool cue, perfectly serviceable for both playing pool and bashing heads.

name: Carbon Nadsat
description: What does a carbon-based fictional system of slang have to do with a pool cue? Who cares, this is still great for snuffing some imps with your droogs. Although you can't help but think that the name could have been less confusing.

name: Fluorite Octet
description: Powerful magic dice best known due to having been used in attacks by Vriska Serket.

name: Tablet Computer
description: A portable computer with the ease of a tablet and the processing power of a high-end laptop. It can run Sburb with a touchscreen interface.

name: Squiddles Lunchbox
description: A cute little red lunchbox emblazoned with the Squiddles logo and characters.

name: Detective-like Revolver
description: A step up from the usual "hard-boiled" revolver. Only rookies would be caught dead with that. And dead they would be, using such a piece of junk.

name: Desutop
description: Pierce the heavens with your astounding internet speed!

name: Fruit Gushers - Spooky Scary Skeletons Candy Corn Catastrophe flavour
description: Spooky Scary Skeletons Candy Corn Catastrophe flavoured Fruit Gushers. According to the box, the "catastrophe" is what will happen to your enemies after you consume these.

name: Meat Cleaver
description: A king-sized knife made for chopping up thick organic matter. Oh hey, that's just what imps are made out of! What convenience.

name: Midnight Staff
description: For the mages which are into organized crime. Don't mess with the Merlin Midnight Mafia!

name: Midnight Slammer
description: Put your enemies away permanently with this hammer.

name: Nobody\'s Tome
description: Luckily this doesn't belong to anybody, so you're free to use it. For summoning Nobodies, probably.

name: Wooden Boomerang
description: A plain wooden boomerang. Renowned for beaning people in the head unexpectedly and generally being a huge Australian stereotype.

name: Tome of Blood
description: A tome specializing in exsanguination, something the Flame Tome foolishly neglected.

name: VUVUVZUVELVA......
description: 

name: Archer\'s Bow
description: As opposed to the bows favoured by non-archers, of course.

name: Viola Bow
description: A somewhat confusingly-named and designed bow representing a musical instrument. It remains plenty deadly, however.

name: Power Gloves
description: POWER!!!! UNLIMITED POWER!!!! ...well, the amount of power a laptop battery stores when fully charged. But still, FOUR TO SIX HOURS OF LAPTOP BATTERY LIFE WORTH OF POWER!!!!! ...well, okay, maybe it's just a souped up game peripheral, but...look, just go punch things with them, alright?

name: Mountain Dew
description: Incredibly sugary soda, great for a sugar rush or a heart attack.

name: Mounted Mountain Dew Machine Gun
description: What's that? A machine gun that fires mountain dew isn't very effective? Ever been hit by a bottle of the stuff going at 400 meters per second?

name: Elite Hacker
description: A medium, black-handled stainless steel axe with an especially broad and sharp blade that has been optimized for cutting through relatively thick materials. It probably also does a number on firewalls.

name: Eyeglasses
description: Standard correctional eyewear.

name: The Legend of King Arthur
description: An epic legend of an ancient hero.... one your foes will relive! Also it's quite heavy and you could probably do a fair chunk of damage just bludgeoning things with it in addition to the book's magical properties.

name: Sniper Rifle
description: Able to hit an Ogre from a mile away, and an Imp or a Giclops's eye from half that. Being big hurts.

name: Throwing Knife
description: A cheap throwing knife. Where'd you get this, the internet?

name: Pointy anime knives
description: For some reason, wielding these makes you want to shout heartfelt rants at your opponents before you dramatically fight them. Or at least before you dramatically pose at them.

name: Mounted Sniper Rifle
description: Shaky hands? No longer an issue. Just make sure you bring a jar for your bodily functions if you're going to be camping out with it for an extended period of time.

name: Time-Line
description: A soft green whip, not at all wibbly wobbly OR timey wimey as one might expect. This is... actually not all that useful for whipping things.

name: Plastic Wolverine Claws
description: Plastic Wolverine Claws: The plastic Wolverine claw-gloves little kids use to play at being X-Men. They may not be made of metal, but they're still pretty sharp.

name: Handheld Sickle
description: This curved blade has a comfortable grip for holding in the hand. It's fairly small but still pretty sharp.

name: Miniaturized Tiberium Statue
description: A smaller, non-harmful version of a parasitic plant which covers Earth in a certain video game series. You wonder if a larger one exists somewhere....

name: Sickly Shard Shooter
description: A weapon that launches dangerous green crystals at your enemies. Do not fire upon self unless you wish to become mutated, and not in the "cool, I got superpowers!" way.

name: Slick Fedora
description: It feels like the fedora you used to create it, only with an eerie field of energy around it.

name: Rosin Blade
description: A rather brittle sword made from rosin, which is like resin but more musical. It has a tendency to get stuck in things, but at least it makes your enemies smell nice.

name: Sharpened Violin
description: Make all the strings razor-sharp and suddenly you have a powerful, if unexpected, weapon. Made all the more unexpected by the somewhat misleading name.

name: Betty Crocker\'s Halloween Spatula
description: A spooky halloween spatula, designed for whipping up terrifying cakes and whipping terrified imps.

name: Fists of Flame
description: Flaming leather gloves! You feel like a true Hell's Angel. Even though those guys are just normal bikers.

name: Umbrella
description: I guess you could use this to protect you from the rain? It's pretty bad at offense.

name: Straight Razor
description: Fancied by dads and emos alike, although the usage by the latter group should be avoided.

name: Barber\'s Best Friend
description: Not actually particularly useful for shaving, the multiple blades in a radial pattern have a habit of chopping off things you probably want to keep attached. On the plus side, they also chop off things your enemies wanted to keep attached.

name: Trifle
description: A rifle with three barrels that is able to fire three shots at a time. It even can shoot in three different directions. Attempts to eat the trifle are strongly discouraged.

name: Magical Madoka Magica Artbook
description: Contains rare and adorable art of your favorite magical girls and serves as a weapon too! Let's hope it doesn't attract more than just imps...

name: The Rewinder
description: This boomerang seems to glow a faint green, and you know there's more to it than meets the eye. You can feel it brimming with unknown magicks...plus, the fact that it returns to you by travelling back in time rather than a curious quirk of aerodynamics is a dead giveaway.

name: Painting of a Horse Attacking a Football Player
description: A beautiful work of art depicting a horse with a fiery mane and a footballer.

name: Harpoon Gun
description: No, I will not call you Ishmael, stop asking.

name: Butcher Knife
description: A simple butcher's knife. Tried and tested for cutting flesh!

name: Kunai
description: A basic ninja tool which has gained increased public attention from the animes.

name: Bladed Boomerang
description: Better hope you don't miss, because catching this thing might be tricky.

name: Wooden Club
description: A medium-sized piece of wood for thwacking people with.

name: Juggling Club
description: A club usually used for juggling, but perfectly serviceable for throwing at or bludgeoning enemies.

name: Electro-Wrench
description: A wrench arcing with electricity. Luckily for you, it has a rubber handle. Just don't touch the metal bits!

name: Brass Knuckles / Megaton Key
description: Said to only be wieldable by the strongest man in the world. Good luck with that.

name: Squiddles Lunchtop
description: The adorable solution for computing on the go. Squiddle time!

name: Squiddles Funtime Colouring Book
description: A fun colouring book featuring the children's cartoon favourites, the Squiddles! You wouldn't hurt anyone with this lovely thing, would you?

name: Grimoire for Summoning the Zoologically Dubious
description: This book is absolutely indispensable for enthusiasts of a certain ilk. Of which there are very few. Some copies of this book are far too dangerous to ever consider using in a strife specibus; fortunately, this is not one of those.

name: Fanged Slammer
description: Drop down on your enemies silently in the night with the intensity of a basilisk and the ferocity of an angry asshole.

name: Jacks
description: A set of knobbly metal jacks to be thrown in the air and caught. Preferably by your opponent's face.

name: Wristwatch Computer
description: A computer inside your wristwatch! Now you can watch porn, even on your own wrist! (N.B: The Overseer does not endorse the viewing of porn by those below legal age. Enjoy your smut responsibly, folks!)

name: Necro-Claws
description: A set of claws carved from bone. Handy for kitty roleplayers because it makes dogs attack them, adding authenticity.

name: Shaving Cream
description: The manliest of self-maintenance products.

name: Girl\'s Best Friend
description: Rifles made of diamonds (or at least diamond grist) are a girl's best friend...

name: Fuzzy Dice
description: A pair of pink fuzzy dice. Sure to spice up any vehicle interior or bout of mortal combat.

name: Bar Stool
description: An old wooden barstool, the kind you would probably find in an english pub somewhere. It's not very comfortable to sit on, but maybe it'll make a good bludgeon.

name: Erhu
description: A bowed musical instrument that goes by numerous names depending on the location. It looks kind of awkward to play. How do you even hold this thing?

name: Keyaxe
description: A key-like weapon that has a large, hatchet-like head. The bastard child of the keyblade and the hatchet. You probably can't unlock anything with this, so the only chests it's going to open are those of your enemies.

name: Headhunter
description: Some times, people are so bothersome you just can't deign to let them exist with a head on their shoulders. This weapon was made for those times.

name: Battleaxe
description: Forget that sissy hatchet stuff, this is an axe made for the battlefield. Chop heads, not wood!

name: Nightmare Chopper
description: An axe made of the pure, unhallowed soul of the most difficult modes of the most difficult games in existence. Practically writhes with dark essence. Any sane gamer (who wished to remain so) would do well to throw this into the depths of the Void.

name: mothrefukrek.......
description: Perfect for fucking one's mother, or that of a friend.

name: Clothing Iron
description: An ordinary iron. Might be useful for ironing out all those crazy outfits you kids keep making.

name: Wrinklefucker
description: Nope. No need for a description, the name pretty much covers it for this one.

name: Sledgehammer
description: It's poorly balanced and difficult to wield, but probably your best bet for cracking some skulls anyway.

name: Clarinet
description: The clarinet is a type of woodwind instrument that has a single-reed mouthpiece, a straight cylindrical tube with an approximately cylindrical bore, and a flaring bell. Just make sure it never falls into the hands of an anthropomorphic squid.

name: Sunglasses
description: A pair of shades that are nonprescription and whose intended function is instead to block UVAB rays and make the user look cool, either sincerely or ironically.

name: Oar
description: A paddle used to row a small boat by hand. It looks heavy enough to deal some damage.

name: Grimdirks
description: A pair of knives made from some jet-black substance with menacing-looking skulls on the hilts. Unfortunately, they seem to put too much emphasis on looking scary to do too much damage.

name: Eku
description: An Okinawan weapon designed specifically for self defense. It is fashioned after a traditional oar but it's heavy blade can deliver a killing blow.

name: Betty Crocker Barbasol Bomb
description: Be careful with that thing! Jesus!

name: Metal Claws
description: These claws are tougher and sharper than their plastic counterparts. Heavier, too. They retract into the gloves when not in use.

name: Coca-Cola Can
description: A red, 12 FL OZ/355 mL can of Coca-Cola. Empty calories at their finest.

name: Miracle Hands
description: Wearing these gloves put you at ease with the world. The plants are singing, and the sun is shining. It's beautiful man. Miracles are beautiful. And now your hands are miracles.

name: Hands of F8
description: It must be f8.

name: Suitarangs
description: A small assortment of boomerangs styled after card suits. Use these when you need to hit things in the face... with class.

name: A Shady Surprise
description: A dark revolver that gives a vibe of trustworthiness, and smells faintly of cigar smoke. Whoever this belonged to must have been a gangster, or maybe a detective.

name: Bloody Horvester
description: A sickle with wicked smashing power and a sharp edge.

name: Circuit Frames
description: Glasses that double as a fully-functional computer. It has the processing power of a 20th-century cell phone and having a computer screen in your face 24/7 makes it hard to see, making it rather useless as either, but it's a start at least.

name: Viking Beard-Trimmer
description: A moderately-sized axe with a straight, sharpened blade. An effective, if barbaric way to trim a thick beard.

name: Sword of Damocles
description: It's just a shitty sword tied to a string. Why did you even need to alchemize this?

name: Faygo - Aquamarine Sugar Bomb flavour
description: It's glowing brightly. You're not sure what that much mercury and sugar will do to you...

name: Whale Punchers
description: A new take on the classic problem of whaling, but about a billion times more fun.

name: Trickster\'s Plight
description: A razor-sharp yoyo. You better be careful doing tricks with this, or you might cut your head off!

name: The Penguin King\'s Hammer
description: A king once wielded a hammer similar to this. Could never smash the little pink blob, however.

name: Sun on a Stick
description: A firey ball on a stick to bash minions with. Careful, it's REALLY hot!

name: Steam Thrower
description: Expertly removes all wrinkles from any article of clothing. Note: Please remove clothes before use. Or if you don't, at least send us a vide of the resulting hilarity.

name: Banjo
description: A blatant ripoff of a guitar. Except it's only played by southerners. You're not quite sure why you own one.

name: Sayaka\'s sword
description: A sword used by a fallen Puella Magi, it is very agile and can beat most witches with ease.

name: Rocket Shoes
description: Unbelievably cool shoes with rockets in them. It's like you can almost fly straight to the top of your echeladder!

name: Rocket Wings
description: No more roleplaying that you're a rocket-powered dragon. Now, it's the real deal!

name: Mushy Gushy Halloween Spatula
description: A terrifying spatula that looks to have mashed some cherry flavoured Gushers at some point. Or brains. Probably brains.

name: Maneki-neko Claws
description: Named after the "Lucky Cat" found in Chinese and Japanese restaurants across the world, these fabled claws are said to be as hard as diamond and extremely difficult to produce. You'd have to be lucky to get your hands on a set.

name: Deuce Daggerlances
description: These are too short to joust with. You probably alchemized these to exploit the strife specibus system.

name: Alonwrite
description: The Tectrixcalibur's Sister Sword. While not as powerful as it's counterpart, it is still extremely deadly and turns even the basest of insults into sick burns.

name: nachons
description: These reduse hit points......

name: Pokemon Pearl Version
description: It's a handheld game all about catching innocent critters and forcing them into battles until they fall unconscious. This one apparently has some sort of connection to space.

name: Spatial Render
description: This radiant battleaxe has a glowing pink pearl in the center, surrounded by blades of white and purple stripes extending outward. Supposedly, it can rend the very fabric of space.

name: Hair Bow
description: Ooh, what a pretty accessory! With this you'll be the belle of the ball and immune to all status effects to boot! ...why are you wrapping it around your fist?

name: Lacrosse Stick
description: A stick commonly used in the game of Lacrosse, it consists of a net-thingy on the end of a stick-thingy. And yes, that is proper lacrosse terminology.

name: DUEDLY FIREARMS.....
description: Are you next?

name: Walking Cane
description: A piece of varnished wood designed to...oh, whatever. You're just going to go beat up imps with it anyway.

name: Replica Reaper Scythe
description: A large grim-reaper stype replica scythe. It is completely blunt, but still pointy and heavy.

name: Knitting Needles
description: A pair of sharp pointy objects that can also whip up a mean sweater if you get cold. What more could you ask for?

name: Demon Bone
description: The bone of a demon. A thick, heavy club capable of doing some serious damage.

name: Black Knight Shield
description: The standard-issue shield of one of many knightly orders referred to as Black Knights. The shield, as compared to the other tools of the Black Knight, is actually a fair sized shield. A bit on the heavy side, though.

name: Fallout 3 disc
description: Radiation! Ghouls! Weird tentacle things! Anything an apocalypse buff could want, and more! Although admittedly after sburb you feel like you might be burnt out on apocalyptic scenarios...

name: Powerfist
description: Some kind of robotic punchy fist thing.

name: Keyblade
description: UNLOCK THE HEART OF THE CARDS! Wait, no, that's not right...

name: Spear of Frustration
description: Powered by the frustration of a million angry gamers. Just don't attack yourself you'll be totally fine. Really, it's not cursed at all.

name: Crocker Cream Grenade
description: A ridiculously volatile mix of fruit gushers, shaving cream, and lighter fluid... Oh god how can shaving cream be so flammable?!

name: Bottle of Vodka
description: A basic way to get yourself drunk.

name: Troll Horn Claws
description: These rather whimsical claws are designed to look like they're made from the horns of trolls.</br>...They aren't actually made from troll horns, are they?

name: Shadowkat Claws
description: Hollow-point claws tipped with poison. They cut through flesh like they're just phasing right through it.

name: Flamberge
description: Known as the "Flame-tongue blade", it offers great offense as well as great defense due to the wavy shape of the blade.

name: Shotgun
description: It is a standard hunting tool, nothing more, nothing less. Also very good for killing imps, as one would expect.

name: Alpha and Yomega
description: This Yo-yo is the plumb line against which the gods measured the universe...before meteors ripped it to bits. They don't really need it anymore.

name: Rocket Gloves
description: These gloves have small rocket-powered engines attached to add some extra firepower to your punches. They also have rad fire decals, which helps them punch even faster!

name: Amulet
description: A charmed magical object that seems to give off a strange aura...

name: Small branch
description: A simple twig that fell from a tree somewhere in your Land. Does your Land even HAVE trees? And do you seriously have nothing better to captchalogue?

name: Simple Wand
description: A charged magic wand that allows you to cast simple spells on your enemy.

name: Poule Noire
description: An enchanted talisman grimoire. It feels like it emits power you shouldn't have...

name: Rosaceae Bow
description: Legend says that the world was once inhabited by witches, and that this bow was used to remove them.

name: Triple Fanged Pogo Slammer
description: Thrice-fanged giant pogo hammer. You can probably injure a lot of people with this weapon... you're gonna kill yourself you just know it.

name: Wooden Backscratcher
description: A 2-foot wooden implement with a rough, curved end. Now you don't have to scratch someone else's back to have your own scratched!

name: Flashlight
description: Battery-operated light in the palm of your hand.

name: Bright Reacher
description: A long, metallic rigid backscratcher with a larger claw and a light attached to it. Extremely handy for retrieving small objects from under furniture.

name: Ore
description: An ordinary lump of mixed minerals, perhaps useful if refined, but not in its current state. Wait, why do you even have this lying around?

name: Ore Oar
description: This oar is made of ore, which makes it fairly effective as a bashing weapon, but useless as a rowing tool... OR is it? (Editor's Note - The aggrieve bonus is for all the puns)

name: Mjolnir
description: A warhammer straight from Nordic legend, said to have been forged in a dying star. It houses a deep, thunderous power, and is strangely adept at percussive maintenance.

name: Game Dice
description: A set of two hard game dice that's probably only as scary as either of its parent items. At least it hurts when enemies step on them. Or roll them and step on your Mayfair hotel.

name: Wheelchair
description: You've got to get around somehow, you guess...

name: Rocket Chair
description: Fly through the sky, in all your paraplegic glory! Or if you're not paraplegic, fly through the sky like the lazy bum you are!

name: Violin Bow-Sword
description: An ordinary-looking violin bow that has been altered to withstand the extreme abuse subjected to it during a swordfight. Perfect for musicians who tend to be attacked mid-piece!

name: Enchanted Dice
description: These dice are ornate and wooden and look like they were pulled out of an ancient nerd convention. But hey, they're magic and more powerful than your other dice shit.

name: Bonespear
description: It's a spear, right? Made from bone. Hence the term, bone spear.

name: Ice Sculpture
description: An ordinary ice sculpture. It is susprisingly sturdy, enabling it to be used as a makeshift weapon.

name: Icedge
description: A sword made of ice, Not really the best weapon due to inherent slipperiness, but holding it makes you feel cooled off.

name: Jackkknife
description: A jackknife for the real badass dudes. Put on your Leather Jacket and your Sunglasses to be the REAL 50's Greaser that you really are. Rock the world man!

name: Special Stardust
description: A box of useless sparkly powder. If only magic was real, then maybe it could be full of magical properties...

name: Pan\'s Sword
description: A golden sword for heroes of legend. It's a bit on the small side for a sword, like it was designed for children.

name: Drill
description: Normally used for digging up dirt, this utility also has potential for putting holes in enemy combatants.

name: Timey-Wimey Wall Clock
description: It looks like a regular wall clock, only painted green. There seems to be a field of distortion directly around it, and it tells time in a way that you don't understand. All...wibbly-wobbly.

name: Doll
description: It's a completely featureless doll, though some Social Justice Bloggers may argue that completely white representing no features is racist.

name: Problem Sleuth Poster
description: Is it even possible to get any more hard boiled than that? You really doubt it. This poster was one of your wisest purchases.

name: Viorinet
description: The musical maestro's weapon of choice. It'll create a great tune if you can double task and cause some massive haemorrhages if you can't.

name: Either Oar
description: A two sided oar that can strike with either end. It's dual nature allows one to attack and defend interchangeably.

name: Anchor
description: A massive anchor. It's far too heavy to consider swinging.

name: CompuShades
description: Handsfree computing solution. Looks cool. Enough said.

name: Back Breaker
description: An axe meant specifically for breaking bone. It's patterned with a morbid motif.

name: Anvil
description: It weighs a lot, you may be surprised to hear.

name: A Grazing Mace
description: It's an average looking mace, except for the majestic metal horse head at the end. You TOTALLY won't pretend to ride it any time in the near future. Nope.

name: Giant Watch Hand
description: Probably more useful for stabbing things than for telling time.

name: Hammerspace Umbrella
description: An umbrella that opens up to a dimension of untold storage. Would probably be useful if you didn't have an inventory system already!

name: Torch Bone
description: It's a bone with a small flame at the top. Not much better then normal, really.

name: Bottle of Blue Slime Ink
description: A bottle of slightly-slimier-than-normal blue colored ink.

name: Midnight Pen
description: A slick black pen with images of the four card suits along the side. Its ink color gradually shifts between black and red when you write with it.

name: More Throwing Knives
description: "And what do we throw apart from throwing knives?"

name: Mami-nigun
description: An older musket-like rifle that apparently requires no ammunition. Might run on MAGIC, if that were real and not FAKE.

name: TRIO FINALE
description: The gun is now big and is also three guns. Amazing. The sight of it makes your head ache. It makes your throat swell up. You'll be ahead of the game with this one!

name: Macetop
description: It's a computer encased in spiked metal on the end of a stick. Not too different from the Medieval Mace in terms of power, but at least the computer is durable!

name: Flamin\' Mace
description: It's a mace on fire! Not very much fire, but every bit helps!

name: Bonemasher
description: A hatchet made of bone, for breaking bones. Don't ask whos bone it is, it would creep you out. (Editor's note: IT'S YOU FROM A DOOMED TIMELINE! Nah, just kidding. Or am I?)

name: Fireaxe
description: The best way to combat fire, and wooden doors! ESPECIALLY wooden doors.

name: Woodcutting Axe
description: Made for chopping wood for use in furnaces. No, not THAT kind of wood. Although it certainly could be used for that...

name: Urnhold, Destroyer of Forests
description: This legendary axe captures the essence of just devastating the ever-loving fuck out of some native foliage. The soul of every forest ever clear-cut resonates in this axe, ready to unleash its rage on your hapless enemies.

name: iPhone
description: An iPhone, one of the many models made by Apple. Looks pretty shiny and sleek.

name: Fruit Gushers - Ultimate Uranium Nuclear Apeshit Apocalypse Flavour
description: These things practically glow with radioactive energy. It would take a brave hero of unending courage to even HOLD the things, let alone eat them. Still, any port in a storm...you hope?

name: Archer\'s Bone
description: A Skeletal Bow that fires bones in an arc. It reminds you of acastle in Transylvania? No, that's not quite right...

name: Sunblock
description: It rubs the lotion on its skin or else it gets the hose again

name: SPF Deadly
description: Throws scalding hot sunblock. Kills and blocks harmful UV radiation. Especially effective against anthropomorphic sunbeams.

name: Sun Blotter
description: Bow that blocks harmful UV Radiation with arrows. Perfect for fighting in the shade.

name: Steam-Powered Proton Pack
description: Steam catches Ghosts! Steam catches Imps! Actually, steam catches anything you steam point the high powered steam jet at. Except other steam jets. Don't try to catch those other steam streams with your steam stream. Did I mention it uses steam?

name: Belt
description: A simple belt. Keeps your pants from falling down when applied properly.

name: Kamen Rider Wizard art book
description: An art book containing various designs and facts from Kamen Rider Wizard. It is an indispensable resource for enthusiasts of your ilk.

name: Gunblade
description: It's a sword whose blade is also a gun. Or a gun whose barrel is also a sword. Either way, it's kind of tricky to use.

name: WizarSword
description: A gun sword with guidable bullets.

name: Deodorant
description: Use this spray-on deoderant to keep the stink off. Or probably apply more, since the spelling of the name makes you think this stuff has ben SBaHJified.

name: Body Spray Axe
description: For ruining losers' lives while smelling super fresh for the ladies.

name: Grenade
description: It explodes when you pull the pin out, leading to either drama and tragedy or total hilarity depending on the kind of setting you're in.

name: Serpent Bow
description: This bow has a particular snake pattern on it, with snake-like arrows too...

name: Dark Souls sketchbook
description: A sketchbook containing artwork and details about a certain video game. Luckily it's also covered in spikes, so you can whack things pretty good with it

name: Drill Spear
description: It's just a spear with a drill at the top. A big old stabby drill. Added bonus of drilling whatever you stab!

name: Extended Wheat Slayer
description: A sickle with a rather large pole for a handle, better used as a Scythe of sorts. Deadly sorts, mostly.

name: Barbascorcher
description: For once, the flammability is an advantage!

name: Whip-Sword
description: A sword shaped weapon with lines running horizontally down the blade.  When swung, the "Sword" breaks apart and is shown to function like a loose whip.

name: Nuka-Cola
description: This bottle is so glitchy and pixellated you have a difficult time of holding it, but you're reasonably sure that it's fizzy, sweet tasting contents is relatively unaltered.

name: Tunnel Snake Jacket
description: Tunnel Snakes rule!

name: iShades
description: Now you can look cool and have a huge array of apps at your fingertips! Er, eyeballtips. Wait... how are you even operating this thing? Telekinesis?

name: Crowbar
description: An astounding combination of birds and alcoholic beverages. Useful for opening boxes and bludgeoning parasitic aliens to death.

name: Laser Pointer
description: Careful, you might put someone's eye out!

name: Lazer Umbrella
description: Oh dear, it seems to be raining. I'll just open up my umbrella here and- BWAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA!

name: Deckmess Whackwatch
description: A pirate's weapon, used for close-combat, down-and-out, no-holds-barred brawling on the high seas. Make sure to sharpen it while grinning evilly every once and a while; gives it character.

name: Heavy Oardnance
description: A heavy metal oar that is useless for anything but battle. Nasty hooks can dig into the opponent.

name: The Unpretentious Wizard
description: What is this? It's as if the magical staff is actually magical!

name: The Somewhat Eternal Struggle
description: Finally, a poster displaying the hardboiledness of a film noir and and the hardboiledness of another film noir.

name: The Other Somewhat Eternal Struggle
description: You make another one of these goddamn posters. Though at least this one isn't a crossover.

name: Katana no Orochi
description: A great 8-bladed katana with a Green edge and a blood red back. A mythical sword, it's said it was made out of Yamata no Orochis remains after Susano killed the Giant Snake.

name: Big Jack
description: A well oiled and dangerous Jackknife, it's said that it's former owner was a giant from Japan. He was apparently pretty violent. He was definitely pretty big, because you need both hands to wield this thing.

name: Chain
description: A simple chain. Has multiple applications, the foremost being completing a dangerous-looking biker ensemble.

name: Horn
description: HONK HONK! Motherfuckers. A simple horn, dude. Often carried by clowns of both the whimsical and homicidal variety.

name: Triple Anvil-Fanged Pogo Slammer
description: You've decided to hold monsters and not hammers at this point.

name: Candy Spear
description: Giant candy corn makes for a great spearhead, and as everybody knows Candy is extremely effective against enemies.

name: Crystal Lance
description: A translucent lance made of thick, cold ice. It looks kind of like a giant icicle. In fact, it pretty much is one.

name: Excelsius
description: A double-edged greatsword. One side of the blade is super-hot, and the other side is freezing cold. Its wielder can fell foes either way depending on their mood! Or the weather.

name: Blackjack Deck
description: A normal deck of cards, nothing unusual here.

name: 4 of Spades / Saber Rattle
description: The perfect card when you need to kill something out of rage and frustration.

name: 7 of Spades / Bait and Switchblade
description: Treat your enemies to a bit of the old BAIT AND SWITCHBLADE.

name: King of Spades / Occam\'s Razor
description: Let's cut to the chase.

name: Ace of Spades / Cast Iron Horse Hitcher
description: Bring me a horse and I am yours forever.

name: Flamethrower\'s Best Friend
description: You shoot a mist of the vodka from the small bottle through the flame, alighting it. Be careful not to set yourself on fire. Or don't, I guess you're entitled to immolate yourself if you really want to.

name: Acoustic Guitar
description: A standard wooden guitar. Light enough to carry, sturdy enough to cave in your enemies' skulls with a few swings. Or one if you happen to be an engineer.

name: Ticking Death
description: A somewhat average scythe in terms of weight and size, but a bit more power than that of most. The blade itself being made of energy allows what passes for sharpness in an energy blade to last.

name: ...SYTH
description: The unhallowed weapon of the JPEG REPAER

name: Lifehunt Scythe
description: With this weapon you can feel out and eradicate the life force of your enemies.

name: Frost Jack Doll
description: A cute little ice demon doll. It feels cold to the touch.

name: Namine\'s Sketchbook
description: A sketchbook filled with pictures that remind you of a far-off memory. Unfortunately this memory doesn't let you whack things with the book any better.

name: Kamen Rider Jacket
description: Wear the jacket. Be the Rider. Wearing this jacket makes you feel like kicking things and watching them explode from the sheer force of your kick.

name: Backpack
description: Just your regular old backpack. Handy for storing things, unsurprisingly.

name: Cigarette Holder / Royal Lance
description: Careful, you might poke someone's eye out with this thing!

name: Chemistry Set
description: Chemistry set: A set of vials, flasks, beakers, droppers, a bunsen burner, tongs, and more. Perfect for the aspiring chemist, but not so much for the aspiring strifer. Maybe you can throw the beakers at enemies?

name: Syringe
description: An empty syringe. It would probably be more useful if it was filled with something...

name: Scalpel
description: A small, sharp tool typically used for surgical procedures.

name: Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time Cartridge
description: Dungeons, Puzzles, Time Travel, and Combat. A truly timeless game.

name: Master Sword
description: As you alchemize the Master Sword, you freeze in time for seven years. You awake to find that your session mates are dead, the Reckoning has occurred, and the kingdom of Derse has taken over the Incipisphere.</br>Nah, just kidding.

name: Regisword
description: Commonly handed out with a hit list with two crown silhouettes to anyone entering the archagent's office.

name: Grenade Rifle
description: You had the mundane thought to combine the Rifle with the Grenade resulting in a semi-automatic rifle that shoots Grenades. For some bizarre reason the term "noob tube" pops into your head as you wield this.

name: Contract Quill
description: A pink and white feather quill that looks like no bird in existence. Could it have or grant magical properties?

name: Scissors
description: You can use these for arts and crafts. With the guts of your enemies.

name: Conductor\'s Baton
description: A conductor's baton, for directing orchestras. Surprisingly sharp.

name: Iron Shrieker
description: A weighty horn that makes a sound similar to a foghorn when squeezed, only more...clang-y. Excellent at waking sleeping guardians and deafening foes.

name: Broom
description: A simple broom for sweeping. The shaft is wooden, with straw bristles. Comes with a dustpan.

name: Yardstick
description: It's a yardstick, to measure the pain.

name: Froot Gushers - XTrEM Nacho Cheese Concussion flavour
description: A pack of fruit gushers consisting solely of yellow-orange colored gushers with a nacho cheese flavoured center. Surprisingly they don't taste half bad, but the packaging is covered in jpeg artifacts for some reason. Plus you're sure the name is slightly misspelled.

name: Blue Slime Pen
description: A shiny blue pen which writes in slimy blue gel ink.

name: Gondolan Garrison
description: Despite having relatively mundane origins, this gondolier's oar is inexplicably powerful. It is also for some reason the first oar you have come across that ISN'T a pun or something.

name: Chess set
description: A board used to play chess, along with some pieces. Aside from being the source of large quantities of symbolism, it makes a pretty efficient bludgeon.

name: pewn
description: pawns dont DOO that you chumpstick.

name: Biggoron Sword
description: A sidequest that has led you on many a delivery quests has finally yielded results: a sword of exceptional size and power, requiring two hands to hold. What beautiful craftsmanship.

name: Umbrellaser
description: This fires a laser when you open or close it. Completely useless against rain.

name: Titanium Umbrella
description: An excellent shield and whacking stick, this umbrella is unfortunately difficult to carry.

name: Grappling Hook
description: The sharply clawed hook is perfect for gripping, and now it can be propelled long distance.

name: The Iron Whip
description: A whip that is not just a prop from a movie, but it actually inflicts damage due to an iron exterior. Who knows how the iron became malleable? It is a mystery.

name: Encyclopedia of Shadow Magic
description: This heavy volume contains everything you could ever need to know about shadow magic. Plus the back has this very handy section on popular card games!

name: Novelty Digivice
description: A virtual pet toy from a popular television series. Well, popular in Japan anyway. And Japan is ALWAYS right! Right?

name: Projector
description: The kind of thing they show movies with in old school TV shows. AV club rocks!

name: Bombitomeicon
description: This cursed tome contains great and forbidden knowledge about the deployment and effective use of explosives, as well as powerful spells to summon such devices. Be careful, or it will haunt your eye!

name: Holographic Digital Monster Emitter
description: Emits a projection of some sort of Digital creature to fight for you. Unfortunately said creature still seems to be a rookie in combat.

name: Pokedex
description: Point it at mysterious creatures, and it will tell you more about them. Doesn't work on the monsters in the Medium, though, rendering it completely useless. Gotta catch them all?

name: Fruit Gushers - Rockin\' Poprock Rigor Mortis flavour
description: Fruit Gushers with a hint of poprocks, producing a sugary, mineral-rich snack that is somehow both crunchy and chewy at the same time.

name: Sasaki Slayer
description: This is the swoard carved by Musashi Miyamoto himself that he used in his legendary battle against Sasaki Kojiro.

name: The 50th Argonaut
description: The last of the recoverable oars used to propel the legendary ship of the Argonauts. Despite being physically mundane a certain amount of legendary power has rubbed off on it.

name: Tablet Stylus
description: This is slightly more durable than your average fountain pen.

name: Ice Shards
description: A pair of sharpened icicles for stabbing and slashing your oppoennts. Conveniently, they never dull. Or melt. Even if you were on the Land of Heat and Clockwork. Yeah, fantasy weapons are a bit dumb at times.

name: The Inheritance Cycle
description: A massive collection of four dense books about an empire, magic, a boy, and his dragon, all bound into one incredibly heavy volume.

name: Blade of Blue Flames
description: A magical flaming sword once wielded by a powerful Dragon Rider. Saying its true name causes the sword to burst into magical flames. Good for slaying tyrants, total overkill on imps.

name: UNREAL chAIR
description: It is RIDICULOUS what kind of chair this thing is getting. Dude come get the...yeah, this isn't working.

name: Octuple Anvil-Fanged Devil Slammer
description: You've done it. You've combined everything within reaching distance to make this hammer. Those dice were probably the last straw. There's nothing else.

name: Pokemon Cards
description: They appear to be cards for some human version of Fiduspawn. Weird. While they lack the summoning power of the Fiduspawn game, this is some sturdy cardboard.

name: Hamaxe
description: A tool with a head that is a hammer on one side, and an axe on the other, combining the best features of both. No, it is not an axe made of ham.

name: Logorg
description: A poorly-constructed wooden robot. Unfortunately, it has no moving parts and is a completely useless statue. Perhaps you could still bludgeon imps with it?

name: Drillgorg
description: The wooden robot-statue Logorg, rebuilt with a drill attached to its arm. Good thing it can't move, otherwise it might just drill your ass.

name: Electric Guitar
description: A modern stringed instrument that is the meat of most rock and roll music. It also makes for a very expensive bludgeon.

name: Heavy Metal Axe
description: This hardcore bladed guitar can do some serious shredding, both on stage and on the battlefield!

name: Fighting Gloves
description: They're yellow. That's... about all they have going for them.

name: Mustafa\'s Odor Cleaver
description: Look at that imp, then back to this axe, then back to the imp. The imp is now diamond grist. Anything is possible when your axe smells as good as this one does.

name: Circus whip
description: A whip unfortunately used on pokemon in the Sinnoh region to train them for the circus. You can feel the pain of pokemon it was used on when fighting with it, and it makes you very sad.

name: Slingshot
description: This simple slingshot lead to many fun and deadly(!!!) times in your childhood, why not take it back out and use it to kill the bad guys?

name: The King\'s Rapier
description: "Only one worthy of a king could wield this deadly, fabulous, and not to mention expensive rapier!" Well, you're no king, but you could use it anyway!

name: Hammerlight
description: A flashlight in the shape of a hammer. Rather than running on disposable batteries, it charges with kinetic energy--just hit things with it to make it glow. Hits pretty hard, too.

name: Red Faygo-yo
description: This yo-yo appears to have a decent quantity of constantly-replenishing wicked elixir stashed within. Luckily there's a small tap on the side to extract some, because you'd very much like to drink it! Wait, no, that's not right, you hate Faygo. Or do you? You're so confused right now.

name: Frost\'s Crook
description: This weapon of legend glows with the power of the moon and shimmers with a mystical icy coating.

name: Kusanagi
description: The Legendary Grass Sword, being able to extend itself and even levitate. It's said that the owner of this blade was a literal Snake-man

name: Steel Bar
description: It's a bar. Made from steel. The captchalogue code strikes you as more literal creation instructions than usual.

name: Fedoratop
description: All the on-the-go computing advantages of a laptop in a slick fedora. And yes, it's running the Fedora linux distribution.

name: The Outrigger
description: A champion oar used in competitive races with an accompanying apparatus. It is unwieldy and difficult to use in battle.

name: Tectrix of the Arbiter
description: The most "potent" weapon of the kingdom, the legendary TECTRIX OF THE ARBITER. (In actuality, even Tektroxcaliburn is stronger than this thing)

name: Iced Tea
description: The cool, sweet nectar of the gods, with just a hint of peach.

name: 2 of Spades / Licorice Scotty Dogs
description: The favourite candy of every slick gentleman.

name: Sledge Claws
description: Almost more like solid blocks of metal than claws. These claws are unbelievably heavy, but man do they pack a wallop.

name: Crimson Blade
description: A blade once wielded by a powerful traitor, it's as red as the blood it's spilled. The sword's original name means "Misery".

name: Boomerage
description: Have you ever been so angry that you just wanted to throw something? Well this something will keep coming back so you can throw it again and again. It just seems to make you angrier every time though..

name: Box of Chalk
description: A collection of various colors of chalk. No matter how tasty they may look, eating them is probably a bad idea.

name: Joker Figurine
description: Why so serious?

name: Batarang
description: Nobody would have expected a sharp hunk of metal shaped like a bat to be aerodynamic, but yet, somehow, it is.

name: The Fury of Ace Dick
description: A pair of powerful gloves once wielded by the archenemy of an unusually hard-boiled detective. Good for punching people's imaginations in the face.

name: Spear of the Demimonde Semigoddess
description: A towering spear with clashing red and blue colors dividing it down the middle. You can't tell if the godly aura it emanates is more holy or sinister.

name: Death\'s Scythe
description: The very scythe wielded by Death himself. It can transform into many different forms of increasingly questionable effectiveness, but one thing's for sure: you'll be reaping some souls tonight!

name: A Jumbled Mess
description: A rocket pack with a cinderblock, violin, and a flower pot stuck inside. This thing will probably not work, not ever. It seems punching random letters into cards is probably not the best method of alchemy.

name: The Call of Cthulhu
description: Once just a simple short story book it has been changed into a tome that summons the elder god himself to your aid. It is a monster whose look cannot be explained. He will surely crush any foes in your way.

name: Beatles Record
description: A vinyl record from the sixties. Ahh, those were the days...

name: Pikachu Figurine
description: A figurine of a small yellow rodent. It's the perfect companion for a journey, if you can put up with the occasional lightning-strike misfire.

name: Maxwell\'s Silver Hammer
description: Bang! Bang! Maxwell's silver hammer</br>Came down upon her head.</br>Clang! Clang! Maxwell's silver hammer</br>Made sure that she was dead.

name: Thunder Whip
description: A whip that was named for its agility, specifically against creatures that can move as fast as lightning. However, the constant whipping of small electric rodents has charged it with a constant, small amount of electricity.

name: Wibbly-Wobbly Timey-Wimey Staff
description: It has a clock on it where a jewel or orb would normally be. Every time you hit something with it, you go one second back in time.

name: Amazing Acehorn
description: It has a long metal handle and a unicorn head at the end with a sharp, thin horn. How sweet the sound of your enemy's body hitting the ground.

name: Hammer, Yo
description: A yo-yo. That's a hammer. Good for smashing imp faces, or your own if you're not careful.

name: Felt Pen
description: A fancy pen with a light green cloth coating, reminiscent to the felt of a billiards table. It also has a small functioning clock embedded into the side. Wielding it seems to accelerate your attacks.

name: Chikin Hakachu
description: A potent oar that embodies the elegant fighting style originally developed by the Okinawans.

name: Guide to Studying the Zoologically Mundane
description: A nice wholesome encyclopedia covering the entire animal kingdom and nothing even remotely otherworldly or terrifying. Well, except for cuttlefish.

name: Ark Yielder
description: A very big oar. For a very big boat.

name: Pillow
description: You sleep on this. Or whack things with it. But the latter isn't particularly effective.

name: Lyre
description: An ancient Greek instrument that plays a tune so haunting that the instrument actually becomes quite the effective weapon.

name: The Harvester
description: Whether your goal is souls or organs, this is the perfect tool to ensure a good harvest.

name: The Overseer
description: Not quite Mr. Overseer himself, but rather a modified version of what ye olde plantation overseers used.

name: 4-D Ripper
description: This emerald-edged whip rends great wounds in time when it is slashed across your opponents, wounding them severely.

name: Horcrux
description: A replica of Salazar Slytherin's locket. It probably doesn't contain a piece of the dark lord's soul, but it does give off some 'bad vibes'.

name: Vengeance from the School Yard
description: As it turns out, when scissors are affixed to the end of a yard stick, it makes for a pretty dangerous weapon.

name: Riot Shotgun
description: A shotgun that's different from the normal double-barelled in that it comes with a nifty ammunition drum! No need to spend time reloading mid-battle with this baby!

name: Sharp-Edged Jacks
description: These extra sharp jacks are guaranteed to poke the eyes out of any enemies you encounter! They also feel rather warm to the touch.

name: Rifled Shotgun
description: Combining the characteristics of the accurate and powerful Rifle and not so accurate but powerful Shotgun results in the Rifled Shotgun. It fires slug rounds for added power and accuracy.

name: Shotgun Rifle
description: You didn't think this would result in an combination that worked but it resulted in a scatter gun that fires Rifles Shots as pellets. Okay?

name: Cavescrawler
description: Good alternative writing equipment for those lacking a pencil or pen. Also useful for stabbing people.

name: Scientific Writeup
description: Drawing with lasers is at least twice as scientific as drawing without lasers.

name: Diatomic Parters
description: Democritus and Dalton have nothing on these.

name: Kamaitachi
description: Makes you feel like doing the bird run, but that's probably a bad idea.

name: Chopsticks
description: These are for eating, not for strifing. But that's never going to stop you.

name: Cool Winter Coat
description: This jacket is so infused with ice, it's immune to cold. It doesn't look very warm however.

name: Skull
description: A humans skull, very commonly used in various necromantic rituals. Spooky!

name: Gross Incandescence
description: Illuminates the darkness and makes you feel inspired to aid your allies. Praise the Sun!

name: Black Firebomb
description: Black bisque urn filled with black powder.

name: Chaindrill
description: A rather large drill attached to the end of a long chain. Can be used effectively by throwing the drill end, then pulling it back to you with the chain. Be careful on the rebound, though!

name: Animal Crossing disc
description: A fishing and mortgage simulator for the Nintendo Gamecube, because being a raccoon's slave is fun for the whole family.

name: Nook\'s Trusty Tree Trimmer
description: All the fun of chopping monsters and being in debt, finally realized in the form of this axe!

name: gUITARD.........
description: A lopsided green guitar. No matter what you do it seems to always be hideously out of tune. WOAWW BWEE!

name: Steel Staff
description: Who ever said staves had to be magical?

name: Black Soul Baton
description: A conductor's baton with an unearthly, dark aura. A strange wailing sound can be heard when waving it around.

name: Grim Reacher
description: A scythe on a chain, with a long reach. Watch your foes flee in fear, only to be pulled back to their demise.

name: Scorpio Tail
description: The secret power of the fabled Thief of Light, but in scythe form. "16777216" is engraved across the blade.

name: Corpse Dropper
description: The name says it all.

name: Dimension Hopper
description: A slice from this green-and-black axe can create small portals through time and space. Your enemies will enjoy being suddenly relocated to the Furthest Ring!

name: Hurricane Rocker Deck
description: Rocket propelled cards which propel themselves fast enough to slice through enemies. They have a windy looking symbol painted on the back.

name: Heavy Bolter
description: Fires fist sized rockets called "Bolts."  An explosive addition to any arsenal.

name: Beam Scythe
description: A scythe with a blade made of hard light. You're not really sure how that works, but as long as it can cut apart imps, you don't need to know.

name: Black Light
description: A pitch black laser pointer with a red heart adorning it's length. You think the light it casts is actually a shadow...

name: The Wrench of Evil\'s Bane
description: The Wrench of Evil's Bane: A long wrench with the hilt of the Master Sword that has been bathed in the three Sacred Flames. It has the power to repel evil, as well as the ability to tighten the loose nut on your bike.

name: Telescope
description: A normal and average telescope. Perfect for looking at the stars and other lewd activities.

name: Soul Eater Vol 1
description: ...You aren't sure how those two items got you this Japanese manga. Hitting enemies with it puts it to the use it was implied to be intended for throughout the series: pain.

name: Devourer of Souls
description: This sleek red and black scythe feels almost alive... it pulses with resonating magic and produces powerful magic attacks depending on your compatibility.

name: Skyrim: Collector\'s Edition
description: A warrior with a dragon's soul fighting dragons, using the language of the dragons. You wonder why this game loves dragons so much.

name: Knee Eradicator
description: The bane of adventurers everywhere.

name: Tome of Sheogorath
description: Simply holding this book can drive its owner to madness. For some reason, has a picture of cheese on the cover.

name: Shovel
description: Can you dig it?

name: Wabbajack
description: A powerful staff that once belonged to Sheogorath, Daedric Prince of Madness. The powerful magic in this weapon has a different effect every time you use it, you never quite know what will happen.

name: SBAHA CROSHAR\'S
description: The most legendary, most piece of shitty legendary piece of shit ever

name: Scythe of Petals
description: A brightly-colored scythe wielded by a Nobody with an affinity for flowers. It has a slight scent of roses.

name: Scorpion\'s Venom
description: Feel the poison of its power consume you.

name: Bayoneted Rifle
description: For when shooting OR stabbing just isn't good enough.

name: Trusty Knives
description: If you didn't have your trusty knives, you think you'd slit your wrists.

name: Ode to Eurydice
description: A fantastic oar that sings a mournful song as you swing it. It appears to come from a sad past.

name: Sunderer of the Seas
description: An oar powerful enough to part the Red Sea itself.

name: Niernen
description: A weapon for the sole purpose of killing dragons...but it should work just as well on Imps!

name: Green Apple Pop Rocks
description: Artificially flavored Pop Rocks! Store in a cool, dry place.

name: Stimpak
description: When the medicine is injected, it provides immediate healing of the body's minor wounds. Short for "Stimulation delivery package".

name: Legend of Zelda Cartridge Sword
description: A sword made from Nintendo 64 cartridges. Well... this thing is rather pointless.

name: Cosby Poster
description: You don't care what anyone says. Ghost Dad was amazing.

name: Wikipedia: Text Edition
description: A bound print of every Wikipedia article in existence. Damn, this thing is heavy...and it keeps getting heavier! On the plus side, having it tends to give you the edge in things like insult wars and fallacy-riddled debates.

name: Kamen Rider W Movie DVD
description: Kamen Rider W A~Z Gaia Memories of fate! NOW ON DVD. And probably in 3D with TWO BONUS DISCS OF EXTRA FEATURES or some shit too.

name: Prism Sword
description: Man, this thing is shiny. It apparently has the power to prevent your enemies from healing their wounds, but your enemies don't heal their wounds anyway so that seems kind of irrelevant.

name: Bicker Shield
description: This shield complains at your enemies when you raise it to face them, sapping their morale and- oh, no, wait, apparently it's based off something called the "Bicker Gaia Memory". Never mind, then.

name: Master WizarSword
description: Clearly the product of either crossover fanfiction or hot, steamy, scandalous sword intercourse. Let's hope it's the former.

name: Flame Alchemist Gloves
description: White Gloves with a alchemic circle on their back. With a Snap of your fingers you could blow up an entire building... unless you can't snap your fingers. Then these are kind useless for you.

name: Shackle
description: Adds some weight to your kicks. Perfect not only for weaponry, but for looking like a convicted felon!

name: Baseball Bat
description: Commonly used to deflect small leather balls, aiming to send them sky high.

name: Chester\'s Long Coat
description: This exquisitely sewn aristocratic suit allows its wearer to move in silence, lending well to stealth.

name: Equestrian\'s Handbook
description: Unruly stallion? Claim mastery over your steed with this handy, easy-to-read tome.

name: Chinese Assault Rifle
description: It's an AK-47, though modified for easy production. Everything about this gun feels fake.

name: Pendant
description: No effect, but fond memories comfort travelers.

name: Smough\'s Hammer
description: Now you, too, can grind the bones of your enemies into your food, if that's the kind of thing you're into!

name: Dead Man\'s Guard
description: This is what happens when your meat shield takes too much damage.

name: Clockwork Defense
description: A compact and always timely shield that will always be there to remind enemies that they really don't have the time to hit you.

name: Utilibelt
description: Useful for containing all kinds of things, except a sense of style.

name: Blank Protest Sign
description: You would protest a worthy cause, but that's too mainstream. Instead, you stand there holding a blank sign.

name: Undeadpprentice\'s Wand
description: A wand used by necromancers-in-training, mostly used for summoning small, unassuming killer skeletons. Try dragon\'s teeth for a better effect.

name: Fus-Rifle-Dah
description: A rifle that makes everything fly away from you. Strangely useful!

name: Demolition Hammer
description: Your enemies will explode with the sheer force of the impact of this hammer. Cool guys don't look at explosions.

name: Heatmaker
description: This fiery axe was forged in the molten core of the volcano it came from! It will melt all of your enemies in your sights! The thing is hot as hell so you better grab some gloves.

name: Magnetic W
description: Of all the magnets you could possibly have, this one was the easiest to find for some reason. You guess it's as good as any other.

name: Magic 8-Ball
description: A device that predicts the future with alarming inaccuracy. You briefly consider just smashing it, but ultimately your superstition gets the better of you.

name: Magic Cue Ball
description: Supposedly, like the magic 8 ball, this device predicts the future. It is said that its predictions are precise and specific. As it lacks a portal through which to view these predictions, this can never be truly confirmed.

name: Green Sun on a Stick
description: A ball of green fire on the end of a stick. It draws its power from an unknown, yet unlimited source.

name: Alpha Orb No. 23
description: A palm-sized white orb with the letter W printed all over it. You have no idea if it can predict anything, but it certainly feels ominous. Chaotic, even. Or at least magnetic.

name: Giant Inflatable W
description: While wavy, this wacky W-shaped widget wavers not when whacking wrongdoers.

name: Zombie Figurine
description: It eats brain figurines.

name: Backgasher
description: A backscratcher with a large and sharp claw. This'll get rid of the itch, all right... as well as your flesh.

name: Spinal Drainer
description: This backscratcher has a particularly long and jointed claw for hitting those hard-to-reach imps!

name: Paralyzer
description: Charged with electricity, getting scratched with this backscratcher is sure to cause some nerve damage.

name: Heated Pillow
description: The device inside this pillow will keep you feeling nice and toasty on those cold winter nights. Turn it up high enough and it can sear the skin off of someone.

name: Sweet Dreams
description: A colorful pillow that smells like candy. It's actually stuffed with fruit gushers, perfect if you want a midnight snack.

name: Tickling Death
description: The feathers inside this pillow are laced with a highly toxic substance. The last thing your foe will feel is a tickling sensation as they suffocate.

name: Towel
description: The real reason the words "hit the showers" strikes fear into the heart of any man.

name: Sweat Dreams
description: This pillow smells weird and is dripping with sweat. Regardless, it just feels... STRONG for some reason.

name: Machine Fun
