description: An automatic weapon that shoots flowers, rainbows, and sunshine. Your enemies' tears are those of joy! They'll die of happiness and explode in a colorful shower of love!

name: Drill Gauntlets
description: The glove of choice for Echidnas everywhere.

name: Zipptoon
description: A spontoon with the central blade missing. Instead, the lighter in the handle will ignite a small gout of flame lancing between the two short prongs. If it were only shorter, then it would be great for party tricks!

name: piBoy
description: With all the rendering power of an Apple II and the computational power of a hundred modern PCs, this wrist-mounted clunky device can analyze and track your mental states, capabilities, tasks, maps, and current inventory (with cartoonish iconography). And yet it doesn't have any games for the ride on the subway. Junk.

name: Wizard Statue
description: A statue of a bearded wizard.

name: Needlewands
description: They crackle with the majyyk enyrjjies. It seems like this is only one step toward an even greater power, though.

name: Thorns of Oglogoth
description: The needles seem to shiver with the dark desires of THE DEEP ONE. Any sane adventurer would cast these instruments of the occult into the FURTHEST RING and forget they ever existed.

name: Squirtgun
description: Why are you using a squirtgun when you could be using an actual firearm?

name: Gasoline Gun
description: Now this is firepower. A real smoking gun. How many fire gun jokes can I get away with?

name: Universe Bifurcator
description: A weapon used to cut entire universes in twain. Be careful where you swing this thing.

name: Silver Spoon
description: The way you wield this, you'd think you were born with it.

name: Timber Dredge
description: A weighty and large anchor you can just barely handle with both hands, but its wicked bladed sides certainly look fearsome.

name: Titan\'s Teastirrer
description: What appears to be a very large silver spoon. Can be used as a stirring solution or a digging solution, and you can smell any bleeding englishmen in the vicinity with surprising accuracy.

name: Thorned Banjo
description: It's like a banjo, except it has huge spikes all over it. You'll be the perfect example of a redneck if you use this.

name: Redneck\'s SledgeHu
description: As if the sledgehu wasn't annoying enough to carry, now it's got spikes all over it!

name: Timeline Resetter
description: The Timeline Resetter: This powerful time weapon was wielded by one of the most acclaimed time magic users. Legend has it that it could stop, rewind, and even change time to an extend by simply using the purple sand in the hourglass inside.

name: Magnetic Wodka
description: Warning: may cause the imbiber to become magnetic. Or poisoned. Or just heavily intoxicated. Drink at own risk.

name: Ultimate Death Ray
description: The weapon of a true mad scientist, capable of instantly vaporizing all but the toughest foes!

name: Low-Focus Laser Sword
description: This weapon makes you feel like you've traveled from a far off galaxy from a long time ago. Doesn't grant any telekinetic powers or anything like that, but it's still a cool weapon capable of slicing imps in half.

name: Double-Ended Laser Sword
description: Careful with that thing, or you might end up getting yourself cut in half!

name: Potted Plant
description: An ordinary household plant. You can't think of any practical use for this thing.

name: Laser-Guided Precision Hatchet
description: A hatchet with an integrated laser sight. You ...guess it could be useful for fighting in the dark? No, not really.

name: Stuffed Bird
description: A colorful toy bird.

name: Legendary Storm Whip
description: A wispy whip said to contain the power of the fabled thunderbird. When this whip cracks, it makes a booming, thunderous sound.

name: Contact Lenses
description: For those who don't want to look like a dork, and don't mind having silicone in their eyes all the time. Some would consider this a fair trade.

name: LAX Rifle
description: A lacrosse stick that fires bullets and lacrosse balls. Also useful for clumsy bludgeoning.

name: Hockey Stick
description: A generic wooden hockey stick, destined to be used to clock someone in the head.

name: Crystal of Light
description: A crystal that glows with a holy light.

name: Crystal of Darkness
description: A light-absorbing crystal that seems to emit a malevolent aura.

name: Soul Calibur
description: A legendary holy sword said to be able to change its form. You also swear there's something alive in there, but don't get caught talking to it...
credit: JakeCrowley is in love love with overseer

name: Soul Edge
description: The Evil Blade. It is said that it devours the souls of those who are slewn with it. Holding this makes you feel uneasy, like a demon is trying to get inside your mind...

name: Frozen Edge of Darkness
description: A dark and grim blade coated in ice. This chills not only your hands, but your soul.

name: Holy Spear of Redemption
description: A golden spear with a crystalline head. You can feel the heavens smiling down on you when you hold it up to the sky. Or that could just be the light reflecting off of it.

name: Excalibur
description: The Legendary Sword of King Arthur. It's said that only a true King can wield it. If you're a Prince or an Heir, you might have to wait a while.

name: Clarent
description: King Arthur's Sword of Peace, better known as the Coward's Blade. Stop absconding, you pansy!

name: Carnwennan
description: King Arthur's dagger, sometimes described to shroud the user in shadow. You feel like you could slice a witch in half with this thing.

name: Rhongomyniad
description: King Arthur's Spear. You think you'll just call it Ron for short.

name: Screwdriver
description: Once used for turning screws, the stalk of this basic instrument now disassembles imps instead of wood furniture. Remember, righty-tighty, lefty-loosey.

name: Sauron\'s Offspring
description: You aren't sure if this thing is supposed to be angelic or demonic. Probably the latter.

name: Laser Pen
description: A high-tech looking pen which can fire a piercing red laser from the tip, leaving a scorching mark on whatever it hits. Sorta resembles writing in glowing red ink, just a lot more painful.

name: Blades of Rage
description: So-called because of the rage wielding this weapon instills when a monster fails to defeat you.

name: Life\'s Dream
description: Row, row, row your boat... This oar causes the target to suffer an existential crisis when struck.

name: Master BiggoroSword
description: This is such a big and impressive sword that you forgot it could still fire bullets.

name: Icicle Shield
description: A triangular shield made of ice. You're kind of afraid to block attacks with it, lest it break into shards aimed at your face.

name: Frozen Pride
description: A sharp, teardrop-shaped shield colored a deep, icy blue. It is freezing to the touch, and gives off an unnerving aura. Oh wait, that's frostbite.

name: White Magnum / White Wand
description: Always make sure to pack plenty of bullets. You can't use magic when you run out of bullets.

name: Crossbow
description: A lighter, easier to fire bow weapon. A good way to be old-fashioned without being TOO old-fashioned.

name: Black Scepter / Black Rifle
description: You\'re not really supposed to hold it by the magazine like that, but whatever.

name: Fruit Gushers - Gnarly Cotton Candy Doomsday Prophecy Flavor
description: Tastes like the screams of the innocent, the suffering of the unrighteous, the calamitous scent of brimstone, and low-quality carnival cotton candy. This may very well be the least appetizing variety of Fruit Gusher, and that's saying something.

name: Abracadagger
description: A magical dagger, covered in whimsy and wonder. And also, you suspect, some dried blood and bits of organ. Charming.

name: Green Ghost Pogo Stick
description: You can move around at the speed of bounce with this cleverly themed pogo stick. It's really hard not to fall over on this thing though.

name: Auto-Buckshot
description: A gun with the power and shape of a shotgun, but the clip and fire rate of a machine gun. Those imps won't know what hit 'em!

name: Sodapopper
description: A fast and annoying shotgun with a burst of carbonated pellets. Wielding this makes you want to taunt your slower foes.

name: Toy Blocks
description: Fun blocks to play with. Not to step on.

name: Brick Stick
description: A staff made of toy bricks. Oh god, the corners...

name: Ghost Blades
description: Oh boy, just what you needed - some high quality fishing lures! ...wait, these are knives. What a scam!

name: Hero\'s Bow
description: A bow that is fabled to have been used by a legendary hero...

name: Bubble Wand
description: Got an Imp problem? These bubbles might... distract them? I guess?

name: .454 Casull Auto
description: A custom-made, long-barreled pistol. It's rather difficult to wield; perhaps if you were a vampire...

name: Jackal
description: A huge, heavy black pistol that fires explosive rounds. Be careful when firing this thing if you want to keep your arm.

name: Goldeneye
description: Two golden contact lenses. They're heavy and cold on your eyes, but they give the world a pretty golden tint.

name: Golden Gun
description: You're not Agent 007, but with this powerful gun, you're well on your way to following in his footsteps.

name: Thunderstruck
description: Somehow, the sound of hitting something with these gloves is changed to "thunderstruck".

name: Bone China Chopsticks
description: Expensive and pretty looking. That doesn't quite mean you should strife with them.

name: Double Bird-Flipper
description: A spatula-sign so big, you could probably flip two birds at once!

name: Nickel
description: Even if your currency was valid here, this measly nickel wouldn't buy you much of anything. You could still throw it at imps though.

name: Steel-Toe Boots
description: Very rigid and thick boots that are made for kicking ass!

name: Leather Sock
description: Wow, a sock made of leather. You guess this is...kinky?

name: Cello-Traumatic
description: It sounds horrid and causes extreme blunt trauma on impact. If only it was flaming...

name: Arsonist\'s Peaceful Protestor
description: Nothing says 'peaceful protest' like a flaming sign to the face.

name: Spinner Spanner
description: Unleash your swirling vortex of tightening and loosening fury!

name: Skullscythe
description: An ancient-looking scythe engraved all over with skulls. You're just about ready to take these imps... to skull.

name: Skull on a Stick
description: If you need a description for this, your IMAGINATION stat is too low.

name: K.K. Slider Plush
description: A plush white dog with a guitar. His eyebrows are weirding you out a little. You believe you will keep your distance from the eyebrows.

name: Black Flare Basher
description: This heavy flaming shield will scorch enemies as you bash your way through the hordes of foes. Using it may cause 3rd degree burns, head trauma and possibly death.

name: Bounce-o-matic Basher
description: Why put a spring-loaded punching bag on the front of a shield you ask? Why not!

name: Bounce-o-Matic Bumper
description: This spring-loaded Shield will knockback your opponents with ease! Also doubles as a useless pogo.

name: Perfectly Unique Object
description: This object is so unique, literally every word you can think of could describe it. Including "ordinary"; the level of uniqueness is so high that it overflows into the negatives.
effects: SHUNT:USELESS.:Your Alchemiter has every possible upgrade at once! Which, ironically, makes it untouchably clunky and impossible to use.

name: Bandage
description: Cloth strips that are usually wrapped around injuries to reduce bleeding.

name: Need for Steed
description: This weapon is a clarion call, an exultation of one of reality's highest truths - more horses are always necessary.

name: Farming Scythe
description: A sharp real scythe used for shearing wheat.

name: Fair Game
description: A weaponized deck of tarot cards taken from the game in question. You can probably cut somebody with these. Unfortunately, the name is a bit of a misnomer, in that it is a complete lie.

name: Special Pikachu Edition Yellow Game Dice
description: These dice aren't really that different from normal game dice, but they are yellow! Oh, and for some reason they cause massive thunder bolts to rain down from the sky. There's that too.

name: Pokemon Knock-Off Game Cart
description: You're pretty sure this game is some kind of Pokemon rip-off, featuring robots instead of cute cuddly little death machines. It's hard to hate robots that are that cute, though.

name: Computer Lenses
description: A functional way to have computing power in your eyes! Extended usage may lead to blindness, though.

name: Batolver
description: This badass bat allows you to lay down the beating by using it as a bat and a baseball shooter.

name: Computer
description: A basic desktop computer. It's not the best, but it gets the job done.

name: Graphing Calculator
description: A math nerd's best friend. It does everything! Graphs, programs, matrices, graphs, calculus, graphs, and even graphs!

name: Chess: Shadow Game Edition
description: The game of life meets the game of Death. The soul of whoever loses is locked in an eternal state of torment and embarrassment.

name: Paper Hand Fan
description: A simple hand fan used to cool off on warm days.

name: Forges Oscillator
description: You'd think that an anvil on a string would make a killer weapon, but it's actually far too heavy for you to even use properly.

name: Yo\'rock
description: This glowing red Yo-yo pulsates with magical might. You might actually be able to shoot the moon with this.

name: Energy Shot
description: Having Mountain Dew injected directly into the bloodstream can't be healthy, so stab an imp with it!

name: Zipper Jacket
description: This jacket is exactly what a hero needs... in a JRPG. Your foes will be so distracted by your endless zippers and colors that you'll be able to defeat them with no problem!

name: ACME Weighted Rear-View Mirror Dice
description: Never again will you have to worry about your fuzzy dice flying off the mirror when you put your convertible's top down. You'll also never have to worry about your rear-view mirror blocking your view through the windshield.

name: Flying With Scissors
description: Remember when your parents told you never to run with scissors? Well, they didn't say you couldn't FLY with them...

name: Magic Scissors
description: These scissors can cut almost every flat surface, as they are MAGIC.

name: Reinforced Club
description: A club with leather nailed awkwardly to the pommel. This gives it a marginally more painful hit at the cost of sturdiness.

name: Felt Bow
description: A soft, green hair bow. When struck, the target experiences minor temporal distortion for extra damage.

name: Lethal Injection
description: A syringe containing a dose of a deadly viral strain that makes many creatures drop dead on the spot. Just be careful not to prick yourself with it...

name: Holster
description: An elegantly-designed pistol holster, the likes of which worn by many a famous gunman, or gunwoman.

name: Einhander
description: It's like a claymore but one-handed. Even the name says so. You are not allowed to wield it using two hands. Only one of your hands may touch it at any time. Comprende!?

name: Clock Shot
description: Cut your foes' time short. With bullets.

name: Grief Bringer
description: It exists solely to cause grief. Now for whom is the question...

name: Shitty Moonlight Butterfly Horn Replica
description: It's nothing like the actual weapon in Dark Souls, and resembles a bent pitchfork more than anything. Still, does some decent damage.

name: Snake\'s Tongue
description: Green shimmers across the forked blade of this serpentine rapier. Stabbing cleanly with it may be difficult though.

name: Green Tunic
description: The garb of a forest-based youth tribe. Just wearing it makes you feel young and lively.

name: Magnetic Gauntlets
description: Although the computer inside is ruined by now, your gloves are now embued with the awesome power of magnets and electricity. A W is engraved on the back.

name: Bandaged Gloves
description: Gloves made out of bandages... are you sure this will work?

name: Drill-Whip
description: Sure, a drill on the end of a whip SOUNDS cool, and it's certainly effective, but the balance is a bit off. Be careful not to hit yourself with the crack!

name: C-4
description: This malleable material can explode on its own, or it can be used to create any number of exploding items. Just be careful with it!

name: Toy Landmines
description: These toy blocks are filled with C4. Scatter them about on the ground and watch your enemies blow their feet off! WARNING: Not for children under 5.

name: Fancy Broom of Protection +1
description: A fancy gold broom. You feel as if it's protecting you. Well, it IS protecting you, you're using it to block attacks!

name: Laser Pistol
description: A normal Laser Pistol that you can find in every Sci-Fi B-movie. Still, you can't deny how cool it is!

name: Razor Claws
description: A pair of imitation Wolverine claws. Instead of cheap plastic, the claws are made from razor blades. It's a step closer to the real thing, at least.

name: Impractically Large Sword
description: Just like from one of those Japanese animes. This unwieldy mass of terrible design could probably be used to bludgeon something to death, provided you had the strength to lift it.

name: Mother 3 Cartridge
description: The last installment of a popular Japanese video game series. This one was never translated, but playing through it is still a blast.

name: Tangle Stabbies
description: Two brightly colored knives covered in Squiddle decals.  An invisible force seems to pull them together.

name: Nintendo 3DS
description: The newest Nintendo Handheld, able to show images on a Z axis in addition to the traditional X and Y. In laymen's terms, it shows 3D pictures.

name: Hot Iron Kite Shield
description: It's a really big iron, but with the defensive properties of a shield! You find it rather difficult to wield.

name: Hylian Shield
description: An ornate, royal shield made to Hylian Knight standards.

name: Scoped Bow
description: A simple bow with a scope attached. You are fairly sure that you will be able to hit the apple on your friend's head... this time.

name: Spirit Bow
description: The ethereal arrows you release from this bow are not fired with your eyes but rather with your heart... or some such nonsense.

name: Book of Mythology
description: The tale of Ulysses... "The fox burying his mother under a holly tree"... you are pretty sure Ulysses said this once...

name: Sinking Feeling
description: An oar that was combined with an anchor for additional weight. Doesn't seem to be useful for rowing anymore, but good for hitting things you suppose.

name: Chained Knives
description: A chain with a pair of knives on each side. Where did you learn how to use that?

name: C4 Boomerang
description: Aerodynamics aside, Im curious what tactical advantage youre expecting to gain by having the high explosive fly back at you if it misses the target.

name: Sharp Dresser
description: As in, it dresses turkeys and stuff. What were you expecting?

name: Darkmoon Bow
description: A bow that is dark as the moon.

name: Magic Bow
description: This Bow doesn't need arrows, becasue magic 'n shit.

name: Gungnir
description: It will never miss, and no matter how strong or skilled it's wielder is, it will always pierce it's target. After hitting it's target it will always comeback to it's owner. Just like an annoying friend.

name: Kilodrill Gauntlets
description: Go beyond the impossible and kick reason to the curb! That's how Team Gurren rolls! ...you have no idea what compelled you to think that.

name: Megadrill Gauntlets
description: These are the drills that will pierce the heavens. Yes, you are just that adamant in the ability of these gauntlets.

name: Gigadrill Gauntlets
description: The sheer power of these drill gloves makes you want to shout at the top of your lungs as you liquefy your enemies' entrails.

name: Super-Galaxy-Gigadrill Gauntlets
description: These drills are powerful enough to open a hole in space. Attempting to take this hole may be a bad idea, though, no matter what your hopes and dreams...

name: Big Starshaped Animeshades
description: These glasses are excessively huge, pointy, and orange. And yet, wearing them gives you the courage to do the impossible.

name: Bloodguard\'s Sickle
description: A bloodred sickle, used by those who are willing to sacrifice their lives for their allies. Or who just want to really cut up some imps.

name: Sungod\'s Lyre
description: This truly feels like the instrument of a deity. Its melodies can range from soothing pieces that calm even the fiercest beasts to horrifying wrathful tones that cause all listeners to burst into holy flame.

name: Cerberhu Slencher
description: A terrifying demonic erhu covered in bloody thorns. Simply looking upon it instills a feeling of deep mortal fright.

name: Death\'s Scull
description: An oar blackened with the deathly waters of the river Styx. A must-have for recreational rowing in the afterlife.

name: Blank CD
description: A CD with nothing in it. Pretty basic, but practically overflowing with potential.

name: Axe of Mass Deduction
description: In this case, 'deduction' means 'an amount subtracted from something', not 'a conclusion drawn from available information'. Although people will definitely deduct the fact that they are being deducted by how friggin' big this thing is.

name: Kamen Rider Super Hero Climax game
description: The latest game in the Kamen Rider Climax Heroes Fourze featuring almost all Riders from the original up to Wizard.

name: Jousting Sword
description: A lance made to also be used as a sword for the purposes of jousting and/or fighting.

name: Barizun Sword
description: Your Friendship will take on the universe! Using the power of space and friendship, this sword lance utilizes cosmic energy to enhance its attacks! It's like friendship is some kind of mysterious governing force.

name: Grenade-Shooting Axe
description: This axe can also shoot grenades, just make sure not to slice and shoot at the same time!

name: Medagaburyu
description: A weapon that is part-axe, part-bazooka. It's best not to ask how that works.

name: BurakkuSuta Dual-Edged Versatile Kusarigama
description: The name sounds as pompous as the previous wielder of myth was. You feel like an asshole just holding these. But it's a fairly powerful weapon and easy to hold and move.

name: Gun of Souls
description: This swordgun fires bullets formed of the souls reaped by the blade. Watch those imps suffer as they are killed by what's left of their friends.

name: Gunade
description: Running out of ammo is the equivalent of pulling the pin, so you better throw this sucker when you hear a click!

name: Cronus\'s Blade
description: The power of an ancient Titan and the father of a God is now in your hands.

name: Stroke of Midnight
description: All you hear is two sounds: clocks chiming... and bodies dropping.

name: Honking Death
description: May the light of the Mirthful Messiahs shine down upon thee. hOnK hOnK mOtHeRfUcKeRs!

name: .hack//GU Set
description: It's a set of all 3 games from the .hack//GU game series. So wait, it's a video game based on an anime about video games... sounds legit.

name: Double Trigger
description: Two pistols, two Blades, and a whole lotta pain.

name: Artifafct Slifer
description: Well... this is a surprise. The artifacting is barely present in this weapon, but it still does a good job of making artifacts of your enemies.

name: Lifehunt Beam Scythe
description: The hard-light blade grows stronger and thicker when it senses a nearby opposing life-force, or if it's feeling a little anxious.

name: Nintendo 4DS
description: All the capabilities of a 3DS... now with the added dimension of TIME! Playing it too long still hurts your eyes though.

name: Duster\'s Shoes
description: Stealthy, smells kind of funny, and makes you feel like you're on the most important journey in the world.

name: Extendable Lance
description: Wow, this thing is really long! And really flimsy. And it keeps retracting when you poke something with it.

name: Lance-A-Lot
description: Loyalty with a fine, long point!

name: STRONG SWEEP
description: The broom throbs in your hands, entirely made out of muscle and footballer blood. You could clean an underwater ocean liner with this deity's gift.

name: Acid Bristle Apocalypse
description: You're going to need some Rad-X after cleaning with this workplace health and safety travesty.

name: Brush with Death
description: The handle is torn asunder as thick rivulets of black liquid hate and pain drip through the otherwise innocuous broom. Safe to say that it's the masochist's duster of choice.

name: Mirror
description: It's a mirror. Look at that.

name: BROME
description: Let's be honest here. If you use this, you're only going to make things worse.

name: The Bat\'s Bane
description: A hammer created with the dark energies of the masterful CLOWN KING OF CRIME as a secret weapon against his archnemesis the NOCTURNAL NIGHTMARE. While not powerful enough to defeat THE DARK KNIGHT, it is a hefty weapon, fit for any who have a firm respect for the art of HARLEQUIN ESCAPADES and just a dash of INSANITY. Haa haa. Hee hee. Hoo hoo.

name: Brotherhood of Derse Poster
description: Come join in the grand Brotherhood of Derse! The Outer Ring is our path to a glorious and noble empire throughout Paradox Space!

name: Late-Night Duster
description: It feels like it's perpetually 3am and this broom stinks like spilled scotch, cigarette butts and long nights. This stained black brush makes you feel tired just holding it.

name: Nimbus 2001
description: As the sleek ebony design is cradled in your hands, you feel oddly awful. Like you've sold out. You've got a future in cleaning up after corporate fat cats.

name: Ice Broom
description: For when you have to sweep up those pesky fire hazards and  freeze imps in their tracks.

name: One-Man Witch Trial
description: The broom, or rather the twisted mockery of a branch, is completely on fire. Grasping it, the heat is palpable as it runs up your arm. Runes glow midst the flame. You're ready to fuck shit up.

name: Zodiac Chart
description: A chart of the western Zodiac.

name: Dominoes
description: Destroy your enemy through the power of CHAIN REACTION! ...Or you could just throw them or something...

name: Bombinoes
description: They put the "reaction" in "chain reaction". Ahahaha... haaa...

name: Dominukes
description: How did we get from children's games to weapons of mass destruction?

name: Sepulchribroom
description: You\'re going to clean up this universe with this almighty power.

name: Pikabat
description: This electrified bat allows you to give foes a small zap when hit. To differentiate it from the "Taser Bat", it also has a cute Pikachu face and makes little sound effects when you hit things.

name: T-shirt
description: A plain old t-shirt.

name: Flash Guitar
description: An electric guitar which emits light; very useful for illuminating dark areas. It seems possible that if the guitar's lights are somehow made bright enough, it could severely burn enemies...

name: Bristle Bearer of the Mountain Master
description: Be as swift as the coursing river. Mysterious as the dark side of the moon. Stand atop the mountain and be a man. More than a man.

name: BROOOM.....
description: What the hell are you holding. What the HELL ARE YOU HOLDING? YUO HVAVE THE POWER BROENHEIM....

name: Shinigami Guitar
description: A guitar with grim reaper motif. Black, emblazoned with a skull and scythe. It seems to be accompanied by a strange background noise every time a string is plucked. This gives new meaning to the term "death metal".

name: Magic Stick
description: You're not too sure how magical this thing actually is, but it looks decent for hitting things. Amusingly, despite the magic being strictly of the "whacky" variety, your strife specibus still considers it a wand.

name: Continuum Orchestrator
description: This conductor's baton seems to distort and bend space when wielded. Anything caught by the warp is torn apart from the inside.

name: Pentennial Penitentiary
description: A small, cylindrical prison with a pen tip. Good for both stabbing enemies and condemning them with five year sentences.

name: The Lost Penore
description: From my books surcease of sorrow - sorrow for the lost Penore - For the rare and radiant pen whom the angels named Penore - Nameless here for evermore.

name: Farmer\'s Market Negotiators
description: When you need a good deal on something, popping these into somebody's hand will surely lower the price.

name: Ambidexcalibur
description: All the weapons of King Arthur's time rolled into one! And then you have TWO of them!

name: Butcher Shop Duet
description: If one's to do a job, one might as well do it professionally...

name: Courtesian Courter
description: This minted coin bears the likeness of a certain DEMIMONDE GODDESS. It has a caribou, too.

name: Mark-It Steele Street Sign
description: This road sign was supposedly placed at Steele St. and Market Lane. Welcome to the corner of pain.

name: Hard-light Holographic Projector
description: Disclaimer: Manufacturers are not responsible for any burns caused by inappropriate use. Seriously, we know that it's solid and that you can touch it, but you really shouldn't be doing what you're thinking about doing.

name: Hard-light Projection Gloves
description: With a flick of your wrist, now you can summon a pair of holographic fists that are guaranteed to crush your enemies. Warning: May inflict minor burns.

name: Hard-light Holo-Rifle
description: Just snap your fingers and you can instantly be ready to face any threat. Considering how it's weightless and has no recoil, all you have to worry about is running out of power!

name: Hard-light Holo-pistol
description: Now you can have a concealed weapon that's stylish, powerful, and impossible to see until you bring it out! Considering the lack of recoil and weight, you could probably fire all day- provided that you keep the power supply charged.

name: Hard-Light Holo-Shield
description: Now you can protect yourself and your friends from a plethora of threats, just with the flourish of a hand. Works at a distance, with variable sizes!

name: Hard-light Holo-shotgun
description: Are you ready to spread the pain to a zombie apocalypse, but find lugging around an unwieldy rifle too cumbersome? Fret no more, now you have all the functionality of a shotgun combined with the the weightless nature of hard-light projections.

name: Hard-light Holo-wand
description: Worried about another wizard using Expelliarmus on you? Worry no more, because with these stylish gloves you can summon a trusty combination of technology and magic to your side at any time!

name: Holy Handgun
description: With bullets made of searing holy majyyks, you couldn't possibly lose! Smite those pesky liches with ease.

name: Dual Lacrosse Knives
description: Two short lacrosse sticks sharpened at the ends like knives.

name: Steeljack Deck
description: A case of 52 steel playing cards, perfect for throwing into the eyes of your enemies or foiling those pesky X-ray glasses your friends always use to cheat at poker.

name: Sparklepillow of Magic and Mystery
description: This plw is vr cmftabl.

name: Cape of Freedom
description: So free. So majestic. Never before has the home of the free and the brave felt so real to you as it does now; fluttering softly in the breeze behind you... it's an American flag tied around your neck.

name: Blahsadfeguie
description: This item is a test of Alchbuddy's stuff, if you can read this that means it worked and you can remove this item plz. If you can read this and you're a player... oh dear. (Note from the malwaredevs: We don't know how to spell Blah's name)

name: Unlit Molotov Cocktail
description: It's a bottle of vodka with a shirt stuffed in it. Seems pretty useless in this form.

name: Molotov Cocktail
description: This improvised explosive will set enemies ablaze when thrown. Not recommended for consumption.

name: Halberd
description: A two-handed pole weapon that came to prominent use during the 14th and 15th centuries.

name: Glassesputer
description: Hands free computer for the nerd who doesn't care how he looks.

name: Daedric Bow
description: A very powerful bow fit for Dovakiin.

name: Pork Chop
description: Oddly enough, no pigs were harmed in the making of this pork chop.

name: Pigpen
description: Now you've gone too farm.

name: Crystal Ball
description: Good for smashing to bits and for pretending to be a wizard. Or actually being a wizard. Y'know, if magic was real.

name: hellTRUMPET
description: Gives your enemies a delicious charred texture without having to stuff them into a toaster. Also inflicts heavy artifacting.

name: Blades Of Drunken Rage
description: Few enemies can withstand the fury of a warrior who is both enraged and totally hammered.

name: Midnight Mobster Kingpin\'s Demon Head
description: A demented staff depicting an evil mob boss who is so shadowy and mysterious, you don't think anyone has even heard of him before. Now THAT is an air-tight operation.

name: Trophy Fish
description: This fish is literally a trophy won in a fishing competition.

name: Tonfa
description: Dual weapons in the traditional style.

name: Gunblades
description: Two guns, two blades. Portable. Deadly. Symmetrical.

name: Green Sun Scepter / Golden Rifle
description: A weapon powerful enough to kill even beings that are beyond gods. Just how meta can you get?

name: Chain Gun
description: Fires so many rounds per minute, you can't even try to count that high. All will fear your giant new gun!

name: Giant Blade of Gunning
description: If you look very closely you will note that there is in fact a gun somewhere in all this sword.

name: Metal Gear Solid Complete Collection
description: A case of all the Metal Gear Solid games, including Peace Walker, but not Portable Ops. Because fuck Portable Ops.

name: Haunted Chopper
description: Dark flames emerge from the ebony handle of this golden-bladed weapon.

name: Shrek DVD
description: This movie's pretty ogrerated, in your opinion. <iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/5xxQs34UMx4?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: Razorsharp Souls
description: You feel an unholy spirit flying through the air. A small cut appears on your upper arm.

name: Bead-Drawer
description: This rifle fires off a powerful wave of unholy energy that's nigh-impossible to dodge.

name: Grimoire for Summoning the Zoologically Fictional
description: A book filled with instructions for how to summon and capture a variety of fictional monsters. It involves... walking into long grass? You suspect this is a load of bullshit.

name: Ghost Rider Jacket
description: Thank you for telling me I'm the Devil's bounty hunter.

name: Sleuthtop Computer
description: This thing is probably a useless piece of shit, but making it has caused you to feel an thrilling sense of adventure.

name: Red Key
description: A magnificent red BLADE. Just the appearance of such a weapon spells a death sentence for all born of illusion and FANTASY.

name: Laptop Sleuth Poster
description: This appears to be an ordinary poster. The only difference is Problem Sleuths gun is replaced by a laptop.

name: Exquisite Body Dissector
description: This bloodsplattered axe was used to cut several corpses into parts that are easier to... dispose. You hope you'll never have to use if for that purpose.

name: Rebellious Skullsword
description: A massive claymore with a skeletal crossguard. This certainly gives you a rush of adrenaline and bloodlust.

name: Chaoskampf
description: Heavy in its owners hand, this conducting baton billows with purple fog.  To wave it is to conjure an array of noises that sends a victim insane.

name: Darksiders 2
description: You play as Wars brother, Death. How incredibly relevant.

name: Apocalypse Horseman\'s Reaper
description: The scythe of the infamous horseman, Death. Not to be confused with all the other scythe-wielders named Death.

name: NINE yardstuck
description: DUDE, when you were told to come get the ruler check this out, you went the WHOLE NINE YARDS........

name: Tesseract
description: A multi-dimensional cube of untold power and mysterious qualities. It's hard to tell if this thing's magical, or simply incredibly advanced. Unfortunately, most mortals lack the capability of unlocking its true power when used alone...

name: Wumbo Wall
description: A shield imbued with the almighty power of Wumbo. It's a lot smaller than you thought it would be...

name: Firewall
description: A new extreme for internet security! If it wasn't for the Laptop, there is no way you would be able to wield this thing.

name: Super Sledge
description: The classic kinetically-enhanced sledgehammer from the Fallout series of games. This thing needs two hands to be used by an ordinary person, and has knockback like you wouldn't believe.

name: Lacrosse Sword
description: Didn't I tell you not to lacrosse swords?

name: Explosive Super Sledge
description: This Super Sledge has been enhanced with a reservoir to hold small bricks of C-4, which explode upon impact. This weapon could easily dislocate a weak person's shoulders, but you aren't weak, are you?

name: Halo\'s Pistol
description: Now you too space marine cyborg headshot pistol gun death bang from Halo 1st.

name: Candy Pop Gun
description: Victory is sweet.

name: Megaton Drill
description: How are you even lifting this?

name: Skipper Plumbthroat\'s Squiddlehunting Harpoon Gun
description: Warning: This item is not suitable for use by anybody under the age of 10. So tell your parents it's a toy!

name: Bottle of Glowing Ink
description: A bottle of dimly glowing ink. It leaves a somehow yellowish trace on the paper.

name: Scissoring Swing
description: A yo-yo with scissor blades that cut as it spins. Catching it may smart a little.

name: Thulu\'s Wrath
description: You aren't really sure who in their right minds would give limitless explosive power to a giant octopus dude.

name: Black King\'s Staff
description: The staff of an unprototyped Black King, while not as powerful as one that has been prototyped, it can deal massive amounts of magic or blunt damage, depending on how you wield it.

name: Sprinting with Scissors
description: Everybody out of the goddamn way, you've got a heel full of rocket, a toe full of scissors, and a head full of whiplash!

name: Scissor in the Sun
description: Scissors with sunglass lens attached to the handles. You REALLY don't feel comfortable with these near your eyes.

name: Atomslasher
description: A nuclear blast of carbonation follows every swing, causing heavy bleeding, truama, and tooth decay.

name: Chocolate Syrup
description: A bottle of store-brand chocolate syrup. Delicious, but pouring directly into your mouth is generally considered a sloppy endeavor.

name: Drawing of a Triangle
description: It's a flimsy piece of paper with a simple drawing of a triangle on it. Pythagoras would weep upon viewing this beautiful piece of art. It may be equilateral, but it feels oh so right.

name: Meat Shearer
description: Have you never been satisfied just shearing the wool off a sheep? Why not get the meat as well? Too bad it doesn't grow back like wool does...

name: Dragonslayer Spear
description: Spear of Dragonslayer Ornstein, from Dark souls. O&S always kicked your ass in that game.

name: Metal Shaft
description: The staff from Kamen Rider W's Metal combinations.  Heavy and powerful, the ends can extend an extra foot and ignite for a finishing blow.

name: Square Shot
description: An augmented slingshot that fires solid cubes instead of pellets.

name: Toy Bombers
description: Dismanteling this pile of blocks will result in a huge explosion. No one suspects anything underneath the wood.

name: Wanderer\'s Shot
description: The Lone Wanderer survived daily danger using old firearms. This slingshot can bestow you with his power.

name: Celestial Shot
description: A galaxy-fueled slingshot, able to shoot the stars right into your eyes. We ask that you be cautious.

name: Golf Club
description: A 9-iron from a standard golf set. Can be used to hit balls of any variety.

name: Digivolving Tarot
description: It's said that with enough practice, the Digimon on these Tarot cards will digivolve and the deck will increase in power. Or the art will get prettier. It's one of those two.

name: Digimon Cards
description: You have no idea what is going on with these cards. How do you attack? Why are there three sets of numbers there and four sets of numbers there? Who even designed this shitty game? Oh well, at least the card stock is sharp.

name: Duel Disk
description: This shitty plastic arm thingy is actually surprisingly powerful with the right set of cards loaded into it. It also folds up and looks somewhat cool, and is easy to use while riding a motorcycle.

name: Nintendium Shield
description: Known to some as the most durable material in existence, this rare Nintendium Shield also has 3D support! Truly the cutting edge in shield technology.

name: Spear Chucker
description: An oversized bow that fires spears. Why, what did you think it was?

name: Belt-top
description: Who needs tables? You can harness the Belt-top to anything with the latest leather technology. Otherwise, it works like an ordinary laptop.

name: Ookami
description: I am the white void, I am...etc etc...THE END HAS COME!

name: God of War Disc
description: The classical God of War game. In which you declare war on gods.

name: Bubble-o-matic Pistol 2000
description: If you find that your traditional pistol is too deadly and not child friendly enough we recommend the switch to this item.

name: Frigid Bubble Blower
description: A bubble wand with the ability to freeze objects and enemies using the bubbles blown with it.

name: Razor Cards
description: When you play a hand of these, you'll probably end up playing your actual hand as well.

name: Saint\'s Sin
description: These knives steal the life force of whatever they cut. They keep all of it, though.

name: Toaster
description: Launch toast at semi-medium speeds! ...Or just bash imps over the head with it.

name: Discwarper
description: A toaster that fires warped CDs at the target at medium velocity, but honestly, the heat does more damage than the projectile speed. You're still better off just using it as a bludgeon.

name: Rotary Disc Dealer
description: This toaster has been upgraded with rapid-spinning launchers inside, so when the discs are done they'll sail towards your enemies for a clean hot slice!

name: Wildcards
description: These cards are brimming with chaotic energy. All of the cards are jokers, and there is a W printed on the backs. If an enemy comes into contact with one, they are overwhelmed with madness.

name: Bladed Tonfa
description: These tonfa are balanced in every aspect, especially between offense and defense.

name: Green Armblades
description: A pair of tonfa that are long, green, and sharp, extending past the elbows. They give off a faint psychic aura.

name: Judge\'s Gavel
description: A solid, miniature hammer generally used in courts of law. Admit it, you've always wanted to pick it up and whack something with it.

name: Phoenix Write
description: A mighty blue pen adorned with a majestic feather, said to have been used by the most prestigious of lawyers.

name: Scissors of Bloody Murder
description: These scissors look more like a giant two-handed greatsword, but either way, it's GAME OVER for those imps!

name: The Nullifier
description: It seems this boomerang can't decide what the hell it wants to do. It's got it's own little display of time magic it seems, but also has a healthy distaste for all time magic. Shit's going haywire and it almost seems like the thing wants to tear itself apart.

name: Lightish rod
description: A lightish rod that is about as cool as those glasses that burned stuff with magnified light.

name: Loaded Cartridge
description: Actions speak louder than words. Write your words with bullets and get your message across!

name: Apollo\'s Bow
description: Some bow from some legendary blowhard who dragged the sun around or something. Probably not important.

name: Wooden plank
description: Got wood?

name: Scoped Rifle
description: A rifle with a telescopic sight, allowing for accurate fire at long distances.

name: Laser Rifle
description: Deadly accurate and powerful, the laser rifle has incredible range and rate of fire, with reduced need to reload. Batteries not included.

name: Channeler\'s Staff
description: A staff that appears to have magical properties. It overwhelms you with the desire to start doing the special martial arts dance, whatever that is.

name: Mosas Oar
description: Fashioned after the far more deadly mosasaur- top predator of it's time, this oar lives up to it's name.

name: Ichthyos Oar
description: An oar carved from the skeleton of a prehistoric beast.

name: Rules Card for Blackjack / Spades Key
description: You have possessed this item for as long as you can remember. You do not yet know its significance. Though you can hustle up a mean game of blackjack when you need to.

name: Infinity Pistol
description: This assault pistol has infinite ammo due to it being shaped like an infinity symbol... don't ask

name: Cosmic Apex
description: An obsidian lyre, coloured by bright ripples that look much like colourful nebula clouds. Each note is gorgeous to the player's allies, but horrific to their foes.

name: A Free Man\'s Crowbar
description: Pick up that can.

name: Shooting Stars
description: This weapon releases power bolts of pure photons.

name: Dark Matter Slinger
description: A children's toy gone horribly wrong. With great pressure comes great responsibility.

name: The Heart of the Cards
description: Sometimes, drawing just the card you need is more skill than luck. This is nothing like that, but it is complete bullshit. Oh, and ridiculously powerful. That too.

name: Kingdom Souls
description: A game that fluctuates between kindergarten difficulty and constantly dying. Hackneyed lessons about friendship are abound as you warp from world to world, attempting to stop lord Gwansem from activating the last kingdom heart, summoning familiar companions along the way. Prepare to ship.

name: Gun of Happiness
description: This gun is lukewarm and smells of hallucinogens. It gives off a giddy, yet capricious vibe.

name: AR Cards
description: Now you can bring your favorite characters to (virtual) life with these augmented reality cards. And when they're not aiding you in a strife, you can always waste time playing fishing, archery, or taking ridiculous pictures.

name: Gladius
description: A weapon used by footsoldiers of ancient Rome. You suddenly wish you had a javelin or at least a shield to use with it.

name: Sea Captain\'s Mace
description: A gorgeous Anchor like Mace that any captain of the sea would love.

name: Handsaw
description: Do you see what I saw?

name: Lug Wrench
description: When you need to lug your nuts, this is the wrench for you.

name: Destroyer Cannon
description: An experimental rifle made with salvaged technology from The Destroyer. I wonder what it does...?

name: Lil\' Spitfire
description: Perfect for the playful arson in you. Strike down enemies with the hot gyrating inferno produced by the spin of this tricked out yo-yo. The sharp thorns on it only add insult to injury, or in this case, injury to injury.

name: Megaton Hammer
description: "A long time ago there was an evil dragon named Volvagia living in this mountain. That dragon was very scary! He ate Gorons! Using a huge hammer, the hero of the Gorons... BOOOM! Destroyed it just like that."

name: Freezychair Sculpture
description: A semi-functional wheeled device for yetis or snowmen to sit in when their legs don't quite work. This chair doesn't quite work, actually, or at least not as a chair.

name: Burning Asfelt
description: A snazzy flamethrower! Now you feel like burning some asshole's mansion... and some clocks.

name: Conjurer\'s Cane
description: A magical staff used by apprentice wizards to cast basic spells. And in this case, "apprentice" means "doesn't know shit about magic".

name: Fabled Fightingstick
description: With every great wizard or warlock comes a kickass magical rod. And a less than flattering beard.

name: Lightgun
description: A shotgun that shoots a spread of light beams. Be careful, too much light is bad for your pasty skin.

name: Graphic Violence Calculator
description: A machine gun with a graphing calculator built into it. Sounds irrelevant, but it actually calculates the bullets' trajectory on the fly and adjusts it to better hit the target.

name: Telescopic Rifle
description: with this rifle you will be able to shoot a imp between the eyes in another Land

name: Targeted Dosage
description: A rifle that shoots syringes. The beaches of LA have nothing on you now.

name: Spear cane
description: One end is for holding to help you walk, and the other end is for stabbing things. Try not to get the two confused.

name: Nod Brand Rifle
description: This looks like your generic rifle, but it has a red and black finish, with a strange logo that looks like a scorpion tail inside a triangle.

name: Battery
description: Not included.

name: Il Barbiere di Siviglia
description: Vanquish your foes with the power of Italian comedic opera!  While the straight razor of famed factotum Figaro may not make you a master barber, it will surely save you from many a close shave.

name: Power Axe
description: A high-tech axe manufactured of high-strength, ultra-light, ultra-dense materials and also includes a kinetic energy storage device to increase momentum.

name: Steel Hockey Stick
description: Far more durable than a plain wooden stick.

name: BlazBlue Game Disc
description: Time shenanigans AND anime characters fighting it out using absurd weapons? What more could you want?

name: Thunderbolt Bow
description: A bow made out of bright yellow wood that gives all arrows fired an extra 'spark'.

name: Electric Pizzicato Violin
description: This is just another violin, but what? We do not need a bow! Hell yeah, electric pizzicato TIME!

name: Wasteland Sidearm
description: An old and weathered .45 revolver, it seems to be rusted all the way through a may fall apart any minute.

name: Iron Flail
description: This chain is improved with a hefty iron ball at the end for extra bone crushing powers. This may or may not be useful depending if imps have bones or not.

name: Stunstick
description: This electrifying club will leave your enemies in shock and awe.

name: Stone Shield
description: A heavy rock shield, both a useful defense and a stylish accessory.

name: Binary Bow
description: A powerful bow that shoots lasers rather than arrows. Comes with attached keyboard, targeting screen, extremely heavy battery and a useless mouse.

name: Psychic Bat
description: A baseball bat that seemingly holds psychic powers.

name: Blueberry Pie
description: This pie is so delicious, you might just eat the whole thing in one sitting!

name: Rider Kicks
description: Boots that bear a striking resemblance to those worn by Kamen Rider Wizard.

name: Lightning Rod
description: A dense metal rod able to attract lighting, just hope you aren't holding it when that happens.

name: Flaming Fedora
description: A fedora with a classic flames pattern. What kind of person would wear this?

name: Fake Arms
description: Convincing fakes for HILARIOUS ANTICS.

name: Stabs Deck
description: A deck of cards with edge sharp enough to cut through granite.

name: Com-Pen-Uter
description: A super computing pen! Has basic computer functions like cut, copy, paste, and undo.

name: Four of a Kite
description: The large shield is broken into four suits.

name: Blue Jello Shots
description:
You can't even taste the alchol!
*alclhl
*alcoholol
*nailed it

name: Defense Plus Badge
description: Cheaper than an actual defense!

name: Shadowboxcars
description: Very black, very threatening looking, very useless plastic dice. They might have potential, but you were expecting something cooler.

name: Astral Pike
description: A solid mahogany shaft topped with a glittering starmetal head in the shape of two fish. Their tails meet in a sharp point. The instructions on the side say to "point away from self" and note "may be stronger in February."

name: StenchSlasher
description: This sharp device will remove the body odor of the enemies, thus allowing for a more pleasant Strife experience.

name: Falchion
description: A dragonslaying sword of divine power forged from the fang of a... half-dragon? However it works, this is a pretty cool sword.

name: Dragonbone Greatsword
description: By the time you had a high enough smith skill to make it, you had enough dragon bones to make it a hundred times over.

name: Rapid-Fire Umbrella
description: Let a smile be your umbrella. Then shoot them with it.

name: Boozerang
description: A vodka bottle in the shape of a boomerang. Now you have an excuse to throw your bottle in a fit of drunken rage!

name: The Final Word
description: This is it. The absolute last word you will accept on this subject! If magic were REAL and not FAKE, then this would be the absolute embodiment of the destruction it can cause.

name: Telenecrotomeicon
description: A heavy, yellowed tome that smells of death and laminate. It is the telephone book of the dead... and now that you think of it, you haven't called your great-grandmother in a while.

name: Lightning Flash Guitar
description: An electric guitar which emits light, very similar to the Flash Guitar. However, it can also generate bolts of electricity and, thanks to its electric supercharge, can generate light strong enough to scorch enemies.

name: d4
description: Sometimes you need to make a decision, but a coin doesn't have enough sides and a regular die has too many.

name: Bewitchin\' Weave Shearz
description: Slightly larger hair shears with a bedazzled handle that emits a dark, ancient power. Wielding these makes you feel a little more powerful, and ghetto fabulous.

name: Buster Sword
description: Possibly the biggest piece of shit you've ever seen, with "biggest" in this case being literal. You should stick it behind the microwave and forget about it.

name: Broken Giant\'s Knife
description: 200 Rupees down the drain and still surprisingly heavy.

name: Laser Scalpel
description: Straight from the future of Medicinal Technology, able to make incisions with so much precision that your opposition might just make the decision to abort their mission.

name: Pocketwatch
description: A spring-driven pocket-watch.

name: English Cue/Pen
description: A dark green pool cue with a flashing stripe running along its side, a gold tip, and a rapidly alternating pool ball-shaped button on the side. If the button is pressed, it shifts to a smaller, yet equally powerful, pen form.

name: Kabuto Blaster 555
description: A very powerful, and unnecessarily complicated to wield gun. It has bug eyes on the handle, thought you're not sure if they serve any purpose.

name: Agagotop\'s Staffly Tablet Pen from the Nethers
description: Wow, what a fine looking tablet pen. Only problem is that it's LONG AS HELL, HEAVY, AND USELESS. That is, unless you're strong enough to wield this thing.

name: The Steady Chemist
description: Well, that was rather obvious, wasn't it?  Alright: you've added your tripod to your chemistry set.  That really doesn't change much, but now you can steady your beakers and flasks.  Or possibly toss them using the tripod as a makeshift atlatl.

name: Astro Star Slider
description: The embodiment and very essence of space all jam packed into one lustrous, jet black sphere that sparkles like the stars in the endless void. The blades orbiting it are reminiscent of Saturn's famous rings. If you can pick up a yoyo with the mass of Jupiter, it should serve you well in battle. Welcome to the Space Jam. Alright?

name: Jackass Poster
description: I'm a poster, and this is Jackass.

name: Stabbier Deck
description: It's the stabs deck, now with 38 percent more stab.

name: Kratos\'s Blades
description: The chained blades of Kratos himself.

name: Sonic Screwdriver
description: It looks more like a small flashlight than anything. Still, the buzzing little light light is very handy for taking apart whatever needs breaking. Unless it's made of wood. In that case, God help you.

name: Twin Blades
description: Huh, this doesn't seem much different than the knives you used? Yet they feel more comfortable and give you a strange compulsion to wear red and run with them behind you.

name: Hand Broom
description: Like a broom, but smaller.  You could probably clean up some small messes - or small enemies - with this.

name: Conksunk Boot...
description: who even MADE this conksunk boot anyway... IMIGRANTS?

name: Firework Bow
description: Arrows fired from this bow have firework rockets on the tips which cause a colorful (but weak) explosion on hit.

name: Ishmael\'s Right Leg
description: A normal sized walking cane weighing as much as a heavy anchor. If you can lift it, it packs a wallop.

name: Candy Corn Cutter
description: This is slightly better than a regular scalpel... I guess?

name: BLUINDERBUS....
description: You aren't actually going to shoot this, right?

name: Wrist Communicator
description: A device for all of your traveling needs.

name: Dual Zippives
description: Dual knives that can switch the fire around the blades on and off. Flames about as hot as a lighter's.

name: Book of Quantum Physics
description: This book contains the far reaching and hella complicated theories of how space works. Invaluable to the intrepid hero of space

name: Sodabomb
description: BE CAREFUL WITH THAT THING! JESUS CHRIST!!!!!!

name: Teddy Bear
description: A cute, cuddly teddy bear to keep you company on the battlefield.

name: Tenacious Teddy
description: This tough teddy bear follows you around and sometimes takes hits for you in combat. A true friend!

name: Super Plush Bear
description: Super soft and super cuddly, this bear makes an even better plush shield. While you use this stuffing to protect yourself, you can better focus on beating the stuffing out of your enemies.

name: History of Skyrim
description: A complex guide to the rich history of Skyrim lore. You suppose there could be less useful things, I mean, as hypothetical thought experiment, not in real life.

name: Sweeney\'s Revenge
description: These razors give off an intense aura of violence, vengeance, and.....singing?!

name: World of Warcraft Disc
description: The world's most popular MMO ever, considered the best by those who play it and the worst by those who don't.

name: Pump-Action Particle Accelerator
description: Forged beneath the Swiss-Italian border, this shotgun spews particles of Pb208 at relativistic velocities. Conduct fascinating research on the torsos of your enemies!

name: Clockpunk Cleaver
description: A brass sword covered in cogs and other various timepiece-related ornamentations. Most of the bulk is purely aesthetic, but hey, it looks cool.

name: Beam Cutters
description: Two blades of concentrated light. Great at parties and weddings!

name: God Acquainter
description: Imagine a gun that could shoot with the accuracy of a sniper and the force of a shotgun. Now imagine meeting your maker. Both of your fantasies are about to become real.

name: Amethyst Ring
description: A pretty gold ring adorned with a majestic amethyst gem. It'd fetch a pretty penny on Earth, but it's kind of worthless in the Medium.

name: Mountain Dew: Pitch Black
description: A not-so-refreshing bottle of Mountain Dew: Pitch Black. It tastes a little fishy.

name: Pencil
description: You may only be #2, but you are #1 in my heart!

name: Bag of Marbles
description: Don't lose these.

name: The Ultimate Doom Disc
description: When you want to take a break fighting countless imps in the Medium, why not fight countless imps in Hell instead?

name: River of Time
description: Looks like a large wristwatch with a narrow 'strap' that makes the handle. You're not sure you can row with this.

name: Prank Revolver
description: The only bullets in this gun are little flags that say 'BANG!' Kind of useless for fighting with, but good for a laugh or threatening caped crusaders.

name: Switchblade
description: Now it's safe, now it's not!

name: Camel\'s Eye Needles
description: "It is easier to put a needle through the eye of a camel than for..." Wait, that's not how that saying goes!

name: Pip-Boy 3000
description: Every Vault Dweller gets one of these on their 10th birthday. Now you have one of your very own!

name: Mass Effect Trilogy
description: All three Mass Effect games in a single set. This is pretty cool, you have to admit, especially if you have a Playstation 3. As long as you remember not to bring up the ending in a room of gamers.

name: Omni-Blade
description: This wrist-computer features the latest technology, including an interface to instantly create a disposable blade for heavy melee hits.

name: Eternal Flames
description: These knives burn infinitely with a spiritual flame that can wound the soul. Just imagine if an emo got hold of one of these...

name: Ruyi Jingu Bang
description: An extendable and retractable staff much like the one used by the monkey king. It only changes size though, no multiplication for you!

name: David and Goliath
description: A staff that is topped with a massive slingshot. It's more effective at range, but don't let that stop you from conking a few heads.

name: Big Ben
description: A dark blue staff topped by a giant, ticking clock. Very useful for crushing enemies and keeping time.

name: JoJo\'s Bizarre Adventure Vol. 13
description: Manga featuring bulging muscle, ghostly spirits, and wild poses. What more could a person want.

name: Phantasy Star Online Ep. I & II
description: A rather obscure and overlooked game featuring magic technology... and catgirls... or something.

name: Royal Guard Flush
description: Be a demon in battle AND at the poker table!

name: Crowd Trimmer
description: A long and sharp scythe, used by soul farmers to harvest necks.

name: Phlegethon Oar
description: Crafted from the burning waters of the River Phlegethon. Purge your enemies' souls.

name: PriSword
description: The magic contained in this sword shines brighter than a television show in heaven playing in the middle of the night.

name: Planet Crusher
description: Fast and packs enough punch to send your enemy into a brand new crater on the moon!

name: Arcus Diabolus: Bolverk
description: A set of dual pistols that bends space around its shots, allowing them to go through obstacles on their way to the target.

name: The D6-Volt
description: The D6-Volt is designed to be used as a die after the battery is drained of power. Unfortunately for the designer, the die is too oddly shaped to fit inside any battery-powered item and the + end of the battery ruins its ability to roll, making it totally worthless.

name: Light Retriever
description: When some light is over there, and you want it to be over here, use this oddly-shaped mirror!

name: Second Splitter
description: A clock-themed sword with the ability to warp time with every thrust. Though there appears to be no moveable pieces, a faint ticking can be heard emanating from the hilt.

name: Basketball
description: Getting slammed in the face with this must hurt. Your enemies will be in a real jam with this in your hands.

name: Chocolate Coin
description: A hand-sized, golden-wrapped coin of chocolate. You can throw it at imps, just eat it before it starts to melt!

name: Abyssal Greatsword
description: Darker and edgier... literally.

name: Disappearing Ink
description: The classic prank, now in alchemical form. Maybe it'll achieve new found popularity now that most of your planet has ceased to exist.

name: Star Ocean Disc
description: A game with a very long and complicated timeline... IN SPACE!!!

name: Coldfinger
description: Your enemies might expect you to talk, but you should just poke them in the eyes instead with these freezing fisticuffs.

name: Steel Wolverine Claws
description: Steel Wolverine claw-gloves used to play at being X-Men. This ain't no plastic knock-off, this is the real deal! Er, realer than plastic anyway.

name: Live After Death album
description:
Legend has it that there was an incredibly rare misprint in this particular release of the album.  Those that were to take the record out of its sleeve and view it would become...
It's a goddamn record, dipshit.

name: Spare Key
description: A spare key for your house. Could do as a stabbing weapon in a pinch.

name: Steel Guitar
description: This ain't your daddy's old dobroe, this is a heavy, blunt instrument, capable of hitting harder than a Van Halen solo!

name: R.O.B. the Robot
description: He's slow as shit, works with two games, and is loud as hell, but you can't help but love him. He helped save the gaming industry, too!

name: Skullarang
description: This is a boomerang... made of skulls? It's not realy efficient.

name: Lead Ion Accelerator
description: Groundbreaking technology that will surely break your enemies and leave them baffled. It's scientifical!

name: A Sweaty Surprise
description: I don't think you want to know what's inside this pillowcase. Whatever it is, it feels like it has a trigger. At least you hope that's a trigger.

name: Sword of Bubble\'s Bane
description: The bubble blower of the legendary hero.

name: Fire Emblem: The Sacred Stones
description: This Fire Emblem game is widely know among the series fans. The Sacred Stones has you fighting to save humanity against the Demon King, Fomortiis.

name: Super Shotgun
description: This double-barreled 2-gauge shotgun is the pinnacle of demon-killing technology. The UAC is not liable for the loss of limbs caused by the recoil of this weapon.

name: Nyx\'s Wrath
description: Wield a power that's been feared since the dawn of existence. Tear asunder the fabric of reality and call forth a night which shall last FOREVER!

name: Chicago Handwriter
description: When you need to kill fast, and writing is too slow, it's time to switch to an automatic pen.

name: X - Wheel of Fortune
description: A revolver with a constantly spinning cylinder. If you put in one bullet, it can take down a hippopotamus. Six bullets and you might take down an imp. When not in use, it is stored within its card.

name: Stratocaster
description: This astronomical guitar can play everything from Greensleeves to Smack My Bitch Up.

name: rifl
description: This thing is so shitty that you're surprised that it can even fire... but when it does, it floats away due to knockback and weight physics throwing in the towel.

name: Circular Saw
description: This gas powered tool makes short work of lumber and enemies alike.

name: Mehrunes\'s Razor
description: It is unknown whether the Daedric Prince of Destruction used this weapon to cut short his facial hair, but in your hands you can be certain it is the lives of your enemies that will be cut short. Or your facial hair if you want, I guess. Who's going to argue when you've got this thing?

name: Geneva\'s Wrath
description: A single diplomatic treatise drafted by the Tetrixcaliber itself. The formalized notation describes a clear and present violation of our most basic human rights notarized in the sickest literary burn possible.

name: Yorick\'s Return
description: A scythe made from skulls, by skulls, for skulls.

name: Black King\'s Beatemups
description: A pair of shining carapacian gauntlets inspired by everyone's favorite endgame monstrosity. Even come with their own custom mini-prototypings and gross appendages!

name: Dustpounder
description: This broom seems oddly... dense.  You could probably whack something pretty damn hard with this.

name: Lance of Olyndicus
description: A god-given silver lance that you could put to good use in a rebellion.

name: Spearmint Candy Cane
description: A king-sized, sharpened cane made of spearmint candy, so you can sneak a lick in between stabbings! Just don't lick the end you use to stab with.

name: Frostflame Claws
description: With the left claw of ice and right claw of fire you can take down the mightiest foe, just don't clap your hands.

name: Card Shuffler
description: Shuffles cards at a whimsy, and may or may not spray them everywhere. It's all up to how it feels really.

name: Star Wars: The Complete Saga
description: All the Jedi goodness you could wish for in one package. But did Han shoot first in this edition?

name: Lancer Assault Rifle
description: Straight out of the Space Marine games and into your hands, this gun will shoot apart your enemies or grind them to pieces. Just remember to thank Cliffy B.

name: The Sword in the Stone
description: Unfortunately for you, only the true king can pull it out. Fortunately for you, nobody had the ingenuity to bludgeon people with it instead.

name: Lucifer\'s Sword
description: The sword of the Prince of Pride and the leader of the fallen legion.

name: Eddie the Beheader
description: This seems like a semi-obscure reference of some sort, but you can't quite put your finger on why.  It looks pretty goddamn metal, though.

name: Fancy Santa
description: It is santa. It is fancy. It is glorious.

name: Doritos
description: Cheesy triangle chips. Great for absentmindedly snacking on.

name: sikc ACKSE
description: slauy smome IMPgs wIth a rockiN SOlo

name: Chain-Saw
description: The underlings are sure to be fearful once they hear you have a chain-saw, what they don't know is that it is literally a chain with a saw bonded to one end, but maybe that's just as intimidating.

name: STELE SORD.....
description: A surprisingly decent upgrade to the SORD. Still looks like shit though.

name: Conductor of Undeath
description: Resonates with a dark power. Any normal person would be afraid to use this.

name: Apple Annihilator
description: A sharp object meant for you hold up to your ear. What could go wrong? Unfortunately the signal gets jammed when the blade is covered in gore.

name: Nominomicon
description: A book filled with obscenely powerful magics, now changed to edible form. You're not sure what the energies will do to you if you eat it, but it's as if the book is compelling you to. It just... looks so... TASTY...

name: Hands-On Guide to the Universe
description: This book contains personal instructions and even pre-made inter-dimensional portals that serve to defeat your enemies swiftly. Also it does a good number to hit your enemies with the weight of the universe.

name: Persona Compendium
description: A compendium of Personas acquired through a certain blue room and a man with a very long nose...

name: Cetus\' Downfall
description: With deadly efficiency, the dread of the seas strikes. With brute force, you crush all in your path.

name: Atomic Bufula
description: Imbued with frost magic, this lance can freeze anything it comes in contact with. Wielding it makes you feel a little mischievous.

name: Dimensional Warper
description: This pistol is powerful enough to tear and bend local space, allowing you to rend your target into billions of pieces with ease- assuming you don't completely obliterate them.

name: Bull Penis Cane
description: Your enemies will dislike getting whacked with it just as much as you dislike holding it.

name: Automatic Card Spewer
description: A machine gun loaded with playing cards that shoots them out at high speeds in quick succession. How's THAT for 52 card pickup?!

name: Lightsaber
description: An elegant weapon for a more civilized age. Unfortunately the Force may not be with you because it is fake as shit, so try not to decapitate yourself while you wave it around.

name: Cocytus Oar
description: Perpetually frozen from the chilled waters of the Cocytus, a faint wailing sound can be heard.

name: Fire Beam
description: Now that's how you start a fire!

name: Signed Till Lindemann poster
description: Well, okay, it has the rest of the band in it, but... you just can't look away.  Dammit, now you looked too long and are attracted to a German metal star.  There's worse fates.

name: Australian Wingtip
description: It's time for your enemies to bend over and receive their destiny.

name: Ace of Clubs / Crook of Felony
description: It's time to deal those underlings a senseless shin-drubbing with your CROOK OF FELONY.

name: utLIMaTe SORACKSE!!11
description: Utimade artifcating for ultmimate DmAGE!

name: thE Time kEper
description: A version of the SORD which has an orange(copper?) color with a light yellow(gold?) lining, and a clock embedded in the blade. For some reason the clock has four hands.

name: Rocket Board
description: It's like a hover board, but a lot cooler... except when it burns your ankles.

name: Pole-wrench
description: A staff with a wrench head, for long-range bolt-tightening.

name: Lava Lamp
description: A psychedelic little lamp, with colorful hot goop floating around inside.

name: Summer Madness
description: A chromatic staff with a shining disco ball on top. Colorful plasma emanates from in-between it's cracks, and can be controlled through the use of powerful disco magics. Or by hitting things really hard and spraying it all over them.

name: Chitauri Scepter
description: With this in hand, you are as a god among mere mortals. All will kneel before you or perish in the face of your wrath. You're not sure why, but you feel a lot more chaotic and emotional when wielding this...

name: Shot in the Night
description: A chrome revolver with a diamond grip, that shoots hot plasma rounds. Bullets come in a variety of funny seventies-themed shapes, like peace signs or those wierd flower things!

name: Winter Sadness
description: This silver blade is covered in frost and cold to the touch. It seems to emanate a variety of colorfully ominous glows, however, and some kind of strange substance runs under its icy cover.

name: Herald of the Aduckalypse
description: Entire species of beast and fowl have fallen before the hungering maw of this terrifying weapon. Blindingly fast, impossibly accurate, it only awaits a bearer to carry on the slaughter. You're... pretty sure it isn't actually sentient.

name: Plasma Pumper
description: A chromatic shotgun with a transparent middle, where colorful gloop floats around  inside. Shoots globs of searing plasma at high speeds. Impress your friends! Burn your enemies!

name: Fists of the Furiously Flaming Furies
description: Feel the heat with these dubiously dark flaming fists of the underworld. Shoot fireballs, flip off JRPG heroes: the possibilities are endless!

name: Ullapool Caber
description: This may just look like a club with a grenade stuck to the end of it, but more people have lost an eye to this thing than you care to count.

name: Eternity\'s Wandering
description: A key-themed sword riddled with clocks and hourglasses, humming with power and obnoxious ticking noises. Useful for locking the front door and causing time paradoxes while you're at it.

name: Rocket Arms
description: Think rocket gloves, but all the way up to the elbows. You can fire these puppies at enemies from afar for a good wollop! Unless you grafted them to your skin like a dumbass.

name: Scattergun
description: You are now an interstellar space warrior! Or at least you look like an asshole impersonating one...

name: The Colt
description: Back in 1835, when Halley's Comet was overhead, same night those men died at the Alamo, they say Samuel Colt made a gun. A special gun. He made it for a hunter.

name: Needler
description: Space alian combinibinmine shrek monster split jaw technology in the hands of a space marine john. Death has a new holiday.

name: Dragon\'s Breath
description: It's an array of backwards rockets on a gun. How you manage to not fly into the sky is a mystery.

name: GyroJet
description: Literally lightyears ahead of it's time.

name: Fat Man
description: A shoulder-mounted tactical nuclear catapult. It looks extremely heavy and you doubt you can safely use such a large explosion.

name: MC Reflectospheres
description: Just make sure not to blind anyone if you use these in the sun.

name: Aged Sword
description: An ancient sword composed of a sharpened bone blade. So light, but so difficult to not cut your arm off.

name: Inksickle
description: This curved blade lets off splashes of black ink when slashed around. Messy but effective for blinding enemies.

name: Light Scythe
description: A scythe with a blade of hard light. The scythe is rather cheaply made and the blade is unstable due to the unconventional shape, but it's more effective than a regular cheap scythe at least.

name: Knifegun
description: So is it a knife that shoots bullets or a gun that shoots knives? The answer is both!

name: Mysterious Doll
description: This odd doll seems to radiate a strange energy. It kinda creeps you out a bit.

name: NIFE
description: This incredibly shitty knife is probably the worst thing you've ever had a hand in creating. How HIGH were you when you had the idea to make this? It emanates j-peg artifacts...

name: Godspeak Amulet
description: When one puts on this amulet, one can hear strange voices in their head. It is suspected that they belong to ancient gods, seeking an outlet through time and space to vent their zeroth-world problems.

name: Godspeak Scepter
description: This staff draws its power from the gods of eons past. You'd be surprised how much faith still drives those gods to this day, especially if the wielder shares this belief.

name: Ahab\'s Sidearm
description: Enemies flee from you in terror, but no matter which direction they run, they cannot escape your double wrath.

name: HAmorr
description: A Sbahjified cartoon mallet that seems to hit where ever you aren't actually aiming it. It tends to have a defective attraction to banging your best bro's mom.

name: Auto-Burner
description: An automatic rifle that shoots lasers. Heat burns, but no knockback. Nifty!

name: Deathscythe\'s Scythe
description: This scythe is almost too big to wield as it is, but it was originally much bigger - it's the weapon of a giant mech, in fact!

name: Laser Skull
description: A skull that shoots lasers. It gives what it promises.

name: Sniper Scythe
description: A gigantic red scythe equipped with a sniper rifle down the handle. With this in your hands, you feel unstoppable.

name: Brisingr
description: This sword is so shitty that it somehow goes out the other side and becomes miraculous again.</br>...wait. That's not a misspelling? Oh dear.

name: Ouroboros Chain
description: An infinitely long black and green chain that has a clasp at the end shaped like a snake's head. It feels like you could pull things out of the void with this.

name: Elven Spellbook
description: Written in the ancient tongue of the elves, this tome gives instructions for casting several potent spells. Most of them require ELF TEARS to function.

name: Amethyst Scepter
description: A shiny staff topped with a gemstone of amethyst.

name: Triangle
description: It's like a tuning fork without the fork or tuning parts.
