name: Plastic Pyramid Poppers
description: For the gambler that doesn't care if he blows his chances.

name: Zweihander
description: A true two-hander. Literally, that's what the name means. Because it's massive.

name: Suite Marbles
description: A bag of 52 marbles, each with a suit and a number inside.

name: ACME Inc. Holo-Anvil Emitters
description: What's worse than getting punched in the face with an anvil? Getting punched in the face with TWO anvils! Whats worse than that? The anvils AREN'T EVEN REAL.

name: Fists of the Knights of the Elderly Male Royalty
description: Shining silver gloves embedded with blue jewels and embossed with a crown of royalty. These gloves seem to allow their user to conduct the wind to a fault, making it possible for him or her to spin around like a moronic (and destructive) top.

name: A Real Human Being\'s Jacket
description: It was acceptable in the 80's. It was acceptable at the time. Its also acceptable when beating someone's skull in with a hammer.

name: Joustin\' Jettison Chair
description: Your rocket ride has been tricked out in full-on feudal gear, including a sweet coat of arms, tournament flags and weapon holders on the side for high-speed jousting. Also includes a shitty fake horse head attached to the front. For all the fun of jousting, minus the disembowelment and equine feces.

name: Cans\' Crushers
description: A pair of goofy green fists modeled after those of the beloved green gangster himself. Knock them into next week, or at least give it a good try, with these fat fake fists. Do a can crush everyone!

name: ACME Inc. Amulet
description: 100% guaranteed not to protect you from falling pianos.

name: Inglourious Basterds Poster
description: Something seems off about this poster. Not enough bare feet, probably.

name: Schutzstaffel Coat
description: A styling leather jacket accentuated with German regalia. Most likely considered a faux pas on your now dead planet.

name: Brass Knuckles
description: Trusty Pair of Brass Knuckles, used for PUNCHING, HITTING, and ATTACKING.

name: Un Amico
description: A suspiciously bloody baseball bat, wrapped in dog tags. Knock 'em out of the park and aim for the head for maximum damage!

name: Electrified Fountain Pen
description: Great for ruining your friend's clothing and frying enemy nerves until they're a twitching heap at your feet! Also, that pen nib is sharp.

name: Fancy Gloves
description: Soft silky formal gloves for formal people and/or corpses.

name: Big Apple Circus Flyer
description: At least they weren't throwing PIES at you.

name: Dead Horse Beater
description: This joke is so dead.

name: Beefy Hard-Light Boxin\' Gloves
description: Give 'em the ol' one two with a new twist: hologram projectors give your punches more range and accuracy! They also aren't technically YOUR punches because they are holograms and not attached to your wrists but lets not get technical here.

name: Toy Story DVD
description: Everyone's favorite animated classic about envy, betrayal and crushed hopes and dreams.

name: Shrek Pistol
description: Whoever gets hit by this pistol's bullets time is OGRE.

name: The Heart Of Darkness
description: A sword shaped like a key, seemingly made of old steamboat parts that still creak with engine power. You aren't sure what else you were expecting, really. There's also a skull on it. THE HORROR!

name: Thorned Bandage Gloves
description: Its like a glove made of bandages, but the bandages are dark and presumable evil thorns. They also hurt a lot. Good job, genius.

name: The Lord Of The Rings Trilogy
description: J. R. R. Tolkien's epic saga about how even the smallest of heroes can have the greatest impact.

name: Gasmask
description: The perfect accessory to any adventure-seeking wasteland survivor and/or fetishist.

name: Beanie
description: You look like one of those hip happers.

name: Blazer
description: Good for spicing up any occasion and just generally looking attractive. Unless you are also ugly.

name: Formal Suit
description: The suit makes the (wo)man.

name: Zip-It-Good Premium Security Stool
description: A bar stool covered in a copious amount of belts and zippers, as well as what seems to be Japanese graffiti. Nobody's going to be able to steal THIS baby from your pub, let alone want to.

name: Ectoplasm-Covered Bar Stool
description: You.. guess you could stick this to someone? You thought it was barf for a second, but then nobody's really puked that precise hue of blue before in YOUR establishment.

name: Panty and Stocking DVD
description: The first and only, ever, season of misadventures between two frisky females.

name: Felt-Covered Speakeasy Stool
description: Taken straight from the Felt Manor speakeasy, this stool has a soft green cushion and legs made out of pool cues. Give them the TIME of their life with this handy seat/weapon hybrid! Actually this wasn't stolen because then you'd be hunted by vengeful mobsters with tired asses, and so far that hasn't happened yet.

name: The Rocky Punch Kit
description: A lone boxing glove and a glass of water, perfect for on and off camera cranial harm. Boxing has never been quite as wet, or obnoxious!

name: Googly Glasses
description: A pair of goofy-ass eyes on springs that jiggle with every step.

name: Nobody\'s Home
description: A little plush friend in a black raincoat, a bit chilly to the touch. You can't take its hood off, so it must be some kind of rap enthusiast.

name: Steel Skull on a Stick
description: Now with 100% more METALLIC ACTION!!!

name: Red Hot Skull on a Stick
description: All the metallic action, NOW WITH THE ADDED HEAT!

name: Thunder Skull on a Stick
description: All the metallic action, NOW WITH ADDED SHOCK!!!

name: SHAKE SPEERANR....
description: YOU CAN NOW REENACT SHAKESPEARE.

name: Snake Eyes
description: The sneakiest dice available. Don't expect to roll anything higher than a two, though.

name: Midnight Cleave
description: A sharp, lightweight dangerous black scythe glowing a faint orchid colour. It emits a crimson aura.

name: Electric Hyperdrive
description: A sharp scythe modeled after a small yellow rodent. It's an electrifying scythe that gives off a wicked thunderbolt that may paralyze enemies.

name: Windows
description: You don't know why these shades are named after an operating system, but it's a really weird pun, you suppose. Eyes are windows for your mind or something...

name: The Magical Toaster
description: It's a magical toaster, you guess. You'd try making some toast with it, but the settings have buttons like "Fireball", "Lightning", and "Blizzard".

name: Guide to the Mythologically Mundane
description: Good god, this book is even bigger than the first two books combined! The table of contents alone is about as big as the book of mythology. You suppose it's because of all of the cultural mythology passed down the millennia.

name: Datawrench
description: Imps can have one of two binary states when it comes to their health: living or dead. And you're all out of 1's.

name: The Twin Hells: Fire & Brimstone
description: The burning power barely contained in these dangerous guns can summon fire and create enitre feilds of smouldering pain when fired at full power, thankfully most people have the good sense not to casually use these at full power...... do you?

name: Leviathans Reignmaster
description: Take control of the terror of the deep and lay waste to all who oppose you.

name: Celestial Fulcrum
description: This conductor's baton seems to be made from a miniature, solidified constellation. Waves of the baton are accompanied by orchestral music and bright bursts of flame.

name: Swordcane
description: This item combines the biting edge of a sword with the drubbings only a cane can mete out.

name: Hero\'s Slingshot
description: A slingshot a hero once used to save a magic tree from a cursed spider. He probably wasn't on drugs. Probably.

name: Dragon Pipe
description: Inhale, exhale fire. Inhale, exhale fire. Or you could just blow out of it so you don't shrivel up your tongue.

name: Wall of Light
description: Your enemies will find it hard to hit you with this shining in their eyes.

name: Chainsaw
description: An actual chainsaw, for the suckers/lumberjacks who couldn't settle for a punny flying guillotine.

name: Marionette
description: A basic little puppet, most commonly used for childrens television, puppet shows and simulating porn shoots.

name: Sock Puppet
description: It's pretty much just a sock with some crummy button eyes glued on. You wish you could've picked a sock to deface that didn't smell this awful.

name: Stone-Cold Fancy Santa
description: A shimmering fancy santa made completely out of ice. Seriously this shit is COLD. If you're actually going to use this junk please wear gloves or something so you don't lose a finger.

name: Ectoslimed Saint Nick
description: Someone sprayed blue gunk all over this poor santa. You didn't think it could look any uglier. Looks like it'll stick to an enemy, or your hands. That would be the worst case scenario because then you wouldn't be able to throw it away.

name: Ectoplasmic Fancy Santa
description: Just what you always wanted for christmas: a gaudy little santa modeled out of disgusting blue slime. You can't even really get a handle on this thing, if you even wanted to.

name: Holly Jolly Ho-Ho-Holographic Santa Projector
description: Its like Christmas, but it's A)not real, B)stupid and C)all year round!

name: Fancy Santa Poster
description: Oh shit this is so fancy, it has fake tinsel and bells and everything you ever didn't want.

name: Santa on a Horse Poster
description: He looks a little disgruntled. The horse, I mean.

name: Midnight Santa Poster
description: Not a creature was stirring, especially not the hundreds of thugs that Santa had just beat to death with a candy cane and a bag full of coal.

name: Skeletal Santa
description: Looks like Santa's been watching his weight. Amaze your enemies with this dynamic holiday fusion, and by amaze we mean smash them over the head repeatedly.

name: North Pole Projector
description: The only thing this junk will display are several projections of jolly winking santa heads.

name: Shaving Error Santa
description: A fancy santa covered in shaving cream. You hope this means he's flammable.

name: Shaving Error Santa REQUIEM
description: You made a fancy santa made completely out of shaving cream. Fucking incredible. And useless.

name: Sleuthin\' Santa
description: Someone cast Arthur Clause a pair of concrete shoes, and now Saint Nick's on the case. Comes with his own little fedora and pipe and smells like stale cigarettes.

name: KRAMPISS
description: Just when you thought it couldn't get any more festive/terrible, you've devised a fanciful santa that clips through walls and pretty much any immediate surface. It also smells like weed.

name: Ore no Santa
description: A weak-structured santa made out of various minerals, and worth about half the price of them all combined.

name: REAL STEEL SANTA
description: A fancy santa made out of SOLID STEEL. Its heavy as hell, but considering its supposedly a weapon this is an actually POSITIVE ATTRIBUTE.

name: Stardust-Covered Santa
description: Ugh, gross, it'll take weeks to get this sparkly junk off your hands.

name: Disappearing Fancy Santa
description: You didn't really want to look at this thing anyway.

name: Xtra Jolly Santa
description: This bouncy santa's decked out in gaudy clown makeup and oversized shoes, and squeaks and honks when you throw him. Set up some SICK RICOCHETES with your new-found rubbery friend(?)!

name: Chainsaw Sluggin\' Santa
description: Just when you thought chopping down christmas trees was getting boring, this santa's equipped with a pair of mini chain-saws and an passion for environmental decay.

name: Santa on a Stick
description: Establish your dominance over the lesser folk with a whack on the head from this tinsel-covered staff of unadulterated shittiness. Careful, it's REALLY ugly!

name: Wooden Fancy Santa
description: Keep this up, and you'll have a WHOLE COLLECTION of flammable fancy santas at your disposal!

name: Temporally-Erratic Saint Nick
description: A santa that keeps shifting in and out of your timeline and emanating strange energy pulses. Worst of all it makes this terrible ticking noise. Maybe that alone will destroy your enemies?

name: Smokin\' QB Santa
description: Great for starting fires, considering this football-themed santa seems to be eternally up in flames. Reenact your favorite plays while wearing asbestos-covered gloves!

name: Fancy Holiday Tux
description: Ever wanted to dress in glaring crimson, decked out in mistletoe and faux fur? Of course you didn't!

name: Plain Mask
description: This isn't going to do you much good by itself, unless you want to look like you have a pimple for a head.

name: Weihnachtsmann\'s Mantel
description: A crimson leather coat adorned with festive mistletoe, bells and white fur trimmings. A ritzy clash of fashions between the fictionally beloved and the historically unsuccessful.

name: Zirkus-Jacke
description: Gold and crimson make up the color scheme of this eye-blinding leather coat, complete with a spinning goofy bowtie. Be the psuedo-ringleader/psuedo-axis power you never knew you wanted to be!

name: Tombstone
description: Something usually reserved to mark dead things is now going to help you make more dead things! Isn't life grand?

name: Blaster
description: How uncivilized. Effective for gunning down untold numbers of Imperial Stormtroopers, but watch out for people with glowing sticks.

name: Razorbristle
description: This is pretty useless for cleaning.  If you don't mind scratching the floors, you could probably scrape stuff off...

name: HammerFall: Infected Poster
description: This poster is black on black.  You're not entirely sure what the image in black is, but you're pretty sure it's either a hand or biohazard symbol.  In any case, the name of the band and album are on it in blood-red.

name: Flamethrower Suit
description: This suit has wrist-mounted flamethrowers and is on fire.  It also has GODDAMN WINGS WITH GODDAMN FLAMETHROWERS IN THEM.  Seriously, what did you think would happen when you mixed pyromaniac pyrotechnicians and lighters?

name: Dirtmaul
description: Sometimes you just gotta beat that dirt into submission.

name: Kitty\'s Bane
description: A horrendously long laser pointer. Not entirely useful, unless you plan on marking your imps before bashing them?

name: Quark-Gluon Plasma Sprayer
description: Do you like plasma? Of course you do. Do you like high-density, ridicunasty quark plasma? Of fucking course you do!

name: Dwemer Crossbow
description: A crossbow made of the mysterious compound metal that was favored by the Deep Folk.

name: Maledictive Megatunneler
description: Thousands of runes sweep up across the flute of the drill, you begin to hear echoes of the dead as soon as you pick it up, and every single one is asking you how the hell can you even LIFT this.

name: Skull Hammer
description: Crush (and creep out) your enemies with this skull-adorned hammer!

name: Umbdrilla
description: An umbrella with a drill tip at the end.  When opened, the entire umbrella spins at high speeds.  Works great on ogre faces.

name: Pen-Guin\'s Umbrella
description: A rather sharp looking Umbrella with a long blade at the end, covered in ink.  Classy monocle not included.

name: Scott Pilgrim & the Infinite Sadness
description: Volume 3 of Bryan Lee O'Malley's graphic novel Scott Pilgrim.

name: Large Hammer
description: Ramona Flower's Large Hammer. Does greater damage against girls... which would be useful if those underlings actually had genders.

name: Jolly Jugulator
description: Bring a healthy dose of holiday cheer, one wound at a time.

name: The Claus Crippler
description: Your enemies will be caroling all the way to the grave with this gruesome weapon.

name: Trident of Poseidon
description: Three-pronged weapon of the sea god himself, brimming with power.

name: The Stool Sample
description: Knock someone's block off with this stool. Might wanna take a few swigs before you touch it though, God knows where it's been.

name: Black Friday Bomb
description: Pull the hat off and throw it for big savings! Hope those bad guys kept their receipts!

name: Flaming Arms
description: Slightly more dangerous fakes for slightly warmer antics.

name: Machine Gun Gauntlets
description: These metal gloves will make you just like Iron Man! Kinda. Not really, actually. Still pretty cool though. Bet Iron Man doesn't have kickass wrist-mounted machine guns. Take that, Stark!

name: K.K. Slider\'s Bass
description: "I hooked you up with a bootleg, man. Hope you enjoy it."

name: Tarot Wand
description: Wands with the mystical power of tariot cards in an attack form. Able to both read fortunes and slaughter enemies.

name: The Fire Emblem
description: The medallion said to drive sane men to murderous rampage and slaughter. Only the pure of heart can hold it without falling corrupt to its influence.

name: R.O.Brella
description: A robotic umbrella, this fellow is the perfect companion for gaming in the rain! Oh no, wait, he's short-circuiting. Poor guy.

name: Magic Umbrella
description: Typically found in the possession of British nannies, this magic umbrella has the ability to merge real life and cartoon fantasies.

name: Chim Chim Cheree Chaser
description: Covered in soot, a magic endowed weapon that can cover the wielder with an impenetrable veil of coal dust.

name: Primordial Sound
description: An instrument in the loosest term. A pitch black orb that creates music. Although, this music is beyond comprehension to anyone other than the wielder. It makes indescribably beautiful sounds and music to the controller, but creates insanity inducing screeching sounds to their foes. The wielder will be in a reverie while their foes are tormented by the darkest, most horrific wails of the horrorterrors.

name: d1
description: It looks like just another marble or perhaps a novelty cue ball, save for the dot carved into the side. Just what the hell were you expecting to accomplish making this?

name: Scythe of Time
description: This vicious clockwork scythe will cause quite the predicament for any sucky snobbs who get in your way.

name: Hand Buzzer
description: Understanding that this prank was never funny, you've decided to just make it a weapon instead. Become the buzzkiller, of the century!

name: Lunchbox Landmine
description: They took my lunch money. I TOOK THEIR LIVES.

name: Kringle\'s Key
description: A holiday-themed keyblade with a candy cane motif, embedded with frosty winter majykks and mistletoe. You hear bells and little "ho ho ho"s on every successful hit, which may make you want to stop fighting or provoke you into attacking as quickly as possible.

name: Emerald-Clad Claus
description: This felt Santa statue will be the perfect addition to your ever growing collection of tacky holiday knickknack weaponry. He's even got his own little number hat with a 25 on the top! Goddamn self inserts.

name: Mirror Shield
description: Oh great, now if there were only puzzles to solve that involved reflecting copious amounts of light!

name: Iron Boot
description: Sometimes its better to sink rather than swim.

name: Auriel\'s Bow
description: The bow said to be used by Auri-El, the Aldmeri counterpart to Akatosh. That always sounds like gibberish to you, though.

name: Resistor
description: Pretty useful for electronics, if you have a degree in electronical engineering that is. Otherwise, they're just tiny colorful thingies.

name: Magnet
description: Fucking magnets, how do they work? I asked a scientist but he only got me pissed.

name: Teslawesome Coil
description: Only needs 1.21 jiggawatts to function.

name: Newton Force Impactor
description: It's a railgun, because Newton is the baddest motherfucker in outer space.

name: Grave Robber
description: Someone put a tombstone on this shovel... What the hell.

name: Cryptozoological Crypt
description: This tombstone is very mysterious and a dark energy seems to emanate from it.

name: Scientific Sepulcher
description: The dark energy was rubbish, there is no such thing as magic which is fake.

name: Death Metal Guitar
description: This guitar isn't even made out of metal, it's made out of bone. You suppose it's the thought that counts. This thing IS pretty metal.

name: Blowtorch
description: This blowtorch is designed for heating metal. As a weapon it's pretty decent, a lot better than a lighter.

name: Knight Light
description: A shield with a built-in light. Useful for fighting in the dark.

name: 8 of Spades / Double Edged Sword
description: A large, double-edged sword. You could kill a room with this thing!

name: Porky Santa
description: Congrats, you just made it 4 times shittier. Unless you're a fan of the Pork Empire, then it's 100 times more awesome.

name: Net Glasses
description: A hands-free Internet Access solution. ...It can also (barely) run Sburb.

name: Netstaff
description: Now YOU can surf the web, and fight at the same time! (WARNING: Usage in combat voids warranty)

name: WWhite Science Cutlass
description: Little do people know, Ahab was also a MASTER WIZAR--scientist. Magic still isn't real.

name: Pokeball
description: A sweet ball thing that captures cute creatures and makes them fight to the death for you! It doesn't work on underlings or consorts, though, so you might not find any use out of it...

name: Ahab\'s Assault
description: Bring fear to the seas and unleash a reign of terror with your high rate of fire.

name: Toy Helicopter
description: A small toy army helicopter. It's very tiny!

name: Happy Colourful Nova Pen
description: When you're writing with this pen, the ink magically fluctuates between all of the colors! All of them. It even makes your enemies bleed rainbow! Yaay! ...oh wait, that's grist.

name: VIII - Justice
description: An ornate swordcane with a blindfolded woman embossed on the side. Oddly enough, the sword is dull and the cane-sheath razor sharp.

name: Universal Stop Sign
description: This bright red sign needs not strength to bring all to its law. Nevertheless, it is a very capable weapon in the hands of a sign-user.

name: Wailord Hunter
description: A harpoon rifle with the sheer size and power to fell the most massive of Wailords. Frowned upon by the Hoenn government.

name: Adventurer\'s Outfit
description: Wearing these brown, sturdy clothes and this sweet fedora really get you in the mood to topple some sacred urns, desecrate ruins, and defile some tombs.

name: Back to the Future Complete DVD Collection
description: The classic story of boy meets mad scientist with a time-traveling car.

name: Biggoron Brad-Point Buster
description: No, really, how the fuck are you lifting this? It's a drill-wrench the size of a minivan. Is it the gloves? It's the gloves isn't it.

name: Keywrench
description: There's more than one way to open a door.

name: Kawaiibar
description: At least 64% more kawaii, or your money back!

name: Drunken Double Screwdriver
description: Why does this thing reek of orange juice?

name: Hephaestus\'s Tools
description: The tools of the god of blacksmithing!... or at least a decent replica of them.

name: Kitty\'s Revenge
description: It seems that the alchemiter simply stuck the Kitty's Bane inside the telescope. The light refracting through the telescope's lens DOES make a sweet laser beam, though. Pew, Pew!

name: Sci-Fi Laserrator
description: Just like in almost every sci-fi movie and tv show ever made!

name: Gothass Stompers
description: Never before have you seen such footwear that has described your inner soul!

name: Green Tennis Shoes
description: For the casual who only owns one pair of shoes.

name: Red Heels
description: Fashionable but impractical, these kicks are sure to catch the eyes of some on-looker. Especially if you kick them in the face with it.

name: Dark Soles
description: Nice and comfy, perfect for sitting at your couch for hours at a time.

name: Kingdom Soles
description: While extremely uncomfortable, they seem to fit well in that hole up that imp's rear.

name: Weaboots
description: I'm not a weaboot im an otakshoe!

name: Otakshoe
description: These shoes are really kawaii desu ne~

name: Very Merry Holiday Eri
description: He's more of a summer kind of guy, really.

name: Tanline Toutin\' Santa
description: A burly tan santa figurine wearing a disturbing bananna hammock. Nobody should have to be subjected to finding this under the christmas tree.

name: Plasma Pulsin\' Santa
description: This santa's made out of chrome with a round transparent midsection full of colorful goop. Its also hot to the touch, making it both painful to touch AND look at.

name: Feverishly Psychedelic Santa
description: You knew you were missing something from your life: a Santa in a disco jacket and platform shoes. He seems to be pulling a John Travolta look here, and that's not helping things.

name: Reservoir Dogs Poster
description: Clowns to the left of me, jokers to the right: here I am stuck in the middle with you.

name: Box of Crayons
description: Colorful. Edible. Non-toxic. Winning combination, anyone?

name: Gloves of the Magii of the Elderly Female Royalty
description: These soft silken gloves were once worn by a royal family magus, as designated by its golden patterns and heart motif. They hold the power to channel great magic, especially when shot in explosive  firework-esque bursts.

name: Goldfinger
description: There is nothing you can show to me that I haven't already punched in the face. And turned to solid goddamn gold.

name: QB QB Santa
description: This garish piece of sporting goods crap looks like it wants to make a contract with you. Maybe it'll get out of your sight if you do so?

name: Pimp Hat
description: You see my swag. Now you wanna come and give me all this drag?

name: Chromatic Plasma Fedora
description: Ok, you guess this would look stylish enough if your head could sustain third degree plasma burns/you were a robot (apologies to all robots playing this game).

name: Holly Jolly Hustler
description: Santa's got a few ho ho ho's to take care of.

name: Barbiere di San Nicola
description: After a barber shop appointment gone wrong, Santa came out with his beard intact and an ton of goddamn razor blades. Face your foes with this daring combination of classic opera, holiday iconography and sharp blades!

name: Horse Mask
description: You get the strange urge to run around partially naked in the freezing rain. And eat a bunch of oats.

name: Clown Mask
description: Honk honk etc

name: Santa Mask
description: Now you can enjoy the whole Santa facial ensemble, sans the obesity!

name: John Travolta Mask
description: You should be dancing!

name: Shrek Mask
description: Ogres have layers, and all of them smell like onions.

name: ICP Mask
description: Whoop whoop to your hearts content: the only ones who can make fun of you now are giant monsters.

name: SMILE Co. Vegamask
description: The chemical protection wear of only the finest science pirates and child abductees!

name: Fallout: Antarctica
description: Christmas... christmas never changes. From the wizards who brought you The Santa Clause and The Santa Clause 2 comes a brand new roleplaying experience that will make you shiver with delight as you deliver presents to good little mutant boys and girls while putting down radioactive elves.

name: Festive Harlequin
description: You're not sure whats a bigger joke, the ugly jester motley or the stupid amount of grist it took to make this junk.

name: Fortune Flingin\' Santa
description: This sleek plastic santa gives you one of many pre-written holiday themed answers once turned over and examined at its base, in case you are that desperate for someone (inanimate) to talk about your feelings with.

name: Sikk Trixx Nick
description: Its a little street santa on a little skateboard, complete with gold chains and grills under a cheeto-stained beard. He's ready to kickflip right into your enemy's face!

name: Space Ranger Santa
description: A sad, strange little man who has your pity. NOT A FLYING TOY.

name: Rip Roarin\' Rocket Claus
description: A tacky santa figurine outfitted with a miniature rocket pack and dressed in obnoxious Fierri-inspired flame decals. The rocket actually works, meaning this little douche can be launched from afar as the worlds most ugly projectile. Somewhere, you hear a sigh of relief from twelve tired-ass reindeer.

name: MAD NASTY B00ST THUG TRIKKIN Claus
description: Rockets, skateboards and holiday icons have never been so deadly.

name: Slimy Sock Puppet
description: Oh no, someone's covered your poor little sock pal with nasty gunk of a paranatural sort. Oh wait, that was YOU.

name: Well-Dressed Marionette
description: Now your strung-up little buddy is ready for the puppet prom.

name: Bearly Dangerous
description: The classic stuffed teddy just got twice as manipulative. Impress your friends/enemies/inlaws with this cuddly bear puppet!

name: Thong
description: Did someone call the meat packaging plant?

name: Bear on a G String
description: People aren't going to look at your junk dude, bear or no bear.

name: Long Arms of the Court of the Crimson King
description: Gold and crimson pauldrons extend down into hardened gauntlets, embellished with an alternating heart and crown motif. With the power of both the power of the wind and the deepest arcane spells and magics at your disposal, you can write your enemies their premature epitaphs whilst kicking their asses at the SAME TIME.

name: ACME Inc. Jaunty Jokester\'s Gag-Ridden Suit
description: This seemingly no-nonsense company suit is filled to the brim with secret compartments and obnoxious pranks and gizmos, from handbuzzers to whoopee cushions and mousetraps. Win the hearts of clown communions/senior committees world-wide!

name: Der Mann der Tausend Witze
description: Reserved for only the most masterful of the clowning arts, this circus-inspired red and gold leather uniform is nearly packed to the brim with obnoxious mystical gags and pranks, some that have been prophesied in hushed whispers by the legendary ringmasters of olde.

name: All Helps and Advantages of War
description: Carved out of non toxic strains of Tiberium the pieces of this set come in emerald green and neon blue. An excellent set for practicing for the wars of the future...or the past. "You'll come for the weather but stay for the people."

name: Exploding Card Spewer
description: You aren't really sure if it's the cards that explode or the gun itself. Either way it's really cool.

name: Cheater\'s Gloves
description: With these on, you'll always have an ace up your sleeve!

name: Hector\'s Hammer
description: It's like Mjolnir, but from a Swedish metal band instead of Norse mythology.  Also, instead of thunder, it's just really, really heavy.  You could probably bust up some heads pretty good with this.

name: Holy Diver poster
description: Honestly, this looks pretty much the exact opposite of what you'd expect a holy diver to look like.

name: World\'s Pointiest Cleaning Object
description: You'll sweep your eye out!

name: Icebreakalibur
description: The upgraded Excelsius, the blade is half intense heat and half sheer cold. Whether it freezes your foes, or ignites them, you'll carve your way to victory.

name: Singularity\'s Slinger
description: They told you dawg, they told you about the miniature black holes.

name: Hover Boot
description: Because jumping is for losers.

name: Crantius Colto\'s Spear
description: It's so huge! It'll take all night to clean!

name: Jumping Dice
description: The numbers mean nothing! The pain is all from being hit in the face by high velocity springy dice.

name: Chain-Yo
description: A yo-yo with a slim and strong chain. Heavier and more durable.

name: Chemical Burner
description: Baptize your enemies in a deadly mixture of toxins, chemicals, and corrosive acids. And remember: responsible scientists always use protection in the lab.

name: Fruit Gushers - Hellacious Hard Light Head Trauma flavour
description: How do you eat light? Is that even possible? Apparently so. Eating these gusher shaped hard hard light projections will produce a barrier of fruit-flavored hard light around you for one strife, protecting you from some damage.

name: Superheated Candy Cutter
description: This scalpel's blade is made of candy corn that has been heated to plasma. It's still tasty as fuck though, and can inflict your enemies with a nasty case of diabetes.

name: Bouncy Ball
description: A rubber bouncy ball. It's got some neat rainbow patterns on it, and bounces really high.

name: Fancy Rubber Snowglobe
description: A hollow ball made of transparent rubber. It is filled with water and white particles to emulate snow, and there's even a fancy Santa in there for good measure.

name: Razor Ball
description: A B-Ball with razor blades glued to it for extra damage. Wear gloves while handling.

name: Holoball Slam Emitter
description: This is a small handheld hard light projector that creates b-balls out of light and launches them T enemies/baskets for massive damage/slam dunks.

name: The Great Communicator
description: This chainsaw allows you to communicate to underlings your desire to have their grist.

name: Vault Boy\'s Bat of the Wastelands
description: This little ditty was once used by a mascot for a certain post-apocalyptic RPG. One should be wary of stat limitations and medical conditions when wielding this.

name: Slot Machine
description: The flashiest money shredder you won't be able to buy! It just dispenses worthless old money now, or equally worthless (though shiny) tokens.

name: CRT TV
description: This TV looks pretty solid, you could probably bash someone real good with it.

name: Game Console
description: Your old ambiguously generic game console has provided you much entertainment, but now? It's much more useful as a bludgeon.

name: Fear The Reaper
description: This gravestone is why you should fear Death. He shall take you. And you shall be his.

name: Holographic Heavenstone
description: The future of dying in a pretty fashion is now!

name: Bad-Axe Vampire Bass
description: Passed down from generations of Nightosphere creatures, this instrumental axe is an exact copy of that used by Marceline the Vampire Queen.

name: LightStaff
description: Some sort of futuristic light sword, only rendered in a more staff-like manner. The light is harder and doesn't cut quite as well, if at all, making you wonder why the hell you even bothered.

name: Deveganizing Ray
description: Your enemies don't even eat food you moron, let alone vegetables.

name: Rubbery Blue Staff
description: This blue staff is very bendy, to the point where you can use it like a whip! Or a staff. If that's still your thing.

name: Stardust Rifle
description: Whatever this thing shoots, it's sparkly and makes bad guys disintegrate. Yet another fun prop for your growing party-trick portfolio!

name: Newfriend Emblem
description: You must be new here.

name: Mtn Dew Dorito Cupcake
description: why wood you MAKE somethig like this?! you'd would have to toke up on be HIGH on weed     drugs

name: STRONG Ahab\'s Crossmare Glove
description: An arm-mounted, scoped, and compact Ahab's Crosshairs on a leather fingerless glove. The glove has studded electrified gem knuckles for extra punching power.

name: Star Wars: The Anime
description: Unholy shit of the darkmind of the Disney. You cannot think of a single reason to watch this, even ironically.

name: Frying Pan
description: A simple frying pan. Useful for making scrambled eggs or bludgeoning your enemies on the head.

name: Hard-Light Holo-Render
description: A completely blinding pink pearl battle axe. A built-in magical hard-light projector is able to tear through any kind of barrier.

name: Flamethrasher
description: The swiss army knife of the pyromaniac/arsonist.

name: Electrified Humbolt\'s Fountain Pen
description: Shock your friends by ruining their clothes and zapping them into a coma at the same time with this fun for the whole family booby trapped pen!

name: Steam Spinner
description: This drill is the drill that will pierce the heavens!... of your dry-cleaning. Or an underling. Or, you know, anything really. Its literally just a hot drill. Go crazy.

name: Recorder
description: If you went to school, you probably played this in a dingy music classroom to the wheezing tune of twenty other students attempting to make music.

name: Laser Guitar
description: This is so fucking metal. It shoots lasers AND you can really headbang with it.

name: Taser
description: Shocking. Much maligned tool of law enforcement everywhere, the humble taser may not be deadly but it can still be rather... electrifying.

name: Pepper Spray
description: The best way to surprise strangers who come too close.

name: Skull Guitar
description: The Grim Reaper used this very guitar to banish the Soul of Music from the Discworld. Fuck yeah.

name: Scorpionis Infinitate
description: First strike was the tail, then the venom slowly did its work. Now the mighty have fallen, and in their place stands merely a spec.

name: Bloody Jeweled Sceptre
description: Sceptre? I don't even know her!

name: Dual Knifelights
description: Now you can make a totally sweet ass light show while you slash and stab stuff!

name: Major Arcana Rapier
description: Rapier infused with the power of the Major Arcana. Attacks vary in power and effect.

name: Yaldabaoth\'s Symphoniser
description: A thick, intensely bright glowing Conductor's baton that shimmers and radiates heat. With this baton, you can take the primal, senseless noise of the universe and turn it into works of beauty.

name: Plasma Rifle
description: A rifle that fires superheated bolts of plasma capable of, with a solid hit, reducing your target to a puddle of goo. Ah, the joys of futuristic military technology.

name: Innuendo Maximus
description: It's a wooden sword that's shaped like a banana. Don't look too far into this...

name: Super Mario RPG Cart
description: Mario's world has been invaded by an evil gang of weapons, and it's up to him and his pals to stop them from taking over his world! Features a talking marshmallow, a living puppet, and Bowser.

name: Froggy Stick
description: You can have a smashing good time bashing your foes on the head with this cane! As long as you can get past the stench of Maggot Pie, that is.

name: Starman
description: You can feel the power! STAR POWER! But you also feel a bit soulless as well.

name: Peachy Parasol
description: An umbrella suited for only the most dainty of princesses. It smells great and packs a wallop!

name: Axem Spirit
description: The souls of the once-proud Axem Rangers reside in this axe. Wielding it, you strive for chaos and destruction.

name: Bowyer\'s Rage
description: This Bow contains the spirit of Bowyer, the archer who devastated towns long ago in the Mushroom Kingdom. This weapon seems to have an odd affinity towards control pads.

name: Heraspear
description: This mighty spear is adorned with the powerful horn of a blue goliath beetle. Just watch the look on your enemies' faces when you pull out your MEGAHORN. (The spear I mean. What did you think I was talking about?)

name: Fluthlu\'s Bane
description: Mankind's burning desire to blast slavering horrors right in the face with a twelve-gauge, coalesced into one legendary, silver-barreled pain-bringer. Said to have ended the dark reign of Nyc'jaula, caused Az'korra's retreat to the Furthest Ring, and completely ruined Fluthlu's birthday.

name: The Yellow Yard
description:
A slightly shortened meter ruler crackling with leftover spatio-temporal energy. Why would some powerful being precisely measure, then exert such enormous influence over, so short an area of space?
You suppose you will never know.

name: Gold-Fingered Gauntlets of the Crimson King
description: What was once part of the armor of a legendary king of scarlet has been imbued with midan magic: they now turn whatever they touch into solid gold. They also shoot golden bullets when you make a finger gun, which earns you both style points and a sizable fortune in the gold market.

name: Killer Dustbiters of the Crimson King
description: These sharp armored hands, attached to arms wrapped in belts and leather, glow with a mysterious violet hue. According to legend a feline familiar placed a bizarre curse upon these weapons: upon touching a surface, the user can make it violently explode with the push of a thumb. Comes with a pair of nail clippers.

name: DisGO Shoes
description: The go means "go away please", due to the overwhelming presence of your magnificent new rocket platform shoes.

name: Spacial Claws
description: Black claws with white specks within to represents the stars... to bad that it comes with a lot of drama.

name: Ogre-Sized Thong
description: No description needed. Why would you even alchemize this.

name: Diamond-Studded Pimp Cane
description: Razzle dazzle, my nizzle. Razzle dazzle.

name: Festive Holiday Pootang Cane
description: An icy sparkling diamond sits atop a swirling pillar of red and white. Does it taste like a candy cane? Ask your foes after you beat their faces in!

name: Speed Racer Poster
description: Go Speed go! On a side note don't do drugs kids.

name: Mach-Daddy 5 Holiday Pimpin\' Pole
description: What was once an ugly-ass combination of the north pole and the world's most expensive walking stick just got an overhaul with some sweet checkered flag motifs! Also enables the user to constantly whack their friends/enemies over the head at breakneck speeds, complete with cartoon sound effects to make cranial damage even more entertaining!

name: Big Money Macher Tri-Ho Crimp Commander
description: Hit an enemy with the diamond covered slot machine on the top of this eye-numbing walking stick to give it a play, and in turn receive a number of possible rewards such as a spray of useless shiny christmas coins or a rush of oncoming spectral traffic pulled from the depths of drag racing hell!

name: Sub-Zero Santa Bouncer
description: This bouncy ball is frozen solid, never melts, and has a jolly looking Fancy Santa suspended in the center. Somehow it still bounces higher than ever.

name: Enchanted Fancy Slimebouncer
description: This is a bouncy ball of ice-cold blue ecto-slime. You can feel festive magicks pulsing from it, and if you gaze into its core, you can faintly make out a Fancy Santa head winking at you. It is truly touching.

name: Spear of Zappitude
description: An electrical spear using the power of an imaginary thunder rodent.

name: Highblood Hamboner
description: An amalgamation of weapon parts spliced between each other. It could make a good prop for a Carrot-Top style comedy routine.

name: Intellibeam Broodfester Flayer
description: A black, twisted Lightsaber hilt that emits sentient laser whip tentacles. Any sane person would not trust the tentacles.

name: Ch8n-Ball
description: This thing looks like it could do some serious damage. You might want to check the 8 Ball to see if it'll be effective before you go swinging it around, first.

name: Watch with Chain
description: Adding this item to your wardrobe automatically gives you +10 Classiness.

name: Dual Cleavers
description: When one cleaver won't do, get two! Handy for all the chopping you'll have to do to get past these Imps!

name: Tyrian Purple Die
description:
In history class you learned that the emperors of ancient Rome used to dye their robes with a color known as Tyrian Purple.  

You don't think this is the same thing.

name: Crayon Scribble Santa
description: It looks like someone threw this fancy santa into a pit of ravenous kindergardeners. On the bright side, this is the most racially diverse santa's been in YEARS!

name: iDigital
description:
Novelty Digivice with iPhone OS installed.
Touchscreen, clips onto belt, occasionally glows for no discernable reason.

name: Heart-Attack Blades
description: Wielding the intensity of the heart attack blades, you possess unequaled speed on the battlefield, and are able to strike faster than the blink of an eye. However, you are also prone to crashes and hangovers.

name: Sound Sword
description: This sword is so sound, it sounds like a sword and the sounds it sounds sword through all your sworn enemies.

name: Iron Infantry Lance
description: A lance that is as easy to use as Sacred Stones is to beat. Much easier to use on foot than your jousting lance, really.

name: The Scalene Triangle
description: A small, triangle-shaped blade. When you take it out you can practically hear a legion of bloggers disappointedly sighing at you. It can easily be thrown at your enemies, but careful, it's sharp!

name: Acolyte\'s Gloves
description:
Two silk gloves with a single Amethyst each embedded on their backsides.
Yeah, these things are far cooler than magic wands.

name: Flamethrower
description: An actual military-grade flamethrower. You can't help but spout maniacal, unintelligable gibberish as you spray a field of imps with flames.

name: Ignition Keyblade
description: Now you can be a keyblade master with a firey passion!!

name: Colt Single Action Army
description:
"This is the greatest handgun ever made. Six bullets... More than enough to kill anything that moves."

Man, you really wish that was true right now.

name: Collapsible Tonfas
description: Collapsible tonfas that are connected to each other by a long chain. Your arsenal of moves just expanded twofold.

name: Bo Staff
description: A long cylindric piece of wood with some cloth wrapped around the centre for increased grip and protection from splinters.

name: Wolf Claws
description: Long, wolf claws made from bones of the dead, read to use in battle.

name: Preposterously Heavy Sword
description: If you needed a paperweight, this is overdoing it a bit. In fact, it's a wonder this thing didn't fall through the floor by now.

name: Book of Scientology
description: Deceptively small, this heavy book seems to have more text on the inside than physically possible!

name: Kingdom Hearts Playing Cards
description: Sometimes you forget these actually exist. In fact, most people you know don't think they exist until you show them.

name: Friendship Yo-yo
description: You can't actually remember if there were any Yo-yos besides this one in Mother 3. If there were they must not have been very useful.

name: Thundershock Tonfa
description: This Tonfa has the added strength of electricity as powerful as Pikachu's thundershocks.

name: Motored Yo-Yo
description: With charged batteries this yo-yo can hit faster than any other conventional yo-yo.

name: Amethyst Tonfa
description: A pretty purple pair of tonfas. You figure gemstones have to be thicker than wood.

name: Combat Yo-Yo
description: This one rocks, for sure. I wonder if it contains some psychic powers...

name: Kinetic Fist
description: This gauntlet automatically charges your swings with kinetic energy, making them a real hit.

name: Sucker Punched!
description: Packed with all sorts of comical super powers that range into intensely nerdy while still retaining some level of "cool", these gloves are certain to pack enough of a punch to remove any crude highlights from the hair of your potential enemies.

name: The Harvey Denter
description: The Harvey Denter is a good example of what happens when you mix the Joker's antics with a lawyer. It has the ability to divide your foe's face into two-faces. Coin not included.

name: Star Wars Fan
description: Slicing through dumb theories and fanning the flames between them and the Trekkies. Decorated with a fellow wearing a t-shirt with Yoda's face on it.

name: Puppet Ganon Replica
description: A replica of the penultimate boss from the Wind Waker, but in a useable yet deadly size.

name: Penknife
description: Your sharp rhetoric and lethal lampooning will leave any dastardly foe felled!

name: Mami\'s Favorite Shotgun
description: They may all seem the same, but rest assured that this shotgun was her favorite.

name: Umbrella Baretta
description: You notice that the umbrella cover has been replaced with a midnight crew design, which is only all the more merrier. The shape of the handle has been transformed to be adjustable, to be either held up as a regular umbrella or a used as a deadly firearm! The only drawback is that to fire it, you have to open the umbrella. You definitely don't want to open this indoors now, huh?

name: Laser Vision
description: You're not sure these spectacles actually give you any notable skills other than the power to blind.

name: Shrek Anime Shades
description: A pair of green pointy anime shades. Apparently allows you to see into alternate dimensions. Sadly, all these alternate dimensions are scenes from Shrek 2.

name: Gently Weeping Guitar
description: You look at the trouble and see that it's raging, while this guitar gently weeps. As you're sitting here, doing nothing but aging, still this guitar gently weeps.

name: Flame Fury
description: A bow that has a mechanism to light arrows on fire.  Careful now, houses are flammable!

name: Wizardly Inker
description: A magical tool for writing magic into the air. They were banned in Russia.

name: Santa\'s Fancy Pen of Judgement
description: Now YOU make the list. Check it twice? Who gives a fuck, you aren't Santa.

name: Ogrepowered Chainsaw
description: Slice through your enemy's layers.

name: Goggles
description: Glasses, but only not. They just about goggle your mind.

name: Chain Blade
description: Forged in the flames of Grell's passion for Sebastian, this sword has a rotating blade guaranteed to cut everything except High Quality Yorkshire Wool.

name: Volt Fencer
description: This mysterious combination of Electric Type rodent and rapier likes to shock its wielder when displeased.

name: Lavaspoon
description: A glowing spoon with a handle full of orange goo. Hot to the touch. Psychedelic, man.

name: Empress\'s Regality
description: Slender fan, the frame made of gold-plated steel, surface of plated gold and each tip with razor-sharp amethyst blades.

name: Razor Fan
description: Aluminum frame, extending past the paper surface to create wicked sharp razor edges.

name: Staff of the Arsonomancer
description: Named for the mighty Arsonomancer, a famed wizard who looked into the future to see a world in flames, then ended up totally setting the fires himself. Kind of a douche, really.

name: Shitty Novel Draft
description: Someone's painstakingly handwritten fanfiction detailing new characters in their favorite series. The amount of backstory and gratuitous romance scenes are slightly unnerving. It would take quite a bit of editing to make this readable.

name: A Farewell to Arms
description: A tight and sparingly written novel about an armless boy and his struggles with his dream of being a basketball player. You actually didn't read this, but this particular edition has a titanium cover and is really, really heavy.

name: Cod Piece
description: You've done it. You've achieved Cod Tier.

name: Wwhite Wwand of Science
description: Blast your foes awway wwith the powwer of science. Not fuckin' magic, science. You knoww, relativvity and all that shit.

name: The Stroke of Midnight
description: A smaller version of Hephaestus's hammer, but imbued with enchantments from an annoying time gang. It sports a green motif, a gold handle, and a big 8-ball encasing the clockwork. You get a strange feeling from the time magic it contains.

name: Extra-Random Dice
description: Two d20s, somehow augmented using a set of gyroscopes and a random number generator. Ironically, this actually makes them LESS random.

name: Bladrill Tonfas
description: Upgraded with the latest Drilling Action, these Bladrill Tonfas will drill your opponents and shred them at the same time.

name: Reaping Tonfas
description: Equipping this weapon makes you feel like you're holding a scythes blade in your hands. Just be careful where you swing it!

name: Battery Staff
description: It seems to emit an small electrical charge. Surely it could be of use.

name: Lighter Knives
description: A pair of flame-patterned knives that spit out flames from their edges. Just click the handles and instant flames!

name: Rubber Pistol
description: A toy gun, loaded with bouncy bullets which fly everywhere when shot. It's anyone's guess who you'll hit. You might just shoot your eye out after all!

name: Electric Chain
description: A long chain charged with electricity. Hope you brought some rubber gloves!

name: Portal 2
description: A popular game that involves teamwork, science, and homicidal robots. A winning combination in the eyes of many.

name: Segmented Spear
description: This spear comes apart in several places, remaining connected by chains. For some reason, holding it constantly seems to remind you not to waste any food.

name: Inflatable Netbook
description: It does a weird squeaky sound when powering up, but amazingly, it still works. It makes your tears cry, though.

name: Nunchucks
description: The female counterpart to the lesser known monkchucks.

name: Prism Science Cutlass
description: Sometimes you just want to hold this cutlass up to the light and look at the colors.

name: IX - The Hermit
description: A base yet pristine bolt-action rifle that helps the user become the only thing alive within a fifty kilometre radius. When not in use, it can be stored inside your pocket in card form.

name: Toy Robot
description: A cute toy robot

name: Marvel Comic
description: A comic starring Marvel super heroes like The Hulk or Wolverine

name: Perpetual Bouncy Ball
description: When thrown, this hyperactive carbonation-filled rubber ball seems to gain momentum with every bounce. You can already hear Newton rolling in his grave.

name: Heroman
description: One would think this is the story of a MAN being bit by a radioactive HERO or something, but it isn't you guess???

name: Self-Dribbling Basketball
description: Never get caught traveling again! Good luck controlling it on the court though.

name: Big Money Hustla
description: Finding that pimping was, contrary to public belief, TOO easy these days, santa decided to start robbing some banks for sport. While dressed up as a ghetto clown cowboy with an unhealthy complexion. Dual wields mini harlequin-cursed glocks AND spits out laughable rap lyrics when you pull a string on his back.

name: Regigigadrill Gauntlets
description: These drills are the drills that will... move the continents... or something?

name: Fus Row Dah
description: With this oar, you are Dovoarkiin... Dragonboat!

name: Pork Chopper
description: THIS axe, on the other hand, IS made of ham.

name: Meteor Hamaxe
description: A double-purposed tool made from a material that is literally out of this world. (hahaha... this is the 21st century, you're way past tired of that joke)

name: Molten Hamaxe
description: Have you ever wanted to slam your enemies in the face with molten lava from the pits of hell? This weapon is so badass it will melt their faces off.

name: Yoshi Plush
description: An adorable doll of a famous green dinosaur who is friends with a plumber. You hope someday he will be friends with you too.

name: Broshi Plush
description: This Yoshi is orange, and wearing those pointy anime shades. You are captivated by his coolness. Now all he's missing is a sword...

name: Orange Dinosword
description: A thick, red-bladed katana with a stunning dark orange handle. Are you a bad enough dude to wield this sword?

name: Scalemate
description: A cute, colorful little plush dragon! Why are you tying that rope around its ne--oh. Oh.

name: Auto Card Gloves
description: CARDS EVERYWHERE!!! MAKE THEM STOP!!!

name: Dragon Cane
description: A long, red and white cane with a majestic dragon head. It splits apart into two separate blades.

name: Power Cell
description: An unstable and highly experimental power cell for future-tech. Don't drop it!

name: Energiced Santaslime Ball
description: Imagine a giant ball of ice. Now imagine that the ball of ice bounces off every surface. Now imagine that it leaves behind an incredibly cold ghost slime residue when it hits something. NOW imagine that the slime residue also painfully electrocutes things, too. And to top it all off, there's a fancy Santa in it's center, winking at everything. WHAT IF THAT DREAM CAME TRUE.

name: Asteria\'s Starsweeper
description: A broom of myth said to be used to sweep the stars away come dawn. Pretty good at sweeping up dustbunnies, too.

name: Purple Piercer
description: A pretty spear made entirely from amethyst. Although it's not diamond it will still mess some enemies around.

name: Acoustic Claymore
description: More killing proficiency with the same musical possibilities!

name: Digitized Joycalibur
description: By fusing the legendary sword/quill with a tablet stylus, you have created a rapier/stylus that can create things that you draw in mid-air! It looks badass too!

name: Strings of Fate
description: An invaluable tool for any musically-inclined Hero of Time. Playing the right notes on this violin can send you forwards or backwards through time. Of course, if you aren't a Hero of Time, you could always just bash imps over the head with it and see what happens...

name: Anti-Vegan Rickenbacker
description: This Rickenbacker bass looks like it's been crudely repaired with duct tape. Despite this, it still makes an excellent bludgeon, especially against those of the vegan persuasion...

name: Digital Clock
description: A nice, simple square digital clock. Plug it into the wall, set the time, set the alarm, wait..

name: Oar of Cetacea
description: It holds the great pent up power of all the world's oceans.

name: Skeletal Suit
description: A suit made of what seems to be human remains! Surprisingly fashionable.

name: Solaire of Astora Doll
description: Ah, hello! You don't look hollow, far from it!

name: Lethe Oar
description: A blow to the head will be just as effective at erasing your opponents memories as a drink from the Lethe.

name: Green Telescopic Shoes
description: The soles of the shoes now extend by about two feet thanks to telescopic technology, making a pair of mediocre stilts. It's hard to keep your balance when attacking enemies while wearing them.

name: Hack\'em Slash\'em Cleaver
description: Too big to be a knife, too small to be a sword, but still great at hacking and slashing. Not very practical!

name: Tektrodice
description: Diplomatic gambling is not an addiction!

name: Con Air Poster
description: Put the bunny back in the box.

name: Nic Cage Body Pillow
description: With this, you can finally live out your nonexistant fantasies of sleeping with Nicolas Cage!

name: Piecemaker
description: Outmaneuver and crush your opponent with this chequered, impeccably tactical shotgun. It's still checkmate if you blow the king's head off from across the board, right?

name: Sniper Knifle
description: A knife with a sniper scope mounted on it. This is very useless!

name: Blades of Athena
description: Powerful blades blessed by the goddess Athena. Don't go trying to kill any gods with them though. You're not Kratos.

name: High Propulsion Circus Wagon
description: Some notable features: stupid wheels that don't do anything because, a large variety of obnoxious horns, a popcorn maker and an organ grinder. Organ grinding monkey not included (BUT RECCOMENDED FOR FULL EXPERIENCE).

name: Prancing Ponce\'s Jet-Powered Circus Swaggon
description: Just when you thought the carnival couldn't get any seedier, someone rolled out the leopard print. New additions include velvet seating, bling'd out waggon rims, lava-lamp infused interiors and... a passenger seat finally. Organ grinding monkey still not included, though the organ can now play Stayin' Alive all by itself.

name: Sea-Worn Tricorne
description: A fine addition to any pirate's and/or alcoholic's ensemble.

name: Mann Co. Postcard
description: Features one of the many self-told tales of bravado that makes up the life of austrailian legend Saxton Hale.

name: Hat of Undefinable Wallets and Wealth
description: This tricorne is outfitted with a large and rather rancorous squid, curled around a mysterious treasure chest. Any attempts to pry the treasure from its tentacles results in a firm slapping, so you'd best stop that while you're ahead.

name: Cane of Inequitable Cephalopod Wrath
description: Similar to the original pimp cane of olde, save for the grumpy octopus wrapped around its expensive top. He's not going to budge, so you might as well tale advantage of his pissy disposition and stick him within tentacles range of your enemies.

name: Mirthful Mollusk\'s High-Rollin\' Rumpus Rod
description: Balloons and red and gold pinstripe decor garner this gaudy cane, topped with an extraordinarily angry octopus in full clown get-up. Beware his barrage of pies and seltzer!

name: Time-Screwin\' Babe-Doin\' Pole of the Octopierrot
description: Someone has infused this bizarre staffcanething with an impressive amount of time magic: its contains a diamond clock on its top that allows time-stream manipulation to a fault. The angry octopus that guards it, now sporting a fez, can use this to his advantage, sending out a stream of cream pies or other painfully embarassing pranks at lightning speed.

name: Scalemate Saint
description: Reindeers got boring over the years. They don't even breathe fire!

name: The Grim Dealer
description: A Deck of playing cards radiating with the darkness of the outer ring.

name: Voltaic Saber
description: A sword capable of running on high-flowing DC. Shocking, isn't it?

name: Shipwright
description: A sword with the power (and weight) to stay a ship. Should SINK your foe's chances of getting the drop on you.

name: Hard-Intellibeam Void Hacker of Giratina
description: A monstrous and massive war axe made of a metallic platinum flesh with a serrated bat-wing like gold blade. A piercing red eye glares at you from an opening in the golden chassis. Highly intelligent black hard-laser tentacles writhe and lash from the blade, which swing and cleave in every direction. If you aren't careful, you'll get sliced just as the void bends around the unknowable will of the bleeding tendrils.

name: Prohibition Moonshine
description: Back in the 1920's and 30's, the USA banned the use of hard alcohol. Which saw a raised production of this, the hardest alcohol of them all. That you can put in your mouth without dying, at least.

name: Mounted Mountain Dew Code Red Machine Gun
description: A rocket-powered heavy artillery weapon that's best used defensively. It barfs atomic cherry soda bottles from hammerspace at 40 rounds per second. It sports a whirling red warning light.

name: Bonesaw
description: A sharp saw made from bone, for bone.

name: Computop
description: The perfect combination of your trusty old and fast computer with the portability of the laptop

name: Scythe of Souls
description: The blade seems to emit a strange hum as a dark aura surrounds you, and if you listen closely voices can be heard coming from it.

name: Devil\'s Contractor
description: A giant blowtorch pen! With it you can burn your enemies to smithereens! Or give them a silly mustache of ashes?

name: Medkit
description: A backpack full of all kinds of medical equipment to keep you from dying a horrible death to the horde.

name: Really Electric Guitar
description: Unlike a normal electric guitar, this one is quite... electrifying. Shocking, isn't it? Well, you're positive that you should keep it grounded, lest you yourself get... electrocuted.

name: Gold Coin
description: A fancy gold coin, the likes of which populate video games and Ren Faires everywhere. This one is just a novelty coin, but it was an expensive one.

name: Delirious Pucknasty
description: Legends say the prince of ancient Earth Canada tamed the wild ride from its lofty apex and forged it into a hockey stick of immense power. With it, he captained his Toronto Maplelegion to victory and dominated the galaxy in the name of the Canadian Empire.

name: Continuum\'s Calando
description: An elegant but deadly blade that seems to slightly resonate. As you swing it, it produces beautiful sounding notes, turning every strife into a melodious song. It also holds a surprising amount of temporal energy, just waiting to be unleashed on unsuspecting foes.

name: Lemon
description: A really sour fruit. Eating this by itself is probably a bad idea.

name: Mascot Head
description: Some kind of novelty costume head? Looks like something you'd see at a baseball game.

name: Giant Foam Lemongrab Head
description: A big hollow head, resembling the titular earl. UNACCEPTABLE!

name: Spare set of clothes
description: Just some clothes you had hanging up or lying around, no biggie.

name: The Call of Cutethulhu
description: WHAT HAVE YOU DONE? You turned this poor eldritch abomination of chaos and destruction in to some sort of cute, loveable, squishy, monster! It still does the chaos and destruction part when you summon it though.

name: Mentos
description: No future deity worth their salt has foul breath.

name: hellzamonzensy cuin
description: A weird coin with the imprint of Hella Jeff on it.

name: Anaklusmos
description: This is a pen. THIS IS A PEN.

name: The Gospel of the Witches
description: This grimoire recounts the witch goddess Aradia. It's slim, but has the spellcasting power of gods. The name seems to have a nostalgic ring to it...

name: Happy Box
description:
A very boxy TV... Monitor.. Aquarium? Whatever It is, looking at the flashing lights inside makes you feel... 
H a p p y...

name: Coca-Cola Shooter
description: Riddle your enemies with supersonic bullets of cola!

name: Santa-vision Glasses
description: These glasses make everything appear more festive and jolly to the wearer. It even makes imps look like elves!

name: Bespectacled Santa
description: He's wearing glasses now. Was he wearing glasses before? We might never know...

name: Fancy Santachu
description: It's a chubby Pikachu with a santa hat and beard. No greater thing has happened to Pikachu in the history of Pikachu.

name: Christmas Rifle
description: 'Cause nothing says Christmas like a decked-out red and green rifle.

name: Coca-Cola Staff
description: An aluminum staff with carbonated-beverage sealed inside. This can only end well.

name: Ebony Floormaster
description: Breathing these floors, killing all who seek power. The Reaper's bullets, striking down all who open their treasure.

name: Prism Astral Science Cutlass
description: The spacey colors on this blade are so sharp you might cut yourself just looking at it.

name: Harlequin Romance
description: This is eight hundred pages of the Joker indulging his whimsical libido with Batman, Harley Quinn and basically every named character in DC Comics. Even looking at the table of contents makes you want to find a lighter and some gasoline. You could presumably beat your foes to death with it, but reading aloud seems to have the same approximate effect.

name: Harshwhimsy Dust
description:
This dust is slightly perturbing. Looking at it, you think about clowns, and knives. And clowns with knives.

You know what can we not continue with this train of thought.

name: Double Messiah\'s Wicked Benediction
description:
Highblood 2:7: And lo, from the skeletal maw of the angel of double death came the Colossal Joke that inspired all future jokes.

Highblood 2:8: And the great Joke came upon his Prophet's drugged ears, though he could not grasp the true knowing of it: but even in his stupor, he could feel the truth within the Joke. 

Highblood 2:9: And he forged it into two holy clubs: one for the first death, and one for the second. And it was fuckin' wicked, my brother.

name: Wicked Elixir
description: Normal Faygo tastes like poor-quality soda. This tastes like poor-quality soda and makes you want to beat people to death with a unicycle.

name: Sledgegavel
description: Slam some sense into those criminals and sentence them to a heavy beating with this large unwieldy gavel.

name: Medieval Banner
description: A flag that inspires bravery and strength in those around the bearer when raised high into the air.

name: Death\'s Colors
description: The banner that is oft seen in the horseman Death's grasp. The black flag heralds the everlasting embrace of death and rebirth.

name: Carbon-Fiber Counter Cubes
description: A set of virtually indestructible, black dice. Perfect for dishing out serious punishment without receiving so much as a scratch.

name: Double-Ended Dice Flail
description: Heavy, tethered dice blocks with spikes coming out of each side corresponding to the dots. Sure to spice up any game of D&D.

name: Tychnemisis Blade
description: The essence of the mythological beings Tyche and Nemisis, controllers of luck and fate, is imbued in this curved blade.

name: Brick
description: An ordinary brick which, despite common belief, is only very rarely found in backpacks to disgruntle those offering to carry it.

name: Prism Astral Alchemy Cutlass Bazooka
description: This extremely shiny space sword can shoot very colorful rockets of pure... color.

name: 8ench Trial
description: Passing judgement on imps is eight times as fun when whacking them over the head yields a puzzling verdict from your hammer.

name: Borderlands 2
description: Two sets of four dubious heroes meet in order to tear the face off a person named Jack. This seems like familiar story concept somehow.

name: Digimon Figure
description: A figure of a Digital Monster. It probably  would fit in your pocket but that would just be silly

name: The Loaded Die
description: A sleek and stylish shaker six-shooter with carbon-fiber rounds. Hit 'em right between the snake eyes.

name: Pickaxe
description: Unfortunately, you don't see any ore deposits around here.

name: Fatherly Pipe
description: Can I call you puff daddy?

name: Sherlock Holmes Poster
description: Hopefully this alchemization was elementary for you. Pretend that the game is finally afoot with the famous detective slapped onto your wall, even if you've been playing Sburb for several hours now!

name: Case Crackin\' Booty Twhackin\' Chronoscopic Carnival Cane of the Terrible Tentacled Timelord
description: A mystical clock-themed cane wrapped in scarlet and gold houndstooth, enshrouded in an aura of temporal magic and carnival mayhem. Topped with the world's most intelligent and uncooperative octopus, evident by his new monocle and pipe, the equal powers of deduction and nonsense are at your fingertips. Solve the crimes AND do the time with this legendary blend of swagger, mystery and maritime delight.

name: Flame Retardant Gasmask
description: Interesting. It seems you can now protect your face against smoke AND fire!

name: Lawn Flamingo
description: Why does everyone want to steal this thing?

name: Blade of Olympus
description: An olympian blade filled with magical energy, used by kratos to sly the gods

name: Suit of the Excellent Host
description: A fancy white suit, the likes of which worn by only the most elegant and clever. You cannot hope to be as cunning as the original owner of this suit, but you can at least pretend, right?

name: The Sound and the Fury
description: This thick, monolithic tome is bound in plain black stone and fills the air with an almost tangible reverberation. Inscribed on the lead pages is the score for a 48 part opera describing the great diplomatic victory of the Chosen Arbiter against a great demon.

name: Odin\'s Walking Stick
description: In the prime of the Norse god Odin's youth, his great spear would course with lightning and smite his enemies. But in his old age, he threw out his back, and made some modifications so it could help him walk.

name: Dull Bread Cutters
description: Look at these pieces of crap. They look like bad manga ripoffs.

name: Russian Ratscrews
description:
Knives with revolving gun barrels as blades. Or maybe they're guns that look and feel like knives?

Either way, with these holstered at your side, you won't have much to worry about. Comrade.

name: The Lights in the Sky are Santa
description: A mystical slingshot of legend capable of extraordinary accuracy and force. Its projectile is a bouncy ball imbued with the power of ice, spirits, electricity, and the cosmos. Legend says that Saint Nick himself used this weapon to fend off a legion of undead reindeer to save Christmas... twice. Those who wield it are filled with Christmas spirit the likes of which mortals can not even hope to conceive.

name: Salmon slammer
description: A fancy plank with a dead fish mounted on it. You half-expect the fish to come to life and start singing any minute now, but it never happens. It's just a dead fish. How depressing.

name: Stun Capacitor
description: This curiously Y-shaped stunstick constantly pulses with a blue light, a label attached to the handle can be partially made out as "2.1 gigawatts". You have no idea what the hell a gigawatt is.

name: Daxophone
description: You put the violin bow to the backscratcher and discover music. http://www.oddmusic.com/clips/daxophone.mp3

name: Bear of the Cosmos
description: This teddy bear has a spotted fur pattern resembling deep space. Looking into its eyes, you can tell this is the gaze of infinity.

name: Super Citrus Mtl8r
description: A gun that fires Mountain Dew at 400 meters a second? Cool. A gun that fires 20 cans of Mountain Dew per round, at 300 rounds per minute? Fuck yes. As if the horrible gashes from the shredded cans wasn't enough, your enemies get the added bonus of delicious, citrusy Mountain Dew in their wounds.

name: Samson\'s Bane
description: Used by the traitorous Delilah to strip the divine power (and luscious locks) from the virtuous Samson.  It is evident that this ancient razor retains some of that stolen puissance.

name: Elemental Rifle
description: Every bullet it fires has a random elemental property attached to it. These properties are so varied that you suddenly have the urge to catalogue each individual type in some kind of electronic encyclopedia.

name: Red Pop Grenade
description: A red grenade that faintly smells like Red Pop Flavored Faygo.. What would happen if it exploded? I sure don't wanna be there to clean THAT mess up.

name: Grim Reaper\'s Cut-Throat Razor
description: The only thing sharper than Death's scythe. Regular use of this razor will give you a distinguished Death-like appearance. The closest shave physically possible!

name: Huge Bonus Holiday Cronus
description: Oh cod he's giving you "the look." Get out from under the mistletoe!

name: Dio Bisector
description: Johnathan Joestar's sword. It gives off a rippling energy that you can't really control on your own. Maybe if you combine it with something you can harness the energy.

name: Omniscient Mute Wizard Statue
description: A completely chalk-white wizard statue. It knows everything but can never tell you its secrets.

name: Scratchue
description: A little statue of a white man in a suit with a cue ball for a head. He resembles the Bic mascot.

name: Candy Corn Liquor
description: With the highest alchemy you successfully brew a potent alcohol from pure candy corn. Drinking this will skyrocket your Imagination and send you to a magical plane parallel to ours.

name: Lithium Bow
description: For once, the batteries ARE included. It's a freaking miracle.

name: Combustible Lemon
description:
"I'm the man who's going to burn your house down! With the lemons!"
That quote fills your heart with unexplainable glee every time you hear it.

name: Murphy\'s Exploding Arrows
description: Just remember to pull the pin before shooting and aim far away from yourself or anything important.

name: Coloured Pencils
description: What color do you feel like stabbing with today?

name: Rainblower
description: ~Do you believe in magic in a young girl's heart?~ Bring love, joy, and bubbles to everyone and everything around you with this magical bubble blower.

name: Glycerin Gloves
description: So what's bad about blowing things up? The fact that your fists aren't involved. Let's change that, shall we?

name: ELBOW
description: ... This is not a bow.

name: Laser Bow
description: A metallic bow with a laser string. You're still not sure how you're getting all these legitimate laser weapons from just a puny laser pointer.

name: Gold Brick
description: A huge bar of priceless and extremely heavy gold. It's really too bad that in this game, it'd be valued more for its heaviness than price.

name: Iron Man Action Figure
description: A sparkling set of Iron Man armor!  Too bad it's just 5 inches tall and impossible to wear.

name: Repulsor Gauntlets
description: Able to shoot a stream of ion propulsion from the palms, these gauntlets are excellent for steering oneself while flying at supersonic speeds. Or, you know, just blasting the hell out of someone.

name: The Casino Crasher
description: A giant, tethered wrecking ball with some sloppily painted dots on it. Usually used by sore losers who just can't beat the system, so they decide to just BEAT the SYSTEM.

name: Light Bulb
description: Just your average incandescent light bulb.

name: Interdiction
description: The ethereal blades of a leader of Nobodies. They glow with the hatred of a body without a heart.

name: Handcuffs
description: A proper set of police handcuffs with a key. There's no easy escape from these beauties.

name: Metal Meteor
description: A yoyo made from steel and covered in spikes. Caution: May result in spike injuries to the hands, arms and pretty much everything else.

name: Bouncing Bomber
description: This yoyo explodes when it hits something and leaves trails of sparks when you "Walk the Dog". Perfect for parties, weddings and making holes in places where there are none.

name: Backtracking Bomber
description: This yoyo explodes when it collides with something, and rewinds through time as it winds back up its thread for reuse. Be kind, please rewind.

name: Slytherin Robes
description: These swanky ass robes are exactly like the ones in Harry Potter. Relish your identity as a Slytherin!

name: Tales of Phantasia GBA Cartridge
description: I who stand in the full light of the heavens, command thee who open the gates of hell. Come forth divine lightning! Indignation! ...it's cooler in context.

name: Ancestral Creationeer
description: Use the luck of the ancients to take control your own fate. Well... they wouldn't be ancient now if they were TRULY lucky, but you get the point.

name: Explosive-Tagged Kunai
description: A basic ninja tool with a handle covered in an explosive tag, just like in the animes.  It can be set off either by you or triggered by a trap.  Just don't set off the trap yourself if you do.

name: Trusty Knife
description: An old makeshift knife fashioned from one of those mailbox arm flappy things.

name: Faygo - Neurotic Nebula flavour
description: A pink, sparkly and glowing variant of the wicked elixir. You can almost taste the absurd amount of health risks.

name: Remington TI-84 XY
description: This 243 caliber device will give you a quantum edge in battle!

name: Nebtacular Writing Instrument
description: It uses stardust for ink. Anything written with it sparkles like the night sky. Dazzling!

name: Yo Yo Ma\'s Yo-Bow
description: Not yo yo ma ma's yo-yo.

name: Bro-Yo Ma
description: I never used this weapon, but I gave it 1.5 hats to keep it real.

name: Afro Wig
description: A bonafide blonde afro wig straight from the funkiest decade of the 20th century. Outta sight!
