name: Circus Afro
description: DA DA DANANANANA NA CIRCUS DA DA DANANANANA NA AFRO

name: Poppa Rocks
description: These orange poprocks are shaped like miniature suns, spines and all. They're kind of sharp, but they have a real kick to them!

name: Blue Gelatin Man
description: A small blue figure made of malleable gelatin that won't stop quivering. It's probably the worst thing you've ever tasted.

name: Whip of Nosehair
description: Once you get over the grossness of it, this weapon makes you feel exceptionally silly. You also get a sudden urge to use your allies as weapons and/or meat shields. It's ok, they'll understand.

name: Donpachigun
description: The bullets fired by this orange, spined machine gun are so numerous and powerful that they are reminiscent of a certain martial artist's flurry of punches.

name: Don Patch on a Stick
description: It seems that some strange spiked sun-shaped guy has completely swallowed the sun, taking its place on the stick. You don't see a problem with using the weapon anyway.

name: Jiggling Jelly Magnum
description: This shiny, wobbling blue pistol fires long pellets of jello. You swear you can hear the pistol crying between shots...

name: Happy Hyper Sunshine Blaster
description: An automatic weapon that fires devastating rainbows and corrosive sunshine. If this fun-gun doesn't finish off your foes, the diabetes will.

name: Yoyoyo-yo Yo-yoyo
description: This yo-yo to the 7th power consists of a yellow, fluffy ball on the end of a thin black string. It looks harmless enough, but every time it is used in battle, the ball opens up and ALL HELL BREAKS LOOSE.

name: New Year\'s Eve Bomb
description: A powerful bomb that reduces all enemies' HP to 1. Don't rely on it, though. It could be a dud...

name: Jeweled x2 combo Sceptre
description: This scepter can't seem to make up its mind what color it wants to be. Red or purple? Purple or red? They're both colors, so just pick one and stop flashing!

name: d20
description: A valuable tool for many a brave adventurer. Just be sure to keep on the lookout for falling rocks if you get too lucky with it...

name: Tubtuner
description: A glorious trumpet that you can play in water. It even has its own music stand, how dandy!

name: Wynebgwrthucher
description: Wait, so you're saying a guy who's sword sheath made him invincible needed a shield to protect him? Really?

name: Hustler\'s Whisk
description: A rather gaudy, bright purple broom covered in leopard and zebra print. The bristles are long, soft feathers. You kind of regret making this.

name: Aperture Science Handheld Sweeping Device
description: Wonderful for shooing away those pesky birds and making some portals! On the other hand, the entire broom is made of asbestos.

name: Bastard Bomb
description: On explosion, it smashes your enemy's skull with a Louisville Slugger.

name: Midnight Guitar
description: This instrument has seen many a seedy nightclub in its day...

name: Joker on a Stick
description: You could have made this by shoving the joker onto the staff, but okay.

name: Swamp Suit
description: This looks... and smells... exactly like the kind of thing an ogre might wear to a wedding.

name: Skullsplitter
description: A chainsaw made of bones, made for sawing flesh. Trimming limbs has never been easier.

name: Sisterhood of the Time-Travelling Pants DVD
description: A gripping dramatic film about a group of girls who are best friends, separated by time, and the only way they can communicate is through a single pair of time-traveling pants.

name: Gamzee\'s Faygo Cupcakes
description: tHeSe fAyGo cUpCaKeS ArE So aMaZiNg tHaT SoLlUx tHiNkS KaRkAt sTeAlS HaNdS. i rAn oUt oF BlUeBeRrIeS So i UsEd mY PiEs iNsTeAd. EvErYbOdY LoVeS ThEm!

name: Volcanic Spoon of the Titans
description: This massive spoon is more than slightly unwieldy, and its glowing handle occasionally drips lava into the bowl.

name: The Longest Yard
description: Even the largest of beings must occasionally resort to base measurement... no one's been brave enough to tell them their system is different than the rest of the world's, though.

name: Ninja Statue
description: This small figurine has a tendency to disappear whenever you aren't looking... but then, so do most things.

name: Ogredose
description: An old surgical injector covered in swamp mud, full of an awful smelling murky substance. Do you REALLY want to inject yourself with this?

name: Fruit Gushers - Carbonated Crimson Corruption Flavor
description: These are so sugary, they are out of control. Good thing the hallucinations will numb your tastebuds!

name: Nuka-Cola Quantum
description: Two times the calories, two times the carbohydrates, two times the caffeine and most importantly of all two times the taste. Comes in a refreshing pomegranate flavor.

name: Red Potion
description: A thick, red potion. You're not entirely sure what's in it, but drinking it restores some of your health and offers you a wave of relief that you don't have to go deaf listening to that horrid beeping.

name: Elixir of Caffeinated Healing
description: You'll either feel better or worse after drinking this, but at least you won't be tired afterwards!

name: Hershey\'s Chocolate Hugs
description: The perfect snack for those who feel lonely being the only human on the planet. If you can't get a real hug, get a chocolate one!

name: Pan Galactic Gargle Blaster
description: The alcoholic equivalent to a mugging: expensive and bad for the head. Do not attempt to drink unless you have a couple of spare days to spend in a coma.

name: Bolt of Zeus
description: A silver and gold lightning shaped spear, it crackles with unimaginable energy. It's too bad you can't hit the same spot twice with it...

name: Dragon Wing Umbrella
description: An umbrella whose flaps resemble the tissue of a dragon wing. It supposedly contains the soul of a dragon, but whoever designed it certainly doesn't have a soul for fashion.

name: Sleek Rifle
description: A long, black, futuristic looking rifle, sure to increase your badass factor at least twofold. They still do nothing to help your social smoothness, however.

name: A Guide to the Felt
description: A large book backed in a felt fabric. Feels good in your hands, makes an interesting read, and is surprisngly painful to be hit by.

name: Vanadine Vigniti
description: The Vanadine Vigniti is a set of twenty D20s made from a luscious red mineral known as Vanadinite. The odds of the highest score possible are microscopic, but god-like power can be unlocked if the odds are beat.

name: Shin Megami Tensei game collection
description: A rare disk containing all of the Megami Tensei games, such as Nocturne or Persona. It probably costed you an arm and a leg to get it.

name: DRAWRINGS.....
description: A sketchbook full of incredibly pixelated sketches of two bros and their struggling friendship, as seen through extremely compressed eyes. It looks worse every time you look at it. None of the pages actually bend.

name: Archimedes\' Delight
description: With the liberal addition of mirrors, even a relatively weak light source can be focused to devastating effect. You're sure that it has to break some kind of law of reflection physics but who cares?

name: Backtop
description: A computer that fits comfortably on your back. Note: Attempting to use computer while worn on the back may result in sub-optimal performance.

name: Torchblade
description: It's a greatsword with a heavy metal hilt and a blade that emits a stream of flames. Perfect for when you like your imps weld done.

name: Medi-gel
description: A futuristic alternative to the primitive bandage, this miraculous medicine heals most minor injuries in seconds. It's still a bitch to remove though, unless you happen to have ultrasound equipment laying around...

name: CC Industries Chemistry Set
description: A colorful set of beakers and vials filled to the brim with noxious chemicals, emitting a potentially toxic gas. It seems to petrify all it comes across into statues, so unless you're looking for the world's most avant garde front lawn you better put a stopper in this junk.

name: CC\'s Noxious Puffin\' Pipe
description: Be the talk of your local steampunk convention with this industrial pipe that spews toxic petrification gas! Better hold your nose dude.

name: Fur Rug
description: Wait, these actually exist outside of period pieces and pornos?

name: Fur Coat
description: Stay warm and toasty while looking ready to strut the runway at the local soup kitchen with this big poofy coat.

name: Bottle of Fake? Blood
description: Fake arms can't bleed! What kind of awful code is this?!

name: SMILE Co. Flashy Faux- Feathered Coat
description: Tug on their heartstrings and their eye sockets with this outrageously pink feathered coat.

name: Bathrobe
description: For the aspiring hustling royalty, or for anyone just trying to get out of the bathroom.

name: Tube of Vampire Blood
description: A sealed glass tube on a string. It's loaded with some evil looking gunk that moves by itself.

name: Dog House
description: No, there's nobody in it. Smartass.

name: Radio
description: A small, tune-able radio with subpar audio quality. Just when you thought someone killed it..

name: Top Hat
description: Pip pip doodly!

name: Phonograph
description: Well now the audio quality is even WORSE and the music selection has become relatively smaller, but at least it doesn't get more VINTAGE than this!

name: Lucky Plucky Bruford\'s Revenge
description: The sword Johnathan Joestar used to fight Dio. It's exploding with Ripple energy as bright as sunlight! Luck and Pluck! I'm going to stop your filthy ambition!

name: Record/Face Breakin\' Playa
description: Show everyone in town your gold teeth AND your golden oldies with this phonograph/pimp cane hybrid. For added fun, be sure to try and knock THEIR teeth out.

name: The Cat in the Hat
description: What kind of fun lies in this book? Why don't you just take a look?

name: How the Grinch Stole Christmas
description: The story of a menacing Grinch with no heart, and how a town full of Who's first gave it a start. Upon shaking this tome you can hear a bell chime, so start smacking some imps for one hell of a time!

name: Measuring Spear
description: You immediately craft a MEASURING SPEAR through possibly the most advanced form of alchemy employed thusfar. This is obviously the most important thing to do first.

name: Vongola\'s Heirloom
description: Gloves fit for the boss of the mafia. Literally, these are the boss's badass gloves.

name: Chilling Cacophony Cane of Mount Crimpet
description: This ice cold cane will give you the shivers, as nasty green slime pours out it in rivers. The Grinch's technology requires some thinking: it allows for the powers of sticking and stinking. The phonograph can launch out green globs of goo, which in turn bring your enemies straight back to you! On their return trip you can simply bash skulls in, but stick them to others to cause a reaction...

name: Coat of Grinchmas Past
description: This furry green jacket will certainly warm you, even if it may smell like old dog doo.

name: Asgardian Atom-splitting Battlecane
description: Now THIS is a weapon. Forged with the divine powers of the Norse gods and designed by Oppenheimer himself, this cane is supercharged with lightning and unstable radioactive isotopes.

name: Oracular Spectacular record
description: The debut album of MGMT, filled with psychedelic synths and experimental pop.

name: Hatsune Miku Plushie
description: A plush of internet diva Miku Hatsune. It's very cute.. Though, you get a certain song stuck in your head when you look at it.

name: 6-Volt Sweep
description: Send sparks - and your enemies - flying! Just be careful to not shock yourself.

name: Staff of Blue Lightning
description: This staff is Blue. And it shoots blue lightning. Did I mention blue?

name: Clockwork Enforcers
description: A set of powered gauntlets, reconfigured with clockwork generators to pack an extra punch. Literally.

name: Cavitational Cestus
description: Massive explosions coming out of your fists? That has to be some kind of safety hazard. Better hope OSHA doesn't sue...

name: Poketop
description: A laptop with the sinnoh starters on it.

name: Spatial Rippers
description: A pair of blades that look awfully reminiscent of Palkia, the main legendary pokemon of Pokemon Pearl.

name: Blue ecto-bandage
description: A bandage infused with blue ecto-slime, used on injuries to both reduce bleeding and regenerate health.

name: Ahab\'s Hooks
description: Salty hooks for only the oceans most desperate of fishers. The knives are actually not real fishing hooks, though they are hooked on the tip, fishing with them is not highly advised.

name: Dual Spicy Bread Cutters
description: Slightly less like pieces of crap, your glorified butter spreaders now smell like spicy burnt toast. Your enemies will have tears in their eyes as you most likely only succeed in jabbing their eye out, leaving them with a painfully spicy sensation in their retinas.

name: Lost Balance
description: A vaguely key-shaped sword that reminds you of the dream kingdoms. It has bright gold and a dark hazy purple that clash at various sections of it.

name: Big Boss Plushie
description: A treasured item on the battlefield, this soft toy keeps your PSYCHE up through thick and thin. Just remember the basics of CQC, though.

name: Immortality Loafers
description:
These shoes were granted, long ago, to a cool teenage punk by the Cool Teenage Grim Reaper. They enable the wearer to outrun Death itself, and look unbelievably cool and teenage while doing so.

They also have those weird individual toes on them. So the benefit is about 50/50.

name: Drying Pan
description: Luckily, my Frying Pan also doubles as... a DRYING Pan.

name: Jelly Donuts
description: ... I'm pretty sure that these are rice balls.

name: Cthulhu F\'tang
description: The Zoologically Dubious are more likely to favor you if you can provide them with sustenance. Because, hey, everybody eats. Everybody. Eats.

name: The Hat of the Cat
description: A red and white topper that leans with a jaunt, perfect for mischief and archagents to taunt.

name: CC\'s Gaseous Bathrobe
description: This flowing robe is made out of some kind of warm white gas, that whips around your arms and legs to form a curious kind of coat that pools into mist at your feet. Surprisingly non-toxic?

name: Catherine Collector\'s Edition
description: Just when you thought infuriating puzzle games couldn't get any more glorious, they added fake pizza boxes and body pillows.

name: Pure White Lover Bizarre Jelly Special Edition Collector\'s CD
description: You're pretty sure this thing shouldn't fucking exist in the realm of reality, but whatever.

name: Puzzling Proctor of the Golden Playhouse
description: A shining golden television that emanates with an otherworldy power: it seems to air only the fears and concerns of those who watch it. How are you going to watch the Jerry Springer Show on this junk?

name: Dapper Topper of Dumuzid
description: A black top hat with a touch of gold lining, seemingly made out of bones and wool. Be your own Boss with this fancy top hat ripped straight from sumerian legend!

name: Crown Corporation\'s Gaseous Slime Spewin\' Stick
description: From the winds of Mount Crumpet to Punk Hazard's flames comes a scientific marvel that's quite difficult to tame. From the cold rusty music player comes a steady stream of slime, but with the flip of some switches it vaporizes with a chime! Swap between goo bursts and streams of cold gas that turn your enemies into strange statues fast. A chilling concoction of mad science trouble , but you've never had more fun with these nasty bubbles!

name: Max\'s House
description: A snow-covered dog house made of old scrap metal, with some funny looking bone stuck inside. Who let him out?

name: Crumpet Corp. Rocket Spring
description: Similar in appearance to a rocket pack, except constructed out of rusted scrap metal with a swirling sphere of slime in its middle. Does not allow for the same kind of constant flight travel like usual, but instead fires its user in extremely fast arcs of stinky gas propulsion. Fueled by 100% noxious rotten eggs!

name: Grinch Copter
description: This rusty slime-infused backpack no longer carries wings: instead its outfitted with a set of swirling helicopter blades that extend above your head and let you rise high up into the air! Admittedly this is pretty damn useless compared to the rocket packs of old, but you definitely look like the world's smelliest 60's super villain.

name: Link: The Faces of Evil
description: Before there was Sweet Bro and Hella Jeff, there was the Phillips CD-i. This irony is what all true warriors strive for.

name: Distortion Scythe
description: A large, sharp lavender scythe with a pink blade. The scythe is embedded with pearls. It gives off a very mysterious aura, and glows purple. If you stare at it long enough, you think you can see into an alternate dimension...

name: San-kyuu
description: A very futuristic looking rifle. It's black and has a large pink stripe on it, while the grip is teal with black music notes, and has the number 39 written in pink on it. It smells of green onions, and has an unlimited amount of bullets.. Which are also strangely shaped like green onions.

name: Unsuitable for Ursa Minors
description: WARNING: Some small parts may be a choking hazard for children, small bears, and imps.

name: Chain-Katana
description: Probably ridiculously impractical. But it does look cool, and that's what matters.

name: Scyther Claws
description: It is nearly impossible to parry these attacking scythes. Your movements will be like a ninja's.

name: Aperture Science\'s Incinerating Device
description: When the time comes for your "friends" to say their goodbyes, show them the business end of this 4000 Kelvin incinerating knife. Parting is such sweet, burning sorrow.

name: Laser Screwdriver
description: Wielding this weapon, the user may start to hear a steady drum beat in the back of their head. It's nothing, don't worry about it. You're not insane.

name: Portalscratcher
description: When this pulsing white-and-black backscratcher is used to scratch a wall, it spawns a portal upon it. Just don't scratch your back with it...

name: Teddy Pajamas
description: Soft, silken pajamas with cute teddy bears printed all over it! Makes you feel like a kid again. ...A younger kid.

name: Huggably Soft Fluffy Teddy Pajamas
description: You didn't think it was possible, but now these pajamas are even softer and cuter! It's like you're perpetually surrounded by clouds...

name: Pan\'s Pan
description: Maybe you should PAN out a little more...

name: Styx Oar
description: Infused with hate and the very essence of invincibility. Styx and stones may break my bones...

name: Chaotic Control
description: CODEThe weaponized souls of two heroes combine to make this weapon, the ultimate bladed weapon of the current age.

name: Chaos Rampage
description: TOThe weaponized souls of two heroes combine to make this weapon, the harbinger of death and destruction with a legendary power.

name: Green Wand of the Sun
description: This wand draws from the limitless power of the Green Sun to obliterate anything in ones path.

name: The Frylander
description: It looks like your ordinary frying pan, but decapitates like a broadsword. Just like in video games.

name: Pimpin\' Planar Pirate Pitcher
description: This thing shoots pirates. Pirates with infinite mass. They murder you while you are subjected to black-hole gravity. Whoah.

name: Swirly Seussian Compushades
description: These hypnotic sunglasses are so fucking tight: its red and white pattern is sure to delight!

name: Emery Nail File
description: A nail file made from cardboard covered with emery. Are you planning to slowly whittle imps to death?

name: Megurine Luka Plush
description: A plush of synthetic diva Luka Megurine. It's incredibly stylish. Though, you think about Squiddles and fish when you look at it.

name: Magic Ribbons
description: Extending from your clothing or summoned out of the air. They can freely extend or constrict.

name: Fatal Crest
description: A skeletal sword shaped like a spine with a dragon head at the top. It has the power to unlock anything!

name: Ogre Crossing
description: A life simulation game where you acquire a small piece of land on an ogre's swamp. The rent literally costs an arm and a leg.

name: Squashed Turkey Body Pillow
description: The stuffing in this pillow is real turkey stuffing! The perfect place to lay after eating a filling Thanksgiving dinner.

name: pELLAW
description: A pillow so shitty that it might as well be filled with shit. Guess that solves the bathroom issue.

name: Key-shaped Electric Guitar
description: This Electric guitar shaped like a key is despicably dysfunctional, and is an electrocution hazard. Dear god, why.

name: The Contract Cycle
description: A collection of five books, meshing the works of the Inheritance Cycle and Madoka Magica, as collected into one book. Gives off a sinister aura.

name: Puella Magi\'s Guide to Magic
description: This book allows the user to use medium to high level spells. However, something just doesn't seem right about it. Not to be used lightly.

name: Ethyl Coma
description: A single shot of this potent spirit will depart you of all worries, at the cost of taking a permanent nap, and possibly all liver functions as well.

name: Bladed Paper Fan
description: Looks like it was a good idea to put pointy bits on your fan! It's heavier now, but that just means more air is pushed towards you. At least that's what you tell yourself.

name: Troll Horn Headband
description: This headband kind of looks like someone stuck oddly shaped giant candy-corns onto a black headband.

name: Rocketar
description: IT'S A ROCKET GUITAR! As badass as that sounds, it's really not that practical. It takes off every time you strike a chord.

name: Tazpear
description: Nasty combination of electric and long pointy object. Deadly potential.

name: Shade Staff
description: A darkly-colored staff. When your staff is this shady, people may suspect you of having a management problem. But you can manage your imps just fine.

name: Sharp Staff
description: For when you need to stab your enemies from a distance.

name: Pogo Staff
description: A staff with some extra bounce to it. However, due to its unpredictability it would be more accurate to say that the staff wields you, rather than the other way around.

name: The North Pole
description: Almost too fancy to fight with. Almost.

name: Yellow Chitauri
description: A scepter filled with limitless power over time and space. Measures precisely one yard long.

name: Chain Staff
description: So, is it a staff made of chains, or a chain in the shape of a staff? Both, really.

name: Tron ID Disk
description: A replica of an identity disk from Tron. The glowing lines look cool, all right, just don't expect it to bounce back at you if thrown.

name: Fizzy Gushers - Bubble Cola Bomb Flavor
description: These soda-filled gushers have so much sugar and corn syrup packed inside it's a wonder your teeth don't dissolve with the first bite.

name: Spacey Stick
description: A slightly luminescent pool cue that looks very pretty. Despite it's name, it does not have any spacey powers.

name: Sly Six-Pocketer
description: Only the truly sly can wield this item... as well as people who acquire the correct code.

name: Fallout Francisco
description: Pocket that eight and prepare to unleash the fallout on your enemies.

name: Marimba Mallets
description: Mallets used for playing keyboard instruments, such as the marimba, vibraphone, or xylophone. You can play a little ditty on that imp's skull with these.

name: Inheritance Cycle Tabletop Roleplaying Game
description: A tabletop roleplaying game based on The Inheritance Cycle by Christopher Paolini.

name: Dragon Knucklebones
description: The knucklebones of dragons, thrown to tell the future.</br>Ah, it appears that you will fall for a very cheap trick and give a gypsy all of your money...</br>that'll be 1,000,000 boondollars.

name: Gunbrella
description: What appears to be an ordinary umbrella is actually a shotgun in disguise! Opening and closing the umbrella pumps the shotgun. How clever!

name: Throwing-Sword
description: This light, thick-bladed sword is balanced just well enough that it can be thrown to cleave like a throwing axe. Just hope it kills its target, or else getting it back may be difficult.

name: One Use Band-Aid Brand Healing Tome
description: This tome is packaged in a sterilized container, and each adhesive medical page of magic is kept pristine by small sheets of protective plastic that must be removed to read them. After a full reading, the average effect is rejuvenation. The pages all get stuck together though, so you can only use them once.

name: Bardiche
description: The bardiche is shorter than most of the other polearms, but its head is a two-foot axe blade, so it compensates just as well.

name: Midnight Crewtop
description: A slick black spade-shaped laptop. The internal clock is frozen, but it runs most programs smoothly and efficiently.

name: Laser-Mounted Jetpack
description: A large, clunky backpack with laser guns mounted on the back. You feel like an anime robot with this thing.

name: Midnight Chainsaw
description: A black, spade-branded chainsaw that runs more silently than most. Try not to bleed on the suits.

name: Magnetic Melody
description: The music this violin plays can really attract a crowd.

name: eyePhone
description: The next logical step in social technology. Why carry around a phone in your pocket when you can wear it directly on your eyes?

name: Companion Wand
description: A nifty little wand you feel very.. close to? Who cares, it's adorable and it emits a pink beam!

name: Handful of Coins
description: A handful of coins! Instead of acting like an actual person and using it as currency, you decide to throw it at things!

name: Rapier Claws
description: It's like having swords between each of your fingers!

name: Plastic Rapier
description: The plastic claws have imbued the rapier with all the legendary properties of a plastic piece of shit.

name: Portal Claws
description: Able to tear orange and blue rifts in space... and opponents.

name: Dual Chainknives
description: Resembles two miniature chainsaws with convenient handles. It looks unnecessarily dangerous.

name: Citrus Scythe
description: Ever had lemon juice in a wound? Well, with this sour blade, your enemies will be able to recount the experience.

name: +1 Pickaxe of Skeleton Slaying
description: Said to have felled entire legions of spooky scary skeletons.

name: Tarot Contacts
description: These mysterious contacts portray the world in an abstract vision of the immediate future. This knowledge is highly useful in strife.

name: Guilmon Grapher
description: A bright red yardstick with a dragon head at the end. Classy.

name: @E-Esch, Staff of the Garden
description: A not-so-legendary stick, grown from a seed of hate by the gardener of Tear Falls, a small suburban community. It tends to attract crows.

name: King of Wands
description: A bit pretentious, you doubt this is the ACTUAL monarch of a wand society. A high-brow bludgeon nonetheless.

name: Graphics Card
description: For when you need to see an imp's blood splatter IN HD!

name: Musclebeast Themed Playing Cards
description: A genuinely disturbing set of cards more likely to mentally scar your opponents than physically.

name: Blank Cards
description: You would have more to say about these if there was anything on the blank cardstock you're staring at.

name: XIX - The Sun
description: Symbolizes light and happiness. Indicates a bright future. Inflicts a mean paper cut.

name: High-performance Carbon Fiber Spoon
description: Aerodynamic with a light-weight frame. For the optimal spoon experience.

name: Wind Waker
description: Control the winds with this legendary baton!

name: Cybertronic R.O.B.
description: You rebuilt him. You had the technology. You made him Better than he was before. Smarter. Faster. Stronger.</br>You doubt it'd sell on today's market though.

name: M.R.O.B.
description: A Magnetic Robot Operating Buddy. Along with magnetic abilites, it's also made of metal! Too bad the magnetism ruins the internal electronics.

name: Full Metal R.O.B.
description: Well, Now he looks more like a robot than he did with the plastic casing. Also look like he'll hurt more too...

name: iClaws
description: Basic claws with iPhone features on the back of the glove. Now you can play Fruit Ninja on your phone AND in real life at the same time!

name: Black Jack Robot
description: A ROB the Robot in a tuxedo and cigar in his mouth, and two decks of cards. He throws the cards at high speeds, which cut through enemies. Works only half the time.

name: Whimsy Whip
description: Nice loot, loser. Where'd you get it? Weenie Hut Weaponry? Ha.

name: Shrek Doll
description: You had no idea ogres could be this cute. That is to say, marginally cute.

name: Reaper Of Time
description: A blue Scythe with the Triforce emblem carved into the base of the Blade. You have no idea why, but wielding this scythe makes you feel like some sort of fairy boy.

name: Shell Shock
description: With the head of an ax and the body of a shot gun you can really wade through a sea of your enemies with ease! You're definitely not over compensating with this weapon!

name: Decapplication.axe
description:
The age of technology meets the age of war. You're ready to hook up, log in, and let the heads roll.</br>~ath</br>[ number exe]</br>
    Head~ (x) Roll

name: OgreSplitter Chainsaw
description: Splits Ogres with ease, as well as Basilisks, Liches.... etc.

name: Slick\'s Hook
description: Because nothing says "hello" like a friendly stab!

name: Violin Rifle
description: An interesting yet effective means of playing sweet, soothing tunes while blasting the face off of an imp or two. The peg box is removed to expose the barrel of the rifle hidden within the body of the instrument.

name: Psychedelic Pooter
description: A funk-a-delic horn that spurts out hot goop!</br>HONK HONK THBBBPT

name: Yoshi Beanie
description: You will be the most happenin' dino that anyone's ever seen.

name: iGlasses
description: A pair of glasses that also happen to be phones. Different from the iShades in that these can also be used as corrective eyewear!

name: Gastop
description: This mask seems to be something like a stat scanner but it also helps with hands-free chat-spelunking: what more could you ask for?</br>Oh yeah, the ability to vent dangerous gasses. That's still a thing.

name: Mirrored Blade
description: A large blade made of mirrors, so the enemy can see the whites in their own eyes (and reflect on their life decisions) before they die.

name: High-Frequency Blade
description: A blade that vibrates at high frequencies, able to cut through almost anything.

name: Droid Razr
description: Smartphone that's not an iPhone. Now you can be a hipster among hipsters!

name: Sheer Heart Attack CD
description: A CD of Queen's album "Sheer Heart Attack". It's not scratched, although if you begin throwing it at imps it /probably/ will be.

name: Steel Bo Staff
description: Pretty much a long steel bar. Maybe you can whack enemies with it? Maybe?

name: Wooden Bar
description: A staff the size of a steel bar. So basically a sturdy stick. This is so useful. You are so proud that you made this thing.

name: Pyro Scissors
description: These scissors spout flames from the tips. It reminds you of something from a monster truck rally.

name: Mancrusher
description: Oh yes, it does a fine job of crushing men. And just about anything, really.

name: Dragon Cosplay
description: You're a dragon. Or at least you larp as one. This outfit is actually pretty comfortable for adventure. And it makes you look adorably threatening.

name: Ink Well Lacrosse Stick
description: A lacrosse stick designed to lash out incredibly sick burns.

name: Acheron Oar
description: The personal oar of Charon itself- to wield it is to wield Death. Not to be confused with the actual Acherons you might be beating up with this.

name: Charon\'s Wage
description: A mystical golden drachma.

name: Lucky Charms
description: It's no pot of gold, but it's a pot of marshmallows and sugary goodness. It's so delicious, it's like magic!

name: Shamrock Block
description: A pale greenish gold cream. The bottle advertises that it blocks "bad luck". It also lists several side effects from rashes to sudden urges to wear green and hide large pots of gold.

name: VI - The Lovers
description: Two knives that can never part, mostly due to the chains that serve as their bond. When not in use they are stored inside their tarot card.

name: XI - Strength
description: The sight of this powerful machine gun firing is proof of strength. Using it properly is a feat of strength. Did I mention the strength? When not in use, it is stored inside an exceptionally heavy tarot card. Which of course requires significant strength to carry.

name: Atacamite Octet
description: The energy of the Green Sun makes these choice magical dice radiate with limitless power. You have all the power, all of it.

name: Die of Loki
description: A large blue die catalyzing the unimaginable power of the Tesseract, it glows with an iridescent blue aura. Basically it's the Tesseract with dots carved into its faces, making it a giant die and therefore wieldable. Hooray for strife portfolio exploits!

name: Fan Fiction
description: A fan covered in slightly-overlapping lines of amateurish erotic literature featuring copyrighted characters. If you slice up enough tar imps with it perhaps your own signature at the bottom will be rendered mercifully illegible.

name: Forceful Author\'s Manuscript Launcher
description: Frustrated by publisher rejection? Insist that they recognise genius with the written word by propelling it at them in a tightly-rolled cylinder. Your delicate prose will touch even the hardest of hearts, and most other organs too.

name: Locksmith\'s Despair
description: Combining two scourges of locked doors everywhere has produced a solid metal shotgun with a vicious claw on its stock, for cracking open just about any obstinate portal. Forget collecting keys for anything any more, you never liked that puzzle-type shit anyway.

name: Speargun
description: Best-suited to underwater strife really, though you suppose getting skewered like a cocktail sausage would ruin just about anyone's day. The combination of short range and slow reload time isn't exactly ideal, either.

name: Fist of Tebigong
description: One of Master Dashi's ancient artifacts of power. Great at cracking the earth. Not so great at cracking equally mystical tunics.

name: High Frequency Blades
description: You are the androgynous cyborg assassin. It is you.

name: Lucky Sevens
description: You'll always be one of those rolling lucky sevens with these dice! It's statistically also the most common result of rolling two dice but let's ignore that.

name: Reptile Murdering Gloves
description: Not for use on consorts!

name: Mac10
description: Small, but fires (automatically) deadly bullets! Disclaimer: trying to install this on your Apple device will void your warranty.

name: Wand of Gamelon
description: An extraordinarily useless wand. Its only power seems to be a spell of porcine enchainment, which could come in handy all those times you have to tie up a pig. Yes, that's zero times.

name: Backbiter
description: The legendary Titan's scythe, now able to turn into a sword, for all those pesky demigods.

name: Titanicalibur
description: Legendary God's Blade? Check. Sword imbued with ice and fire? Check. Killer of mortals, immortals, and everything between? Check, Check, and Check. Congrats, now go freeze, burn, or otherwise harm everything in your way.

name: Meteo Claws
description: Claws made from the metal of a meteor with immense destructive power.

name: Golden Sun GBA Cartridge
description: A short yet fun RPG.

name: Two Pump Chump
description: Who knew the son of Hell's Monkey had such a tool? Wait, I'm already out of ammo?

name: Felt Puppet
description: I don't know anything else that looks that good in neon green.

name: Puppet Knight
description: A small yet powerful puppet that specializes in fighting with a sword.

name: Puppet Marksman
description: A puppet that specializes in ranged combat.

name: Drive Slammer
description: This hammer has been passed down from generation to generation of Black Rangers. Now, it is your turn. GoGo Sentai Boukenger!

name: Commie\'s Contraption
description: It is time to protect Motherland.

name: Green-flamed Wwhite Baton of Og\'og
description: THEThis is it: the pinnacle of sciensorcerous bullshit. The raw natural and arcane power coursing through this featureless untarnished rod is insurmountable. Raw existence is yours to command. Even bringing two within arm's reach prompts a cataclysmic battle of jealous wills that causes one to shatter uselessly.

name: Amethyst Chain
description: A chain made out of the hard rock amethyst. It is no normal chain and is much sturdier/prettier than a normal chain.

name: The Family Nuclear
description: With this groundbreaking nuclear discovery, you are seriously packing a lot of punch. Enough punch to break up families and nations, in fact.

name: Cat-o-nine-tails
description: Multiple whips with a single handle tipped with scraps of broken chains. Ain't no kitty got time for that!

name: Hylian Arquebus
description: This rifle fires a retractable hookshot. It might take a few tries before you can get it to stop yanking out of your hands, but it is so worth it.

name: Prometheus Puckbuster
description: A hockey stick crafted from a brass-like metal, with glowing blue cubes spinning in chambers that line the shaft, and crowned with a cruel metal blade. This ancient weapon has given the gift of invention to thousands of worlds, and each of them spanning great and mighty empires. It could probably also slapshot entire planets.

name: Plastic Lightsaber Chopsticks
description: A duo of chopsticks shaped like little lightsabers. They're made of plastic and are strictly for eating. Hand-wash only.

name: Beamsticks
description: A small pair of beam-emitting needles. The tips can burn through a wide variety of materials.

name: Quills of Echidna
description: A pair of pure white quills from the Queen of Monsters. They have a sharpness that can dent even the most durable game constructs.

name: Personal Rocket Ship
description: A rocket chair fully revamped for space flight. It includes a windshield, hyperdrive, and fully integrated steering. If drive it recklessly you do, the force with you may be.

name: Magic is Real as Ship
description: A personal spacecraft that runs on the PUREST MAJYYKS formed when you wish hard enough that your friend's limbs will be cured. It's covered in fancy decor.

name: Cronus\'s Huge Bonus Real Magic Ship Space Sleigh
description: A fancy as FUCK magic Santa sleigh themed like the Bard of Hope outfit. It has a space ship cockpit, a HUGE BONUS bag of presents,(all of them are cod pieces and dubstep mixtape CDs) a FTL hyperdrive engine, and an installed car radio. It fires magic hope lasers too.

name: Paddle Axe
description: You'll cut through monsters like they're made of water with this blade. No mermaid's ever going to tip over your boat while you're slicing through the water with this baby.

name: Homemade Wand
description: A homemade Harry Potter or Pottermore wand. Its fakeness attribute is through the roof. It's a little shoddily made, but for someone just starting out, it may just do the trick.

name: Wizard Wand
description: They say the wand chooses the wizard, though you wonder just how that works when you're the one who designed it.

name: Skulltop
description: Now this is a real thinking man's computer. Wearing this, you look like you mean business. Just hope you don't get a seizure from all those flashing lights right in your eyes.

name: PDA
description: A small, handy device for pestering on the go. Wait, who even uses PDAs anymore? You do, apparently.

name: Obsidian Knives
description: Two well balanced knives crafted from razor sharp glistening obsidian. Just don't expect them to last very long. Contrary to what those sandbox games may have you believe, obsidian is actually rather brittle.

name: Toast-chair
description: A chair that dispenses toast at high speeds, in the form of wheels. This sure is a more accessible way to eat toast!

name: PlayStation 1
description: Because new things are overrated.

name: PlayStation Controller
description: Well, you'd definitely feel silly if you didn't have this! Who would own a PlayStation and have no controller? Nobody, that's who!

name: Amulet of Yendor
description: This amulet sparkles with a magical blue light. You're not entirely sure the amulet itself is magical, but it's definitely pretty.

name: Crystal Globe
description: A scale model of the earth. It's fragile, just like the planet's ecosystem!

name: Plasma Ball
description: Look at this thing. It's bright and glowy and even reacts to your touch. That right there is a miracle.

name: Hunter Wrench
description: The combination of a major timesink and a useful tool creates a major waste of everyone's lives. It looks like there's some wings, but they kinda look like plastic. As you move the tip closer to your face, you can nearly feel yourself decaying and perspiring. You also think you might smell cheeto dust.

name: Metal Platform Shoes
description: No one's worn these since the 80's but they won't go out of style when it comes to crushing a few toes.

name: Chain Axe
description: Good at cutting through bone, EXCEPTIONAL at cutting through wood!

name: Metal Folding Chair
description: Your basic folding chair, perfect for relaxing at a school play, or smacking people around. Wrestlemania!!

name: Set of Wooden Darts
description: A basic set of wooden darts for the aspiring aficionado.

name: Pair of Compasses
description: Great for making circles, not quite as great for battling. The sharp end might hurt a bit, though.

name: Laser compass
description: With this you can etch circles in any material. Including your enemies!

name: Optic Circumferifle
description: The fact that the laser emitter circles the main part of the gun makes this a bit hard to aim, but you can\'t fault its power output.

name: Archimedes\' Wrath
description: Nobody disturbs your circles. Nobody.

name: Globe
description: A memento of Earth. Looking at it makes you feel kind of sad.

name: Cruxtruder
description: One of the machines that marked the start of this whole mess. You can't help but check it every now and then to make sure that there isn't a new countdown to some other terrible catastrophe.

name: Cruxite Cannon
description: What better way to make use of the cruxtruder's unlimited supply of cruxite dowels than turning them into ammunition? It has one hell of a knockback though.

name: Skaia Globe
description: A button on the stand allows the model of the Battlefield that can be seen through the clouds to switch between its various forms.

name: Pawn Gun
description: Guaranteed to keep your opponents in check.

name: Schrodinger\'s Chess Set
description: Playing a game of chess is kind of difficult when you can never be entirely sure where any of the pieces are.

name: Touhou CD
description: Cute girls, nice hats, and thousands upon thousands of colourful bullets - does a game really need anything else?

name: Spellcard Deck
description: Magical cards that allows the user to conjure beautiful and complex bullet patterns. Includes twelve sets of five patterns, one for each aspect: pick the one that corresponds to your own for best results.

name: Electro-Orb
description: An elastic sphere that crackles with electricity. Handling it without insulating gloves is not advised.

name: Pocket Supercomputer
description: Calculates as many digits of pi as you could ever desire in a flash, and also allows you to keep contact with the rest of your session when you're not in your house.

name: En Passant Chess Computer
description: The Medium is a big place, and finding someone willing to play you isn't always easy. Includes the latest version of Pesterchum for correspondence games.

name: LAZOR
description: The "lazors" this thing emits travel at about walking speed, and tend to bend off at weird angles after a few meters. You are fairly certain light isn't supposed to work this way.

name: Magic 9-Ball
description: Ask it any question, and this mysterious artifact is guaranteed to answer it completely and utterly wrong.

name: Yin-Yang Orb
description: Other than being incredibly bouncy, this ancestral weapon of the Hakurei possesses a wide variety of mysterious powers, including the ability to transform into a cat and allowing the owner to eat lots of sweets without getting fat.

name: NetROB
description: ...Welp, at least you don't have to deal with the internet directly. Evem though it's a kinda slow at the ONLY THING IT CAN DO

name: Robotic Optical Buddy
description: Robotic glasses that can detect... things off of screens. It also has a Zoom Fuction.

name: Cheap Animatronic Pikachu
description: Now you have your own Pikachu! ...It's still as slow as the original R.O.B. though...

name: Rocket Orbital Buddy
description: This R.O.B. has been upgraded with rocket thrusters on the bottom, like in Brawl. That's all it can do. Besides what it usually does.

name: ROn. the robbb
description: LEts plAY Robatr. CREEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE-cakl CrEEEEEWWEEEEEEEWEEEEEEE-dlack creeweWEEWeEWEEeEEEEEEEEeeE-CLAKe//

name: Phatomon\'s Scythe
description: A ghostly Digimon scythe left over. It's rumoured to be somewhat unlucky if in undeserving hands. Even it's power level is unlucky?

name: Legend of the 3Dualscreens
description: Tells the story of the three Legendary Nintendo 3DS Brothers and their quest for the Holy Cartridge. It's probably better for hitting things than reading, to be honest: Alchemeters were never known to be quality Authors.

name: Chains of Yg\'latha
description: The great Old God Yg'Latha was once held down by these chains. Now the souls of the slightly disgruntled are at your fingertip.//

name: The Galvanizer
description: Who needs some whimpy willow BattleAxe when you have the Galvanizer. This baby is 500,000 Volts of power on a friggin stick. Whos overcompensating now?

name: Row row fight the power
description: Pierce the heavens with your drill!//...Er, cane...

name: Time-Powered 1958 Gibson ES-335
description: The guitar Marty McFly used in "Back to the Future." What a great movie, you wish you could travel back and forth in time...

name: Lagiacrus Plush
description: A plush toy of the Monster Hunter's fabled electric leviathan. He appears ferocious in game but as a plushie you can't help but constantly hug it. Recommended for any hunter to create some shocking weapons based on the game.

name: Tesla Coil
description: A decent size coil that arcs lightning in all directions.

name: Toy Shotgun
description: A brightly colored yet deadly shotgun... when the right target is hit.

name: Toy Knife
description: Looks like a toy.//It is not.

name: Speeding Lead
description: Accelerat your bullets even beyond your wildest dreams.

name: Draconic Dagger
description: You feel that with enough skill in sneaking , you could backstab a dragon with it.

name: Plain Necklace
description: A very plain necklace consisting of a thin chain clasped by a weak hook. May be able to be modified to make a weapon.

name: Glow-in-the-Dark Stars
description: Little pastel-green stars. They glow in the dark, hence the name 'glow-in-the-dark stars.'

name: Plain Shoes
description: Your shoes. They are pretty fucking plain. Very comfy.

name: Star Wars Episode 1 DVD
description: The DVD of the first episode of the Star Wars series. Which was actually the 4th episode, if you go chronologically. And the 4th Episode is actually the 1st. George Lucas was obviously a Time Player.

name: Jar-Bar
description: Wow. Uh.. This...//This is pretty unsettling.//Yousa in beeg doo-doo.

name: Practice Shinai
description: A practice kendo sword made of bamboo shafts. It makes a very satisfying noise when you whack something. It has taken years of calloused hands to wield this effectively.

name: Kendo Armor
description: It took you a year to earn the right to wear this armor. You feel the spirit of bushido coursing through your veins when you put it on. That, or the smell of unwashed fabric after years of arduous, sweaty training is getting to your head. Probably the latter.

name: Safety Goggles
description: Your peepers are gonna be so safe in these. So. Fucking. Safe.

name: Mountain Dew: Premonition
description: A deep purple variation of the Dew. Drinking it gives you a "Blast of Real Psychic Flavors" according to the bottle..

name: Lemongrab Dummy
description: A decent-sized dummy of the Earl of Lemongrab. The effigy of the sour royalty has a malcontent look on his face, an incredibly sturdy body, and a nose long and sharp enough to be a weapon all on it's own.

name: Apple Juice
description: The most holy of the juices!

name: Z-Saber
description: Holding this sword really makes you feel like a hero (though you don't recall ever calling yourself one.)

name: Hoodie
description: A snuggly hoodie. It has pockets for you to put your hands into when they get cold. It also has your symbol on it.

name: Night Owl Suit
description: These new duds make you look super sleek, not to mention super badass. You feel like a smooth swinger... or a smooth assassin.

name: Hooded Suit
description: This strange combination certainly makes a statement, although what that statement is isn't entirely certain. Whatever the case, everyone's going to know that you're making it, potentially while sheltered from rain.

name: Shadow the Hedgehog Poster
description: A poster of Sonic the Hedge- oh, wait, no, my mistake, it's actually Shadow, the Ultimate Life Form. You take a moment to admire his dark and edgy visage, and reflect briefly on his dark and troubled past. Or you don't: the narrative couldn't care less one way or the other.

name: Shadowy Jet Shoes
description: Not to be confused with any other imitation rocket shoes, these are those worn by the supposed ultimate lifeform himself. Hover in place, jet through the skies, with these you can do it all.

name: Yo of Myth
description: An ancient yo-yo used by children of a past era. Somewhat primitive, but not all that different from a modern yo-yo. What, you didn't think it contained the power of the gods, did you?

name: Blue-Ecto-yo
description: You wonder if this could be empowered with the power of some legendary blue ghost, or just got dropped in something nasty.

name: A YO! From the Past
description: A yo-yo manufactured about 30 years ago, but transported straight to the present so that it's good as new. You can feel some sort of of power humming from inside this yo-yo.

name: The TRI-YO
description: Three yo-yo's on a single string... they're really difficult to manage, but you know that if you can pull it off it'd be quite an awesome sight. Just try not to make them touch or hit each other, that'd be awkward.

name: Yo Shepherd!
description: You feel that this yo-yo would bring not only death but also depression to whoever had to see the end of it.

name: X-men Comic
description: A comic from Marvel's X-men franchise.

name: Ruby Quartz Visor
description: A replica of eyewear used by a mutant with vision problems... well, a different kind of vision problem.

name: Optic Blaster
description: A rifle that opens a portal to the punch dimension, firing objectively absurd amounts of punches. To say that this weapon packs a punch would be a gross understatement.

name: Optic Sweeper
description: Can't decide if you want to sweep the dust or punch it? Why not do both!

name: Ruby Quartz Shield
description: A shield made completely out of ruby quartz, the only object that can successfully block punch dimension energy. It's a shame that it's not the most durable substance.

name: Cyclops Was Right
description: Large red sign with a visored man. A favorite of mutant rights activists.

name: Ruby Punch Bomb
description: A grenade made of ruby quartz and filled with highly volatile and concentrated amounts of punch from the punch dimension.

name: Kinetically-Charged Cards
description: A deck of playing cards that glows pink and explodes on impact.

name: Spandex
description: It's almost like you're wearing nothing at all. Nothing at all. Nothing at all.

name: Blue & Gold Spandex
description: The standard uniform of the X-men.

name: Filthy Mutie Puppet
description: A puppet dressed in traditional mutant garb.

name: The Ragin\' Cajun\'
description: A retractable metal bo staff that's been charged with kinetic energy. Cajun accent sold separately.

name: Wyrm Staff
description: A glowing red staff decorated with dragon scales. It's warm to the touch.

name: Plasmic Pillar
description: This thing is so frantic with color that just waving it around causes a miniature aurora borealis. Tumblr couldn't possibly tag this thing with enough seizure warnings.

name: Wands of the Demoness
description: OVERSEERThese magical clockwork wands are one of an ancient alien legend. Their death goddess wielded them and used them to escort the dead to the afterlife.

name: Homura Akemi cosplay
description: Wear the legendary clothes of an emotional fourteen-year-old magical girl.

name: Electric Banjo
description: A slightly heavier metal version of the Banjo, for when you need to rock hard. Country hard.

name: Redneck\'s Revenge
description: For when the crowd turns sour, this banjo will quickly cut down any complaints about the music.

name: Voodoo Bristler
description: A simple wooden broom-staff with an eerie skull at its tip. Hidden potential thrums when it's gripped. A basic weapon for any fledgling magicianwho wants to make a grim mess and then clean it up afterwards.

name: Volt 9
description: A brightly colored shotgun that fires mild, electrically-charged shots. The shotgun shells look kind of like batteries.

name: Lucky Shot
description: You never know if this thing will hit or not...

name: Unbreakable Makita
description: One of the sturdiest drills around. You can't wait to bring some innovation to your renovations.

name: Sonic Saw
description: Ironically, this sonic device actually works better on wood.

name: Ultim8 Yo-Yo
description: A really powerful weapon that it's supposed to give you ALL the luck, even when it doesn't. It may or may not be the more powerful Yo-Yo.

name: Tron CD
description: This CD allows you to play some sort of game involving lines and motorcycles or something...Your computer probably can't handle its insane graphical requirements.

name: Triforce Axe
description: A long, golden axe with a triforce-shaped blade. You can feel the will of the Hyrulean goddesses surging through you when you wield this.

name: Timestabbing Thorn
description: A flashy green knife. When thrown, it travels backwards through time and hits an enemy before the battle even started. Good luck finding it if you miss though!

name: Smilemaker
description: Help others to smile all the time. Also a great reason to start a conversation.

name: Timeside Story
description: Legends say that this knife was created during a short period of the eternal gang war between the Midnight Crew and The Felt. It is full of clockwork and shadow majyyks.

name: Schrodingers Throadslipper
description: When nobody looks for it, it is jammed in everyone.

name: Timekiller
description: The bane of all that is boredom in the universe.

name: The Shreds of Fate
description: 20 strings of face melting fortune or misfortune. Hard to tell which string is which because they all play in the key of D.

name: The Pen of The Histoire
description: This ancient quill pen was said to belong to a well-known Alternian historian called The Histoire. Scientific analysis of her notebooks and journals indicate that her writings were created within days or even hours of the events they recorded. Some legends even say that she might have been able to manipulate future events with her writings.

name: The Night Santa Went Crazy
description: Saint Nick won't accept your bribe of milk and cookies. Everyone is on the naughty list and the coal is set to full-auto.

name: The Epitaph Staff
description: A long staff with a weighted end and an ornamental top, it looks an awful lot like something a mage would use in a video game. Too bad magic isn't real.

name: The Atom Smashers
description: Ever wanted to crack an atom with a punch? Now you can! Warning: Try to avoid standing within a kilometer radius of your atom you are smashing.

name: Technicolour Quantum Cane
description: ...is that rainbow acid running down the cane? I can barely even tell what it looks like and I'm getting dizzy just looking... at it...

name: Tarot Torch
description: Though tarot has long been used to tell fortunes, this new method is 100% accurate! I see fire in your future.

name: i HAVE the card
description: the sock ruse was.... A DISTACTION

name: DISTACTION
description: AGAIN with the socks what IS it even with you and the SOCKS MAN

name: Spectral Cobalt Ore
description: This blue mineral glows eerily. You're not convinced it's non-radioactive.

name: Light-Up Kiddie Spoon
description: The type you get from cereal boxes.

name: Horribly Inefficient Weapon
description: Some murders take seconds... Others take minutes... Some murders take hours... Now, THIS murder... takes YEARS.

name: Tangled DVD
description: Ah, yes - the story of a young girl who never leaves the house. You should have no problem relating to this.

name: Star Shooter
description: A glow-in-the-dark, star-spangled toy shotgun with shooting star shells. Turns out, those sharpish corners actually hurt when lauched at high speeds.

name: Star Chart
description: The stars will guide your path. Or they would, if the Medium's night sky was anything like the one on this chart.

name: The Little Dipper
description: Shaped like the Little Dipper constellation, this is truly the teaspoon of the heavens.

name: The Big Dipper
description: With this massive spoon the gods themselves once supped. This thing is an ursa major pain for you to hold though.

name: Quantum Spoon
description: It's said that this spoon can tear holes in the fabric of spacetime itself. It seems to be just a spoon, though, and you're not really sure who says that.

name: Titan\'s Medicinal Applicator
description: The gods once used this spoon to heal their young ones, and to this day it fills itself with their medicine. Warning: keep away from mortals.

name: High-Performance Santa Claus
description: Everyone thinks Santa Claus only delivers to Earth. Everyone is wrong.

name: Mailbox
description: It's a box, that you put mail in. Or, rather, the mailman puts mail in, and you take mail out of. Unless you're sending something. But let's not overcomplicate this shall we?

name: Mailglobe
description: Draw your letters from the bowels of the earth!

name: Keyspoon
description: With a turn of the key, your mouth falls open and the tea moves in.

name: Chainspoon
description: The most inefficient chainweapon ever.

name: Silver Backscratcher
description: This ridiculously expensive backscratcher would be much more effective if the tines weren't sharpened.

name: Singing Bass
description: Why anyone would ever buy a wall-mounted singing fish is beyond you, unless of course you bought this thing yourself.

name: Star Batinum
description: A steel-blue baseball bat, the bulging muscles of the manga inscribed into its wooden surface. It seems almost unbreakable, like you could stick it between two diamond teeth and it wouldn't budge.

name: Silver Moon Goddess Bow
description: The weapon of the Greek goddess Artemis. This bow makes you feel like a real huntress! ...unless you're a huntER, in which case you should probably hide this bow if anyone's around.

name: Ogredrive Woodwand
description: This green wand is thick and swollen with magical powers. Despite its power, it makes you feel really weird. Not only is it barbed and prickly to the touch, but it also whirrs and vibrates whenever you use it...

name: Sharpened Wand
description: A small metal wand, sharpened to a fine point, prefect for stabbing your closest opponent. Wands and knives are actually kind of similar, now that you think about it.

name: Reflective Knife
description: The surface of this knife is so shiny, you can see a perfect reflection of yourself in it.

name: Shady Puppet
description: A sock puppet made out of shaded glass. Pointy yet fragile.

name: Minty Fresh Belt
description: Finally, a decent place to store your candy canes!

name: Scything Spades
description: A black-bladed scythe perfect for tearing through your kismesis!

name: Fairies Paradise Scythe
description: A special blade infused with fairy majykks. Disclaimer: Scythe not 100% guaranteed to work on bottles.

name: Schrodinger\'s Claws
description: Amazing claws used by a legendary shipper. Myths state that these were formed from The Forge itself, but most people say a strange neko-girl received them from a fish-boy. Either way, they're incredibly powerful.

name: Santa Claws
description: These festive claws stay jolly even after use! The blood of your enemies is almost indistinguishable from the paint colour.

name: Clawshot
description: A claw on a chain that can pull you closer to things. A creative player might be able to weaponize them.

name: Safety Scissors
description: The 100% child friendly weapon!

name: Scissors of Death
description: It's said that the three fates used these to cut a string of life when it is forced to end. At the very least these could be used to cut off a few imps.

name: Rifle Magnet
description: It's a rifle-shaped magnet. It has all the firepower of a regular magnet in a tiny rifle-shaped package! That is, none. I guess you can put it on the fridge?

name: Gauss gun
description: A rifle powered by MAGNETS! You don't have to understand how they work to understand that this is a pretty neat weapon.

name: Replicated Reaper\'s Fryer
description: The Reaper himself used a frying pan? Well, he uses it to prepare deviled eggs of course!

name: Reflective Pan
description: The back side of this pan acts like a mirror, for the cook that cares about his look. Now you can really reflect on yourself during a meal.

name: Racing Yo-Yo
description: Covered in red and white speed stirpes, this yo-yo can go very fast. Very fast indeed.

name: Purple Laser Ring
description: Oh, boy. A purple laser ring. Now you're all set to rave.

name: Puella Magi\'s Guide to Magic Monsters
description: A high level spell book that allows one to summon power beasts to command.

name: Portal Staff
description: A fabulously original Aperture Science Hand held Portal Staff. Perfect for throwing imps all around the place!

name: Aperture Science Hand-Held Portal Device
description: A gun that shoots portals. You're not too sure how it could be used offensively, but it's still ridiculously cool!

name: Plush Scythe
description: A scythe with a black handle and a plushy grip, and it plays japanese music whenever it hits an enemy. You have no idea why this exists.

name: Persona 4
description: A copy of the popular RPG, Persona 4, for the Playstation 2.

name: Oriental Blades of Death
description: An elegant pair of deadly chainsaws with a sleek, tapering design that creates a sharp, dangerous tip at the ends.

name: Nuclear Bomb
description: With great knowledge comes great power...

name: Draconomicon
description: A glance at this book gets your heart pounding, but after a second look you realize this is a dragon encyclopedia, not a spellbook for summoning dragons or other dragon-related magic. Bummer.

name: Nook\'s Slashed Prices
description: This item is the embodiment of one's search to pay off the debt of bells to a certain raccoon.

name: Chain Spear
description: A spear that can detach sections with chain links. Hard to master, easy to fall in love with.

name: Nancho Spear
description: A spear that's lasting forever. It's a little bit hard to hold, since it almost always goes through your hands.

name: Nails
description: A set of nails, you suppose this could be useful for hanging something, assuming you had a hammer.. or a poster.

name: Mythology Crossing disk
description: A game where you and friends get to play as a god from ancient Greece or Rome! Farm, go shopping, lose your family, it's a fun game everyone can enjoy!

name: Froliche Fahrenheiten
description: Nothing captures the feel of Christmas like underlings roasting on an open fire.

name: Rockfist
description: Throw up your rockfist if you're feeling it when I drop this... POW, POW! That's the sound when the rock hits.

name: Running Shoes
description: There's an instruction manual to go with them... "Press and hold B to run super fast!"</br>You have no idea what that means, but they're pretty comfy.

name: Spade of Aces
description: A shovel with a head that is literally shaped like a spade. This digging implement is surely one of a kind.

name: The Renegade
description: A cheap, neon-green recorder. You have no idea why such a mediocre weapon has such a cool-sounding name.

name: hella JEFF shird
description: he warned you about the staris bro. and now he can warn you on your shirt all day........

name: GLOWN IN THE DARK hjshirt
description: This fancy BLAPCK rendition of the HELELA JEfF shirt also now GLOWNS IN THE DARK....... you sure are glad this one glows in the dark, cause they might not all do that?

name: Half-Life: Full Life Consequences
description: A draft of a shitty Half-Life fanfiction that is so terribly riddled with grammar and spelling mistakes that you can't help but get a laugh out of it every time you read.

name: Original Character Sketchbook
description: A sketchbook full of drawings of someone's Sonic the Hedgehog fan-characters. The only way you can tell that these are not just different drawings of existing Sonic characters are the various names labeled underneath, as well as the slightly altered and/or ridiculous coloration. If these were your characters, you'd certainly not want this sketchbook falling into the wrong hands. Someone might steal your ideas!

name: The Double Dipper
description: Two jumbo, deep-cupped spoons for the gluttonous and careless. Don't use them while others are watching or else you might not get invited to any more parties.

name: Bass-Playing Bass
description: Great. Now, not only does he sing, he also plays music with a little guitar. What's worse, he doesn't even take requests.

name: Mystical Staff
description: Oddly enough, the only thing mystical about it is the green glow it emits. Oh well, it'll at least make a good nightlight!

name: Muse\'s Soul
description: SYSTEMAn item any musician would kill for. A small mote of rainbow energy that transforms into a powerful aura when held, that allows the wielder to create any kind of sound possible, from full blown orchestral music to supersonic explosions.

name: Motherboard
description: You can now have whacky zanny adventures with your friends just like Ness! This thing can rend anything in twain... except for those M#$%@#!ing TREES!

name: Magnetic Sword
description: It's all in the name. A magnetic sword. Just be careful not to wave it around anything metal.

name: Magic Tarot Cards
description: You can feel the magic powers within these cards. What powers could be hidden inside them? Magic ones, obviously.

name: Magic Eight Pen
description: This pen is like a regular ball point pen, except possibly more future seeing. Or maybe the ink is just more blue.

name: Magic 8-Wand
description: It is capable of producing 8 different magical attacks, but rarely the one you want to use.

name: Mad Father Game Disc
description: Horror game from creator Sen.

name: Lighter Figurine
description: Still quite useless as a weapon, but now it's atleast 5 times more hilarious.

name: Faygonight Brew
description: This darker and edgier Faygo drink tastes mostly like the same with an added darkish flavour. Oh and there seems to be some knifes in it, too. Yuck.

name: Miraculous Burn
description: A deadly flamethrower that uses a highly flammable concoction of different Faygo flavours. Sweet death, best death.

name: Khajiit Claws
description: Khajiit were a tough race of wandering cat-people, often known to be stealthy and clever. Wearing them gives you a sudden craving for Moon Sugar, though...

name: Action Claws
description: A set of fierce, hook-ended claws. They were used by a certain, special kitty :33

name: A Farewell to Curtains
description: "And this is the price you paid for shredding my favorite pair of jeans."

name: Galilean Talons
description: These diamond-hard claws blaze with a white light and always seem to be moving, whether they're being used to slice your enemies to shreds or if they're just vibrating in your hands. You think it has to do with relativity and stuff but you don't really care because goddamn these claws are soooooooo cooooooool!!!!!!!!

name: Kero-Kero Cola
description: Tadpole Pond's specialty. Somehow, drinking this cola heals yourself and everyone near you. It has a very froggy taste to it.

name: Katana
description: You scaled the Mountains of desu, passed the trials of the Yandere, Drank from the kawaii fountain, and were handed this sword by the one true otaku... Okay, let's face it, you just alchemized this sword.

name: Jones\'s Chainlink Trident
description: This metallic trident was once wielded by a legendary shark pirate. Now it's in your fins. Or hands.

name: iDOLM@STER 2 Disc
description: A game that's popular in Japan. The player takes the role of a producer and manages idol groups. This particular game focuses on unity, to the despair of otaku longing to produce their waifu as a solo unit.

name: Cello
description: A larger, heavier stringed instrument, making it kind of like a giant clubhammer... if you don't care about music, that is.

name: Magically-Enhanced Bat
description: Witches and Major-Leaguers look out! This fancy club lets even mere humans fight off terrors of all kinds.

name: House of Leaves
description: A book about a book about a movie that never even existed, House of Leaves details the adventures of William Navidson as he explores a seemingly endless, constantly changing labyrinth in his home, as well as a young Johnny Truant's rapidly decaying psyche. Reading this book properly, you might be able to invoke some of the effects suffered by the protagonists onto your foes. It would probably drive them mad.

name: Hookshot
description: When I dug a hole, I found a treasure that stretches--BOING! and shrinks--BOING! It's so fun, I'll never give it to anybody!

name: Home Fissiomancy Manual
description: A tome full of means by which the practiced scientist or the practiced wizard can summon and command the fantastic power of the ATOM in combat! It is also hideously radioactive.

name: Healing Slime Donuts
description: The good news, blue goo in these delicious baked treats heals most wounds! The bad news? They taste like ghost sweat.

name: Long Fall Boots
description: With this pair of boots, you can't help but always land on your feet.

name: Headset
description: A plastic headband with dual headbands and a microphone. You can use it for easy communication at your computer.

name: Hand-Held Mr. Fusion
description: This portable version of the Mr. Fusion makes a most excellent club, like the base model this is also powered by garbage. In this case the garbage happens to be your enemies.

name: Handheld Projection Computer
description: All the power of a Laptop and Projector contained in a small flashlight sized package.

name: Hammerhead Pogo Ride
description: It doesn't look like it's as much fun as the original ride, but to be fair it's probably a lot safer.

name: Dutton Photo
description: Is that...Is that Charles Dutton?

name: Evoker
description: In this case, magic is real and is a completely viable option to use in defeating foes. Or you could save it for later in case you need to off yourself.

name: Gunman\'s Cane
description: It's just a normal cane, but it shoots people. Imagine if the elderly man down the street always carried around one of these...

name: Gunheels
description: Firearms and fashion combined into a pair of sleek, barrel-heeled pumps. Daring and deadly.

name: Grid-erang
description: A Boomerang shaped ID disc. The Black gloss finish complements the orange glow around the edges. it now does more than just bounce back.

name: Black Guard Light Staff
description: With this staff no Disc on the grid will reach you. You might have a harder time with bigger things though, like imps.

name: Dancing Flame Chakram
description: You now look extremely bad ass,and have an overwhelming desire to shout "got it memorized" to the heavens while thrusting your weapon skyward.

name: Green Claws of the Sun
description: Claws imbued with the vast amount of energy from the legendary Green Sun. They make you feel like some kind of feline First Guardian.

name: Government Sanctioned God Killers
description: Washington has poured trillions of dollars into finally creating a weapon powerful enough to slay Zeus himself. Let's see the fat bastard try and fuck with us now.

name: Gleipnir Tome
description: A hefty tome of dark magic, named for the chain used to bind the wolf Fenrir in Norse mythology. Sealed shut with a chain as nigh-indestructable as its namesake. In combat, its extreme weight is far more useful than any supposed magic contained within.

name: Pyromaniac\'s Lighter
description: Big things come in small packages and this baby has burnt down homes all over the planet. Never fails to ignite and never needs refilling.

name: XIII - Death
description: This Tarot card depicts death itself. Use its magic to rip the life from your enemies.

name: XXI - The World
description: The most powerful of all tarot cards. It can represent Success and will hopefully lead you to victory. Use it wisely.

name: Stainless Steel Cleaver
description: As seen on TV! It really can split a skull with no dulling!

name: Terrifyingly Nuclear Utensil
description: This spoon has several bio-hazard and nuclear warning stickers on it's handle. It appears to cause those struck to undergo nuclear fission.

name: Returning Throwing Knife
description: It took years of practice to catch this thing with out stabbing yourself.

name: Soccer Ball
description: A standard soccer ball. European players will insist you call it a football.

name: So Spice Lemongrab Dummy
description: A beet red and somehow more furious looking dummy of the Earl. It's perpetually hot enough to just barely not burn your hands, and exudes an aura of incredible spiciness, making your eyes water if you hold it too close to your face.

name: Raider Breakfast Breaker
description: Load this sucker with bread and it'll fire toast with pictures of your favorite Fallout 3 characters on it! Do you have the crust to use it?

name: Rough Stone Claws
description: Finally, you got rid of those shitty plastic toys and made THESE suckers. The jagged edges prove ineffective for most cutting other than flesh.

name: Flashy Crystal Sceptre
description: This jewel encrusted stick is sure to get you all the ladies! Assuming there are any in your session that is.

name: Blue Ghost Cleaver
description: Useful for ghost butchers and ghost butchering hobbyists. Glows with a blue light at all times so also useful for people who are scared of the dark or like to pretend they're under attack by orcs.

name: Angelic Fantasia Ultimate Slammer
description: Covered in sugar, spice, and everything nice. It also hits REALLY HARD.

name: Solid Gold Sketchbook
description: Not so much a book as it is a book-shaped gold statue. It's heavy, and shiny... but ironically, it's basically worthless as a sketchbook.

name: Skeleton Key
description: The spookiest of all possible keys! Used by savvy trespassers to open all manner of locks.

name: Ginormo Sword
description: A legendary and almighty 8 bit universe weapon of old age, a true gem of classical value at your finger tips.

name: Ghoul Gasmask
description: A gasmask themed like the zombies from the famous Fallout series. Now zombies will confuse you for one of them and also it functions as a gasmask. Woop.

name: Gemsaber
description: A small iron saber with the hilt being made out of a cheap amulet. The grip is wrapped in light leather.

name: Fuzzy Dragon Outfit
description: It's like wearing a gigantic scalemate plush. There's no way anyone could possibly resist hugging you now!

name: Fiduspawn Host Plush
description: A red and white ursine plush. You're not entirely sure what its purpose is... some kind of alien game?

name: Fiduspawn Cards
description: If you can ever learn how to play this game, it looks like you can use these cards to summon monsters through a very messy and convoluted process to do your bidding. Such as stomping imps into oblivion. Worth it!

name: Fiduspear
description: You have no idea how a lance made out of plushes could possibly be practical in any way, but it seems to be quite effective indeed.

name: Formal Armor
description: A sort of happy medium between functional armor and a snazzy suit. "N7" is printed on the front for some reason.

name: Fork
description: It's a fork with three prongs. It seems like it might be useful for something. Who knows what you might want to try to eat... or stab.

name: Medieval Flail
description: It is a flail. A spiked ball and chain. Stabby-stabby smashy-smashy.

name: Box of Fireworks
description: A bunch of unused fireworks left over from some celebration. Perhaps now's a good time to celebrate your entry to the medium by shooting some bottle rockets at imps?

name: White Bear Hat
description: The hat is so soft and warm, perfect for keeping long flowing locks of golden hair tucked away and hiding from man-eating rainicorns.

name: Demonsblood Sword
description: This sword comes from the far-off land of Ooo, where it has a history of heroic deeds all to it's own. If a demon appears asking for it's blood back, quickly say "Kee Oth Rama Pancake" before he cuts off your love handles!

name: Faygo Red Ink Lacrosse stick
description: A lacrosse stick so incredibly sugary it rips sick burns at exponential rates.

name: The Soul Ripper
description: This lacrosse stick steals souls from monsters, and tosses it back in their friends faces in the form of a compressed ball.

name: Black King Lacrosse Stick
description: A lacrosse stick that was once said to be wielded by a black king prototyped with the greatest lacrosse player ever.

name: Fingerless Gloves
description: A pair of fingerless gloves. They retain their warmness, but also let you have your finger dexterity as well!

name: Drillblades
description: This thing will cut holes in you in more ways than one.

name: Dragon Spear
description: The point is a hand crafted razor sharp dragon scale. The rod is covered in tiny red scales.

name: Breath of Odahviing
description: The flames of a powerful dragon are in your hands, loyally searing whatever foe stands in its line of fire.

name: Drake Nicholas
