description: A fierce red dragon figurine dressed in rustic holiday garb. Do dragons even celebrate Christmas? Either way, this thing is decked out with claws, fire breath, and a cheerful fur parka, making it incredibly dangerous and incredibly tacky.

name: Whipper-Snapper
description: This yo-yo snaps like the cracks of a geriatric person's joints. Adolescents these days, you swear...

name: High-Voltage Pistol
description: All the lethality of a stunstick with the range and finesse of a pistol. Why try to close the distance with your enemy when you can watch them spasm about from a safe distance?

name: Shoe
description: Just an pair of ordinary shoes, perfect for kicking with.

name: Lock of hair
description: Did this hair just come off of your head, or is it from someone special? Regardless, I doubt that this little clump could save you from a hairy situation... on its own, that is...

name: Faygo - Star-Powered Rainbow Massacre flavour
description: After staring at this bottle, you realize that it's... glowing? Well, you've had weirder drinks.

name: Discord Statue
description: The inflictor of eternal chaos, trapped in stone forever by 6 legendary heroes. This statue is a miniaturized version, so you doubt it could be the real deal... right?

name: Digichu
description: This appears to be a badly morphed Pikachu. Is seems to have been partially fused with a digital rival.

name: Defrisbeelator
description: One part throwing disc, one part hi-voltage tool, : this weapon is capable of delivering quite a SHOCK to enemies on impact.

name: Death\'s Plaything
description: You can almost picture a tiny little Death playing with this doll. It's creepy and slightly cute. Accessories sold separately.

name: Death Note
description: "The human whose name is written in this note shall die." (Boy, do you hope this applies to everything around here that ISN'T human.)

name: Darts of Whimsey
description: A set of darts that polish off foes with a regal HONK.

name: Dark Rainbow
description: This appears to be a rainbow, in the sense that it's pretty much just a regular bow that's been painted with a ROYGBIV colour scheme. The arrows it fires seem to be made of shadow, though. That's pretty cool, you guess.

name: Mascot\'s Skullfucker
description: This gigantic weapon has a massive axehead attached to one side of the ornately designed shaft, while the other is a massive hammer. It glows softly in your hands. Are you ready to fuck some poor imp's head up with this? Hell yes you are.

name: D-Arts Megaman
description: Super Fighting Robot Megaman! Superior articulation allows for recreating a variety of action poses. Also included in set is an extensive array of accessory parts such as shot effect parts, as well as two interchangeable face parts, additional right arm Mega Buster parts and Mega Buster barrel opening part, interchangeable right arm, and interchangeable left/right hand parts.

name: D-Arts Vile
description: Vile! This figure accurately portrays the violent antagonist from the Mega Man X series with not one, but two shoulder mounted cannons. The figure also features knee cannon and shot effect parts, as well as a full array of interchangeable hand parts.

name: D-Arts Zero Type 2
description: Zero from the Mega Man X series is back and better than ever! In his Type 2 form, the Mega Man X Zero D-Arts figure is a great addition to any toy collector and/or fan of the Mega Man franchise.

name: D-Arts Megaman X
description: Megaman X! Figure set includes a full array of buster effect parts, including rotating effect parts. Figure also includes interchangeable face partsx2, as well as interchangeable hand and arm parts. Figure comprised of composite ABS, PVC, and POM materials for enhanced detail, durability, and articulation

name: Sonic 06
description: The awful 2006 reboot of the Sonic the Hedgehog series. This game is only enjoyable by some of the most masochistic gamers due to its wide array of glitches.

name: Iced Aid
description: A refreshing bandage with a mildly peachy scent.

name: Homestuck Crazy Fan
description: This kind of fan would not bring chilling breeze, but frenzy! YOU READ THIS WEBCOMIC THIS INSTANT or he'll annoy the shit outta you.

name: Homestuck The Anime on Blu-Ray
description: The anime adaptation of mangaka Hosei Ando's masterpiece, Homestuck (Kono Burogu Wa Shinkoku De Wa Nai : Sore Wa Joudan).

name: Cross necklace
description: A metal necklace with a cross made of iron. Maybe you could jab someone in the eye with it? Or keep cocaine in it. Not that you've got any cruel intentions or anything.

name: Country Orchestra
description: The strings of this banjo seem to release the sound of a full orchestra. Of banjos.

name: Southern Slaughter
description: It's almost impossible to play the strings on this for all the rotating meat cleaver teeth, but you could swear that when you rev it up you hear the sound of distant banjo playing....

name: Banjalope
description: Looks like someone strapped a car engine to this banjo. And made it spew fire whenever you play.

name: Plain Pins
description: A small handful of generic pins of no particular interest. You're not sure why you weaponised them, but you guess you can throw them real hard.

name: The World Ends With You
description: Judging by the fact that it's past December 21st, 2012, the world probably won't end in your lifetime.

name: HALculator 9000
description: An extremely advanced portable AI. It is completely operational, and all its circuits are functioning perfectly.

name: Gambler\'s Gambit
description: A pair of dice made for only the highest rollers. As a fella once said, go big or go home!

name: Candy Corn Dice
description: If you have high blood sugar, please contact your denizen before using Candy Corn Dice. Side effects may include Diabetes.

name: Drunken Dice
description: You feel slightly euphoric while holding the dice, they seem to be from an unknown time where Drunken fighting is a skillful technique.

name: 6 Rolls Under
description: Two tombstone-esque objects small enough to fit in one hand, with 6 dots on either of their faces. You wonder what the actual use of these are.

name: Chester\'s Cheat
description: These dice are simply marvellous!

name: Skeletal Malice of The Gambler
description: A duo of dice with a bone texture stained red, the edges are sharp as knives. There is faint light emitting where normal dice have their dots from underneath the bone. You think it'd be best to be careful with them while strifing.

name: Mad Moxxi\'s Underdice
description: These were made to decide the penalty or boon of challengers each round in Moxxi's Underdome Riot. Now you can use their power yourself.

name: Wizard Hat
description: With this master conjurer's hat you will look like the most dapper mage in the wizarding world. I mean, if magic existed.

name: V.A.T.S. Mask
description: This highly radioactive mask allows you to see the world as if the enemies had percentages for their limbs, while giving you a healthy glowing tan.

name: Unbreakable Katana of the Frozen North
description: A real cold sword for a real cold dude.

name: Truth as Hard as Steel
description: Usually hidden beneath the velvet lies.

name: The Killjoy
description: Louder than god's revolver and twice as shiny.

name: Sword of Mercy
description: A sword with a fine blade broken to be square in shape, an act of mercy by an angelic being to save innocence.

name: Steel Shield
description: Pretty straight forward, really. It is a shield that is made of steel.

name: Starman Hoodie
description: This poly-tech hoodie has a large picture of a Starman emblazoned across the back, the alien, not to be confused with the small power giving stars from Super Mario Bros.

name: Mother 3 Handbook: A Guide to Nowhere
description: A very thorough guide to the game Mother 3, includes content such as cheese and dairy preferences, navigating the darkness that follows the apocalypse and much, much more.

name: Megaman 3 cartridge
description: Contrary to popular belief, this is the best Megaman game leaps and bounds ahead of a certain installment.

name: sbemail volume 1
description: Dear Strong Bad, how do you type with boxing gloves on?

name: Metroid Prime Disc
description: The first in a trilogy of western made Metroid titles, all the fun of Metroid in first person.

name: Snifit Mask
description: A mask worn by the nozzle-mouthed, bullet-spitting relatives of Shy Guys. You aren't sure if this qualifies as a body part or not.

name: Cosplay Dragon Armor
description: It may not protect very well, but damn does it look cool.

name: Draconic Armor of Ages
description: With a slight green glow and complete awareness of time, the wearer of this armor will ride into battle.

name: Power Armor
description: Power armor not only looks stylish, but also provides massive defensive boosts and minor offensive boosts. Sadly, the armor weights so much that it slows you down by an unreasonable amount.

name: Armor of Sea Bane
description: Purple. Decorative Wings. Actually, as silly as this armor looks, it's pretty effective.

name: Embrace of the Mother of Death
description: With a pitch black shine, you feel the support of the goddess of night as well as the support of her children.

name: Bayonetta Player\'s Guide
description: An official (and out of print) guide for the video game Bayonetta. An essential collector's item for any fan of fanservice overdosed shoot-em-ups.

name: Scarborough Fair
description: A quartet of high calibur pistols perfect for taking down angels and blasting holes through anything in the line of fire. Demon-crafted, witch approved.

name: Rose
description: They say that every rose has its thorn. You beg to disagree, you did a very good job removing those.

name: redBiscus
description: A hands-free computer and headset for texting and/or yelling at your friends on the go. But usually both.

name: Prometheus4 Tempestas Toy
description: A (miniaturized) replica of the giant mecha IDOL piloted by Ami & Mami Futami in iDOLM@STER: Xenoglossia. Does not sing or dance.

name: Player Pin
description: A black pin with a white skull emblem, it appears to buzz with untapped energy. Sadly, right now all it does is let you read minds.

name: Skull Mask
description: You're pretty sure in the dark someone might mistake you for a skeleton in this. Assuming you lost all your skin of course.

name: Holy Hardback
description: A thick tome filled with wise words about how to live your life. Makes a good bludgeon.

name: Eviscerator
description: This chainsword is so big, you're struggling to even hold it. At least it lives up to its name, though.

name: Ogre-amped Banjo
description: A banjo with layers! It's also green.

name: Opticamo Suit
description: The OptiCamo Suit is a form of smart camouflage that can, within moments of coming into contact with almost any surface, replicate both its pattern and texture.

name: Cape
description: A long, plain cape that hangs from your shoulders.

name: Nuclear Fashion
description: No self respecting wanderer of the wasteland would be caught dead without this fancy fabric.

name: Shocking Shank
description: Electrically charged, acid filled knife.

name: Nine-shot
description: Dressed to the nines, and wielding a smoking gun? You are the very definition of a stud.

name: SUTT
description: FOR CLASSEY POPEL ONLY.....

name: Dress
description: A typical dress for women and men.

name: Combat Dress
description: A glamorous outfit for women who fight.

name: Feather Boa
description: A pink fluffy thing, it could almost be a blanket.

name: Fashionable Armor
description: For the fashion oriented, who also want to protect their vital organs.

name: Strange Thread
description: A stray piece of thread, but you don't remember seeing it here before.

name: Miori Shirt
description: A strange shirt that feels like rain on your skin.

name: Charm Robe
description: Robe with a charm embedded in the fabric.

name: Shinra Robe
description: A magnificent robe made of the finest materials.

name: IMIGRANTS.....
description: Divine creators of the conksuck booties.

name: Faygo - Polychromic Atomic Nova Flavour
description: This bottle appears to be shaking... You feel that it would not be wise to open it.

name: Faygo - Leviathan\'s Rampaging Bloodbath flavour
description: The bottle contains a pulsating black liquid. It's rather offputting, but you've had worse. There is a note on the side of the label reading "You're Welcome."

name: Faygo - Chaotic Genocidal Decimation Flavour
description: The contents of this bottle fades from black to a medium red near the bottom. Judging by the name, you feel that drinking this might not be the best idea...

name: Shiny Diamonds
description: These two rings do not have diamonds, but an onyx and sapphire. They shine like the eyes of a cat in the black and blue (respectively). Wearing these makes it feel like something's coming for you, Holy Diver.

name: Rainbow Viper
description: A classy ultra powerful rainbow knife pair. Easily slicing colorful fear into the hearts of any opponent unfortunate enough to stare down these blades.

name: Ninja Clothing
description: The bodywear of choice for aspiring assassins. While not very protective, it lets you move silently and looks badass as hell.

name: Nail Rifle
description: A rifle that fires nails, every handyman's dream.

name: Astartes Power Sword
description: Astartes Power Sword: An ancient and most righteous blade with which to smite the foes of the Emperor. The disruption field that surrounds it allows it to cleave through any armour, even though that makes no sense scientifically.

name: Unbreakable Ninjato
description: This ninja-to is nigh unbreakable making it the perfect offhand weapon for an aspiring ninja... or much more likely, a nerd who collects old weapons.

name: Nail Gun
description: A basic nail gun with the safety removed, good for placing 2 by 4's and holes in imp's heads.

name: Plasma Cannon
description: This rifle shoots blobs of superheated plasma at your enemies, enjoy!

name: Screws
description: Screws, for maximum stability and strength in your home building projects, also the spirals look cool.

name: Time-Screwin\' Babe-Doin\' Universe Bifuricator
description: ONThis staff, outfitted with an axe on the end, has been imbued with insane amounts of time magic. Add to that it's ability to chop a hole through the space-time continuum itself and you've got one hell of a weapon.

name: Shotgun Nail Rifle
description: What's better than a blunt bullets? SHARP BULLETS! And the nail gun fires a glorious 900 nails per minute, making a very nice pincushion out of your foes!

name: Paintbrush
description: This artisans' brush has been recently repurposed- it is now wonderfully suited for painting the walls with your enemies' blood. Assuming they have any, that is.

name: Generator
description: This seems to be a device that makes power for appliances. It's really heavy though. Thank god for Captchalogue!

name: Thundergod Armor
description: This cape looks like your mom's drapes...

name: Lily
description: A beautiful flower, symbolizing innocence and pureness. According to legend, lilies grow where the pure of heart are buried.

name: Lacrosse helmet
description: A pretty standard Cascade lacrosse helmet. Able to absorb a pretty decient amount of shock without paralyzingly the wearer.

name: Lacrosse chest pads
description: Generic lacrosse pads designed to keep the wearer safe from blows to the shoulders, chest, and sternum.

name: Lacrosse gloves
description: Standard pair of padded gloves regulation for lacrosse players.

name: The Black Yard
description: A dimensional measuring instramental fit only for a king... an evil king.

name: Izanagi\'s Headdress
description: The God of Life's bandanna and face mask. Wearing it makes you feel like a master of Lightning.

name: iSafety Goggles
description: Safety goggles with access to a an iphone via a series of blinks and mindwaves or some other sci fi logic.

name: Grimoire of Alice
description: A grimoire that shines with a brilliant multi-colored light and is said to contain the ultimate magic. You gain a sudden urge to play with dolls whilst holding it.

name: Sailor Moon Complete Collection
description: The complete DVD set of your favorite magical girl anime. In the name of the moon, I'll punish you.

name: Godzilla Sunglasses
description: Your face is a kaiju, sugoi.

name: Frequency Blade
description: This crazy bugger of a sword will split even Metal Gears in half. Use only if you're fabulous enough.

name: Fancy Seiga
description: For those who do not entirely understand Christmas. You aren't entirely sure that you are comfortable with storing it alongside your valuables. Slightly magical.

name: Gravity Beat
description: Basically a magical mortar in the shape of a broom. You're going to kill yourself if you fool around with stuff like this.

name: Explosives Vest
description: Now you won't blow up as much!

name: Dual Saw Knives
description: These tiny knife sized chainsaws will rip holes in even the most sturdy tiny trees!

name: Dragon Ball DVDs
description: A collection of DVDs of the entire Dragon Ball Z series, along with Dragon Ball, and Dragon Ball GT. You feel like you can learn a thing or two about yelling from the main characters of this show.

name: Nazo Unleashed DVD
description: A short fan-made flash series, burned into a disc. Interestingly enough, this version seems to have some visual upgrades. Now you can watch a standard DBZ plot with recycled Sonic voice clips in glorious HD!

name: Shadic\'s Jet Shoes
description: Once worn by a mighty warrior with the strength of two, these shoes retain the abilities of flight, while being twice as durable, not to mention twice as stylish!

name: Aperture Science Personality Core
description: Standard Personality Core that is well-suited for both calculations and managing slaughterhouses. It has no personality loaded into it, though.

name: Orange Portal Gun
description: This gun is capable of creating orange portals. Not really useful, is it.

name: Blue Portal Gun
description: This version of Portal Gun is capable of making blue portals. Because its portal net is distinct from that of an Orange Portal Gun, it's not really useful, either.

name: Half-Life 2 disc
description: Some people like games. Other people like killing people. This disc lets you combine both those pursuits!

name: Gravity Gun
description: This amazing technology of Black Mesa allows you to hurtle heavy objects into your enemies, or vice versa.

name: Astartes Power Fist
description: A holy weapon of oh who are you kidding. It's a big armoured gauntlet that smashes things.

name: Old Papercraft Hammer
description: A very large wooden hammer. You have no emotional attachment to it all and will most likely throw it in the garbage as soon as you find a slightly better hammer. Sorry, thems the breaks.

name: Classic Magician\'s Wand
description: Top of the line wand, a helpful addition to any conjuror or spell-caster's inventory. You wonder if you will finally be able to pull a rabbit out of that old hat you used to alchemize this...

name: Battery Powered Wand
description: It lights up! Its distracting at the very least.

name: Clarinot
description: It's an unusually long clarinet, and if you detach the head, whoops, it's actually a sword. Guess you won't be playing that any time soon.

name: Barbell
description: It's time to get RIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIPPPPPED!

name: Canadian Glory
description: Mmmm, what's that America? Oh, that's right. It's the smell of FREEDOM.

name: Aegis
description: The shield of Zeus, king of the gods. If you believe the Greeks that is.

name: Caledwyneb
description: What happens when you mix a scabbard that makes you invincible with a legendary shield that makes no logical sense? Another completely pointless shield, it seems. Albeit a really strong one.

name: Double Devilfuckers
description: Two burnished black peacemakers containing the full powers of darkness yet designed for slaying demons. Fight fire with fire, that sort of thing. You try not to think about how little sense that makes since you're probably not going to be going up against anything particularly demonic.

name: Suit of Armor
description: You... can't actually move in this stuff.

name: Armet
description: Great! A medieval helmet that protects and deflects! Pity you can't see anything.

name: Heaume
description: You are now more top-heavy than anything that expects to stand without significant difficulty. Also you're effectively blinded. Ain't nothin' getting through this, though.

name: Solid Gold Tux
description: This is quite possibly the tackiest thing that has ever been conceived.

name: Solid Gold Jammies
description: What is the point of these? You're going to sleep in them! Nobody is even going to see how horribly chintzy they are.

name: Jeweled Golden Codpiece
description: You alchemise the codpiece with a brick of gold because you're just so funny. Little did you expect to be greeted by the most beautiful thing you have ever laid eyes on. You weep slightly in reverence and consider a career as a travelling minstrel.

name: Golden Shades
description: You can't see anything but everyone else can see how incredibly gaudy you are.

name: Brosaw
description: THE ULTIMATE NEW CHAINSAW FROM IGN AND EA GAMES! THE BROSAW! GET BONUS EXP WHEN YOU USE THIS EXCLUSIVE PREORDER WEAPON FROM GAMESPOT, AND PWN NOOBS WHILE QUENCHING YOUR OWN THIRST!

name: DMC Collection
description: A collection of 4 rather challenging games. The main character uses an assortment of weapons such as swords, rifles, and electric guitars to defeat generic monsters. This seems fairly relevant to your situation.

name: Space Marine Figurine
description: It's a small figurine of some angry space guy from a board game. It's not really useful on it's own, though.

name: Hospice CD
description: An album by The Antlers. All things considered, this is actually pretty cheesy.

name: Bladed Cards
description: A deck of weighted playing cards lined with sharpened steel. Attempts to shuffle inevitably lead to self harm.

name: Medusa Slayer
description: A polished bronze shield that doubles as a mirror. For both gorgon slaying and hygienic purposes

name: Violin on R Sharp
description: The neck of the violin thins down into a single sharp point. You think to yourself that this is a pretty terrible violin, but at least the strings are still there, going through a hole in the rapier-neck.

name: Varia Suit
description: Armor similar, if not identical, to that of the legendary hero Samus Aran.

name: Hyper Armor
description: This armor greatly increases mobility, defense among other things, you sure are glad this uses the hyper chip instead of any of the other chips.

name: Tsundere B-Ball
description: Though it may appear rather angry and dangerous, this ball is actually quite safe and good for your child.

name: Temporal Timekeeper
description: This baton is little more than a white cloud of mist that gathers in a baton-like shape, but when it is waved, it leaves behind white traces that float in the air, each humming a note at a perfect pitch. With this baton, the wielder can command the very fabric of the multiverse itself to create beautiful music unlike that will ever be heard again.

name: Pyrokinesis Pin
description: A pin that allows you to create small fires when you focus your mind. Only small ones though.

name: Long Live The Ice Pin
description: When you hold this, you feel a chill on your breath like a cold winter morning. And when you focus, you can freeze enemies with this breath. Until temperature kicks in and they thaw.

name: Holy Light Pin
description: You're not sure how strong these lasers are, but you're definitely able to fire lasers from your hand now. Pew pew!

name: Eldritch Skull Mask
description: There seems to be some sort of black...tentacled mass coming out of this mask. You're not sure about putting this on your face any more.

name: Medusa Wig
description: Petrify your friends and foes with this lovely collection of snakes growing out of your head! Note: May not actually turn anything to stone.

name: Parrying Dagger
description: A favorite of the Knights of Carim and Darkwraiths everywhere.

name: Generator Backpack
description: Just like how it's described, it's a backpack not meant for carrying objects, but providing power instead. Not sure who even uses backpacks anymore with the implementation of the Captchalogue.

name: Faygo Spear
description: This wonderful weapon is a manufacturing nightmare. But once you have it, its a weapon of a respectable Harlequin.

name: Fate/Stay Night Disc
description: Baby's first visual novel. Filled with dragons, not-underage sex, and sword boners.

name: Falcon Gauntlets
description: A pair of mechanized gauntlets with hot rod flames on them. They give you the ability to punch things incredibly hard via built-in thrusters, though there's a bit of a warm-up period leaving you vulnerable. They can also be used for flight, but it involves pointing your arms in the direction you want to go and hoping they don't rip your arms out of their sockets.

name: Iron Man Armor
description: Fully functional superhero armor! Unfortunately, you have no idea how it works. Eh, you'll figure it out.

name: Dual Palette Knives
description: Dual painting palette knives. Good for canvas painting and throat cutting!

name: Pendragon Wide Guard
description: A dragon tissue shield that is both durable and light. It also folds out to keep the rain off your head. Handy!

name: Brain Gusher
description: It's a little bit squishy, will it even damage on impact? Of course it will, you've seen the commercials. The batter-witch packed those things with explosive, juicy power.

name: Magnetic Lasher
description: A strong electric magnetic whip that buzzes with energy. When lashed, it sticks to whatever it comes in to contact with and unleashes a flurry of volts. Shocking, isn't it!

name: Panty Sniffer
description: Enjoy breathing through a pair of- wait, why the hell would you want that!?

name: Whiplash
description: Whiplash's Whips that Lash! Slice through cars with ease!

name: Magnet Apostrophe
description: Remember to mark your letter omissions, your possessive cases, and plurals! Oh and REMEMBER TO DIE.

name: Bow of Parabolas
description: You can shoot at any angle and it will go to where you want. Wowza.

name: Bottle of Water
description: In the event of dehydration, open and drink.

name: Portable Hydroelectric Generator
description: Put it under one of those infinite-rain clouds and you're good to go.

name: Hydra-o\'-Nine-Tails
description: Like a cat-o-nine-tails, but with nine angry chain snakes instead.

name: Sword of Decay
description: It's kind of a shitty weapon, but do you look damn cool swinging this thing around or what?

name: Hydra-electric Chains
description: A nine-in-one collection of infinitely-long, electrically charged chain serpents. Have fun!

name: Bobobo-Bo Bo-Bobo DVD
description: A DVD box set archiving the hilariously absurd anime known as Bobobo-Bo Bo-Bobo, following the adventures of a man who fights using his nose hairs and his various teammates against the evil Chrome Dome Empire.

name: Blue Bomber Helmet
description: The stylish blue cranium protector of everybody's favorite Jump-and-Shoot hero. Side effect of looking too awesome.

name: Bladed Staff
description: A staff with knife blades on either end. You'd better not try to twirl it around too much...

name: Blackstar Deck
description: A glowing deck of blackjack cards. When thrown, a card splits into several spinning stars. Kinda makes you feel like some kind of gambling ninja! (Or maybe ninja gambler? Yeah, that definitely sounds cooler.)

name: Chaos Zweihander
description: This sword contains entirely too much chaos for a one-handed sword. Good thing it's not!

name: BFG9000
description: This rather bulky weapon is capable of clearing a room instantly.

name: BFG65535
description: This weapon is as powerful as you can THEget. If it was any stronger, it would cause a stack overflow.

name: Gun of Cosmocide
description: It is said that this weapon annihilates a universe every time it's fired. Hopefully it won't be yours.

name: Security Armor
description: A bright green suit of form-fitting space kevlar. Provides exceptional defense without limiting your mobility at all.

name: Full Metal Jacket
description: You've somehow made a jacket out of plate mail.

name: Beginner\'s Guide to Necromantic Rituals (Vol. III)
description: A thick, musty-smelling book with a bunch of weird, garbled words and instructions. Also it sometimes makes zombies.

name: SBurb Game Manual
description: Yeah you have no idea what this thing is talking about.

name: Schrodinger\'s Suit
description: Schrodinger was a pretty fashionable guy.

name: Bandit Mask
description: You'd call it the domino mask, but you're pretty sure most bandits don't know shit about dominoes.

name: Cat von Tausend Hute
description: This magical cloak will give you great pleasure: its gadgets and gizmos bring fun without measure!

name: The Lorax
description: From the desks of old Giselle comes a tale about greed, a man wearing gloves and the birth of the Thneed...

name: Azure Wings
description: Once these were the wicked blades wielded by a virtual assassin rumored to have emerged from azure flames. His only mark was a three edged sign left at the site of his attacks.

name: Aviators
description: Ben Stiller's favourite pair.

name: Autospiral Gun
description: A machine gun that spews huge quantities of drill bullets capable of penetrating through most surfaces. Great for just closing your eyes, believing in yourself, and firing while panicking.

name: Magnetic Poker
description: As if getting poked in the face was bad enough, now you'll get poked in the face... with a MAGNET. Wearers of braces, beware!

name: Aperture Science High-Tension Portal Device
description: Thanks to the Aperture Science High-Tension Portal Device, the impossible is made less easier than before.

name: Skaianet Handheld Defense Portal Device
description: Now you too can use spirograph portals to redirect threats aimed at you, just like Skaia! Or if you happen to not have any threats currently aimed at you, you can use them to better aim some of your own! (Disclaimer: to prevent unauthorized paradoxes, these portals can only move things across your session and can not access any part of your universe's timeline.)

name: Yakumo Science Gap Gun
description: This device opens mysterious holes in space-time from which just about any object may be retrieved and/or fired at your adversaries. Popular choices of projectiles include tombstones, road signs, and trains.

name: Sun Gun
description: Using the same thermonuclear processes that fuel stars, this gun heats hydrogen gas to a temperature of several hundred thousand Kelvin and then expels the resulting plasma in a thin beam.

name: Control Rod Arm Cannon
description: Imbued with the spirit of a dead sun god, this allows you to harness the powers of nuclear fusion to create and fire miniature suns up to ten meters across. Indoor use not recommended.

name: Orbital Fusion Apocalypse Cannon 60000
description: With this satellite in orbit around Skaia, you can rain pinpoint-precision nuclear death on any Land in your session as well as the Battlefield. Just plug the coordinates into the remote and press the big red button, and BOOM!

name: Angled Bisector
description: Two blades stuck together at a single hilt at an adjustable angle. You guess this might be better than a single sword? Wielding it is kind of awkward, though.

name: Hard-light Holographic Chess Set
description: While the functionality is exactly the same, there's just no denying that this is a lot cooler than a normal chess set.

name: Hard-light Holo-Suit
description: Worn like a wristwatch, this wonder of technology projects tangible clothes onto you, allowing you to instantly change your outfit whenever you want! Just make sure to keep an eye on the charge meter.

name: Anvilhammer
description: More or less an anvil on the edge of a long handle, this thing could give a serious pounding... if you could even lift it!

name: Chainsledge
description: An extremely top-heavy hammer, and now that top has a high-speed rotating chain on it... you'd better be REALLY careful swinging this one around.

name: Skullhammer
description: A wicked sledgehammer with a skull-shaped hammerhead. It's a lot easier to wield, at least.

name: Amethyst Pan
description: A pan made of pure amethyst. You can't cook anything with it, but it sure does look snazzy!

name: Allfather Lloyd\'s Coin
description: Coin made of gold, with Allfather Lloyd and his white halo shown on its face.

name: MK23 SOCOM
description: A silenced pistol for a silent dude.

name: Cueballer
description: A pistol that fires small cueballs that draw on an infinite source of power. Have been known to destroy a universe in a single shot.

name: Omniscient Tarot Deck
description: A magical tarot deck that always answers any question with perfect accuracy. Also, every card is blank. It's a win-lose situation.

name: Afro Gandalf
description: A useless figurine of Gandalf with an afro, why did you even make this thing?

name: Adele\'s Umbrella
description: Feel the wrath of Adele under the fire-setting rain protector. Literally feel the power of making rain feel the pain of flames! If you're going to have a broken heart might as well ablaze your enemies while your at it!

name: AccelaBrick
description: This hurts. A lot.

name: Solar Flames
description: Did you... Did you just set Jupiter on fire?

name: Pocket Laptop
description: Sort of like a phone...you guess.

name: Green-flamed Infinitely-sparkling Yo-yo of Og\'Og
description: This is it: the pinnacle of Yo-Yos. The raw natural and arcane power coursing through this sparkling, deep yo-yo is insurmountable. Raw existence is yours to command, with gentle oscillations.

name: A Blaze of a Very High Degree
description: An ominous flamethrower with sleek design and a sinister history. Good for night owls, wise birds, and those who want to roast people alive. With style.

name: 8r8kr 8ar
description: A lug wrench with a loooooooong handle for the 8est possible leverage.

name: Adze
description: A woodcarving tool with a blade perpendicular to its handle. Did you want to adze me a que--you know what that doesn't work quite as well.

name: Halligan Bar
description: This thing is a hydra among tools. You're not sure if you'll ever need anything else.

name: Greenfireman\'s Multitool
description: If the first guardian was a fireman, you can bet your bottom dollar he'll carry this around everywhere he goes. Green fire is no joke.

name: Greenfireman\'s Set of Irons
description: Do you find yourself with lots of irons in the (green) fire? Then this is the tool for you!

name: 8-ball Lenses
description: What the...? These are completely pointless. They have no purpose whatsoever in seeing the future, or seeing anything at all. You just look like you have 8's for eyes. Good job.

name: Bone Blade
description: The sharpened edge of this bone actually proves to be much more useful than you'd think.

name: Green Sunta
description: An omnipotent fancy santa. What more could you need?

name: Ambo
description: A bo staff that floats. That's it, it just floats. Well, at least you don't have to use both hands to hold it.

name: Mystical Goggles
description: Steampunk goggles that are an odd green color.

name: Homemade Staffwand
description: Honestly? It's the same as your homemade wand, just about four times longer. Probably slightly more effective as hitting things though.

name: Staff of Mythological Dead
description: This staff is rumored to hold many powers of all the Dark Gods. You read it on the internet once, it must be true!

name: Belt of Sorcery
description: Ok, most sorcerors wear robes, but if they wore belts you are positive this would be around the waist of every last one.

name: Pen-Y-Fan
description: You feel like you could fight your way up a mountain with this in your hand. It also allows you to comprehend Welsh, though you can't see how that would be relevant.

name: Le Fantome
description: An ethereal, enchanted fan which confers invisibility on its holder. Perfect for magic-assisted espionage, or battering unsuspecting enemies into submission.

name: Snuggly Bathtime Fan
description: For those who like their baths hot, a colorful, soft fabric fan appropriate for use in steamy situations. Soggy paper fans are a thing of the past, though it was your own fault for dropping them.

name: Sophisticated Lass\'s Face-Hider
description: Intelligence and charm radiates from this finely crafted fan. It's plain for anyone to see that you are one individual that ought to be paid close attention to. If only it was suitable for more formal occasions...

name: Courtesan\'s Guile
description: Become the talk of the court with this dazzling, scarlet, heavily jewelled fan. Don't go making too many enemies though, even if it can slice a meddling footman in two.

name: Fan Art
description: This fan is emblazoned with a lurid drawing of your favorite fictional pairing, complete with love hearts, written onomatopoeia and a full display of your anatomical knowledge. You'd really rather not have to open it where anybody can see it.

name: Fanny Santa
description: Santa's decided to hide what little could still be seen of his bearded face behind a fan. This is somewhat of an improvement, in that it decreases the amount of this piece of shit you can see at any one time.

name: Fanned Saw
description: A curved, collapsible saw with beautiful designs laser-etched into the metal, that can lop off a tree limb in a single flick of the wrist. Perfect for the elegant carpenter or genteel tree surgeon.

name: Fanny Pack
description: This demented feat of punnery has yielded a hip-mounted knapsack to store keys, money, Pokemon cards or legendary artifacts somewhere more accessible than on your back.

name: Midnight Whisper
description: Eat your heart out, Void players: this jet-black fan lets you move about unobserved, slice up some unwary mooks and get home for sunrise like the slick professional you are.

name: Femme Fatale
description: Be everywhere, and nowhere. Cut the threads that bind the lives of your enemies with a casual flick of the wrist. To see your eyes above its rim is to know the meaning of fear, and the essence of style.

name: Ragnarokalibur
description: As its namesake suggests, this weapon is the god-ender. Titans, Olympians, immortals, souls. None can escape your blade. The blade is awake. Your shit is wrecked.FORUM

name: Proton Cannon
description: This huge kickass PROTON CANNON is so unspeakably heavy you are having a hard time even holding it. Deals some serious chip damage if you can get it off though.

name: Overcoat
description: Protecting you from cold, rain, wind, and fire since 1935.

name: Literally Flaming Fedora
description: The barbasol shaving cream's flammable properties turned the Flaming Fedora into a literally flaming fedora. Who knows, maybe the fire will intimidate foes? You'll just have to get used to having your head on fire all the time.

name: Light-Arrow Bow
description: Filled with the power to repel evil, this bow is infused with the power of the light spirits present in every lightbulb.

name: Stark Fusion Laser Bow
description: Have YOU ever wanted to make new elements in your garage? Now you can, with this extremely nonsensical bow!

name: Aperture Science Elastic-Powered Portal Bow
description: With this Aperture Science Elastic-Powered Portal Bow, the impossible is easy! For instance, you now fire portals, from a bow. A bow. What is this.

name: Aperture Science Hard Light Launcher
description: This Aperture Science Device compresses light to a form that can be shot. Remember how we said the Hard Light Bridges set your hair on fire? Yeah.

name: Trident
description: Just your average, run-of-the-mill trident. Nothing special about it, really.

name: Flame Staff
description: This staff is on fire. Literally. Try not to get burnt.

name: Lava Launcher
description: While technically it no longer fires flames, it's still packing heat! Though you kinda wonder why it doesn't just melt in your hands...

name: Helios Ray
description: They said you were crazy to use the powers of the sun to power your flamethrower. But its strong and self sustaining, what's not to love?

name: He-Man Action Figure
description: By the power of Greyskull, he has the power!

name: Technipower Ecstacythrower of Rainbowskull
description: And I cry sometimes when I'm lying in bed, just to get it all out what's in my head, and I feel a little peculiar... so I wake in the morning and I step outside, and I take a deep breath and get real high and I scream at the top of my lungs, "What's goin' on?"

name: Super Apostrophe
description: LR: Shooooooooooosh. It's a secret to everyone. EL: Who's everyone and why have I not met him? Overseer: AND JUST WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON HERE?  LR: ummmm.... /absconds Overseer: *grumble grumble*

name: Yasogami High School Blazer
description: High school blazer from popular RPG Persona 4.

name: Meteor Galaxy
description: Weapon of Kamen Rider Meteor in his base state. Has three buttons to execute special punches: Punches are like in the show, Saturn, a ranged punch that launches the rings at the opponent. Jupiter, an over sized punch that deals heavy damage at short range. Mars, small one inch punch, deals fire damage at close range.

name: Flame Style Wizard Ring Replica
description: Recreation of Haruto Souma's main transformation ring. No, it will not actually turn you into Wizard.

name: Warhammer 40,000: Space Marine
description: A videogame about 8-foot warrior monks eviscerating aliens. Probably has no immediate use in battle.

name: Astartes Chainsword
description: This ancient and holy weapon, wielded by the servants of the God-Emperor, is in y aour hands just a lump of metal for pulping Imps.

name: Astartes Boltgun
description: Forged by the finest artisans of mankind, the holy Bolter is a majestic weapon. It's also roughly the same size as your torso, so that could be a problem.

name: xxxHOLiC Vol. 1
description: Watanuki Kimihiro is haunted by visions of ghosts and spirits. Seemingly by chance, he encounters a mysterious witch named Yuuko, who claims she can help. In desperation, he accepts, but realizes that hes just been tricked into working for Yuuko in order to pay off the cost of her services. Soon hes employed in her little shopa job which turns out to be nothing like his previous work experience!

name: Marker
description: Felt tipped coloring device.

name: Magic Marker
description: A magic marker, this one is actually magical instead of just fun to color with.

name: Black-Magic Marker
description: A black marker imbued with shadow magic. I think it's permanent.

name: Enchanted Skull
description: Death and a bit of magic together. Magic is real enough if you know where to look. Sometimes you think you can hear it speaking to you.

name: The Return of Cthulhu
description: You can't believe you've done it.You've rewritten The Call of Cthulhu with your trusty pen and made the elder god stronger, better, faster. Yes that's right, all hail the MECHA CTHULHU.

name: The Ogreseer Project
description: With this, the show's ogre.

name: Stringed Sword Launcher
description: A violin-gun that shoots out its magically guideable sword-neck like an unchained harpoon.

name: Inky Drill
description: A drill head attached to the handle of a pen about as big as an axe handle. When you click it, it not only furiously spins, but also spits out ink!

name: Scythe of Space
description: The blade of this scythe is coated with the essence of deep space. You can hear a small humming sound coming from handle.

name: Scottish Folding Chairmore
description: Forged in the druken fires of Scottland, this folding Chairmore has a sturdy blade for each one of its legs.

name: Salted Caramel Flintlocks
description: No more waiting around the ol' stove for your caramel to be just right, these guns do all the work for you! They also pack a nice surprise for your foes.

name: Adagio Pistolina
description: The bullets for this pistol vibrate in your hand. If you hold them to you ear, you can faintly hear a sub-par high school orchestra playing.

name: Complete Doki*Doki Sailor Jacket!!
description: A jacket that's styled to look like a magical girl's outfit. How sugoi.

name: Rainbow Vision
description: Well, look what youve done know. these shades allow you to see in acidic colors as if you are very high, but this isnt really the best thing to wear at night.

name: Proto-helmet
description: It's always been on your mind... what it means to be born with weapons in our hands. You haven't found the answer yet, but with the powers you've been given, you will crush their tyranny.

name: Portable Dirtbane
description: A fold-able broom with a massive circular head. It works unnervingly well as both an umbrella and a broom. It can be a little hard to swing around in the event that you ever go mad and decide to use it as a weapon for some ridiculous reason.

name: Hakurei Lint-Roller
description: A Ying-Yang Orb attached to a witch's broom via a metal housing and a shaft through the middle of it. You can clean your floor with it, but it's just as likely to destroy your floor as it is dirt.

name: Electric Chair
description: Going up against this thing would be a death sentence.

name: Pizza
description: A whole pizza, from your favorite delivery joint. This party's starting to get crazy!

name: Astartes Plasmagun
description: The mighty Plasmagun's roar is that of a burning sun. Yes, you're going to be in contact with a weapon hurling lumps of sun at the enemy. You didn't really think this through.

name: Astartes Bolt Pistol
description: The Bolt Pistol, though less powerful than the holy Boltgun, is still a very useful weapon. By which you mean it's still a man-portable missile launcher.

name: Astartes Chainaxe
description: A brutal weapon for a less civilised age.

name: Assorted BIONICLE sets
description: Fond relics of you childhood. Or, depending on how pathetic you are, fond relics of your adulthood.

name: Quake-Breaker
description: A giant chainsaw that was once the weapon of a hero with mastery over earth: it still carries some of his power.

name: Two Ton Tunic
description: An Armor weighing just as much as it's name entails, it restrains all mobility at the cost of all movement. Only the greatest Shaolin monks can master it's use.

name: Trench Coat
description: A long ankle-length trench coat.

name: 3D Glasses
description: A pair of glasses with red and blue lenses. You find the multicolored lenses to be a bit strenuous on your eyesight, so you decide to wear them on your forehead.

name: Yo-yoyo
description: A steel Yo-Yo with a picture of Bo-Bobo on one side and Don Patch on the other. The string is actually an incredibly strong nose hair.

name: Titanic Trionfante
description: This legendary sword combines the elemental fury of both fire and ice, and calls time itself into its service. Very few could stand before a blade this powerful. It seems to softly hum, although whether it's with power or melody you aren't entirely sure.

name: CD Case
description: "Fist of the clacking CD case!"

name: Whale Plush
description: A soft, squishable whale the color of ivory. How could anyone possible want to seek revenge on this little guy?

name: Monstro Plush
description: He's big! He's bad! He'll eat your family!

name: White-Clad Whaleskin Jacket
description: Dress to the nines as a scourge of the seas with this nautical and probably highly illegal coat.

name: Hat of Unstoppable Nautical Wrath
description: Where a miserable octopus once nestled now resides a considerably miniaturized version of everyone's favorite evil giant whale! While he probably can't swallow anyone's father whole anymore, he's still perfectly capable of squirming and spouting in adorable anger.

name: Pinocchio DVD
description: For little wooden boys with horrible habits.

name: Triforce Wand
description: Your old homemade shitty wand now has the power of the Triforce of...shitty wands!

name: Fedora Phone
description: The fedora now can give off a hologram that has the same functions as the iPhone.

name: Pocket Digiwatch
description: For those too cool to wear a wristwatch and too impractical to just use a cellphone.

name: Pimpzilla Suit
description: When Zilla be walkin' down the street, he makes sure everyone damn well knows who owns this town.

name: Octets of Oglogoth
description: Pairing the Green Sun's Power with the Power of Horrorterrors is a good idea. Really. You now have dice that glow black and green and try to eat your hand whenever you use them.

name: Nrub\'yiglith\'s Carapace
description: Not even the tentacles of the great writhelord could penetrate his own sturdy carapace. A must have for those wishing protection from the shamebeast.

name: Third Leg
description: The powerful canon used by Utsuho Reiuji in Touhou 11 is now yours to wield in a tiny, portable handgun.

name: Monokuma
description: Upupupu! This adorable black and white bear will fill your enemies with so much despair that they just won't know what hit them - unless it's a bunch of spears. They'll know it if it's spears.

name: Metastealth Suit
description: Thankfully not a King's New Clothes situation, this ultra-sleek battle suit is so mind-numbingly black your eyes have enormous trouble looking directly at it. Plus you can make it invisible at will for spur-of-the-moment streaking, kind of making it a King's New Clothes situation.

name: Lemonjon Candies
description: A handful of small, lemon-shaped candies, a product of the colossal son of the Lemongrabs sacrificing himself to save his starving kingdom. He dissolved the bonds uniting him and become component to all. A pretty morbid candy, once you think about it.

name: Mega Pistol
description: While its shots bear a striking resemblance to lemons, this handgun shouldn't be underestimated. No, you can't take the power of your enemies with it.

name: Bottle Rocket Pistol
description: Two of Jeff's favorite means of combat in one.

name: 10mm Pistol
description: The first best friend of anyone with the audacity to try and take on post-nuke America.

name: The Emperor
description: The fearsome stand of Hol Horse, now in a form that can actually be seen by people without a stand.

name: Martial Arts Gi
description: A traditional uniform designed for training.

name: Light Headache
description: A vuvuzela that emits a bright, hot light when blown into. Those on the receiving end of this abomination will not be able to tell if their headache is from the bright light or the loud noise.

name: Laser Cannon
description: Through combination of Laser technology and a particle accelerator this weapon shoots a large laser, unfortunately it's not as focused as you'd like, but it is damn powerful.

name: Crystal Drill
description: A Drill made out of pure crystal... possibly a bit more for show than practicality but it does allow light to pass through it.

name: Applemonade
description: A bottle of juice with a blast of dual fruity flavor. Half sweet, half sour, ALL AWESOME.

name: Focused Laser Cannon
description: By running the laser through through this drill you've managed to get it fairly well focused, if only you could somehow make the tip a bit finer...

name: Geyser-in-a-Can
description: You don't need energetic drinks with our amazing Geyser-in-a-can! Instant fun for large company of friends, sudden foam to surprise your foe, and even jet engines all with our incredible Geyser-in-a-can(r)!

name: Hyper-focused Laser Cannon
description: By turning the tip of the drill into a screw, the laser has been focused into a beam so precise it can cut through the hull of a ship in seconds.

name: Candy Bandages
description: No longer will you have to choose whether to wrap yourself in bandages or snack on some Gushers -- now you can do BOTH.

name: Laser Ninjato
description: This smaller copy of a lightsaber is capable of cutting through or parrying most weapons, making it an ideal offhand weapon.

name: Fueled Lantern
description: Your everyday steel lantern with a small area for oil. This thing could almost one-up a barbasol bomb.

name: Luck of the Roses
description: A set of beautiful ornate dice, they look hand crafted and resonate with life. Yet a cold chill washes over you while holding them.

name: Jack-In-The-Box
description: A somewhat harmless joke toy meant to open up and surprise you with a clown. You consider using it to build your Prankster's Gambit.

name: Die-In-The-Box
description: This toy has been modified to shoot dice out instead of a clown: making it sightly more of a choke hazard than what you'd normally get out of a toy store.

name: Dice of Oglogoth
description: The spiked dice quake with vigor under THE DEEP ONE'S dark desires. You think you'll take the chance of using them against doing the sane thing.

name: Music Disc
description: Stored on this disc are your favorite songs, it looks sharp enough to be used as a weapon too though.

name: Nuclear Plastic Pyramid Scorchers
description: A set of pyramid shaped dice glowing with radiation contained inside them. You're not sure if its even safe to be near them.

name: d24 Karat
description: A solid pure gold die with engraved diamond numbers on each face. Now you can play your money and big as you spend it!

name: Swiss Army Knife
description: A Pocket Knife / Multitool that can be quite usefull in a multitude of situations.

name: French Flag
description: The national flag of France features three vertical bands of blue, white, and red in that order.

name: French Army Knife
description: A dandy little tool for the frenchman on the go. This little guy sports a cigarette holder, wine bottle opener, and a white flag.

name: Network Digivice
description: We're going digital with this specialized portable computer. No Digidestined would be caught digi-dead without this important accessory.

name: Keys to the Kingdom Seven Book Set
description: All seven books from the Keys to the Kingdom book series.

name: Minute Hand
description: An enlarged minute hand. You can give someone a minute and give them a hand at the same time!

name: Hour Hand
description: An enlarged hour hand, looking like it comes from a fancy old clock. It could probably be used as a stabbing implement in a tight corner.

name: The First Key
description: This "Key" bears the form of a sword. It gives dominion over the Lower House and Monday, whatever that means.

name: The Second Key
description: ThisKey looks more like a pair of gloves, but made of metal and very shiny.

name: The Third Key
description: This Keyusually looks like a fairly intimidating trident, but it can also shrink down to the convenient size of a regular fork.

name: Truncheon
description: Also called by such names as billy club, nightstick, and cosh, this club is a weapon used by law enforcement for the purpose of negotiating forced compliance.

name: The Fourth Key
description: This Keyappears as a Marshal's baton normally, but it doesn't seem to mind taking the form of whatever weapon its wielder prefers, to a certain extent.

name: The Fifth Key
description: This Keylooks like a bright silver mirror, though it feels like a lot more than that.

name: The Sixth Key
description: This Keylooks more like a fancy quill, but it can write in thin air so you dont even need paper!

name: The Seventh Key
description: The Keys to the Kingdom, at least in one universe.

name: Lime
description: A zesty, sour fruit of the citrus persuasion.

name: Key Lime
description: A lime with a key inside it? Supposedly the key gives it a unique flavor, but you aren't so sure you want to try it.

name: Lime Key
description: A small, green key. You... really don't see how this is different from your other key, aside from the palette swap.

name: Key Lime Pie
description: The meringue on top makes this pie look temptingly fluffy. It's tempting you to throw it right in somebody's face.

name: Izanagi Buster Sword
description: A fabled spear-like sword, the likes of which said to have been used by a Japanese mythological deity. You kind of doubt that though, this thing isn't all that impressive.

name: Sandman Sandbag
description: A bag full of magic sand. The purpose of this supposedly magic sand isn't apparent, but you do know one thing: splashing it in someone's eye should hurt at least!

name: Tzitzimitl\'s Hand
description: The priestess of darkness's right hand. Granted, she has more than enough. She shouldn't notice one gone...

name: Mithra\'s Tool
description: A tool used by a lion with wings, wrapped up in a snake... How HIGH do you even have to BE just to IMAGINE something like that??

name: Norn\'s Clock
description: The threadmistress of fate's time counter. It's said if you stare at it, it will tell you how long you have to live. The last thing that your enemies will see is a gigantic zero right in their face.

name: Energized Protodermis Energy Drink
description: Normally, exposure to energised protodermis either causes you to either transform or dissolve. Fortunately, this stuff is dilute, so it'll just either power you up or burn a hole in your intestines.

name: Holy Hardbrick
description: You thought this tome couldn't get any heavier or bigger, fortunately it also packs more of a punch.

name: TIC Chain
description: Replacing this overweight collection of book's bookmark with a chain seemed like a good choice at first, just try work on your aim.

name: Hermit Purple
description: All-purpose energy tendrils. Wielding these, you feel vaguely telepathic.

name: Sawhands
description: Loud and dangerous powered glove-saw hybrids. Having those spinning blades that close to your hands might get uncomfortable after a while...

name: Grief Seed
description: Supposedly, putting this next to your soul will drain it of grief, restoring your magical abilities. You're not sure if you want this anywhere near your soul, though. You don't know where it's been!

name: Green Solar Flare
description: Green flames are supposed to be the hottest, right?

name: Pokemon Gym Badges
description: These are symbols of the challanges you've faced. Each one gives you a nifty boost and you have all 8.

name: Green Lint-Roller of the Sun
description: Marisa Kirisame, your youthful hijinks have doomed us all.

name: Temporal Beat
description: Brooms tend to be more threatening when each of their individual bristles weigh enough to kill a cat when dropped. Being able to strike from everywhen at once also helps.

name: Gold Drachma
description: A gold coin from way back when, used in Ancient Greece! Currency of the gods, my friends. Well, almost.

name: Reploid Head Part
description: An upgraded Armor Part made by Doctor Light for one blue Maverick Hunter. Breaks some blocks.

name: Gasclock Flamershield
description: This thing is a shield with a flamethrower sticking out of it. It's a clumsy and crude weapon, but atleast it grants some defence also.

name: Game of Stars
description: A deck of cards enhanced with the power of the stars- or at least some shitty sparkling dust. It might have magical power, except everyone knows magic isn't real.

name: Franklin Badge
description: A small golden badge, it can be used to ward off electricity. But it won't stop those tears from falling.

name: Hasbro Hoverboard
description: Tell me, doctor, where are we going this time</br>Is this the 50's, or 1999</br>All I wanted to do - was play my guitar and sing

name: Fission Battery
description: Damn, this thing is heavy! It also blew up the flashlight you tried putting it in.

name: Powered Power Armor
description: This power armor has been upgraded with a nuclear power pack. The hydraulics and servo-motors inside keep the weight off you and provide added defense somehow.

name: Pimp Robe
description: Look pimpin', I ain't playin'.

name: UAC Helmet
description: This helmet is almost too manly for you to wear.

name: Mega-armor
description: This armor looks just like the security armor, except blue. It's better, though.

name: Red Trenchcoat
description: You suddenly feel the overwhelming urge to jump around and shoot demons. And eat pizza.

name: Fenrisulfr Tome
description: A formidable tome of dark magic, now unfettered by the mighty chain that once bound it shut. Odin is surely pissing his pants right now.

name: Favorite Felt Fedora
description: Wow look at that it has your favorite felt member's number and everything! What luck!

name: Fake as Shit Lightsaber
description: This lightsaber is fake as shit. It does make real fake as shit battle sounds when you whack something with it, though.

name: Drill-Lance
description: A lance with a drill on the end. What did you expect? A lance that spins like a drill?

name: Lance-Drill
description: A lance that can spin like a drill. What did you expect? A drill on the end of a lance?

name: Dragon Reaper Scythe
description: If the Grim Reaper was a dragon, this would be the exact scythe that he'd use. Probably.

name: Dragon Claws
description: Dragon-sized and dragon-strength claws used by dragons. Dragons!

name: Double Shrek Blades
description: When you just want everyone to stay out of your swamp, nothing gets the message across like these bright green stabs.

name: Needlessly Large Pencil
description: You may be asking yourself why this writing utensil is so excessively gargantuan. The answer is that it was intended to WRITE OUT your foe's doom.

name: Naked Snake\'s M1911A1 Custom
description: A real pistol for a real Big Boss.

name: The Patriot
description: Weapon of a patriot who saved the world.

name: Nail Bat
description: A bat with several nails protruding from it. Do not try this at home, children.

name: Gamblignant\'s Boots
description: The black leather boots that the feared gambligant Mindfang wore herself. A step beyond just simple roleplaying or FLARPing attire, these boots are sturdy and strong. They are a powerful tool for any arsenal. Assuming you can get past the dusty old musk scent of them.

name: Gamblignant\'s Gloves
description: The very gloves of the feared gamblignant Mindfang. The black leather is quite comfortable still, despite their age. And now, you will use these to your advantage, carrying on the legacy she left of punching many an enemy and friend in the nose to assert your dominance.

name: Gamblignant\'s Saber
description: A saber once used by the illustrious Mindfang herself. Terror of the Alternian seas, so was her blade. Warning to Roleplayers: Not a toy!

name: Red Paint
description: A can of red paint. Paint your house with it. Paint your bike. Paint anything you want.

name: Blue Paint
description: Just a can of blue paint. You can paint things with it, if you want. And if you like the color blue.

name: Purple Paint
description: After mixing your paints together, you create paint in the color purple. Congratulations on learning how the color wheel works.

name: Rapunzel\'s Golden Locks
description: These long, golden locks are imbued with divine magic, capable of healing any and all wounds. Let's just hope you're confident in your singing voice...

name: Audrey Hepburn DVD Collection
description: Beauty, class, elegance, and grace - you've watched Audrey Hepburn's films dozens of times over, desperate to learn the finer points of these traits. It's been a frustrating journey.

name: Fruit Gushers - 8ad 8r8ks 8egone 8lue8erry flavour
description: 8ad 8r8ks 8egone 8lue8erry flavoured Fruit Gushers. Every gambler's dream, these dice-patterned treats make you feel luckier just by looking at the box.

name: Prospit Globe
description: Although designed for ornamental purposes, the massive amount of spires and pointy towers on this thing makes it a fairly respectable weapon.

name: Derse Globe
description: Although designed for ornamental purposes, the massive amount of spires and pointy towers on this thing makes it a fairly respectable weapon.

name: Prospit Pajamas
description: These magical pajamas stay permanently clean, and are also really comfortable. Now you can wear them even when you're not asleep!

name: Derse Pajamas
description: These magical pajamas stay permanently clean, and are also really comfortable. Now you can wear them even when you're not asleep!

name: Rifle Pointer
description: A novelty laser pointer in the shape of a tiny rifle. You suppose it looks sort of neat, but it's really not all that useful.

name: Tri-legged Compass
description: With this, you can draw your circles twice as fast as with an ordinary pair of compasses! Perfect for the ridiculously busy geometer, and just about nobody else.

name: Perfect Maid\'s Pocketwatch
description: An ornate watch that allows the user to stop time briefly.

name: Extension Sword
description: Press the button on the hilt, and the blade extends to five times its normal length! There's overcompensating, and then there's OVERcompensating...

name: Tesla Blade
description: A sword with lightning arcing along the blade. Good thing the hilt is made of rubber!

name: 24-Karat Gold Bo-Bobo Wig
description: An exact replica of Bo-Bobo's legendary golden afro. If you open it you find two squirrels having a tea party inside.

name: Pen Fifteen Club Honorary Member\'s Coat
description: A luridly colored trench coat with "PEN15" printed on the back in comic sans. You feel embarrassed wearing this.

name: Slick Coat of Spades
description: This is quite the fancy coat. There's a knife in just about every pocket.

name: Red Flowered Suit
description: A red suit that looks perfect for any formal occasion adorned with a red rose.

name: Amphitrite
description: The greatest Electrical Lance known to Hunter kind. Its materials comes from a mighty sea Leviathan. Sparks can be seen when it makes contact with its enemies.

name: 0 - The Fool
description: The wild card. Grants the wielder to shape the facets of their personality into summoned demons.

name: Armor of the Sun
description: Wearing this, surprisingly, does not fill you with a desire to engage in jolly cooperation. Unless you're sort of always like that. At any rate, all these sun decals are sure to make you look like a Light player, regardless of whether or not you actually are one.

name: Aya\'s Chainsaw
description: Aaaaayyyyaaaaaaaa come back to Father!

name: Pokemon Chainsaw Pearl Version
description: A wild foe appeared! What will CHAINSAW do?

name: Barkley\'s Basketball Jersey
description: A mesh b-ball jersey worn by famous baller and herald of the cyberpocalypse, Charles Barkley. Incredibly valuable as memorabilia, but not very effective as armor.

name: Rosy Fedora
description: This fedora glows a bright red and has an intricate rose pattern on it.

name: Leather Armor
description: A light, basic armor. It offers limited protection, but does not hinder your movement too much. It's covered in all kinds of straps and buckles and shit, too.

name: B-Ball Armor
description: This is a suit of leather armor, but it uses the same material as a b-ball instead of leather, making it bright orange and bumpy for grip. The agility of 1000 b-ballers courses through you when you wear this. It has b-ball logos on the shoulder pauldrons.

name: Baroque Power Armor
description: This suit of armor feels like a second skin! Additionally, it's pauldrons are the size of your head. There are roman scriptures inscribed all over the armor. That Latin class certainly is starting to look useful right now.

name: Bicycle Helmet
description: This might protect your head if you crash your bike, but it won't do you much good against terrible monsters.

name: Golden Crown
description: Wearing this makes you feel all majestic. You're basically the king of your planet, why not look the part?

name: Final Fantasy VII
description: The game that sparked the imagination of countless young minds of the nineties, and now your imagination as well as you think of all the potential for awesome alchemy contained within.

name: Birthday Cake
description: For that special occasion.

name: Birthday Suit
description: Well... it may not be a suit, and it's got precious little to do with your birthday, but on the plus side, you're thankful for the frosting...

name: Thorn of My Eye
description: These certainly push it past the idea of an apple. The shades shimmer with a gallant red.

name: Blades of Exile
description: Even after a soothing dip into the river of death, these blades just keep on fighting without a stop. You can barely put them down, they're just that eager to fight.

name: Thorned Amulet of The Roses
description: This amulet emits heat from its red rose shapen gem attached to a thorny lace.

name: Bleach DVD
description: A DVD containing all seasons of an anime called bleach, its about some high school student who can see ghosts.

name: Senbonzakura
description: This is the Zanpakuto of Sixth Division's Captain, Byakuya Kuchiki. If only making it gave you the knowledge on how to use its Bankai.

name: Cherry Blossom
description: A pink flower that grows on several trees, also called sakura after the Japanese.

name: Senbonzakura Kageyoshi
description: Scatter.

name: Rose-Steel Fedora
description: A tough reinforced classical red piece of headwear. Because even the classiest people need head protection!

name: Rose-Steel Suit
description: Not as comfortable as your everyday suit, but certainly not any less fashionable! The steel should keep it from staining any different color than red.

name: Thorny Rose Amulet of Steel Protection
description: The amulet surrounds its wearer with a gray magical aura. From the looks of it, the aura reflects most physical attacks from your foes.

name: Rose-Steel Shades
description: Hardened steel thorned eyewear made fit for an adventurer with a passion for the color red. Also for anyone with a STRONG sense of fashion.

name: YOYOAH...
description: This is, without question, the most conksuck yo-yo you have ever seen.

name: Snow-yo
description: This yo-yo releases a small flurry of snowflakes whenever used. Hope you brought a scarf!

name: Wintertime in the Furthest Ring
description: The pompous scope of influence this jolly deity holds reaches beyond the very fabric of existence. Even the most powerful beings to ever hold sentience quiver in anticipation of his momentous list. To be on the "nice" side is pure absolution. To be on the "naughty" side is irreparable damnation. This is it. This is holiday endgame.

name: Titan\'s H8mmer
description: You hear angels moan and demons sing when you strike your enemies down with this beast.

name: Cosplay Cat Tail
description: You'll look mad adorbs with this trailing off of your back.

name: Mechapimpzilla Suit
description: With your new robot chassis, you'll make sure to get your money from your "partners."

name: Textridaggers
description: The dual blades of the chosen arbiter. Blessed by the DEMIMONDE SEMIGODDESS.

name: Superheated Candy Scissors
description: These delicious looking scissors can be taken apart into two different red hot Blades of pure Sugary murder.

name: Godhand CD
description: CD Copy of Godhand, for the PS2.

name: Formella\'s Blade
description: This blade was one of the best kept secrets of a legendary royal court beyond our universe. A far sharper and easier to wield alternative to the traditional royal weaponry, it's a dual-ended tri-bladed scythe best known as the Die By Tri-Scythe.

name: Grand Steel-Thorned Rose Suit
description: The suit glows with a magic gray and red aura, adorned with steel thorns from the shoulders down to the cuffs. It shimmers red like blood and has an unearthly texture in the fabric sewed together to create this magnificient wear.

name: Looney Toons DVD
description: A collection of cartoons from Looney Toons on a single DVD.

name: Mortal Kombat Disc
description: A Mortal Kombat 9 Disc.

name: Miracle
description: Just... miracles<iframe width="0" height="0" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/embed/3W32h-3EHCg?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: MiRaClE
description: mOtHeRfUcKiNg MiRaClEs<iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/watch?v=3W32h-3EHCg?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: Doctorate in Bitchology
description: A degree earned from the University of Fuck You.

name: Star\'s Fate
description: This deck accurately tells the future of anyone who peruses it. Or at least robs gullible idiots of their money.

name: Queen of Spades / Portent of Death
description: What this card's draw means is that something is going to die.

name: Spear of the Force
description: A mystical energy spear that seems to gleam with life energy and power.

name: Spear Of Illuminant Souls
description: A spear that is made out of pure souls. It glows a golden color when held.

name: Sorcerer\'s Catalyst
description: You probably should have maxed your intelligence. Prepare to die.

name: Sims Disc
description: Why build your own skills when you could build the skills of a million fictional single minded pixel people?

name: Shitty Kunai
description: Don't wave them around at the food court.

name: Best Banchou\'s Golf Club
description: Face yourself, then beat the shit out of yourself with a 9 iron!

name: Shitty Fake Diamond
description: Marginally less beautiful to most, extremely less valuable to all.

name: Salvaged Medkit
description: A medkit that is filled with less gauze and splints than it is stimpaks and purified water. You don't know why, but it seems to have a locking mechanism. Try not to engage it when you're bleeding out behind a rock.

name: Cue Ball Helmet
description: A Giant Cue Ball with a hole that you feel like your head will fit in. Even though it doesn't have any eye-holes, you can somehow tell what's in front of you when you wear it.

name: Popcorn
description: The simplest of movie foods. Needs salt, though.

name: Ninjatop
description: Hands-free computing for the on-the-go assassin. Even helps you sense hidden enemies. (Un)fortunately, the interface is only in Japanese.

name: Pizza Hat
description: This looks exactly like a pizza in every way, except you can wear it as a hat. It's also inedible.

name: Megidarts
description: Magic darts that inflict medium Almighty damage.

name: Z-Helm
description: Maybe with this on you'll finally have the answer to the question... "what am I fighting for?"

name: Pitbull
description: Hey McFly, you bojo, those boards don't work on water. Unless you've got POWER. Which this thing has whole lot of, and plenty to spare.

name: Physics Spatha of Complex Spacey Energy
description: The secrets of hella complicated physics bullshit courses through this ancient blade. Invaluable to the intrepid hero of space and bacicly usless to anyone else.

name: Phial of Galadriel
description: A small glass bottle of water, corked tight with a glass stopper. It seems to glow gently with an inner light.

name: Headlampset
description: Useful for communicating in dark and dangerous places, the Headlampset shines light in front of you to ensure you're never cut off or blind.

name: Spirit Lantern
description: Spooky in just about every way. You're not sure how it's fueled, or where that eerie fog is coming from, but it's pretty hefty, so you're happy with it.

name: Junior Reaper\'s Starter Sepulcher
description: Every beginner reaper needs a tool, and this effective, simple stone-bladed scythe sings a jaunty dirge to help ease first-reaping nerves.

name: Skull Beanie
description: This black beanie will make you almost look like a gangster. The skull on top is pretty cool, and hopefully will hide your inner-nerd from the world.

name: Red Skull Pin
description: A red pin with a black skull on it, looking almost exactly like the Skull Pin. Be wary, this pin may open you up to mind control!

name: Mr. Mew
description: This hand-made stuffed cat toy will be great for all, and may well help bring out any psyche potential you have. Mostly though, it's a precious memento.

name: Red Coin
description: A coin of some strange red metal from a popular series of games about an Italian guy who can jump ridiculously high.

name: Blue Coin
description: A coin of some strange blue metal from a popular series of games about an Italian guy who can jump ridiculously high.

name: Purple Coin
description: A coin of some strange purple metal from a popular series of games about an Italian guy who can jump ridiculously high who flies around collecting stars to save several galaxies.

name: Star Coin
description: This coin shines brilliantly, especially the star on it. Perhaps you should get more of these? But no more than three.

name: Orbital Fusion Apocalypse Spirograph Portal Rifle 413000
description: Because the only thing better than an orbital death ray is an orbital death ray that can be fired like a normal gun. Pulling the trigger activates the satellite\'s firing sequence, and the resulting beam of nuclear destruction is immediately redirected to the barrel of the gun via spirograph portal.

name: Prospitian Lemonade
description: A refreshing, home-made drink from the kingdom of light. Best enjoyed in glasses made out of solid gold.

name: d2
description: A coin with dots on its faces instead of the usual heads and tails. Why did you make this, again?

name: Golden Armor
description: Show your lack of both sense and taste at the same time by wearing this incredibly gaudy suit of armor that's both too heavy to move around in and too malleable to offer any real protection!

name: Electric Lantern
description: Stop having to worry about running out of oil, and instead start having to worry about running out of batteries!

name: Laser Lantern
description: Just like a normal lantern, except instead of emitting white light in every direction, it emits high-intensity light with a single wavelength in a narrow beam.

name: Jeweled Pagoda of Bishamonten
description: You aren't entirely certain how the massive amounts of colourful lasers fired by this thing are able to curve in mid-air and home in on your enemies, but to be honest, you don't really care.

name: Now Serving Breakfast at Tiffany\'s
description: Straight from Fifth Avenue, this lavish and expensive frying pan is made entirely out of diamond. Nothing conducts heat more efficiently than diamonds. With this pan, you'll be packing lots of it.

name: Naglfar
description: The pinnacle of dark tome, carrying great destructive power: named for the ship that will carry the Gods of old to battle in Ragnarok.

name: ZILLION OF EVERY GRIST TYPE
description: LR: You asked for it, so here you go. Maybe next time dont be such a smartass. :p

name: Stuffed Boondollar
description: Sadly, not viable currency.

name: Salaryman Pistol
description: ...is a pistol. Bang. Bang.<iframe width="420" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/UWKg_E3mWsw" frameborder=false></iframe>

name: Sleuth Jacket
description: A reasonable and worn looking jacket that seems to scream "Calm down, I'm adequate at sleuthing problems".

name: Ripper\'s Blades
description: Like with any weapon, making them mini-death machines by turning them into chainsaws it always a swell idea. Just holding them drives you to track down your enemies and destroy them for vengeance.

name: Heavenly Dawn
