description: This sword's just as large as you, not counting the dozens of roaring metal teeth spurring around it's edge. Holy Damn. Warn the neighbors, because there will be blood. Probably yours.

name: Paper Mario poster
description: A classic rpg represented in a way that keeps the original artstyle intact.

name: Blank Badge
description: Just thinking of all the scouting you can cheat with this is making you nervous.

name: Orthus\'s Whip
description: A whip with the power of 100 monsters and .1 archaeologists

name: Nata Taishi\'s Wheel
description: The dragon slayer's flaming wheel.

name: Legion
description: A 3-headed axe. On the hilt it reads: "We are many."

name: Kartikeya\'s Barrier
description: A shield glistening with many different color facets.

name: Gae Bulg
description: The legendary weapon of the Northern Hero, C Chulainn.

name: Girimehkala\'s Dagger
description: Where could that elephant-cyclops have hid this even? Up his trunk? ..eww.

name: Oukuninushi\'s Bravier
description: The ultimate hero's weapon, a peacemaker and war ender.

name: No Okami
description: A sword fallen through the very cracks of Heaven, a sword that has no rival. The Circular hilt represents the world and all that it can destroy. This weapon should only belong in the hands of the god who gives life to all. A blade worthy of being claimed by Izanagi.

name: Myriad Truths
description: "I am thou, and thou art I...  From the sea of thy soul, I come... I giveth thee the power to shine light upon your allies... And bringeth to vision the path to the truth."

name: Thousand Lies
description: "I am thou, and thou art I...  From the sea of thy soul, I come... I grant upon thee the power to cloud the judgement of thine enemies... And bring forth the fog that shall shroud the truth."

name: Loki\'s Suicide Note
description: <iframe width="1" height="1" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/lVCFP8_Hthw?autoplay=1" frameborder=false></iframe>

name: Bangarang CD
description: A great CD by the dubstep artist known as Skrillex <iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/KAUwpbXywNQ?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: Waifu ARbot
description: SENDJC: i can see you cybering with my bot</br>Overseer: *facepalm*

name: Yaoi Hands
description: You're not even sure how you equipped these exactly, but regardless, your hands feel much larger and rather homosexual.

name: Bishonen Shoulders
description: You feel as if your posture has ascended to anime-levels. Though you may just be imagining things..

name: Shoujo Eyes
description: Eyes are the window to the soul. Though, still not entirely sure how you even equipped EYES...

name: Keyboard
description: The smaller, lighter version of a piano. Now you can create beautiful music and smash the skulls of your enemies!

name: Angel\'s Harp
description: A small golden harp that plays wonderfully entrancing melodies, almost reminiscent of what you imagine an angel's song to be like.

name: Rock Music CD
description: A mixtape of classic and contemporary rock music. You wonder where music would be without the advent of the electric guitar!

name: Map of the Incipisphere
description: With this trusty map, you'll be able to navigate the planets with ease!

name: 2-Hole Buster Sword
description: The High Quality standard of a BFS. How do you even swing this thing around?

name: Animishades
description: You're beginning to think that these triangular lenses are just shards of a broken iPhone from when it was dropped. They still function, ironically enough.

name: Aperture Science Bow of Physics-Fucking
description: Cave Johnson here, as you know at Aperture, we make SCIENCE. The lab boys tell me this bow is so smack-dab full of science, it can warp the fabric of reality to do.. well whatever you want it to do, really. Somehow it launches arrows from all forms of reality directly into your crosshairs, which probably makes some nasty tears in spacetime, but who do we care, right?

name: Authentic Dragonskin Suit
description: This suit is 100% real dragon leather! Or at least that's what the dealer told you. Right after he sold you a used car.

name: How to Slay a Zombie
description: This handbook has pretty much all there is to know about zombies within its text. Coincidentially, one of the top strategies of dealing with them happens to be hitting them with the book itself.

name: Banjiolin
description: An unholy combination between a banjo and a violin. You don't really want to play this, unless you have a spare pair of ears.

name: Birdess Gown
description: Looks nice, but you probably could've reached the same result if you tarred yourself and rolled around in a pile of feathers.

name: Dual Claymores
description: You thought one was heavy enough.

name: Featherlinked Tickle-Stabber
description: The fashion of boas meet the stabbity-ness of knives. It's quite the statement.

name: Bladed Wrench
description: A bladed wrench for all your fighting-fixing needs.

name: Brutal Legend Disk
description: A game about babes, metal, and shredding sweet licks in the name of Humanity, what's not to like?

name: Bronze Khopesh
description: The Egyptian equivalent of a Claymore. The sickle-shaped blade is wickedly sharp, and you are in awe of the sheer awesomness of this weapon.

name: Butcher Apron
description: Let's face it - in your line of work, your clothes are bound to get dirty without one of these.

name: Champion\'s Belt
description: One of us is walking out of here with the belt, and the other one's getting RAWKED!

name: Plain Paper Badge
description: Apparently there were so many badges in Paper Mario that the laws of alchemy couldn't decide on a specific one for these plain pins to create when combined. Oh well! Maybe you can combine it with something else?

name: Power Plus Badge
description: When equipped you feel a power surge throughout your body...or you poked yourself when you sowed it on.

name: Hammawhack 2005
description: As a hammer enthusiast you know all the ins and outs of this fine machine: the handle, the wedge, THE FACE. It would be amazing if it weren't so outdated.

name: Ultra Hammer
description: No more fancy names! This is a serious weapon for a serious person. Try not to get any ichor on the ribbon.

name: W Emblem Badge
description: Your clothes change to a yellow and purple color scheme while wearing this, for some reason.

name: The E-Lemonator
description: A promo from the Juice Bar but it seems like something is missing...

name: Lime Time Golden Fruit Juicer
description: Its time. Lime time time.

name: Space Cape
description: A flowing, magic cape that displays a view of a sector of space. A must have fashion statement for any up-and-coming god.

name: Candy Cornsaw
description: Tastes like sugar and death!

name: Rubik\'s Cube
description: The more you play with it, the harder it gets!

name: Unbridled Instinct
description: Thine power dost be taken lightly. Thou dost not know of thine consequences of forging this unholy blade of sepulchre.

name: Cairo Overcoat
description: You have a feeling that this belongs to a certain someone. A certain everyone.

name: Trumpet
description: A snazzy-looking trumpet. Despite its particularly shiny looks, this is still made of brass, not gold.

name: The Stone Tablets
description: There is some kind of inscription on these old stone tablets that you can't really read. They are really heavy and they seem sort of useless. However, you feel empowered by some mysterious force when you hold them.

name: Jegus\' Hopy Penstaff
description: This legendary writing utensil was used by Jegus Grist to inscribe the 413 reprimandments on the Final quest bed after parting the Candy Blood Sea. You're not entirely sure where that fit's into scripture, but hey, it's a bad-ass staff.

name: The Separator
description: An axe said to have killed the Demon Emperor Doviculus himself: "DECAPITATIOOOOOOOON!"

name: Clementine
description: This heavy metal guitar can shoot licks of lightning and pyrotechnics to burn your foes! Careful on playing too much though, she heats up pretty fast.

name: The King\'s Cue
description: With a decorative chess inspired base and a smooth white orb on the top, this staff doesn't seem to be worth the Grist it cost but the longer you hold it the more you feel that it doesn't belong in the hands of mere mortals.

name: Pole-Arm "L\'Etranger"
description: This spear, made out of arms, can be used as a whiplike weapon as well as a sturdy polearm. Now when you're asked to quickly retrieve your arms, you'll get the best of both worlds.

name: Metal Gear RAY Statue
description: You're not even sure how this qualifies as a statue, seeing as it's a life-size replica of a RAY.

name: Sol Blade
description: The ultimate sword! Or it would be, but you have to wait for the sequel.

name: Gloria Helm
description: A crown-like golden helmet with a silver visor and two green gemstone horns coming out of the sides.

name: Slap Chop (TM)
description: Stop having a boring life! With the slap chop, you can just slap your troubles away, and you can make the world a skinnier place at the same time by enforcing EXCITING healthy food! It's so easy, if Vince can do it with one finger you can do it with your whole hand!

name: Shadow Hammer
description: A black and red sledgehammer. You're willing to bet that this was genetically engineered to create the ultimate hammerform.

name: Rod of Reckoning
description: With no decorations other than a small rock set into the end, this staff might look relatively unassuming. But appearances can deceive: whap an enemy with it, and seconds later a meteor will fall out of the sky right at them! Just make sure to stand well clear of the blast.

name: Riflescope
description: A gun with a barrel that can extend to a length of several meters. Great for people with abysmal aim who want to increase their point-blank range, but not particularly useful for most other people.

name: Prospitian Assault Rifle
description: Standard issue equipment for the Prospitian army.

name: Dersite Assault Rifle
description: Standard issue equipment for the Dersite army on the Battlefield.

name: Gold Ring
description: A plain ring made out of pure gold.

name: GameBro Magazine
description: A totally rad magazine featuring reviews of awesome games for awesome bros.

name: Elementless Wizard Ring
description: This useless ring's jewel is misshapen and has a dull grey color. Which is too bad, because it feels like it has a lot of potential...

name: Flame Wizard Ring
description: A Wizard Ring that contains the element of fire. It is embedded with a magical oval ruby fashioned to look a bit like a mask.

name: Water Wizard Ring
description: An elemental ring of water created from a magical sapphire. The sapphire has been fashioned into a thin oval with a mask design.

name: Hurricane Wizard Ring
description: An air elemental ring that was created from a magic emerald stone. The jewel has been made into the shape of a triangle and covered in a sort of mask-like design.

name: Land Wizard Ring
description: An earth elemental ring made from an amber jewel. The jewel has been made into a square shape and has a mask-like design.

name: Ragnell
description: The favored blade of the Hero of Blue Flame. Blessed by a goddess to be able to cut through any armor known to man, her plan backfired when it was used to kill her.

name: Flaming Herald
description: The legendary, emblematic shield that has been passed down through Archanean legend for generations.

name: Purple Shirt of Sex
description: The buttons have been sewn back on too many times to count, but it's more the fact that OHMYGOD ALL MY FAVORITE ACTORS WORE THIS that you care about.

name: Oscar
description: A small heavy gold man useful for bludgeoning people with. Other than that you're not sure what its purpose is. Maybe you could give it to Leonardo DiCaprio.

name: Revolution Pin
description: CAN YOU HEAR THE PEOPLE SING

name: Les Miz Headphones
description: You can hear the people sing now. They are too loud.

name: Psi-blade
description: It's a powerful weapon used by a highly advanced alien race. Excellent for slaying zerglings.

name: Psi Candy
description: A small piece of candy that seems to radiate a mysterious power. You're pretty sure that you'll be able to perform wondrous feats if you eat it.

name: Prescription Goggles
description: More protective than glasses, with the added bonus of being able to see! These prescription goggles will not break as easily as glasses.

name: Power Pole
description: A magical staff with the ability to grow or shrink to any length. If you wouldn't touch something with a 10 foot pole, try a 20 foot one!

name: Guardian Skaian Portal
description: Attacks thrown at you seem to vanish into the swirling Skaian portal on your shields surface. A negative player might blame themselves for adding to the destruction they escaped by entering, but you aren't so pessimistic, are you?

name: Pole  Frire
description: It can cook and flip; now you can have french toast ANYTIME.

name: Burnt Smut
description: Risen from the ashes, this beast will destroy any being with it's sassy moves. Also, it's good to hit things with, and it can cook a mean Pantycake.

name: Pepsi Perfect Bottle
description: A vitamin enriched bottle of Pepsi. At first glance you really aren't sure how to open this thing.

name: Legend of Marty: A Link to the Future
description: A video game rivaling the Legend of Zelda in quality, it stars time-traveling teen Marty McFly and his quest to fix the time stream by playing sweet demon-slaying tunes on his Master Guitar. A piece of gaming history that truly withstands the test of time.

name: Tony Hawk\'s Pro Skater 2 Disc
description: One of the best in the line of outdoor sports simulators. Why go skateboarding outside when you can play a video game and get the same experience, without the broken bones?

name: Pearl Pokeglasses
description: A pair of sunglasses with an iridiscent look to them. They allow the user to block strong light, as well as capture hundreds of cute creatures without using hands.

name: Mirror Portal
description: Have you ever wanted to jump inside a mirror and meet your reflection? Well now you can! ...the first part, at least. Whoever's on the other side probably won't be your reflection.

name: Chemical Firethrower
description: Chemical fire! Toxic Fire! Hazardous waste fire! In gun form! To throw the fire!

name: Steelix Cube
description: This hardened cube will cause great frustration as you taunt your enemies into attacking, and torment them by blocking all of their hits.

name: Rubik\'s Cubone
description: The more you fumble with this cube's different shades of off-white and brown, the more it makes you cry. You wish you had your mother around to help you with it.

name: Weighted Storage Cube
description: Hard to lug around, hard to befriend, hard to solve puzzles with. Whoever's putting you up to this can only be a cold, evil robot.

name: Bracelet
description: Makes you wash your wrist with excessive use.

name: Party Hat
description: Happy birthday to you. Hooray.

name: Kazoo
description: Bzz bzz bzz? Bzz!

name: ESC Key
description: Did you take this off of your keyboard? You do know that this means there is now no escape, right?

name: Fake Mustache
description: You can't help but wiggle your eyebrows with this on.

name: Wood Chipper
description: Disposes of logs and stiffs alike.

name: Electro-Homerun Machine
description: Reduces need for steroids. Powered by "steroid" brand batteries.

name: Surround Sound Sneakers
description: Your pumps are really pumpin' now!

name: Acid Syringe
description: Not so much acid more of whatever would fit. You're pretty sure that if this cheap syringe was filled with real acid, it would dissolve.

name: Angel\'s Dirge
description: A small golden harp surrounded by a white glow. The music it plays is distorted by hideous shrieks, as if a thousand damned souls were sent to torment the ears of your foes.

name: Book of Actual Mythology
description: Because just about anything could be considered Mythology these days, the application of an actually functional oracle lets you see past the fog of modern fiction and get right down to the brass tax of ancient gods and their shenanigans.

name: Atlas\'s World Hefters
description: Wrested from the now non-existent grasp of the actually mythologically significant Titan, these actual mythological artifacts could help anyone bare the weight of the world on their shoulders.

name: Masamune
description: Outrageously long blade used only by the most legendary of warriors. Use this to make a huge impact on the plot - specifically from above.

name: Munf Munf
description: Highly dubious-looking cereal. Supposedly turns you into a True Warrior, but rumors say people eating it sometimes aren't heard from in a month. "For Mah Boi's Dinner!"

name: Chained Sword Launcher
description: It's basically a harpoon gun that also doubles as a sword, now that the launched part is actually attached by a chain, making it easier to get back. In addition, all the violin strings are chains and it just feels stronger overall.

name: Chainmail Coat
description: A coat of sturdy chainmail. Cheap and easy to make, especially for the surprising amount of defense it gives. While knights may prefer flashy armor, warriors on the battlefield take whatever they can get to keep them alive.

name: Dragonslayer Greatbow
description: A steel greatbow used by the silver knights of Gwyn to hunt dragons and snipe those seeking to invade Anor Londo. The Bow fires spears as opposed to normal arrows in order to pierce the stone scales of the dragons. Inhuman strength is required to fully draw the bow, and it must be anchored in the ground to be fired.

name: MK7 Aquila Power Armor
description: This armor is so huge its impressive you even can wear it without being crushed. It has some great bonuses though.

name: Split Ends
description: With this, not even magic hair will stand a chance. It's pretty good against monsters, too.

name: Beowulf
description: A set of gloves of supposedly holy light. They seem to boost your speed a lot, too.

name: Brogresaw
description: THE weapon for adult male fans of the Shrek series who don't have a problem with a little brogre pride. You'll fight those gender roles by shrekking it out with this beast!

name: Chalk Stabber
description: You drilled holes into a staff and jabbed chalk into it. WTF. Either way, George and Harold would be proud of you.

name: Cheshire\'s Grin
description: A vile weapon once wielded by an ever-grinning figure. It inspires ruthlessness in whomever holds it.

name: Chocolate Lemon
description: A brown lemon oozing questionable-looking brown juice. So... does this count as a fruit or a sweet? Only one way to find out...

name: Candy Paintbrush
description: A paintbrush with a handle of hard candy and bristles made out of spun sugar. If it weren't for the gross bitterness of the paint you'd go through packs of these faster than a world-record-setting chain-smoker!

name: Chromatic-Coated Scythe
description: What are you even doing any more? A coat and scythe? Stop.

name: Chrono Trigger Cartridge
description: A classic Super Nintendo title of the ages starring a time traveling hero and his various odd friends. Now that you think about it, that sounds oddly similar to SBURB if it were a classic Nintendo game.

name: Cloak and Daggers
description: A real sneaky cloak for a real sneaky dude.

name: Code Lyoko Season 1-4 DVD Box Set
description: Best French anime in the history of paradox space. Keep away from quantum supercomputers.

name: Motorcycle
description: A two-wheel device with +25 to badassitude. Doesn't fly, unfortunately.

name: Legendary Infinite Popcorn
description: The sugar rush from this thing is uncannybrutal. Note: Not actually infinite.

name: Coin of Tempest
description: Perpetually wet coin with a swirly pattern. You suspect that this may be used as currency by mermaids.

name: Companion Cube
description: In times of loneliness, this cube will always be at your side. It can't speak and will never threaten to stab you. What more could you ask for in a friend?

name: Computer Scythe
description: Browsing the internet with this device will steal your enemies' souls instead of yours! A must-have for the modern teenage reaper.

name: Computing Goggles of Ultra Safety
description: In addition to protecting your eyes from all forseeable threats, these shaded goggles posess the remarkable ability to act as a computer. It would be remarkable anyway, if everything else didn't already do that.

name: Martial Hoodie of Training
description: This stylish blend of martial and stree arts acts as an effective training tool whilst still being remarkably comfortable and easy to wear.

name: Electric Nikoloar
description: Warning: Not intended for use as a traditional oar. The manufacturers of this product may not be held responsible for any electrocution that comes about as a result of the misuse of this weapon.

name: Alternating Current
description: An oar that is capable of sculling the river of time. It can feel the backward and forward flow of the universe.

name: Cosby Thong
description: A thong with Bill Cosby's smiling face on the front of it.

name: Snoop Dog Bust
description: "Well, hip-hop is what makes the world go around."

name: Solid Gold Pimp Robe
description: You thought you knew swag. You thought wrong.

name: Cosmos Cartographer
description: A detailed map of the stars beyond - or a black ball with some multicolored dots painted on it. You're not really sure.

name: Cosplay wings
description: A small set of white feathery wings worn for cosplay, or just for fun. Doesn't do much but weight you down, but still looks cool.

name: Shaggy Overcoat
description: A rather large overcoat that doesn't seem to fit very well at all.

name: Felt Duds
description: A felt-coloured tux. Rather bright, but will still make you look classy.

name: Fusion Exoskeleton
description: An orange and gold suit, fueled by incredibly long-lasting power cells. This suit augments your body's natural attributes, effectively making you stronger than a body builder and faster than an athlete. Host to dozens of in built systems and functions - essentially a second body.

name: Creepy Weepy Barrier Pin
description: This pin seems to summon an aura of unearthly flame, both for harming enemies and protecting yourself.

name: Ice Risers Pin
description: With but a swipe of your hand, this pin allows you to spear enemies from below with rising pillars of ice!

name: Nenekiri Pin
description: Rather than shooting random lasers out of your hands, this pin now lets you concentrate them into blades for slicin' and dicin'!

name: Cruxite Staff
description: Behold this scepter made from the very cruxite you used to alchemize it. Due to that, it's vaguely paradoxical. Holding it makes you feel a part of cruxite royalty and as though you'll fall through a hole in space-time at any moment.

name: Cube of Curiosity
description: A large cube made of many layers. The only way to find out what's inside the cube is to peel them all away. You figure the fastest way to do this is to bash it against enemies until it breaks, however long that may take.

name: Demon Razors of Dagon
description: These blades seem to constantly drip with blood, as If influenced by some otherworldly force. It's more disgusting than scary, though. You can barely fight with these things without your clothes getting soaked.

name: Disinfected Bandage
description: You think wrapping yourself with filthy cloth will magically heal you? Florence Nightingale would stab you with a (disinfected) scalpel for that.

name: Waifu Computer
description: Man this shit is so wrong on so many levels. This thing probably cant even work as a computer anymore, putting focus on what is or should be a crime...

name: Rainbow Sword
description: A sword flashing with myriad colors.

name: Temporal Parasocks
description: These socks tend to phase in and out of the timestream. You might find yourself wearing five pairs one minute, and the next, none at all!

name: Uncharged Godhand
description: An busted version of the Godhand. If only you had some way to charge it... It's still fairly powerful, though.

name: Steel Shieldpack
description: A handy item to have on the battlefield, this compact buckler can be used as a shield, but also doubles as a backpack to carry your spoils and cover your back while you make those "strategic retreats".

name: Dungeon Master\'s Scepter
description: A sleek black staff with a plastic orb on its tip, containing a d20. Can't rule a game without one.

name: Magic 20 Ball
description: A mystical ball of chance and power...hopefully.

name: Ring of Power
description: There is a dark power in this ring, drawing you to it. You want to put it on. Its so pretty...preciouss...

name: Power Armor Helm
description: Brotherhood of Steel ain't got shit on you.

name: Apocalypse Gambit
description: Cards this great are only meant to be weld by those with luck enough to pull exactly what they need exactly when they need it.

name: The One Quill
description: Forged in the fires of your alchemiter, this quill was once used by one of the greatest scribes of all time to pen a tale of short people and very dangerous magical jewelry. Keep it secret, keep it safe.

name: Candy Kit
description: A medkit that has been gutted of its medical supplies and filled with power restoring treats. A nice little lunchbox to carry with you while you beat up Ogres and Basilisks.

name: Tele-JoJo
description: Not only does this thing make an excellent weapon, looking into it results in seeing everything in the artstyle of Jojo's Bizarre Adventure. It also lets you see your enemy's Stand (if they have any)

name: Silver Chariot
description: Wielding it fills you with an urge to seek out a man with two right hands. Try to ignore the little suit of armor hanging from the pommel.

name: Weaponized Rocket Chair
description: A flying chair with a large machine gun mounted on the front for easy usage. Whether you got here from the rocket chair or machine gun, it's a huge improvement no matter what.

name: Throne
description: A simple stone throne that still manages to command respect from those around you. Or maybe they're kneeling because you just whacked them over the head with a throne.

name: Psi Shotgun
description: A shotgun that fires unstable candy buckshot with each shot. Even the people you shoot with it can't help but come back for more.

name: ZA WATCHUDO
description: After you turn the time-stop off, you REALLY want to ram a finger into your skull and shout "The strongest has arrived!" Try not to do that first one.

name: JoJo\'s Bizarre Adventure Vol. 6
description: No matter how untranslated it may be, anyone can appreciate the scantily clad men and bubbles.

name: LR\'s Fuck
description: How in the hell did you get ahold of one of these. He certainly didn't GIVE it to you.
credit: pops like five boners and runs into overseer memo

name: Psi Candy Stick
description: Stop eating your wand and get back to fighting.

name: Earthbound cartridge
description: Sadly, the guide and scratch-n-sniff stickers are nowhere to be found.

name: RoboVisor
description: A sturdy metal visor that covers most of the face. Wearing it both provides ample protection to the wearer and allows one to take advantage of the internal display, which what is in front of the mask and allows you to mess around on a computer while smashing imps.

name: Armor of Silver Chariot
description: If you were a stand, you wouldn't need to worry about crashing ever again. As it stands, this stuff is so lightweight you don't need to worry about that anyway.

name: Master Spark Broom Cannon
description: Enough magical power to level a mountain combined with the full force of the subterranean sun, all packaged at the end of a very, VERY magical stick: The perfect tool for someone who appreciates a sterile surface. You'll still never be able to kill more than 99.9 percent of germs, though.

name: Silent Hill 2
description: A copy of Silent Hill 2 for the Playstation. A classic.

name: Shockball
description: Basketball that delivers an electrifying shock when it collides viciously with your targets face.

name: Blessed Battlesplitters
description: One blade from the armies of darkness, and one from the armies of light. You can feel these blades infused with some divine power, leaving you to cast the final vote in the fight.

name: Bladed Yo-Yo
description: A yo-yo with blades extending from it. Be careful not to cut yourself.

name: Power cord
description: Plug it in! Increase the distance at which an appliance can be plugged in. You can also use it as a really long and awkward whip, if you're feeling creative.

name: Lawn mower
description: Keep that grass cut and your lawn will be the envy of the whole neighbourhood. Yeah you probably won't need this anymore.

name: Portable Electric Fan
description: Pretty handy for keeping cool. Not good for much else.

name: Power Pack
description: Provides power to electrical devices in lieu of an outlet. Will need to be recharged eventually.

name: Green Sun Slicer
description: A bright green yoyo fueled by an unknown but infinite power.

name: Metsamor MK9999
description: You've finally done it, you've surpassed mankind's greatest scientists and engineers by harnessing such a ludicrous amount of nuclear energy in a simple club. Despite the simple appearance of such a weapon you fear the cataclysmic results that would result from two of these meeting, you find yourself retching at the mere thought of it.

name: Black Staff / Green Scythe
description: With all the radiance of the Green Sun this is either going to reap space/time itself or kill you upon contact, possibly both.

name: Dress of Belts
description: In a world without pants, belts are used for dresses. Also in this world, it's popular with punks. How are they held together? More belts.

name: God Tier Pajama-Kit
description: For those envious of their God Tier friends, make your own faux pajamas! Seamstress not included.

name: Ballet Leotard
description: A plain pale blue leotard. Not recommended for males, lichs and Aperture Personality Cores.

name: Piercer of Heaven
description: A true bladesman sword. Just holding it straight up, you feel the immense energy flowing through it into your hands. Oh wait. That's lightning.

name: Pretty Pony Performer
description: It looks like a leotard...covered completely in horse prints? Perfect for those who like to leap through the sunset whinnying the delightful tunes of 'My Little Pony'.

name: Handsome Jack\'s Mask
description: You have a sudden urge to talk a lot of trash. While looking handsome of course.

name: Azurite Tower Shield
description: A large shield about as tall as you are, you can hardly lift it.

name: Morphball
description: A ball of armor that supposedly was supposed to have originally been a full-sized human. You're pretty sure that would hurt. Regardless, this is just a ball.

name: First Guardian of the Hoop
description: You're not sure if it's even possible to dribble this thing without burning your hand off. It makes a killer slam dunk though.

name: Spiked Ball
description: It's not that hard to pass, just make sure whoever's receiving it knows it's coming...

name: Magnoball
description: With all the strength of a magnet and a ball, this weapon had the total power of...a magnetic ball.

name: Angels Gridiron
description: Cleansed of Salmonella Impurities: return from over hard to over easy Scrambled Motherfuckers!

name: Toy Nuclear Power Station
description: The most fun a kid can ever have with science! just watch out for radiation poisoning!

name: Fukushima Tanko
description: Wearing this bad-ass set of armor would be very lethal to your health, but one extra arm can't be that bad.

name: Masterball
description: The most powerful pokeball. This is still not that powerful of a thing, in retrospect.

name: Lucky Golden Shades
description: You feel massive amounts of luck flowing into you as everyone still thinks you look gaudy.

name: Packaged Curaga
description: Who needs a White Mage when you can have all the benefits in a small, plastic wrapped, preservative-infused wrapper?

name: Uncle Dante\'s Pizza Pan
description: Filled with the strongest powers of Sparda; this pan can make the most badass pizza to ever hit your mouth.

name: Vergils Coat
description: Even the power hungry son of a god demon has to have some style.

name: Nectar of the Gods
description: This yellow drink shines with an inner light. It glows with power, and you know that it is meant for no less than a god.

name: AllSpark
description: More than meets the eye!

name: Model Airplane
description: A scaled-down replica of an airplane. Unlike an actual plane, it won't fly - even if the model kit said it could.

name: Propeller Beanie
description: Even though the hat has a propeller on it, you still can't fly. Running around making airplane noises doesn't help, and only serves to make you look like a dumbass.

name: Cherub Mask
description: This mask is a rather dark green with red dots on the cheek. When the dot is solid red, it fills you with anger for some reason.

name: Meteor\'s Fulcrum
description: A stout staff with a constellation design etched into it's side. With every swing of this weapon brief bursts of flame leap from the meteor shaped head.

name: Mehrunes Devilfucker
description: All the power of a Daedric god and hell itself in a gunblade.

name: Megaphone
description: You're sure to get SOMEONE'S attention with this thing. Or maybe give them ear ache.

name: Lumberjack\'s Little Helper
description: You've got this little hatchet, right? Except now the blade is motorized and also part saw. Just imagine that your enemies are some very unfortunate trees and LET 'ER RIP.

name: UNREAL hAIR
description: It is absolutely ridiculous what kind of hair this thing gets into.

name: Legend of Zelda: The Minish Cap
description: The 12th game in the Legend of Zelda series. The game takes a new spin on puzzle solving by letting you shrink down to microscopic sizes and explore the world through the eyes of a Minish!

name: The Four Sword
description: The Four Sword is a legendary sword that has the power to create three identical copies of its wielder's soul to aid him/her in combat and puzzle-solving.

name: Laser Back Hair Remover
description: A small handle that projects a 1 foot long red laser beam, that curves at the end. The unwise can use it to burn the hairs off their back. The wise will use it to slap some imps around.

name: Katniss\' Bow
description: The bow used by Katniss Everdeen in the hunger games. Never misses

name: Kanohi
description: This relic of your child/adulthood is imbued with the awesome powers your favorite plastic figures used to have. With this, you feel ready to battle the forces of darkness.

name: Zamor Launcher
description: A life-sized, working replica of one of Bionicle's many different kinds of launchers. It's even got the multi-shot attachment!

name: Midak Skyblaster
description: The Toa Phantoka's light-based shoulder cannons, now functional and human-sized! Except small enough to be a pistol.

name: Nuva Armor
description: The armor of the Toa Nuva, now life-sized. It looks like plastic, but it's pretty heavy and durable. You feel waves of nostalgia and silliness wearing this. Good thing nobody can see you.

name: Cordak Blaster
description: This life-sized hunk of metal looks just like the shitty revolving rubber-shooters the Toa Mahri used. Fortunately for you, it looks like it could actually deal some damage.

name: Disk Launcher
description: Ahh, the memories of days spent collecting those shitty glow-in-the-dark plastic disks that look virtually the same in every way except for three numbers at the bottom. Well, now they actually deal damage!

name: IVIII Rifle
description: A sleek black rifle with a chain strap. Its scope gives readouts on things like distance, wind pressure, ammo capacity, and most importantly, the time. Who gives a crap about that other stuff, anyway?

name: Prospit\'s Next Top Model poster
description: Boringest show EVER. Seasons only last one episode since the clouds always spoil who the winner is. Whose idea WAS this?

name: Derse\'s Next Top Model poster
description: Derse doesn't HAVE syndicated TV. You're pretty sure this is only a thing because they want to show up Prospit. Losers.

name: Improbably Large Hadron Collider
description: It'll kill your enemies, probably without killing you! Good luck lifting it.

name: Handheld Hadron Hurler
description: Only has a .05% chance of exploding when fired, causing reality as we know it to collapse into a black hole! Mind you, that's every single time it's fired.

name: Imperial Blade
description: A dark and royal scepter that can transform into a powerful sword. Perfect for looking regal and having a weapon on you at all times.

name: Highwayman\'s Cowl
description: A light, face-covering hooded cloak. While not necessarily stealthy, you certainly feel faster, stepping blows and slipping around defenses you might not have before.

name: Hell\'s Janitor
description: No wonder the place is always so messy. You can hardly sweep with something that's on fire.

name: Headstone Hammer
description: This hammer has gone from pounding nails into wood to pounding foes into the ground.

name: Hard-Light Headstone Hammer
description: The solid weight of a tombstone, the striking force of a hammer, and the flashy neat-o lightshow of the future.

name: Dark-Light Projector
description: It seems to just project a black rectangle. Something about how dark it is unsettles you, though.

name: Hard-Boiled Autorevolver
description: When you absolutely need to put six bullets in to something or someone as fast as possible, you will accept no substitute. Side effects include weapon jams, wasting ammo, and massive recoil. Suggested use with speed-loaders, because you will be reloading frequently.

name: Hard Light Realtime 3D Session Viewer
description: By watching the 3D projections in this model, you can see everything that happens in your session unfold before your eyes! Zoom in close enough and you can even see the tiny pixellated monsters...

name: Hale\'s Own Sword
description: A blade fit for only the best mercenaries!

name: Gurren Lance
description: The lance that will pierce the heavens!

name: Gunblade Scythe
description: Some kind of red scythe that also contains a functioning firearm. Light-weight, and folds up neatly into a box for easy access and storage.

name: Grim Angelic Lament
description: A dark harp glowing a sickly white. Its music is almost entirely composed of otherworldly shrieks, the angel's song from before twisted to a fallen angel's dying scream.

name: Green Sun Spade
description: You can't bring yourself to look directly at the cards that you draw from this deck. Best to aim away from face.

name: Greater BBQ Skewer
description: A spear with a claymore's blade crudely, but sturdily, melded to its pointy end. Great for keeping globs of Underling meat together as you slowly roast them over an open fire. Yum!

name: Chainsaw On A Stick
description: Popularly known as a pole saw. For the suckers/lumberjacks who don't know how to keep themselves from falling out of a tree as they attempt to cut its branches off with an ordinary chainsaw.

name: Grand Steel-Thorned Rose Fedora
description: The most epic of all rose-colored fedoras!

name: Grand Steel-Thorned Rose Shades
description: Oh yea!

name: Returning Prophecy
description: No matter how hard you try to throw it away it keeps coming back.

name: Morning Star
description: A shiny metal club with a ball on the end covered in spikes.

name: Mythical Trickster\'s Glowing Green Toy
description: You have picked up a tricksters ultimate weapon. Glowing green and imbued with the power of a Sun.

name: Grand Rose Steel Thong of Crosby Thorns
description: This impenetrable string of steel offers unparalleled protection for your family jewels. Bill Cosby's grinning visage graces its front, benevolently shielding your loins with a gray mystical aura.

name: Touhou Fortress 2 Disc
description: This game is either about murdering the other team with ridiculous amounts of bullets or about wearing as outlandish hats as possible. You honestly aren't entirely sure.

name: Golf Trophy
description: Got feelings? Bludgeon a bloke to death with this! Recommended by 2 out of 2 snipers!

name: Golden Sword
description: Although the metal is soft enough that it won't really hold an edge, it's still heavy enough to make a decent bludgeoning tool. Said to be especially susceptible to enchantments.

name: Rose-Tinted Shades
description: Guaranteed to cheer up even the most die-hard of pessimists.

name: Prism
description: A triangular piece of glass that splits light into its constituent wavelengths through the miracle of dispersion.

name: Newton\'s Lament
description: Using an arrangement of approximately twice as many lenses, mirrors, and prisms as your average optics lab, the beams from the five orbiting emitters are combined and amplified to ridiculous intensities. A team of physicists could spend weeks trying to trace the paths of the light rays.

name: Fruit Gushers - Maestro\'s Musical Madness Watermelon flavor
description: Maestro's Musical Madness Watermelon flavored Fruit Gushers. Guaranteed to temporarily turn even the most hopelessly tone-deaf into the next Mozart, according to the text on the back of the box.

name: Hearts Boxcars Spirited Horse Poster
description: Farmin' all these goddamn horses. Fuckin' pain in the ass.

name: Magical Reactor
description: A small wooden octagon with trigrams carved into the sides, capable of emitting immense amounts of magical energy. Among other things, useful for cooking and firing giant rainbow-coloured lasers fuelled by the power of love.

name: Godhand
description: The ultimate fist. This thing completely replaces your arm, but you can't use your other arm for anything due to how much power it takes to use.

name: Smoke Pellets
description: When broken, these small pellets release a preposterous amount of smoke. A valuable tool for an aspiring escape artist!

name: Gallantmon\'s Lance
description: The right arm of Gallantmon, of the Royal Knights. It is refined and constructed from 99.9% pure Chrome Digizoid, and is also known as the holy lance "Gram" in the digital world. Feel like the Exalted Knight you are with this in hand.

name: Filthy Wifebeater
description: I got a present for you, Casey. It's a little dirty. A LITTLE ROUGH AROUND THE EDGES JUST LIKE YOUR DEAR OLD EX CON DAD WITH A HEART OF GOLD

name: Feltputer
description: This computer comes in a round shape, is green, and in keeping with Felt theming, has Die's number on the top of the lid.

name: Deck of Personas
description: This stylish deck of tarot cards featured in SMT: Persona 4 are quite the treasure, but something is missing...

name: Wooden Art Posing Mannequin
description: A wood posing mannequin mainly used for artists to have a basis for a person in their portraits. Thanks to alchemization, it can be anything else you want it to be!

name: Fancy Doll
description: This faceless doll has been dressed to the nines in fancy (male) clothing: a monocle, a top hat, a snazzy suit, and even tiny suede shoes. How novel!

name: Encyclopedia of Generic Items in Stories
description: A hulking gray tome, it lists many different items, cliches, and tropes used in multiple works of fiction. Perhaps you could mix it up to read something else?

name: Codec
description: This receiver is small enough to fit in your ear canal. There is a potential to make one that can be implanted in your head, but it'll be a while before that.

name: Boombox w/ Detachable Speakers
description: This large stereo can handle any music or antagonistic creature you throw at it, provided it's either on CD or cassette.

name: Fedora of the Chosen Arbiter
description: This snazzy hat once rest atop the head of a legendarily charismatic warrior. It is a fedora of unparalleled style and defense.

name: Masamune Textridaggers
description: The best just got better. It took hours of sidequesting to get these, but now you're set for the rest of the game.

name: Smoke Thrower
description: All it does is blow slightly toxic smoke in your targets' faces. The clever strifer might make some pretty good use out of it though.

name: Fairy statue
description: Isn't it just adorable? A pretty little stone-face expressing purity.

name: Antique Sword
description: Can anything compare to the grace and beauty of the neatly detailed golden handle? Could one imagine what the blade has been through, during the past 400 years. Imagine all the heroic brutes and their sweating hands holding it, perhaps once held by a king. It shall lead to victory!

name: Eryx
description: Gnarled gloves of a demonic origin, wrapping themselves firmly around the user's arms, they course with an incredible power that easily offset their weight.

name: Epic Dragon Outfit
description: Combined with working wings and a fluffy tail, this outfit makes you pretty much both the deadliest and most adorable thing on Skaia.

name: Electromagnet Key
description: This is just a key with a bunch of wires wrapped around the blade, hooked up to a battery. At least it should electrocute anyone that you stab with it.

name: Duality Fan
description: A fan with a lovely red and blue theme. Any light that shines through it turns red, blue, or purple! Also works as an emergency replacement for normal 3D glasses.

name: Dual Meat Slicing Blades
description: Two sharp butcher knives excellent for cutting enemies' flesh.

name: Triforce T-Shirt
description: This white t-shirt simply holds the most powerful insignia in game history. Well, it doesn't do anything really. Just a white shirt with three black triangles.

name: Droid Headset
description: Bzzzzt

name: Dragons\' Dogma CD
description: Fly into free with this fantasy game about being a bad enough dude to get your heart back that was kidnapped by a DRAGON!

name: Chain Lightning Separator
description: The Separator, now with an axe treatment of pure lightning awesome, but I wouldn't swing this in the rain, you don't even know if it's properly grounded.

name: Blade of Ormagden
description: Ormagden's gift to the First Ones, you can feel the Cremator of the Sky guiding you as you send this blade cleaving through your enemies in the name of METAL!

name: The Pimperor
description: This pistol is studded with gold and diamonds, and you can swear whatever it is, shouting out "WHERE'S MY MONEY!?" makes it appear in your right hand, instantly.

name: Dragon Armor
description: Steel armor stylized to resemble a dragon. Very warm.

name: Dragonrend
description: A book filled with powerful shouting magic from a lost era. Too bad you can't use any of them.

name: Amulet of Talos
description: An amulet made for the worship of a lost god from lost times. Makes you feel like shouting.

name: Dragon Jetsuit
description: Your dreams of flying around as a dragon have finally come true. Well, sort-of.

name: Saigyouji Fan
description: A massive fan famous for being used by Yuyuko Saigjouyi. Holds great power, but is incredibly unwieldy due to it being a giant fan.

name: Dr. Mobius\'s Screwdriver
description: Dr. Mobius designed this powerful device after his somewhat scattered, yet brilliant, mind lead him into some rather dangerous situations.

name: Golden Power Armor
description: An armor that allows you to be gaudy and look terrible without consequently getting torn apart by Acherons.

name: Doctor Who Poster
description: A poster depicting a British television show about a man who travels through time in a blue phone box. It's much better than it sounds.

name: Dark Arts
description: Fluxuates with the dark energy of the Deep One. Also has a slim handle for easy maneuverability.

name: Common Plastic Sword
description: Oh, great. One of THESE things, the swords that were in practically every BIONICLE set from 2006 onwards. Except this one's 5 feet long. What are you meant to do with this?

name: The Felt Tip
description: A multicolored pool cue, with markers on either end. It's incredibly inconvenient to write with, and the tips aren't solid enough to shoot a pool ball, but at least it makes a decent weapon, which is why you alchemized it in the first place! Right...?

name: Fairly Large Drawing Board
description: This big drawing board doesn't really boast any special powers, other than the fact that you could probably knock someone with it.

name: Chain of Memories
description: Looking at this chain brings back so many memories. Like the memory of alchemizing this chain. Good times.

name: Lance, now with Aim Assist(TM)
description: There is a small laser pointer jutting out of the bottom of the lance, making it easier to aim at people to poke.

name: Dragonplate Helmet
description: Here's your helm, you're overwhelmed, and when you wear it you want to yell... FUS ROH DAH!

name: Gurren Lagann DVD
description: Several episodes of the well-known anime Tengen Toppa Gurren Lagann.

name: Escavalance
description: A red-striped steel lance. It's kind of small and simple, almost as if it could have been used by some kind of giant insect cavalry.

name: Oversized Combat Screw
description: A giant screw with a handle. It's probably pretty dangerous. Yep, those imps are... what's the word? Oh yeah. Fucked.

name: Rocket Lance
description: A flashy red lance with flame detailing and wings, powered by a rocket. There is no way this could go wrong.

name: Kuroko no Basuke DVD set
description: Handsome men playing handsome basketball! Rimfire!

name: Konami Code
description: Up, up, down, down, left, right, left, right, B, A, start. Oh yeah, you know this like the back of your hand. And it's always managed to come in handy before, so ...

name: Skrillet
description: The skrillet of Skrillex! This tricked-out diamond pan is the ultimate in dubstep technology: bright lights and sick beats emanate from the surface of the pan! Drop the bass on someone's face, or decapitate your enemies: jagged CD razors whir around its circular exterior like sharp, toothy propellers. Throw it at your foe! Watch as it veers through the air at breakneck speeds, tears through their jugular, and flies back to your palm like a proper Bangarang should!

name: Kanohi Gasmask
description: This Bionicle-themed gasmask, despite having a Kanohi design, doesn't give you any special powers.

name: Kato Mask
description: A stylish mask of the domino family that makes you feel energized, in control, and like the invisible sidekick of an old timey D-list superhero.

name: Hood\'s Coif
description: With a warm, trim neck and a mysterious hood, this nigh-magical garment seems to draw attention away from the wearer. Even your reflection is too boring to focus on.

name: LR\'s Pantsu
description: for all of you fans of leviathansReignmaster out there. You now have something to remember him by. ;3

name: Thrower of the Back Wind
description: This noxious gas-spewer is silent, but deadly.

name: Very Red Faygo
description: Drinking too much of this might make you see red.

name: Very Blue Faygo
description: You can drink this until you're blue in the face.

name: Clown Shoes
description: Hilariously long shoes that squeak and honk with every step. It's bound to drive the listener mad. And the wearer.

name: Shoe Horn
description: A slim piece of metal, used by distinguished gentlemen to slip into their loafers more easily.

name: 4-Dimensional Rubik\'s Cube
description: Okay, this is just bullshit.

name: Retro Arcade Machine
description: Aha! Through clever alchemy, you have managed to salvage a valuable piece of gaming history. Now if only you could figure out how to get your quarters back out of it...

name: Wreck-it Ralph DVD
description: Finally, a movie about video games that doesn't suck!

name: Golden Hammer of Fixing
description: A golden, magic hammer. It can repair just about anything back to its former glory in a single hit. Unfortunately, it doesn't seem to be capable of dealing actual damage.

name: Mammoth Fists of Wrecking
description: Huge gauntlets that seem imbued with a deep lust to smash and destroy. But remember, even though your every punch wreaks destruction, it doesn't make you a bad guy.

name: Sonic Space-time Rift Opener
description: With this sonic portal device, you are no longer constrained by the boundaries of time and space. You can create portals anywhen and anywhere you want!

name: Void Reacher
description: A darkened backscratcher capable of reaching between dimensions to reclaim things that have slipped between the cracks of reality. It can also scratch your friend's backs from halfway across the universe.

name: Sadfeguie\'s Scratcher
description: An orange-and-black backscratcher with a thick head and a gigantic W on the back. This thing seems to glitch out with every hit, transporting you and the target a few feet in a random direction.

name: Free Blimp Ride For 3
description: Who am I going to take...<iframe width="1" height="1" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/PQ-mdBbU8KE?autoplay=1" frameborder=false></iframe>
credit: Ben (cuspalArirus) (has a hot butt hot wow)

name: Giant Electric Pinwheel
description: Mostly a novelty, although it certainly looks intimidating.

name: Storm Spirit
description: Like a leaf blower only this thing could actually do some damage. Avoid using in tight spaces, unless you really want to.

name: Captain\'s Haori
description: Only those with power and rank worthy enough may wear this garment. It's a good thing you're your own boss.

name: Magic Staff of Chaos and Chance
description: This powerful staff could either make a spark or destroy a city.

name: Celestial Nectar
description: This golden liquid shines with the light of stars and glows with godly power. It seems practically ethereal.

name: Ancient Bo-Staff
description: A well-worn but sturdy staff dating from Ancient China, this is one armament that stood the test of time.

name: Almost-Fashionable Blazer
description: Conventional and attractively black on the outside, the inside of this blazer is victim to the Black Queen's silly colour regiment. The buttons are just as garish. Hardly name-brand stuff, but at least it's comfy.

name: 110011101 Rifle
description: A technological upgrade to the IVIII Rifle that gives its scope an advanced readout, allowing for more precise shots. You can play Snake on it, too.

name: Zoroastrian Bacon N Eggs
description: With a bit of olive oil, this thing can cook up some mad calamari, a must have for any professional wizard.

name: Rainbow Rucksack
description: What magic could you find inside this cray-cray sack of color!?!

name: Wicked Comestible of the Juggalo Juggernaut
description: This pie is a manifestation of all things Circus. The flavor is like that of newly-roasted juggler flesh, and the taste presents the brutal violence, the invulnerability and the raw vitality that is inherent to all clowns. On the other hand, you feel like eating it will subject you to the wrath reserved by the universe for all irritating jesters. Really a toss-up here.

name: Faygo - Crazy Citric Atomic Detonator flavor
description: When life gives you lemons, brew them into this. Then throw it at life and watch it explode in life's lousy, stupid anthropomorphized face.

name: Welder\'s Sword
description: A strong, thin blade coated in concentrated flames. The blade glows a bright yellow under the orange fire. Could be used to cut through solid steel, given enough time and patience.

name: Tough as Nails Gloves
description: So you've fought with the rest, and the rest are actually pretty strong. This glove, complete with nails poking out of the knuckles, are sure to give you an edge! (It can also give the enemy tetanus.)

name: The Everyman\'s Guide to Halloween
description: For turning dead imps into delightful decorations! Now in hardback.

name: Tesla Pointer
description: A tesla coil in a laser pointer. When you normally press the button for the laser, the laser comes out.

name: Bandito Tecnologico
description: For the modern robber that likes to update on social networks while breaking into the hip new hotspots.

name: Serious Business Goggles
description: A pretty nice hands-free communication solution that looks a bit like the sort of gadget you might see in one of those movies about kids that are spies.

name: Sword-Chucks
description: This is probably the most useless item ever made. It harms your opponent as much as it harms you. However, if you can somehow just... sort of... wield it...

name: Spiral Cape of the Cosmos
description: Why pierce the heavens when you can wear them instead?

name: One-Winged Coat of Angels
description: This coat instills feelings of great evil, as well as hatred for gigantic swords and people who wield them.

name: Scythe of the GLADITORIAN
description: This blade was forged on the bedroom floor of a child, it's power forged in the flames of imagination. They must've built quite the epic fort for this one.

name: Scrifle
description: This high-powered rifle fires screws and at high velocity, too. The barrel also conveniently spins the screws in a way, that makes them bore into whatever material you are aiming at, be it wood, metal or Imp.

name: Scarf
description: Makes you feel much cooler. Even though it's actually keeping you warm.

name: Suzuka Gongreaves
description: Even these powerful greaves can't help your cooking, but they do help with whooping some ass!

name: Jumbo Pincushion
description: Bludgeon your enemies to death while you make one mean sweater.

name: Santa Crusher
description: Santa has come and visited all the little boys and girls and given them presents. Except for you. Teach that all powerful fat man a lesson with this slingshot and force some idiot to save Christmas.

name: Blackjackknives
description: Normal playing cards with razor sharp edges made of, guess what, knife blades!

name: Legend of Zelda: Majora\'s Mask Cartridge
description: The 6th game in the Zelda series, it's unique among the games due to its 3-day time system. Majora's Mask is one of the few Zelda games that does not focus on Ganon and Princess Zelda.

name: Majora\'s Mask
description: The mask is an ancient artifact that was used by an ancient tribe for its bewitching rituals, but the mask's wicked power became so great that it was sealed away to prevent a great catastrophe. "You've met with a terrible fate, haven't you?"

name: Amythrister
description: This backscratcher is embodied with a purple, otherworldly light, such that it could be mistaken for a cool futuristic beam weapon... at a distance... if you squint a little.

name: Mirthful Messiah Chucklecutter
description: Enbued with the lighter side of some powerful ass chuckle voodoos, you can't help but feel a sinister air to it, like it has a plan eons in the making.

name: Mirthful Messiah Punishcutter
description: This item reeks of powerful chuckle voodoos, as they worm their way into your head and tell you to do HORRIBLE THINGS. Thankfully you can tide them over by brutally murdering underlings, but...

name: Aperture Science Handheld Hewing Device
description: The intra-dimensional slices of this hyper-technical axe can carve portals into nearly any surface, including imp carapace. Whatever you do, though, don't touch the ball of energy on the end. Trust me on this one.

name: Aperture Science Paper-Separators
description: Disclaimer: Many cuts were made in the making of this device, including but not limited to: budget cuts, safety cuts, performance cuts, and corner cuts.

name: Ball of Infinity
description: Hidden within this unseen domain is all that has and all that ever will exist. Too bad you can't look at it without dying.

name: Black Mesa Glasses
description: Now you can protect your eyes from nuclear meltdowns, alien attacks, and strange visions from G-Men.

name: Blade Gloves
description: A pair of fingerless gloves, each one fitted with a large blade running parallel with the arm. Somewhat awkward to use offensively, but they're fairly effective at blocking.

name: Blazing Star
description: A magical wooden rocket pack propelled by a massive rainbow laser, with the added benefit (?) of vaporizing just about everything behind you at takeoff. Braking might be slightly problematic, though. As might steering.

name: Master\'s Sparkdriver
description: Why would you ever need to loosen a screw when you can vaporize it (and a large chunk of the surrounding material) instead?

name: Orbital Circumscriber
description: Etch circles around (and through) your enemies from space! Laser satellites are always the best kind of geometry tools.

name: Fruit Gushers - Apocalyptic Apple Detonation flavor
description: Apocalyptic Apple Detonation flavoured Fruit Gushers. A new experimental flavour that literally explodes in your mouth! ...yeah, you probably shouldn't try eating these yourself.

name: Fruit Gushers - Skaian Strawberry Symphony flavor
description: Skaian Strawberry Symphony flavoured Fruit Gushers. Get in touch with your aspect through the powers of candy and music!

name: Deity\'s Die
description: At first glance, it simply looks like a plain white sphere about two meters in diameter, but closer examination reveals it to be a gigantic die with more sides than you could ever count. Its rolls are said to influence all the events in the universe, but now that you're in the Medium instead its main use is flattening smaller foes with its sheer size.

name: Prospit d12
description: A golden twelve-sided die favored by the carapacians of the Kingdom of Light. Useful for determining how nerdy you are on a scale from 1 to 12.

name: Derse d12
description: An amethyst die featuring twelve faces, each depicted with a unique and tawdry illustration of a group of ebony carapacians. The Kingdom of Darkness must really not care about it that much to let it into circulation.

name: ? Block
description: What could possibly be inside? Hit it to find out!

name: Swimsuit
description: A plain one-piece swimsuit. Maybe one of the Lands in your session has a nice beach you can relax on in between beating up imps?

name: Armoured Swimsuit
description: A swimsuit made entirely out of plate mail. Too heavy for swimming in, and not all that useful as armour since it doesn't protect your arms or legs: in short, not all that useful. At least it doesn't encumber your attacks that much...

name: Bobobo-Bo Bo-Bobo Staff
description: A slender, black bo staff with a yellow orb on the end of it. It's slightly flexible and causes mild disorientation when used to whack things. For both the user and the target, that is.

name: Plain Panties
description: At least they won't get raided with you wearing them... right?

name: Belgarath
description: Purple silk panties with white lace. The name "Belgarath" is written inside. They seem incredibly dark and ominous for some reason, but you've taken a liking to them.

name: Born To Rock
description: It's uncanny, it's like you were destined to wield this silver guitar. That doesn't mean you know how to play it though. Still, it's heavy enough to swing around like an idiot.

name: Nostalgia Goggles
description: Everything from your childhood was way better and these glasses let you see everything like it's 1999. The power of remembering your childhood also makes you immune to arguments, er, I mean it reduces physical damage.

name: Color Sword
description: A sword that colors. Paint not included.

name: Crease Reaper
description: All Creases need to go to the afterlife someday.

name: Sovereign Sceptersword
description: With this sleek, dark scepter that transforms into an immensely powerful blade that can shoot bullets, its no wonder your friends will envy you as you slice, dice, bash, slash, and shoot your way through to victory.

name: Flaregun
description: Good for signaling your friends, but unreliable in combat.

name: The Tree
description: A thick, otherworldly, oak-like tree, several sizes larger than any tree save for a redwood has any right to be. The cracks in the bark, itself resembling stone more than wood, glow a faint yellow-gold and pulse with power. Touching it draws blood painfully, though no skin is split. You're struck with a sense of majesty and awe but that's all pretty difficult to discern since it kinda mostly just creeps you the hell out.

name: Glowing Sap
description: Golden sap from an ancient, powerful tree. It makes you nervous somehow.

name: MK8 Errant Power Armor
description: An upgraded version of the previous power armor. It also works as a sign of rank.

name: Miniature Candy Factory
description: When turned on, this nifty contraption will begin to spew out copious amounts of Psi Candy into the gaping mouth of whoever is holding it, and probably at several other things. It's too bad it breaks after a minute or so from the sheer amount of power it uses.

name: Sevith\'s Portrait
description: Where'd this thing come from? It's not even supposed to be here, but that is one good looking mugshot.

name: Sevith\'s Autographed Portait
description: Nothing ups a picture's value quite like a celebrity(?) autograph. Next stop, gristBay!

name: Mr.Dr.Prof. English
description: You're not a doctor or a professor, but you do have this colorful scythe. You wouldn't be able to treat patients with this, anyway. Stop trying to be a doctor, that shit is illegal.

name: Ghost Metal Visor
description: The sheer practicality of this nifty facewear is well worth the occasional ghost murmurs donning it causes.

name: SkullVisor
description: For the adventurer that likes to think he looks threatening to the horrible monsters.

name: DollVisor
description: If you stay away from mirrors you may be able to forget how creepy this makes you look.

name: Perfect MaidVisor
description: This specially built RoboVisor comes not only with improved aesthetics, but the capability to lightly manipulate time with its internal clock.

name: Skaian Defense Chair
description: This rocket chair comes equipped with a modified Skaianet Defense Portal Gun capable of shooting meteors at a rate of 10 per minute. It also hurts to be hit over the head with, if you're that kind of person.

name: Derse Throne
description: It really doesn't surprise you that even their thrones have been optimized for damage output.

name: Invisible Armor
description: Basically regular armor, but invisible. At least there's an advantage in having your enemies not realize there is a plate of steel between you and them, you guess.

name: Betty Crocker Psi Bomb
description: A small bomb that damages everything around it with a mysterious power. When it goes off, it's almost as though you can feel some of your strength seeping back into you.

name: Jeweled Branch of Hourai
description: A magical branch with what looks like jewel bobbles growing out of it. You aren't entirely sure that you should be able to have this.

name: Meteo Hammer
description: An ancient Chinese weapon that is quite similar to a yo-yo. If you build up enough speed with the two weights on opposite sides of the chain, it can be quite deadly.

name: Magick Buckler
description: This shield is said to channel magicks throughout the metal on the face of it, plus it packs a pretty good whallop and has a "k" on magic, making it completely different from actual magic!

name: Dragons\' Dogma
description: An exquisite blade made by, and for, destroying dragons, too bad they don't really exist. This thing still brims with magicks used to completely decimate.

name: Dwells-In-Light
description: This-Blade-Is-Really-Bright. Ow, your eyes.

name: Force Hatchet
description: No, not like Star-Wars, you dork, this axe is said to be able to build up strength with each successful strike. That's probably not true, but damn if this thing doesn't look wicked!

name: Magic Dual Knifes
description: Two knives with special magical properties. Great for duel wielding and ranged attacks.

name: Laser Eyeglasses
description: Now you can live out your dream of shooting laser beams from your eyes! ...well, not directly from your eyes of course, but it's the same basic effect.

name: Lady Justice vs. Stheno vol. 1
description: A new and extremely under the radar comic book about a blind woman turned hero and an alien scorpion lady who both have depressingly tragic lives. The latest and greatest of the mediocre world of Charm Productions. No seriously, what is this piece of shit?

name: Universal Cosmic Inferno Pin
description: The Universal Cosmic Destroyer, Giegue left this in his absence. Whomever wields it is destined to cleave universes.

name: Adroit Lacerator
description: There is no escape. No, literally, we stole it for our twisted experiments. The result is an axe that makes your enemies wish they could abscond. Unfortunately, there is no commands for Imps.

name: Atom Smasher
description: One missed swing, one wayward twitch, and KABLEWY! So be careful.

name: Coin Block
description: Whenever you hit someone over the head with it, a coin pops out! What a pity that all kinds of currency that aren't boondollars are mostly useless in the medium.

name: Invisible Coin Block
description: In some mysterious way this thing always tends to be right in the path of your opponent. You have a feeling that having this used against you would be seriously annoying.

name: Crescending Roar
description: A mace, the electricity on this thing crackles near the air around it, sure to give your foes a nasty shock.

name: Totem Mace
description: A double-headed mace said to reflect two holy fists of a particularly righteous God, the magicks in this thing are pretty dang bright to boot.

name: Obliteratrix
description: The name of this should be warning enough that whatever is in your way is about to be wrecked in all senses of the word.

name: Deathwing Cosplay
description: All will burn beneath the shadow of your wings! Not really, but this Deathwing the Destroyer costume certainly makes you feel ready to bring destruction upon your foes.

name: Diablo
description: A stuffed raven familiar with a heart as black as its feathers. You guess you could learn to deal with having this feathered fiend as a companion... Until some fairy decides to show up and turn it to stone. Who even does a thing like that?

name: Dresden Files RPG
description: Based on the series by Jim Butcher. Now you too can enjoy having everything in this world and the next trying to eat your face off!

name: Dice of FATE
description: Supposedly made out of fudge...

name: Pyramidic Head Chopper
description: sssscccccrrrrraaaaaaaaaappppppeeeee... sssscccccrrrrraaaaaaaaaappppppeeeee... sssscccccrrrrraaaaaaaaaappppppeeeee...

name: Pyramidic Impaler
description: Her death is on your head...

name: Faygo - Rusted Otherworldly Discovery flavour
description: Gets your motherfuckin understand on. This blast from the past will remind you of what's important.

name: Pyramid\'s Head
description: Looks heavy. And painful. Are you supposed to wear this?

name: Brookhaven Syringe
description: You don't want to know what that liquid is...

name: Ten Ton Blade
description: You CAN'T be expected to wield this. You wouldn't even be able to lift it!

name: Air Horn
description: Loud enough to temporarily deafen something.

name: Dungeons and Dragons 4e book set
description: Books holding vast power and knowledge of an entire universe! Also good for role playing games with friends.

name: Scepter of the God of Fates
description: The staff wielded by he who commands the hand of fate. Will you defeat the beast? Or wi-"Rocks fall. Everyone dies."

name: Scepter of the Random Number Gods
description: The random number gods shall determine your fate. And with this scepter they perform that duty. But now the scepter falls to you. What will happen now?

name: Electric Boomaloo
description: Too bad "batterang" sounds too much like "batarang". This is the second best name.

name: Excelsior!
description: A marvelous yet comically large blade usable only by true believers. 'Nuff said.

name: Punch Dimension Hopper
description: This giant red axe can slice a hole into the punch dimension, unleashing a torrent of punches at your foes.

name: D&D: The Complete Animated Series
description: There is no escape. For you have entered the realm of Dungeons and Dragons!

name: Hank\'s Magic Bow
description: A ranger's bow imbued with the magical ability to be incredibly useful in any circumstance.

name: Eric\'s Magic Shield
description: A cavalier's shield imbued with the magical ability to not give a fuck.

name: Diana\'s Magic Staff
description: An acrobat's staff imbued with the magical ability to pole-vault the user over and/or near enemies.

name: Bobby\'s Magic Club
description: A barbarian's club imbued with the magical ability to hit the ground with godlike strength.

name: Presto\'s Magic Hat
description: A magician's hat imbued with the magical ability to be incredibly useless in any circumstance.

name: Cloak
description: It's like a cape! But with a hood!

name: Sheila\'s Magic Cloak
description: A thief's cloak imbued with the magical ability to turn the user invisible just long enough to cause embarrassing situations.

name: Droid Razr Maxx
description: It's like the regular model, except the battery isn't absolute garbage anymore.

name: Extra Sharp Black Drawing Pen
description: A pen that is used to draw things with amazing detail. It can also be used to stab people with amazing detail.

name: Fate/Extra Disc
description: A video game about a certain Holy Grail War taking place within a digitized world. Does not contain jackhammers or mollusks.

name: Aestus Estus
description: The ultimate instrument whose sound the Muses praise. Unfortunately, the former wielder and player wasn't very good.

name: Fire Starter
description: Well, that's great. It's a yoyo. That occasionally sets things on fire.

name: Good Ol\' Fashioned Scissoring
description: Yes the lesbian kind.<iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/gn7GG4UO2-g?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: Glowsticks
description: Make everyday feel like a rave. All you need is darkness, glowsticks, and music<iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/biAwoUAiOQ0?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: Jaws of the Leviathan
description: || Let loose the /reigns/ of you /chaotic/ beast and let him /rampage/ freely.<iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/aX4LaK22Jdw?autoplay=1"></iframe> ||

name: Circle Carver
description: Four deadly blades, whirling at high speed at the end of a sturdy pole. Makes a great salad, but use with caution.

name: Nuclear Wind Turbine
description: This doesn't even make sense. What are you going to do with such an impossibly huge item?

name: Typhon\'s Breath
description: Named for the father of all monsters. Rev it up and let havoc spew forth against any enemies or buildings unlucky enough to stand in your way.

name: Miniature Air Man
description: Based on the boss from Mega Man 2. Doesn't appear to be fully sentient but follows simple instructions. Can also create tiny tornadoes.

name: "Please Shut Up" Flashy Skull Sceptre
description: Please.

name: Armor of the Green Sun
description: A lot like the armor of the sun, but this glows bright green. Just by wearing you feel an immense power flowing through your arms. Or it could be radiation poisoning.

name: Blood Moon Crescent Scythe
description: A perfect crescent blade in resemblance of the crescent moon. A normal hard steel blade with two blades on the scythe to represent both the lunar and solar eclipses, it separates into two smaller sickles in the middle of the staff.

name: Crucifix Shotgun
description: A shotgun in the shape of a cross. Fires blessed buckshot into all non-believers.

name: Fabulous Dersetop
description: With this purple, moon-emblemed headset, you can play all kinds of online games without losing your aura of fashion!

name: Fencer\'s Cuirass
description: A cuirass designed for a fencer. It looks like it's from the 16th century, how did you get your hands on it?

name: Flail-Saw
description: A flail covered not in spikes, but in saws. The underlings would be in awe at this abomination, were they not fleeing.

name: Flamemasher
description: So much heat energy packed into such a small hammer. Don't try to mash flames with it though. It will only make them bigger.

name: Flute
description: Flutes are highly effective to damage opponent's ears. Or you can just smash their heads in with the metal tubing.

name: Giegueklusmos
description: It seems to just be a pen. Touching the ink causes you to feel immense pain though. You cannot grasp the true reason for this.

name: [K] Season 1 Disc
description: Collection of the anime [K] on one disc.

name: GLaDOS Computer
description: It's the murderous AI herself, GLaDOS! Quick, put her away before she... oh, wait, it's just a computer that just so happens to be shaped like GLaDOS. And occasionally voices quotes from Portal. And draws ASCII art of cakes while you're not looking.

name: Gloves of the Ultimate Science
description: Who says science can't be fun yet deadly? These powerful gloves send a shock to your enemies, making use of the many wonders of electricity! You might want to wear some other glove underneath them though, for insulation.

name: Freezie
description: A frozen, syrupy treat in a large plastic package that is ALWAYS going to cut your mouth with its sharp sides. Maybe be worth hitting things with.

name: Cooler
description: A cooler filled to the brim with the delights of your choice... assuming the "delights of your choice" cost about 20$ or less. It might be worth smacking an imp with it.

name: Thermos
description: A thermos that has been filled with coffee at some point prior to you possessing it (hopefully not too long ago, though). Throwing it at something is at least somewhat viable.

name: Golad, Twilight of Aspects
description: One of a pair of legendary daggers known as 'The fangs of the father'. Incredibly powerful, made from black, jagged metal and pulsing with molten energy. The blade is dangerously hot to the touch, and holds a disturbing, moving eye.

name: Tiriosh, Nightmare of Ages
description: One of the pair of daggers known as the 'Fangs of the father'. It feels as if it is full of unbridled hate, and rage. Staring at the hate it holds, set against its black metal makes you want to destroy something, and with this weapon, you could easily do so.

name: Grenade Launcher
description: A device used to propel a grenade at your foes. Long-range explosions have never been so easy!

name: Halloween Prop Crow
description: A passable imitation crow, the likes of which tends to appear on certain porches around Halloween. Upon close inspection you are able to determine that it is not alive, never has been, and never will be.

name: Dragon\'s Dogma Chess Set
description: A very odd version of chess, in which you command a veritable legion of pawns against a single piece representing a dragon.

name: Journal
description: A plain and serviceable leather-bound journal.

name: Miscellaneous Gundam Models
description: A collection of scale models representing various mobile suits from the iconic Gundam franchise. You spent a lot of time on these... better stash them in your sylladex before the imps get to them.

name: Halloweenie Reaper
