description: Perfect for scaring away trick-or-treaters so that you can have the candy all to yourself.

name: Note From A Dev: LR
description: LR: You're Welcome ;p

name: The Canadian Classic
description: A licky Boom Boom Down. <iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/NtILxBszyf8?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: Safety Shades
description: Safety goggles that will not only protect from sharp objects but also the sun's harmful ultraviolet rays!

name: Xanathos Speed Rifle
description: Sure to bring a swift Game Over to any foe.

name: Shackles of Sundering
description: This spiked chain gets imps hooked quicker than you to of those mangas with the flying robot ninjas.

name: Wrinkle Bludgeon
description: The combination of an ordinary kitchen iron and a baseball bat. You can't imagine what getting hit in the face with a chunk of metal attached to a stuck actually feels like: though to be honest you probably don't want to know.

name: Remote Ghost Gauntlet
description: Gloves that project a blue ghostly appendage that can grab and hit things. This should make weapon-handling easier! Unless you just want to punch imps with your ghost hand. That works too.

name: Uranium Chainsaw
description: Cleave your enemies in two with SCIENCE.

name: Red Mage\'s Jacket
description: The jacket of a Red Mage, one who is proficient in the Sword and the magic arts, though they kind of fall behind the masters of either field.

name: Cleaversaw
description: Chop enemies into a pulp with the combination of a cleaver and a chainsaw.

name: Red Mage\'s Hat
description: The hat of a Red Mage, it has a fancy gold rim and a feather, designed to make you look awesome when casting spells or dicing monsters with your sword. It looks especially good if you have long hair!

name: Questionably Helpful Pawn Plush
description: A charming plush doll representing a pawn from Dragon's Dogma. When you pull the string on its back, your cuddly companion will offer a classic bit of pawn wisdom, such as: "their kind is weak to ice and fire both!" or "even in numbers, a weakling is a weakling still!"

name: UmbrellaBlade
description: A mixture of an umbrella and a sword.

name: Umbrapier
description: The Umbrapier is an Umbrella with a Rapier craftily hidden inside the handle. You could probably poke somebody's eye out with it. Or some other organ in their body. The user's tongue is probably not as sharp as the blade itself.

name: MonoEye Combat Visor
description: A more combat-oriented wearable computer that provides you with a useful heads-up display and rudimentary targeting system. Resembles the "eye" of a Zaku, or any number of other Zeonic Mobile Suits.

name: Black Crow Hood
description: For those up to no good.

name: Waistcoat
description: This snazzy little coat only covers your torso. It has two tiny pockets on the front for carrying small things, like watches, and small change. It makes you feel classier than you actually are.

name: Book of Fairy Tales
description: A thick anthology of lesson-heavy folktales about fairies, witches, gnomes, elves, and leprechauns. Some of these endings are pretty grim.

name: Quantum G-String
description: A thong that only exists in one dimension, reaching a whole new theoretical field of skimpiness.

name: Troll Doctor Who Poster
description: You are not quite sure what this is, but it sure looks neat!

name: Potato
description: A potato. If you haven't realized that by now there is little hope for you.

name: Catenative Doomsday Dice Cascader
description: A doomsday device capable of dealing 7.9586611 times 10^24 hitpoints of damage. Normally it just does ones, though.

name: The Colt of a Very Hot Hellfire
description: A gun that can kill anything, what can be better than that? Well add a flamethrower to it and lo and behold you have a pistol unlike any other. Instead of firing bullets, you fire the infernos of hell straight into your opponent.

name: Paper Mario Sticker Star poster
description: This poster sticks to your wall, kind of like how the experience of playing it sticks to your mind. It just won't come off.

name: Swortar
description: It's a sword! It's a guitar! It's probably as likely to injure you as it is your enemies.

name: Origami Orcsmashers
description: Two large papercraft hammers enlarged into threeeeeee deeeeee space through the magic of 2 screens and like ten cameras.

name: Nintendium Cube
description: One of the hardest and most well constructed metals known to man compressed into a small cube.

name: STRONG Explosive Impact Gloves
description: You get sweaty because these gloves are also bombs. Luckily the gloves makes you strong enough to withstand the explosive power of the gloves. You get sweaty to the thought of whoever receives these gloves to the face.

name: Stick Figurine
description: It's... a figurine of a stick figure. As in the kind people draw when they can't draw, but not it's in the form of a figurine. You have no idea what you could use this for, let alone the severe lack of skill used to make it.

name: Warehouse 13: Season 1 DVD
description: A DVD copy of the first season of a s how revolving around two secret agents and a Warehouse stocked with supernatural artifacts somewhere in South Dakota.

name: Nintendium Armor
description: Relegated from an ancient civilization galaxies away, mined from the very asteroid that executed the dinosaurs, forged in Mount Fuji, emblazoned secretly in shrines across Japan, overseen by both Miyamoto and Fils-Aime: its finally here. The strongest material known to hardware developers. Your body is ready.

name: Sleepy Stomp Badge
description: Do game constructs even sleep?

name: 3D(S) Glasses
description: Its like everything is in three dimensions!

name: Baseball
description: A brand new baseball you hadn't gotten around to using until just now.

name: Staff of the DewRito Pope
description: Our game fuel, who art in supermarkets Delicious be thy taste They review scores bought Thy will be done on IGN as it is in Kotaku Give us this day our daily 10/10 And forgive us for our unbiased reviews As we forgive those who review alongside us May your free PS3's lead us not into temptation but deliver us from honest reviews For thine kingdom is EA the Activision, and the Ubisoft For ever and ever Video Game Journalism

name: Space Marine Jump Pack
description: Good lord, this thing looks heavy. Should help you get out of the way of attacks though.

name: Suit of Armour
description: Imbued with the smugness of a thousand scholars.

name: Electric Apocalypse
description: Nothing more dangerous than a sharp ass scythe that has electricity coursing through it. It's about time Death got with the times.

name: SKUL TRUMPMET......
description: The last sound you hear before you go insane. No, but seriously, who would want this thing anywhere near them? It's the most frightening instrument ever created.

name: Shanghai Doll
description: Shanghai doll is one of Alice Margatroid's dolls from Touhou series. It is said that it is specialized in destructive magic.

name: Madoka\'s Wings
description: Cool wings from the last episode of Puella Magi Madoka Magica.

name: Oversized Paintbrush
description: From the artist who prefers to paint the world from a distance - literally and figuratively.

name: Scream Popper Megaphone
description: Yell into this megaphone, you will get more than an amplified voice. You might not want to stand in front of this thing, you'll get your face blown off.

name: Oktavia von Seckendorff Final Symphony
description: A beautiful blue tome written with lead pages. Inside, it describes the life and times of the fallen magical girl Sayaka Miki and the rise of the great witch Oktavia von Seckendorff.

name: Scratcher Blaster
description: For those tough itches.

name: Scissorhands
description: Hardcore tool for lock-picking, hedge-trimming, hair-cutting, and even ice-sculpting! Be wary that you have to resist the urge to relieve your itch.

name: Necronomicon
description: Either full of dark and eldritch majjyyks, or a load of fakey fake fake bullshit. If there's any difference between those things.

name: Multi-Tone Kazoot
description: The multi-tone kazoot is capable of playing the harmonic sounds of the majestic kazoo in all of the tones that a flute could. It's also twice as annoying as both of them, unless you're into this sort of thing.

name: Ms. Paint Pin-up Poster
description: Just let the picture say a thousand words... and leave everyone else speechless.

name: Mozaik Scissors
description: A certain scissors that will pierce your heart... actually, all scissors can.

name: Compumask
description: This mask does an excellent job of hiding your identity online as well as in real life. Troll on, anon!

name: Death\'s Watch
description: A scythe with a built-in timekeeping device. All the better for getting the message across: Your time has come!

name: Magic Throwing Knife
description: It`s a knife which hold a magic aura. It contain a power of amulet.

name: Turtle School Gi
description: An orange martial arts uniform with the kanji for 'turtle' on the front. It seems a lot more durable than something you'd expect something made of regular cloth to be.

name: sUBitO SbAHj...
description: You've finally done it. You've taken one of the most powerful blades you've ever seen, and reduced it to a worthless pile of shit. Congratulations.

name: Gundam Helmet
description: Molded from Lunar-Titanium alloy, this internal HUD equipped helmet with enhanced sensors is a sturdy helm. Your V-Fin gleams brilliantly under the light of Skaia. Bring it Zeon scum.

name: Dwarven Axe
description: A big axe for a little man. Or woman. It can be hard to tell with dwarves.

name: Aperture Science Sentry Turret
description: An white gun turret with a weirdly adorable voice that will shoot anything it sees. Despite the tripod legs, it falls over and breaks easily.

name: Compasscope
description: Sort of like a bigger pair of binoculars, except the two eyepieces point in different directions and you can change the angle between them. Looking through it is more disorienting than useful.

name: Extending Compass
description: For when the circles drawn by a normal compass are too small.

name: Electric Acid Inferno
description: Burn, electrocute and corrode your enemies all at once! The perfect mixture of chemistry and physics.

name: Grand Snack Fuckyeah disc
description: Trash up stunts something uncannybrutal on your quest for "MAD SNACKS YO" and get this way rude hunger under control! And try not to glitch into walls in the process.

name: Solid Gold Santa
description: As if these things weren't gaudy enough already.

name: Christmas Chemist Claus
description: A fancy santa clad in a bright red labcoat with a reindeer motif. Pull the string on his back, and he'll fling a beaker full of some unidentifiable glittery substance at your enemies.

name: Schrodinger\'s Santa
description: Sadly, its wavefunction seems to have collapsed to the "shitty" state the moment you first laid eyes on it.

name: Quantum Tunneler
description: Rather than displacing dirt, this odd shovel just sort of phases through it. Sadly, this makes it pretty much useless for both digging and strifing.

name: Engineered Sentry Gun
description: For solving all of your practical problems.

name: Sungod\'s All-In-One Harp-Bow
description: A certain sun god is well known for wielding a bow. This sun god is also known for playing music on a legendary lyre. What most people don't know, though, is that his bow and his lyre were actually one and the same. This ranged instrument is hand-crafted and worthy of a god.

name: JEFF DA KILLAH NAIF
description: Didn't expahct this ded you? I could tell you but i'd would have to kill yuoh, now go teh sleap.

name: Multifunction Pen
description: The Multifunction Pen has the long-lastingness and fluidity of a pen, plus the shading and erasability of a pencil.

name: Felt Blazer
description: Despite the name, which would make you think of a tool for blazing felt, this is really just a green jacket.

name: Magical Girl Outfit
description: A bit frilly for battle, but hey, it seems to fix itself everytime you put it on.

name: Saber\'s Armor
description: A powerful set of armor covering a dress. Extremely resistant to magic.

name: Incubator\'s Recipe Guide
description: Call forth legions of fallen witches, but at your own risk. Something about this book, overall, is too enticing.

name: Holy Water
description: Hurts zombies, skeletons, vampires and atheists. If you're not one of those, though, it's delicious and nutritious.

name: General Romero\'s Fancy Stick
description: It's said that General Romero had this made, not as a sword inside a cane, but as a sword usable as a walking stick. Either that, or someone lost the cane's sheath.

name: Gandalf\'s Staff
description: The Grey Wizard's staff, brought into reality. Can be used to fend off unwieldy foes, mad kings, or hobbits with an appetite. Has a strange magic around it: be wary when using.

name: Flesh Wound
description: A Claymore with a trigger on the hilt, shoots buckshot and slays enemies. Sure to inflict plenty of "flesh wounds".

name: Fangs of the Father
description: Wielding the two daggers in unison unlocks untold power. The blades seem to work by themselves, pulling your body along as you fight and turning you into a killing machine.

name: Facefucker
description: A heavy sledgehammer with resemblance to the Pogo Hammer and Wrinklefucker before it, but instead of hammerheads or irons, this hammer sports solid iron fists. Ever wanted to hit something with a hammer, AND punch it in the face at the same time? Now you can.

name: Event Horizon
description: Forged using a combination of science and complete baloney. These blades spin fast and sharp enough to rend spacetime itself. There's no going back after you cause that kind of damage.

name: E=m(c^2)
description: This bow tested Relativity.... And won.

name: Blade Whip
description: This whip has segments of blades in it, slicing your enemy when you crack it. Or yourself, if you're not careful.

name: Crushades
description: These steel shades with gold trim allow you to fight without getting all that nasty heathen blood in your eyes!

name: Golden Lion Armor
description: This armor is said to have protected against generations of giant monsters...Sounds kind of similar for you, if you wore it.

name: Dogmatic Sun Armor
description: This armor is nigh-unstoppable, shielding you completely from swords, dragons and magicks. The plate and chain-mail is adorned with the coat of arms of a large sun on the front, and a griffin on the back.

name: Heaven\'s Key
description: This dagger is glowing brightly with a heavenly magick, said to unlock the inner good of any being, you know, by stabbing them.

name: Ace of Hades
description: This glowing red and green card can be transformed into a large axe if blood is dripped into the mouth of the demon present on the face, like a medieval blood sugar tester!

name: Computer Headset
description: A totally mobile computer that allows you to communicate with others on the move. You could've just gotten a laptop, you know.

name: Checkmate (Black)
description: A pure-black shotgun, adorned with symbols representing chess pieces.

name: Checkmate (White)
description: A pure-white shotgun, adorned with symbols representing chess pieces.

name: Stalemate
description: A double-barreled shotgun, with one pure-black and one pure-white barrel, adorned with symbols representing chess pieces. You feel the power of the Battlefield running through it.

name: Hourglass
description: An old-fashioned, yet effective timer.

name: Slams of Time
description: A light hammer with an hourglass-shaped head filled with sand. It's too bad you'll be swinging it around too often to use it as a timer.

name: Crystal of Balance
description: A crystal that is equal parts dark and light, neither one overpowering the other. Holding it gives you a sense of pure neutrality.

name: Hammerny
description: An amazingly balanced warhammer in all senses of the word, one side is white and the other black, an hourglass resting in the middle. The hammer's alignment changes depending on the amount of sand in each side. You sense a lot of potential in this hammer, as if it could become anything.

name: Blackjack
description: A hammer composed solely of two large metal numbers 2 and 1. You feel a lot more open to taking risks holding this, and like a true gambling addiction, if you lose this hammer it always seems to turn up somewhere, waiting.

name: Judgement
description: Not unlike a giant gavel, this hammer carries feelings of justice and order. If struck, the properties of the attack it blocked are copied over into its next swing. Justice is served.

name: Soviet Russia
description: This "hammer" is more like a thick log shoved through an anvil to make a hammer shape. You can barely lift it, but when you do, you get a sense of manliness and dominance. In Soviet Russia, anvil hammer YOU!

name: Weathervane
description: A thin metal weathervane.... wait, did you take this from the roof of your house?!

name: Zephyr
description: A long, yet light hammer made up of thin wiring. Looks underwhelming, but swinging it creates a breeze that increases its momentum and blows your target away. You might even be able to fly with it, given enough practice.

name: Chaincrush
description: Looks like someone literally taped two chainsaws to the end of a sledgehammer, but upon closer inspection it's actually a cleverly put-together machine of destruction and vengeance. Great for crowd control, as well as those... "special" enemies.

name: Hancock Smith
description: A hammer that is made of pure imagination and ideas, its form changes depending on the situation and the wielder's thoughts. It can become just about anything, but be warned that it's not the most predictable of weapons.

name: Icemaul
description: A thick, gigantic hammer made of solid ice so rigid that it'll shatter bones before it shatters itself. Just hope you do all your fighting in the winter!

name: Adorable Cat Cosplay outfit
description: A full-body cat suit for the true cosplayer and animal enthusiast. When you say you're a cat person, you're really not kidding!

name: Amethyst Shield
description: A shiny purple shield that is both very pretty and very impractical.

name: Backlace
description: A pair of panties that transform into a pretty sweet pistol. Awesome against ghosts, terrible if you have any sense of shame.

name: Animal Claws
description: These claws look exactly like they came from a real animal! ...You're just not sure which.

name: Aperture Science Quantum Luck-8r8king 8ow
description: A bow that fires arrows of Hard Light, tipped with replicas of the famed Flourite Octet. Because of the quantum component, the result of the die tips is all possible results. Point this bow only at things you really, really want dead.

name: Autohunter
description: You're not sure how it works exactly, but it's a bow that fires arrows with the frequency of a machine gun. Why question it?

name: Spice Rack
description: You captchalogued an entire spice rack? Genius.

name: Pan-Dimensional Spacethyme Herb Mix
description: These herbs seem to emanate unusual power... you're not sure if mixing them into your soup is a good idea.

name: Scarborough Bulletmaker
description: You've got parsley, sage, and rosemary... but with this gun in your hands, there'll be no thyme to lose.

name: Galaxial Green Sun Dragonshaver
description: This blade releases faint green energy which hums when you whip it through the air. Legends tell that it has the power to cleave whole galaxies in twain and pierce the hardest dragon scales.

name: Attack the Block DVD
description: Oy bruv this is a fookin' wicked movie about alien gorilla wolf motherfuckers, believe

name: Bast
description: Procedures for using this Stand: Snap fingers. Create electrical outlet. Lure foe into touching outlet. Make foe magnetic.

name: The Emperor v1.1
description: Half of the Emperor's power was its near inability to be detected until it had fired and its lack of recoil. Both of those issues have been addressed.

name: Bee Movie DVD
description: This movie is unbeelievable.

name: Dress of the Green Sun
description: This green, radiant dress shows that you're always the life of the party. And the universe.

name: BIONICLES ADVENTURES COMICS
description: A light-hearted, JPEG-riddled comic series about the adventures of the BIONICLE characters Tahu and Lewa. Or Gresh. It's not entirely clear.

name: Black Butler vol. 1-3
description: A manga detailing the Victorian era life of an orphaned stuck-up rich kid and his demon butler who loves cats.

name: Board Game
description: A fun game played to bond with friends or family. Or to make enemies.

name: Board Game Hammer
description: A hammer from a board game, thankfully blown up to size to allow for better handling and damage. Sure to send your foes back quite a ways.

name: Autohammer
description: A hammer for paladins. Blows back any enemies that dare invade your space.

name: Holy Hammer
description: A hammer meant for only the best of paladins, sending any enemy who crosses its path to square zero.

name: Book of Theology
description: A book describing gods and religions of all kinds. Is there a religion that worships everything?

name: Chainscythe of Memories
description: A chained scythe that absorbs the memories of those cut by the blade. Better than letting them die with the corpse, you guess?

name: The Sanzu Slicemeister
description: The scythe used by Komachi Onozuka, ferryman of the Sanzu River, from Touhou. The scythehead glows with the powers of a shinigami, albeit an inefficient and lazy one.

name: The Official SCP Sales Catalog
description: The catalog contains pictures and information on almost every single SCP artifact known, though the information on each object is written more like a sales pitch than an official document. Prices, item numbers and an order number are also listed. The bottom of the cover reads "Our best issue ever!!!" suggesting that there might be more issues of SCP-000 floating around...

name: Yukianesa
description: One of the Nox Nyctores, this sword in particular was used by Major Jin Kisaragi. Holding the sword in your hands you suddenly feel like murderously obsessing over a sibling figure... that or it's frostbite.

name: The Dapper Poshtana
description: Nothing says "I'm classier than a butler-ninja" than an umbrella with an unbreakable katana inside the handle. Never has being a gentleman been so SUGOI.

name: One Piece: Chapter 454: Humming
description: A chapter of popular Manga series One Piece in which the Skeleton Brook first uses his humming swordsman ability.

name: Sora\'s Practice Shinai
description: Oh, hey! It's that one sword from that one game where you constantly get your ass handed to you by that kid with spiky white anime hair... Yeah, I remember that! Man, what a piece of shit. At least you can smack stuff with it.

name: Rock-it Guitar
description: Blast off with some high speed riffs! With rocket assistance, you can now swing your guitar at speeds which frankly just aren't safe.

name: Plush Sheep toy
description: What an adorable plushie. This soft woolly sheep is an invaluable addition to anyone's bed. Don't eat it, though.

name: Explosive Sheep
description: This adorable little sheep will hop in any direction you steer it... until you press the button and it explodes. You definitely can't eat this one.

name: Overseer Pantsu
description: How cute! There's little SQL codes stitched on the waistband.

name: Drillmerang
description: A boomerang with drills for arms. You... you can't even hold this safely. There's no way you could use this in a fight. But dang if it doesn't look cool.

name: Spiral Energy Boomerang
description: A small metal center releasing a concentrated mass of pure spiral energy, curved to allow it to be thrown. Just holding onto this instills you with confidence, and bolsters your will.

name: Drill Fists
description: Your arms are now drills. Well, ok, technically they're actually just a set of drill gloves that connect to a power source on your back. But you don't care, these things are awesome!

name: Battery-Powered Battery Pistol
description: This gun uses the charge from one battery to propel the previous depleted one into your enemies. Thankfully the Medium doesn't have environmental laws, or alchemizing this would probably have broken just about all of them.

name: Rummy\'s Furybrolly
description: Only a being who smelled this much like Captain Morgans would be daft enough to sharpen his hidden-umbrellasword to this extent. When brandishing this dastardly tool, people think twice before they approach you... Though you're not sure whether it's the stench of rum on your umbrella, or the stench of the dead on your blade.

name: Blood Scythe
description: The Sword of the SS Class Criminal Ragna the Bloodedge. This sword has destroyed thousands of foes and appears no worse for wear. It can fold out into a scythe for greater destructive power.

name: Broken Caledfwlch
description: You couldn't even pull this legendary piece of shit out of the stone. So you broke it.

name: Blunderbuss
description: An old, yet alarmingly effective hunting rifle used by the gentlemanliest of gentlemen.

name: The Exorscissors
description: These scissors glow with an AWESOME POWER, their burning GRIP tells you to defeat evil!

name: Snakeskin Jacket
description: This jacket feels tough and leathery, how many snakes died to make this thing? You don't know, but damn if it ain't cool.

name: Liches\' Leviathan
description: This giant gravestone looks like it could hold an entire zombie cyclops' weight, or maybe it's just a giant, evil gravestone.

name: Sore Ass Slammer
description: This leather and stud covered barstool ain't for sittin', it's for smashin'. SOUND THE BATTLE CRY!

name: Razorboar Carcass
description: This thing looks more like a pump action engine than a gun, quite unwieldy, but the flame-shooting monster is worth it.

name: Stake Nailer
description: Not to be confused with shooting steaks at your enemies, this revolving crossbow fires large wooden stakes in rapid succession, reloading takes a while though, not a lot of small trees around to shove in.

name: 3D Goggles
description: Now you can watch your 3D movies with slightly less flimsy glasses. They still hurt your eyes a little, though.

name: 20 Fortunes
description: The f8 of your foes rests with this die. Depending on the roll, your enemies' luck may change... but it is extremely fickle.

name: Torn Banner
description: This two sided banner is red and black on one side, and blue and gold on the other... You can't quite make out the coat of arms on either side though.

name: Spruce Santa Slinger
description: Santa is carved into the handle of this solid wooden slingshot, and the arms resemble reindeer antlers. Tacky, but its aim is truer than the legend of Santa Claus.

name: Typewriter
description: A Smith Corona brand typewriter.

name: Smokin\' Six-Stringed Scorcher
description: Man, these riffs are so hot! You'll come swinging through the fire and the flames at your enemies with this number.

name: Kriemhild Gretchen Armor
description: This armor is powered by the malevolent magic of a Witch powerful enough to destroy the world in a week. Because if nothing exists, the new, empty world will be a safe haven without pain.

name: Ancient Root Sword
description: An old, incredibly light sword with a rather bizarre gnarled wooden hilt, appearing as if part of a tree had grown in the shape of a grip and crossguard. The white blade, strangely, also appears to be an organic component, with no discernable split between it and the root-like handle. It unsettles you for no reason you can place. Maybe because the pointy bit makes stuff glow and then blow up.

name: Otherworldly Paradaxe
description: This axe holds within it the power of countless vengeful forest spirits, enraged at the decimation of their homes. Presumably, anyway, to you it just looks like a root that grew a sharp metallic crescent somehow. Branches grow out of whatever you chop with it. It is exactly as painful as it sounds when used on something living.

name: Skullgirls
description: A game about young ladies with interesting back stories and shoddy mental stability beating the ever-loving snot out of each other.

name: Krieg
description: An umbrella, wielded by the commander of the Canopy Kingdom's royal army, with quasi-sentience and the ability to cry tears of pure napalm. Also there's a sharp part!

name: Shady Pistol of Merry Maladies
description: This pistol appears to have a whole range of gags sequestered within its ammunition chambers. You've seen a "BANG!" flag, a couple of different swords, actual bullets, baseballs, a few very irate avians, a pair of brass knuckles strapped to a glove... The list goes on, really.

name: Pikachu Cosplay
description: With this suit, you might just give someone a heart attack! Not from electricity, but from cuteness of course.

name: Our Glorious Speaker (New Testament)
description: Tales of "The Speaker of the Vast Croak" and other prospitian messiahs.

name: Eldritch Abomination Helmet
description: A powerful helmet. If only the tentacles didn't stick to your head.

name: Handyman\'s friend
description: Honestly, why would anyone tape nails to a pair of gloves? This can't be safe.

name: Gae Bolg
description: Famous Lancer's cursed spear from Fate/Stay Night. It is said that it always strikes the heart of your opponent.

name: Glass of Milk
description: A nice tall glass of nutritious Grade A Milk.

name: Mad Chemist\'s Wheelchair
description: It probably belonged to one of those "mad scientists". No one knows how he died... Wait, there's an acid leaking from it!

name: Death\'s Pistol
description: A spooky-looking pistol adorned with little skulls. Just holding it makes the air around you sort of... Eerie.

name: Brick of Computing
description: A durable brick of solid computing power.

name: Lon-Lon Milk
description: Fresh milk straight from the famous Lon Lon Ranch. This ain't no store-bought preservative-riddled swill, this is the real deal!

name: Book of Prisonic Fairy Tales
description: A thick anthology of gruesome folktales about fleshy abominations, hellish environments, and people with deep-seated psychological issues. ALL of these endings are pretty grim.

name: Green Potion
description: A magical emerald brew that supposedly restores your... magic. You're not sure if what you do really counts as that, but it's worth a shot?

name: Red Riding Hood
description: An eye-catching red hooded cloak, of the sort known to repel wolves. Or was that "attract wolves"? You honestly can't remember.

name: Mountain Dew Concussion Grenade
description: You could have achieved the same effect with A LOT of arm shaking but wheres the fun in that?

name: Dewrito Shrapnel Grenade
description: A shaking bottle of Mountain Dew that shoots itty-bitty Dorito shrapnel every which way when the unfortunate target touches the bottle.

name: GAME FUEL
description: Stop drinking like a noob. This scientific concoction of sugar and sugar water will keep you gaming all night and through the next week!

name: GAME FUEL Dewrito shrapnel grenade
description: Even MORE volatile. Youre actually kind of scared of holding this thing.

name: Three-Green Glasses
description: Glasses featuring three different shades of green; one for each eye and one for the frame. Looking through it is actually kind of calming.

name: Apple Jacks
description: A set of jacks that together somehow manage to function as a phone. Mother of God, what will they think of next??

name: Kolhii Stick
description: The proper item for playing Kolhii.

name: Krampus\' Chain
description: This chain has an eerie field of energy, as if you have his powers.

name: Knight\'s Gore
description: It looks like a chess set but spookier. Maybe it's cursed, maybe it's just a fancy hunk of marble.

name: Juggalo Bone
description: You know you have something special when you rip it out of somebodys body. Regardless this thing hurts.

name: Itchy Trigger Finger
description: Click the (strangely yellow) trigger once and the whole magazine has been run through.

name: Helm of Silver Chariot
description: Blinding speed and a sudden case of skinless face are not consequences of removing this helmet.

name: Fists of Star Platinum
description: Next time someone tries to get you to wager your soul on a video game, do the both of you a favor with these.

name: Zeppeli Bubble Gloves
description: They don't seem intimidating, but they come with Ripple included.

name: Baseball Cap
description: Keeps the sun out of your eyes and whatever team you liked on display.

name: Multi Bottle Rocket Pistol
description: Reloading this thing is gonna be a bitch.

name: The Hanged Man
description: Anything that has a reflection can now have knives in its throat, courtesy of this Stand's two right hands.

name: Faygo - Emerald Splash flavour
description: Drinking this slimy green stuff ought to turn you a bit stretchier. And also glowing green.

name: The Lazy Postman
description: Great for delivering mail from half a mile away, or for blasting imps in the face with tightly rolled-up envelopes travelling at roughly the speed of sound.

name: Extra-Dark Sunglasses
description: ...you can't actually see anything through these. They sure are stylish, though!

name: Holy Handgunnade
description: You decided to play God and improve upon the weaponry he bestowed upon his crusaders to smite those naughty in his sight. Look what you've wrought.

name: Wrenchlight
description: A wrench with a flashlight attached, for when you need to tighten bolts in the dark.

name: Pistol of the Cleric
description: Roll to hit just took on a whole new meaning.

name: High-Voltage Lemon Battery
description: A lemon with two electrodes stuck into it. It is sparking with electricity, sending out errant bolts of lightning every which way: better make sure you are properly insulated before handling it.

name: JoJo\'s Bizarre Adventure Vol. 30
description: Ignore anyone who says the name of the arc with the best-haired Stand user in the world is "Diamond is Unbreakable."

name: Clackers
description: Everyone loves a nice banned toy every once in a while, don't they?

name: Purple Ripple
description: Blue sparks of Ripple energy course over this Stand's tendrils of purple energy. Wrap them around you and you're 100% safe from time-stopping vampires.

name: Stone Mask
description: Try not to bleed on this thing while you're wearing it. Unless you want to become a vampire, but that's a whole different story.

name: JoJo\'s Bizarre Adventure Vol. 1
description: As much as you might want to make jokes about Fist of the North Star, you'd be sort of a jerk to insult the one that started it all.

name: Anubis
description: For a scimitar stand that hasn't had a master in 500 years, this thing remembers the moves used against it like the day it was made.

name: Joestar Tommy Gun
description: If New York were still around, now would be the time to put this thing to use in your search for a guy named Straits.

name: Ripple-Conductive Sledgehammer
description: How do you make a sledgehammer better? An ingenious Joestar thought to cover it with oil that you could be made electric just by breathing.

name: Ripple-Conductive Super Sledge
description: You one-upped the Joestar geezer using kinetic-enhancement technology. This thing might as well be a passing truck if swung during a chariot race.

name: Golden Wind
description: The thin gold makes this fan both lightweight and grants it a sharp cutting edge.

name: JoJo\'s Bizarre Adventure Vol. 48
description: Remember that time anyone understood how King Crimson worked? No, neither do you.

name: Sunlight Yellow Hermit Overdrive
description: Once upon a time, you had to fistfight a vampire to put the explosive Sunlight Yellow Overdrive to use. That's a thing of the past.

name: Steel Balls
description: When a square section of a golden rectangle is removed, the remainder is another golden rectangle: the Zeppelis mastered the spiral created by this phenomenon for the Spin technique.

name: JoJo\'s Bizarre Adventure Vol. 82
description: This manga flawlessly combines a paraplegic protagonist, a horse race, and a guy who likes to sing about cheese with a search for the body parts of Jesus Christ.

name: Rocket Toaster
description: This enhanced toaster uses rocket engines to propel finished pieces of toast several hundred meters into the air or your enemies. Guaranteed to spice up any breakfast.

name: Demon\'s Souls
description: With this shit-rockingly hard exclusive, the East proved it could, on occasion, do WRPGs better than the West.

name: iPewn
description: They say that iPods keep getting smaller and smaller. You have handheld proof to the innovation of portable multimedia. Now introducing: The iPewn.

name: Light Sword
description: A... sword hilt that emits a beam of light? You honestly have no idea what use this could possibly have.

name: POTaTOS
description: An evil robotic mastermind attached to a potato battery. Useful for snarky comments and slow claps on the go!

name: Pinata
description: A festive doll you can beat the ever-living shit out of. Sadly, it's hollow.

name: Pikachu Pinata
description: A piata in the shape of a pikachu. Quite cute and well made. Do you still plan to whack it open?

name: Pikapoop Pinato
description: A hideous abomination of GameFreak's favorite mascot and cash cow. Break it into smithereens.

name: Pinata Grenade
description: A grenade for the festive pyromaniacs who love explosions.

name: Nokia Phone
description: Some say that only the hardest materials can break this strange device... Claiming even that dropping it is more likely to break the floor tiles.

name: MC Hammer
description: Getting hit on the head by this baby will send you unconscious, only to awaken in the future! Though who knows if you are actually time traveling or have just been sleeping for several years...

name: Hammer Laser
description: This battery operated device projects the image of a hammer, which unfortunately cannot actually make physical contact with enemies. You could probably point it at their eyes to blind them a little though.

name: Tux-Shirt
description: A regular T-shirt with a printed design that resembles a tuxedo. It's the perfect way to stay classy and cool all at the same time!

name: Metal Jacket
description: A literal steel jacket. This thing is definitely bulletproof.

name: Gentleman\'s Suit
description: Look like a proper gentleman. Tophat not included.

name: Tickmore
description: A sword that's oddly ticking. Sometimes it appears older or younger than usual.

name: History Textbook
description: A particularly heavy book recounting in great detail the history of civilization on your home planet... in light of recent events, perhaps you ought to take special care to preserve such a record.

name: Bedsheet
description: A plain white bedsheet. You could potentially wear it like a robe... Surely such finery will impress the fashion-conscious consorts of your land!

name: Encyclopedia of Paranormal Phenomena
description: A comprehensive guide to the ongoing study of ghosts, extraterrestrials, psychic powers, and other such matters of dubious scientific legitimacy.

name: High Frequency Rummy\'s Furybrolly
description: No longer are you an alcoholic ninja butler. You're an alcoholic CYBORG ninja butler. The high frequency part of your overly sharp (and still odorous) katana-umbrella will give you the ability (and the god-given right) to cut pretty much anything that isn't longer or wider than it in any given direction. Gives you a sudden craving for robotic spines.

name: Docking Staff
description: A staff that has an anchor coming from one side: it looks like could be useful for grabbing.

name: Clock the Block Rifle
description: A simple looking rifle, but shoots laser shots with an echo-y sounding pop.

name: Blade of Aegis
description: The ultimate unbreakable sword capable of deflecting anything. Cannonfire, Cannons, Cannoneers, not a problem at all. And it can still cut a tomato clean in half. ..And probably the rest of your kitchen too.

name: Agathian Leather Jerkin
description: This leather armor provides good mobility to dodge, but LEATHER or not you let them get close, it does a good job of protecting you.

name: Masonic Maul
description: This hefty hammer smashed many a man. For some reason you like to scream evilly when swinging it. Creepy, dude.

name: Sir Loins\' Smasher
description: This hefty gravestone belonged to a great warrior, he must've had a huge head or was a really angry dead man, because this thing is HUGE.

name: Dubious Doublehead Axe
description: This double headed, if not short and stocky battle-axe is crested with a small sword in the metal, more akin to fast swings than slow, heavier strikes, careful not to hit your toes!

name: Tojo Snake Crest Eyepatch
description: This eye patch is great looking and head fitting, too bad you have two good eyes and this doesn't offer much in the way of defense, but you just feel more crazy wearing it.

name: SPAZ-21
description: This chromed shotgun has just the right amount of kick and shoots perfect, a small snake crest is in the pistol-grip handle. Try not to go crazy, unlike the name suggests.

name: Dogmatic Snakemail
description: This form-fitting, tough scale-mail armor makes you feel crazy and aggressive when you get into a fight, like a snake poised to strike.

name: Icy Claws
description: These icy claws are perfectly suited for making an ice-cream! Just dip them in a mixture and freeze it immediately! Just fantastic!

name: Inflated Hammer
description: This toy hammer squeaks loudly when you bop something with it. Even if it doesn't hurt your enemies, it'll drive them crazy at least!

name: Squeakfucker
description: SQUEAKSQUEAKSQUEAK! This hammer is almost an eldritch abomination with how loud and grating on the ears it is. Smashes pretty hard for an inflatable, too.

name: Hot Beats
description: The personification of those hot beats that we all so desperately crave but do not actually want because they can kill you.

name: Laser Guided Darts
description: You cheater, no one would ever let you use these in a REAL game.

name: Luciful Darts
description: The darts appear as roses before thrown, once inside something, they appear to turn to red, glowing, and pretty thorny swords that explode once you clap. You must be some Spanish stud.

name: Spatu-bluh
description: YOU VANT TO FLIP ZUH BLUD-...wait no, that's not right.

name: Homura\'s Time Shield
description: Ever wanted to go back in time to stop your friend from signing a contract with an alien? No? Well that's OK because you can still travel through time with this!

name: His Dark Materials Omnibus
description: The acclaimed but controversial trilogy by Philip Pullman, bound in one volume. Involves adventures, magic, and parallel universes, with a side of anti-religious sentiment.

name: Rockula
description: This looks like some caveman attempted to make a spatula, and as such it's heavy as hell and could slap any hand reaching for the mammoth-steak before it's done!

name: Hatsune Chainsaw
description: A rather dashing Chainsaw covered in images of leeks and Hatsune Miku, every otaku's dream.

name: Harry Hammerson
description: It's Harry Anderson's Gavel from Night Court!

name: Hale\'s Own Chainsword
description: What's the shit you've just inve...Oh my, is this a chainsaw?! Sooooo coool.

name: Glass Cane
description: A walking cane made of glass. If you use it to clonk someone on the noggin it will probably shatter, which actually sounds pretty painful.

name: Walking Glasses
description: If you can't see without your glasses you better pay very close attention to these!

name: Orange Candy Cane
description: A striped orange colored cane-shaped hard candy stick associated with Christmas.

name: Brandistock
description: This three-pronged, long shafted spear was used to keep the enemies from reaching you. In ye olde days, they still do, just hope you have the arm length to use it effectively.

name: Trianholdint
description: This heavy trident has a large chunk of rock on the bottom end, so you guess you could club something with the other end if the prongs broke...

name: Shaman Cane
description: A spooky cane topped with a skull. Perfect for summoning zombie dogs or whatever creepy stuff it is that you do.

name: Stainless Steel Walking Cane
description: A walking cane made of steel. Anyone strong enough to wield it is probably strong enough to not need it.

name: Spellfile
description: A play on spellfire, but this nail file can magically file down any unruly nails (and faces) you rub it on.

name: Fake Plastic Skull
description: A fake skull made of cheap plastic. Makes for a good halloween prop.

name: Fireile
description: This nail file, when exposed to enough friction, lights on fire, careful which end you rub it on.

name: Super Jacket
description: In is said that anyone who wears it will gain mystical powers. Once Bo-bobo was determined to save his friends, the true power of the jacket was activated and his was granted with the power of love and all 5,634 supermarkets in Japan.

name: GLaDOS Headset
description: This snarky headset will always be ready to give you advice and guide you through the game! Though how jumping into a vat of neurotoxin will help is unknown.

name: Scratch-Five
description: This off-white backscratcher glows green with, what else, green electricity. It also makes your back feel glow-y when you scratch it.

name: The Claws of Bastet
description: Bestowed with the powers of an Eye of Ra, these claws burn like the sun and are perfect for protecting those in need.

name: Giga Drill Breaker
description: An incredibly powerful drill, clearly capable of digging upwards and through the very heavens.

name: Gorechild
description: A Chainaxe almost the height of a man, forged for the hands of a demigod. Its strength is mighty, but it exerts a strange power over y - KILL! MAIM! BURN!

name: Snake-Eyes Shot
description: This, faintly glowing, teleporting pistol has two barrels, and doesn't require reloading, give 'em a roll they just can't win.

name: Arsonist\'s Best Friend
description: Keeps the rain off you by VAPORIZING IT.

name: Tahu\'s Swordbrella
description: A flaming sword, worthy of being borne by a mighty Toa-hero! ...Yeah, this is still an umbrella that's on fire. It's made out of miniature swords, though.

name: Protosteel Armour
description: In contrast to the previous set of Nuva Armor you had, made of plastic, this set is made of diamond-hard Protodermic steel. It should provide a decent defense.

name: Tainted Axe of Morthol Dryax
description: Contrary to what the name might suggest, this is an axe of the musical variety! Now you too can rock out to the power chords of the Ageless Ones just like the Argus of the Undead astride his Bonemount Guard!

name: Tectritar of the Lyrist
description: The mightiest musician is nothing without the mightiest songwriter. With this powerful guitar you will blast your foes with the greatest rock ballads ever concocted.

name: SolCetus Flare
description: A glowing, light refracting sphere. When you hold this, you can feel a faint buzzing in your hands. When thrown, however, it explodes in a myriad of colors and energies, and reforms in your hands shortly after.

name: Echidna Shell
description: This shield is a spiral of pure space. The blows aren't reflected from the surface, rather sucked into the black and white expanse upon the face.

name: Typheus\'s Breathtaker
description: This blue and teal fan feels weightless, yet, you feel as if you could move wind and manipulate it however you'd like.

name: Armok\'s Quill
description: The tip of this pen, adorned with the facets of all living beings, writes a bloody history whenever you wield it, generally not a good one for whoever you write about.

name: Nyx\'s Scarf-String
description: You feel as if you shouldn't hold this, like it doesn't belong here, never-the-less. This string from Nyx's Scarf is used to wipe your enemies from existence.

name: Sophia\'s Heartstringer
description: This bow is ornately carved and rose-colored, flourishing and twisting on its' own, said to be able to pierce any heart.

name: Moros\'s Bolas
description: These bolas make almost life-like shadows, casting them everywhere when swung, reaching, pulling, and grabbing at your enemy to show them their inevitable doom.

name: Sunsmog Giest
description: They say that light mirrors from the dark, and this ethreal, ghostly axe is severely large, yet weightless and incredibly powerful as it wafts through the air like a wisp of glowing smoke.

name: Sunspot Steamer
description: This shotgun shoots puffs of severely hot and searing smoke, almost like steam, but something feels off, and righteous about it.

name: Smoky Veil
description: This cloud of smoke envelops you as a suit of armor, seemingly an aura to everyone else, but invisible to the wearer.

name: Spectral Echo
description: This axe/instrument combo gives off an aura of cold chill, and a fog machine all in one, making you a walking rock show. The bladed end also seems to envelope foes. You don't want to see what happens in there.

name: J. Geil no Danha!
description: It's simple, really: The more glass The Emperor breaks, the more reflections The Hanged Man can bounce between. What baffles you is why there's always glass above your opponent.

name: Rose Tinted Umbrella
description: Things under this just seem a little bit better.

name: Angelic Parasol
description: Float off into the sky on the wings of angels.

name: Umbrella-ella-ella
description: Eh eh eh.

name: Vacuum Cleaner
description: The modern cleaning solution.

name: GameBrow
description: A cheap plastic bow with various snack logos plastered all over it. It's a wonder you can even fire this piece of shit without it snapping.

name: Gas-Staff of Light
description: This staff has the ability to filter smoke... and produce light, or something. Alien technology sure is weird.

name: Scorpio\'s 8 String
description: This unusual 8-string guitar hums with a deadly aura, its striking cobalt strings reverberating to unleash bone-rattling power.

name: Rocket Propelled Umbrella
description: An umbrella with rocket pods attached to the canopy. Decisions don't come less wise than this.

name: Pump Action Marker
description: A modified marker that fires ink-soaked felt coloring nubs at your foes. This seems like a really strange concept to you, but you just decide to roll with it.

name: Fiduspawn Marker
description: At first it seemed to just be a Fiduspawn-themed marker, but drawing a Fiduspawn with it causes the image to come to life and fight by your side! Although, you should probably hope nobody prototyped with an eraser...

name: Psychic Paintbrush
description: Predictions painted by this brush have an uncanny record for becoming true. Your foes had best hope you don't paint them ill fates...

name: Paint palette
description: A wooden palette covered in stains of old paint.

name: Lava Lantern
description: This Psychedelic Lantern happens to be a little bit base, bit it'll keep you up all night looking at it.

name: Vadertop
description: This computer runs on pure force. Luke, I am your motherboard.

name: Daemon-Tooth Chainsword
description: This Astartes Chainsword has been posessed by a Daemonic servant of the dark gods that hungers for blood. Too bad it'll only be getting Grist!

name: Hard-Light Projector Tablet
description: Draw anything on the tablet, and the projector will project a hard-light image of it for you to use! It doesn't seem to process details very well, though, so better stick to weapons that don't require inner mechanisms to function.

name: B.R.O. the Brobot
description: A plastic toy robot with a hat and a skateboard. Comes programmed with cheat codes for thousands of games, but the only way to access them is to have it shout them out one character at a time in a grating, over-the-top announcer voice.

name: Giant Battlebrush
description: A paintbrush model larger with the brush part fashioned into a sharp spearhead. Kind of useless for painting, but all the better when it comes to poking.

name: Electric Tickmore
description: This sword has more than just a puny watch battery now, and you are managing to actually use it to travel minutes into the future and past with a dial on the hilt. All this time travel is making the sword rust a little, though.

name: Broseidons Barker
description: yo bro wanna play some halo i got the natty ice and dewritos

name: "Humming" Swordsman\'s High Frequency Piratical Brolly-Sword
description: On top of ALL those things the sword made you before, you're now a pirate. These prefixes are getting slightly out of hand, and so is the awesome blade you are now in control of. Forget even moving properly, just sliding your sword in and out of it's sheath has a habit of tearing up the environment around you now. Don't be too hasty to fully unsheath it, lest you want to keep your limbs. Which you don't want to cut off. Again. You've now the sudden urge to sing sailor's songs. Oh and "Humming" t

name: Zangetsu
description: This item is big heavy and sharp. You might need some more reshi to use it if that was a real thing.

name: Hollow Mask
description: Of course it's hollow, it's a mask! Why did that even need to be said? What do you mean "missing the point"?

name: Whacky Rules of RPG Physics
description: This large book with a molecule wearing a wizard hat on its cover gives an introduction to creating physics in a random RPG world. It generally explains how magic is stupid and fake but can be explained with physics laws and tricks.

name: Pizza Cutter of the Futuristic Ninja
description: It slices, it dices, it burns with the heat of the rising sun!

name: Vio-yo
description: This yo-yo produces a note when flung, much like that made when a bow is strung across a violin, but you're not entirely sure how. Maybe the yo-yo string is made of horsehair...

name: Stylist\'s Best Friend
description: Hair shears that dye highlights on the tips of your hair while they cut. Also dyes the tattered remains of your foes in hilarious colours.

name: Brushwalker
description: A cane in the shape of a paintbrush. Real Talk? It's a giant paintbrush.

name: Sound Slicing Windbreaker
description: This axes' blades are filled with tiny indents and crescent shaped holes. When swung, it emits a whistle that seems to cut in the direction you swung it. Try not to make music.

name: Spectral Banshee\'s Scream
description: This steaming, pump-action shotgun looks as if the barrel was a trumpet, and yet the pump is actually on a guitar neck. The strings pump out ear-shattering waves of holy-steam reinforced sound waves, blow your enemies away and ROCK their world.

name: Screech-Sticks
description: These drum-sticks practically crackle with METAL energy, knocking them together elicits a sound so great, you will either break out into a drum-solo or break your enemies' wills.

name: Foghorn Filleter
description: This straight-razor smokes and feels incredibly weightless, and yet when you cut through the air (and other things), you can hear an otherworldly, if not faint and beautiful melody.

name: Hazing Headgear
description: This mask lightly wisps in the wind, puffing smoke from the filter, feeling as if you weren't breathing through a face-constricting piece of plastic.

name: Seers\' Seeingstone
description: This opaque lanterns' flame shifts to show possible outcomes, most of them include beating whatever you didn't like with this lantern.

name: Twisting Torchholder
description: This lantern holds a small green, and flaming snake, constantly coiling and and relaxing on the wick. It's really hard to actually open the thing, but it can spit green fire through the lens, that's a bonus.

name: Laser Guided Inflata-Stud Gloves
description: These inflated gloves actual give you some pretty good jabs, and the knuckles are pretty dang pointy.

name: Deafening Drillbox
description: This drill actually drills through the sound-barrier at whatever's in front of it, hooray for the face-twister drill!

name: Spectral Spherehelm
description: This constantly spinning, glowing, and wisp vortex around your head forms to it, giving you some helmet hair, but it seems to catch or deflect most hits going towards your head.

name: Swirling Smokemail
description: These wisps of smoke gleaming with an inner-light coil endlessly around your limbs, giving you complete focus on how to make you the most lethal you can be, as for defense, they want to live like you, so they'll probably move.

name: Skull Helmet
description: Protect your cranium with this oversized cranium!

name: Plush Yoshi Hoodie
description: An unbelievably comfortable hoodie designed after the Nintendo character. Others might be tempted to ride you once you start wearing it though.

name: Animal Print Bathrobe
description: Now you can look like the suave, millionaire playboy you see on the cover of those dirty magazines.

name: Picture Frame
description: A wooden frame for holding a painting, although it's empty now. It's also pretty sturdy: getting hit over the head with it would probably hurt quite a bit.

name: Golden Picture Frame
description: An overly ostentatious picture frame made out of solid gold. It's heavy enough that it could probably outright flatten some of the smaller Underlings.

name: Compass Brush
description: For the amateur artist who can't seem to get those circles right.

name: Tomahawk of the Wolf
description: An ethereal green axe of Native American origin. Wielding it, you can call upon the powerful, fierce will of ancient Apache ancestors. And possibly wolves.

name: Magic Paintbrush
description: This large paintbrush exudes a toxic red/yellow gunk that harms the environment just as much as it hurts your enemies.

name: Jouraltop
description: The perfect computer for the writer on the go!

name: Incredibly Hard-Boiled Fedora
description: You wanna be *really* hard-boiled? How 'bout a hat made of steel? You wish you had a jacket to go with it, though.

name: Battery-Operated Fancy Santa
description: What's more scary/festive than a Fancy Santa? A battery operated one that moves on it's own, of course! You think this thing is a little frightening. But just a little.

name: Fanciful Fairytale Finery of Frivolous Frills
description: An ostentatious, whimsical parody of traditional gentleman's formalwear from the late who-gives-a-shit period. These impractically frilly sleeves doubtlessly conceal their fair share of tricks.

name: Videotape
description: An unlabeled videotape. Could be anything on here, really. Well, anything from the 20th century at least.

name: Defensive Palette
description: A large wooden shield splattered with paint and the blood of your enemies.

name: Cosplay Bunny Ears
description: Fake white rabbit ears. Very easily makes you look cute, attractive or maybe just creepy.

name: Cosplay Bunny Tail
description: A white, fluffy bunny tail. Looks really adorable with bunny ears, and really weird with any other ears.

name: Wooly Jumper
description: It's warm but kind of itchy, and it reminds you of christmas morning disappointments.

name: Blade Before Time
description: This blade is so antique it was made before time even started, but with the power of alchemy you appear to have salvaged it. It's pretty much still a piece of shit though.

name: All the Colors of the Wind
description: Can you paint with them? If you're some settler taking over native land, probably not. Makes you rethink just what you're doing to these imps, huh?

name: 1/2bowkind
description: Since your puny arms are likely too weak to make this unorthodox use of a bow by hand, you resorted to alchemy. Are you proud of yourself yet?

name: Fruit Gushers - Aggravated Andalusian Pineapple Fracture flavour
description: The fact that you've never seen a blonde Andalusian bothers you for some reason.

name: Bronco .44
description: Even if this thing could drop a Bulldozer, there will ALWAYS be a stupid Shield in your way.

name: Blazing Stallion
description: Remember all those people that told you incendiary rounds were useless save for piercing armor? Prove them wrong with this revolver's scorched barrel.

name: Mirror World
description: A globe with all of the continents mirrored. It's like a video game trope right at your fingertips!

name: Man in the Mirror
description: If you've ever wanted to drag someone to a place everything is reversed and they're the only thing living, here's your chance.

name: Umbrellance
description: This umbrella is absurdly long. It could probably cover an entire horse and rider if opened.

name: Steel Top Hat
description: Now you don't need to worry about your health AND your appearance. It's awfully heavy, though.

name: Slenderman Doll
description: A gangly life-size plush representation of a popular internet pseudo-cryptid... and a favored guest at tea parties.

name: Scouter
description: A headset with a screen covering your eye. The display shows the stats of the person or underling your looking at. It also acts as a communicator.

name: Scarecrow
description: This scary figure with malicious grin and huge scythe gives you real chills.

name: Pearl Pounder
description: For some reason, holding this hammer makes you start to wonder where it is exactly that you find all that space to hold your other items...

name: Dimensional Beatdown
description: Every hit of this hammer causes miniature inter-dimensional rifts on impact. Be careful not to let anything through from the other side!

name: Medical Nanopaste
description: This small, black polymer packet buzzes faintly in your hand. If you smash it open, the paste will help clean up your wounds. No, it's not living peanut butter.

name: MedPro-Ject
description: This small metal container gently whirs when you hold it, pressing a button analyzes your wounds, and as such helps heal them. Don't use it for the more internal stuff though, unless you like swallowing hard-light surgical tools.

name: Syrette Shooter
description: This shotgun fires large syringes, if it doesn't pin whatever you were shooting at to a wall, it'll at least give them a really bad fear of needles.

name: Doctors\' Coat
description: This long, white coat is worn by medical practitioners everywhere, and, well, by anyone who could afford a lab coat.

name: Bonesmashing Bonesaw
description: This large axe has a jagged underside of nasty metal teeth, good for ye olde medicine and ye olde letting out of the head-demons, whether your enemies want it or not.

name: Soundshatter Lightslicer
description: This axes' shaft looks more akin to a trombone, the grip being encased in brass with buttons as if to play. The head itself is covered in strings that glow and smoke lightly in the breeze, when you swing it, steaming slices of wind create a faint, beautiful chorus that's heard somewhere as if to cheer you on.

name: The Hurting
description: This nondescript red folding chair doesn't seem to dent, bend, or otherwise break no matter how much stuff you beat the crap out of, that and you feel like you could do some pretty sweet wrestling moves involving it.

name: Sundowner Shawl
description: This over-sized, red and black trench coat has has a fairly good synthetic fiber, considering you can wear it without monsters tearing you apart immediately, watch the coat-tails!

name: Studded Seater
description: This stool is literally covered all over in sharp screws along the cushion, why would you make this?

name: Paperweight Pusher
description: This over-sized, steely clothing iron is covered in chunks of iron ore and rock, it's not gonna iron anything but someones' face now.

name: Cue-tie
description: This cue is quite stunning, the laquered wood and...okay yeah, it's just a dressed up pool-cue.

name: High Frequency Scratch-Sinker
description: This carbon steel and pointed cue-stick crackles with blue electricity, you can't play pool without going into slow-motion and cutting the balls into bits either, guess you'll have to settle for wrecking your enemies.

name: The Sunsnake Coilshot
description: This pistols' barrel and slide look strangely like a snake curled around a stick, its' mouth the barrel. The eyes of the snake glow faintly with inner unlucky powers, that and it shoots light-snakes you can control in mid-air, how cool is that?

name: Magi-Cuel
description: This cue stick looks odd, with symbols carved into the wood, you look like you'd belong more in a fantasy casino holding it.

name: ME Assault Rifle
description: The Standard automatic weapon in Mass Effect. It's basically just a normal machine gun, but more sciency.

name: Familiar Hood
description: Nothing is 8luh and Everything is 8luh. Most assas... I mean, thieves and rogues would like one of these awesome looking hoodies.

name: Snake Camo
description: The white and black patterns of this camouflage body suit... you prefer not to talk about what they remind you of.

name: Sinai\'s Standardbred
description: Deliver unto your enemies fires not quite as good at racing full-speed as those of the Mount's thoroughbred, but still plenty capable of wrapping your enemies in smoke from the flames descending upon them.

name: MegaMan Zero cartridge
description: The only hope of Reploids near-overrun by Mavericks is to awaken a hunter from a bygone era, fabled to have fought by the side of the legend known as X: Zero.

name: Soddom and Gommorah
description: Two of the Ten Shining Weapons have landed in your possession: the twin arm cannons of Fighting Fefnir.

name: Amulet of Black Magic
description: The Amulet has been told to help protect the user through means of magic when worn. Or science. It's never completely clear.

name: A Marker of a Very High Degree
description: An ominous marker with a sleek design that fires ink fueled flames of pain from it's tips. Handy for your next ash art endeavor.

name: Prospitian Tip of Poking
description: A golden cue stick with two sharp edged white markers on each stick. It's far too sharp to actually use at a pool table, against your enemies though is another question entirely.

name: Froot Jooce- Now wit Nancho
description: It looks like someone just squeezed that nacho filling into a juice bottle and made a wrapper out of paper and scribbled "JOOSE" on it in crayon. Did you ever want to drink nacho flavored candy? No? Good, this should never have been made.

name: L-Face Mask
description: :L

name: Keroscribbler
description: This marker appears to be filled with lighter fluid. You could draw a flaming smily face on an imp's chest if you wanted, but it's kind of useless without a source of fire.

name: Canvasscorch
description: With this flaming paintbrush, your blazing passion for art really shows on the canvass! Especially since it sets it on fire. Hence, you know, the name.

name: Fuego de Salvador
description: The endless streams of colorful fire emitted by this stocky paintbrush are so hot, they could melt a clock!

name: Nature\'s Palette
description: It's a piece of bark slathered with sap of various colors. The sap gives it mystical NATURE powers. Seems like the kind of thing an elf artist might use.

name: Picture Pitcher
description: A gigantic, square slingshot big enough to fire entire picture frames and paintings. This'll put all those useless wall decorations to good use!

name: Smith Corona Blotspitter
description: The most powerful set of KEYS in the universe.

name: Intercontinental Ballistic Guitar
description: Rocking out with this explosive number, you'll be sure to kiloton of enemies!

name: Skullbrush
description: It looks like the skull mysterious grew a sort of ponytail brush. Figuring out how to paint with this would be a feat all in itself.

name: Shrekmono
description: A kimono with Shrek on it, hand forged by Duegars, evil dwarves who constantly hunger for rubies and gemstones. Surprisingly good armor though! For a kimono with Shrek on it.

name: POTaTOS Headset
description: Less of a headset really and more of a holder for an angry potato. On the plus side with the slight increase in power supply POTaTOS is a little grateful and spends more time insulting other people than you.

name: Sharp Stilletos
description: As if regular heels were hard enough to walk in! At least these have the added bonus of being easier to kickstab with.

name: Scary Scarecrow\'s Mask
description: Especially good for the "trick or treat" thing. Underlings will be happy to give you all their sweets. Maybe because of your burning red eyes?

name: Tora-Shinai
description: A demonic sword that will not rest until it tastes blood, still sealed by the Fujimura family. Still, useless in combat.

name: Nylon Stockings
description: Just ordinary stockings. Nothing special about them.

name: Reflective Cane
description: Strange cane that is decorated with lots of mirrors. Not sure if you can scare an imp with his distorted image...

name: Guns N\' Roses
description: Fine pistols that make you good ol' rock.

name: Rose-Tinted CompuShades
description: Hands free computing solution. Awesome looking. And guaranteed to cheer up anyone. A must have.

name: Slick Wizard\'s Fedora
description: A slick and hard-boiled hat for stylish conjurers. It emanates an eerie magical field.

name: Smoldering Jacket of Spades
description: A slick black trench coat with knives in about every pocket. It smolders like dying embers and radiates badassery and hard-boilediness.

name: Pyre Jar
description: The jar itself is hot to the touch, so you can smack your enemies with it and give them a nasty burn.

name: Pedestal
description: A marble pedestal made for holding a bust or a small sculpture. It's heavy enough that you can barely lift it, but anything you manage to hit with it will be in for a world of hurt.

name: Easel
description: A wooden stand for holding in-progress paintings. Using it as a weapon is kind of unwieldy due to its size, but it will do in a pinch.

name: Pokemon Diamond Version
description: It's a handheld game all about catching innocent critters and forcing them into battles until they fall unconscious. This one apparently has some sort of connection to time.

name: Palkiastartes Chainsword Pearl Version
description: A weapon once used by a great hero in the service of the God-Arceus.

name: Paintbrush of a Horse Attacking a Football Player
description: No matter in what manner you paint with this brush, it always seems to end up painting that majestic stallion aggrieving a champion of the gridiron.

name: Painting of a Horse Peacefully Standing by a Football Player
description: It seems you have quelled the equestrian's rage with the handbook, and the horse and football player are no longer fighting.

name: No Name
description: You received No Name from a Nobody, after a long and grueling battle. To figure out the recipe, that is.

name: Limon
description: This is where lemon-lime soda really comes from.

name: Metal Toasterang
description: The inclusion of the heating coils does little seeing as it has no power. On the bright side, it does hurt more with all of those spiked bits pointing out.

name: Laughing Skullarang
description: Cloaked in blue fire, this boomerang has a animated skull embedded in it that cackles disturbingly.

name: Lava Glowstick
description: The psychedelic floating glob of a lava lamp in the portability of a glowstick! This thing is awesome, and your new favorite light source.

name: Battery Operated Hourglass
description: The latest in hourglass technology, this model has a precisely controlled sand release aperture to ensure exact time keeping! ...Yeah, it's worthless.

name: Lodestone
description: A chunk of magnetite, the most magnetic mineral naturally occurring on Earth... or you know, that place that doesn't exist anymore.

name: Lillymon Figure
description: A small plastic sculpt of the flower themed faerie digimon.

name: Pixie Tricksterang
description: A cute pink boomerang that sparkles and flashes as it flies! Mild epilepsy warning.

name: Razor Bluemerang
description: A shiny metal boomerang that has razor sharp edges. It glows disconcertingly, and may be irradiating you currently.

name: Katana Lagann
description: FORGED FROM TWO FIREY HEARTS, THIS BLADE WILL PIERCE THE HEAVENS! (Disclaimer: Blade will not actually pierce the heavens. May pierce enemies, though.)

name: Reflective Dress
description: This dress doesn't actually have any fibers, but is instead one stylish sheet of mirror draped around you in a way that's sure to dazzle all your enemies, and quite possibly your friends, too!

name: Wing of the Thunderbird
description: This fan does more than just move the air, but also crackles with quite a bit of electricity when fully extented, and that's not even counting the slices that its bladed aspects can do. Truly, this fan calls to mind the absolute power of a storm... Well it does if you have the AA batteries to power it.

name: Hyperion Conference Call
description: A stylized shotgun of Hyperion manufacture, famed for its accuracy, efficiency, and ludicrously low drop rate. It fires projectiles that bounce from enemy to enemy and off of walls, making it deadly against larger foes in tight spaces. For when you need to ping everyone all at once.

name: His Dark Inheritance
description: A massive new and controversial tome about an empire, adventures, magic, parallel universes, a boy, his dragon, and a touch of anti-religious sentiment.

name: Frostland and Flameland Claws
description: A pair of claws that draw their power from a portal to the core of a place entirely covered in flames and a place entirely covered in ice. Yes, it's entirely possible for a planet's core to be supercold instead of superhot, shut up.

name: Bird Slingshot
description: You're pretty sure the birds are angry about this, but it's just too much fun!

name: Appleture Science Phone
description: Two of the greatest companies combine to make the Appleture Science Phone! Warning: This phone will NOT give you cancer: Only hepatitis. Homicidal AI pre-installed.

name: Aperture Science Hand Portal Device
description: Two gloves. The right glove has an blue ring on the back, and the left has an orange ring on it. It seems to create portals of the respective colors when you point at something. Just don't point out any of your friends with these on.

name: Heaven\'s Mirror Knife Inferno Launchers
description: You didn't know fire could be reflective like that. Or that the knives in the fire were reflective too. Really, this boils down to a gun that shoots infinity mirrors where each reflection gets torched and stabbed.

name: Fruit Gushers - Psychic Savant Pyrokinesis Paradise flavour
description: The box established a telepathic link when you made it and it's telling you it'll help you set shit on fire. You begin to ask yourself if it's trustworthy.

name: Whale Hoodie
description: A bulky blue hoodie with a whale on it. With the hood up, it looks like a whale is chewing on your head!

name: Telepotome
description: This book harnesses the power of science to create wormholes in space!

name: Super Sexy Fists of Fire
description: Pimps, playas, and pain purveyuhs envy your swag when you get the murder on, ya' dig?

name: Nan-ProJect Plus
description: This dispenser is the pinnacle of medical technology. The machine, when turned on uses hard light nano-bots that decompose naturally, as well as adding to healing the wound in question as they disintegrate!

name: Pyrotechnic Pokers
description: These laser guided rocket darts ignite as soon as you throw, propelling themselves quickly, too bad you're still a cheater, you cheater.

name: Silent Shears
description: These rusty, bloodied shears reek of regret, perfect for the edgy kid in any session!

name: Smokin\' Sizzler
description: This smoking spatula looks like it came out of the greasiest, smoke filled dive this side of your session. You bet you could grease your hair back with this and pick up a few bad habits.

name: Sundowner Light Seperated Shawl
description: This coat reflects light brightly into the different wavelengths offensively at anyone who dares to look in your direction.

name: Perception Screwing Seater
description: You can't look at this thing without thinking the screws and sharp bits are going INWARD, yet when you hit something blood seems to stain the screws inside, rather than out.

name: Twin Snake Tearer
description: This axes' head is comprised of two, glowing, flaming and particularly pissed off snakes. They're twice as crazy as you and you feel compelled to be at least half.

name: Slithering Snakewear Ring
description: This rave-tastic ring shoots laser snakes, which in turn shoot lasers from their laser eyes, THE RAVE OF THE FUTURE IS HEEEEERE!

name: Bladed Boomaboo
description: This eldritch boomerang writhes in your hands while you hold it, sort've like you and holding a girls' hand. OOOOOOOH!

name: Hard Light Wrestling Wrangler
description: This looks like a shitty WWE wrestling chair from the future, as such you have a hard time not trying to break it on something. You'll also have a hard time breaking it on something, considering it doesn't break.

name: Spectral Squeaker
description: This (inflated?) hammer looks transparent, and you can see what looks like a Viking rock concert going on inside of it. When you hit things you can hear a small cheer from the inside. Metal.

name: Back Master
description: This black hand chained to the end of the stick seems to hover menacingly, unfortunately you get the feeling you need to pause before actually going forward to attack and teleport your enemies back to the beginning of the dungeon...OF DEATH.

name: Stripe
description: Striped black and blue stocking, that can transform into a katana. +9999 against ghosts, yeah.

name: Smith Corona Stratocrasher
description: This is it. You've climbed this whole mountain and become a god of rock. A living legend. This is the most powerful guitar in the universe. Its strings sing at your touch, your enemies weeping at its magnificence before being blasted to ash by paradox space shattering power chords. With the Stratocrasher in your hands, you are a living legend.

name: Shitty Pin
description: OH MY GOD, it's just a shitty pin. The point isn't even that sharp. Not that you'd even want to wear it.

name: Energy Pin
description: Gives you backup energy to keep you awake. You're not really sure how this works, but it's probably not magic.

name: Pokemon Platinium Version
description: It's a handheld game containing features present in both of it's sister games. This one apparently has some sort of connection to antimatter.

name: Mjolfar
description: This mythical Nordic warhammer can now be thrown at enemies and retrieved with a simple yank of the chain! Though that's somewhat pointless, as the original weapon could already be recalled magically.

name: Wind-up Key
description: Round and round and round and round it goes...

name: Core Drill
description: This is it. A man's drill. With this, you will... what was it again... penetrate the skies? Yeah that sounds about right.

name: Key to the Heavens
description: The alchemiter allows you to bypass all that strong heart bullshit and just unlock the heavens already.

name: Luck Ticket
