description: An odd little ticket that seems to give you a second chance when the odds are against you.

name: Emergency Spellcard
description: A special spellcard to be used in the event of suboptimal situations. When met with a strong impact, it will begin to spew a near impenetrable wall of lasers. Too bad most of the stuff here isn't instakilled by this stuff.

name: Faygo - Leviathan\'s Deathbomb flavour
description: You feel like drinking this will allow you to break the rules of life and death for a little bit when the going gets tough. It'll also fuck up everything around you. You probably won't come out of the process too healthy, though, so try to save it for emergencies, if you can.

name: Silver Flesh
description: A horrible, cold lump of...meat? You don't want to know what it has in it that restores your aspect powers.

name: Leaf Wings
description: Green wings perfect for photosynthesis. Or cosplay, if that's your thing.

name: Lillymon Dress
description: A pretty pink ensemble made out of flowers! A nice homage to the Digimon series.

name: Jeweled Skull Staff
description: It might just be the mysteriously dangerous vibes from the skull, or the sheer value of the jewels embedded in it, but this staff sure packs a wallop!

name: Ravetastic Knife
description: A trusty blade forged from a broken off mailbox danglybit and a whole lot of cheap glowsticks. It emits a radioactive glow and is no doubt bad for you, but totally fun at parties. Knife parties.

name: Pokemon Black Version
description: So there's two games, Black and White, and two mascot Pokemon, one black and one white... and this game has the white one. Makes sense to me.

name: Butterfly Plush
description: A cute and colorful plush butterfly toy. You may have outgrown this a long time ago, but there's still plenty of alchemy potential in it!

name: Pokemon Orange Version - Special Volcarona Edition
description: An unusual, nonexistant Pokemon game from the most recent generation in the series: it seems to replace your choice of starter Pokemon with the Bug/Fire type moth, Volcarona.

name: White King\'s Staff
description: The staff of an unprototyped White King is, while not as powerful as it could be, is a force to be reckoned with.

name: Volcarona\'s Vengeance
description: "I swear, call me Dorito God one more time and I'll bash your face in."

name: Magnemite Toy
description: You'd use it as a weapon if it weren't for the fact that it has a built in AI.

name: Tron: Legacy DVD
description: DVD of the popular Sci-Fi movie Tron: Legacy. May or may not be pirated. Who cares? The only thing about this movie worth pirating is the cool special effects.

name: Robotic Rebel Robes
description: A short-sleeved hoodie that cuts off just beneath the ribs. It's covered in a neat pattern of neon lines that shimmer white. It has a socket on the back perfect for fitting disckind weapons. The socket can also any typical strifekind, such as bladekind, chainkind, pistolkind and fancysantakind. Although a fancysantakind has never been known to actually fit inside the socket, you can still try. Gold star.

name: Minecraft CD
description: A copy of the popular sandbox game Minecraft. Guarantees a lot of swearing and "GODDAMNIT YOU DAMN CREEPERS".

name: Wooden Minecraft Sword
description: A pixellated sword from the popular sandbox game Minecraft. Although it's the weakest of the swords, with some fine tuning it has potential to be a formidable blade.

name: Pokemon Chainsaw Volcarona Edition
description: The teeth are in the shape of doritos/moth wings, which is a nice touch.

name: Timeline Bow
description: A bow used in the memory of someone special. This bow is laden with memories, strength and time. With it, you can end suffering.

name: The Bandana Code
description: This handy little rag accepts voice commands and projects a small screen for the user.

name: Swiss Army Gloves
description: Cool fingerless gloves, but powerful and handy like the famous multitool knife!

name: Spectral Pain
description: A ghost Wrench!... Are Wrench even alive? How can it have a ghost without have been alive?? Well, it can smash Imp, who cares the anomalous nature of this thing. The bad part is that sometimes they come back...

name: Soviet Sickle
description: Get a warm hat, it's going to be a cold war.

name: Shuraba
description: This is one fancy sword. It seems to be possessed by demons, but when it's this cool, who CARES?

name: Sawstaff
description: It's a chainsaw attached to a staff, what else could be better?

name: Roukanken
description: "The things that cannot be cut by this sword, forged by youkai, are close to none!" Or at least, so you've been told. It's a pretty long sword for a one handed weapon.

name: Hakurouken
description: Shorter than its sibling Roukanken, it has the power to dispel the confusion of those it cuts. Or rather, using it on ghosts will cause them to attain enlightenment, and using it on living beings will only cause discomfort and a bit of pain.

name: Pearly Plasma Chainsword
description: The plasma bolts fired by this chainsaw/sword/gun/video game can rend holes in space, which probably isn't very healthy for anyone nearby.

name: Gas Lantern
description: An old-fashioned, gas-powered, hand-held lantern. Its main uses are the fact that it's heavy and the fact that it has a tendency to set things on fire.

name: Advanced Gas Lantern
description: A more modern, chemically-fuelled version of the gas lantern. Probably very dangerous to everyone, including you.

name: Rosy Hollow CompuMask
description: A scary looking white mask with rosy lenses over the eye-holes and computing capabilites. Most awesome hands free computing solution you'll find.

name: Chandelantern
description: A fancy lantern based on the Pokmon Chandelure. Unlike Chandelure, it's neither mobile nor sentient, and it doesn't suck out your soul to use as fuel... probably.

name: Lava Ink Lantern
description: A psychedelic lantern that lets you write multicolored, glowing messages and symbols in the air with its tip.

name: Jeweled Pagoda of RAZORS
description: A magical jeweled pagoda that shoots a barrage of homing lasers at your enemies which, upon impact, explode into several wildly flailing razors. Science weeps before the sheer effectiveness of magic.

name: Combat Light-Show Lantern
description: A lantern that holographically displays fierce battle between a horse and a football player. If you're fighting imps they'll probably just ignore you to watch it, really. They may even share some popcorn with you, if you're nice.

name: Robes of the XIII
description: Allows travel between corridors of time. Gives you a pretty sweet look, too. They also sorta look like really fancy, dark bathrobes.

name: Hard-Light Combat Lantern
description: This lantern uses hard-light to summon a mighty stallion and a rugged football player to duke it out on the battlefield, annihilating anything caught in the fray. Try to hope they don't sort out their differences when you're being eaten by basilisks.

name: Sterilization Lantern
description: A lantern with a bizarre magic broom core. When you turn it on, it'll instantly begin scrubbing chunks out of any unclean surface in front of it with high-powered, star-shaped lasers. Try not to put your hands in front of it if you haven't showered within the past 5 seconds.

name: Slot Sweeper
description: A hand broom with a slot machine embedded in its side. It unfortunately only has one outcome to it, three brooms, so it's useless. At least the slot machine makes it unbelievably heavy.

name: Octet Sweeper
description: A hand broom that comes with a fluorite-octet-themed slot machine in it that is capable of 8^3 different magical attacks based on the outcome. Legend has it that it will give you better results if you can prove your worth against the forces of grime.

name: Hidden Broomsword
description: A sword that uses a broom as both a hilt and a sheathe. A perfect dual-pronged assault against any imps prototyped with dust bunnies.

name: Reactor Broomsword
description: A broomsword with a powerful magical reactor crafted into its hilt. Aside from costing a lot more grist to make, it charges the blade with a mystic power every time you sheathe it. Great for that laido stuff.

name: Great Maid\'s Hand Broom
description: A time-stopping pocketwatch that has had its entire outside covered in bristles. The question is, does making this watch a cleaning implement make you a truly better maid?

name: Black Queen\'s Ring Replica
description: A replica of the ring worn by the queen of Derse. Doesn't provide any of the powers or prototypings that the real one does, but it still makes for a neat piece of jewellery, especially when the orbs are all lit up.

name: Red Miles
description: A branching red whip with a golden handle that tears through anything it touches. Sadly doesn't have quite the range or inescapability of its namesake, but it's still pretty damn powerful.

name: Pole Lantern
description: A lantern on the end of a long stick, all the better for bonking imps on the head with.

name: Candlestick
description: A fairly hefty candlestick made out of some kind of metal. Try not to murder any of your sessionmates with it.

name: Candelabra
description: Three arms mean three candles and three times the light. And perhaps more relevantly to your situation, it also means three times the weight as well.

name: Chandelier
description: A plain three-armed chandelier. Wielded by the chain it's supposed to hang from, this thing makes for a surprisingly effective makeshift flail.

name: Spiked Chandelier Flail
description: An ornate chandelier covered in more spikes than your average Gothic mansion. The flaming candles just add insult to injury for whoever you smash it into.

name: Trigun DVD
description: 26 episodes about a man named "Vash the Stampede" and the two Bernardelli Insurance Society employees who follow him around in order to minimize the damages inevitably caused by his appearance.

name: Energy \'Rang
description: It's like a light saber, but in throwable, returning form! How do you hold it without burning yourself, though...?

name: Yoyorang
description: A boomerang on a string. Seems kinda redundant since it comes back anyway, but it's easier to control, and surprisingly powerful.

name: Electric Greatsword
description: A proud weapon filled with the power of a mighty viking sword and the energy of an electric guitar. There's a valhalla joke in here somewhere...

name: Yellow Paint
description: A can of sunshine in paint form. You could paint something with it... or just save yourself the trouble and combine the paint with the desired object via alchemy.

name: Green Paint
description: You did it. You learned how to mix colors to make new colors. This skill should prove to be very useful when saving the world.

name: Orange Paint
description: Orange you glad you combined those two colors?

name: Red Ring
description: A sturdy red-colored ring. That's all there really is to say on the matter.

name: Blue Ring
description: A sturdy blue-colored ring. That's all there really is to say on the matter.

name: Yellow Ring
description: A sturdy yellow-colored ring. That's all there really is to say on the matter.

name: Purple Ring
description: A sturdy Purple-colored ring. That's all there really is to say on the matter.

name: Green Ring
description: A sturdy green-colored ring. That's all there really is to say on the matter.

name: Orange Ring
description: A sturdy orange-colored ring. That's all there really is to say on the matter.

name: Indigo Paint
description: Ok, now you're starting to get a bit reckless with your color combinations.

name: Indigo Ring
description: A sturdy indigo-colored ring. That's all there really is to say on the matter.

name: Captain Planet Poster
description: A poster depicting a fictional pollution-fighting superhero and his 5 sidekicks, each one specializing in the elements of Fire, Water, Earth, Wind, and Heart. Best not to ask about that last one.

name: Lantern of Heart
description: This lantern channels the mysterious and arguably most powerful of the elements, Heart. It governs emotions of all kinds and gives the user the power to manipulate the feelings of others.

name: Green Lantern
description: A shining green lantern with matching ring. Allows the user to harness the power of will.

name: Yellow Lantern
description: A shining yellow lantern with matching ring. Allows the user to harness the power of fear.

name: Orange Lantern
description: A shining orange lantern with matching ring. Allows the user to harness the power of avarice.

name: Red Lantern
description: A shining red lantern with matching ring. Allows the user to harness the power of rage.

name: Blue Lantern
description: A shining blue lantern with matching ring. Allows the user to harness the power of hope.

name: Indigo Lantern
description: A shining indigo lantern with matching ring. Allows the user to harness the power of compassion.

name: Violet Lantern
description: A shining violet lantern with matching ring. Allows the user to harness the power of love.

name: Imagination Station
description: A game device that can display anything you can imagine. Only comes in green.

name: Chandefear
description: This pale yellow chandelier burns with a vermillion flame that strikes fear in the hearts of those who gaze upon it. Best used with sunglasses.

name: Mine Precious
description: An all-powerful ring that causes the wearer to never give it up, driving them mad with avarice.

name: Rainbow Lantern
description: This incandescent flashing lantern allows you to utilize the power of ALL of the emotions! All of them.

name: Streetlight
description: How did you get this? More importantly, how are you HOLDING it??

name: Snow Crash
description: A slim volume on virtual reality hacking, Sumerian linguistics, and epic sword moves. Refund not provided for brain damage sustained while reading.

name: Book of Philosophy
description: A hefty book detailing the thoughts and theories of many great and ancient philosophers.

name: Diogenes\' Lantern
description: I am looking for an honest man.

name: Illuminated Hourglass of RAZORS
description: This brightly glowing hourglass contains not sand, but a mysterious liquid filled with what looks like tiny little straight razors. It spews out razor-propagating lasers like the Pagoda did, but when you flip it upside-down, it can even shoot them backwards through time to retroactively murder things. Good luck trying to dodge that, shrine maiden imps.

name: Witch Hat
description: A floppy witch hat that seems to at least contain enough magic to shield you from moderately strong blows. No self-respecting magic user should be caught dead without one.

name: Ordinary Magician Hat
description: A magical witch's hat from the great land of illusion itself. You feel like you'd die if you ever took this off. The immense amounts of magical power stored in it is making you feel kind of reckless, too.

name: Star in a Sphere
description: A small star contained in a hardy crystal ball. Fortunately for you, it seems to be capable of focusing its powerful beam in front of you, rather than at everything around it.

name: Green Star Sphere
description: A crystal ball with a cueball cover and a poolcue-themed handle for safe handling. This...lantern, for lack of a better term, contains what appears to be a barely contained piece of a green sun. It seems like even the cueball is struggling to hold back it's power...

name: Emergency Flare Lantern
description: Lighting this lantern propels it high into the air while flashing brightly, allowing you to call for aid from any nearby sessionmates. Or you could point it horizontally instead of vertically and send it rocketing into your enemies instead.

name: Mach 5 Rocket Razor
description: For once the name isn't hyperbole: this razor actually does travel at about five times the speed of sound, thanks to the built-in rocket engine. You probably shouldn't actually try to use it for shaving, though.

name: Pierobe
description: Congratulation's, you just combined a pie with a bathrobe. Good Job. Science and bad fashion sense are surely smiling down upon you.

name: Freezerang
description: Only a cold hearted person would use this chilling boomerang to send their enemies back to the cooler. Just thinking about it makes me shiver.

name: Coatca Cola
description: A coat of ever unbreakable* aluminum. Not comfortable in the slightest.

name: Fortune\'s Die
description: Each face has one of the Major Arcana on it. It's theorized one can determine their own fate with one throw of these dice.

name: Bloodedge Hoodie
description: A deep red hoodie with black metal plating. Seems incomplete, somehow.

name: Pocket Watchtop
description: An easy, portable computing and timekeeping device for all those Victorian buffs!

name: Undead Handcannon
description: A heavy looking piece of cast iron that fires miniature skulls.

name: Rose Print Dress
description: A lovely dress with a rose print. Looks more like something you could have bought in a store rather than alchemized, but oh well.

name: Spiffy Dragon Blazer
description: Well don't you look handsome in this nice little blazer? It even has little wings on the back!

name: Midnight Suit
description: With this suit, you can be a night owl and a wise bird too. And then maybe stab someone.

name: iPad
description: All the form of an iPhone, all the function of a computer. So trendy. So hip.

name: Chocolate Cane
description: It's ye olde cane but made from melty chooclate? You don't even know what the deal is with that.

name: Tronpan
description: A regular pan decked out with the special effects from Tron. Or possibly another sci-fi movie, you can't really tell.

name: Geisha Doll
description: This doll now has some features. Now many Social Justice Bloggers will argue that this doll is asian stereotyping.

name: RainSaw
description: When you unfold this umbrella a large number of menacing teeth start rapidly spinning around the canopy. The handle also produces petrol fumes, try not to breathe in.

name: Shuggoth\'s White Deck
description: These cards are pure white on one side, and the darkest black on the other. While you hold them, you begin to hear the Horrorterrors whispering to you, speaking dark secrets and terrifying fortunes.

name: Bottled Judgement
description: Drink this, and you might just be able to trick the bridesmaid.

name: Majora\'s Hammer
description: A hammer with dark powers. No one really knows how it works.

name: Legend of Zelda: Twilight Princess Disk
description: Join Link in a brand new half-HD adventure to save the land of Hyrule!

name: Sniper Joe\'s Helmet
description: Guaranteed to make any Protomen fan break down in tears.

name: The Spadaccino\'s Sweetest Tooth
description: A sword with an elongated candy corn for a blade. Don't aim for the mouth, or you might end up swordless.

name: Artists Agony
description: Despite its chipped and seemingly dull edge, this axe seems to deal as much damage as any other. Perhaps it has something to do with its garish paint job and anguish of centuries dead artists.

name: Ember Shot
description: A not so great weapon, but will light something on fire. Even if it is you.

name: Cardcaptor Sakura DVD Set
description: An anime series about a magical girl named after cherry blossoms.

name: Clow Cards
description: A set of magical cards, each one holding captive a powerful spirit.

name: tRUSTY Key
description: You don't know what this could be a key to. Possibly a long forgotten door from a mystical realm. Or it could just be really old from your mom's basement. Who knows!

name: Three Foot Angel
description: It is reminiscent of a powerful enemy from another realm... unfortunately, its most prominent quality is being a shitty yardstick.

name: CRITICALLY PANNED
description: We here at X-Play give this game a 1...out of 5.

name: Glow Shears
description: Cut your enemies' lights with these starry scissors.

name: Death By Sugar
description: If Candyland had the three fates, this is no doubt what they would use to snip the presumably delicious licorice lifestrings of the sugar-sweet inhabitants. Do not lick.

name: Scissors of Atropos
description: Atropos, most feared of the three Fates, chose the manner and the time of each living creature's death. No living creature could hide from her: with her tools in hand, they can no longer hide from you.

name: Cairo Dress
description: A vibrant green dress with flashy trim that resonates with the rhythms of time and space. It tends to rip when temporal distortions and paradoxes are involved, though, so this may not be the best attire for shaking things up.

name: Chainsaw Necklace
description: Just like the lipstick, this necklace transforms to a chainsaw at the wielder's will. Granted, a smallish and kind of weak chainsaw, but who wouldn't want to wear a chainsaw around their neck?

name: Felt Belt
description: While most belts are made of hard leather, this one is composed of soft, green felt. Great for keeping your pants up during those pesky paradoxes.

name: Dream Bubble Castor
description: This wand seems to be able to conjure up bubbles containing the infinite memories of the dead, and then weaponize them.

name: PogoGun
description: While it doesn't pack that much of a punch, its power can be increased by pumping the pump faster and faster.

name: Dungeontop
description: A grim laptop covered in ornate ironwork. Seems to radiate magic, and never runs out of power! Comes pre-loaded with E-tools for your D&D needs.

name: Volcarona Sun Lantern
description: This lantern shines as brightly as the sun does. It could be substituted for the sun in dark times, just like a Volcarona!

name: Wheatley Lantern
description: This little Lantern looks just like everyone's favorite Personality Sphere, Wheatley! You have the nagging feeling it's going to betray you at some point...

name: Journey: Collector\'s Edition
description: A downloadable game by thatgamecompany. It's simplistic playstyle and emotional allegory has placed it in high regard, although the only goal is to reach a mountain in the distance.

name: Drawing of a Triforce
description: Isn't that lovely? You're wondering what porwerful stuff could be done with this simple drawing.

name: Hoodtop
description: Pretty self explanatory: a hoodie which displays a laptop screen in front of your face, and a keyboard in front of your hands. Unfortunately, portability comes at the price of performance.

name: A Mother\'s Dress
description: It smells like sunflowers and old memories, why you are smelling it is beyond anyone.

name: Lemon Leather Jacket
description: A bright yellow and lemony-fresh leather jacket which still manages to make you look cool.

name: Doctor Who Glasses
description: Headwear, allowing you to see time and space around you. Increases defense via making you more aware of your surroundings.

name: Headtop
description: A portable computer that makes hands-free communication and computation a breeze!

name: T51b Power Armor of Love
description: A mechanised breastplate of vibrant pink hue. Confers +2 to BALLS (but not really)

name: Whale Beanie
description: A plush beanie that resembles a whale. Not only does it not protect you, but it looks kind of dorky.

name: 3AM Suit
description: A snazzy, starry suit for all your spiffy space-related needs!

name: Tales of Symphonia Disc
description: The story of a group of chosen friends who cross the boundaries of dimensions to save the world they love from a giant meteor. Sound familiar?

name: Hula Hoop
description: A colorful plastic hoop which you attempt to whirl around your waist.

name: Sonic Spatula
description: A spatula with a relatively normal handle, but it's blade is made of sonic energy. Perfect for when you want to flip your flapjacks with a piercing shriek.

name: Laser Cane Sword
description: You feel like a classy gentleman from the future who has to protect himself from the future.

name: iPan
description: A frying pan with all of the computing and telecommunications power of an iPhone. Want to cook breakfast while texting your friends "Good morning"? There's a pan for that.

name: Mumei
description: A pair of incredibly sharp blades. An unknown forger's seal is stamped in the pommels.

name: Lagiacrus Puppet
description: A menacing sea-serpent puppet with gleaming red eyes and dagger-like teeth. Holding it feels a little electric?

name: Diamond Pickaxe
description: It's a pixellated diamond pickaxe, excellent for breaking large cubes into smaller cubes. If you prototyped with anything shaped like a box, you're gonna have a good time with this.

name: Amporan Lantern Ring
description: In deepest wwavve In darkest trench this ring wwill help savve many a wwench but not only that it shoots lasers wwoww! It wwill surely make your enemies disappear wwith a poww!

name: Righteous Agathian Bearded Axe
description: This sterling silver axe is lined with gold on the finer in-laid details, and you feel chivalrous and the need to scream "AGATHA!" At the top of your lungs.

name: Agathian Heavy-Plate
description: This polished silver and gold armor exudes and reflects light, if the enemies don't get blinded seeing you coming, your weapon will be the next to last thing they see.

name: Smoking Ninja Outfit
description: This grey on black armored ninja armor exudes smoke seemingly from the fabric itself, the amount of smoke, however, is great enough to confuse most foes into striking where you HAVE been.

name: Fuzzy Spotted Yo-yo
description: Guaranteed to make you look ridiculous while keeping your palms nice and sweaty.

name: Grinning Gasmask
description: Protects you from lethal laughing gas, all the while expressing your joy for those dying around you!

name: Shitty fake diamond sword
description: This sword is even more shitter then the usual shitty sword. You thought the shitty sword and fake diamond is going to cancel out well it became worse.

name: Time Tunnel Goggles
description: With these goggles, you can see a few seconds into the future. It makes you battle better.

name: Mini AC Unit
description: For keeping you cool in the summer.

name: Molecular Resonator
description: The sheer volume and bass of this OUTRAGEOUS sound system can cause enemies' atomic structure to break apart. It is used in concerts by only the most prestigious bands.

name: Hexagonal Digislyce
description: Using the interface of the .hack GU games, along with the edge of a scythe, the green tinted blade features omnidirectional slicing as well as mysterious properties.

name: Kujo Cap
description: Make everyone around you uncertain of where your hair ends and your hat begins!

name: Flamesaw
description: I got tired of my old chainsaw, so I put flames on it.

name: Dungeonmaster\'s Staff
description: The dungeonmaster's staff is a weapon as old as roleplaying itself, and is intended to create the ulimate escape. Mostly what it really does is make you slightly sadistic and look like you are the one in charge at role-playing sessions

name: Arch Welder
description: This crooked staff has the great ability to shoot forth a dragon's flames! Not really, but it can burn the shit out of someone if you get close

name: Scaly Overcoat
description: This coat grants it's wearer the ability to look like a brave hunter without actually having killed and skinned any large reptiles. It also is pretty damn tough and fire resistant, but those are less visible qualities

name: Armor of Godoka
description: The dress worn by hope herself, Madoka, after becoming something along the lines of a god.

name: Homura\'s Glasses
description: You instantly feel more moe just putting these on.

name: Eridan\'s Yaoi Chin
description: Wwell it seems that Sol and Vvris are in for quite a surprise~

name: Uber Yardstick
description: Well look at this brave little toaster. Returning from what is known as Blah's disapproval.

name: Hair Dryer
description: Although it's vaguely shaped like a gun, using it as one won't do you much good unless your enemies happen to be made of ice. Better just to hit things with it instead.

name: Extreme Hair Dryer
description: On fire still counts as dry, right?

name: Hair Brush
description: A brush for taming (or teasing) you luscious locks.

name: Toothbrush
description: A dainty brush for taming (or teasing) your pearly white teeth. Unless you follow your dentist's directions.

name: Bottle of Perfume
description: A fashionable-looking bottle containing an attractively-scented perfume.

name: Magical Key Lime File
description: Pale green with a dab of whipped cream, this nail file smells delicious. Why would anyone use it for a pedicure?

name: Lipstick
description: An off-brand lipstick from a drug store that isn't worth remembering, really. Finding a practical use for this in battle could very well make you a worthy warrior by that alone.

name: Glow-in-the-Dark Lipstick
description: You look absolutely ridiculous with this gunk on your lips. You're not sure it's that healthy, either.

name: Starshine Armageddon Passion
description: A fanciful name for a lipstick, yet a rather accurate one. This experimental lipstick has a nasty tendency to embed horrible, horrible plasma into any surface not previously shielded by its complimentary supply of supernova-resistant wax.

name: Horrible Lipstick
description: Lipstick fused with what may very well be the embodiment of ugliness to create what may be the worst shade of lipstick ever conceived. The great lords and ladies of fashion from before the end of the world have now hit 60 RPM in their stone tombs.

name: Starshine Delight of the Sleuthgod
description: When you apply this to your lips you will begin to feel the very forces of charisma fortifying your strength with their almighty flames. This thing will also fire stars of pure personal charm at stuff if you swing the tube around wildly enough.

name: Galatic Soul Bog Dirge
description: A lipstick tube capable of generating a straight tear in space a centimeter in diameter and a good 7 meters long. Basically cuts cleanly through anything and deposits the remains in a very star-filled section of space.

name: Magypsy Lipstick
description: A tube of Lipstick containing an odd power within it. You feel as though it is only half of a duo of items that would be capable of doing a far better job of healing together than this does alone. Such a shame, that.

name: Mauve Illusion of the Leviasleuth (with added sparkle)
description: A tube of lipstick that contains the power of several gods from all ends of history and fiction trying to one-up each other to fuel your strength. As petty as it all feels, you aren't exactly complaining about the gods of the land of illusion trying to one up the forces of charisma by murdering any nearby acherons.

name: Truly Awful Lipstick
description: It turns out the bar for the worst lipstick imaginable was quite a bit higher than you thought. Did you know that apparently a tile-texture of Hella jeff's face is a shade of beige? Can something even BE a shade of beige? This lipstick defies all notions of colour coordination and logic.

name: Curling Iron
description: This device is useful for giving your hair those adorable Shirley Temple curls. It can also burn pretty bad.

name: Nailfire
description: This fireaxe's blade is covered in emery. You have no idea why you thought this would be a good idea, but hey, it'll still do some damage, at least. And you can still file your nails with it!

name: 24-Karat Diamond Ring
description: A large diamond certainly leaves an impression. Figuratively and literally.

name: Acid Perfume
description: Sadly, the smell of dissolving Underlings overpowers the nice cherry scent of the liquid inside.

name: Mascara
description: With this slim tube of mascara, red carpet-ready beauty will be yours. If you don't stab yourself in the eye first, that is.

name: Gravity-Defying Quantum Volume Mascara
description: Lengthens, defines, and thickens your lashes with the power of science.

name: Wands of Blackest Black
description: These wands seem to crackle with an aura that absorbs all light and makes you look fabulous.

name: Red Wine Vinegar
description: A bottle of red wine vinegar. Drinking it may give you bragging rights, but will do nothing good for you.

name: Baking Soda
description: This box of powder has many uses, the most popular of which are baking and deodorizing.

name: Science Fair Model Volcano
description: This tiny, homemade volcano which will surely impress the judges. Surely.

name: Pyroclastic Perfume
description: Hidden inside this obsidian spraybottle with fiery ornamentation is the fire and ash of a pyroclastic flow. You shall spray such sweetly-scented woe upon your enemies!

name: PK Lovolver
description: A gun designed to shoot blasts of PK Love at the opponent. Jesus that thing is powerful. Be careful or you're going to kill someone with that thing.

name: Giga-Drill Spear
description: A spear truly fated to pierce the heavens. Comes with two modes: Dig and BREAK.

name: Scalpel Sword
description: If there was a such thing as a 15th century surgeon, this would be the tool they'd use. You can never tell if the dried blood on its blade is of a friend's or a foe's.

name: Cirno Figurine
description: A figurine of the self-proclaimed strongest ice fairy. Careful with those wings - they are sharp!

name: American Flag
description: You proudly wave the banner of the home of the (mostly) free.

name: Toastertop
description: A computerized toaster, which gives you internet access as it spits out toast.

name: The Dark Side of the Moon Poster
description: A poster of the cover art from Pink Floyd's Dark Side of the Moon.

name: Embersaw
description: Certainly a marvel of modern alchemy! The ember saw is a rather underwhelming flamechainsaw...since its barely on fire at all. But goddamnit it's a flaming chainsaw and that's amazing enough for now.

name: Laser Staff
description: This staff emits light in all directions, blinding anyone who looks directly at it and bathing everything around in a red light. Sneaking up on someone with this is impossible.

name: Daruma Doll
description: A round Japanese doll of the Bodhidharma, typically acquired with its eyes left unpainted. One eye is painted in when you make a wish, the other eye is painted in when the wish is granted.

name: Kindergarten ColoreDARTS
description: A full set of colorful darts. Maybe you can make pretty pictures with them, too.

name: Discoball
description: A sparkly, mirrored ball which turns your room into a magical starscape. Damnit, now you want to dance to some ABBA.

name: Lord\'s Partizan
description: A shining spear typically wielded by starting Lord Partizans in The World. Capable of rapid assaults or charge-and-release burst attacks.

name: Faygo - Golden Experience flavour
description: This swirling yellow beverage seems almost luminescent in its bottle. You suspect pouring it on the ground would cause assorted insects to appear.

name: Ursa Major Hat
description: A comfy hat with stars speckled on it.

name: Fencing Glove
description: A single leather glove that is worn to protect a fencer's weapon hand.

name: Spiked Boots
description: Useful when dealing with mutated cockroaches.

name: Children Record CD
description: Boys and girls, face forwards. It's a CD with a few tracks from the Kagerou Project. The red eyes on the disc give you the creeps.

name: Laser Show
description: This makes the laser go everywhere! Now everybody's blind!

name: Nurse\'s Scalpel
description: One of the scalpels used by the nurses in Silent Hill.

name: Robes of Shrieking
description: In contrast to the Armor of the Sun, these robes are decorated with designs that would cause any Void player to KILL in order wear them. The fact that Horrorterror screams can sometimes be heard emanating from them probably doesn\\\'t help.

name: Cosbytop Computer
description: This thing is probably a useless piece of shit, but making it has caused you to feel an alarming sense of satisfaction.

name: Ness\' T shirt
description: A t-shirt that a legendary hero wore in a quest to save the world... or that's what you like to think about this t-shirt. It's a lot better than a normal t-shirt, and it's really resistant.

name: Wikia Pin
description: A pin that is bestowed ONLY upon the Wikia helpers.

name: Welcome to Night Vale Recording
description: A recording of a few episodes of the community radio program, 'Welcome to Night Vale,' although one that appears to be slightly corrupted with white noise. Goodnight, dear listeners.

name: Amulethead Darts
description: The ones you throw give your enemies a magical shock. Those in your hand retain some protective powers.

name: Checkered Scarf
description: Should be pretty self explanatory, but this is a scarf of black and white checkered design.

name: Sweet Ketchup
description: Condiment that is very appreciated on hamburgers and hot dogs.

name: Vash\'s Coat
description: Wearing the coat of the Humanoid Typhoon, you feel nigh invulnerable.

name: Gangbangarang
description: A malicious boomerang that uses powerful shadow majykks to replicate itself. The copies then proceed to surround the target and explode.

name: Burial At Sea
description: A stone anchor with an epitaph engraved around it. Time to drown your sorrows.

name: Sanguinary Scissors
description: This scissors' dark magic could overcome your sane mind into a blood-thirsty psychopath... Be sure to think over this before wielding it or you'll be awkwardly bathing in your victim's blood.

name: Yu Yu Hakusho: The Complete Series
description: A set of DVDs containing the entirety of the Yu Yu Hakusho series, a show revolving around a young boy who died and consequentially became a detective of a place called spirit world. It started out mostly comedic and ramped up to a mostly action focused show rather quickly, you feel like you've seen that before somewhere else.

name: Ancient Draconic Blade
description: A sword from the lost ages, with faded draconic designs covering it.

name: Tron Headgear
description: Perfect headgear for navigating the dangerous lands known as the grid! Take down the MCP today!

name: Compu-Goggles
description: Not just the goggles you needed, but most certainly the goggles deserved too. They function as both a computer and a snazzy set of mind bogglingly awesome goggle modules.

name: Parawand
description: An umbrella that was used by only the best of magicians. It is so powerful that you almost forget that magic isn't real.

name: Dual Scope Dual Shot Compass Bow
description: A crazy bow that allows you to fire two arrows in two directions at once! ...as long as you don't mind firing at a 90 degree angle.

name: Pan-Galactic Pan-Pan....Pan
description: Expensive and bad for the head, this pan drastically increases the alcohol content of anything cooked in it.

name: Invisibility Cloak
description: Your Father left this in my possession before he died. It is time it was returned to you. Use it Well.

name: Slice of Watermelon
description: A sweet, summery treat.

name: Watermelon Rondels
description: These summery daggers have needle-fine pink tips ideal for piercing armor. Watch out for the seeds.

name: Embroidery Hoop
description: A hoop-shaped frame used to stretch fabric for cross-stitch and embroidery.

name: Mistletoe
description: A bundle of this parasitic plant was hanging over a doorway in your home last Christmas. It brings back memories you'd like to forget.

name: Big league Bat
description: A kinda cooler bat than a normal one. This bat looks like it could have had cork put into the core! (but instead it has some metallic stuff put into the core)

name: Shopping Cart
description: Did you just steal this from a supermarket?

name: MarioKart 64 Cart
description: Mario based Racing game for the Nintendo 64.

name: Aperture Science Quantum Powered Cleaner
description: A very scientific broom which sometimes has a few SMALL sideeffects, like bringing garbage instead or disintegrating what is touched... But now it is made of lunar rock!

name: Aperture Science Literal Vacuum Cleaner
description: Rather than using a fan to suck up dust, this device uses portals to exploit the pressure difference between your house and the moon, transporting your dirt into outer space! Caution: using it for extended periods in an enclosed space may result in a lethal lack of oxygen.

name: Hoverboard
description: A skateboard that hovers instead of rolling. Seems like it's real after all.

name: Anti-Master Sword
description: As you alchemize the Anti-Master Sword, you are teleported into The Surface next to your new sword: a weird guy with an asymmetrical haircut, purple eyeshadow, and a weird diamond suit, who keeps trying to lick you... I'm kidding. At least you're not in SS Link's shoes...

name: Princess Dress
description: Slipping into this dress transports you to a whole new world, filled with magic and adventure: you're the heir to the throne and one day you'll marry a prince... yeah, you aren't even fooling yourself anymore.

name: Starcraft CD
description: A classic real-time strategy computer game with a hardcore, competitive playerbase.

name: Overlord Tentacle
description: Sure to give you all the control you need over a small group of vicious, swarming beasts.

name: Pokemon Red White and Blue Version
description: This Pokemon game features the patriotic bird Braviary as its mascot, and takes place in the greatest region on Earth: the Merca Region.

name: Pylon
description: A large, floating crystal that radiates psychic energy. This doesn't seem all that useful on its own, but a voice inside your head keeps telling you to make more of them...

name: Psionic Blades
description: A pair of wrist-mounted blades made of pure psionic energy, perfect for ripping organic matter to shreds. Or any kind of matter, really.

name: Hella Mustard
description: This and ketchup go together like... ketchup and mustard.

name: Water Wings
description: To help children float in the water. Why do you even have these? I suppose you can try to smother your enemies with these...

name: Inflatable Mattress
description: This incredibly shitty excuse for a bed never seems to keep the air in it for long enough periods of time. Still, it's fun to use it to smack imps off of cliffs with its large size.

name: Beach Ball
description: A fun item for almost any occasion, the most obvious being the beach.

name: Life-Sized Inflatable Nic Cage
description: You feel uncomfortable yet extremely satisfied that you made this.

name: Inflatable d20
description: This d20 is huge, but you're unsure as to how it'd be useful as a weapon.

name: Colossal Airbag
description: Using the power of nuclear weaponry, this giant airbag will expand so quickly that your enemies will be sent flying for miles: maybe even into space! Good luck getting the grist, though.

name: inflaTABLLE
description: The question you're asking is why it is a table

name: Inflatable Pegasus Wings
description: With these strapped to your back, you're sure to float through the air! Or maybe just water. Yeah, these are pretty much useless.

name: Puffy Thundercloud Studbumpers
description: Crackling with electricity and studded with charged metal spikes, these gloves give you a punch that rivals the might of Zeus himself!

name: Squeak Chop
description: Introducing... Squeak Chop! The latest in inflatable mealtime hammer technology that grinds your ingredients and enemies into powder with every smash! Want to spice up your strifes AND your supper at the same time? Then the Squeak Chop is for you!

name: Inflatable Mattchess
description: An inflatable mattress with a checkerboard print, so you can play chess in your sleep. And best of all, it's king-sized!

name: Double-Tempered W
description: One half of this inflatable letter W is coursing with heat, the other half is freezing to the touch. Hold it in the middle and you have a two-pronged attack of two temperatures! (oh wait, that was the wrong letter to alliterate with. whoops.)

name: The Cagey Doctor
description: A poster depicting Nicholas Cage as a hypothetical Twelfth Doctor. Is this the world you want to live in?

name: The Nick of Time
description: He's always there for you.

name: Poetry Book
description: It's a book filled with poems of greatest minds of their time. Let's just pretend you didn't write somewhat less dignified stuff in the "notes" section.

name: Poe-red Power Armor
description: You Poe-red the power armor. Now it's got a crow emblem on the shoulderpad and a "Nevermore" writing on the chestplate. It's also a bit lighter than before.

name: Rose Scythe
description: A rose scythe with decrative thorns and a blooming curved rose blade.

name: Crescent Rose
description: A High Velocity Sniper-Scythe (HVSS), a hybrid between a Scythe and a Rifle.

name: Rick Astley Poster
description: Whoever thought of printing this guy on a poster is stupid. The thought of keeping this eternal Rick Roll around makes you feel even more stupid. <iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/VBVFUZJmfCY?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: Client/Server Chain
description: A colorful chain, each individual link in the shape of a spirograph. It has the same number of links as there are gates across all lands in your session. If you stick a finger in one of the gates, it will come out another one in the chain... kinda freaky.

name: Beatmania IIDX Controller
description: A plastic controller with seven keys and a turntable, meant for a punishingly difficult rhythm game. You can practically feel the carpal tunnel just by looking at it.

name: Laser Throwing Quills
description: Throwable feathers made of hard red light with pointy tips.

name: Mercury Dew
description: A bottle of sweetened and caffeinated quicksilver. It will probably kill you if you drink it. Probably better to shake it up and spray it at your enemies.

name: Mad Hatter\'s Throwing Feathers
description: A set of needle-sharp red and silver feathers, perfectly weighted for throwing and perfectly loaded with quicksilver to afflict madness on those they strike.

name: Don\'t Fear the Reaperang
description: Enemies beware! Death is approaching...in the form of a very sharp boomerang! Returns to owner after successful throw and, when thrown, plays Blue Oyster Cult's "Don't Fear the Reaper" in the background.

name: .45 Long Colt
description: A custom made .45 caliber nickel-plated revolver, a classic six-shot double-action with atop break reloading mechanism. However, using it makes you a pacifist.

name: Angel Arm
description: Yes... With sufficient energy from the Power Cell, great powers start to boil in this pistol! It even capable of making a hole (or two) in the moon...

name: Yucca Scissors
description: These scissors have blades made from the sharp leaves of the yucca plant and white yucca blossoms hang from the handles.

name: Streetsweeper Gatling
description: This is a broom with gunbarrels for bristles. Useful for sweeping streets of scum. Your house, not so much.

name: Team Fortress 2 Disc
description: A video game the features 9 violent cartoon characters who go around killing people who look oddly similar to them themselves, while using ridiculous weapons. It is also known as the only "hat simulator" in existence.

name: Over-carbonated Cola Can
description: This can is distended under the extreme pressure it's under. If you threw it, it might explode.

name: Hyrule Historia
description: Lots of information about a hero and his ancestors rescuing the same princess and her ancestors from the same evil mage. Still looks epic though.

name: GAM SISTYM...
description: You can't wait to be a useless piece of shit all day and play all these games.

name: Kamina\'s Tomb
description: A blade planted in a thick chunk of earth. A ragged cape is tied around the sword's hilt. Unwieldy, but effective.

name: Parachute Pants
description: What are these doing in your closet? You could have sworn you left these in the eighties, where they belong.

name: Old Valentine\'s Day Card
description: An old Valentine's Day card from your school crush. It was one of the many mandatory cards given out in your class Valentine's Day party, so it probably meant nothing to them, but it means the world to you.

name: Assassin of Time\'s Hood
description: Only few could use the garment of the Royal Assassins group, formed by the last Sage of Time. The Hero of Time trained each one himself. Weird time shit included.

name: Skaia\'s Light
description: The light of Skaia echoes forth from this lantern. With it, all shall bow before you, as you stand tall and wield that which symbolizes the ultimate goal.

name: Silver Combat Spork
description: A spork that is almost as fancy as it is large. You can't wait to stir up some trouble with this!

name: Plasma Scalpel
description: A scalpel outfitted with a plasma current to assist in cutting. May result in lethal electrocution of patient.

name: Orbital Triangulator
description: Excellent for surveying....or drawing triangles in the ground.

name: Pythagorean 3-Ball
description: A 3-Ball which claims to predict the future with esoteric mathematics. Since it contains a 2-D triangle, there are only two possible fortunes. For some reason, they both read "Ask again later"

name: Principia
description: Nothing more than an explanation of all of classical mechanics.

name: First-Edition Fantastic Four Comic Book
description: It's a first edition Fantastic Four comic book in all its corny, mint-condition glory!

name: Sooth Specs
description: Just as good for stalking your friends as it is for detecting surprise attacks.

name: Caltop
description: The single greatest alchemization that cherubkind has ever been able to see. A combination of a slimy puppet and a Skulltop created the most beautiful thing in existence. Gaze upon it. Gaze harder. Harder. HARDER.

name: Ecto-Glow Dress
description: A mirror-dress combined with glowy blue slime. It gives off a REALLY bright bluish light. This... really hurts your eyes to look at.

name: Mobile Fighter G-Gundam figurine
description: Incredible scale model of that one Robot suit armor, you know the one. You feel your blood boil just from watching it stand there.

name: Tome of the TARDIS
description: Brilliant blue and full of the wonders of all of space and time. Just don't let any dinosaurs or killer robots out.

name: Please Hammer Don\'t Hurt \'Em
description: An obnoxiously large hammer made of solid gold and bearing the visage of the Master of Masters of Ceremonies, MC Hammer, on one of the faces. You swear you can hear the sultry sounds of U Can't Touch This whenever you use it. In fact, everyone else can hear it too and would very much like you to stop.

name: Journeyer\'s Scarf
description: A unique red scarf with golden symbols flowing along the sides. It grants you the ability to fly a short distance.

name: Tuning Fork
description: Finding the correct pitch is easy when you have a tuning fork. Plus, you can whack your enemies with it!

name: Apocalyptic Magikalibur Scissors
description: These scissors are literally made of magic: they have a blade made of scorching flames and a blade made of subzero ice. This is definitive proof that science is fake as shit. After all, what kind of science would make you use two hands to wield a pair of scissors?

name: Coin of Cthulhu
description: The pitch-black steel that this coin is made of sends shivers down your spine. You're holding the wealth of pure evil.

name: SwitchScythe - Bladed Tonfa
description: Behold! The awesome slaying power that is the SwitchScythe version 3 point OH! With a turndisc mechanism that rotates the Scythes blades it can transform into a bladed tonfa-like weapon into just 1.8 seconds! That is 3 times less than the previous version! ORDER YOURS NOW!

name: Bottle of Pink Sake
description: This is likely to make you *WAY* too anime to drive.

name: Strawhat
description: This ordinary Strawhat is actually quite precious to one up-and-coming Pirate King. Wear it well.

name: Christmas Wreath
description: This wreath is made from pine branches, holly, and a bright red bow. It's festive and spiky.

name: Sonic\'s Screwdriver
description: You just can't get over how unbelievably BLUE this is.

name: Fez
description: No matter how cool you think it is, nobody will ever let you wear it.

name: Laser-Sprayer
description: This machine gun sprays lasers in all directions, causing massive carnage to everybody within a wide radius.

name: RAZR Specs
description: With this mobile phone technology in your eyewear, the world has never looked so sharp.

name: Mask of the Father
description: Well, what is it? An anguished-looking mask. Wearing it makes you feel like a pro gamer.

name: Anvil Baseball Bat
description: It's a weird looking bat with a top shaped like an anvil and doesn't weigh that much despite having "anvil" in its name.

name: Adventurer\'s Hat
description: The dust of the latest delving into the dungeon lingers on this hat for seemingly an eternity. Seems a bit singed on the side, however. +2 on reflex saves.

name: Astral Lightning Spear
description: This spear calls lightning down from the sky with the tiny tesla coils that are embedded in it.

name: Painclaw
description: A set of claws that will extract deliciously sadistic amounts of pain from your enemies.

name: Sunslammer
description: A warhammer burning with the heat and intensity of a sun. The time powers inherent to the weapon make sure that the flames never go out.

name: Triple Header
description: A three headed baseball bat with pointed ends, great for a three headed ball and a game of three headed baseball.

name: Compy 386
description: A spectacle of graphics and sound! Checking your email has never been so easy!

name: Codex Astartes
description: Before you ask: no, this thing doesn't support what you're about to do with it.

name: Union Jack
description: The Union Jack is the flag of the U.K, by the way. Learnin' you some knowledge here.

name: Alternian Empire Flag
description: A flag bearing the insignia of Her Imperious Condescension, sure to strike fear into the population of any civilized planet. And even if the flag itself doesn't scare your opponents, the fearsome spikes on the end of the flagpole surely will.

name: Mario\'s Shoes
description: Plumber shoes said to enhance jumping height and stomping power.

name: Eruption Saviour
description: This umbrella will burst your enemies into ashes and occasionally save you from volcanoes.

name: Tonfa of the Road Warrior
description: Leave tire tracks all over those enemies with these engine powered tonfa's with wheels!

name: Pointy Leslie Nielsen Glasses
description: Your attempts to make a clever reference to a popular anime have been foiled. You are now in possession of pointy glasses with their dark lenses replaced by a stained glass cut-out of the area around Leslie Nielsen's eyes. Congratulations if this was your goal, though, you weirdo.

name: Psycho Mask
description: This mask makes you want to start screaming at your enemies and to start throwing whatever is next to you at them.

name: Used Paintbrush
description: You hate it when people don't clean the paint from the brushes The bristles are stiff with red paint.

name: Crystal Shirt
description: This shirt has an image of a crystal on it. It's suspiciously shiny for a decal.

name: Shirt of Crystal
description: A shirt that is made of crystal. The coverage is good, but it's kind of fragile and hard to defend with.

name: Dragon Helmet
description: It's like you're wearing a real dragon's head! Rawr.

name: Camera
description: A modern digital camera. With this baby, taking pictures is a snap!

name: Vintage Camera
description: The big, clunky kind of camera that spits out a black-and-white photo at the bottom. Developing just takes a little shake. Even holding it makes you feel rather grayscale.

name: Newspaper
description: This'll teach those imps not to touch your junk.

name: The Gray Ladies
description: No clothes, no shame, no chroma.

name: Mantello di Vongola Primo
description: A fluid black sheet that can protect you from attack, it is pinned closed by a silver and blue roman numeral I. For the true successor of the Primo's will.

name: Slightly Less Shitty Sword
description: This shitty sword has been imbued with unrefined ore, making it less shitty. But only slightly so.

name: Naegling
description: Beowulf once received Naegling as a reward for his heroic deeds. Now, as the hero destined to save the universe, it belongs to you.

name: Nethack floppy disk
description: Ah, Nethack. The only game that could run on a toaster and keep you playing for eternity.

name: Teslascope
description: A pretty radical telescope that shoots lightning wherever you look. Pretty nice.

name: Fantastic 4-Ball
description: It's a 4-ball and it's fantastic....somehow.

name: Electrifying Needles
description: Name speaks for itself: the needles will electrify enemies that you'll attack.

name: Yaldabaoth\'s Keyton
description: A baton morphed with a key, with many clocks, riddles, and destructive time properties. It seems to be glowing with the power of the ultimate Denizen.

name: Black Rose Lantern
description: A thorny lantern, emanating a dark and spooky aura. You're not entirely sure how to hold it and it keeps dropping petals everywhere.

name: Social Circle
description: A hoop-shaped computer/communications device. Completely practical.

name: Ego Wings
description: Water Wings that inflate and deflate according to your current opinion of yourself. You can see them swelling from your newfound confidence from making them.

name: Razor Razr
description: Crazy women before this airhead always would cut me with an iPhone. Now, they use a Razr.

name: Nintendo Gamecube
description: A surprisingly sturdy game system that has a convenient handle for smacking things with!

name: Super Mario Sunshine
description: A Mario game that not only has you running around, jumping on platforms, and collecting stuff, but this time you can spray water at things. Innovation!

name: Shadowy Sludgebrush
description: A long purple paintbrush with all the powers of pollution and contamination. Using this will secure you a top spot on Captain Planet's hitlist.

name: Heisenberg\'s Revenge
description: Somehow, the lasers fired by this gun take every single possible path at once before hitting an enemy and collapsing their wavefunctions to a single one. Quantum mechanics sure are weird!

name: Hawking\'s Fury
description: Rather than collapsing to a single one, the possible lasers now all converge on the unfortunate target to temporarily create a miniature black hole. This weapon truly is the pinnacle of modern science.

name: Dragon Hoodie
description: Now you have an awesome Hoodie that looks like an awesome dragon! Its also nice and warm on the inside and protects you from the outside.

name: SCP-1546
description: An anomalous baseball cap. Wearing it seems to boost your confidence and persuasion skills.

name: Gunbristler
description: This broom is bristling with guns, and has guns for bristles. This is incredibly unwieldy!

name: Umbrella Dress
description: By pushing a slide on the back of this dress, you can poof out the bottom! Varies between short and wide to long and thin.

name: Nintendo Dicecube
description: You're pretty sure that rolling this will eliminate any chance of the thing playing Super Mario Sunshine, but it's still heavier than the dice you alchemized it from.

name: Sunglasses of the Stampede
description: Sweet! These sunglasses make you look like Vash the Stampede-- VASH THE STAMPEDE!?

name: Ballpoint Pen
description: It's a pen with a ball at the end for smooth writing. However, its utility in battle is not quite as impressive.

name: Z-4 Roller
description: This ballpoint pen is the smoothest there is. Continuous ink feed, no bleeding through the paper. Absolutely perfect.

name: Fiery Shotthrower
description: This shotgun shoots out fireballs the way a normal one would shoot pellets. Use it to warm your food, dry your clothes, or to listen to your enemies scream as they burn alive.

name: Pop Goes the World
description: A rapier with a bubble wand for a pommel and a distinct Skaian aesthetic. As you swing the rapier, it releases bubbles which look like tiny Skaias.

name: Exalted 3rd Edition book set
description: It's finally here! And you didn't even have to wait on the kickstarter!

name: Burning Falcon Gauntlets
description: Your hands are burning red!! Their roar tells you to grasp victory!! BURSTING. GOD. FINGER!!!

name: Book of Weight
description: An extremely heavy book that describes many heavy objects, up to and including the Earth itself.

name: Anvil of Mythology
description: A smaller anvil covered in pages from the Book of Mythology.

name: God Tier Panties
description: Panties styled after your God Tier. You're not sure if they actually provide any benefit but you certainly feel empowered.

name: Prismatic Dragon Armor
description: To represent all that is good, this armor's shiny scales shine in bronze, silver, gold, and brass.

name: Wand of Dungeoning and Dragoning
description: This wand is perfect for your level 3 wizard.

name: Goliath Doll
description: A prototype magical doll at least thrice your own size, wielding a pair of equally ridiculously oversized swords. Try not to use it for extended periods of time, or it might explode.

name: Formal Dress
description: A slick, comfy black dress for when you need to attend a swanky high end party. Or bash in the heads of some Imps.

name: SCP-1022
description: An anomalous labcoat. Wearing it makes you able to see things that are usually microscopic, but this usually does more harm than good.

name: SPC-SBAHJ
description: ojbect class: KETUR

name: Kazoot Suit
description: This brightly-colored zoot suit emits music as you move. How dandy! All you need is a matching fedora.

name: Glowscythe
description: It's a scythe with a glowing handle. Now you can fight in the dark!

name: Horrorterror Speak Sceptre
description: This staff draws its power from the gods of the furthest ring. You'd be surprised how much evil drives in the monsters still today.

name: Cid\'s Spear
description: The spear of an ambitious pilot. He later went on to find better lance and items, but hopefully, this can be as powerful for you.

name: Nerf Longshot
description: A nerf gun that has only a tiny fraction of an actual rifle's power, but it is still useful for clubbing enemies over the head with it!

name: Pink Computer
description: Everything you wanted in a computer... just pink! Oh, and it has some flowers on it, too!

name: Candy Cane Cleaner
description: This special broom with a sweet tasting handle doubles as a cane! Although I wouldn't put too much weight on it...

name: Scattershout
description: An over-sized air gun with the sole purpose of ripping apart every eardrum in a fifty yard radius around the user. A warning on the handle says: "Always use protection. On your ears too."

name: Piercing Light
description: A metallic blade with a light bulb on the end that turns on once you've killed a thing! Very handy.

name: Blue Eye Flame
description: The flame seems to be generated by the will of the user alone. Who\'d have guessed that your newest cosplay idea would be that useful.

name: Killua\'s Yo-yo
description: Yo-yos used by professional hunters. The yo-yos are extremely durable and heavy, each weighing 50 kilograms.

name: Captain\'s Hat
description: The ghosts of a hundred soldiers swear allegiance to this symbol of authority. Something seems to bide that it will not work with underlings, however.

name: Glowchucks
description: Ninja Rave! Yeah!

name: Valentine\'s Day Wreath
description: A wreath of hearts, love, and Valentine's Day kitsch.

name: Holy Mackerel
description: It must be pretty annoying to be killed with a fish.

name: Inkmaker
description: A Marker pen that appears to change color according to the owners mind. It appears to be refilled by any liquid. The tip emits some sort of small power.

name: Toilet Paper Roll
description: This'll show those imps for not giving you candy on Halloween.

name: Royal Golden Tissue
description: It turns out that fancy ornate solid gold TP is more ideal for whacking than wiping.

name: Pile of Assorted Yugioh! Cards
description: A huge stack of Yugioh! cards you've kept lying around. You wonder if there are any good cards somewhere in this pile...

name: Red Formal Suit
description: Don't wanna look like a penguin? Here's a flaming red one that will make you look hot as hell, cool as ice, a walking target.

name: Rose-Steel Cane
description: They say the thorns around this cane make it hit harder. They actually just make you look like even more of a pompous jerk. Or so they say.

name: Lover\'s Fez
description: A red and pink fez with hearts on it. It's a little embarrassing to wear.

name: Jewel-Encrusted Floral Gown
description: An silver evening gown beaded with jewels in an elegant iris pattern.

name: Aperture Science Wrecking Ball Launcher
description: Uses the power of portals and vacuums to accelerate wrecking balls to ridiculous degrees of smashing-enemies'-faces-in, and yet it only weighs the same as your typical vacuum cleaner... from quite a few decades ago, which is to say that it weighs the same as a wrecking ball.

name: Rainbow Rifle
description: Shoot the Rainbow. Taste the Rainbow.

name: Dersite Scepter / Dersite Rifle
description: Luckily, the Black King hasn't gotten his hands on this weapon.

name: Steel Darts
description: Being thrown swiftly and painfully- these metal darts are faster, sharper and heavier: they can do more damage than the Wooden Darts.

name: Theoretical String
description: This string only exists as an explanation for some freaky physics stuff. Doesn't mean you can't hurt somebody with it.

name: Book of String Theory
description: Since string theory is so amazingly complicated and easy to misunderstand, the book dedicated to it is much heavier.

name: PokeDollar
description: The currency of the Pokemon world. This coin will show how devoted a fan you truly are, while packing quite the wallop.

name: Golden Netbook
description: A netbook that, by all accounts, should be heavier than it is. It is decorated with a dial covered in strange symbols.

name: Four Aces Suited
description: A suit that should only be worn for late night occasions.

name: Droid WristRazr
description: Like a phone for your wrist, and it tells the time too! Well, it already could tell the time before, but its main purpose is that now. The only time putting a raz[o]r to your wrist is not considered emo.

name: Wand of Mythology
description: This is the most ironic thing ever.

name: Block of Bedrock
description: A dark grey cube made out of a completely indestructible material. Just don't put it down, or you'll have one hell of a time retrieving it.

name: SOMUC 6
description: SOMUC IS BAKC IN THID HELLA AWSEOME GANE

name: Crown of Thorns
description: This is wreath is a bit too thorny to handle.

name: Ultimate HUD
description: This visor can display anything! From the weakpoints of your enemies, to warning you of incoming attacks, to displaying codes for alchemy (although most of the time it results in a potted plant anyways). It almost feels cheaty.

name: Soul Gem
description: You're pretty sure this is wrong to have, you've seen this in an anime once. It's dangerous.

name: Animal Crossing Chopsticks
description: Chopsticks with various Animal Crossing characters/symbols on them.

name: SCP-572
description: An anomalous, yet still incredibly shitty, sword. Wielding it makes you think you're more powerful than you actually are. Why did you even bother with this?

name: Sword of Time: Smithing
description: This lost grimoire have many details in the arts of creating and tempering with the so called Master Sword. Really complex and extense for a guy who just swings it around.

name: Heart Specs
description: Not only can you see anywhere in the Incipisphere with these; you can also use a weak form of mind control to make imps do your bidding!

name: Felt Umbrella
description: An umbrella with felt texture. It has a fancy pool design. It's really nice to touch it. Occasionally, you can feel time stopping/slowing down/speeding up when using this.

name: Jack\'s Knife
description: Holding this wants you to say hello to others through stabbing, and just to stab people in general.

name: Bandaged Broom
description: Wrapping some bandages around ordinary broom makes it easier to handle it when ya sweeping!

name: Popsickle
description: A tasty treat that's labeled as "Strawburial Flavor". Whatever that means.

name: Duct Tape
description: If it's not stuck, and it's supposed to be, duct tape it. If it is and it's not supposed to be... Well, good luck at finding something that can get duct tape off.

name: Goreguts Shredders
description: What did you expect to get when you combine a videogame where the protagonist hack n'slashes everything he finds with some claws?

name: Clothing Iron ring
description: A ring with a tiny working Clothing Iron on it! Though the clothing iron part is rather small so it would take time to get all of the wrinkles out.

name: Sombrero
description: A Latin hat. It is great for wearing while intoxicated.

name: Cosplay Cat Wings
description: A connected cosplay back piece, featuring an adorable cat tail and a pair of white feather cat win- Wait cats don't have wings!?

name: Orange
description: This bright orange citrus fruit is just what you need to kick start both your days, and your strifes.

name: Cosplay Midnight Wings
description: A pair of midnight black feathered wings used for cosplay. Proof that you can cosplay as a badass birdman.

name: Apple
description: A bright red fruit that is extremely popular. Eat it raw, or cook it with cinnamon or caramel!

name: Kawaiiron Man Heart-Throb Armor
description: A highly advanced suit of armor complete with repulsor rays and pink titanium alloy bows.

name: Magician\'s Top Hat
description: The big gold star on this hat supposedly gives it magic powers. But even if that's not true, you still admit it makes it look all the more classy.

name: Swiss Army Paintbrush
description: A convenient device that folds out into any kind of paintbrush you could desire. Every artist's dream come true!

name: The Power of Love
description: With this sword you feel more loved and powerful.

name: White Flag
description: The white flag is an internationally recognized protective sign of truce or ceasefire, and request for negotiation. Unfortunately, the imps you're fighting don't appear to understand and continue to attack you regardless.

name: Ghostbusters Poster
description: A promotional poster for the greatest sci-fi/supernatural/comedy of all time. OF ALL TIME!!

name: Glow-in-the-dark Claws
description: You can now claw away your enemy's faces... in the dark! May require sunlight exposure.

name: Turn Tables
description: You use this to make some sick beats.

name: Raydent
description: A fairly average trident made of a crystalline material that leaves behind a trail of rainbows. Useful for distraction.

name: Compubeanie
description: The fuzzy fabric keeps your head warm, while the cold hard electronics keep you informed. A must have for the aspiring Techno-Rapper.

name: Luigi\'s Mansion CD
description: Luigi steps out from the shadow of his brother Mario and into the gloomy shadows of a very haunted house in this, his first-ever starring role. Armed with a flashlight and a customized vacuum cleaner, Luigi must rid the mansion of Boos and ghouls--and find his missing brother to boot.

name: Super scope
description: The Super Scope, or Nintendo Scope in Europe and Australia, is the official Super Nintendo light gun. The successor to the NES Zapper, unfortunately it is powered by six AA batteries.

name: Inflatablazer
description: It's puffy as shit, but DAMN does it look fine!

name: SCP-714
description: An anomalous ring. Wearing it seems to make you sleepy, but boosts your mental defenses.

name: Vigilante uniform
description: This coat has been treated like it has been to a fight club and took first, second and third place.

name: Bowler Hat
description: This Victorian-era Bob Hat has a history of shielding the scalps of many official workers.

name: Bowling Ball
description: This could split a skull as well as it could a pin.

name: Afro Ring
description: A ring with a tiny Afro where the gem is supposed to go.

name: Clawed Sledgehammer
description: A hammer with a large head and two sharp prongs on one side.

name: Chakram
description: A hoop-like bladed weapon. Best for when you are pretending to be Xena, the Warrior Princess.

name: Hula Chakram
description: A large bladed hoop you can swing around your hips.

name: Microphone Stand
description: You've recently discovered that this stand is just as useful for clubbing imps as it is for holding your sound-recording equipment.

name: 3D Sunglasses
description: You have no idea why you made this, although it does appear to have an identity crisis with the ironically purposed sunglasses and the already purposed 3D glasses.

name: Great Knife
description: Barely qualifiable as a knife, this colossal, rusty machete is almost too big to wield. Almost. You suddenly feel attracted to mannequins.

name: Flapper Headdress
description: It's a lace-y looking headdress with a feather on it.

name: Will-o\'-the-Wisp
description: A bouncing ball of ghostly blue flames.

name: Honkunai
description: This seems to defeat the whole point of being a ninja. It honks every time you throw it.

name: Sweet Tooth Tower
description: You've alchemized a sweet-smelling red, yellow, and white computer. You will treasure your candy corn computer, stuffing it into a large hat if needed (although you've yet to find a hat that fits an entire computer).

name: Plasma Cell
description: With even more power, this cell has proven to be even more unstable and actually quite predictable explosive (since it explodes almost all of the time)

name: XLVI Angel of Double Death
description: The creature pictured on this card is obscured by an impossibly dark shadow, to the point that the card is black with some green lines on it. And yet... It terrifies you.

name: Chainlink Scarf
description: A scarf made of interwoven chains. It's not the most comfortable of scarves, and is actually rather cold, but it seems to deflect blows rather well.

name: Magical Dungeon Gun
description: A Shotgun which shoots magical bullets. It is pretty heavy, and seems to pulse magic where there are cracks in it's frame..

name: Discordic Faceted Scythe
description: This shiny scythe glimmers in the light, but each reflection shows the person viewing it in a different world, and for a moment they seem lost. The blade also seems to have a mind of its own, moving randomly with each swing.

name: Very Yellow Faygo
description: This Faygo flows like liquid... gold? You don't really want to think about it.

name: Very Purple Faygo
description: This Faygo is an unnaturally purple color, and tastes vaguely of grapes.

name: Vampire\'s Bloodlines
description: A book containing the story of the vampires, it is written in the blood of the various races and vampiric clans. you can almost hear the screams in each page.

name: Burned Umbrella
description: Did you actually needed to use alchemy to do this?

name: Madoka Plushie
description: A cute doll with the appearance of Madoka.

name: Blatantly Blue Restorative Pop Rocks
description: They might sting your mouth a little, but you'll feel better over all.

name: Kingdom of Loathing poster
description: This is genuine merchandise from the beloved parody RPG know as Kingdom of Loathing. You can feel the irony radiating from the poorly-drawn stick man's sword and martini.

name: Felt Dress
description: A green-and-black dress worn by the sole female member of the Felt. It has a collared top and a long back.

name: Power Glove
description: The Power Glove is a controller accessory for the Nintendo Entertainment System, and the first peripheral interface controller to recreate human hand movements on a television or computer screen in real time. You love it, cause it's SO BAD

name: Virtual Boy
description: It is the first video game console that was supposed to be capable of displaying "true 3D graphics" out of the box, in a form of virtual reality. You feel kinda silly wearing those...

name: Superhero Costume
description: Probably the most important thing to have to look like a superhero. What's a cape without a costume, right?

name: Edgeless Safety Cube
description: Hey, this isn't a cube at all!

name: BFLG9000
description: This weapon fires a large ball of plasma ripping everything in it's path to shreds, while the plasma ball fires lasers in all directions. Like carnage in a can, but a rifle.

name: Miniature Air Fan
description: You're not entirely sure how you're supposed to hit anything when your shots keep flying upward.

name: Black Blade
description: A sword previously used by a Rock Shooter. Holding this in your hands, you feel unbeatable.

name: Pack of instant noodles
description: An esteemed culinary addition to dorm kids and starving artists alike! Just add water.

name: Post-War Pre-War Hat
description: It went through Fallout's apocalypse, then came back. It's slightly radioactive.

name: Bramble\'s Memorial Statue
description: After dying in a tragic accident involving a BFG and one too many jokes, Bramble was killed. Later, this monument, a statue made almost entirely from caulks, (cough) I mean caulk, was placed in his honor. At the bottom "Mikle was here" is engraved.

name: Skull Cane
description: A thin cane with a tiny skull on top. It looks like a villain's cane--and a rich one's at that.

name: WD-40
description: Something to unstick things. Particularly duct tape.

name: SCP-2100-J
description: An anomalous, and very hard-boiled, fedora. Wearing it makes you have an irresistible compulsion to narrate what's going on around you in detective film noir fashion.

name: Bouncing Flames
description: With each comes a medium sized blast. Forests beware.

name: Lord Potato
description: This most regal potato, happens to be lord of all potatoes. Unfortunately, there's a rapier sized hole through it, still, it matters not to you.

name: Black Rose, Green Lantern
description: The lantern now pulsates not only with a dark and spooky aura, but with green energy that seems to tear at the very fabric of space!

name: Bluegrass Dueling Spatula
description: An instrumental spatula with a country twang. Best used in duels.

name: The Light of the Mountain
description: This lantern is imbued with the spirits of ancestors long past, gathered together so finely that touching that lantern's light makes you feel as if you could be reborn anew.

name: Broken Blue Phantasmic Caledfwlch
description: A legendary broken piece of shit... It's infused with ghost goo, too, so it constantly glows blue. It's kinda suckish for killing imps, especially since contact with the goo-coated blade slightly heals them.

name: Flapper Dress
description: It's a pretty swanky (if short) dress. You have no idea where the beads came from, though.

name: Dai-Gurren Flag
description: With this flag, you boost your fighting spirit tremendously! You feel the need to pierce the heavens! You can't do that with this flag, though.
