name: The Cartoon History of the Universe Omnibus
description: This illustrated chronicle claims to detail the universe in full. Recent events in your life suggest otherwise.

name: Pillar Man\'s Loincloth
description: You can only think of two things: being buff and posing.

name: Clio\'s Unabridged History of the Universe
description: This is the history of everything, as penned by the goddess of history herself. Nothing is left out, making this tome exceedingly large, heavy and boring.

name: Two-Face\'s Quarter
description: It looks like a regular quarter at a first glance, but on close inspection, it's double-headed with one side scratched.

name: 3D iGlasses
description: Fuck, how do you work this shit?

name: Xbox
description: This large, coffee-table sized game console has a green glowing X on the front and seems to be more technologically advanced than others of its kind.

name: Golden Irony
description: Sporting a golden hat and shades, this disguise is so ironic on so many levels that most people can't take it anymore. It's also ironic that this golden gear is harder than most metals.

name: Shitty Fake Hammer
description: A useless shitty hammer made of fake diamond. This thing couldn't crush an orange.

name: The Shining Slicer
description: A glimmering chainsaw made of pure gold. This thing looks impossible to break.

name: Hamethyst Ring
description: This is a ring with a Hamethyst stone in it. Wearing it makes you feel beefier (because everybody knows there's nothing beefier than ham), like you could shrug off any number of slings and arrows as though they were sticks and stones, only the kind that can't hurt you.

name: GLaDOS Overcoat
description: Will keep you warm with hazardous uninsulated electrical parts. For more information, please attend an Aperture Science Electrical Safety Seminar.

name: Bramble\'s Claws
description: These claws, empowered by the remnants of Bramble's poor tattered soul, are rather powerful. Something about them seems to unlock your warrior spirit and channel it directly into the claws. (Bramble, if you're reading this, it means you're finally enough of a man to make an item by yourself, I am so so proud of you. Or I get fed up and gave you the codes, in which case you suck caulk. )

name: Fulltin Jacket
description: It's a jacket made from the tin of a soda can. Lookin' stylish!

name: Giant Amethyst Ring
description: How the hell are you going to fit this on your finger.

name: Derse Banner
description: Derse dreamers represent!

name: Prospit Banner
description: Prospit dreamers represent!

name: SCP-241
description: An anomalous cookbook that seems to customize its recipes for everyone who opens it. It only gives you things you're deathly allergic to, though.

name: Can Opener
description: It opens cans. Wow, that is BRAND NEW information right there.

name: SCP-448
description: An anomalous Jack-in-the-Box. It changes expression based off of the emotions of the person nearest it. Needless to say, it gives you the creeps.

name: Blue Ecto-slime Nunchucks
description: What can't you make out of ecto-slime? Nunchucks. These things are so soft you can't imagine them doing much damage.

name: Lightbulb Nunchucks
description: This is just a nunchuck with lightbulbs instead of handles. Why did you make this, it's more likely to hurt you!

name: Box of Legos
description: A box of assorted lego sets has murdered many a careless foot. They're also quite fun to build with, when they don't get lost.

name: Long-Handled Billhook
description: You found this gardening tool in the back of your garage. At least it helps keep the imps at a distance.

name: Billy Club
description: For knocking thieves, criminals, and peaceful protesters out cold!

name: Bladed Nunchucks
description: Nunchucks with their edges honed to razor-sharp blades.

name: Prescription Sunglasses
description: Hooray, now you won't have to sacrifice either your visibility or coolness anymore!

name: Stuffed Bunny
description: An adorable, cuddly soft plush toy in the likeness of a lagomorph.

name: Glaive
description: You think a suit of armor might be missing this somewhere.

name: Blades of Time Grimoire
description: With this book open and hand gestures, you have at your disposal a swarm of the Swords of Time, scattered through time and space. If your team mates see this, you say: "Time shenanigans".

name: Mountain Goo
description: It appears that some Mountain Dew has been poured into this beaker, but the container hadn't been thoroughly cleaned. What remains is a mix of soda and whatever chemical residues it held before.

name: Spinfusor Disk
description: Explosive Frisbee! Just fling it at enemy and see what happens. Bonus points if said enemy is airborne.

name: Mistletoe of Christmas Compulsion
description: You feel an uncontrollable urge to kiss people while you're around this mistletoe.

name: Lightning Claws
description: These claws just seem to crackle with electric energy. Try not to hurt yourself!

name: Bleachtop
description: This jet black laptop has a hole in the center and a white skull decal on the front. It leaks a small amount of spiritual pressure, not that you would be able to tell anyways.

name: Naginata
description: The extent of the blade allows you to give your attacks more force through the power of momentum. And you're safer, since you're attacking from further away. Whoever calls this a woman's weapon with get stabbed right in the family jewels.

name: Baker Scarf
description: Look like a Doctor, or a Baker, with this incredibly long and goofy scarf.

name: Sonic Umbrella
description: They'll make a sonic everything these days.

name: Steam Powered Giraffe - The 2 Show CD
description: An album of music played by steam-powered robotic performers.

name: Double-Headed Halberd
description: A halberd with a head each on opposite ends of the shaft, letting you become a deadly dervish as you spin the weapon around like a madman.

name: Reapfractor
description: The blade of this prismatic scythe scatters all the colors of the rainbow... but with extra red from the blood of your enemies!

name: Drunken Boxing Gloves
description: The alcohol in these gloves is absorbed by your skin in a precise dosage. Enough to stave off sobriety, but not so much that you have to face The Mother of All Hangovers later.

name: Dragon Dress
description: It is a formal wear that makes you look terrifying and beautiful at the same time.

name: Rocket Suit
description: A suit bursting at the seams with rocket engines.

name: The Star of the Cosmos
description: The power of invincibility holds close to this one. How could anyone use such a powerful item? It is so terrifying that no one could deal with its existence. The star glows devilishly, knowing it is too evil to be used by anyone.

name: Fiestatop
description: A sombrero computer said to be have worn by Fiesta Ace Dick himself. I mean, then he threw it away but, yeah. Apparently he wore it.

name: Kimono
description: An all purpose eastern outfit made of very comfortable fabric. You feel like a Samurai or a maiden of those shitty japanese movies.

name: Newtonian Calculacerator
description: A laser-bladed saw that can derive the volume of your enemies. It's not hard because the volume is always zero after you've obliterated their bodies.

name: Trick Yo-yo
description: A surprisingly easy to wield Yo-yo. This one rocks for sure!

name: Elrondtop
description: They're taking the hobbits to ISENGARD! And you can let them know using this lovely laptop, which comes with a free copy of Elfsterchum. Who's this douchebag?

name: Bombinomicon
description: If ye gaze at one tome this year, MAKE IT NOT THIS ONE

name: Bag of Jellybeans
description: Assorted jellybeans of almost every flavor imaginable. There's even a ketchup bean!

name: Asauchi
description: The unnamed zanpakuto used by low ranking Shinigami. But as this blade's user uses it more it will grow along with its user, and if they become powerful enough it will grow into its own unique powers! ...or at least, that's what is believed to happen.

name: Blueberry Brainfreeze
description: A slushie that'll turn your tongue blue! Feed your friends! Freeze your foes!

name: Zaptastic Crowbar
description: If a normal crowbar wasn't enough, here's a electrically charged fuckin' one. Enjoy, you sadistic freak.

name: Ultimate Faygo Powered Arm Cannon
description: A Faygo Powered Arm Cannon. Dare I say more?

name: Extending Arm
description: A wooden contraption with a glove on one end and handles on the other. Push the handles together and it extends to several times its retracted length, making it great for bopping imps on the head from afar.

name: Riot Shot-tar
description: Your average guitar, complete with six strings, volume knobs, pickups, and the capability to fire like a shotgun out of the neck.

name: Pogotar
description: Send your enemies flying and playing some sweet jams on this adorable guitar!

name: Flying Guitar
description: It's a guitar with wings! Just make sure it doesn't fly away when using it.

name: Basketbox
description: This cube-shaped ball is remarkably heavy for its size. Good luck trying to dribble this!

name: Green Solar Flare Protecter
description: This umbrella is one of the few things that can withstand the heat of the green sun. It's also pretty damn powerful.

name: Spiral energy overcoat
description: You can feel the Fighting Spirit flow through you as you wear this coat.

name: Ghostthruster 9000
description: This appears to be the lovechild of the Ecto 1 and a Rocket Board. While undeniably cool, it has unfortunately inherited the Ecto 1's annoying siren. You can't turn it off. You've tried. A lot.

name: Shuriken
description: Star-shaped throwing blades iconic of the deadly ninja.

name: Tennantop
description: David Tennant's stern young face peers at you, a sonic screwdriver in hand. Yes. This is a laptop only suitable for timelords.

name: Crochet Needles
description: Sure, they're not as sharp as some needles, but they have hooks on them, and who doesn't love things with hooks on them?

name: Daft Punk CD
description: Daft Punk is an electronic music duo wich is also known for its use of disguises, particularly the ornate robot costumes, while in public and/or performing. A must for every Eletronic music fan.

name: Cloak of the Zephyr
description: A blue-and-teal cloak that ripples with the wind, a lot lighter than it seems. Just wearing this makes you feel like you could glide through the air, or even whip up a small tornado.

name: Echidna Cloak
description: This cloak is seemingly made of the fabric of space, displaying thousands of stars and nebulae on its black surface. What's more important, however, is the fact that all attacks are absorbed upon contact.

name: Sandman\'s Pinch Hitter
description: When you forget your bag of sleepy sand, this bat will get the job done just as well.

name: Roll of Quarters
description: Not really a fist fulla dollars but keep em close and they'll be your punch's best friend.

name: Empress\'s Naginata
description: A gaudy weapon of bright gold and lined with glittering purple gems, it is nonetheless effective for defending the castle from ninjas.

name: Pike
description: You wouldn't touch those imps with a 10-foot pole. You'd touch them with a 10-foot spear instead.

name: Pike Pike
description: Usually, an excessively long spear would be perfect for fishing, but unfortunately this one seems to have already been used for that purpose many times over.

name: Naginata Flail
description: Well it isn't a flail. But with the chain link giving you even more momentum, it can certainly be swung like one.

name: Houzukimaru
description: Separated into three sections and decorated with a red horsetail, this naginata is more than it seems. A simple thought will alter the length of its chains and the direction of the pieces. Not much good once the element of surprise dissipates though.

name: Fluffy Cream Pillow
description: This is just about as soft as a pillow can possibly be. As in, it's not entirely solid.

name: Beanbag Basketball
description: A nifty pillow of roughly the same shape and size of a basketball. Perfect for tossing around the house in times of boredom.

name: Basketball Cap
description: It looks almost like you cut a basketball in half and put one of those halves over your head like a hat. It's an oddly snug fit.

name: Super-Heated Anvil
description: This anvil is always searing hot to the touch - perfect for heating your metal as you hammer it into shape!

name: Baldurbane Darts
description: Darts made of mistletoe, the only thing in existence that could slay the beautiful god Baldur.

name: SCP-442
description: An anomalous pocket watch. Having it seems to make it impossible for you to be late to anything.

name: Death Jacks
description: You DEFINITELY do NOT want to step on one of these things.

name: Refraction Darts
description: Nearly invisible, the only way you can see these things coming is by the light that flares through them, creating a rainbow on the ground in their path.

name: Mobster Darts
description: You give the bright green dart a flick and- it disappears. Straight into the future, or maybe the past. Damn, you hate time travel.

name: Hard-Light Reapfractor
description: This scythe's refracting blade reflects a solid, and rather deadly, form of light that cuts through almost anything unfortunate enough to get in it's path.

name: Ring of Fire
description: A flaming hoop, much like what circus animals and daredevils jump through.

name: Heavy Glow
description: You wield these links of chain with to smash your enemies heads in. You suppose you can also poison them with what ungodly concoction is inside those glowsticks that have been haphazardly attached to the chain.

name: Glaive/Glaive/Glaive
description: You've created a weapon with 3 distinct forms, one being a throwing star, another a polearm, and lastly a blade, all under the same name. Who wouldn't think THAT was confusing?

name: Discworld Box Set
description: Subdue or distract your foes with a blend of dysfunctional fantasy and social satire.

name: Penguin Plush
description: Waaaaaahk. It's an adorable penguin plush wearing a bowtie! Perhaps it's all dressed up for a night out on the iceberg.

name: Giant Shuriken
description: Despite the bulky size, this weapon make sup for its lack of stealth with its power and ease of retrieval.

name: MSAK...
description: AWSUM MSAK TO WER IN PARTAYS

name: Elven Knives
description: These knives are capable of using ancient spells to attack and weaken foes. They are also used for casting protecting spells for their friends.

name: Dart Launching Air Horn
description: Frankly you're surprised jamming darts into an air horn actually works! Your enemies will not be surprised however, you can hear this thing a mile away.

name: Lizard Plushie
description: Despite being a plushie, the sharp claws on this stuffed animal make for a somewhat practical weapon (as practical of a weapon as plushies can get).

name: War Scythe
description: This masterfully crafted (alchemized) scythe was built for downing cavalry and peasants alike.

name: Electric Acid Inferno Lizard
description: A mechanized little lizard plush that spits acid, sets itself on fire, and shocks enemies like a tesla coil. And yet, it remains absolutely adorable while doing so.

name: Appcycle Helmet
description: A bicycle helmet with all of the functions of a iphone hanging infront of your face. Headgear for comfortable chat with friends and relatively ok protection.

name: Foxfire Hoop
description: A black iron hoop with balls of ghostly blue fire.

name: Laser Hard-Light Reapfractor
description: With a laser sharpened edge, deadly Hard-Light refractions, and the blood of thousands of enemies, this scythe will continue to reap death in a spectacularly colorful fashion.

name: Cloak of Spacial Wind
description: This cloak strangely distorts its surroundings; items near it may teleport a few feet, or a cool breeze may lift them up and take them into the clouds. You're not sure what wearing this would do, other than make you look cool with the flickering sky/space design, but you're willing to find out.

name: Madoka Swagica
description: This is a sweet ass hat. Makes you feel...kickass. Like you've got the potential to wipe out all the bad shit that ever happened, ever. Must be your imagination.

name: Sun-dows
description: The wonderful functionality of windows 7, combined with the convenience of sunglasses. Where would you be without Microsoft?

name: Anchor Ring
description: Its somehow as heavy as a normal Anchor!

name: Poltergust 5000
description: The Poltergust 5000 is an advanced version of the vacuum invented by Professor E. Gadd to catch ghosts. You can stun a ghost with the flashlight, and then can suck it up. It's a must-need item when your older brother is trapped in a portrait by ghosts.

name: Extended Afro Comb
description: When your afro is as big as that of the Botector of Hair, you can't comb it without something as long as a backscratcher.

name: Extra-Fuzzy Earmuffs
description: These earmuffs are so warm and cozy you almost forgot they can still plug into a computer.

name: Winternet Headset
description: Sometimes, on the coldest days of the year, you just want to settle down with a hot cup of cocoa and chat with your friends on the warmer side of the globe. These earmuffs stay warm and cozy thanks to the computer built into them, making this dream a reality!

name: Butcher\'s Backstabber
description: If you're a vegetarian, never turn your back to a butcher or you might end up with one of these sticking out of your spine.

name: Sparkly Prom Dress
description: This has only been worn once. Now that you're so far away from home and anyone who might appreciate its beauty, you doubt anyone will care if you ruin it by fighting in it.

name: Con-Air Pins
description: Hopefully, these pins will keep the bunny in the box.

name: Three Musketeers Chocolate Bar
description: This chocolate is so light, it might just float away from you...

name: Chocolate Cream Pie
description: A dessert truly fit for a monarch, and with your alchemiter you can alchemize and eat as many of them as you want! Just... try not to go overboard, they aren't the healthiest things in the world.

name: MAGANETIC m
description: You successfully turn the magnetic W it flipways, creating this.

name: Mickle
description: This coin is rumored to have perfect balance, and can be balanced on any surface, regardless of how unbalanced the surface itself is.

name: Tron ID Pedestal
description: An old version of data storage. These pillars became cumbersome, so they switched to the discs. Still, this thing is great for hitting people.

name: Oarpheus
description: Supposedly this "magic" oar can make music that can charm any creature, but you're pretty sure that magic is bullshit. Besides, how the fuck do you play an oar?

name: Backscratcher of the Arsonist
description: Attempting to scratch your back with something that is more or less a gigantic garden rake is likely to end poorly... hence the bloodstains.

name: Backslasher
description: This should subdue any apostrophes you run into... as well as any enemies.

name: Giygas Mask
description: A horrifyingly disturbing mask with the face of the main antagonist of Earthbound.

name: Clothing Amethyst
description: Its like a clothing iron, but made of amethyst! Sadly, amethyst doesn't get as hot as iron so it doesn't boil the water, thus it doesn't really work. It still looks COOL!

name: Battery-Acid Squirtgun
description: With a pH of zero, those monsters probably won't be having faces anytime soon.

name: Flashy Flapper Shuriken
description: Glittery, feathery throwing stars. Perfect for deadly dancing.

name: Bag of Knucklebones
description: Marbles made from knucklebones. You have no idea where the bones came from.

name: Dragon Armour o\' the Wisp
description: Although your armour appears to be more frame than plating now, it's ghostly glow seems to ward off attackers.

name: Horned Lemon Screamer
description: An air horn with a lemon inside it. This horn's blaring, vuvuzela-like sound is bound to invoke a sour expression in any listener's face.

name: Tales of Symphonia 2: Knight of Ratatosk Disk
description: Not quite up to par, but still a missing link between Symphonia and Phantasia.

name: Forward Slasher
description: You just got COMMENTED!

name: Distortion Bat
description: Hitting a homerun with this bat will send the projectile roaring through time. It's technically out of the ballpark if it's 5 million years before the field was ever constructed, right?

name: Sharpened Mangler Iron
description: The heat coursing through this blade makes it easier to cut through just about any material, especially hair.

name: Ravaging Bangstick of Explosions
description: A black-blue-white-patterned shotgun that shoots rockets. There's a note attached to it: ""Did you know over 97% of all creatures on Medium aren't exploding right now? THAT'S BULLS***! TAKE THIS WEAPON, YOU'RE MOTHERF****NG WELCOME!"

name: Piranha Plant
description: A carnivorous plant. It looks like the Piranha Plants from the Mario games, but is significantly smaller.

name: Doll ring
description: A stylish ring with a dolls head as a gem! Its actually kind of creepy because the band looks like a stretched out doll body.

name: 3D Compuspecs
description: Standard red/blue 3D Glasses, now with cool holographic computer screens!

name: Cola Pistol
description: Why would you do that! Do you have any idea how long that will take to clean up?

name: Anvilicious Urgosh
description: An anvil on the end of a stick. You're not sure if this would be best described as a hammer, a spear or an axe, but you DO know it would hurt to get hit with.

name: Yoyo DAWG
description: YO DAWG I HERD YO AND YO DAWG LIKE YO YOS SO WE PUT YO DAWG IN A YO YO SO YO CAN YO YO YO DAWG WHILE YO DAWG YO YOS, DAWG.

name: Limited Edition Mario RPG SNES Controller
description: A Limited Edition Controller. Actually this never actually existed, but it's pretty fucking cool that you made this thing anyway.

name: Armageddon Quill
description: This shimmering black quill seems to spill the darkest of shadows from its nib, and never needs to be refilled. They say that it can write in thin air, and even summon words to do your bidding.

name: Squigethon Oar
description: Ornate carvings of mysterious tentacled creatures decorate the handle of this burning oar. Some irreverent individual has apparently tried to make this oar more "fun" by painting the carvings with a variety of bright colors. You disapprove.

name: Phantom Edge
description: A spear that is... a ghost? This spear is partially transparent, yet you can still grasp it and wield it.

name: Magic Violin
description: The perfect beginner weapon for an aspiring Instrumage. Little wisps of totally not-fake magic waft from it. Used for playing magical songs.

name: Amethyst Anvil
description: An anvil made completely out of amethyst. You're not quite sure if this makes it better or worse than a normal anvil.

name: Anvil Ring
description: A normal ring with a tiny anvil placed where a jewel would go.

name: Amethyst Wig
description: A hair piece that makes your head look like some amethyst.

name: The Bowie
description: Navigating the mind of someone crazy enough to make this must be like a labyrinth.

name: Dragon Hammer
description: A scaly yet handy little tool for strife.

name: Shigure Kintoki
description: Holding this blade in your hands, you feel the calm of the rain. And the water control is a bonus too.

name: Scientists Superb Safety Shako
description: This hat is the ultimate in safety and dapperness, especially for that scientist who often says 'I have no idea what I'm doing!'

name: Kamikorosu
description: With these versatile tonfa in hand, you'll bite to death any herbivore that crosses your path.

name: Reimutop
description: Preinstalled with the latest exorcising and demon-sealing software, this is the perfect tool for the modern shrine maiden. For some reason, it has a coin slot marked "Donations" next to the keyboard.

name: Mega Glove
description: The gloves of a heavy-fisted hero!

name: Black Rock Shooter: The Game
description: "Nineteen years of nonstop battle threatened the existence of humanity. A weapon, merely created to save us all, awakens to end the battle once and for all, but it's too late." Gosh, how you love this game.

name: Rubber Duck
description: No one can resist squeaking this thing.

name: Sidearm of the Fowl King
description: Duck monarchs wielding guns? Has that happened in any kind of fantasy before? Judging by the captcha code of this item, you're pretty sure its actual purpose doesn't really matter.

name: Oarange
description: It appears to be an Orange that somehow grew into the size and shape of an Oar. Genetically modified fruit has clearly taken a turn for the worst.

name: Star Oars
description: A long time ago in a galaxy far, far away It is a period of civil oar. Rebel rowboats, striking from a hidden base, have won their first victory against the evil Galactic Canoe. During the battle, Rebel spies managed to steal secret plans to the Empire's ultimate weapon, the Death Propeller, an armored canoe with enough power to get across the mighty Mississippi. Pursued by the Empire's sinister agents, Princess Longboat races home aboard her starship, custodian of the stolen plans that can save

name: Blue Whale Plush
description: This is actually kind of big for a plush. About the size of a small club, in fact. If only it were more rigid.

name: Alternian Dueling Fork
description: From a young age, prospective heiresses to the Alternian empire are trained in deadly combat: honorable and otherwise.

name: Hoarn
description: Whenever you attempt to propel your boat with this, it emits a loud HONK. I hope you're not planning on fishing, because it's scaring away the fish.

name: Tuning Foark
description: Important if you're looking to tune the entire oarchestra.

name: Tenoar Flute
description: Tuned a bit lower than your average concert C flute to give you that deep, burly, sailor tone.

name: Electric Guitoar
description: It's a guitar, but shaped like something you could row a boat with! Yeah, we're not sure how that's any different either.

name: Banjoar
description: It's a french banjo! No, wait. It's just a banjo you can use for sculling. Nevermind.

name: Tron Gloves
description: These gloves will also store your identity, because you should always have your identity stored in 5 different places at once.

name: Sparkling Apple Cider
description: This fruity beige liquid seems to twinkle in the light. You probably could have achieved the same effect by dumping the special stardust into your apple juice.

name: Acoustic Guitoar
description: Warning: Moisture from use as oar may render use as guitar impossible.

name: Cetacean Barnacle Remover
description: This massive blue hooked implement seems to be large enough to reach around something the size of a whale. The reason you think of a whale in particular is because of the blue whale ornament near the base. Nifty!

name: Nordic Bat
description: A roughly carved baseball bat. Nordic runes are etched into it, and the grip is of worn leather.

name: Heated Swing
description: A deadly bat that, with enough strikes, can be set ablaze! Much to the disadvantage to your foes.

name: Week-old Baguette
description: A completely dried out, long loaf of bread. This thing has become so hard, you could cut your teeth on it.

name: Space Sword
description: Defending yourself from underlings is no problem when you can pull swords out of Uranus.

name: Casino Royalty
description: You look sharp enough to cut more than the deck, too bad you're not licensed to kill.

name: Chocolate Cleaver
description: Same cleaver shape, new chocolate flavor! It's literally just a cleaver made out of chocolate. Whee.

name: Phantasmic Dress of the Aquamarine Sun
description: This ghostly dress radiates with infinite energy that disintegrates most attackers upon contact, but it also allows you to float around like a ghost, as well as become intangible and pass through walls! The only problem with your near-invincibility is the blinding aquamarine light this thing gives off... Ow...

name: Evil Dead 1981 Poster
description: A classic piece of memorabilia for a classic masterpiece in cinematic horror. Even if you weren't really around when it came out, you are certain of this fact. You haven't seen its latest incarnation, but it couldn't possibly live up to the original.

name: Wish-Guided Darts
description: A set of red and gold darts which are guided by your wishes.

name: Bangin\' Blue Ecto-Pizza
description: A whole pizza with ectoplasm sauce, mozzarella cheese, and blue pepperoni! It has healing properties, but you never really feel full after eating it.

name: Magnetic Knives
description: These two long, sharp curved blades are made of magnetite, the most magnetic naturally-occurring mineral on that place that doesn't exist anymore. I hope you don't live on a metallic land...

name: Guard Armor Puppet
description: A puppet that resembles the Guard Armor. The arms, legs, head, and torso are all separate pieces, just like the actual Guard Armor, but they do not move independently.

name: Fluorite Scepter of Infinite Chance
description: A dark blue scepter inset with 252 gems of varying sizes adorning the handle that change color as the light hits them, and a large 8 sided die for the head. You feel as though this scepter contains the magic to do anything...so long as its wielder can control the immense chaotic energies that is...

name: The Bat of Nrub\'yiglith
description: A powerful baseball bat with the powers of the Grimdark arts. Be careful using this item. The power may overthrow someone.

name: Bandit Headset
description: A bandit mask with built in communicator. Now you can chat with your friends whilst you loot the corpses of your enemies!

name: Dual Kamas
description: Two basic reaping tools with short handles and sharp blades. Crops or throats, they know no difference....

name: Frisbee
description: This plastic throwing disc is a timeless toy for outdoor fun.

name: Knitted Bunny
description: After your bunny got messed up, your friend luckily knew how to fix it.

name: Chargin\' Targe
description: A shield used by a legendary Black-Scottish warrior used for charging in and bashing assailants. Though worn and torn, it is still as effective as if it was brand new.

name: Strange Frying Pan
description: After combining your favorite game's disc with a frying pan you had, nothing new visually can be seen. However, unbeknownst to you, the imps see their own death in third person and a kill counter slowly rising in value.

name: Mountain Dew - Livewire
description: The original supercharged soda, now with the citrus zing of vitamin C. Start the day with flavor! (Disclaimer: product does not actually contain vitamins of any kind)

name: The Reaper
description: Makes the skin crawl just to touch it.

name: Parappa the Rapper Disk
description: A game about an anthropomorphic dog rapping about every single thing that happens in his life. If repeating everything someone says is considered rapping...

name: Cola-Canister: Caustic Crab-apple Flavor
description: Rip the seal, throw and pray. Open up happiness (and shrapnel).

name: The Punisher
description: A ridiculously heavy, incredibly large cross. Of course, the reason it's so heavy is because it's so full of mercy!

name: Studded Skull Gloves
description: The biker who made these must have been one hardcore dude, cause he killed two people just to make this pair of gloves. ...or at least two midgets.

name: Iji USB Drive
description: A game where you are Iji, the lone survivor of an alien invasion. Oh, she also had a lot of guns.

name: Tasen Nanogun
description: It fires all sorts of different weapons. However, you do not have a nanofield, so it's just a fancy shotgun right now.

name: Buster Gun
description: A modified Tasen Nanogun that fires shotgun shells at triple speed.

name: Hayato\'s Smokin Bombs
description: This set of dynamite is more than you'd expect. In the right hands, they can cause MASSIVE damage.

name: Beef Jerky
description: A package of leather-hard beef jerky, smoked and spiced to perfection.

name: SCP-426
description: I am an anomalous toaster. My effects include being completely unable to refer to me in the third person.

name: Youkai Buster
description: The Ultimate Weapon used in Youkai extermination. Careful, Excessive use of this needles may make you get obsessed with donations.

name: Tesla\'s Boomstick
description: A powerful rifle that fires a powerful burst of lightning strikes. Caution: Could really mess up your brain chemistry or something.

name: Cyclic Fusion Ignition System
description: Fires a short-range beam that cuts through enemies. Well, ok, it doesn't really cut, it kind of just turns whatever you point it at to ash.

name: Keycane
description: This walking cane is rumored to be able to open any lock, or seal it away forever. Also notably good for opening skulls.

name: Swiss Army \'puter
description: A multitasking computer with an edge. Haha, you see what I did there?

name: Skulltop Lite
description: A smoother, less bulky model of the highly sought-after Skulltop, for high connectivity, endurance AND menace!

name: DRAOGWN RAMOR
description: An incredibly warm and pixellated set of steel armor, stylized to look like... Well, maybe at one point it looked like a dragon. Now you're just not sure.

name: Exteeeending Aaaaarm
description: The latest in Kappatech innovations, now with added reach, durability, and lasers!

name: Kotowari
description: The sword of the Colorless King. It is said that the sword was sealed away deep within a lake and guarded by giants.

name: Braviary Staff
description: A bo staff colored red, white, and blue. It knows the moves Brave Bird, Roost, Fly, and Tailwind. Yes, that's right. It knows Pokmon moves. And it's a staff.

name: Timeboard
description: Finally you can travel through time while playing your favorite music on your portable piano!

name: Butcher\'s Mascara
description: It takes sacrifice to be beautiful, and this mascara takes that to heart. Using this makeup, you have a bigger chance of stabbing yourself in the eye, but you'll also be better at stabbing Imps with it!

name: Slinky
description: The springy, sproingy, classic toy for all ages. May spontaneously combust in extrememly rare cases.

name: Moxxi\'s Very Mentionables
description: Don't spill anything or they'll get all wet

name: Come Hell and Highfire
description: The grim reaper's souvenir given to him when he returned from hell, and still he can't find the switch that turns off the flames.

name: Red Robe
description: You start your new Journey in a Red Robe. And although you wished you could wear a White Robe like your Ancestors, you are not ready yet. And yet, you are proud to wear this robe.

name: Prismic Shield
description: It's be useful if you want to block a flashlight, but nothing much else.

name: Double Headed Scythe
description: A large Scythe with two heads. Try not to hurt yourself

name: IRONIC CLASSEY KRAMPISS...
description: This extremely stupid santa toy is so ironic that it transcends the system of irony entirely and becomes cool again.

name: Casey\'s Cricket Bat
description: Cricket? You gotta know what a crumpet is to understand cricket!

name: Fairly Grimm Fedora
description: This hat looks wicked sharp! Maybe a little more wicked than you were expecting.

name: Rave Outfit
description: A new set of clothes decked in neon colors and flashy fabric, perfect for a rave!

name: Film-action Rifle
description: This sophisticated, finely crafted weapon lets you zoom in reel close for the perfect snapshot. Smile for the bullet!

name: Cardboard Tube Sword
description: The crowning POS for your amazing Cardboard Tube Samurai costume.

name: American Wand
description: This red, white and blue wand is basically only useful for using unlocking spells and shooting off fireworks sporadically.

name: Etch A Sketch
description: No need for a bulky computer to make sophisticated digital artwork. The triumphant, lo-fi technological wonder device...that is also a toy!

name: Dovahpiin
description: Dovahpiins contain the souls of dragons. This of course gives them some weird powers, like shouting.

name: Captain Planet\'s Rainbow-Tron Identification Pedestal
description: Oh my god what have you done. Now it won't stop flashing different colors. It also won't stop spouting quotes about saving the environment, which is even WORSE.

name: Tron Mascot Headgear
description: It's annoying to wear this, mostly because of the bright blue rave lights flashing all over the face of it.

name: Great Abrasion
description: The lost souls contained within this backscratcher are said to have itched themselves to death. Relieve your foes of their discomfort by bringing them a swift end.

name: Tree Trimmer
description: A bladed polearm with rapidly rotating cutting teeth. Useful for trimming the tops of trees, or the heads of your enemies.

name: Violet Sports-Rake of Equine Fury
description: This purple backscratcher, topped with a sharp, hardened hoof, fills you with the burning rage of a mighty mustang as it tramples a field full of athletes. How dare they use such a beautiful, wide open field to play some silly game where they tackle each other? Why would they use such artificial and tasteless grass? Now these itching questions can be dealt with. It's time to put your hoof down and rub out the annoyances.

name: Parallaxe
description: Enemies that come in contact with this axe will automatically lose control of all motor functions, courtesy of the absolutely ridiculous amounts of electricity running through the blade. That way, once you've cleaved open a portal in space-time and tossed your stricken opponents into the Furthest Ring, they'll stay still long enough to appreciate the view.

name: LizardLord\'s Science Elemental Science Laser Sci-Scithe of Sciencey Science
description: This scythe, bolstered by many different kinds of science, lasers, and (again) science, bears the name of a reptile fanatic who was known to wreak havoc on the minds of everybody.

name: Sonic Pen
description: A sleek, black pen with some kind of noise-making device at the end. It would probably be a bad idea to hold two of them together.

name: Lightningstorm Tonfa
description: The magnetism of the blade increased the electrical flow, making this weapon even deadlier than before. Ow ow ow your hand is going numb. Ok stop holding it now.

name: Toweltop
description: The perfect thing for any hitchhiker. If you can get wifi, that is.

name: Wig of Beauty
description: This wig is so unnaturally PINK. Wearing it makes you want to shout at just about everything that confuses you.

name: Masamune of the Frog
description: Weapon of a legenday hero. Some say it could get stronger...

name: Blue Key-Slime Pie
description: You're not sure you want to eat this. Sure, key lime pie is pretty great, but not when it's dripping slime and glowing blue.

name: Kanohitop
description: A laptop shaped like the Kanohi Hau, the mask worn by the BIONICLE character Tahu. Its eyes glow relentlessly. Ever-staring. Ever-watching. Ever-waiting.

name: Motorcycle Suit
description: A suit lined with durable rubbers and plastics designed to withstand high-speed dismount and the following impact. Also insinuates that you own and/or are riding a motorcycle.

name: Caledfwlch
description: A legendary sword, reforged. A piece of shit is a lot better when it's a whole piece of shit.

name: Blue Phantasmic Caledfwlch
description: A legendary sword, now able to hit ghosts! That is, if they existed. Other than that, it acts as a pretty neat source of glowing blue healing ghost goop.

name: Wreath of the Clown\'s Squirting Flowers
description: You've always thought squirting flowers were a rather obnoxious accessory. Now you have an entire wreath of them.

name: Pillow of Heart
description: A pillow that seems to be able to mentally influence or slightly mind-control those beaten by it... Or smothered, if that's your style.

name: Captain Planet\'s Lemon Flavored Identification Pedestal
description: This rainbow pillar is now covered in delicious citric acid. However, instead of being delicious, it seems to be so concentrated it will eat through anything it touches.

name: Lampo\'s Shield
description: Capable of delivering mild to severe electric shocks to all, this shield is useful for both attack and defense. Let's just hope you:re immune to its zaps as well.

name: Party Scalpel
description: This surgical tool is sure to lighten up any birthday party. Or, you know, not.

name: Faygo Cannon
description: Why shoot cannonballs at enemies when you can shoot wicked elixers at them instead?

name: Flag of Cleaveland
description: It's a flag. With a bunch of crossed meat cleavers decorating it. Waht.

name: French Cleaver
description: A meat cleaver with a small French flag waving from the handle. Somehow you're pretty sure that it got a power increase even though the flag is literally the only difference. God this game is weird.

name: Nobody\'s Deck
description: No matter what, I'll never forget...

name: Blood Rocket
description: Take to the skies in this Blood Red Jetpack. PCHOOOOOOOOH GOD THIS THING IS POWERED BY ACTUAL BLOOD OH GOD OH GOD OH GOD OH GOD

name: Drillstaff
description: A staff with a drill head attached to each end, good for digging and for fighting!

name: Pool Balls
description: A set of 15 billiard balls.

name: Magic Pool Balls
description: A set of 15 billiard balls that may or may not have magical properties.

name: Darkmoon Tonfas
description: A pair of tonfas as mysterious as the dark side of the moon. Perfect for defeating the huns.

name: Poppin\' Green Apple Hoop
description: This apple-green hoop pops and sparks as you whirl it around your hips.

name: Suit of the Green Sun
description: What is a dapper, omnipotent gentleman without an equally omnipotent suit?

name: Limange
description: This fruit couldn't decide whether it wanted to be a lime or an orange... so it settled for a compromise.

name: Glowstaff
description: A giant glowstick and some cool spinning tricks makes you the life of the party.

name: Squiddles Happy Playtime Scissors
description: All your squishy, cephalapodal friends, now present on your scissors. Be careful not to hurt yourself! Others, not so much.

name: Blast Scythe
description: This scythe is a modestly powered weapon with a machine gun function. Why worry about range when you can slice 'n' dice and blast to kingdom come!

name: Skyshatter Talon
description: A tremendous trident, its tines hewn from the talons of an ancient, primordial hawk. Also machine washable!

name: Hooded Trench Coat
description: The perfect attire for blending into the shadows. People will look out on the horizon, see you approaching, and think "who is that mysterious figure?" You're the mysterious figure. It's you.

name: Fanchor
description: Sinking ships before it was cool.

name: Claymore Knives
description: These blade-like knives are best used in close combat, but are very durable.

name: Rebellion Flag of the Villein
description: A tattered red flag that inspires unity and allegiance to the holder in all who see it.

name: Game Boy Classic
description: An 8-bit handheld video game device. Uses 4 AA batteries. You wonder why does it have the label "do not matrix with stereo sound"

name: Dual Shovelknives
description: A pair of long, flat knives that sorta resemble shovels.

name: Exploding Chocolate Cream Bow
description: A bow made of chocolate and cream? Oh boy! Arrows fired from this bow explode in a cocoaphonous burst! Delicious!

name: Lemon Necklace
description: A necklace with a small lemon charm. Great use of alchemy here!

name: Rave Gloves
description: With colored lights on each of your fingertips, you'll soon be gloving like a champ.

name: Unofficial SBurb Cheat Code Manual
description: With a cover decorated with pumpkins and candy corn, and the pages inside shifting randomly like a roll of dice, constantly spinning and showing new facets, you're sure that this is the weirdest book you have ever seen. Undoubtedly, it will take quite some time sifting through this hefty guide before any of it can become relevant. You're probably better off just using it to hit things.

name: Toilet Duct Tape Roll
description: Toilet "paper" made out of duct tape instead of paper. This won't end well at all.

name: Timekeeper Gear
description: A plain red gear that, despite not being attached to anything, spins at a perfectly constant rate.

name: Duct Tape Trench Coat
description: A long ankle-length trench coat made entirely of duct tape. The material is a bit stiff, but it's completely waterproof and even has several duct-tape pockets.

name: Emptier of Kiddy Pools
description: A dangerous combination of electricity and water, and water safety devices. At least you won't drown!

name: The Tesslator
description: This clawed coily implement can cast electrically-charged portals onto flat surfaces from afar. Experience the magic of science without the itch of potential failure!

name: Supersonik Elektronik
description: Electricity courses through this miracle of reclaimed retro-modern technology at a variable rate specified by the user - at low levels, it will gently massage your back as it scratches. At high levels, you could probably overload an entire power plant. Whoever came up with the name must have been subjected to too much of the latter.

name: Super Sitrus Sider
description: This swirling multicolored drink is packed with almost too much citrus (and alliteration) for any sane human to handle.

name: Magician\'s Red
description: Your foes can make all the fried chicken jokes they like: you'll have the last laugh when the blazing ankhs start flying.

name: Lava Shot
description: You want to shoot hot, glowing, psychadelic lava straight into your veins? Maybe you should point that at the imps instead.

name: Dramon Killers
description: Claws which aided a powerful Dragon type Monster in battle and are very effective against any Dramon-species. You are not sure what that means, but you are sure they would be a two-edged sword if you were one yourself.

name: Assault and Battery
description: This giant club-shaped battery might not fit in any of your appliances, but it makes up for it by being much better at smashing imps than your ordinary ones.

name: Ghost Whisperer\'s Hoop
description: This sleek, silver hoop has little skulls adorning it and is rumored to aid communication with the deceased.

name: War of the Roses
description: This battleaxe is simultaneously elegant and hardcore. It has red and white roses growing around the handle and what looks like the Luck of the Roses dice inside a crystal globe at the end.

name: Captain Planet\'s Radioactive Lemon Detecting Pedestal
description: Now this pedestal is covered in lemon juice that can sense radioactivity. However, the juice itself is also highly radioactive, which makes it quite deadly.

name: Stuffed Toad
description: Kissing this will not give you a wart.

name: Essence of Emptiness
description: A glass vial filled with an odd blue liquid that somehow doesn't seem to be entirely there. It's labelled with a darker blue swirly symbol.

name: Double-Bladed Crafting Cutlery of the Squiddlesassin
description: Don't let the cheerful characters and awkward, tentacle-like shape of these scissors fool you, it could be the last mistake you make.

name: Breeze Pipe
description: A foot-long blue tube with a constant stream of air flowing through it and what looks to be a symbol representing wind on the side. Perfect for those hot days.

name: Golden Master Sword
description: This legendary blade was once used by The Hero of Time, who saved the world from the evil Ganondorf. Now it can be used by you, and with a new golden design!

name: Razor Star Shades
description: Now you can get messages in the most bad ass way.

name: Life-Timer
description: It looks like an ordinary hourglass egg timer, but the sand continues to flow one way no matter how you turn it. You wonder who it belongs to.

name: Bill Door\'s Scythe
description: You wouldn't have thought it possible to cut only one blade of grass with each swing, but somehow this scythe won't let you do it any other way.

name: Flaming Needles
description: A pair of strong, steel knitting needles with a flame design along the back edge, that use a fiery attack against enemies.

name: Amethyst Gasmask
description: Its a Gasmask made out of Amethyst! Now its a cool Purple color!

name: Gold Octet
description: Magical dice, now with the added enchantability of gold! That, and the fact that they shimmer in the light.

name: Historic Grinchmas Darts
description: These swift darts are covered in metallic green fur and moldy memories.

name: [K]omputer
description: Thanks to this computer, you are no longer required to use the CD in order to see some SaruMi feels, or other such [K] content.

name: Moustache Hammer
description: It's a hammer with a clever disguise. The enemy will never see what hit them.

name: Silver LightSpaff
description: About as useless as your Lightstaff, except now it can be used as giant spoon and has a more silver-y tint.

name: Mistletoad
description: Normally, you would kiss while hanging under a sprig of vegetation during festive times. But now you have to contend with the beady eyes of a fake frog staring at you while you do it. Happy Holidays!

name: Emblem of the Freedom Toast
description: A red- and white-striped flag with a blue piece of starry toast in the center. Show those French chefs who the REAL toastmaster (and recipe thief) is!

name: Laptron
description: While your glowing laptop features the sleekest of themes on the grid, it cannot unfortunately teleport you into cyberspace.

name: Hoodie Armor
description: it keep you warm, but it also protects you from attacks of monsters/or enemies. Not only that, but it looks kick-ass too!

name: Z-Knuckle
description: The gloves the legendary Reploid Zero, it is used to steal your oponents weapons, but you feel like you are pulling "other" things as well.

name: Swiss Army Die
description: A d20 that opens up into a variety of tools depending on which number is rolled. Very helpful if you're lucky, but it can be a hassle to roll the right tool.

name: MPFB Devestator
description: This gun shoots three fission based explosives that cause massive damage. You better be pretty strong to fire this thing, otherwise it will knock you over.

name: Shining Naginata
description: Made of pure gold, this thing sure is heavy. You can barely swing it around.

name: Draconomikunai
description: This not-so-basic-anymore ninja tool is decorated with dark red scales and an edge of sharp teeth.

name: Deathscythe Easel
description: Scythe blades jut out of the ebony legs of this easel, making it awkward to wield and impractical to use. The haunting sound it emits when you touch it are just mocking you now.

name: Superheated Pizza Cutter
description: With the searing rotary blade, you no longer have to cook the food you cut with this! Of course, you're just as likely to burn it as well. It also doubles as a neat weapon.

name: Blade of Amaterasu
description: Glowing with the rays of the morning sun, this would only be the weapon of the goddess herself.

name: Tainted Goddess
description: The green blade is enveloped in emerald flames. Wielding it makes you feel like an excellent warrior.

name: Kanaya\'s Choice
description: You can choose between black and stunning green. Or a roaring blade that shreds anything in front of it. Whichever you like.

name: Guan Dao of the Heart
description: This red polearm glows with the power of the human soul.

name: Aperture Science Anime-Themed Ocular Heads-Up Display Device
description: We at Aperture Science know that it is important to know where you are going and what you are looking at while you are testing. This device simply makes it easier for you, for us, for testing. Please use the device wisely and thank you for being such an... adequate testing subject.

name: Electric Halo
description: This isn't a true halo. You need power it up from time to time to ensure it continues to give off a faux-saintly glow.

name: Bow Staff
description: A combination Bo Staff and Bow. It looks a bit odd. It is designed for more defensive fighting than some other weapons. It has a relatively long reach.

name: Miniature Paper Anchor of Quantum Fansics
description: Thanks to the science of Quantum Physics, this miniature paper fan can cut straight through to the bottom of the ocean.

name: Lich\'s Phylactery
description: What a nice piece of jewelry you have there... You most certainly didn't have to destroy any being of dark power to obtain it, right?

name: Grater
description: This wonderful metal kitchen tool is useful for grating cheeses, potatoes, turnips and any number of food items you would like grated. When you're all done, it doubles as a sponge-mangler.

name: Sode-garami
description: A spiky Japanese polearm once used to snag the sleeves of thieves and intruders.

name: Holy Cutting Tool of Divine Squiddlescension
description: "And unto squiddlekind, their god giveth the power to taketh away." What a grave mistake it would be if these were to fall into the wrong hands.

name: Captain Planet\'s Radioactive ElecTRONic Lemon Homerun Pedestal
description: This pedestal is shaped like a baseball bat and is covered in radioactive lemon juice. It's much more threatening than it sounds.

name: The Hard Truth
description: To better inform the populous of the steely truth and to give them the cold, hard, facts. Or maybe just a massive black eye.

name: Empiriceist\'s Wand
description: This wwand can obliterate your lowwblood enemies wwith science, as wwell as freeze them wwith the power of subzero temperatures!

name: Checkmate Chainsaw
description: Only a true Grandmaster should use this duality themed chainsaw.

name: Book of Elven Songs
description: A book of sheet music for the lyre, written by elves. The music is supposed to be hauntingly beautiful, but whenever you try to play any of it, it just comes out as a hissing screech. Maybe you need ELF TEARS to properly play any of it.

name: Gold Octet of Celestial Fire
description: This bunch of golden dice shines like normal gold, but burns with the heat of a thousand stars. It's good it doesn't hurt you, considering that it can incinerate your enemies in less than a second.

name: Katanasickle
description: Its basically still a katana, just curved into a sickle-like shape. You're pretty sure that would make it useless, but it seems that in this game it made it stronger.

name: Chainchucks
description: A pair of nunchucks with spinning blades attached. Probably not the safest thing in the world.

name: Sunlight on a Stick
description: You're not sure how sunlight can be on a stick, but it's too blinding to look and see for yourself.

name: Reaper Man\'s Scythe
description: Sharpened on daylight, the blade glows blue and is keen enough to cut through sound.

name: Linkin Park CD
description: I wanted to write a description for this, but even though I tried, it all fell apart. I guess in the end it didn't even matter.

name: Compu-Sooth Gasgoggles
description: Now you can stalk your friends both online and IRL while spelunking through dangerous dungeons.

name: Plasma-Bladed Spacerenders
description: These claws are heated to the point where they start to both burn and cut through space and time alltogether. However, you're more interested in the fact that you can cleave through many a foe with a single flick of the wrist.

name: Aperture Science Anti-Injury Cranial Protection Device
description: As per Aperture Science Self-Protection Protocols, this helmet has been reinforced with several layers of metals and has shown maximum efficiency in the field of testing. Please use the device wisely and we thank you for being such an... adequate testing subject.

name: Amethyst Anchor
description: An Anchor made out of solid Amethyst!

name: Kappa-deep-dive-night-o Vision Visor 2.0
description: The New and improved Visor of the kappa tribe to deep-dive waters and night missions, it shoot cucumber-like lasers and bubbles. You wonder what happened to the 1.0 version(?)

name: Rose Star
description: The blades of this shuriken are as sharp as the thorns of a rose, and just as beautiful as the flower as the rose red metal gleams in the light.

name: River Spirit Armor
description: Kendo armor that once belonged to a River Spirit. A gift to the mortal realm, they serve to protect the wearer through all battle and weather.

name: White Blazer of the Scratch Doctor
description: A blindingly white blazer with a faint green aura. Wearing it appears to give you a glimpse of knowledge of relatively everything, but you try not to think about that too much.

name: Trombone
description: Now you too can sound like an adult from Charlie Brown!

name: Ball of Yarn
description: This is just an ordinary ball of yarn. Just a boring ball of yarn.

name: Silken Wizardbeard Yarn
description: This ball of yarn has magical properties because it is made of a wizard... You can probably make something with magical properties that is more useful than this.

name: Color Guard Flag
description: A 3'x4' piece of colorful silky fabric attached to a metal pole six feet long. You can spin and toss it quite gracefully before swinging the weighted end into an opponent's face.

name: Golden Apple
description: An apple made from gold! It's almost certainly worth a lot of money!

name: Sock Choppet
description: It looks like an ordinary sock puppet until you open its mouth. Chop up vegetables, nuts, fruits, and imps quickly and easily. Vince would be so proud.

name: Dragonbreath Darts
description: These fiery darts were forged in the gullet of a fierce draconic adversary...or they would have been if you hadn't cheated with alchemy.

name: Life Preserver
description: A ring-shaped floatation device, useful for rescuing people from water.

name: Touhou Flag
description: This flag is white with a red dot in the middle like Japan's, but with various Touhou characters decorating the white space. What more could a flag need?

name: Spades Flag
description: A black-as-night spade rests on a field of grey. This flag reminds you somewhat of old noir movies, for whatever reason.

name: Flag of the Imperial Legion of Skyrim
description: A silver dragon soars on a field of black- this flag is adorned with the symbol of the Legion and the Empire.

name: Time-Stopping Overcoat
description: Gears on each of the sholders spin constantly. Holding them still freezes you in time, allowing you to evade attacks.

name: Life Savers Candy
description: These fruit-flavored candies are shaped like little life preservers, but likely haven't actually saved any lives.

name: Deathblade
description: With the knowledge of a dungeon master and the skill of an alchemist, this poison will bolster your attack by crippling opponents.

name: Crystalline Goddess
description: At the core of this diamond weapon lays a pulsing center of liquid gold. Thank goodness it's unbreakable.

name: Meeting of Sun and Moon
description: Sporting a slightly more curved blade than usual, this sign of yin and yang is an excellent weapon for a spritualist on their journey through Nihon.

name: Polearm of the Opposing Sides
description: You can't go wrong in a fight between good and evil when they're too busy making out to actually fight.

name: Time Slasher
description: Forget the DeLorean, forget the Police Box, forget the Well. The real way to travel through the 4th dimension is by slashing a hole in the fabric of spacetime.

name: Timetables
description: With these time-travelling turntables, you can take DJing to a whole new level!

name: Blue Phantasmic Caledailddirwyn
description: A blue ghost-sword with a funny gear on it! It's always spinning, but if you hold it down, you can stop time around you, or even turn it back. The time properties this thing has don't interest you, though: you're more interested in how to pronounce the name...

name: Ground-Ripper Gauntlets
description: With Drills made of Pure Energy, these gloves can cut through stone and steel with ease. Point away from face when in use.

name: Lantern of Mind
description: This lantern glows with the energy of thought, the power of the aspect of Mind. Using this, you can read minds, and even see what those pesky imps are planning to do with all of your stuff they nabbed earlier.

name: iSBaHJ
description: This used to be an iPhone, but now it's some otherworldly abomination. Pixelly and glitchy, this thing barely works, and it's so unreal it's hard to even hold onto. Why the fuck did you even make this useless thing?

name: Long-Handled Billputer
description: It's the same weapon as before, but now you can check your e-mail while battling imps and ogres.

name: Shocking Billhook
description: Whenever you attack an underling, lighting arcs from the tip of the gardening tool to anything nearby.

name: Fairy Ring
description: This hula hoop has little butterfly wings on it and sheds fairy dust when you twirl it...or maybe that's just glitter.

name: Hula Dancer Figurine
description: This Hawaiian souvenir depicts a hula dancer and actually dances when it's sitting on the dashboard of a car.

name: Badassitude
description: Forged from the fiery cleft of Mr. Tourges pecks, this shotgun of pure adrenaline pumping, gut wrenching, badass makes grown men weep in its awesomeness.

name: White Gloves
description: Necessary for anyone who likes to dress 'sharp' and 'to kill'. Might be a bit too sharp for formal occasions though...

name: MURRIGAN FLGA
description: A distorted, pixelly version of the American flag. It saddens you to see it in such a farcical state. You shed a tear any time you see it wave in the wind, the lossy graphics shimmering in the sun.

name: Aperture Science Knitting Needles
description: Whos idea was it to make a Portal Device out of knitting needles? Because youre fired.

name: Jake\'s Booty Shorts
description: Do he got the booty? He dooooooo.

name: Blue Ecto-Potion
description: Kind of tastes like chicken for whatever reason.

name: Blue Eyes White Dragonskin Suit
description: This suit is made of the skin of one of the rarest dragons ever. Wearing one just screams, "Screw the rules, I have money!"

name: Sieglinde
description: A sacred weapon that is matched with Siegmund, this sword was wielded by Princess Eirika of Renais. Holding this, you feel somewhat stronger and ready to fight monsters.

name: Razor Sword
description: This sword was reforged by two master blacksmiths and was wielded by a legendary hero with a silly green hat. Elegant in it's design, this new, sharper blade is a cut above the rest!

name: Acid Rain Platemail
description: This ancient piece of armor once glowed with a bright blue like the water of a clear river. But now, pollution has hardened this mystical item, causing its majestic glow to dim to a hazy gray.

name: Aperture Science "Fine Taste" Compu-Robe Prototype
description: This is a robe we here at Aperture Science have developed for those who have a refined taste in their testing uniforms. As per Aperture Science standards, this robe has been fitted with a connection to the Aperture Science Global Database for your browsing pleasure. Please use the device wisely and thank you for being such an... adequate testing subject.

name: Wind Steel Suit
description: The steel for this armor is forged from powerful winds. You don't know how this works at all.

name: Pyrovision Goggles
description: While seemingly harmless, when you put these on you see horrific visions of rainbows, candy and unicorns. Truly terrifying.

name: Claidheamh Mor
description: This massive sword gives you the urge to charge drunkenly into your enemies and gouge their eyes out.

name: Meteo Star
description: A throwing star made of a strange rock with Ancient Chinese writing on either side, its impact is like that of a small meteor when thrown.

name: DISE
description: A crudely made, uneven, and pretty much unusable d20 with numbers painted in comic sans.

name: White Squiddle Scissors of the Scratch Doctor
description: Something about these scissors feels... off. Save for the Squiddles, they are pure white and never seem to scratch or otherwise become marred. Still, they cut with such ease and efficiency that their creator must have been inhuman.

name: Squiddleture Science Cephalic Defense Prototype
description: Hello testing subject, as per security protocol 1-3-F, we have requested that all personnel wear this prototype in the honour of our new Squiddle Overlords-- I mean, to test it. Because that is what we do. Test.

name: Boxing Gloves
description: Alright! Now give em' the old one-two, Rocky!!

name: Captain Planet\'s Radioactive ElecTRONic Lemon Timeflow Altering Pedestal
description: This baseball bat shaped pedestal is covered in radioactive lemon acid, and now has a gear that alters the flow of time for the enemies it hits. A truly fearsome weapon indeed.

name: Sweet Vengeance of the Maple Variety
description: Show them what it's aboot. Show them ALL what it's aboot, eh.

name: Chromatic Octet of Celestial Plasma
description: This bundle of magical dice radiates with colours... So pretty... It also can melt enemies with super-hot plasma, too. That's also important.

name: Magic 8-Glasses
description: These black and blue corrective lenses are also excellent fortune telling devices.

name: Portal Katana
description: This double-edged blade glows blue and orange. It seems that whenever you cut something open with this weapon it opens a portal. It seems useful, but the underlings collapse into grist before you can get through the portals.

name: Union Rifle
description: A rifle with the Union Jack on it. Time to show those blasted revolutionaries what for!

name: Cloaked in Midnight
description: An inky black trench coat, much like a member of the crew itself would wear. A little stiff, and it also something of an eerie feeling to it...

name: Haunted Billhook
description: This gardening tool constantly seems to be emitting an eerie, whispering groan. The plus side is, the underlings don't want to be near that thing any more than you do!

name: Consort\'s Skull
description: The skull of a consort, decayed to the bone. What a poor fortune that has befallen this individual.

name: Slytherin Hoodie
description: A black hoodie with the crest of Slytherin House of Hogwarts: School of Witchcraft and Wizardry. Shows off some Slytherin pride!

name: Clockwork Rose-Steel Suit
description: This suit of rose-steel armor is covered in gears that move with the flow of time.

name: X.A.N.A. Glasses
description: These computerized corrective glasses flicker and glow with the red symbol of a certain quantum supercomputer virus.

name: Ancient Draconian Whip
description: A whip, most likely favored by the ancient archaeologists, with faded draconic designs covering it. What did you ask? Did they even have archaeologists back then? Of course they did! What kind of civilization would they have been if they didn't?

name: Bigby\'s Explosive Fist Generating Apparatus
description: With this glove, you can literally throw punches at your enemies that explode on impact. Now you can keep your distance from enemies and enjoy the spectacle of gibbing them in a flurry of fists.

name: Blade-Launching Russian Roulette
description: This massive pair of pistols was supposed to be loaded with a single deadly dagger each as ammunition for lethal rounds of Russian Roulette. However, you've opted to load all twenty chambers for a more efficient way of skewering your enemies.

name: Buzzaxe
description: Essentially an axe with a buzzsaw for a head, it is positively begging to be used to shred up some imps in a psychotic massacre.

name: Woolen Clothes
description: Exactly like your current clothes, only warmer and made of yarn.

name: Dutton Bubble Goggles
description: You can see into eternity. Forever. Ok that's enough.

name: Steel Life Preserver
description: This won't be very useful for saving your life if you're drowning, but if you're attacked by underlings, it'll be far more helpful like this.

name: Fairy Tutu
description: This looks like something your 3-year-old sister would wear to her school play, but the wide tutu protects you from getting too close to any underling teeth.

name: Ears of the White Rabbit
description: You're late, you're late, for a very important date!

name: Holy Fountain Pen
description: This pen writes in flowing red ink that seems to glimmer slightly.

name: Glass of Chocolate Milk
description: What would every meal be without this nectar of the gods? BORING.

name: Industrial Revolution
description: A modified digging drill that instead of a normal drill head, has a very heavy anvil on the end. As it turns out, an anvil spinning at high speed makes for an effective, -if also messy, weapon.

name: Safecracker
description: A brighty colored pickaxe that releases multicolored explosions when striking something - this isn't safe in the slightest.

name: One Thousand Fantastic Colors
description: With a flick of the wrist, a sweep of this fan, an array of colors will assault the enemy. Or, at least paint your walls a few pretty colors.

name: Narpas Sword
description: Hacked from the darkest corners of the virtual realm by the Red Circle of Death for use in the Console Wars, this mighty blade commands the fear and respect of video game antagonists everywhere.

name: Tatooine Flag
description: The international flag of Tatooine, a planet that does not exist.

name: X.A.N.A. Flag
description: The symbol of X.A.N.A. stands out red on the field of black. You feel uncomfortable holding this flag: even though X.A.N.A.'s not real, it would be awful if it was and took over an underling, or worse, the Denizen.

name: Night Flag
description: This flag flows in the dark, as well as being a map of the Earth's old stars.

name: Laser Hard-light Reapfractor Sickle
description: This sickle bends a mix of lasers and hard-light through a prism into a curved, extremely sharp blade.

name: Mickle Sickle
description: This perfectly balanced sickle almost seems to have a mind of it's own, guiding your hand to strike vital parts in enemy physiology as if the weapon itself has an in-depth knowledge of anatomy.

name: Firework Rifle
description: A ranged weapon loaded with leftover Fireworks from a celebration. Packs some highly explosive dakka. Keep very far away from children and face.

name: Tinker-Bell\'s Demise
description: Your new wand shines with sparkles and pink crackling mayjicks.

name: Cello Bow
description: An archer's bow designed in the same fashion as a certain musical instrument. It also happens to be a fully functional instrument and a rather heavy weapon.

name: fanci SATAN
description: All the festive qualities of KRAMPISS, now with extra hellfire!

name: Golden Drilling Gauntlets
description: Some truly opulent drilling gauntlets. Pity you can't use them without getting dirty with all the ore, dirt, and/or blood.

name: Slamhamma
description: This sledgehammer has both the head and the shaft covered with purple and orange stripes. Use it well to slam some imps.

name: Amethyst Crown
description: This is a snazzy gold crown with giant amethysts set into the side. Unfortunately, this is probably better for cosplay than selling here in the Medium.

name: LizardLord\'s Science Elemental Impervious Fedora of Reptilian Sciencey Science
description: This scaled fedora displays more types of science than you can count, forming a protective shield of deadly science perfect for any budding combat scientist or engineer, and it doubles as a throwing chakram. It's also great for science expos.

name: Shadowman\'s Shuriken
description: Holy nuts this thing is huge. It's also supposedly poisonous, so you'd best watch your hands.

name: Music Box
description: A music box that plays a short, haunting tune.

name: Crystal Music Boxes
description: This is a set of beautiful music boxes, each embedded in a bright quartz... Though why anyone would make a pair of music boxes inside some chunks of crystal is beyond you.

name: Adze of the Molten Core
description: Now all the trees you cut down set fire. Not that this matters, since you're just going to use it to burn through imps.

name: Drillshot
description: You know what's better than a Hookshot? A Drillshot, that's what.

name: Flag of Rohan
description: A galloping horse takes up the majority of this flag, with a golden sun shining in the corner.

name: Ruby\'s Knife
description: This is the ancient demon-killing knife of the Kurds- The handle is made of bone and the steel blade has inscriptions on it that are perfect for killing those pesky demons that won't stay down in hell.

name: Flag of the Varden
description: The flag depicts a purple dragon with a red rose flying on a field of white. This is the flag of a true revolution.

name: Pixelated Shovel
description: This shovel isn't much of an upgrade if you intend to use it for diggy-digging holes, but if you try to wallop somebody with it, the sharp, blocky blade should make quite an impact.

name: The Most Opulent Pickaxe In All The Land
description: This thing has enough diamond in it to make a jeweler's eyes fall out.

name: Pickaxe Head Barrage
description: This new line of fireworks is made to launch pickaxe heads everywhere, making it ideal for blast mining or decapitating several imps at once.

name: Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney Game
description: Being a defense attorney has never been so awesome. Although you feel that yelling objection at everything is not a viable strategy in a court of law.

name: Sun-Strengthened Steel-Smelting Stone Striker
description: This pickaxe digs through stone with a voracious appetite, leaving behind nothing but scorch marks and pools of molten metal.

name: Suns #34 Hoodie
description: Sure, some might say that Barkley's career was better with the 76ers or the Rockets, but you know better. Keep warm with this hoodie emblazoned with the number and team of the Round Mound of Rebound.

name: Awakened Masamune
description: So, you got bored of long subquests and decided to ameliorate your weapon, WITH SCIENCE! And guess what, it worked!

name: Player\'s Lucky d20
description: The d20 of choice for any Dungeons and Dragon's player: unbalanced enough to roll the 20's just a bit more often, and with critical results.

name: Naginata: Level Up
description: The naginata attains the sought-for tier of 'Lord, What Lord?' for defeating the terror that plagued all the known universes. Let the world cheer.

name: Junior Compu-Sooth Spectagoggles
description: You can never have too many cool computers.

name: B-sharp
description: A blade with piano keys etched into it, which makes bloody and beautiful music as you slash your way through imps.

name: Clockwork Wind-Steel Suit
description: The gears on this suit now turn with the flow of time and the flow of the wind.

name: Steel Game Dice
description: A pair of fairly heavy steel dice. They are the fairest dice to date, because we all know how much your GM hates cheating.

name: Hazama\'s Fedora
description: Just wearing this Fedora makes you feel like an absolute trolling GOD. It doesn't seem to be affecting your mind in any way, however. ... You have the sudden urge to cut somebody's arm off.

name: iWatch
description: An Apple-branded digital watch with resolution far greater than the eye could reasonably want to see. Even though this didn't exist before the game wrecked Earth, it seems just like the kind of thing the company would do.

name: Woodwind Steel Suit
description: This suit of armor has a constant wind blowing through two clarinets attached to the sleeves of the jacket, causing imps to flee from the annoying noise.

name: Statue of Dutton, the Sleeping Oracle
description: Oh, that this too too solid flesh would melt, thaw and resolve itself into a dew!

name: Googly-Eyed Fortunetelling Mask of the Steed
description: This horse mask tells the wearer's fortunes by displaying, with alarming inaccuracy, a transparent 8-Ball in each eyesocket.

name: SCP-1024
description: An anomalous... Dungeons and Dragons manual? It seems to be filled with incantations rather than game information, though.

name: SCP-005
description: An anomalous key with the ability to open any lock in the world. Why you're using something so useful to bash imps is beyond you.

name: Captain Planet\'s Time Altering Breeze Making Pedestal
description: This pedestal can change time and make the wind blow. It also has a shorter name.

name: Dark Space Reapfractor
description: Rather than causing light passing through it, this scythe's blade instead sucks it in, emitting a (scientifically improbably) beam of darkness instead.

name: SCP-1413
description: An anomalous black ballpoint pen that writes in... red? Urgh. No. That's... not right.

name: Pyro Gasmask
description: This gasmask seems to be constantly on fire. You're not sure what possessed you to put it on, but it doesn't burn you, and you feel rather intimidating while wearing it.

name: The SkullKraker
description: An oversized, squid themed mace. You guess it's time to... get Kraken'.

name: Golden Pick
description: This hideous display of opulence is a surprisingly decent imp-thrashing weapon. Just don't expect it to hold up very well against attacks... being, you know, gold and all.

name: Gelatinous Magic 8-Ball
description: A translucent, blue 8-ball that's quite slimy. However, the viscosity of the ghostly gel keeps the little die inside in place, so all you can do is jiggle it around... until it breaks and makes a mess, that is.

name: Orcish Mace
description: This mace is comprised of orichalcum and blood, but the blood got there after smashing in a few skulls.

name: Grenade Glove
description: A simple glove that allows you to fabricate an infinite quantity of grenades and toss them around.

name: Woodcutting Hatchet
description: Now you can be a lazy fucker and do the same thing as a woodcutting axe! Except with one hand and faster, of course.

name: One Thousand Fantastic Stars
description: A fan depicting several flashy, colorful star clouds, with the intent to dazzle your enemy. You doubt color needed to be added to the plasma clusters, as star clouds are already full of color.

name: A Bone to Pick(axe)
description: A giant bone with the head of a pickaxe at one end, perfect for venting your frustration caused by the incredibly stupid name of said weapon. I gotta axe, why do you have to take a dig at puns?

name: Gigaton Drill Demolishers
description: A wicked pair of massive drill fists, with these on you feel you punch your way through mountains! Just who the hell you think you are?!

name: Claydriver
description: Who cares if claymores are sub-par at thrusting attacks? That's what you're going to use this for since the blade has been replaced by a screwdriver shaft.

name: Maps of Pandora
description: A complete guide to all the nooks and crannies Pandora has to offer. You know, the ones you're too lazy to find yourself.

name: Steel-Toed Drilling Boots
description: These boots have drills in the soles, making them useful for wrecking the linoleum and acquiring extra ore whenever you're digging.
