name: Fear No Wolves
description: A cloak forged in the fires of Hephaestus, it strikes fear in the hearts of those that see its red hue.

name: Chocolate Crown
description: This chocolate crown has little golden coins set into the sides. You feel like it's going to melt in your hair...

name: Industrial-Strength Crowbar
description: Well, if you ever wanted to smash through a a crate of solid steel, this is the bludgeon for you. Hope you can lift it.

name: Mind Specs
description: You can see anywhere in the Incipisphere with these cool glasses... and somehow that includes your friends' minds. It's weird seeing every decision they make, but just as fun making them change their minds.

name: An Axe to Bind
description: Despite how warped and spike-encrusted the blade of this weapon is, it cuts smoothly through the air when swung. The engravings on the handle allow the axe to seal any foe it strikes within the tome from which it was drawn, as an offering to the tentacle-ridden horrors sealed within.

name: Nyx\'s Soulstealer
description: The original romantic rosy colour of this bow has darkened, now a grim, darker pink. The string is a dark indigo, and when you pull it back, you can feel a dark power in it, sucking in the energy of the life around it.

name: Computerized Hoodie
description: Long may you compute in comfy comfort with this fluffy hoodie with an entire computer integrated into it. Too bad it's rather bulky - but who needs to move when you have the entire Internet at your fingertips?

name: JoJo Clackers
description: No, not crackers, clackers. These balls have Js embossed on their smooth steel surface and should make for some good hurt when volleyed.

name: Catch Ya on the Flipside
description: A bent spatula, it will always come back to you.

name: Tron-Handled Billshock
description: A gardening tool adorned with lightning bolts and glowing blue lines. It's maybe the most high-tech thing you've ever seen that originally came out your backyard shed.

name: Shameimaru Hauchiwa Fan
description: The fan of the fastest Tengu in Gensokyo. A simple gesture can create the mightiest of gusts.

name: Cubic Diamond Chestplate
description: Forged from the diamonds precariously harvested over sizzling lava blocks, this armor is guaranteed to last for a long time.

name: Zombies Arisen
description: OH GOD WHAT IS THAT THING!

name: Punishment of the Balance God
description: He'll deliver a boot to your ass if you ever do wrong in his territory. For he is a wrathful God. And you should fear his judgement.

name: Leather Trench Coat
description: A long, ankle-length trench coat made from brown leather.

name: Chancing Death
description: Supposedly what is seen reflected in this prismatic scythe is the image of that person's death. Of course, there's no way of testing this quality without offing yourself.

name: Magnetic Pickaxe
description: Now the ore comes to you!

name: Envy\'s Ambition
description: This pickaxe is magically attracted to precious metals. Fortuitously, it has a nasty tendency to be attracted to the precious metals in the anatomy of nearby enemies instead of ones in nearby rocks.

name: Steel Shovel
description: A shovel made of hardened steel, perfect for showing imps what for if they catch you doing your gardening.

name: Unbreakable Drill Gauntlets
description: Now you don't have to worry about your drill breaking while poking about in that Ogre's stomach.

name: Tesla Whip
description: A whip infused with the electrical power produced by a tesla coil. A long, silver whip that occasionally flashes with violet electrical discharges.

name: Hekatonchire\'s Arm
description: A large arm ripped directly from a four-armed monster. You guess it's disconcerting to be hit by it, as just holding it is uncomfortable enough.

name: Omnifocal Laptop
description: This laptop has a scanner in it, scanning your eyes and adjusting the screen accordingly, making it crystal clear at all times, regardless of your eyesight.

name: Bat out of Hell
description: A flaming baseball bat! Those home-runs are sure going to... Bring on the heat.

name: Tesla Hoop
description: As long as you keep it spinning, you should be safe, as it sends arcs of electricity to your enemies... and friends. Really anyone who happens to be around at the time.

name: Wind Steel ID Suit
description: The winds that blow around this suit hold the identity of whoever wears it. They also happen to glow orange and blue, which is a cool side effect.

name: Hands of the Developing Team
description: The code is develope. Get it? Like "dev" and "elope". Eloping with the devs! ... It wasn't the original intention. I just couldn't fit "developer" into it.

name: Grid Boy Glove 3000
description: This Pip Boy is connected to the grid, and now is connected to a glove.

name: Blue Dragon\'s Talons of Arcing
description: These massive, elongated, and draconic claws are charged with such intense power that you end to liquify enemies with your slashes rather than simply cutting them in two. Ah, the power of science is absolutely shocking when it's in a fantasy-derived form.

name: Little Red Riding Flag
description: A flag made of a silky, deep red fabric. You feel the urge to tear it off the flagpole and wear it as a hood. You fail.

name: Dragonfury
description: These flaming gloves let you hurl MASSIVE fireballs at enemies which explode in the most dramatic fashion, usually leaving behind ashes and liquefying a large variety of non-flammable things in the process.

name: Crazy Diamond Ring
description: The facets of this diamond alternate between blue and bubblegum pink. Strangely enough, you feel like you could punch something and fix it instead of damaging it.

name: Slechet
description: Difficult to wield and fairly imbalanced but it's bound to get the job done at slicing through a few unwanted 'friends'.

name: Bottle of Rat Poison
description: You kept this under the sink and were instructed to never, ever drink it. Of course, now that there's no adults around...

name: Molebane
description: This shovel seems to poison all it comes into contact with, making it perfect for killing moles in the garden. Well, it kills the plants too, but nothing's perfect.

name: The Yardstick of the Reckoning
description: A yardstick charged with the power of space itself, fueled by the Green Sun and crackling with energy. This Yardstick is great as a weapon and as a measurement tool.

name: Flaming Whip
description: This whip is always set aflame, and cracking it down on enemies tends to result in bleeding gashes and third degree burns!

name: Bladed Bow
description: The limbs of this bow have been partially replaced with blades, allowing for close range combat, along with the normal use of a bow.

name: Blank God Tier Pajamas
description: These dull-colored pajamas feel like a gateway to something far more powerful, or just a gateway to your more perfect cosplay.

name: Tesla Knives
description: These knives have built in tesla coils that discharge shocking amounts of electricity upon impact.

name: Slab of the Jaded Fool\'s Ennui
description: This is just an ordinary maroon slab. It's a giant old stone, far too heavy to lift. You guess you can... sit on it?

name: Amber-Encased Insect
description: This firefly is trapped in a hunk of amber. It's still glowing for some reason, although you thought it took hundreds of years for amber to form. You guess you can... use this as a distraction to flee from imps? You're not sure.

name: Stone Pillow
description: This is a pillow made of solid stone... Great for beating imps up with, but probably not very comfortable to sleep on.

name: Feesh\'s Phylactery
description: This is a dead fish on a string. ...It's starting to smell really bad.

name: Watermelon Iced Tea
description: Sweet watermelon-flavoured iced tea, perfect for cooling off in the summer sun!

name: Soul Specs
description: This pair of glasses allows you to see into your opponents' souls, as well as anywhere in the Incipisphere. In addition to your stalking abilities, you can also take control of underlings and make them your own minions.

name: Pillow of Mind
description: Smother imps with this to strip them of their ability make decisions... They'll just sit there, unable to make up their mind on what they should do. That being said, this might not be the wisest thing to sleep on...

name: Metal Folding Easel
description: An easel made of metal. A less capable artistic tool, a more capable offensive tool.

name: Ratchet and Clank CD
description: A video game about a furry creature who purchases vast quantities of absurdly overpowered weaponry with which to demolish his enemies. You somehow feel as though you can relate just a bit.

name: Touch of Corrosion
description: These gloves drip with deadly acids and poisons, rotting away anything it touches asides from the gloves themselves. Also, thanks to SCIENCE, these gloves also lets you literally throw a nasty punch which explodes this deadly cocktail on whatever it hits.

name: Fantastic Fore
description: A clever pun turned into a clever weapon. Not a great club for golf, but it'll sure keep the baddies at bay. WARNING: club may randomly burst into flame.

name: Anarchic Grenade
description: With boredom of philosophy this grenade brings in anarchy with a bang!

name: Vocaloid Headset
description: This headset comes with a pair of butterfly wings attached to the ears, giving its wearer the ability to fly while singing. ... Pfh. Yeah, right.

name: Gentlemanly Sports Rifle
description: Just holding this rifle makes you feel dapper! Sometimes, you can swear you hear someone say 'pull' when you fire!

name: The Full Suit Guitar
description: This acoustic guitar definitely has a card theme going on with its card suit shaped pegs and the four suits emblazoned on the guitar's body.

name: Whip of Karma
description: Don't be foolish you foolish fool wearing the foolishly foolish clothes.

name: Stereoscopic Computer
description: The computer feeds out a 3-d image, but without proper eyewear, it's almost impossible to make out what's what in the blurry mess

name: Kraken\'s Eye
description: The ocular organ of a cephalopodic monstrosity.

name: Banner of Adventure
description: An aged banner bearing the symbol of a giant red d20 representing the struggle and strife of the heroes' adventures.

name: Slytherin Flag
description: Never tickle a sleeping dragon.

name: Orca Mace
description: This black and white mace studded with killer whale reliefs is often used to "persuade" others into saving the whales.

name: Laser Needles
description: Now you can knit yourself a sweater AND bake your enemies at the same time! What else could you need?

name: Gooey Mento-slime
description: A gooey sticky container of gooey sticky Mentos! It looks disgusting.

name: Pointy Dersime Compu-Shades
description: You thought regular anime shades were cool until you saw these. Now you can read the update while staring somebody down with your cool, purple gaze.

name: Gem Star
description: A shuriken made of iridescent gems. When held up in natural sunlight, it will sometimes cast an array of colors onto the ground, almost like a crystal. It has been known to have the impact of a drill when thrown.

name: Fish Skull Chestplate
description: While not actually made out of bones, this enchanted metal breastplate is shaped so that it resembles the skull of a fresh water fish, the eye sockets radiating a pale grey-blue color.

name: American hoodie
description: The ultimate souvenir of American origin!

name: Prospitian Gown
description: With this fancy garb, you'll look more elegant and graceful when moving around!

name: Higashikata Pompadour
description: What did you just say about my hair?

name: Limange-Flavoured Cream Pillow
description: This is basically like a giant cream pillow, except for the fact that imps are put off by the citrusy taste.

name: LARGE HAM-mer
description: A stupidly large hammer made of meat. For some reason, you feel compelled to act completely over the top and put a lot of emphasis in everything you do.

name: Chunk of Uranium
description: This thing looks pretty tasty. Better not eat it, though, because you might need it to power something.

name: World Atlas
description: An extensive book of maps of the planet Earth, from one pole to the other.

name: Horseplay Cosplay
description: For all of your horsing around, this cosplay will fit the requirement for any equine fetish.

name: Lightpick
description: All of the power of a lightsaber, with none of the elegance.

name: Felt Top Hat
description: Now you too can look like a real classy felt (wo)man with this green top hat, comfortable and overall stylish.

name: Rocket Dragon Wing Umbrella
description: This rad weapon can be tricky to use at first, but it sure is convenient! It's size is great for walloping Underlings and as a durable shield. It also grants you the power of flight! Just make sure you don't get hit by the flames.

name: Shield of Draconic Blaze
description: This shield is now covered with an overlapping pattern of faintly glowing and noticeably warm crimson scales. Frostbite should be a nonissue with this on your arm.

name: Crappily Painted Fancy Santa
description: In an effort to make a Fancy Santa more attractive, you made it even uglier.

name: The Ear Rupturer
description: Just when you thought you couldn't make the already annoying "CLANG" of a frying pan any more loud and painful.

name: Limey Lockpickaxe
description: This thing is capable of picking locks in the traditional sense, as well as "picking the lock" by hitting it really hard. Also, it smells vaguely of limes.

name: Faygo Cola Bottlecan
description: Is it a bottle? Is it a can? Nobody can tell, but this stuff tastes awful either way.

name: SolCetus Crown
description: This glowing, rainbow crown is infused with the energies of the fortuitous aspect of Light. In addition to entertaining you for several hours with its glow, it can also blind attacking enemies with blasts of chromatic light!

name: Tesla Miner
description: This pickaxe has lightning arcing off of it in random directions. You should probably wear as much rubber as you can while handling it.

name: Wicked Beheader of the Bloodthirsty Subjugglator
description: The serrated edge of this hatchet's blade sacrifices cutting power in order to maximize internal damage: even a light graze to an Acheron would draw enormous torrents of blood, which would promptly be absorbed into the blade. A small fraction of this bounty would be imbued into the axe and its wielder to add to their combined strength, the rest being offered up to whatever dark and terrible deity its designer served. (Also, its weirdly light. You could probably juggle a bunch of these things ea

name: Spellbook of Mining
description: Most of the spells in this book have something to do with digging, which doesn't make any of them really useful in combat. It is, however, quite heavy, and covered in pointy rocks.

name: Golden-Toed Drilling Boots
description: The added weight from the golden toes make these drill-bottomed boots even better at kicking shins while stepping on toes.

name: Eightfold Magic Deckwand
description: An shiny black wand with a white tip, resembling the ones used by "Magicians". If you don't mind its fake appearance, this thing has some firepower. It has 8 sides and 8 angles.

name: Cheap Fastfood Taco
description: A beef taco with some cheese and a sprinkling of lettuce from Taco Bell. Greasy and cheap.

name: Fruit Gushers - Fantastical Bracingly Sour Lemon Flavor
description: Judging by how most every other edible thing you make is glowing, you don't seem to find this particular item that bad.

name: Galaxy Cell Laser Rifle
description: This laser rifle's powerful beam is powered by a synthetic star within a spherical containment chamber of some sort. You'd love to tinker with it but you'd rather not disintegrate.

name: Coffee
description: Now you can stay up all night killing those imps around your house!

name: Godot Blend #102
description: Blacker than a moonless night, hotter and more bitter than Hell itself... That is coffee.

name: Angel of Death\'s Halo
description: Careful where you grab this thing, now. Although that may not be much of an issue if you're just going to be hucking this ring with scythe blades around its circumference like a chakram and picking it back up.

name: Wrinklefister
description: Now, you can smoothen your clothes and your enemies by punching them with these heated gloves!

name: Staff of Basic Magic
description: This... doesn't really look much different than the original staff. You guess it couldn't hurt to give it a try, though.

name: Security Goggles
description: The hands-free computing device that protects both your files and your eyes!

name: Faygo - Gushing Golden Apple Flavor
description: This Faygo comes in a golden bottle which conveniently obscures the nature of the contents.

name: Smoldering Suit-Jacket of the Clockwork Wind
description: This slightly burnt jacket/suit combo is decorated with time altering gears, and breeze channeling pipes.

name: Northland Drake\'s Permafrost Barrier
description: Waves of chill mist emanate from the icy blue scales of this shield. Curiously enough, your arm is never discomforted by the low temperature. Keep it away from fizzy drinks though. It'll freeze them to the point of explosion.

name: Wwhite Wandstaff of Skaia
description: Bigger than a wand, smaller than a staff, but counting as both, this weapon of science now bears the orb of Skaia on the end.

name: Aperture Science Man-Powered Portal Device
description: Now you can dig portals to wherever you like, provided you have enough manpower and that there's structurally stable dirt between you and your destination!

name: Echidna Crown
description: Made of the fabric of space, this crown is great for absorbing any attacks. Of course, no one ever really attacks the area above your head unless they miss, so this is only really good for headbutting enemies and watching them teleport fifty feet away.

name: Spellbook of Stone Apertures
description: A useful mining spellbook containing spells for opening large holes in the earth. Everything is written in orange and blue, though, making some of the spells really hard to read.

name: Commemorative Aperture Science Man-Powered Portal Device
description: To commemorate your efforts in digging massive holes in imp skulls, here's a gold-plated shovel. Now get back to digging holes in imp skulls.

name: Reversible Sweatshirt
description: A sweatshirt that you can wear inside out or outside out, depending on your mood. Your acquaintances are sure to dig your sense of adaptable style!

name: Wyvern King\'s Stronghold
description: This royal purple shield seems like the perfect thing to keep a hostage monarch company as he awaits the addition of his ransom to a dragon's stronghold.

name: Warm Striped Scarf
description: A thick triple-weave characteristic of the cooler months, this candy scented neck wrap sequences dyed wools of canary, yellow, and mahogany.

name: Chronodrill Gauntlets
description: These are the drills that have pierced the heavens, are piercing the heavens, and will pierce the heavens at some point in the future. Time travel's confusing, guys.

name: Dustdrill Gauntlets
description: These gauntlets turn all the scrap rock you dig up into dust, which is then vented away behind you.

name: The Tear of the Overseer
description: IZ: This was going to be a cool description about lacrimal glands and PSYCHIC TEARS YO PSYCHIC TEARS but then LD-san reminded me that Overseer was a giant 8 8alls and I had to find out what the liquid was. Find out more on my journey next time....

name: Bottle of Tear of the Overseer
description: IZ: So then i went onto google, the logical choice. Bing might have been funnier, but i was looking for answers yo, MANSWERS. Im no hussie, ill put this shortly: ITS A MURDERER, SHE IS. A MURDERER. SHE LIKE THAT WOMAN WHO CUT OFF HER MANS DIDDLER AND TOSSES IT DOWN A RUNNING GARBAGE DISPOSAL AS HER HUSBAND WATCHES. ITS LIKE ACCIDENTALLY FIRING A BAZOOKA IN YOUR HOUSE AND TAKING OUT YOUR KIDS LEFT BRAIN. BUT IT WASNT AN ACCIDENT. THATS WHAT OVERSEERS TEARS ARE. THAT MAGNITUDE. IT PERMANENTLY TURN

name: Tanker of Tear of the Overseer
description: S YOUR FINGERTIPS BLUE. BLUEEEEEE!!!! THAT'S NOT ALL HOMIE, THAT AIN'T ALL. "The trial subjects self-administered small doses of the fluid to their tongues. Trial subjects reported the following side-effects:  Hideous taste (100%) Numbness of the application area (100%) Blue fingertips (100%) Headache (50%) " AND "However, the authors recommend that no further human trials begin without animal studies." YOOOOOOO WHAT THE FUCK

name: Illegal Contraband
description: This shit is so illegal, yet so critical to your success. Of course, this is all on the assumption that this is not a null or void session.

name: Faygo - Completely Crazy Krispy Kreme Flavor
description: Who knew that donut-and-ghost flavored Faygo could taste so good?

name: Jeweled Wand of Time
description: A wand studded with jewels and...a giant gear? You're not really sure what it does, but damn it looks cool.

name: SPAS
description: A shotgun you're fairly certain is banned in a few Liberal areas. Used by everyone's favorite silent protagonist.

name: Antique Claymore
description: There was pretty much no way alchemiting a claymore and an antique sword wouldn't make this.

name: Flag of the Dew Nation
description: Quench your thirst with the blood of your enemies, and Mountain Dew! Having this flag will let everyone know how rad you are.

name: Nicer Slicer
description: This razor glows just like a glowstick, allowing you to shave while you rave!

name: Quantum Computer
description: A really powerful computer. So powerful, in fact, that you have almost no use for it.

name: Golden Flesh
description: A slab of aspect-restoring meat with a golden hue. Can also be a surprisingly useful consolation prize.

name: Pocketshield
description: It's a TINY ordinary wooden shield, small enough to snugly fit into any pocket. You're not blocking anything with it, but at least it's handy to carry around...

name: Cosplay Dark Cat Wings
description: A connected back piece of midnight black feathered wings and a pitch black cat tail. As though someone combined a Panther and a Crow. Wearing this makes you feel slick, sleek, badass, and not the least bit ridiculous.

name: Dark Cat-Bird Tier Pajamas
description: This monochrome set of God Tier Pajamas seems to have a set of dark feathered wings and a black cat tail coming off the back of it.

name: Lemon-Lime Grimdark Fruit Juicer
description: The power of lime has mutated due to exposure to the energy of the Eldritch powers. With the power of the Horrorterrors on your side, is it even possible to lose? The answer is yes. You can still lose.

name: Botted Goggles
description: A guided aiming system that attaches to your face. These specs will "help" you land your blows more effectively.

name: Smaug Cosplay
description: This cosplay is almost exacly the same as the Dragon Cosplay, however their is now a magical energy surrounding it.

name: Compu-Robe
description: A robe with computer wiring all through it. Be careful not to damage the circuitry!

name: Triglaive
description: A powerful item created by the gods many years ago, coveted by evil. The ancient Triglaive is the secret of the power of Prospit. If Derse ever gets their hands on it, the kingdom will surely be corrupted by darkness. ...Wait, those are the rings. This is just a very powerful weapon.

name: Ctrl X
description: If you're planning on using this on some imps, you'd best hope they don't know how to Ctrl Z...

name: Sword Art Online DVD
description: The English dubbed version of a very popular anime, featuring the exploits of teenagers in an online game that is literally life-threatening. Something about this screams irony to you, but you can't quite imagine why.

name: Clown Trenchcoat
description: A colorful, energetic rubber slicker comfortably lined with short, ink stained fleece tentacles that feel up the wearer.

name: Anvilcano
description: This noble hammer is fabled to have been found in a great baking soda plain on a land in a session now devoid of players. Although it initially seems underpowered and pointless, large quantities of baking soda will awaken the hammer's latent power, and imbue it with destructive powers of flame.

name: Four-Sided Lipstick
description: Lipstick with four different colours. Granted, they're all still horrible shades that no self-respecting person would ever put on their lips, but at least you get a choice. Other than, of course, the option not to even use it.

name: Legend of Prospit: Model of Time
description: An awfully shoddy game that follows an up-and-coming model trying to find her way among multiple timelines.

name: iSuit
description: This sleek suit comes with Apple goodies aplenty. In built capacitive surfaces, and a5 processors give this suit incredible internet capability.

name: Thomas Jefferson Body Pillow
description: Sometimes you just want to snuggle up to an old, dead president. What a creep.

name: Long-Handled Brickhook
description: The corners on this thing are comparably sharp to the original tool, and can get the job done just as well, if not better. And by "job", you of course mean "killing imps".

name: Shadow Chainsaw
description: Them blades be runnin' around at the speed o- Oh wait. That's Sonic. Oh well. Still fast as hell.

name: Purple Die-on-a-Stick
description: A purple-ish d20 mounted on a long stick. Doesn't seem to have any cool properties, though.

name: Slamshocka
description: This purple sledgehammer's head has been replaced with an electrified basketball! Good thing the grip is rubber.

name: Crazy Bastard Sword
description: They said it was impossible. The odds were against you. But here it is! The coveted hand-and-a-half from the Sleazy Back Alley is yours.

name: Time Star
description: A shuriken made out of ruby gears, they all rotate together, keeping time perfectly. However, throwing the star causes time to speed up for you and your weapon.

name: Massive Nuclear Drill Gauntlets
description: Holy crud these things are heavy. The most you can hope to do with them is sort of flail your arms in the enemy's general direction and hope you hit something with the massive drill head on each hand.

name: Nuclear Drill Turbine
description: This marvel of modern science allows you to drill through just about anything. The main downside is that nobody thought to put wheels on the damn thing, so you have to push it around like a chump.

name: Captain Planet\'s Timey Wimey Breeze Conjuring Pedestal
description: Captain Planet and the Doctor were good friends, with this weapon being one of their collaborations.

name: Commemorative Aperture Science Man-Powered Portal Device Trophy
description: This shovel is probably less useful for digging since you had it mounted on a trophy stand, but it's still a great conversation piece.

name: Violin of Difficulty Overcome
description: It is said this violin is possessed of great sorcerous powers, embued with them by a mighty undead sorceror. According to legend, the instrument is made of the bone, horn, and gut of a Capra demon, and the bow of hair from the demon's pet hounds.

name: Sithpick
description: This pickaxe appears to have been corrupted by some anomalous evil. It's still perfectly good for hitting imps with, though!

name: Firebrand
description: This tremendous sword crackles with a roaring fire, searing enemies as it slashes them.

name: Big Hat
description: A large hat worn by a famously unsociable sorceror. It has no known magical properties, though it does have the ability to distance one from the masses around oneself.

name: Blackjack Shurikards
description: These blackjack cards have shuriken blades slicing out of their sides. An excellent deck for demonstrating the many ways to play poker!

name: Lead Phone
description: Every time you pick up the phone it is like a full workout! Although it's not a very practical for communicating.

name: Faygo - Blue Fairy Blood Berry
description: After drinking this Faygo you feel great, all your wounds are gone from fairy magic! But you have the urge to be really annoying for some reason.

name: Luck of the Draw
description: A bow that has the four suits along the front and fires different colored arrows randomly.

name: Cosplay Cat Ears
description: Of course, what feline cosplay ensemble would be complete without the iconic ears? The answer is none of them.

name: Nailcannon
description: Is there anything more fun than nailing imps to walls? Hint: The answer is no, there isn't.

name: Flaming Arm-Chucks
description: It has blades for fingers and fingers for blades and it's on fire. Why did you think this would be a good idea?!

name: Black Arms Sword
description: Created by the Black Arms, this weapon is the most common melee weapon used among its Army.

name: Dooming Bow
description: The arrows fired off this bow cast a curse on their aim.

name: Miracle Screen
description: An oddly-shaped computer with a pulsating, bubble-filled psychadelic screen. As if you didn't have enough incentive to stare at your computer screen for hours on end already!

name: Grim Glow
description: What more could you want than a florescent scythe that shoots rave lights? Be the death and rage of the party!

name: A Jab In The Dark
description: This spear is very shiny! It seems to be emitting light, even though it is not clear where it's coming from.

name: Backpowerpack
description: A comfortably portable double-shoulder-strapped power pack. Will need to be recharged eventually. Handy for storing things, surprisingly.

name: Wrenchchucks
description: Two wrenches connected by a chain, in case one breaks down from breaking bones.

name: Fiesta Mallets
description: Now you have the firey power of Fiesta Ace Dick infused with these mallets. It's hot, hot, hot!

name: Defender\'s Timetable
description: This shield bears a striking resemblance to the outside of a pocket watch. It has a clock within it, but the time it tells is inaccurate. Probably because you keep letting imps bash it.

name: Tri-Dimensional Coat
description: An ankle length black trench coat with tribal-like markings, red on the left half and blue on the right.

name: 3D Nunchucks
description: You know whats even better then regular old nun-chucks? How about nun-chucks in 3D, that will teach those imps who's boss. Now you can bash imps and you will have an excuse to wear 3D glasses all the time, oh yeah.

name: Peeperputer
description: Featuring hands-free computing and protection from all harmful rays! (Outside the goggles, inside, you're on your own.) Also provides extra defense against harmful UV rays.

name: Stupidly Long Piece of Chalk
description: This piece of chalk is not only unbearable to write or draw with, but it's useless in a combat situation as well!

name: Unabridged History of the British Empire
description: Or in other words, shipping for fun and profit.

name: Bunny Ears Headset
description: A headset with a pair of adorable bunny ears on top. Listen to sweet beats while looking like a cute bunny kid!

name: Slick Scarf
description: You marvel at the scarf's slick, smooth feel around your neck. You have a bit of trouble keeping it from slipping off.

name: Sushifucker
description: An excellent weapon for those foolish enough to prototype sushi or clothing.

name: Protocloak
description: This weird red cloak seems to be glowing with static. The cloak head appears to be made of black glass.

name: Creeper Bat
description: It's got that creeper skin going on, plus, it's got that extra POW in every hit!

name: Plasma Pummeler
description: This baseball bat now has a a field of supercharged plasma that flies off in balls when swung. Somehow it isn't searing your hands off.

name: Portrait of Server Dude
description: A rare instance of Server Dude Ben's face, in its full glory. No gask mask to obscure his visage, no beard to rival Ovaryseer's, and no upside-down smile to smite his innnocence.

name: Love
description: Strangely, it is not made with money, but grist! Very peculiar, but you do not feel like questioning the game about this. In the first place, how did an intangible object become tangible enough for you to captchalogue it? Is it even love? What is love?

name: Extended Apocalypse Slayer
description: A sickle said to belong to a famous death master recreated to be used as a scythe. Its extended handle makes it better used as a slayer of evil. Mostly apocalyptic evil.

name: Pillow of Soul
description: Imbued with the power of the aspects of Mind and Heart, this strange pillow seems to give you complete control over anyone who is creamed by its fluffy surface.

name: Nyx\'s Shadowspecs
description: This eerie pair of all-seeing glasses allows you to not only see everything go on in the Incipisphere, but also wipe anything from existence in the blink of an eye.

name: Indigo Chains of Fury
description: This weapon is for one serious fighter. You don't think you can handle how ironically awesome this is. It has a smaller blade on one end, and a large katana on the other. It is indigo and strong as reinforced cobalt.

name: Final Fantasy XIII
description: Wow, no money was wasted in the animations department for this game. You wonder what awesome new gear can be made from alchemizing it...

name: Hulk Hands
description: HULK SMASH!

name: Faygonight Dew: A Knife in the Pitch Dark
description: The darkest, edgiest soft drink you have ever laid eyes on. It doesn't say a world leader responsible for genocide did nothing wrong on the label, but the entire bottle is loaded with more knives than you can fill an orange gourd with. It's also rugosely caffeinated and tastes like grapes mixed with licorice.

name: Angeltop
description: This is stupid. Who wants a computer covered in feathers? It tickles when you type.

name: Propellor Breezie
description: Whrrr... Oh, sorry. You were just enjoying the kind of avian freedom a propeller that can actually fly provides.

name: Tempered Master Sword
description: After having the Master Sword be reforged by expert blacksmiths, you have managed to almost double its power. However, you have a feeling that its true potential has yet to be unlocked.

name: Kopaka Mata Figurine
description: This white-and-grey Bionicle figurine is the Toa Mata of Ice, Kopaka. He's a bit of an introvert, so to speak.

name: Moon Princess Gown
description: A shining, opalescent gown with strange shell-shaped sleeves that only cover the shoulders. It drags behind you and gets stepped on when you're standing in line, but never seems to get in the way for magic battles.

name: Journalbox w/ Detachable Speakers
description: A strange device used for having written words turned into sound to voice your opinions and arguments rather loudly.

name: Gali Mata Figurine
description: This is a blue Bionicle figurine from your childhood, Toa Mata Gali.

name: Lewa Mata Figurine
description: This is a Lewa Mata Bionicle, a green plastic figurine of Air from your childhood.

name: Blessed Rapier
description: Perfect for piercing the hearts of imps, vampires, demons, and other unholy enemies.

name: Quadrainbow Disperserator
description: The flames inside the lantern are surrounded by four sharp prisms. Demolish your foe with two double rainbows!

name: The Jaded Staff
description: This staff has a thin ring of jade around its head. You're pretty sure it can still shoot fire, but you're starting to feel a bit sleepy...

name: Crystalline Quarters
description: At the core of these diamond quarters lay pulsing centers of liquid gold. Pretty, but worthless as actual currency. They hum with some sort of divine power. You have a feeling they'll hurt anything stupid enough to stand in your way.

name: Yoshimac
description: A cute computer that features the egg-laying dinosaur from Mario, complete with a soft, plush coating that prevents damage when dropped. It has a Mac operating system with an exclusive Yoshi's Island interface.

name: Broom of Doom
description: This hand broom, while capable of 8^3 different magical attacks before, has been upgraded to use an ultimate death ray instead of bristles, capable of instantly vaporizing all but the toughest foes. You jump with joy before realizing that even with all its upgrades, this thing will probably do nothing against your denizen.

name: Demolition Spear
description: Sometimes you want to stab your enemies from a distance. Sometimes you want them to explode. Sometimes you want both.

name: Sonic Splitter
description: A clock-and-trumpet themed sword with the ability to warp time and play a note with every thrust. If you keep up a good rhythm, you can play a symphony by stabbing enemies!

name: The Generic D&D Campaign Ultimate Sword of Doom
description: This weapon could destroy the world if it fell into the wrong hands. No, seriously. You don't want this getting into the wrong hands. Still, you get the feeling that the world won't be destroyed because you're on the case. You always seem to survive these things. It's almost like you're a protagonist who will definitely get this sword and use it to become a benevolent god.

name: Explosive Science Sticks
description: The simpler way to heat up some Chinese takeout.

name: The Nuclear Tarot
description: A tarot deck. Though tarot has long been used to tell fortunes, this new method is 100% accurate! I see fire and radiation poisoning in your future. Luckily this thing has a lead box that fits nicely on your shoulder.

name: Zombietop
description: This thing is probably a useless piece of shit, not to mention that making it has caused you to feel an alarming sense of dread and satisfaction.

name: Santa Frost Doll
description: This one was pretty obvious. What did you expect combining Jack Frost and Santa?

name: Gateway Knife
description: This is how it starts... first you're stabbin' things with one of these and next thing you know, you're a full blown ninja...

name: STABS....
description: Showcase your shitty knives to any adversaries you meet.

name: Nuclear Nintendium Drill Turbine
description: As though all the previous engineering powerhouses weren't enough, this drill is reinforced with Nintendium, the toughest material known to man. The lack of wheels and the weight of Nintendium makes it even harder to move, though.

name: Nintendium Drillcube
description: A fist-sized cube made out of the sturdiest substance known to man, powered by nuclear fusion, and completely covered in tiny diamond drills which run constantly. Be careful where you throw this, because you might not see it again.

name: Wheeled Nuclear Drill Cart
description: All the reliability of a giant nuclear-powered drill, with less friction and more handbrake turns! Warning: brakes may not be as reliable as expected.

name: Massive Nuclear Inflatable Handrills
description: They don't pack as much of a punch as they would if they were made of metal, but if they were made of metal you wouldn't be able to move your hands anyways. This seems like a worthwhile compromise, especially since there's a woven lead sheet around the nuclear power core keeping you from being irradiated.

name: Echantillonneur
description: A narrow syringe of some tough, transparent material, reinforced by a system of joined metal rings which double as graduations. At one end, a sharpened hypodermic needle; at the other a padded hilt surrounding the plunger. Perfect for the gentleman scientist interested in both fencing and sampling (or injecting) his foes at once. Remember, good hygiene means replacing the needle after every use!

name: Prismatic Pickaxe
description: This pickaxe has a head which glows with every color of the rainbow.

name: Blighted Lightpick
description: This pickaxe has a head with glows with every known shade of red. Hey, at least all the blood won't stain it....

name: Hand-Held Nintendium Drillsun
description: This tiny sun is encased in an incredibly sturdy material which is absolutely coated in drills of every size. Caution is advised when using this, as it may leave third degree burns on your hand while throwing it.

name: Nuclear Nintendium Drill Cart
description: The absurd amount of inertia this thing tends to get combined with its incredible sturdiness means that you could probably mine out just as much rock by crashing into a mountain at full speed as you could by just drilling it out. Either way, it's an absolute barrel of fun.

name: Quantum CompuShades
description: With automatic targeting and weak point detecting software, these glasses are sure to aid you in battle. Now if you could just stop watching Spy Kids on it...

name: Massive Rocket Drill Punchers
description: The absurd amount of work it takes to lug these things around is made more than worthwhile by the sheer hilarity that ensues when you launch one of the gigantic drills into a series of unsuspecting enemies.

name: Empty Barrel
description: You may or may not have been planning to ride over Niagra Falls in this, but why do that when you can do something many many times more dangerous?

name: Statue of Uncle Crimbo
description: This small statue portrays Uncle Crimbo, who has taken over the gift-distributing duties from his brother, the late Father Crimbo. Every year, he and his elves provide gifts and adventure to the Kingdom of Loathing, and his sack is absolutely bulging in this rendition. It's not much of a weapon, but it's a statue of a stick figure, so it's pointier then your usual Santa.

name: Mask of Paternity
description: This golden mask bears the valiant visage of a father, all curly-haired consternation.

name: Prepare for Death Metal
description: Every twitch of these sticks draws forth a burst of dark, gorgeous symphonic death metal, fit only to accompany the most kick-ass occurrences ever, such as a dueling a giant wolf wielding a tremendous sword or fighting a spider-demon made of fire, hate, and lava.

name: Piece of Paper
description: A piece of eight-by-eleven-and-a-half letter paper, the kind you'd find in any printer. You suppose you can try to papercut imps with it, or fold it into new things.

name: Captain Planet\'s Undefeatable Timey Wimey Air Man-Powered Pedestal
description: You can't hope to defeat Air Man in a breeze conjuring contest. He is simply the best there is. Luckily for you, a miniature version of him now generates tornadoes for this pedestal.

name: Omnibus of Paranormal Paraphernalia
description: The conclusive compendium on powerful artifacts and illusive objects. There is no better source for determining the appropriate weapon in any situation of arcane foe. Not, of course, that all the secrets it holds are violent. But most of the fun ones are.

name: Sugar Cube
description: This is a single cube of sweet sugar... With your Alchemiter, you could make hundreds! ...probably not a good idea to eat them, though.

name: Uranium Power Cell
description: An extremely unstable, extremely tiny nuclear reactor. You should probably put this down before you poke it the wrong way and wipe out all life in a 1000-foot radius.

name: Balancing Nuke
description: This nuke embodies the power of the balance god himself, smiting all imperfect beings. Luckily as you only need to man the 1-button remote, it needs but one hand.

name: Unbalancing Nuke
description: This nuke is the polar opposite of it's similarly named companion, despite powered by a small controller, this nuke can destroy entire planets with ease.

name: Mask of Goldfinger
description: A mask of a prominent business man which also helps increase your ability to carry loads of gold.

name: Blorble Transparent Crystal Ball\'s Shiny Edition
description: This eerie crystal ball lights up each room with different colors depending on what future awaits you within that room. It glows an ominous bloody red, as if warning you of impending danger.

name: Celestial-Strength Crowsbow
description: A metal cast crossbow that shoots iron bolts, dipped in stardust.

name: Bargain Bin Fall Boots
description: Looks like something you might find in the half off basket. They should still work though, right?

name: Rainbow Cape
description: It looks fabulous, but isn't doesn't provide much protection...

name: "No Loafing" Sign
description: A sign with the words "No Loafing!" printed on it in red, you're not sure why it packs such a punch but you suddenly feel much more productive while holding it.

name: Dragon\'s Judgement
description: It looks exactly like the Judge's Gavel you just put in, but has a cute dragon's head for the head of the gavel.

name: The Most Advanced Pickaxe In All The Land
description: This pickaxe is both flashy, stylish, and advanced far beyond anything you've ever seen. Watch it carve out a fragile fractal pattern in one rock face, only to decimate an entire mountain afterwards, all without requiring input on your part.

name: Yellow Dragon\'s Phalanx
description: You're pretty sure that one shield does not a phalanx make, no matter how many bolts of electricity crackle across its dragon-clutching-a-lightning-bolt motif. It also needs a spear to qualify. But the Alchemiter doesn't care.

name: Unstable Rainbow Pickaxe
description: This pickaxe is made of rainbows, powered by rainbows, and will probably one day explode into a giant radioactive fireball of rainbows. Let's hope that doesn't happen while you're using it.

name: Unstable Hatepick
description: A pickaxe powered by the user's unending well of hatred with a side of uranium. Warning: If used improperly, may lead to side effects of perpetual hatred against all things living, dying in a massive nuclear fireball, or vomiting.

name: Sunlight\'s Circumference
description: This hoop is filled with concentrated sunlight, with the scythe-like spikes crafted to leave the searing substance exposed. If thrown the wrong way, a puncture wound is the least of your problems.

name: The Stylish Samurai
description: Not only was it crafted with the blood and tears of 1001 elite monks, it also looks pretty DAMN good!

name: Piece of Barbed Wire
description: A piece of barbed wire you found in your garage. It hurts you more then it hurts your enemies.

name: 40K Warhammer
description: A big hammer, with the words "fourty thousand" written across its length. Its style is almost reminiscent of something from the Warhammer 40K universe. Oh well.

name: Crystal 8-ball
description: Made specifically for the disruption of someone's privacy and the pleasure of the user .

name: Multifunctional Paintbrush
description: This is just an ordinary paintbrush, except for the fact that you don't have to deal with pesky paint palettes anymore, any color you could ever imagine is already programmed in.

name: Ahab\'s Sburban Crosshair Manual
description: Never judge a book by its cover, because when you open this book, it just shoots out a continuous stream of blue spirograph lasers.

name: Electric Scythetar
description: An electric guitar with the top replaced by the head of a scythe. Metal!

name: Fractal Fist-Sized Matter Perforator
description: If you look very, very closely at the surface of the drills covering this sphere, you'll find a series of tiny drills on the surface of each drill head. And then tinier drill heads on those drill heads, and so on and so forth. This is, of course, presuming that you can maintain a hold on this thing without it chewing through your hand.

name: Green Celestial Flare
description: Using the power of the Green Sun, as well as the constellations of the Gods who created the universe. If used right, it can end all life in existance. Sort of.

name: The Most Saccharine Pickaxe In All The Land
description: You're certain that if you started chewing on this delicious-looking pickaxe, you'd never be able to stop.

name: Thor\'s Headcleaner
description: An amazing piece of legendary craftsmanship, this sword also has the ability to shoot bolts of lightning... as long as you can wait days for the battery to recharge.

name: Cooking Mama
description: A quirky little game about... cooking! Who'd have thought?

name: Future Diary
description: Strangely enough, this black-bound book is filled with general information about your daily life. Before it's even happened.

name: 40KT Warhammer
description: An extremely heavy warhammer, styled after a certain popular tactics game.

name: Devastating Crafting Utensil of Mass Squiddlestruction
description: Wield the destructive power of these unholy scissors and prove to your enemies that liking Squiddles is no laughing matter.

name: Perfumegun
description: Instead of shooting water, his squirtgun shoots perfume. Wonderful. You hear perfume can really burn the eyes, though.

name: Hate to Chop and Run
description: Hate to... shit, wait. Hate to chop and... No, wait you were on to something. Fuck it. Hate to chop and cut all your heads off.

name: Probability Calculator
description: Calculates the probability of any given event occurring! May be disheartening to check the odds of beating Sburb.

name: Steampunk Tarot Deck
description: This deck holds the power of the Gods of the Machine and the clockwork majyyks they possess. Use them at your own demise, for metal does not bend so easily. (Wow, ominous much...)

name: Twin Cylinder Manual Choke Pickaxe
description: This thing gets 95 miles of your enemies intestines to the gallon. You could also break some rocks with it or something too, you guess.

name: Card of Mjolnir
description: A card depicting the legendary hammer Mjolnir. It is said this card has a thunderous power, and will always return to the owner if thrown.

name: Golden Frisbee
description: It's heavier than your normal Frisbee and much harder to throw. So you just hold it in your hand and hit imps with it that way.

name: Slightly Faster Frisbee
description: This Frisbee seems to naturally find air currents which allow it to glide for faster and longer than ever before.

name: Aperture Science Family Stress-Relieving Device
description: Yes, please, play with your family using this disc which glides on air currents. At no time should you all expect to be killed by deadly neurotoxin. Just ignore that large pipe overhead.

name: Drillsbee
description: A frisbee with drills around all the edges. It even has a little hopper that carries back whatever you mined with it, although it does have a tendency to get clogged with grist.

name: The Disc Annoyance
description: Not only does it kill imps, every time it does it takes a picture of the grist and shares it to every social media site known to man. It's a good thing Earth got crushed by meteors, otherwise you'd be annoying a lot of people right now.

name: Radioactive Drillsbee
description: Ever since your Drillsbee dug up some uranium, it's been acting kinda funny. Almost as though radiation exposure has damaged the electrical circuits..... Nah, it's fine.

name: Nuclear Drillsbee
description: Throwing a drill-covered disc powered by a barely-stable nuclear reactor at enemies is probably a great idea. You should probably just stand a long, long way away.

name: Aperture Science Reactor Monitoring Core
description: Even while he's in your sylladex, this core won't shut up about all the various safety mistakes you're making. All the time. Every day. He's more fussy than your grandmother, and it's starting to get on your nerves.

name: Aperture Science Nuclear-Powered Mineral Extraction Disc
description: The personality core in this drill-coated frisbee keeps yelling at you about how incredibly unsafe it is to throw such a dangerously radioactive frisbee around, but you stopped listening to him a long time ago.

name: Aperture Science Long-Range Decapitation Device
description: One of Aperture Science's more chilling inventions, this frisbee-launcher is capable of removing a man's head at 100 yards. Providing your aim is that good, of course.

name: Frifle
description: A rifle specially modifed to shoot frisbees.The barrel looks kind of like an ogre smashed it, and there's a hopper on the top too hold the discs. Like nerf.

name: Depleted Uranium Drillsbee
description: This drill-coated frisbee was once malfunctioning due to highly concentrated uranium in the drill bits. Now, that uranium has been depleted of (most) its radioactivity , leaving behind a hard shell - making the drills more effective than ever.

name: The Most Festive Pickaxe In All The Land
description: This pickaxe smites with all the force of Santa's 12 reindeer pulling at maximum speed. Now you, too, can smite your enemies with the power of Christmas Cheer!

name: Festive Frisbee
description: A frisbee covered in easily-shattered glass ornaments. It would be such a shame if one of them were to break on your opponent's face and gouge their eyes out. Such a shame.

name: Frisbee-Plastic Wreath
description: A wreath made up of cut-up Frisbees. Not only is this thing incredibly tacky, it's also dangerous. And it doesn't even have the customary hole in the middle!

name: Faygo - Festive Fantasia Flavor
description: It tastes like someone mixed eggnog and soda. And yet, somehow, you just can't stop drinking the stuff.

name: Solitary Holiday Rum
description: You've heard this is a very special type of liquor mixed with eggnog that makes you forget that you're all alone during the holidays. Maybe it'll help you forget that you played an important part in the extinction of your entire species.

name: Barrelfull of Water
description: It's a barrel full of water. This would be incredibly heavy if you didn't have a handy inventory system to lug everything around in.

name: Steam Wizards Alchemic Gloves
description: Combining a magic circle with the science behind an alchemy circle, engulf your enemies in a steam cloud hotter than fire itself.

name: Double Umbrella
description: Double umbrella, double fun! It's bad at protecting from the rain though.

name: Timetraveler\'s Pocketwatch
description: A red glowing pocketwatch with a constantly moving time aspect symbol carved on top. It actually creeps you out a bit, considering it's a metallic object and its carving is moving without any gears or complicated contraptions attached.

name: Acoustic Sun Guitar
description: A glowing guitar that gives off warmth and solar flares at enemies. A fresh new way to play fusion!

name: Ro-bo Yo-yo
description: The yo-yo seems to spark and make static sounds when spinning.

name: Google Maps Disc
description: A disc containing a program that lets you find the location of anything on Earth. Well, anything on what was once Earth.

name: Barrel of Blue Healing Sludge
description: Eugh. This is disgusting. You know that drinking it will heal most of your injuries, but the closest you're willing to come to that is sitting on the barrel and making a pouty face.

name: Barrel of Eggnog
description: You're not quite sure how you managed to get this much delicious eggnog all in one place, but you're pretty sure that you're going to drink it. All of it.

name: Barrel of Blue Eggnog
description: The eggnog is... blue? You're not quite sure how it got that way, but it's probably still delicious.... right?

name: Time Traveller\'s Truncheon
description: This truncheon sends whoever it strikes forward or backward in time. Of course, the wielder has no control over that, that would be too simple.

name: Hemera\'s Scarf-Shred
description: This golden, glowing shred of Hemera's scarf radiates the energy of all living things... Despite giving off a soft light, it isn't warm at all.

name: God Tier Thong
description: How in the world is a THONG so good at protecting you. IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE. Even if it is the colour of your aspect.

name: Rock Cannon
description: Oh man, this is gonna come in handy. Nothing like an over sized cannon of ultimate awesomeness to be beheld by the beholder which is the holder.

name: Dead Die
description: This die grants the power to raise the dead! Just don't expect the reanimated zombie to be very effective...

name: Smoldering Suit-Jacket of Identity
description: This slightly singed jacket now comes equipped with a Tron ID Disc for extra protection.

name: Nuclear-Powered Rocket Pack
description: Fortunately this Rocket Pack comes complete with a hatch for loading and unloading chunks of Uranium. Unfortunately the power source is unstable and the rocket has a tendency to blow up sometimes. Use with caution!

name: Ethernet Cable
description: This cable lets you connect to the internet via a port on the wall, but you have no idea if that even needs to happen now that you're stuck in the medium.

name: Four Suit Necklace
description: This deep purple chain comes with a set of four charms: red heart and diamond, black club and spade. Looks great, and strong enough to strangle an ogre.

name: Barrel of Radioactive Waste Water
description: Maybe drinking this will turn you into a superhero. Maybe it'll just give you radiation poisoning. There's only one way to find out.

name: Rainbow Rocket Pickaxe
description: This pickaxe adds extra force to each rainbow-empowered blow with the ring of nuclear rockets around the head. It's advised not to point either end of this at your head at any time due to the radioactive waste the rockets produce.

name: Rocket Hatepick
description: The more you hate whatever you're hitting, the faster the rockets launch the pickaxe forward. It's a useful mechanism, but highly unstable - if you hate something too much, the rockets will rip it right out of your hands and it'll go careening into the distance.

name: Bo Peep\'s Cane
description: This cane seems to have the magic power to round up weaker enemies. This will make them easy picking.

name: Solid Wind-Gold Suit of the Time Traveling Pimp
description: Travel through time with a wind forged golden pimp suit. You look as classy as can be while wearing this. Well... as classy as a pimp can look

name: Kiddie Table
description: This table is barely even suitable for a 2 year old, luckily plastic still works for hitting imp heads.

name: Deprecated Satellite
description: You have absolutely no idea where this came from, what it did back on Earth, or even how it's supposed to be powered. But that makes it all the better for combining with random weaponry, right?

name: Slimy Cloak
description: You're not really sure why you thought this was a good idea. Yuck.

name: Mobius Hoop
description: You start spinning it around your self, and you seemingly can't stop?!

name: Rotary Centrifwlch
description: An Arthurian Power Drill, if that makes any sense. You don't need to pull this out of a stone, you can just turn it on.

name: Sunsplitter
description: One of the most kickass light weapons, sure to: provide good reading light, keep the monsters away at night, and dismantle all opposition into gore dust from which they will never regenerate.

name: Holographic Santa Shooter
description: Whatever this thing shoots, it's bound to be stronger than the Stardust Rifle OH GOD ARE THOSE SANTAS.

name: Long Sharp-Hooked Crow Bar Staff
description: A very long, crowbar-like staff that possesses sharp, clawed hooks. Useful for opening just about anything from doors to imps.

name: Rebellion
description: A big ass sword said to awaken the more demonic side of it's wielder. You don't know about all that, but you DO know this is gonna be one hell of a party.

name: Sanguine Inevitability
description: A weapon with temporal powers wrought from crimson cogs, the two large cogs that make the axe's blade can tear foes apart with relative ease.

name: Iset
description: A hands-free iPhone that wraps around your head.

name: Loch-n-Load
description: Just like the Demoman, now you too can fire recklessly in a straight line! Has to be reloaded every two shots, but should pack a mean punch.

name: Door Opener
description: A gigantic, very sharp key on a handle. Multiple sticky out bits to hit things with.

name: Weak Tractor Beam
description: It can weakly grab things that weigh about as much as your average orange. So you won't be lifting cows into an alien spaceship any time soon, but it's still useful.

name: Overseer Staff
description: This scepter rapidly changes colors, and the nature of its attack changes depending on the color that it was in that instant. It's almost like this thing contains 20 different spirits, all bickering over who gets to embody the scepter. You shudder at the thought of the conversations that take place inside it.

name: Citric Truncheon
description: This truncheon is covered in delicious (and painful) citric acid.

name: Plastic Bag
description: This is a run-of-the-mill grocery bag. You guess you can... stick it over an imp's head and hope they suffocate?

name: Aperture Science Space Core
description: This core wants to go to space. And given how much he talks about it, it would seem there's nothing else he ever wants to do - and you're inclined to grant his wishes with a stern rocket-powered boot to his face.

name: Overpowered Tractor Beam
description: It works great, except for when you don't want things pulled towards you at ninety miles per hour. Then it's kinda crappy.

name: Inky Mop
description: This dingy thing seems to spread more mess than it cleans.

name: Aperture Science Prosecution Assisting Whip
description: This whip is actually a thermal discouragement beam that acts like a whip. Aperture claims it is best used by angry prosecutioners.

name: Archaeologist\'s Afro Whip
description: This whip is woven out of the finest afro hairs. And by "finest" you of course mean "oldest". Eww.

name: Ancient Thunderbolt Whip
description: With each crack of the whip, bolts of lightning arc toward your foe.

name: Calculation Die
description: When you roll this die, you initiate a complicated series of calculations. As it nears a target, it prepares to initiate a bit of an electric shock. The best part it, it's usually smart enough to avoid shocking you while running pesterchum.

name: PSI Whip the Defense
description: Cost: 20 PP. Causes the foe to reconsider his defensive argument.

name: Cyclic Fusion Whipping System
description: This gun fires a seemingly endless stream of plasma whips to pummel your foes.

name: Formal Walking Cane
description: This stylish cane may be used at any formal affair. Also leaves a big knot when hitting something over the head.

name: Majora-Possessed Captain Planet\'s Undefeatable Timey Wimey Air Man-Powered Pedestal
description: Is that the moon that you're controlling? Dropping the moon on enemies is awesome, but a humongous pain in the ass. You also start to feel unnerved around this weapon.

name: Temporal Frisbee
description: By combining a timeless toy with a timekeeping gear, you've created an abomination. Luckily, its constant turning motion makes it rather accurate and gyroscopically stable.

name: PSI Defense Whipstorm
description: Cost: 50 PP. Causes particularly stubborn foes to rue the day they became defense lawyers.

name: One Thousand Lashes
description: Forget learning how to whip! This whip simply has a trigger, pull it and release endless pain on your target.

name: PSI Whipstorm Omega
description: Cost: 20 PP. Causes endless whipcracks to rain down on your opponent.

name: Aperture Science Psioniic Rapid-Fire Whip
description: Aperture's newest innovation in whip technology allows for psychicly controlled discouragement beams to whip your foes at near light speed.

name: Kamen Rider Fourze Armor
description: You discover that you've had the ability to turn into a Kamen Rider all along...It's Space Time!

name: Chainsaw of Mystic
description: This seems more magical then your ordinary saw, somehow.

name: Flaming Needles of the Thunderclouds
description: Now you can start forest fires twice as fast!

name: Chain Lightning Whip
description: This whip is made lightning chains that jump from target to target.

name: Pearl Necklace
description: A swanky string of pearls like this must be pronounced "neck-liss" instead of "neck-lace".

name: Whip of Thorns
description: Thorns run down the side of the whip, and a rose sits in the handle for decoration.

name: Rocket Broomstick
description: You can blast opponents with sparks and fly above the treetops with this fire spitting baby.

name: Barrel Pants
description: It's a little less comfortable and a hella a lot breezier, but it'll protect you better than regular pants ever did. Mostly however it's simply better than being snarf naked.

name: Eastern Armor
description: A distinctive armor made in an Eastern land. Exquisitely crafted, this armor offers excellent defense, particularly against slashing weapons, which are one of the main threats in battles of the East.

name: Midnight Bow
description: The arrows seemed to be enveloped in dark energy, and the bow itself seems to be enchanted.

name: Tie-Dye Nebula Bedsheets
description: The pattern on this linen resembles a breathtaking image straight from the Hubble telescope. You think you could fashion it into a robe, or a tippet, a ferraiolo, or something outlandish nobody else has never heard of.

name: Magical 8-laser Compass Wand
description: A magical wand that not only shoots one laser 8ut 8!!!!!!!! Sadly, it does so in a circle........

name: Old Crone Broom
description: Not the prettiest thing anymore. You hope this thing doesn't come apart while you're using it.

name: Pointy Stardust Specs
description: All the "stars" inside the plastic lenses make it kindof hard to see, but damn are these pretty.

name: Stargazing Eyeglasses
description: Everything below the horizon looks blurry now, but to hell if these don't make the night sky 10000% clearer.

name: Cursed Skull Amulet
description: This seems to be an ivory pendant engraved with a shape vaguely resembling a human skull. It's said to radiate death and magic.

name: Apprentice Dragomancer\'s Cane
description: This Dragon themed Cane will strike fear into your enemies hearts, if only you knew what you were doing.

name: Looking For Group Comic Print
description: Now you can read the adventures of Cale A'non and Richard(but mostly Richard) offline!

name: Chained Wand Blades
description: Whether you're an enthusiast of the mystic arts, or just a moron who loves shiny things, either way you just seriously need something that can perform magic beams and is pointy as fuck.

name: Capital Wasteland Compendium
description: This compendium is crammed full of history about the Fallout universe. The fictional one, to be more precise. You don't doubt that there is literally a universe that underwent an interstellar nuclear war.

name: Revolving Carbine
description: Like a rifle, but more efficient, its revolving chamber allows for quicker reloads and more shots between reloading. Also, it looks pretty neat too.

name: Keyrapier
description: A rapier with teeth on the end like a key. While this makes it look pretty cool, it's actually now useless as a stabbing weapon.

name: PSI Whipshock Beta
description: Cost: 75 PP. Causes major neural damage with a swift whip to the face, ending any argument they may have had with you.

name: Astro Lamp Oracle
description: A rounded lava lamp that predicts the future, with the state-of-the-art ambiguity the 70s is known for. Watch it for hours as it changes color and shape.

name: Winged Tricksterang
description: A feathery flyer that leaves golden sparkles trailing as it flies. It seems to also direct itself towards your target, which is nice.

name: Magnetite Boomerang
description: Mostly just a heavy boomerang. It could seriously mess up electronics, but you doubt the robot apocalypse will be any time soon.

name: Sonic Generations
description: From Classic to Modern, this Sonic game reminds you of how beautiful the series is.

name: Faygo - Gargling Grapey Grief
description: A refreshing taste of grape, pure sugar, and a hint of unfulfilled desires and shattered dreams. If you listen closely the carbonation sounds like sighing as it pops.

name: Cairo Bedsheet
description: You have a feeling you're a little safer under this over-sized sheet. Safer from a certain everyone. Wear it like a big rumply robe.

name: Big O Witching Hat
description: This ragged thing! It's brim flops over the back of your neck and the pointed end droops down to the narrow of your back. You hope it packs enough fire power to make up for covering your eyes half the time.

name: Flame Darts
description: Small darts with fire on their peaks. Powerful enough.

name: Blorble Transparent Crystal Ball
description: This lava orb predicts futures through the colours of the lava inside. For most things you'll encounter, the future it will predict will be a painful death.

name: Miraculous Holo-Projector
description: A powerful projector with computronic features that turns any image it captures into a holographic projection that can be easily manipulated with its features. Occasionally, it glitches and a rugby player on a horse will show up for some fucked up reason. When you don't tinker it enough, it starts to make random giant bubbles, so be sure to turn it off when you don't need it!

name: Dead Pilot Summoner
description: A weird wand, its appearance resembles that of a bony finger with a somehow see-through, metallic handle. You start waving it around a bit, but nothing happens; yet the moment you point at a grave, a corpse immediately shoots out of the ground to the sky and beyond.

name: Broken Broom-Wands of Asteria
description: This was once a legendary brush, said to have been enchanted by a great Queen so that she may sweep the night away and bring dawn every morn. Now it's broken in two. You suppose you could take a half in each hand and wield these things like a kickass set of wands.

name: Grand Thong of Darkwraith Kirk
description: This blood-dripping thong is said to have belonged to the infamous Darkwraith, Thorn Knight Kirk. It glows with the malevolent crimson aura of the Darkwraith Covenant's members.

name: Dirge of the Darkwraith
description: This ominous looking harp of glowing crimson and black shrieks forth songs to herald an Age's End.

name: Cosmic Cape of the Spiral Sea
description: This cape is overflowing with the unstoppable might of spiral energy.

name: Spiral-Steel Shades of Cosmic Thorns
description: Who the hell do you think these shades are?

name: Skull Candy Cane
description: It seems that evil has a sweet tooth and with this candy themed skull cane you'll be the height of villainous debauchery.

name: Bombchucks
description: These nunchucks cause explosions. Hitting yourself on accident has never more painful.

name: BIBBL......
description: If you go to whatever church reads this book of crudely-drawn comics, you probably won't be chastised for praying incorrectly.

name: Surgeon\'s best friend
description: A tad dull, but with a strong grip for precision. Just what the doctor ordered.

name: Acoustic Hacker
description: Great for kicking axe and rocking out!

name: 5-Digit Split
description: A ridiculously heavy bowling ball with various blades sticking out of it in every angle possible. The only way to get a spare with this thing is to not use it.

name: The Ultimate Life-Fork
description: The epitome of fork-kind. Wait, what?

name: Game Bow
description: This high tech bow can shoot arrows without any ammo at all. Beware of glitches!

name: Really Fast Frisbee
description: This aerodynamically efficient frisbee now generates its own wind currents to fly on and hit your enemies in the noggin with severe concussive force.

name: Camerang
description: Tired of photographic projectiles that don't come back with your picture? Well, here's a solution for your strangely specific problem!

name: Timekeeper\'s Boltgun
description: A large, powerful rifle adorned with bronze gears fastened to an ornate, large, brass barrel covered in roman numerals. The bullets accelerate to their targets but slow down upon exiting, leaving devastating wounds.

name: The Golden Throne of Mankind
description: The throne in which the God-Emperor of Mankind sits, extending and preserving his life. WARNING: God-Emperor of Mankind comes separately.

name: Crook of Frailty
description: In the hands of a great leader, or an occultist necromancer, a twirl of this staff could prod the spirits of the dead from the very air, raising an undead army to turn the tides of your failing session. You are neither of these things. A wooden stick is a wooden stick though, so whack something with it and maybe majyyk will happen.

name: Trauer
description: An axe wrought from silver and solidified anguish. Best not to dwell on how one would solidify anguish. You might lose your head!

name: Generic Postal Stamp
description: A generic postal stamp, used for sending mail.

name: Postal Drill
description: This drill is covered in so many stamps you could probably send it wherever you wanted.

name: Golden Stamp
description: A stamp made out of pure gold. You probably shouldn't use them to send postage, since that would probably give your mailman a heart attack (presuming he isn't already dead).

name: The Peacemaker
description: Something to help resolve your more heated discussions.

name: Patriotic Stamp
description: A stamp which, despite only being about one square inch, manages to depict an American flag, a crying eagle, the Statue of Liberty, and a photo of Mount Rushmore in great detail.

name: Sharp Postal Stamp / 3 of Diamonds
description: A postal stamp with really, really sharp edges. You'd rather not try to lick the back of this one, thanks.

name: Festive Prankster Crate
description: This team fortre... I mean strange unknown crate can only be opened by a key. Looks like you need a festive key...

name: Stamp-Headed Shovel
description: A shovel with a stamp where there would normally be a metal head. Well ain't that just incredibly useless.

name: Faygo - Double Rainbow Flavour
description: This miraculous new flavor will have you seeing miracles in no time. :o)

name: Liquid Pie in a Bottle
description: For the on-the-go adventurer who doesn't have the time to sit down and eat pie. Now it's more compact and easier to consume!

name: 70s Necklace
description: A simple twine necklace featuring a daisy shaped bead. Awwe.

name: Barrel of Blueberry Pies
description: A barrel full of delicious blueberry pies. You could also call it "a stomachache waiting to happen".

name: Empty Pie-Crust Barrel
description: A very large barrel-shaped empty pie crust. Now you just need a couple dozen gallons of filling and an oven the size of your living room.

name: Unearthly Black Bedsheets
description: To fashion this into a hooded cloak might make you feel like a great wizard's apprentice. If you were three.

name: Example Stamp
description: This large wooden stamping device was stolen from an English teacher a long time ago, and has since been passed down through your family as an extremely strange heirloom. It stamps the word "EXAMPLE" onto things - you have no idea why anyone would ever need this, except to hit imps with..

name: Example Stamp with Blue Ink
description: Now you can stamp the word EXAMPLE into things in blue ink! You're still not entirely sure why that's a good thing, but it is a thing you can do!

name: Example Stamp with Blue Ectoacid Ink
description: Now you can turn enemies into an example of your wrath by stamping EXAMPLE into their foreheads and watching them writhe as the word burns itself there.

name: Fire & Ice Rayalibur
description: This sword has the ability to shoot both hot lava and freezing ice.

name: Magmaflurries
description: These gloves are both flaming and freezing at the same time. These babies can do any thing from creating magma storms to making a volcano erupt snow. they are truly the ultimate glovekind weapon!

name: Divine Lance - "Spear the Gungnir"
description: A powerful spellcard, capable of firing piercing blasts of energy at your foes. When you wield it in battle, thoughts of seven-person music groups and deceased royalty cross your mind for no apparent reason.

name: Card Suit Bed Sheets
description: These are just bed sheets spotted with cardy symbols, they're no big flipping deal. But damn do they look cool.

name: Blue Sky Bedsheets
description: A blue blanket covered in a patter of white clouds with a big white sun. This isn't very mysterious looking but just seeing it makes you feel cheerful and awake.

name: Cross Amulet
description: An elaborately embellished cross pendant.

name: Reploid Armor
description: With the head and the armor parts, you're only two away from the full suit!

name: Magic 8 Portal Wand
description: Ever wanted a wand that has the ability to shoot not one, not two, but EIGHT different portals at one time? If so, then this is the item for you! The portals aren't really that helpful when strifing but the SHARPNESS level of this wand is over 8000!!

name: 90s Necklace
description: A string of pearls featuring a huge, painted, wooden rose-shaped bead. You'd feel pretty classy and independent wearing this.

name: Barrelful of Coins
description: A barrel full of a wide variety of coins. You can pull individual coins out of it and hit your enemies with those, or just roll the thing into a mob of enemies.

name: Coinspewer
description: Light this firework and run, because pretty soon coins will be embedded everywhere. It works best in clusters of enemies, although getting them to hold still long enough for it to blow up is a problem.

name: Singing Angel\'s Talons
description: These fine claws cut through flesh cleanly and without immediate pain, but they leave a delayed searing sting.

name: Aperture Science Portable Throwing Devices
description: Shuriken that will open a Portal when they do not hit your enemy. Throwing two of them in the right position may cause some confusion.

name: Felt Nunchuck
description: This soft green nunchuck may actually prove useful since it can freeze the enemy in time. But since it is so soft, you are distracted by how strokeable it is.

name: Chainlink Armor
description: Instead of being made of interlocked circles, it's made of woven chains! How bizarre...but still effective!

name: Rules of Timetravel / TARDIS Key
description: Finally something that explains the inner workings of timelines in words that a temporally-challenged being can easily grasp. You think everyone involved in time-shenanigans should have access to this helpful little item.

name: Cinder Lord\'s Inferno Storm Shield
description: You don't remember Gwyn having a shield. If he did, you don't think it would be made of dragon scales. Little things like that don't matter when you have a black, visibly electric shield that is also on fire though.

name: Oktavia\'s Bewitched Sword
description: A sword that belonged to blue Madoka who now became bad witch blue Madoka. It has an aura of loneliness that can only be broken with the love of red Madoka.

name: Symbol of Divine Protection
description: When you put this symbol around your neck, you feel a warm and protecting presence. The stress from all these past days seems to cause some minor halucinations, you might wanna get that checked out.

name: Shitty Barbed Wire Blade
description: Delivered from the fires of hell, this magnificent blade has been boiled in broken dreams and drunken tears, forged in the mighty wood shop that never was...it's just your shitty sword with a piece of barbed wire wrapped around its blade. Why did you even need to alchemize this?

name: Whip Scythe
