description: A long, segmented whip with a curved blade at the end. You're not sure if it's a scythe or a whip, but does it matter if it kills the imps?

name: Omnidunk Crasher
description: The basketball on the end of this long-handled hammer crackles with dark electricity. With it, you can perform the slamminest of dunks from anywhere on the court, creating an explosion of thunder and darkness at the point of impact. It's still only worth 2 points though.

name: Silverlight Sickle Scratcher
description: The light that emanates from this prism is silvery and very shiny, forming the shape of a long blade that is hooked at the end. It also sears anything it touches. Your foes won't see it coming, mostly because they'll be blinded long before they're branded.

name: Halloween Trick-or-Treating Bag
description: A Halloween-themed canvas bag that reminds you of your childhood: dressing up as lame monsters to get bad-tasting candy. It's good to know that you've moved on to better things...dressing up as lame anime characters to get bad-tasting grist.

name: Makeup Bag
description: Not only can it hold your other beauty weapons, but it doubles as a weapon also!

name: Example Stamp with New Intimidating Features
description: Every time you fight an enemy with this stamp, it automatically takes a picture of the enemy so that you can make a montage of everything you've ever made an example of (that is to say, killed with a stamp.).

name: Example Stamp with New Embarrassing Features
description: Now for every enemy you fight with this stamp, it'll take a picture and post it to the internet, saying "[NAME] has made an example of [ENEMY_TYPE]!" It's a fun gimmick, but it gets old fast - especially when you start getting messages from everyone else to please cut that shit out.

name: Rabbitslayer
description: The magicks bound within this blade insure that its owner never goes without a weapon. Probably useless for anything other than killing rabbits though...

name: Strong Bad\'s Cool Staff for Attractive People
description: Watch out for: "Strong Staffia, the free", "Dangeresque 3, the Criminal Projectile" and "The Staffest of the Bands"

name: Creationist\'s Pen
description: This pen can summon just about anything by writing out its name. Sure, it'll be barely tangible and all doodly, but that doesn't make it any less awesome!

name: Red Slash of Death
description: This massive, demonic backscratcher pulses with a spine-chilling red glow, the likes of which would send many a gamer into a panicky rage. When you're up against this beast, you are beyond help.

name: Puzzle Breaker
description: When you can reach between dimensions and retrieve cubes from anywhere and anywhen you please, you can make just about any platforming puzzle your bitch.

name: Butterfly Swords
description: Dual wielded swords meant for close contact strifing. Their beautiful craft work is enough to bring a tear to your eye.

name: Swiss Army Axe
description: A brilliant feat of Swiss engineering for chopping wood while opening a bottle of celebratory champagne, filing your nails, and screwing in a couple of bolts.

name: One Winged Cosplay
description: Just like the feathery wings of the Cosplay Wings, but now with only one! You're not sure how practical this is, but at least you look cool wearing it.

name: Ace of Wands
description: The Ace of Wands is a sign of inspiration, a sign of a new Beginning. It encourages you to "go for it" It also turns into a really powerful wand. I probably should have said that earlier...

name: Candy Corn Mace
description: This delicious weapon is both useful as a halloween treat and a useful weapon against imps.

name: Santa\'s Keycane
description: This seems to be unusable as a normal walking cane, leave alone opening doors. Pretty good at whacking enemies though.

name: HOUR-HAND SHOOTING GUN-THING
description: It shoots hour-hands. Also it's a gun-thing.

name: Remote Door-Opener
description: With this beauty you can open any door from a considerable distance, being able to repeatedly shoot keys at the lock. The door opens even if you miss the lock though. Also works if the door has no lock. Also works if there's no door.

name: Dad\'s Journal
description: Dad's on a hunting trip, and he hasn't been home in a few days. He even left his journal behind, full of all his information on monsters and their weaknesses. Looks like it's time for a road trip.

name: Eternity\'s Gatekeeper
description: This shotgun has resemblance to an oversized Key and is constantly ticking and whirring. You can blast enemies into next week with this, literally.

name: Dice of the Bearded Dungeon Master
description: A copper coin, shiny with constant use and flipping, with scraps of paper labeled "1" and "20" taped to the sides.

name: Power Ring
description: While you hold on to this, you feel as if you are invincible, but you need to remember to hang onto it!

name: Green Coin of Starry Omniscience
description: Laying your hands on this coin gives you an absolutely massive migraine as you take in a significant piece of all the knowledge in the multiverse. It also seems to have the same effect on your enemies, and they don't take the headaches nearly as well...

name: Diamond-Cored Coin
description: A small gold coin with a massive, shiny diamond mounted in the center.

name: Bismuth Bilaterals
description: A handful of enchanted bismuth coins that give a variety of different effects when flipped en masse. You can't tell which sides are supposed to give good effects, though.

name: Prismatic Coin
description: A coin that bends light into a small rainbow. Cute, but not really all that useful.

name: The Blasphemous Bullets of Bad Faith
description: You thought you had it all figured out didn't you? Well guess what. You didn't. Oh, and you're dead now too.

name: Electromagic Key
description: It's a Key wrapped in magic yarn. It's pretty magical.

name: Slender Orphan\'s Knife
description: This pale dagger seems unnatural. It makes no noise no matter what you hit it against and it hurts to look directly at it. And, come to think reflect on it, it never feels hot or cold. It's always the exact same temperature as your hands. 'Great for shanking though.

name: Chansy Conductor Baton of Danny Elfman
description: This musical wand radiates sensations of nostalgia, oddity, and sugar headaches. A normal person would pretend they didn't like it.

name: Nerf Gatling Crackshot
description: Works as either a lightweight plastic long-range machine gun or as the most epic nerf gun ever. Careful kids, might accidentally become a homicidal maniac! Better hide those video games.

name: Green Slime Ghost Bedsheet
description: This blanket is covered in... ghosty things? Tenta-whales? You aren't quite sure what those ecto-tadpoles are.

name: Rifle Arm
description: A simple combination that has the likeness of a diver's bang stick. When striking an opponent with the rifle arm, it shoots out a bullet from the glove.

name: The Fanciest Goddamn Santa
description: The supreme fancy Santa. Bejeweled and decked out with a massive codpiece, you're pretty sure that getting any fancier is pretty much impossible.

name: Claw of the Time Stream
description: An enemy defeated with this weapon will be sent back to a random point in their past, where they will undoubtedly encounter themselves and cause a paradox, locking them in a doomed timeline. It still leaves the grist drops, thankfully.

name: Broom-Wand of the Lich Queen
description: A once broken tool is now miraculously mended, and it most certainly did not need to consume the soul of a dark being to become so, right? Anyway this long, eloquent wand is a bit of a hassle to manage, but works just fine if you use the other arm as a counterbalance.

name: The Seventh Keyblade of Hammer Time
description: Ain't nobody can try to touch you when you're swinging this deadly ass key hammer around.

name: Ringmaster\'s Coat
description: A royal red blazer vest with thick yellow trim, large black buttons, and outrageously fashionable coat tails. Prefect for yelling at lions and not actually fighting them.

name: Homestuck Poetry
description: Your eyes are an ocean. Your breasts, are also an ocean.

name: Crumplehat
description: You've dishonored your ancestors a million times over by even looking at this frivolous head accessory, but damn does that look fashionable.

name: Rumpled Hat
description: The rumpled look is on the rage. Just make sure not to unsit on it or your look will be ruined.

name: Octuple Hydra-Fanged Devil Chains
description: Two Octuple Anvil-Fanged Devil Slammers connected by a chain of Hyrda-electric chain serpents. Not only is this thing ridiculously dangerous to use, you're pretty sure using this at all is a war crime.

name: Majora-Possessed Captain Planet\'s Portal Generating Timey Wimey Air-Man Powered Pedestal
description: The bad news? The portals only work on certain surfaces, the surface of the moon included. Also, you're having trouble reciting the name to your own weapon. The good news? The moon is under your control.

name: Hurricane Summoner
description: A pretty normal wand with the same appearance as its cousin, the Wind Waker, but sharper. This mystical item supposedly has the power to summon wind powerful enough to push a mountain into space at the speed of a bullet, so be careful where you point it.

name: Purse
description: Cliche as it is, this thing is actually capable of inflicting some respectable damage when slung around.

name: Fuzzy Bunny Purse
description: A super-soft brown bag with adorable bunny ears. This purse is probably not the most useful at beating enemies because it is so darn fuzzy! However, you can't resist its cuteness!

name: Hitchhiker\'s Rabbit-Skin Bag
description: This bag looks like a caveman killed a rabbit, took the skin off, and crudely sewed it into a pouch. Still, it's useful for keeping things in. Inside is a collection of gray stones and a pink towel - wait, you could've sworn that the towel was blue a second ago.

name: Radical Fashion Statement
description: For the not-so-precise modifications to clothing. It's recommended not to use these chain-shears on clothing that is currently being worn.

name: Heavy-Duty Bowl Cutters
description: Mostly for cutting long, thick locks, but with the size of these things you could probably manage to cut actual bowls...

name: Lemony Snippet
description: Some might say only fruits are interested in sewing... Well, now they're right.

name: Groom and Dye
description: The black ink on the end of these shears dyes the tip of your hair black as you cut! A convenient way for a quick, fashionable style.

name: Adept Dragomancer\'s Resurrection Cane
description: Now you can resurrect the dead - well, dead dragons, that is. Even the most seasoned veteran will tremble before your undead army. Unfortunately, finding your future subordinates is easier said than done.

name: Revenge of the Ninja Biker
description: So much hatred and rebellion went into the making of this sign that even describing what's on it would leave an entire highway's worth of commuters offended beyond sanity, as well as bring a world of shame to their ancestors.

name: Robot Link Cable
description: Seems to be a link cable for connecting two toy robots together. You have no idea what this could possibly go to, nor what purpose it might serve.

name: No Raving Sign
description: You think this might have been used by policemen in the 60's and 70's to quell some unruly crowds. Psychadelic raves were common in that era... right?

name: Netskater Extreme
description: A black cord with red flame patterns across its entire length, guaranteed to make "skating" the net 500% faster. Radical!

name: Life Diminisher
description: A length of barbed wire curled into the shape of a life preserver. If you get thrown one of these, you're probably better off drowning.

name: Barbed-Ass Mother Pucker
description: An absurd amount of barbed wire wrapped around what was probably once a hockey stick. The only thing this sport was missing was a faster way for its players to beat each other into a bloody pulp...

name: The Ringmaster
description: Somewhere, behind the smiles and spectacles, lies a muffled yet desperate cry for help.

name: Buzzing Fork
description: When stricken, this fork makes a loud buzzing sound much like a bumblebee. You can't help but flinch sometimes, even when you use it to whack an imp.

name: Space Fork
description: It's a space fork, the exact kind of fork used by astronauts in space! It's really not all that different from an ordinary fork, and also you're pretty sure astronaut food can't be eaten with one, but still... space fork!

name: Three-Pronged Key
description: This seems useful for unlocking 3 locks that are close together in a line. It will surely come in handy.

name: Hard-Boiled Fork
description: This fork seems exceptionally hard-boiled. You could probably use it to eat a hard-boiled egg or something.

name: Old Timey Bolterbuss
description: All the impact of 42nd century technology packed into a 16th century blunderbuss. The trigger is also shaped like a small gear. How quaint!

name: Dr. Banner\'s Keyring
description: These green oversized gloves have keys sticking out of them, which makes them prefect for opening those frustratingly tough chests.

name: Eternal Wait 2: Electric Boogaloo
description: This key-themed boomerang sure takes it sweet time returning to you.

name: Spooky Lemon Pogo
description: A lemon-shaped pogo toy for youthful enjoyment, surrounded with a creepy ethereal green glow. Aside from its novelty, it appears quite useless.

name: Snake Wine
description: An alcoholic beverage produced by placing the whole bodies of snakes in otherwise run-of-the-mill and non-threatening bottles of alcohol-based liquid.

name: Vintage Final Fantasy Yo-yo
description: Damn these things used to be cool, then they were $130 on eBay but essentially useless. Now that your home planet and civilization is gone, you're left with nothing but the novelty.

name: Fallout Semaphore Shank
description: It's that thing off a mail box, the flag doohickey. You guess this was pulled out of the rubble of some post-war shit? Whateves. It's been sharpened to a point and is still moderately radioactive.

name: The Call of English/Green Sun Railgun
description: This book contains the stories of a time-travelling cherub's adventures with a clown, which are surprisingly entertaining. In addition, when the fifth word on the copyright page is read, it turns into a railgun. Neat.

name: Jack\'s Key to Christmasland
description: A keyblade that is the perfect combination of Halloween and Christmas. You really have to hand it to Tim Burton and Square Enix.

name: Roentgenium Brick
description: As you hold this brick of the 111th element, you feel as if you've unlocked a large ammount of magical potential. Or it might be the radiation poisoning kicking in.

name: Defense Against the Dark Arts
description: You may or may not have alchemized this just for the pun, but it turned out to be a fairly useful and powerful magic paintbrush/shield duo. Wield your pun with pride!

name: Tektroxkeyliburn
description: It's a powerful writing key of legend. Why have you never heard of this?

name: Black Flaming Scorchpen
description: This pen singes across the page by writing with gasoline ink. Can also be used to stab your enemies, effectively injecting them with gasoline. It might not be actual fire, but it'll still burn!

name: Stone Cold Keyaxe
description: Looks like you made your Keyaxe dark grey. And indestructible.

name: Hephaestus\'s Hot\'n\'Heavy Handshake
description: This gun is covered in ticking Hour-Hands, and fires timestopping keybullets. It glows red and you seem to hear faint sounds of a heavy hammer repeatedly hitting an anvil.

name: comPOOTer
description: Great, you just managed to create a horrible piece of shit that crashes all the time and barely has any memory. At least you can still run SBURB on it...

name: Color Pan
description: Quite useful to make either the food in your kitchen or the bumps on your enemies' heads more colorful. Paint not needed.

name: Pan Opener
description: So it's a can opener... and a pan. It hardly does either! What were you thinking?!?

name: Lime Knuckles
description: Not much different than brass knuckles, but at least your enemies will taste the delicious citrus of lime before the inevitable blood.

name: Obnoxious Radio
description: A checkered radio with no off-switch and apparently no power source. A bothersome voices speaks quickly about nonsensical race chatter without pausing for a breath. Why did you make this distressful thing?!

name: Epoch Scythe
description: A large, barely-wieldable black scythe with golden engravings of clocks on the blade. Each slash of the scythe seems to ripple time itself, hitting everywhen wherever you strike.

name: Homing Chakram
description: Your old bladed hoop now homes in on targets. No more accidentally missing your foe and hitting your friend!

name: Color Spword
description: A deadly weapon that could bludgeon heads with the flat base of pan and slice your enemies in half with it's sharp circular edges. All the while, brilliant bright colors mix with the blood, making the battle seem more of a work of art.

name: Dangan Ronpa: Hope\'s Peak Academy and High School Students of Despair disc
description: It seems to be a murder mystery video game in which a bear forces teens to kill each other to escape the fate of being trapped. Sounds kinda weird to you, and it only plays in Japanese.

name: Miraculous Holo-Projector: Genius Strategy Edition
description: This marvel of post-modern science creates entities out of hard-light of varying capabilities and power that you can order around the battlefield. It's kind of like playing a giant game of chess, except instead of putting your opponents in check, you just ram your pieces into them.

name: Business Ninja Attire
description: When your modern ninja needs to go to work, what else to wear but the uniform of a Business Ninja? Now even better at sneaky tricks!

name: Thong of Skaia
description: You strut with renewed vigor and pride while wearing this glorious thong. It conveys all the beauty and majesty of Skaia, with absolutely no exceptions.

name: Mirthful Messiah\'s Why So Serious Voodoo CommDaggers
description: These dark daggers emit a powerful aura. Their darkness snakes its way into your mind, echoing voices through your consciousness... Some of them are your co-players, but others seem... darker...

name: Currency of the Dark
description: Legend has it these coins are either made of souls, concentrated evil, or some form of captured demon. Whichever it is, they're still extremely powerful.

name: Piss Stained Wings of the Holy Avenger
description: You thought it was Apple Juice, but sometimes mistakes happen... These once wicked blades have been infused with the essence of the Holy Juice that was once contained in the Apple Juice bottle as well as the unholy liquid currently contained, making them (almost) Holy.

name: Farmer\'s Market Drunken Negoti-Nego-Negotiatiatorses
description: O-o-okay. So, um, mayb.. *hic* maybe adding alcohol ishtn't uhhhhh always... a, uh, a gud... uh good idea. Yeah... I don't think I can, uhh, go back to the, ummm, Farmier's, errr, Ffffaaarmer's Market any-any- *hic* anymore... yes.

name: Triple Knifinale
description: Thrusting with this knife causes three blades to emerge from three separate portals to stab your foe, potentially inserting itself into multiple vital points where it will then fire multiple rounds into said victim.

name: Aperture Science Quantum Luck-8r8king Space Bow
description: Behold, the pinnacle of Aperture Science technology. It's capable of firing arrows tipped with the result of every possible roll of some very powerful dice over incredibly vast distances thanks to gravity manipulation and the occasional lemon catching fire, while still maintaining the extreme reality-bending and questionable side effects that you'd expect from an Aperture product.

name: The Core of the Crosshairs
description: Not many people know this, but the power of the legendary Ahab's Crosshairs is actually taken from one source - a small crystal coin, chemically enhanced to provide absolutely silly amounts of power and still be removable in case straits ever became so dire that it needed to be spent. This is that coin.

name: Ragged Hatsune Miku Plushie
description: A ragged plush of internet diva Miku Hatsune. It's very cute, although it looks like it's been through a wood chipper.

name: Omnisexual Gunblade of Gender Identity
description: A diamond bladed Jackknife Gunblade. The handle is wrapped in black studded leather. No matter how you identify, this weapon will suit you just fine.

name: Gold Marbles
description: A bag full of marbles that are made of pure gold.

name: Ecto-blue Blur Potion
description: Loaded with some kind of uncontrollable energy, one cant help but want to go fast after drinking this.

name: Faygo - Toxic Intoxication Flavor
description: Finally, a way to get drunk less classy than boxed wine. It nearly doubles the miracles, though.

name: Lemony Cutlass of Yellow Light
description: Man, is this thing shiny. The yellow light given off by this thingy almost tastes like lemons!

name: Plasma Pistol
description: Rain down thermocuclear powered plasma bullets at your enemies.

name: Extenda-lance
description: Have you ever wanted to stab something far away? This might help!

name: Life-Sized Pencil-Cage
description: It's a life-sized Nic Cage, dressed as a pencil. How are you even able to use this against your enemies?

name: Sweet Bro and Hella Jeff: The ArePeeGee
description: iTS LIKE SWEET BRO AND HULLA JEFF THE MOVEY THE DRAGEN THEN GAME GET YOURS NOW

name: Revolution\'s Edict
description: You excel at turning phrases and your razor sharp wit can rally the masses. Its time to start a riot.

name: Pratchett\'s Problematic Beheader
description: This is a short, relatively heavy knife, made from two differing worlds, one of Insanity and Discord and the other one is Silent Hill... Despite its size, it seems to be relatively good at severing heads.

name: Ripper\'s Head-acopter
description: By attaching the blades to the helmet, you have achieved flight! No, I don't know how you did it... You're the genius with all the bright ideas...

name: Faygo - Heavy Golden Flavour
description: It's a very heavy bottle of golden faygo. You aren't quite sure what exactly's in it, but it is certainly dense.

name: Barrel - Heavy Golden Flavour
description: A heavy golden barrel that tastes like soda. This is... actually kinda gross.

name: Barrel of Heavy Golden Faygo
description: An entire barrel full of an incredibly dense form of soda. You don't think you could drink it all in one sitting, but yet... it calls...

name: Golden Faygo Brick
description: A golden brick filled with Faygo. As though you didn't look silly enough drinking that stuff in the first place.

name: Fake Unicorn Horn
description: You used to put this on your forehead and run around pretending you were the noblest of steeds. Used to. Right. You are most definitely not going to do that again in the near future.

name: Painting of a Unicorn Attacking a Football Player
description: A majestic work of art depicting an impressive unicorn attempting to eliminate the looming threat of a football player.

name: Really Fake Unicorn Horn of a Painting of a Horse Attacking a Football Player
description: A tacky unicorn horn created by ruining a beautiful piece of art. You monster.

name: Faygo - Fake Unicorn Meat Flavour
description: A bottle of Faygo that's supposed to taste like fake unicorn meat. You have no idea how this is accomplished, especially since you don't even know what real unicorn meat tastes like.

name: Fruit Gushers - Not Entirely Fake Unicorn Tears Flavour
description: Fruit Gushers filled to the gushing brim with "unicorn tears". You question the ethical implications of consuming such a thing.

name: Old Leprechaun Costume
description: An old leprechaun costume you wore when you were like five years old. It probably still fits...

name: Retailored Leprechaun Suit
description: A leprechaun suit designed for a person of normal size. Now you can pretend to follow the rainbow without cutting off bloodflow to your extremities!

name: Leprechaun\'s Rainbow Overcoat
description: Why would you try to follow the rainbow when the rainbow is ALREADY HERE.... and way too small for you to even try to wear as a coat?

name: Golden Leprechaun Suit
description: You followed all the rainbows and came back with enough gold to coat your suit in the stuff. So you did, and now it makes some fairly effective armor.

name: Example Stamp with Internal Computing Power
description: Why bother carrying around a computer and a weaponized stamp when you can have both in one simple package? It can still only stamp EXAMPLE on things, though.

name: Extelar Magic Hat
description: A wizard hat, rumored to have the strength of all the galaxy's constellations. After putting it on, though, all the power just feels to you like lightning shooting through your body whenever you use it.

name: Ring Blade
description: Dull on the inside, yet sharp on the outside, this hula hoop on steroids guarantees mass slaughter of imps, without causing damage to you. Gloves should still be worn when handling the blade, just in case.

name: Sex Pistol
description: It's the strangest thing, you swear. The rounds aren't "fired" like they would be in the conventional sense. What leaves the bright orange cylinder leaves it with powder unburned.

name: Bagged Milk
description: You gaze upon the legendary object with a sense of wonder. You never thought you would see the day when you would lay eyes on an actual bag of milk.... Unless you're Canadian. Then this is just an everyday object and you don't understand all the uproar.

name: Troll Horn Headset
description: Now you can chat with friends and cosplay on the go!

name: Example CompuStamp: Wax Edition
description: Now you can stamp EXAMPLE onto your enemies' foreheads with a variety of wax colors and fonts! Caution: Example CompuStamp: Wax Edition is not as delicious as crayons. At no point should you attempt to consume the Example CompuStamp: Wax Edition.

name: Example CompuStamp: Jewel Edition
description: Instead of stamping with fluids, this remarkable stamp embeds various types of gems into whatever you stamp it with. Now you can stamp EXAMPLE into things with STYLE!.

name: Training Sais
description: A pair of small, pointy, trident-like weapons. They're mostly for practice, as they're a bit dull, but you probably could still put an eye out with them.

name: Smells Like Burning Graphicsgun
description: Fill the air with artifacting and the fragrant smell of an overheated graphics card.

name: Frost Wizards Defense Gloves
description: The strange silvery gloves are surrounded with the soft glow of frost magic, and are capable of creating a weak magic shield.

name: Small Hard-Boiled Collider
description: Bam! Look at that, a weapon combining the prohibition era and the modern age. It is able to fire portals and shoot enemies. Not at the same time though. That would be...weird.

name: Neckcuffs
description: These Handcuffs are the perfect size for fitting around a person's neck. It gives you naughty ideas.

name: It\'s No Use
description: This sign gives you the power of ESP so long as you shout out ridiculous battle cries. The downside? You can only pick up and throw crates and hedgehogs.

name: Eagle Suit
description: An honest-to-God, flying business suit. Now you can give the term "rising up in the company" an all-new meaning.

name: American Compasses
description: These compasses always points to America! Yes, even though they're not THAT kind of compass. But seriously, what kind of country uses the term "compass" for anything other than the navigation tool? Not America, that's what!

name: Whale Skull Hoodie
description: This hoodie seems to be made from the remains of a whale-looking consort.

name: Shitty Bladed Knitting Needles
description: These needles will really give you an edge in the competitive knitting world!

name: Ghost of Starman\'s Hoodie
description: You are going to cast PSI Starstorm Alpha at the beginning of every combat. That is what this hoodie tells you. You begin to hope underlings are incapable of learning PSI Shield Omega.

name: iMask
description: A somewhat creepy hands free computing device.

name: Vegetable Peeler
description: No more unpeeled potatoes! With this peeler you'll make your vegetables NAKED.

name: Quantum Clothing Iron
description: This strange thing is based on quantum effects and destroys an enemy at which is thrown (because of heaviness).

name: Amethyst Dress
description: Another pretty stylish dress for a pretty stylish girl.

name: Hel\'s Shaft
description: Trailing eldritch wisps of mist behind it, this towering spear of smooth bone gives off a powerful and chilling aura. Being in its presence brings existential dread.

name: Robes of the Lich
description: A fanciful black robe with a pendant sewn into the neck. You can practically feel the dark magical energies emanating from this garment.

name: Luck o\' the Irish
description: A bunch of coins imbued with all of the luck of the land of Ireland. Given that potato famine a while back, and the fact that it's probably meteor hell right now, it's safe to say this probably isn't as powerful as you'd think.

name: The Great Green Coins
description: A bunch of green coins, pulsing with an entrancing light. Sometimes, enemies aren't killed by them - just transported elsewhere, and you don't have the foggiest idea where.

name: Torch Pipe
description: A small pipe with a constant breeze flowing through it and a small eternal flame on the end. It's most useful for lighting purposes, but you could probably use it as a weapon if things got desperate.

name: The Great Green Conflagration
description: A cluster of coins that seems to seek out enemies of its own accord and encase them in a small tornado of fire and green, glowing metal. Most things don't survive the aftermath.

name: Silver Wyrmclaw Scraper
description: You'd think silver wouldn't be a very sturdy metal to use, but there's a dragon claw at the end of the thing so you can't really complain.

name: Magnifying Glass
description: This is a regular old magnifying glass, perfect for searching for clues, or frying ants on the sidewalk.

name: Wailord Plush Rifle
description: The Wailord Hunter was seized and refurbished by the Hoenn government to fire soft and cuddly Wailord plush toys -- at horrifyingly devastating speeds. Who knew cute things could kill so efficiently?

name: Potato Masher
description: After centuries of being pounded on mercilessly, the potato finally decided to get its revenge. The mashed has become the masher.

name: Steel Bow
description: This stainless steel bow is sure to not break under your STRONG grip, and can also be used to forcefully bash your enemies' heads in.

name: Fleshmangler
description: A mace composed of multicolored bricks massed into an amalgamation of sharp corners and pain. If you leave THIS in the middle of the floor, you may not live to tell the tale...

name: sTick Tock
description: A light grey staff decorated with what seems to be circular runes. Two clocks are built into either end, one moving clockwise, one counter. You don't know why, but despite your class, wielding this makes you feel like a Lord. A Lord of Time.

name: Unstable Green Star Sphere
description: Oh god, you combined the barely-stable piece of a green sun with Pop Rocks, didn't you?! It's ready to go mini-supernova at any time!

name: Wristbands
description: Used purely for fashion. What else? Now available in all colors!

name: Grimdark Textridaggers
description: Poison-laced daggers from the outer ring. They sing songs of the Old Gods, forcing you into the fabled blackdeath trance of the woegothics, making you quake all the while in the bloodeldritch throes of the broodfester tongues. These are dark blades indeed...

name: Midnight Bat
description: It's an ethereal black obsidian bat with dark, neigh hellacious, attack nulling properties on your assailant.

name: Sniper King\'s Crown
description: A magical crown with the power to turn anyone who wears it to the world's best head shooter, don't be fooled this crown is big enough to be considered a helmet, it even has eye holes.

name: Broom of a Lynched Witch Queen
description: There's hardly a bristle left on this decrepit broomstick, and the sun-bleached wood creaks loudly every time it's touched. The creaking sounds like vengeful cackling, which promises to be an annoying gaming mechanic.

name: Razor bat
description: It slices! It dices! It pummels and it bruises! This razor bat is a surefire way to ensure your opponent loses!

name: Shrieking Magician\'s Hat
description: It's like the sorting hat, from that one movie, except it has no brim and it screams 24/7. You'll get used to the sound after while but you'll never fully regain your hearing.

name: Extendable Daedric Wabbajack
description: This staff has wacko majyyk AND you can adjust it to reach the other side of the room if you want it to. Yowza! This baby has super-rad secret-weapon written all over it.

name: Bastion Poster
description: Well, it's technically less of a poster and more a background that you printed out, laminated, and stuck to your wall. It's still awesome, though.

name: Cael Hammer
description: A large hammer. Kid's gotta hold it tight in both hands - make sure he doesn't lose his oldest friend.

name: Fang Repeater
description: An old hunting weapon, favored by the Trappers. The rapid-fire capabilities are quite handy in a pinch.

name: Breaker\'s Bow
description: A large, red bow used for breaking things. It works best if you pull the string alllll the way back.

name: Galleon Mortar
description: A massive mortar that was once used in some sort of navy, refitted to be portable for a kid. It packs quite a punch.

name: Armour of the End
description: Any Doom player would END YOU to wear this ensemble. The sick skull shapes knee and elbow pads don't hurt.

name: Black Wand of Tidy Necromancy
description: Channel the contrived science of spirit puppetry to command the raw power of doom upon your enemies and then enslave their ghosts to clean up afterwards. Hahahahaha. (And by "clean up" I'm talking about the guts that are going to be all over the place.)

name: Basshunter
description: Your favorite musical detective fish, Basshunter!

name: Patriot\'s Overcoat
description: Show your intense patriotism while crossing the delaware!

name: Epimagic Staff
description: This is a long, black and white staff that has a magic 8-ball at the top which shoots out magic darts.

name: Night-Striker Cane
description: Wielding the power of the ancient dragon Nidhogg, you feel more fearsome than ever before. With thunder at your fingertips, you can feel the energy flowing through your veins. It kind of hurts - but that could just be the radioactivity.

name: Tainted Truth
description: Honeyed words and sweet, sweet lies Tainted Truth, callous eyes.

name: Azure Pair-o\'-souls
description: A pair of sacred Umbrella-daggers, one is blue like the sky, the other blood red. When unfolded, they appear to be normal parasols, but when collapsed, they form deadly, sharp blades.

name: Continuum Fabric Waste Chute
description: Any attack that hits this shield is immediately transported to the point of least spacial and temporal resistance: the End of Time. Try not to fall down with this thing on. Who knows what might happen.

name: Glovetops
description: Fingerless gloves with little screens on the back for communication! Also great for backhanding.

name: Weighted Companion Gloves
description: Your Aperture Science Weighted Companion Gloves will never threaten to stab you, and in fact cannot speak.

name: Sharper Postal Stamp / 5 of Diamonds
description: A postal stamp with incredibly sharp bladed edges. The Postal Service does not recommend mailing anything using this stamp due to several unfortunate accidents in which it shredded someone else's mail.

name: Fluorite Stamptet
description: A set of 8 stamps, each containing immense magical power. Pity there's no more effective way to extract that power other than gluing one to an enemy's forehead and running away.

name: Bottled Anger
description: A purple bottle containing massive amounts of fury. You would try to drink it, but every time you open the bottle it starts screaming at you.

name: Model Heart
description: A small, magenta model heart that beats in your hand. It's kind of gross, but you can't help but love the little thing.

name: Think Tank
description: A small brain submerged in a jar of green fluids. You can almost feel new ideas emanating from it.

name: Stamptellite
description: A massive stamp with attached solar panels, originally used for monitoring the locations of packages. Now it's used for hitting things.

name: Stafftellite
description: A staff that was unfortunately knocked into orbit during a highly-classified NASA judo experiment. It's accumulated a fair bit of space debris, mostly consisting of circuits from other broken satellites.

name: Handful of Old Galactic Credits
description: A handful of credits from the times before the Galactic Federation switched to an all-digital currency. They're made of an extremely resistant alloy of metals, known only to the High Lords of the Mint.

name: Barrel Satellite
description: A barrel that was put into orbit by a bunch of rocket scientists as a memoir of their frat-boy days. Being in space has preserved it remarkably well, and it still has the stench of old, shitty beer.

name: Barrel of Satellites
description: A barrel full of tiny working satellites. Well, they would be working satellites if they were actually in orbit instead of shoved into a barrel.

name: Launchable Barrel of Satellites
description: A barrel of satellites primed for launch. You could follow through with the launch the way it's supposed to go, and end up with a bunch of tiny satellites orbiting your Land... or you could point it at an underling and use the satellites as tiny, expensive shotgun pellets. Totally up to you.

name: Vodka Barrel
description: What's better than a bottle of vodka? What's that you said? You've got a whole BARREL of vodka? HELL YES!

name: Gold-Plated Satellite Replica
description: A giant replica of a satellite that was decommissioned a long time ago. It's quite heavy.

name: Gold Bricked Satellite
description: A golden satellite which is no longer functional. I guess you could say that it's.... bricked.

name: Rake
description: A rake, generally used for scratching your back and gardening.

name: Raked Over the Coals
description: A rake with lighters attached to all of the tines. Slightly less effective at actually hitting things, but better than ever before at lighting them on fire.

name: Collapsible Wolverine Claws
description: While still pretty crummy, these claws are at least made of metal. And also collapse for easy storage!

name: Viola Noir
description: A monochromatic, metal viola that sounds like smoke and hits like a metal viola.

name: Black Rock Reaper Scythe
description: A death scythe with a lightly curved blade. It also comes in three different colors!

name: Electric Acid Stompers
description: It's a miracle that your feet manage to stay safe in these things. Regardless, now you can not only burn, electrocute and corrode your enemies all at once, you can now stomp on them as well! Isn't science amazing?

name: Pyrophiliac\'s Blunderbuss
description: While the whole "flaming bullets" gimmick is a little old, this thing is deadly as hell. This gentleman's rifle is oddly flame-retardant, although unless you plan to fight flaming Ogres, it's probably only going to be protecting itself from it's own bullets.

name: Tome of Clarke
description: This spell book contains knowledge on how magic truly works, allowing you to create even more powerful magical spells.

name: ShockChet
description: Hatchet && Teslacoil Shockrifferfy your opponents while you cut them down with your trusty ShockChet! An electrifying new way to make your foes suffer.

name: Broom Handle
description: This is a generic house-hold broom, minus the bristly head.

name: Totally Rad CellBro
description: Combining the most rad magazine with the elegant cello has created the most rad classical masterpiece. Ever.

name: Screaming Fueled Lantern
description: This large lantern's horn is powered by the fire of the lantern itself. Nobody could ever lose track of you with this!

name: Candle Fanstick
description: The more you wave it, the larger the flame. Best to never use it to cool off.

name: Green Sun Bedsheets
description: These white linens are spotted with green suns. Perfect for religious iguanas, but good for kids too.

name: The F Bomb
description: We like to keep this PG-13, so be careful to only use this once, kay?

name: Slenderbro Mask
description: This blank, white mask has no distinguishing features but a pair of shades. Staring at it gives you a chilling feeling.

name: Fake Arm Staff
description: A thin wooden pole, painted white, with a fake arm on one or both side(s). It has a variety of uses, such as being a staff, a stage prop (with the staff part mostly offscreen), or as a backscratcher.

name: Majora Captain Planet\'s Con-Air Portal Timey Wimey Air Man Pedestal of GUARANTEED MAYHEM
description: By the time the name of this weapon has been recited, the enemies are already dead, and the bunny is back in the box.

name: UNIVERS COSMOC INFIRO SORD......
description: Whomever wields this is supposed to be destined to cleave universes, but you'd be lucky if you could cleave a stick of butter with this thing. Going into battle with this blade is probably more of a risk to yourself than it is to your enemies, but do you really care?

name: Bear Bear Buns
description: This strange roll of super-soft toilet paper has a wonderful design of soft bear buns!

name: Barrel of Fish
description: It's a barrel filled with fish swimming around merrily. It's good for stress relief when you just need to kill a couple things without much of a fight.

name: Poisoned Starman
description: It appears to be a normal Starman. But when you try to use it, it just makes you frail and weak. Perhaps you could throw it at your enemies instead?

name: Tacky Starfish Decoration
description: Your guardians loved this thing for some reason, but you always thought it was hideous. And now that you've got complete control over the house, you think that it's best used as alchemy fodder instead of decoration.

name: Sea Starman
description: A starfish with huge cartoony eyes. You're kind of afraid to touch it out of fear that it might do something weird.

name: All-Seaing Starman
description: A glowing white starfish with eyes that occasionally flash with all the green fury of an extradimensional celestial body.

name: Glass of Mikle Milk
description: Drink up! You just saw me milk this, it's fresh from the Balance God's teats! Come on, you need this to make you biiig and strong!

name: Startellite-Fish
description: A fish-shaped satellite that was in orbit for a while, mapping Earth's oceans. Now that Earth is no more, it has wandered the cosmos searching for oceans to map and starfish to befriend until it somehow ended up here.

name: Book of Dreams
description: A book full of normal dreams and how to interpret them. It's such a shame you deal with Prospit and Derse now: you could have had so much fun with this!

name: Stamp of Obnoxious Omnipresence
description: How can you hope to send that letter when that letter's ALREADY THERE?!? How can you hope to hit that imp with this stamp when it is ALREADY LODGED IN THE IMP'S ESOPHAGUS?!?

name: Basic Spellstamp
description: A stamp that holds a couple of very basic spells. Things like this are generally used when stealth is necessary and carrying around a big ol' book would be a gigantic pain in the ass.

name: Spellbook of Shipping Yes That Kind
description: A spellbook that helps you make graphs and charts to figure out which of your friends are best paired with one another. It doesn't actually do the physical pairing up, though, which is a bit of a shame.

name: Star-filled Spectacles
description: These round-framed glasses sparkle with the wonder and brilliance of a child looking up at the night sky for the first time.

name: Anti-Shut Eye
description: There's NO WAY you'll be able to sleep on this. But it does pack a bigger punch than the normal pillow did.

name: Shitty Starfish Sword
description: A starfish with one leg so long that it could almost be confused for a blade. Well, until it was sharpened.

name: Gnarly Nautical Starfish Spellbook
description: A book full of water spells, most of which summon starfish to rain upon your enemies like some sort of plague.

name: Spellbook of Starfish Shipping
description: A spellbook specifically crafted for the possible incidents that may arise if you decide to ship a crate of starfish halfway around the world, ranging from a spell to monitor the health of the starfish to a spell that cures them of various starfish diseases. You never knew starfish shipping could be so complex.

name: STARFSH...
description: And you thought this thing was tacky before. Now it smells like the garbage can outside of a Subway and can't decide if it has four legs or six.

name: Barrel Aquarium
description: An aquarium in a barrel. How quaint.

name: Sattael Hammer
description: A hammer designed to send enemies into orbit without doing the same to the person holding it.

name: Cael Coin
description: A coin used in the lands of Caelondia before the Calamity hit. Now it's just a memento of days gone by.

name: Blue Potion
description: By combining the healing slime from your sprite with a potion that restores magic, you have managed to create a brew that preforms both jobs.

name: Bagged Mikle Milk
description: This strange bag of fluid is making an awful stench, somewhere between rotten eggs and rotten fish. Yuck... old milk.

name: The Guiding Light of Hope
description: This lantern shines brighter than the stars. You feel like it's saying "You must not lose hope!"

name: Bibidi-Babidi-Ballgown
description: A gorgeous ball gown perfect for getting out of a dead end job and kicking ass, just be careful not to stay out too late. How embarrassing!

name: Meat Cleavage
description: It cleaves your cleavage efficiently.

name: Glass Orb of Void
description: A palm-sized glass orb with an odd dark blue liquid that doesn't seem entirely there. It feels like if you get too close... ...WHOOSH! You'll get sucked into its depths.

name: Frost Wizards Defend!Time Gloves
description: These cold, shimmering gloves are designed with frozen spinning cogs. Capable of creating defensive ice barriers that are hard to break due to being frozen in time.

name: Prismatic Steel Rainbow-Bow
description: This spectacular steel bow can shoot beams of rainbow light! ...You're not really sure how this is supposed to hurt the enemy though.

name: Prismatic Cosplay Wings
description: These feathery and transparent wings refract light, sending rainbows everywhere. Now your enemies will die laughing.

name: Air-Conditioned Gas Mask
description: It gets hot in these things, you know...

name: Monstrous Hand-Held Cutting Apparatus of the Ancient Squiddle Clerics
description: You can feel the eons of ancient history coursing through these blindingly white scissors as you wield them. Although they do seem rather large for scissors, they could easily pose a great threat at almost any range.

name: Gentlemanly Cue
description: Only the most dapper of patrons use this marvelous specimen of pool cues. It's made of mahogany you know.

name: Titanic Anchor
description: A truly huge anchor, probably meant to hold an ocean liner or something. It's almost completely covered in barnacles, too.

name: Sniper\'s Longbow
description: An absolutely massive longbow, used to pick off targets in the distance in the days before rifles were a thing.

name: Nic Cage Nocker
description: A massive bow that can only use inflatable Nic Cages as arrows. You see absolutely no problem with this.

name: Titanic Anchorbow
description: A giant anchor turned into a longbow. It'd pack a huge punch if you could actually pull the string back all the way.

name: TimeBands
description: All the power of Time itself, in the palm of your hands... or... at your wrists... whatever.

name: Steel Dragon Skull On A Stick
description: this dragons skull look GREAT on this stick. its effects are oddly magical as it seems to breath fire when held.

name: Hemera\'s Glorious Golden Phantasmic Dress of the Aquamarine Sun of Life
description: It's getting harder and harder to die when you just get revived by Life powers every time. And, you know, the fact that everything that even comes close to touching you just goes through, gets disintegrated, or teleported to their doom.
art: Hemera's Glorious Golden Phantasmic Dress of the Aquamarine Sun of Life.gif

name: Captain Zappy\'s Retro Rocket Launcher
description: A stainless-steel laser-guided rocket launcher! Great for bringing down communist tyranny from the comfort of up to 30 yards!

name: Bearrel Bearrel Buns
description: A barrel made entirely of incredibly soft toilet paper. It's a miracle how the thing manages to stay together - just don't get it wet.

name: Spellbook of Heavy Nautical Shipping
description: A hefty spellbook that helps you keep track of exactly what kind of cargo there is in your hold, where it's all supposed to go, what's fragile and will be broken if you do something stupid like try to turn by using the anchor as a handbrake... Things like that.

name: Supreme Sea Shipping Spellbook
description: A book containing spells for quite literally any incident you may encounter while sailing the high seas. And if you run into an incident that it doesn't have a spell for, the book itself is quite heavy...

name: Anchors Away
description: A mortar that fires massive anchors at targets far in the distance. It's difficult to aim, but incredibly rewarding when you actually manage to hit something.

name: High-Frequency Knife Gloves
description: Luckily, it's only the blades that are vibrating: if the gloves were vibrating too, you probably wouldn't even be able to keep these things on!

name: Aperture Science Portal-Conducting Device
description: Have you ever been strained to carry both an Aperture Science Hand-held Portal Device and a baton whenever conducting your favorite orchestra? Of course you have, and so we have created the Aperture Science Portal-Conducting Device! With it, you can create portals without missing a beat of the Turret Anthem.

name: Triforce Beanie
description: Just because you are saving a kingdom from a power hungry desert bandit, doesn't mean you have to be cold while doing it.

name: Hero\'s Frostrainer
description: The bow belonging to a legendary hero plus a power-up! Now you can darken the skies with your volleys of icicles or freeze your opponents in place with your frost-imbued arrows!

name: Squiddle Shirt
description: A white shirt emblazoned with the image of a lavender Squiddle, with a label in the back declaring this "Officially Licensed Squiddles Material." There appears to be something slightly off about the design on the shirt.

name: Green Slime Ghost Shirt
description: Preferred attire of the junior, junior ectobiologist.

name: Life Seed Packet
description: A packet of small seeds which, when planted and watered correctly, coats everything nearby with various plant life in a matter of seconds.

name: Awesome Auger
description: BILLY MAYS HERE WITH THE AWESOME AUGER, THE INCIPISPHERE'S MOST EFFICIENT AND POWERFUL YARD TOOL YOU'LL EVER USE.

name: Justice Robo Costume
description: This costume is fairly sturdy, but it's made up entirely of cardboard and you can barely move your limbs in it. It'll make enemies hit slightly less effectively, but you'll be lucky if you can make any attacks in this thing.

name: Uranium-Powered Starfish
description: A starfish powered by uranium to do... whatever it is that starfishes do. Whatever that thing is, this starfish is going to do it even better now, yes siree.

name: Mmm Whatcha Sei
description: Ooooh, that you only meant well~ <iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/9NIZM-hMF_8?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: Canister of Gasoline
description: A small tank of gasoline that you found out in the garage. It's still just as flammable in the Medium as it was on Earth, so be careful with it.

name: Canister of Radioactive Gasoline
description: As though gasoline itself weren't dangerous enough for you, now it's emitting dangerous radiation. Way to go, genius.

name: Apocalyptic Billiards
description: End of the world? Doesn't mean you can't look snazzy.

name: Ancient Tome of Server - Ban
description: THEThis is the ancient tome belonging to "He Who Owns the Server," whatever the hell that means. Either way, this book is way large and way overpowered. It would take nothing short of a staff member and/or cocky little shit to obtain such a piece.<iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/9B2-dJcPJTw?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: Perforating Raydent of Annihilation
description: A crystal trident that is surprisingly lightweight and easy to wield. You'd expect most tridents to have a set of prongs, but this one is special: the end is a sphere with micro-drills spinning along the surface, obliterating any form of matter that even grazes the gyrating sphere.

name: HyperPowerGlove
description: A technologically advanced gauntlet that utilizes binary code for strife.

name: Greased-Up Squeak Chop
description: Introducing... the Greased-Up Squeak Chop! This upgrade to your household inflatable mealtime hammer comes with its own lubrication to both ease your strifes, and deep-fry your ingrediants at the same time, all with impeccable style! [Health value of food and/or vital signs after eating are not guaranteed.]

name: Powered Christmas Wand
description: Have you ever wanted to control the power of christmas and command snow beasts? Well now you can for the low cost of 87 AAA batteries!!!

name: Crimson Inflata-Stud Gauntlets
description: Coated in never-ending blood of an unknown origin, these inflated gloves have a pair of sharp scissor on the end that snip with each jab. Careful not to pop the gloves!

name: AA16
description: A fully automatic 12gauge shotgun that decimates your enemy with 300 rounds per minute.

name: Black Magic Froggy-lixer
description: This black elixir billows with an ebony nebula-esque smoke. You can sense a lot of power contained within, but power leads to corruption...

name: Freelance Witch\'s Hat
description: A massive staple-top bonnet adorned with a length of ribbon, string of pearls, and two roses. A dressed up look for the working witch with an "independent" sense of style. It smells of hemlock oil.

name: Black-Hole Spectacles
description: These round-framed glasses radiate the brilliance and wonder of a child who looks straight into THE DEPTHS and sees only beauty. The owner of a matured psyche, you feel that getting too close to these could rip something from you, but you're sure that's irrational.

name: Path of the Glacial Master I
description: As you begin your journey to master the powers of ice, the gloves turn into a cold, shimmering whiteness with the slightest bit of purple. You can now summon a Bow and Arrows to attack your enemies, along with your normal defensive capabilities.

name: Vongola\'s Tears
description: X-Gloves that have been modified to channel Rain Flame in addition to Sky Flame. Has heat, cool and steam settings!

name: Brainmangler
description: Look at all these colors and cubes! Your enemies' minds will cease to function long before you strike them in the head with this puzzling mace.

name: Maceball Cap
description: What kind of twisted variation of baseball is this? Just be wary of anyone sliding to your base head-first!

name: Pyrokinetic Jawspiker
description: The head of this mace is covered in purple flames and appears to be made of the same stuff as jawbreakers. Whether you're casting storms of psychic fire or dislocating someone's jaw, you're sure to cause all kinds of cavities.

name: Couch Potato Masher
description: After having its revenge, the potato decided to settle down and watch some TV for a while. Don't worry, it was already a vegetable.

name: Cup of Absolutely Terrifying Mysterious Liquid
description: It's easy to mistake this as a cup of coffee, but the strange unctuous film that accumulates on the surface, as well as how shitty it would appear to taste leaves a lot to be desired. You quickly wish for a bottle of AJ or something as the stench hits you.

name: Pool for Peace
description: What better way to end strife and war than with a game of pool, played magical, winged cue stick?

name: Assassin\'s Scalpel
description: This scalpel is laced with the lethal poison brewed by those chaotic evil assassins. At least you don't have a chance of poisoning yourself, right? You have the "Use Poison" ability... right?

name: Coffee Bear Hat
description: Despite the name, this hat is not the hat of the fabled Coffee Bear. It's just a bear hat that smells like coffee.

name: Chameleon Lasher
description: This plushie blends in with whatever it's held up against, owing to some unique properties of its scales. Additionally, squeezing the thing can cause a sticky and spiked tongue to launch from its mouth to strike opponents.

name: Killer of the 15 pins
description: Even though it sounds dangerous it is not really. The only thing that is different about this bowling ball is the fact that it has more holes and is far more colorful.

name: Protoman\'s Scarf
description: The scarf of a lone warrior who paved the path of greatness for our famed blue bomber.

name: Nidhogg
description: The sacred bow of Frelia wielded to defeat the Demon King, Fomortiis. Bringing luck to aid the archer's shot, it is a relatively heavy bow, but it seems a bit ancient compared to your other gear.

name: Tusken Laser Rifle
description: A laser rifle used by the Tusken Raiders of Tatooine, now with deadly inaccuracy and an old-fashioned look.

name: Bloodstain Fever
description: The scissors of the legendary serial killer herself, specially crafted for her crimes. Useful for killing both imps and cute boys.

name: Aperture Science Singing-Turret Instructolizer
description: Have you ever wondered what possibilities are hidden within your lovable Aperture Science turret? Expand their repertoire with the new Singing-Turret Instructolizer! Lead them through countless varieties of stored songs, including the "Turret Anthem".

name: Starry Space Bedsheet
description: It looks like this linen is actually made of the night sky, and on a beautiful night at that. It could be worn as a shawl, a cape, a short cloak, or anything you want.

name: Time-Space Bedsheet
description: This elaborately decorated cloth emanates the feeling of being part of something bigger. To touch it is to feel everything that ever was and ever could be vibrating against your flesh. Everything is already here and there and inside everything else. Not that you can predict the future wearing it, it pretty much has the same effect as too much faygo.

name: Mikly Way
description: A small milk chocolate treat with a chewy nougat and caramel center that emits an irresistible aroma. Biting into it makes you feel an urge to TALK IN ALL CAPS and murder everyone with your sickle.

name: Guide to Studying the Zoologically Improbable
description: A complete guide on creatures that do not exist, from little dusty faeries to the fabled Austrailian. Perusing through this book fills you with vast knowledge of a completely fictional realm, this stuff may not exist but if it did you'd be the go to expert here.

name: Phoenixfire Quill
description: Control the wings of the inferno with this wand! Watch as even the toughest foes are incinerated on the spot! You might see the avian demon of fire itself!

name: Painting of a Musclebeast Attacking a Football Player
description: A framed, and honestly horrifying portrait of a STRONG Musclebeast engaged in mortal fisticuffs with a mentally scarred and emotionally traumatized football player.

name: Cosmic Darts
description: This darts are imbued with cosmic rays, bombarding whatever they hit with deadly radiation!

name: Midnight Shadow-Double Bass
description: Club your enemies as you hit them with the shadowy waves of your midnight jazz. Once you fill 'em with midnight, these underlings will wish they never picked a fight with you.

name: Sherlock\'s Observation Lens
description: The lens of the magnifying glass of the great Sherlock Holmes, wizard master of deduction. It still carries a bit of his power, allowing you to see the true nature of things when you look through it.

name: Rings of Saturn
description: A miniaturized, extremely dense version of the beautiful rings that used to surround Saturn. They've still got all the mass they used to have, making them quite heavy and good for walloping things with.

name: Fractal Disc
description: A black disc with smaller black discs attached to the edges, and each of those smaller discs has another set of even smaller discs, and each of those discs has an even smaller set of discs, and... you get the point. The infinite layering of tiny discs actually makes the edges of this thing surprisingly sharp.

name: Ancient Stamp of Legend
description: A stamp made legendary due to its incredible resilience, reusability, and ability to summon a small army of angry postmen at any time. Its most notable use occurred in riots of 1878, when the honorable men and women of the Postal Service stormed the golden archways of Congress to protest their jobs being replaced by magical carrier pigeons.

name: Nuclear POTaTOS
description: Wouldn't it have been easier to hook up the nuclear generator to a normal robot body instead of pumping all that power through a potato just to give more power to an AI? Well, yes, but that's nowhere near as fun or potentially lethal.

name: High-Frequency Murasama
description: Originally crafted by the master swordsmith Muramasa, one of the idiots who used to wield this thing misspelled its name as "Murasama". How a centuries-old blade somehow became one of the deadliest weapons on the planet you don't know, but you don't really care, do you?

name: Hot Wings
description: A choice meal for the budding masochist in you!

name: Macicle
description: This mace is made of solid ice. It's also quite delicious, but if you're going to lick it, mind the spikes...

name: Mace as White as Snow
description: This mace head is covered in fluffy wool. You... don't think this will do a whole lot of damage.

name: Funky Flail
description: It's time to get down with your bad self and fling that flail all around the dance floor! Oh yeah! Watch out!

name: Chaos Dragon Armor
description: The surface of this scaled armor rolls with gouts of flame, corrosive acid, and arcs of electricity, all in a completely random manner, whilst showing off a scintillating show of colors at the same time.

name: Caltrops
description: These sharp metal spikes are typically scattered along the ground by ninja to cover a retreat or as a trap for the unwary.

name: Ghost Arms
description: A floating blue glob of unresponsive ectoplasm in the shape of a right forearm floating in the middle of the room. This is completely useless! If only there were a way to control it from a distance...

name: Cyber Paddle Axe
description: Cuts through monsters at the speed of the internet current itself. Although it's a little hard to hold since it is digital.

name: Pincer Blades "Bloodlust"
description: Created from battle data obtained from Sundowner, these gigantic scissor-like blades LOOK like they would just be gimmicky and ineffective, but while they are slow, these things pack a devastating punch that can slice most normal enemies straight in two. Too bad you're not fighting "normal" enemies.

name: Tactical Sai "Dystopia"
description: Created from battle data obtained from Monsoon and powered by Lorentz force, this Sai acts as a grappling hook of sorts, allowing you to propel yourself towards your foes.

name: Hylian\'s Cataclysm
description: Carrying the legendary bow used by the Hero of Time, you can decimate the battlefield with arrows that have harnessed the power of the inferno and the blizzard. Too bad you still can't beat Ganondorf with it.

name: Apocalypse Always Pocket Dimension Protector
description: It hurts your eyes to look at the "point towards enemy" side, but what you can make out suggests lots of lightning and an enormous blaze of hellfire. Something tells you not to poke the front. Probably common sense.

name: 8 Paths To The Future
description: This new form of a prediction is a real pain in the neck. Although it no longer gives off an annoying light and the color is easier to read, it now predicts eight different futures and shows you allllllll of them at once. So be prepared for a massive headache if you look directly at it. (Ouch!)

name: Eternal Rings of Saturn
description: The beautiful rings of the planet Saturn, miniaturized and preserved forever in their most beautiful state. Their most beautiful state also happens to be their sharpest.

name: Incomprehensible Fractal Disk
description: The tiny discs appended to the body of this main disc are always growing, repositioning themselves, or merging with the main disc itself - and yet, the whole thing seems to maintain some state of order. It's rather baffling, but at least it's still sharp.

name: Dad\'s Special Brew
description: You're not sure what exactly is in this, and you're also pretty sure you don't want to know. The hell, dad?

name: Crystal Necklace
description: A sparkling crystal hangs from the delicate links, reflecting and refracting the light that shines on it. Isn't it just gorgeous?

name: Transformation Brooch
description: Maybe if you shout 'Moon Prism Power' with enough vigor, you'll actually transform.

name: Miraculous Holo-Projector: Modern Magical Warfare Edition
description: Have you ever wished you could control your own army of wizards and soldiers? Well, wait no longer! Even though they are holograms, these warriors can still harm your opponents with their magic and bullets, and their formation and loyalty to their commander are flawless.

name: Die of Power?
description: What's so special about this? It's just the die from inside a magic 8-ball.

name: Monobear Plush
description: It seems to emanate an aura of evil and cuteness at the same time.

name: Monomi Plush
description: Such a cute little bunny must hide some sort of evil secret...

name: Irradiated Candy Clobberer
description: This hard candy mace is filled to the brim with psionic heat energy amplified to ridiculously dangerous levels by nuclear power. It's difficult to discern the exact cause of death of anything struck by it - is it the flames or the radiation? Or perhaps blunt force trauma? Cause it can still do that too, in case you forgot.

name: Tadpat Bat
description: Born in the fiery heart of the great frog himself, this tool is entwined with the sovereign amphibian. It writhes lively under your grasp. I think it likes you!

name: YOYOAH STRAWHATE....
description: This is, without question, the most conksuck yoyo designed to look like a strawhat you have ever seen.

name: Plastic Cow Toy
description: An old plastic cow figurine you played with when you were a little kid. Bashing imps with it brings back fond memories.

name: Painting of a Cow Attacking a McDonald\'s Employee
description: A painting depicting a magnificent bovine display of valor against an underpaid fast food employee.

name: Bovine Quartet
description: A set of four black-and-white splotched dice. When rolled, they can provide a variety of magical effects, most of which summon angry hordes of cows on top of whatever unfortunate underling has incurred your wrath.

name: Example CompuStamp - Midas Edition
description: Now everything you stamp turns into gold with an imprint of "EXAMPLE" on it. Neat, but not entirely useful unless you're killing stuff. Which, coincidentally....

name: Example CompuStamp - Really Heavy Edition
description: Lugging it around is a royal pain, especially since it's so huge, but it's entirely worth it to see an imp get pulverized into the ground, with an EXAMPLE imprint three feet deep as the only evidence it ever existed.

name: Example CompuStamp - Rapid-Stamping Edition
description: Now you can just wheel this incredibly heavy stamp from one stamping to the next. The incredible convenience almost makes up for still having to push the damn thing.

name: Example CompuStamp - Turbo Edition
description: An incredibly heavy stamp that does most of the heavy lifting for you - but it's probably a good idea to stand back whenever you're pointing this at something.

name: Example CompuStamp Launcher - Explosive Impact Edition
description: Now you can stamp the word EXAMPLE into enemies from long-range - and the explosive scarring will make sure they remember it!

name: Example CompuStamp Launcher - Precision Stamping Edition
description: Make every stamp count, and let no enemy leave without an EXAMPLE on - or through - their forehead.

name: Example CompuStamp Launcher - Extra Penetration Edition
description: The drill bits integrated into the stamp ammunition make extra-sure that the word EXAMPLE gets engraved into each and every poor sod you fight. It also proves minimally useful for mining purposes, allowing for precision engravings of EXAMPLE into the tunnels to confuse anyone who may venture inside.

name: Example DrillStamp Launcher - Extremely Shocking Edition
description: Now each drill-stamp is lubricated with a superconductive fluid and carries a small battery capable of delivering quite a jolt. As though having a stamp drill the word EXAMPLE into your flesh wasn't bad enough.

name: Example DrillStamp Launcher - Taser Grappling Hook Edition
description: The stamp-drills fired by this rifle carry along a chain with them - and with that chain comes several thousand amps of electrical current, easily capable of felling the largest of beasts. It also functions as an impromptu grappling hook, although you might want to make sure you're wearing quite a bit of rubber.

name: Example DrillStamp Launcher - Every Attachment Ever Edition
description: This rifle has thirty different types of drillstamp ammunition ranging from small hunting rounds to something you'd expect to shoot out of a cannon, as well as over a hundred types of grapple cabling, a small oven, and who knows how many knives. You're pretty sure there's a dishwasher and an ectobiology station in here somewhere too, but you've yet to actually find them.

name: Captain Planet\'s Practice Pollution Pounder
description: A blunt cleaning device for the aspiring Planeteer, it can purify water, safely dispose of your garbage, and even recycle metals, papers, and plastics! Now if only it could do something more than marginally annoy your enemies.

name: Path of the Glacial Master II
description: Your journey is off to a fine start. As you master the ability to create ice drills, your gloves become more purple and you can see faint snowflake-like cogs spinning all over it.

name: Acid-Tongued Lasher
description: This lizard plushie's spiked tongue drips with the deadliest poisons that SCIENCE has to offer. Just aim and squeeze for the funniest way to attack your enemies.

name: Photodischronation Bow
description: Infused with the power of the Highest Spirits within every lightbulb, this bow fires its arrows through the space-time continuum before reaching its final destination lodged through your opponent's head. The time shenanigans are way too complicated for you to understand, so you just enjoy the pretty lights as your arrows warp into the temporal fabric.

name: Nyx\'s Death Chime
description: The Denizen Nyx is said to use this baton when bringing you closer into nothingness...

name: Burning Strike
description: This thing's almost too hot to handle. Perfect for those jump shots too.

name: Draconic Reaper Lizard Plushie
description: Using the scientifically badass elemental powers imbued within the long, scythe-like obsidian claws of this lizard plushie, you can deal devastating damage to enemies. Still, the plushie is soft as hell and somehow adorable despite the chunks of imps and ogres that have fallen victim to its awesome power.

name: Couch Potato Chessmaster
description: While channel surfing one day, the couch potato stumbled across a broadcast of a chess tournament. After hours of observing chess matches and common player patterns, it decided to pursue a new hobby as a master chess strategist. It now dons a crown of chess pieces to celebrate its ascension.

name: Ninja in Sheep\'s Clothing
description: The wool on this mace does a great job of concealing the sai-like spikes hidden underneath, ready to be deployed when the timing is juuuuust right. As in, right before connecting with your unsuspecting victim's face.

name: Hyrule\'s Ekpyrosis
description: Wield the power to finally stop your shadow from following you like a creep and wreck havoc throughout your planet while you are at it. With arrows infused with the power of the nature elements, your shots will be hitting with the magnitude of a category 9 hurricane, solar flare from the sun, and the energy from a small sun, all wrapped in one.

name: Coldblooded Murder
description: A blunt weapon coated in spires of thick, black ice, just like the heart of its owner will soon become. C-c-caw c-c-caw m-m-motherf-f-fuckers.

name: Black Sheep Blackjack
description: This bludgeon is composed of spikes as sharp as knives between a coat of black wool that camouflages with the night. Black sheep, black sheep, have you any wool? No, but I've got three bodybags full of stiffs. Now shut the hell up or you'll make four.

name: Assassin\'s Spine-Chiller
description: A much sought-after weapon of killers the world over, this frozen midnight black mace is known to instantly freeze the blood of anyone whacked with it, preventing it from spilling everywhere and therefore not making it obvious that the body is a dead one. From a glance, anyway. But more importantly, none of the victim's blood gets on the weapon. There's no telling how many suckers were bonked with this.

name: Magician\'s Deck
description: A basic deck full of magic spells and monster descriptions. They glow with a faint light when touched and often make weird noises.

name: Hoops of Fury
description: Hmm. The 2 foot long indigo blades sticking out from this hoop aren't discreet enough? Well shoot...

name: Spear Fluted
description: This extra long silver flute's a bit hard to hold, you have to admit, but it serves two functions. One, it CAN play beautiful music (though you may not know how...?), and two, it's got a spear head on one end of it, allowing for maximum stabbity. Don't try to do both at the same time, though!

name: Soul Helm
description: You can hear the courageous voices of chivalrous knights long fallen calling out to you, pushing you onward in battle. ...You get the urge to fight a dragon and save a maiden.

name: Croakenspiel
description: This very bat is said to have once been wielded by the Speaker of the Vast Croak himself during one of his legendary bouts with other omnipotent beings. That is, however, preposterous. This would have to be much larger.

name: Furthest Ring Bedsheet
description: Supposedly this linen has a perfect map of the furthest ring printed on it. Bullshit. It's a pure black sheet, so perfectly black it seems to freaking glow darkness, save what appears to be the tiniest spec of green paint on the back. It looks pretty ordinary but hell is it good at absorbing damage.

name: Cherubin Flash Crystal
description: At first glance, it's an ordinary crystalline sphere, but on second glance and every glance thereafter you nearly have a seizure from all the flashing pool ball colors. You don't think you will ever glance at it again.

name: Bunny Panties
description: These pink panties have a small bunny embroidered on them, and are adorable enough to cause your enemy to falter, and occasionally squeal.

name: Blessed Thong
description: This cute thing endows you with the magical protection of the heavens. Nevermind the fact that it's just a thong.

name: Valiant Dragon Armor of the Sun
description: This beautiful scaly armour shines with all the brightness of the sun, showing off its beautiful design of several gold, silver, copper, and brass dragons.

name: Chaotic Sun-Dragon Armor
description: This chromatic armor displays an ever-twisting dragon with a sun for a head on its scaly surface. Unfortunately, the acid, continuous streams of flame, and arcs of electricity kind of cover it up.

name: Prismatic Sun-Dragon Armor
description: This beautiful scaly chestplate shows off a the image of a dragon with a sun for a head on its bright gold-and-silver surface.

name: Chaos Reignmaster Armor of the Dragon
description: This armor tugs at the threads of reality, of space and time. Seemingly random things tend to happen, ranging from the incredibly bizarre to the even more incredibly bizarre. Luckily, there are some crazy time powers built into the armor that act simply as a safeguard.

name: Holy Atomizer
description: The glowing fuel cells in this technical marvel of a weapon combines holy wrath with nuclear physics to burn your enemies in a brilliant green fire! let's just hope it doesnt leak radiation and melt your fingers off.

name: Flame Pendant
description: This necklace glows with an inner light, as if a flickering flame were encased within the pendant.

name: Squiddles\' Embrace
description: With the power of your weighted, bladed throwing squiddles, your love for squiddles can truly reach everyone.

name: Prismatic Sword
description: A sword that reflects visible light that passes through it and divides its spectrum. The effect is pretty, but is it practical as a weapon...?

name: JellyCane
description: This thin white cane is made of sugar and flavorings and gives off a delicious aroma. As you bend down to lick it, the eternal question comes to mind - Is it popcorn, or rotten egg...?

name: Viva Las... Geneva?
description: A sweet novelty army knife from the bustling gambling circuit of Geneva, Switzerland. With a quaint little flamingo daintily shaped into every tool, you'll be shredding through foes with this deadly flamboyance!

name: Explosive Throwstick
description: You combined a wooden boomerang and a grenade to create an explosive boomerang! It will explode when it touches an enemy and even though that is pretty neat, you should probably make sure that this happens BEFORE the boomerang returns to you.

name: Ball of chain
description: The same heavy chain you're used to wrapped up as a noisy interlocking wad. Holding it hurts your fingers and back but damn you could knock somebody out with this.

name: Explosive Bubble Wand
description: The explosive bubble wand allows you to blow bubbles that create an explosion when they pop.

name: Paper Shuriken
