description: Using the ancient art of origami (alchemy), you have crafted this paper shuriken. It probably isn't going to do much damage...

name: Staffwire
description: A long staff with a long piece of barbed wire wrapped around the end for close contact encounters.

name: Lava Lamp Bat
description: This transparent baseball bat contains that strange goopy stuff you find in lava lamps making it hot to the touch.

name: Bifrost
description: This visually stunning weapon has an inner ring made entirely of stained glass, arranged to resemble a rainbow. The edge is protected by a ring of silver, with blades shaped like sharpened wings. Despite its fragile appearance, the ring-blade is impossible to break, making it a useful defensive weapon.

name: Tatooine\'s Uprising
description: The Empire has bossed you around enough! Its time that the Rebels took a stand for this desert planet

name: Black Magic Skull
description: A charred skull, this relic has a red gem embedded in its forehead and generic glowing symbols carves around its top. It leaks a foreboding air of great power and would look so punk hanging from your neck or something.

name: Six Pocket Maelstrom
description: Hey, be careful where you jab that thing! Don't want to send a fire cyclone towards anything other than the cue ball, right? And if you mistake an enemy for the white white thing, no problem.

name: Premium Voltage Sweep
description: The classic 6-V upgraded with innovative recharge technology allows for over twice the power of the basic model. Recharge rope may be a bit cumbersome though.

name: iSweep
description: Apple brings you the future of sweeping technology. Sure it's a little bit overpriced, but now it has apps. Consorts LOVE apps.

name: Premium Voltage iSweep
description: The future of sweeping technology is here with Apple's new and improved version of the market leading smartbroom. Now with increased charge capacity for the busy broom enthusiast on the go.

name: Premium Voltage iSweep Mini
description: Everything you loved about the original in a sleek, new handheld form. You can practically feel the power of the apps coursing through your arm.

name: Thong of Draconic Chaos
description: You...aren't even sure if this armor is safe to wear. It looks like it could kill you. But it's quite comfortable, despite the rough-looking, flame-coated scales. And the lightning, can't forget the lightning.

name: Polar Flash Orb
description: GAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHHH!!!!!!!!!IT'S EVEN WORSTDBHDNOOOOOOOOOOOOOWWW!!!! YYYYYYYYYFDGNDID I THINK IT WAS A GOOD IDEADFBG TO MAKE THIS SHIT!!!!!?!? Y ENGLIHGNSDXSH!!!!????!! YFCJN HUSSIKHKGHGDNT!!!!!?!? MTFCKGkdcyjyfrhxstCdhtDthTmhdtyjYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!? THE FLASHJFJKSH! THE FLASHINGLIGDXRGMJHGMHTS!!!!!!!("foams from mouth wile roling on floor")

name: Void Spword
description: The colored spword goes from being a colorful medium of weapon to a destructive weapon that can ooze black liquid which can suck in enemies into its watery dark slime as it is hit or sliced, making a one-hit super effective.

name: Egg Beater
description: You used to use this to blend together ingredients. Now you are using it to blend imps into grist.

name: Paper Wings
description: They might be made of paper, but they're still functional at least.

name: Sergeant Potato of Skaia
description: Taking note of the Potato Chessmaster's incredible tactical skill, the White King and Queen of Prospit decided to offer it a position in their military. Naturally, our hero accepted, eager to prove its worth in battle, and become a role model for potatoes everywhere.

name: Mashed Potato
description: This vegetable has met a grisly end at the hands of some mace-wielding maniac. Its story has ended before it even began.

name: Blue Postal Stamp
description: A normal postal stamp painted blue.

name: Razor Spellstamp
description: A spellstamp containing an enchantment that makes it razor-sharp. Good for assassinations, impromptu knife fights, and dicing vegetables.

name: Computerized Spellstamp
description: A spellstamp with slightly less portability but significantly more computing and spellcasting power.

name: Cow Corpse
description: The massive corpse of what was once a real, live cow which didn't seem to have enough life to keep going. You don't really have any idea what to do with this.

name: Pile of Raw Hamburger Meat
description: A pile of raw hamburger meat. It's kinda gross, and isn't useful for much unless you cook it.

name: Bunless Hamburger
description: A hamburger patty without the bun. It's kind of depressing.

name: Cow Cowl
description: A cowl made out of black-and-white patterned leather. It's quite stylish.

name: Intestinal Bovine Drill Gauntlets
description: A pair of drill gauntlets covered in cow guts. What it lacks in power, it makes up for by completely disgusting your enemies and maybe giving them mad cow disease.

name: ded COW...
description: oh noO the COW is dead... the BEEf is LOXST...

name: Plastic Cow-Patterned Drill
description: A drill with a bit made out of black and white plastic. It's a bit flimsy, but still fun to use.

name: Nearly Generic Object
description: It's almost perfectly generic, but it still has a few defining features that need to be ironed out. Like those corners.

name: Radioactive Cow Corpse
description: A cow that you suspect may have been a victim of the Chernobyl accident, preserved for a very long time by the massive half-life of its muons..

name: Muon Moo-on
description: A tiny cow-shaped particle capable of mooing at up to - okay does anyone else see the pun in the title? I can't make a description for this with that pun just staring me in the face. Please, make it stop PLEASE PLEASE OH GOD WHY

name: Bovine Bereaver
description: A woodchipper painted to look like a cow. It takes things in from the "mouth" and... errr.... dispenses shavings from the other end.

name: Nuclear Windchipper Turbine
description: A nuclear turbine that chips the wind. It's really heavy and really useless.

name: Massive Nuclear Drill Chippers
description: A pair of gigantic nuclear drilling gauntlets that utilize woodchipping technology to completely destroy any leftover rubble, making digging a much cleaner exercise.

name: Nuclear Wind Bovine
description: A cow-shaped nuclear reactor that leaves behind devastatingly reactive "cowpies" all over your lawn.

name: Commemorative Cow Trophy
description: A mounted cow trophy. An attached plaque reads "A stuffed cow to memorialize August 8th, the Night of the Many Cows, and all those who lost their sanity in the fracas afterwards." You have no idea what this means, but you feel an odd sense of reverence for it anyways.

name: Udder Cowtastrophe
description: The remains of a cow bound up in barbed wire. Unfortunately, it's bound incredibly tightly and it's kinda leaking blood and milk everywhere - it's taking quite a bit of willpower not to vomit.

name: Untanned Leather Jacket
description: This isn't as comfortable or stylish as a normal leather jacket. Why did you think this was a good idea again?

name: Nearly Unique Object
description: It seems pretty unique, but it still needs a little... SOMETHING to be perfect.

name: Barrel of Cow Bits
description: A barrel filled with miscellaneous pieces of bovine flesh. It's starting to smell bad.

name: Sea Cow Corpse
description: A manatee corpse. You feel incredibly sad about the death of such a majestic creature.

name: Roadkill
description: An animal you picked off the road one dreary day. Your guardian didn't approve of bringing it into the household, but you embalmed the animal in formaldehyde and kept it as a beloved pet anyway.

name: The Games Will Never Stop
description: A disc with a hat printed on it. Any attempt to play the disc is met with a continuous audio of "THE GAMES WILL NEVER STOP" from Gamebro's theme song.

name: Roadkrill
description: You want to call this roadkill, but it probably falls under "vehicular homicide". You encased the beautiful gem in no less than one hundred liters of formaldehyde, and question why you have cancer ten years later.

name: The Cows will NEVAR STP
description: An unending line of shitty cows that clip through the floor and take pixelated shits on everything. You can only hope that once enough cows arrive, the line will eventually stop and you can get rid of them all. But the cows will never stop, will they?

name: Road-quill
description: You see, this is a fine example of society. Porcupine quills fashioned into a blade, dripping ink or blood. Diplomacy and running over small animals with giant machines is the foundation of a functioning, happy civilization.

name: Plastic Cow Staff
description: A staff made out of shitty toy plastic. It breaks too easily to be a worthwhile weapon.

name: Broken Cowledfwlch
description: The broken sword of the legendary bovine hero Betsy the Third. The leather hilt is made from the skins of her fallen enemies of the Farmerian Kingdom.

name: The Remains of Betsy the Third
description: The well-preserved remains of the legendary warriorcow, Betsy the Third. You're probably going to desecrate this, aren't you.

name: Cowntendium Armor
description: As thought the Nintendium coating wasn't enough, now there's a solid layer of extra meat that enemies have to punch through to get to you. Just finish using it before it starts to smell.

name: Methane Pipe
description: A pipe that emits a constant stream of methane. It smells really, really bad.

name: cows & c0ws and COWS and C0W5 and cows
description: A small tome that allows you to summon an unending stream of continuously mutating bovines. You're pretty sure you saw a video about this somewhere before...

name: Plastic Cow Spellstamp
description: A spellstamp that can only create, destroy, or manipulate plastic toy cows. Well, you guess you could try to drop a giant plastic cow on things...?

name: Ribbon
description: A pretty little strip of color made to wrap up presents, making it not at all dangerous.

name: Nuclear Powered Coat
description: This coat uses nuclear science to collect the radiation resulting from the nuclear power cells in the coat into a force field. You are not sure how safe this is.

name: Harmonica
description: Nothing like an old metallic mouth organ to feel like you are in the Old West, or maybe a prison cell. In either situation, you really need a heavy metallic tool to protect your rear.

name: Anvil Heels
description: Good luck walking in these, hope you've got calves of steel. Still good for fashionably bashing in your enemies head though

name: SHOBEL...
description: You've pixelated the shovel even further, rendering it useless. Dear god, my eyes.

name: Path of the Glacial Master III
description: Your journey is only half done. As you master the ability to generate spears, the gloves take a darker shade of purple and the snowflake cogs become more clear.

name: Midnight Spellstamp / 7 of Spades
description: A spellstamp containing a variety of spells for stabbing things and breaking clocks.

name: Candy Bow
description: Made of the finest candy canes and stringed syrup, this tasty bow will put a smile to the enemies faces... assuming they aren't diabetic.

name: Firework Stamp
description: A stamp which starts spitting sparks in every direction shortly after you lick the back.

name: Explosive Stamp
description: A stamp which explodes spectacularly shortly after you lick the back. It's good for both combat and demolition.

name: TV Remote
description: The remote you use to change channels on your TV. Who knows what you might get by alchemizing it?

name: Remote Detonation Explosive Stamps
description: A set of stamps and a remote detonator. Simply stick them to whatever you don't want around any more, then press the button. It's that simple.

name: Retroactive Remote Detonation Explosive Stamps
description: A set of stamps and a detonator that allows you to choose what time they explode at. This allows you to explode them several hours in both the future and the past, meaning you should probably hold them at arm's length before a future self decides to suddenly rearrange your anatomy.

name: Retroactive Even-More-Remote Detonation Explosive Stamps
description: Now you can stick explosive arrows to enemies from even greater distances, run away, and hope that your future self doesn't decide to detonate the rest of your quiver before it's deployed. It would be fun if it weren't completely nerve-wracking.

name: Time-Traveling Stamp
description: A stamp that can send objects to any point and time, provided you have enough of them attached to the package.

name: Timestamp
description: A large bunch of floating text that tells you what time and date it is in some form of parallel universe that doesn't have time travel.

name: The Rapid Fire Repulsor Blast
description: Cut down your enemies from a distance with these rapid-fire blasts. Be careful though, you can be left open to attack if you don't pay attention.

name: Doctor Whood
description: This stylish hoodie went out of date long ago.

name: Faygo - Candy Corn Flavour
description: What the heck is this swill? Why did you even think this was a good idea?

name: Symphonia Adventure Bow
description: This yellow longbow shoots discs instead of arrows... You'd think it would be stronger, but you'd be wrong.

name: Electric Boogaloo Needleurchin
description: This bouncing bundle of pure shocking stabbetry is a great thing to have around in a fight, so long as you stand as far the fuck away as you can possibly be.

name: Timed Condutor\'s Baton
description: A baton that keeps a constant beat, flipping over once in a while to keep the cycle going.

name: Space-Rending Javelin
description: This javelin has a strange feeling to it when you hold it in your hands. Like it's just ITCHING to both rip through something, and rip itself apart.

name: Faygo-Potion - Aquamarine Ectosugar Bomb
description: This strange bottle of aquamarine slime sloshes around in its container... You're not sure if ghost slime, mercury, and sugar is a good combination.

name: Rainbow Waxbow
description: This rainbow-coloured bowshoots arrows that glow with random colours of light! Be careful not to get too near to the heat, though, or this bow will melt.

name: Stop Sign
description: The entry of your house managed to bring one of these with you. Might as well make some use of it.

name: Spiked Yo-yo
description: A chunky, metallic yo-yo with spikes all along its circumference. Although this is much more useful for imp-smiting than a wooden yo-yo, it's also quite useful for giving yourself accidental cuts.

name: Grog Nozzle
description: Throw a kegger wherever you go.

name: Toothbreaker
description: Lightly glowing boxing gloves made of various luminescent crystals and gems. Wow, they're heavy.

name: High-Frequency Chainsaw
description: The mass-produced weapon wielded by the LQ-84 units, now in the palm of your hand! This chainsaw can rip and shred through just about everything, although bizarrely enough, it seems to excel at stealth kills. Not like that matters to you.

name: Domino Sais
description: These Bakelite Sais aren't very impressive normally, but their periodic chain reaction attacks are much more useful.

name: Blueberry Corn
description: Blueberry flavoured candy corns are surprisingly delicious.

name: The Holy History Book
description: History is written by the victors. God is always the winner, so of course that guy wrote this book. Who knows how much is true anyway.

name: Diamond Edged Ribbon
description: The perfect weapon for slowly cutting through enemies! ...This could use some upgrading... Especially since the diamond is still fake anyway...

name: Three\'s the Lucky Charm Keyblade
description: Great, first Santa, Jack, and now a demented Leprechaun haunt this wrathful weapon. The faint sound of jolly laughter,ghosts, and a fiddle give your enemies an aneurysm.

name: Davy Jones\' Unlocker
description: A gigantic, rusted out key. You suspect that the lock to which it goes sank to the depths of an ocean long ago, but hey, you could probably still open skulls with it. If you can lift it, that is...

name: Ring Key
description: A key shaped like a large ring. No, really. It even has teeth along part of it. Wonder what the lock looks like...

name: Siege Tank Ignition Key
description: This key goes to a giant futuristic tank! Kinda makes you wish you actually had one of those...

name: Lamiakey
description: A breathmint shaped like a key. Now you can unlock your fresher side!

name: Swiss Lockpicker
description: This Swiss army knife has been fitted with a variety of keys and thin instruments perfect for fidgeting with locks and getting doors open. They had to get rid of everything else to make room, though, including the knife part.

name: Key to the Furthest Ring
description: This key can unlock anything and everything: not limited to just locks, but also entire universes, dream bubbles, the deepest thoughts and secrets of horrorterrors and deities alike. And yet you're just going to use it to rob a bank or something aren't you.

name: Hood\'s ACoif
description: Congratulations. Now, not only are you able to move through enemy territory unnoticed, you can also stay comfortably cool while doing so.

name: Path of the Glacial Master IV
description: Your journey is coming close to an end. With the power of swords at your command, you feel almost unstoppable. Almost. The gloves maintain a shade of purple, and the snowcogs are colder than before.

name: Dynacrusher
description: This is one powerful-looking hammer. No enemy's gonna mess around with you when you bring this bad boy out. As an added bonus, it releases a concussive blast on impact, giving it an extra punch!

name: Prismatech Steel Rainbow-Bow
description: This strange mixture of technology and magic has resulted in a computerized steel limb of the bow, and a wiry bowstring that shoots high-powered rainbow lasers.

name: Darkspectrum Lich Wings
description: These strange cosplay wings glitter with every colour of the rainbow, and yet are surrounded by an ominous dark aura.

name: Net-Knives
description: You... you aren't sure how you are supposed to surf the net with these without grievously injuring yourself at all, let alone while in combat, but you guess you can try.

name: Angry Marine Jump Pack
description: The standard issue Angry Marines variant on the jump pack, used more for slamming down than jumping up. Should help you get in the way of attacks though.

name: Lich\'s Phylaxery
description: As you stare into the shadowy frat shades of this mysterious skull, you hear whispers. Dark, empowering whispers of the Shadow Bro.

name: The New iSweep
description: The PV iSweep has been completely retrofitted with cutting-edge MR technology to combine the fan-favorite shocking power with bass that THROWS. Too bad the battery sucks.

name: Reaping Knives
description: Two miniature farming scythes with their blades rotated 90 degrees to come straight out of the hilt.

name: Scarf Knives
description: You've heard of things like rope darts, but really? Using two scarves, with knives attached to the end, at the same time?

name: Silver Knives
description: These sterling silver knives more than make up for the loss of sharpness with their sheer weight.

name: Dual War Victorinox
description: These unusually large Swiss army knives add imp-cutting to their array of features.

name: Acoustic Knives
description: These knives have uncomfortable hilts in the shape of acoustic guitars. With a button press strings inside the hollow blades vibrate and produce music, or rather, noise. It doesn't sound very good. It does cause the blades to vibrate for increased damage though.

name: Bayonetx2 Acoustic Guitar
description: This acoustic guitar has two knives attached to its headstock, making it a sort of musical spear.

name: Martial Blazer
description: For those times when you need to look good while kicking ass, this attractively tailored black uniform will do the trick.

name: Star Scarf
description: This may be a pretty bad position from which to navigate from but it makes an impressive wardrobe addition.

name: Chione\'s Frosttrident
description: This chilly ice trident glimmers with a coating of snow, and reminds you of a white Christmas back on your homeworld.

name: Moon Powered Bow
description: This pink, moon-themed bow shoots heart-shaped arrows that are surprisingly deadly.

name: Midnight Sai
description: This sai is extra good at stabbing things. And it has a sweet card motif, too!

name: Bone Fork
description: Pierce an underling's bones with a bone!

name: Cardigan
description: An open-front sweater of itchy wool and wooden buttons. Everything you need to take 'yo grandpa's style, you look incredible.

name: White Mage Gloves
description: These soda-soaked gloves have surprising healing properties.

name: Head Breaker
description: A power-packed pistol that shoots cue sticks at high speeds, making it more of a spear gun now that you think about it. Imp head, corner pocket.

name: Lord of Lizard\'s Immense Science Robotic Science Elemental Sci-Mount of Reptilian Sciencey Science
description: Why fight with a weapon in your hands when you can instead ride one into battle! This giant robotic lizard uses SCIENCE to instill fear into your foes, as well as crushing them as you desire. Note: Just because you aren't wielding it in your hands doesn't mean that you have hands free. You still have to control it!

name: The Symphonic Shotgun
description: They say music is the universal language... Pfft. With THIS baby, the only communication skills you'll need are some good old fashioned Shotgun Diplomacy. And... maybe some earplugs for those screechy chords.

name: Tentirifle
description: This thing is making weird whisph.... fthna'gagtath nyeh fmw'atmuiue Flthlu gosthgnyah hg gigrth wau m ptblawaufh gbeu wb'brub fthhh.

name: Soul Gashelm
description: With this strange amalgamation of a gasmask and armet on, you can hear the voices of long-dead chivalrous heroes asking you if you're their mummy.

name: Ugly Christmas Old-Man Coat
description: Oh my god you can hardly distinguish one pattern on this hideous thing from another. And there... seems to be an actual candy cane tangled in the wool sticking out of the jacket's lower chest, but you were so distracted by the blocks of conflicting color that you hardly noticed it.

name: Helm of the Shadow Bro
description: The helmet supposedly worn by the Dark Lord of Pounding Shots. Even now it courses with demonic beer pong magics.

name: The New iSweep: Forever
description: The apex in modern smartbroom technology. The new power source allows the iSweep to operate at max power for over 40 dungeons no problem.

name: Hood\'s Sooth-ACoif
description: Wearing this magical, air-conditioned hood allows you to view any area in the Incipisphere!

name: Emptiness\'s Glasses
description: These glasses are so dark they consume your gaze. Your fears and pleasures drain away leaving you placid as a tentacled jellyfish floating in the void. Yet there is a subtle shimmer on the round lenses, and you can even see light through them after your eyes have adjusted. Like spots of light filtering through thick canopies. You think the light is hope.

name: Fate\'s Hand
description: No matter how many times you shuffle and draw, you always get the same card. Fate has decided your path. The only question is: Which card did you draw?

name: The Vast Hudda
description: With this, you can send out a battlecry that will have everyone in earshot dousing themselves in questionable, flame-retardant fluids.

name: Royal Retaliation
description: The best defense is a good offense and what's better than a shield with plastic explosives smeared on the face?

name: Baah-mi-naah-mi-caahn
description: A rather well-read and slightly demonic sheep who has an unfortunately explosive temper. Be careful how you press his buttons.

name: White Broom of Dawn
description: This is a very powerful, magical broom you suppose. But more than that it's very comfortable to lean on it while you think. You're sure that if you hold on and follow what feels right victory will unfold before you.

name: Purple Suit
description: So shiny it hurts the eyes. It's very strong, despite appearances.

name: Uranium Minecraft Sword
description: Sharp sword, and a nightlight! Great for surviving the hostilities of the night, but you might not want to hold this for too long.

name: HAZMAT suit
description: All the shadiness of a trench coat with the protection of a gasmask. WARNING: Does not protect against bites.

name: Celestial Dilation
description: When one of these is thrown, it warps through time to arrive before it left. With the right timing, you can deliver the fury of a supernova to your opponent's face before they even see you move.

name: Lion Tamer
description: This stool isn't much help against a vicious lion, but at least you have the whip to go with it! Let's just hope the beast isn't hungry for leather...

name: Pole-Scythe of Reaching
description: This is the sniper of melee weapons. What you lose in speed you gain in reach. The blade is also edged in green, for some reason.

name: Chicken Noodle Soup
description: This noodly soup has a rich broth that is sure to cure a cold!

name: Elixir Soup
description: Made by your grandmother, this nutritious soup chock full of magical ingredients is also quite delicious!

name: Ancient Amethyst Sword
description: An ancient sword embedded with an amethyst gem. It's made of a bit of hard material, and the amethyst feels really cold.

name: Wristpiano
description: A piano you can wear on your wrist! Sadly, the keys are too small to play.

name: Brown Paint
description: This brown paint looks like watery mud... yuck.

name: Blue Key
description: This key is blue! It probably held its breath too long. The suspense of what was behind the door killed it because you took too long to unlock it. Good job.

name: Crimson Key
description: This key is red! It's probably mad at you because you're taking the time to read some silly description instead of unlocking a door already.

name: Yellow Key
description: This key is yellow! Actually, a lot of keys are yellow already, so what makes this one so special anyway?

name: Orange Key
description: This key is orange! Orange you glad it's not some boring color like brown or gray?

name: Green Key
description: This key is green! It's probably sick of you not opening any doors with it.

name: Purple Key
description: This key is purple! That makes it stronger than all of the other colored keys, obviously.

name: Indigo Key
description: This key is indigo! If you find a similarly colored door, you can probably put this key indigo through it.

name: Brown Key
description: This key is brown! Be careful not to drop it in a swamp, you may never find it again.

name: Red/Blue Striped Paint
description: No matter how much you stir the paint, the two colors never completely mix. The red and blue stripes sit separately in the can, alongside each other.

name: Blue/Yellow Striped Paint
description: No matter how much you stir the paint, the two colors never completely mix. The blue and yellow stripes sit separately in the can, alongside each other.

name: Yellow/Red Striped Paint
description: No matter how much you stir the paint, the two colors never completely mix. The yellow and red stripes sit separately in the can, alongside each other.

name: Rainbow Paint
description: Paint that's striped with all the colors of the rainbow. You don't think that's how paint works, but the idea of easily painting your house in rainbow is just too awesome for you to care.

name: Rainbow Key
description: It's a key patterned with all the colors of the rainbow. Maybe it'll unlock a magical land full of unicorns and fairies!

name: Black Key
description: This key is black! It's not that much different from any other color key, though. All keys were created equal, after all.

name: White Key
description: This key is white! Almost as if its just seen a ghost or something. Or maybe it IS a ghost!

name: Murky Milk
description: This is some seriously gray milk. You have no idea what this would do to you if you drank it.

name: Gray Key
description: This key is gray! What a very boring color. You wouldn't be surprised if the door it unlocked contained nothing interesting.

name: Ironically Cool Reindeer Cardigan
description: This shit-brown old-man sweater has a blocky reindeer pattern knitted all around its sides. But ultimately retro is back and wearing this lets everyone know you have the confidence to go against the in-style and wear what everyone else is starting to wear too.

name: Roller Broomstick of the Green Dawn
description: This stick is clearly very, very powerful. And great for cleaning even carpets. You find that a thoroughly cleaned room can really liven up the people inside it, much like unleashing the power of the green sun can really liven up the battlefields of Skaia.

name: Sparkledust Fairy Sweeper
description: A pretty broom that can fly (albeit without you on it) and sprinkle pixie dust that has no effect on others whatsoever.

name: Midnight Crew Pillow
description: Make her a pillow of the Midnight Crew.

name: Conductor\'s Scalpel
description: A conductor baton with a small blade at the end, for cuing in musical instruments with surgical precision.

name: Chainblades
description: Two hiltless blades connected by a chain. It'd be like Bruce Lee meets Musashi, if only you could figure out how to hold them. Possibly the worst idea anyone has ever had.

name: Radioactive Flamers
description: Black finger-less gloves that sport a dome on the back. The dome houses a chunk of uranium used to power the glove's flame controlling properties, bringing it to a whole new level!

name: Compbook
description: A notebook combined with a computer. It has wifi, google chrome, everything that you need/want.

name: Call of Duty Black Ops Disc
description: Call of Duty Black Ops. It's a bit scratched after you moved your console while the disc was still inside.

name: Raking Gloves
description: Fighting gloves with rake ends on it. Great for itches.

name: Crystal Map Shuriken
description: It's a slightly larger shuriken with a smooth white look. Pink translucent shapes that look like the continents are on it, although it seems there wasn't enough space for all of them. Nice for looks, but too fragile for serious fighting.

name: Globerella
description: An Umbrella. The top has the western hemisphere on it. The handle has a sphere on the tip, with what looks like a miniature earth.

name: 4 of Hearts / Quadrant Keyblade
description: This time of year, love is in the air... as well as Christmas, Halloween, and St. Patty's Day when you're wielding this keyblade.

name: Lich\'s Sooth-ACoif
description: This shadowy magic hood allows you to comfortably view everything in your session, while looking like some evil undead mage.

name: The Slimy Observer
description: This bulbous bat breaks your concentration with its eternal disconcerting stare. It's searing into your mind with vivid images of its multidimensional heart. Try to be careful with that! Jegus!

name: Glowing Sphere
description: A small glowing sphere of light that never goes out. Holding it makes you feel lucky.

name: Bottle of Toxins
description: A small bottle filled with a variety of deadly toxins. You probably shouldn't open this, especially if the little green skull on the bottle means anything.

name: Compu-Helmet
description: A helmet with a visor that functions as a computer monitor. It is controlled by the user's mind to allow for hands-free operating.

name: Verdant Stamptet
description: A set of stamps with magical life-infused powers, capable of doing anything from patching up your wounds to turning your enemies into a new national forest.

name: Gamelon School Blazer
description: You feel like a Japanese school boy wearing this, one who might also be a princess taking matters into her own hands and exploring a foreign kingdom to rescue her father, uncle, and main love interest. Anime sure is weird.

name: Maybe Water-repelling Wand of the Wrathful Wizard
description: This wand(er, umbrella?) once belonged to a very angry, and incredibly powerful wizard, who absolutely hated water. Maybe magic is real?!?

name: Astrologer\'s Fire-Breathing Broomstick
description: You're a bad mo' fo' with a flamethrower of a cleaning tool. You'll accost your fortune and blast your way through obstacles. Whether or not it burns your hands, you'll decide your future and make it come true. This broom gets ashes everywhere.

name: Spacial Compass
description: This strange black compass bears a white spiral symbol in the middle, instead of a needle... which pretty much renders it useless. Nevertheless, you feel like you have a better grasp of where you are in the universe when you hold it.

name: Dream Feather
description: When holding this luminescent feather, all your hopes and dreams from your childhood come back to you, and you feel as if anything is possible if you believe it is.

name: Blood Vial
description: This small vial of deep red blood seems to remind you of all your past friendships and bonds.

name: Hammer of Eden
description: This very hammer has been fabled to have been used to form our world on the eternal infernal forge. Now you can use it to whallop imps. Nice.

name: Ancient Stamptet of Legend
description: A series of ancient stamps, forgotten by time itself. The power within them, however, is far beyond aging or next-day delivery. No, these stamps go above and beyond the call of duty to deliver any package through sun, rain, hail, sleet, or snow. And it just so happens that the package you need them to deliver is DEATH.

name: Retractable Chain Blades
description: This item is the product of multiple years of physical engineering by a bunch of nerds. Its self-sharpening blades can rend even the most stubborn foes to mincemeat in mere minutes. Try not to tear the leather grip, okay?

name: Anvilope
description: I'm not sure why you thought this was a good idea; you can't even get up. Gives new meaning to the term "hardheaded," though.

name: 8lue Fairy Shard
description: It's said that when you are in the 8addest of 8r8ks you just have to wish upon a star with all your might, and the 8lue Fairy will guide you to victory.

name: Embroidered Pulpurea Scarf
description: This silky rosewood sash is decorated with a rich rosy pattern in cardinal thread and carried an aroma of flowers.

name: Commander\'s Sash
description: A strip of red velvet that symbolizes leadership and accomplishment. But also tragedy.

name: Yellow Stole
description: This long, florescent scarf looks gleeful and positive.

name: Translucent Black Rebozo
description: This ridiculously long scarf seems to hardly be there.

name: Boston Harbor Scarf
description: This warm knit hugs you tightly, and would make you look like a passionate and dedicated student of the arts.

name: Neckerchief
description: This is a sash of someone free as the clouds. Someone with this could confidently survive away from the security and convenience of societal bonds, a carefree as the wind!

name: Itchy Red Scarf
description: This bright knit looks very vintage and itches like hell. Perfect for surviving the late fall or the night in an unheated apartment. It has needles stuck in its weave, like someone was crawling though bushes with it...

name: Majora\'s Wand
description: This new wand has even more power then the simple Pottermore wand you used to have. Yet somehow, it also seems a bit more sinister, and also maybe a tiny bit darker.

name: Pink Paint
description: A can of lovely pink paint. Such a bright and cheerful color!

name: Frozen Sponge Cake
description: A sponge cake that's been in the freezer since before you were born. It's harder than most rocks.

name: Betty Crocker Chocolate Cake Mix
description: A box of cake mix. You probably shouldn't eat it without baking the cake first, but the temptation is still there...

name: More Cake
description: A cake that's twice as big as most cakes. Double the cake for the same inventory space!

name: More Cake Mix
description: A bunch of cake mix for making a cake of a rather absurd size. Maybe you could split it into several cakes? .... naaaah.

name: Oh God More Cake
description: It's a neverending stream of cakes raining from the sky. How you even managed to captchalogue it is beyond mortal comprehension.

name: Breezy Cake
description: A birthday cake with large holes in it that make different noises when the wind blows through them. Blowing out the candles has never been more fun!

name: Windy Cake Shooter
description: A throwback to old peashooters of your youth, this tube amplifies your breath to propel pieces of cake toward your enemies at bullet-like velocity.

name: Cow Cake
description: A massive cake made from every piece of a cow's rancid corpse. It's hard not to vomit while carrying it.

name: Cakeburger
description: A massive hamburger made with cakes instead of buns. This looks really gross, but you can't help but take a bite...

name: Beef Cake
description: A giant cake made of cooked beef. What were you expecting?

name: Frozen Brick Cake
description: You are entirely sure that this cake is just as hard as stone now. It barely even qualifies as cake, considering that you could try to build a house out of it...

name: Grandma\'s Festive Cake
description: An old cake your grandma used to make. It tastes terrible, but at least it's not a fruitcake, right?

name: Frozen Cake Wreath
description: A wreath made entirely out of frozen cake. You should probably eat it or something before it thaws.

name: Cake Clock
description: A cake with a working clock face made of frosting. You aren't sure if the insides are cake or not, and you aren't sure if you want to find out.

name: Old-School Betty Crocker Chocolate Cake Mix
description: A box of cake mix from what appears to be 1950, still proudly bearing the Betty Crocker logo.

name: Unfrozen Sponge Cake
description: A delicious sponge cake that will eventually be frozen. Maybe. Time travel's hard, ok?

name: Burthdy CAEK
description: a CAEK for ur burthday. eat up man.

name: Jungle Cake
description: A cake covered in a variety of foliage. It would be kind of pretty if the venus fly trap didn't keep trying to eat your nose. And don't even think of eating it, it probably tastes like dirt.

name: Braincake
description: A cake that's either made out of brains or is iced to make it look like it was. You don't have any particular desire to figure out which.

name: Angry Cake
description: You don't even know how this cake tastes - whenever anything gets close, it lets loose a terribly angry roar that scares everything away. You could probably make a few dozen and use them to secure your home against imps if you get some earplugs.

name: Frozen Cake Disc
description: A disc made out of frozen sponge cake. It doesn't look that appetizing, though.

name: Fruitcake Gushers - Grandma\'s Favorite Flavour
description: A bunch of tiny 'fruit'cakes that taste like the fruitcake your dad used to use as a doorstop. Gross.

name: Uplifting Cake
description: A cake that makes you feel hopeful when you eat it in the bleakest of times. Obviously the best thing to do with such a cake is to bash imps over the head with it.

name: Dimensional Cake
description: A small cake that seems to fade in and out between various planes of existence, occasionally becoming 1- or 2-dimensional for seemingly no reason.

name: Vaccum Cake
description: A cake shell that contains a vacuum inside. Whenever the shell is broken, the vacuum sucks in whatever is nearby before the cake patches itself up magically.

name: Toxin Cake
description: A small green cake loaded with most poisons known to man, and a few that weren't until now. You probably shouldn't eat it.

name: Bleeding Cake
description: A cake that seems to be always bleeding, even when you don't cut into it. It's really gross.

name: Luminescent Cake
description: A yellow cake that always lets off a slight glow. You feel slightly luckier whenever you eat a slice.

name: Vongola\'s Dreams
description: Black finger-less gloves that have a blue ring permanently attached to the sleeve for the middle finger. The back of the glove sports a dome with a large "X" mark on it. Inside the dome, one can see the outline of a creature made with pure flame. With enough willpower, one can summon the creature to aide one in battle!

name: Monocromatic Holo-Projector
description: This machine looks a lot less complex; no fancy dials, no beeping lights everywhere, just a simple, user-friendly hard-light projector. This simplicity extends to the holographic units created with it, as they appear to have reached a state of inner balance, increasing their strength and focus.

name: Oglogoth\'s Hypodermics
description: Two long black hypodermic needles glowing with the purple energy of something DARK. They were rumored to have been created by doctors dabbling in the DARK ARTS withe intention of extracting LIFE energy to feed some MONSTROUS HUNGER. They seem to take the shape of a menacing caduceus.

name: Spuddly Sergeant Spiral Coat of Skaia
description: Gee Willikers! Your overcoat now exudes the moxy and determination of a certain spud. Oh, it also gives you a good defense.

name: Rose-Distortion Cane
description: The power to screw everything up plus the bonus of it being pink!

name: The Overseer-Approved Egg Beater
description: Just an eggbeater with a stamp that has a thumbs up and lettering that says: "Personally approved by The Overseer!" That and it's 3 inches wider to fit the stamp.

name: Aquamarine
description: This transparent light blue colored gemstone would be worth a pretty penny back on earth. It also apparently imbues travelers with good luck?

name: IDK
description: this description is so shitty it causes your opponents to whither as the sheer sight of it

name: Emerald
description: This large, transparent green gemstone would be worth a fortune back on earth. It also supposedly enhances one's well being.

name: Ruby
description: This large, transparent red gemstone would be worth a fortune back on earth. It also supposedly contains the power of the cosmos.

name: Sapphire
description: This large, transparent blue gemstone would be worth a fortune back on earth. It also supposedly protects travelers and seekers.

name: Diamond
description: This large, bright clear gemstone would be worth a large fortune back on earth. It also supposedly increases one's focus.

name: Topaz
description: This large, transparent golden gemstone would be worth a fortune back on earth. It supposedly protects the holder of the gem.

name: Amethyst
description: This large, transparent purple gemstone would be worth a fortune back on earth. It also supposedly has the power to make one more nimble.

name: Kirigiri Gloves
description: These black gloves seem to increase your cleverness when worn. Like you could solve any mystery. They have the added effect of keeping you unnaturally calm and nonchalant as you thoroughly examine corpses.

name: Chione\'s Darkmoon Frosttrident
description: Holding this frozen, shadowy trident reminds you of Christmas Eve. When you shake it, tiny snowflakes float to the ground.

name: Time Eater
description: Made from the bone of a dinosaur and the pocketwatch of a 1840's gentleman, no time traveling food connoisseur would be caught dead without one!

name: Electrified Dice
description: These dice are attracted to each other, and when you touch them, you hair stands on end. So you don't know why you alchemized them.

name: March of the Renegade Twins
description: The reincarnation of the souls of twin musicians drafted into their country's civil war on opposite sides. Both were killed for treason upon refusing to fight each other. Playing this bombards your foes with the pain and torment these two faced.

name: Holstered Timestabbing Thorn
description: A flashy green knife in an elegant knife holster. When thrown, it travels backwards through time and hits an enemy before the battle even started. Somehow it always ends up back in the holster ready for another throw afterwards.

name: Time-Computing Shades
description: These shades make it really easy to keep track of timing things. Though not even the most efficiency obsessed businessman would find a use for half of these functions.

name: Star Hour Scarf
description: The stars on this scarf are arranged in an hour glass pattern and slowly move across the fabric from one end to the other.

name: Adventurer\'s Techhat
description: A dashing, dusty and somewhat singed hat suitable for dungeon delving that also serves as a handy portable computer.

name: Midnight God Suit
description: A black suit patterned after your god tier outfit that makes you feel like a hero of a very high degree.

name: x1
description: Wait. Is this for real, or is it a bug? You didn't think you could possess the concept of quantity itself... you should probably keep this a secret.

name: Strong-Willed Skaian Superspud
description: Upon learning that its side was destined to lose in this grand war, our potato refused to accept its fate. Through the power of sheer determination, this earthen vegetable becomes even stronger, vowing to break the mold and shape its own destiny!

name: Human Cannonball Cap
description: This brightly-colored, gigantic wig was clearly designed to create a flashy show as its wearer is shot out of a cannon at spine-crushing speeds to smash through brick walls. The fact that it's as hard as steel and is covered in spikes certainly helps with that last bit.

name: Omni Flash Orb
description: Staring into the core of this infinitely-flashing orb will reveal to the beholder every form of life in the universe simultaneously. Any human brain subjected to such impossibly limitless stimuli would shut down in an instant, unable to keep up. Upon regaining consciousness, the wielder will be both dumbfounded and enlightened.

name: Mr. Baseball Cap
description: It is said to have been given to your friend by a famous player at the ballpark. You're not sure what that means, since you just made it yourself.

name: Pyrazor Ball
description: A razor ball that leaves a trail of flame wherever it is dribbled or thrown. Unfortunately, doing either of those things usually inflicts the wielder with burning cuts.

name: Martial Mail Blazer
description: An attractively tailored black uniform with a hidden mail layer.

name: Clarke\'s Dagger
description: This sufficiently advanced knife is obviously a potent athame practically dripping in powerful dweomers. Of course youll probably arrange for it to be dripping in monster blood as well soon. Also effective at carving ineffective Elbereth engravings.

name: Variable Setting Timestabbing Thorn
description: A flashy green knife with a dial-able clock face. When thrown, it is displaced in time letting it hit an enemy unexpectedly. The dial lets you adjust how far back or forward the knife will be displaced. Good luck finding it if you miss though!

name: Pharaoh\'s Whip
description: Dating back to Ancient Egypt, this little babe was the main motivator of the people to get the pyramids done before Ra's boat for the underworld left. The hilt of gold was quite inspiring too.

name: Kartikeya\'s Spword
description: Combined with powerful shield, the void weapon has been enlarged to have stronger hits, sharper slices, and more deadly dark ooze. Not much of a shield, though. Sucks for you, dude.

name: UAC Spectral Spherehelm
description: With the added manliness, the constant spinning, glowing, and wisp vortex around your head that gives you that terrible helmet hair has increased in power, making hits directed to your head easily deflected.

name: Vongola\'s Wings
description: A black, finger-less glove that is powered by your inner will and uranium! There's so much power in it that it'll give you WINGS~

name: Dragon Axe
description: The natural power and strength of the Dragons is now in your hands, their energy channels through the axe you now hold! ...Okay maybe that was a little over dramatic, but its still a pretty good axe.

name: Great Fairy\'s Tears
description: This enchanted water created by the Great Fairy herself is filled with incredibly powerful magic.

name: 4 of Frogs / Saber Croak
description: Frogs ain't a real suit and sabers don't croak!

name: Massive Frozen Anchor Cake
description: A gigantic cake shaped like an anchor and frozen for what you estimate to be several eons. You aren't entirely sure what purpose it was meant to serve, but now you use it to whack stuff over the head.

name: Cake Stamp
description: A stamp with a little picture of a cake on it.

name: Star Kingdom Cake
description: This is rumored to be the cake Peach was making for Mario before she got kidnapped. Again. But now it's YOURS and that stupid plumber isn't getting any.

name: Cakechipper
description: A woodchipper made of cake. It's... actually pretty bad at chipping wood now. As well as anything else.

name: Vodcake
description: A cake filled with so much potato booze you could probably drown in it. You probably shouldn't eat it, but what the hell, right?

name: Golden Sword of Light
description: Magic increasing the power of this sword's swing twofold, its true power lies in the skyward strike, which seems to have been improved exponentially.

name: Caketellite
description: A satellite made of cake, presumably so astronauts wouldn't starve if they accidentally ran out of food in orbit.

name: Nuclear Cake Turbine
description: A turbine that takes in uranium and produces cakes at a rather alarming pace. You probably shouldn't eat the cakes, delicious though they look - they're probably radioactive.

name: Cake Slice / 2 of Cakes
description: A very pointy cake slice and a very low number in a card suit that doesn't even exist.

name: Cake Slice on a Stick / 4 of Cakes
description: The pointy cake slice is now on a long stick, so it has a little bit more reach. Cakes still isn't a valid card suit, though.

name: Frozen Sponge Crosshairs
description: A frozen spongecake replica of an infamous rifle. It can't shoot anything, but you could probably just butt imps over the head with it...

name: Cakeridan
description: A cake that seems to whine at you whenever you aren't looking at it. It's decorated with little rifles and wands, and oddly enough came pre-alchemized with a large, sloppy cut down the middle.

name: Totem Lathe
description: You can insert up to two cards in the device's slot, carving a blank cruxite dowel with a code.

name: Alchemiter
description: You can place a cruxite dowel on the smaller platform, and the device will scan its surface and produce the item with that code. If you have the grist, that is.

name: Punch Designix
description: You can use this to punch a captchalogue card with a given 8-digit code.

name: Sherlock\'s Observation Cake
description: A cake enchanted with Sherlock-like observation powers. You aren't entirely sure it does what you think it does, though, so you're probably safer just hitting imps with it.

name: Lime Time Golden Cake Baker
description: You aren't sure if you've ever tasted lime-flavored cake before, but after seeing this amazing appliance you certainly want to try!

name: vvrisKACE
description: a shitty cake mde from ded troll corps. it tasts like asshol.

name: Nancho Birthday Cake
description: Well it's obviously someone else's birthday cake, because you're pretty sure it's NACHO BIRTHDAY CAKE! Shitty puns aside, this thing tastes like someone took perfectly good cake batter and mixed in finely ground Doritos. You're probably better off hitting things with it than you are eating it.

name: Caxe / 3 of Cakes
description: An axe with a pointy-looking cake slice instead of a head. You can't really see this being more useful, and cakes aren't a valid card suit?

name: Ornchake, Destroyer of Arteries
description: A large axe made of a form of highly concentrated cake. Whether consumed or used to chop, you can be confident in the fact that any arteries involved will probably not be the same.

name: Omnom, Destroyer of Childhoods
description: A combination axe and digging tool made entirely out of incredibly sweet cake. Such cake is said to completely obliterate any childhood memories in favor of exquisite memories of consuming the cake, even when you haven't eaten any of it. Use it carefully.

name: Cakel Hammer
description: A hammer that would remind you of a destroyed civilization if it were not made entirely of cake. Instead, it's just delicious.

name: Skeletor\'s Head
description: It goes 'myeeeah' every time you swing it.

name: Scissorblade
description: It doesn't look the the blades of this fancy pair of elongated scissors come apart, but the edges have been crafted to razor sharpness. Possibly not the best thing to cut hair with.

name: Shitty Enchanted Fancy Bladed Slimebouncer of Knitting
description: You create some... Hammer thing with needles poking out? What the fuck is this exactly? At least it will work... Hopefully...

name: Atomic Frisbee
description: A frisbee with two chemical knives sticking out of the side. It's surprisingly lightweight, and very lethal.

name: Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Pan
description: Amazing. You believe this LoZ-styled frying pan has super special powers. In reality, it's just a neat frying pan.

name: Tron Hoodie
description: A tech-y hoodie made of metal and lights. It surprisingly works well as a form of armor, and it's super stylish too.

name: Vriscake
description: A blue cake with blue icing covered in little bits of glowing blue fluorite. That stuff's probably toxic, but WHO CARES LET'S EAT IT ANYWAYS

name: Orange Dragon Cosplay
description: A slightly modified dragon LARPing outfit. And by slightly modified you mean painted orange. Still adorabloodthirsrty, though.

name: Homemade Gymnastics Ribbon Wand
description: An elegant yet powerful rainbow-colored wand that promises to assist you in your performances and magic at the same time, for the aspiring wizard gymnast - oh, who are you kidding? This is just a piece of cardboard with a ribbon tied to one end.

name: K.K. Mic Stand
description: A microphone stand designed with the world renowned K.K. Slider in mind. You can just feel the famous radiating off it. You know, despite the fact that it's just cheap fan merch.

name: Lunchmuffs
description: Finally, an easy hands-free computing solution that keeps your ears warm, and looks amazing to boot!

name: Godel, Escher, Bach: an Eternal Golden Braid
description: A hefty tome on computer science and self-reference by Douglas Hofstadter. http://xkcd.com/917/

name: Needlessly Electric Staff
description: Zappity zap, an electric staff!

name: 3x Skull Hammer
description: Creep out your enemies three times the amount.

name: Kitty\'s Lightstaff
description: What appears to be a telescoping staff which is incapable of collapsing with a glowing crystal at the top reveals itself as also capable of shooting sweet lasers with boosted power from being concentrated through a lens and then imbued with holiness by the crystal.

name: Mocha Hot Chocolate
description: This gourmet hot chocolate is perfect for the winter months.

name: Meteor Fragment
description: A piece of a meteor that crashed into earth. You've had it for a long time and there might be something special about it...

name: Extra-Purple Amethyst
description: This gemstone is just... so... PURPLE. What secret powers could it contain?

name: Twin Acrus
description: Eye-catching dual blades. They release lightning that makes them shine even brighter.

name: Magenterator
description: This gemstone-infused generator harnesses the power of purple energy to fuel whatever it's plugged into. You have no idea where this purple energy comes from, but it's efficient as hell!

name: Magentaggrevator
description: The purple generator has swollen with rage and is now producing ten times as much energy as before. You had no idea the color purple had so much potential... just keep an eye on it, this thing looks about as unstable as a nuclear reactor.

name: Emerald Laser Ninjato
description: A smaller copy of a lightsaber with a green blade and comfortable green felt hilt. It's ability to cut through or parry almost any weapon makes it ideal for offhand use while it's ability to turn off the blade at a button press is excellent for stealth.

name: Ectoberry Corn
description: Twice as blue as a conventional blueberry corn and twice as delicious. Incidentally capable of healing serious wounds.

name: Captchalogue Card
description: Your primary method of storage. Totally useless outside of a Fetch Modus... or is it?

name: Cruxite Dowel
description: A cylinder made out of a crystalline material known as Cruxite. Your Cruxtruder seems to be able to produce an infinite number of these.

name: GristTorrent CD
description: Contains some software that gives you the ability to wire grist to other SBURB players.

name: Holopad
description: When a punched card or Cruxite totem is used with this device, it displays a holographic version of the item it corresponds to. Perfect for when you want to know what an item is without spending your hard-earned grist!

name: Jumper Block Extension
description: A gigantic captchalogue-card-shaped device that seems to be able to connect to your Alchemiter. It's useless on its own, but maybe those eight plugs on the top are for something?

name: Punch Card Shunt
description: A red captchalogue-card-shaped device which contains a thin slot on the front. Judging from the plugin on the bottom, you think this might be a component of a larger device.

name: Intellibeam Laserstation
description: This machine seems to be capable of reading captcha codes with 100% accuracy. Seems rather useless, but this is honestly no small feat.

name: Suit of Time Armor
description: This scarlet suit of armor with a continuously rotating gear on the breastplate regenerates by swapping in versions from up or down the time stream. Just be prepared to have it suddenly develop damage.

name: Tron Phylactery
description: Store your soul and identity in the same place like a sensible person. Not that someone like you would resort to such dark magics.

name: Time-Computing Holographic Shades
description: These shades are perfect for people who have an improbably amount of requirements in timing things and have no time for messing around with questionable hands-free interfaces.

name: Fancy Santa Hat
description: It's time to get into the holiday spirit, and you have JUST the hat for it... and it sparkles too!

name: Green Apple Popbrush
description: It seems to splatter everything with a bright green paint that pops when it lands. Talk about pop art!

name: Pile of Gold Coins
description: This is a gigantic mound of gold coins... pretty, but absolutely useless here in the Incipisphere.

name: Dark Chocolate Mocha Hot Chocolate
description: This dark, chocolate, mocha-flavoured beverage is just so... dark... and chocolatey, and it tastes slightly like very dark coffee... That's really all there is to say about this.

name: Self-Lighting Frying Pan
description: Ever get an undeniable sudden craving for fried sausages, but find yourself with a pan but no hob? No worries! This step forward in pan technology lights without any hob necessary, and you can cook your sausages as you walk! This, my friend, is the future.

name: Chione\'s Darkmoon-Chocolate Frosttrident
description: This icy trident, in addition to ice and shadow powers, can somehow shoot hot fountains of a mocha-flavoured beverage at your enemies... or into your mouth, you guess.

name: Miniature Steam Engine
description: Using this Steam Engine, you will be able to run your weapons on STEAM POWER!

name: Miniature Nuclear Reactor
description: This portable nuclear reactor could power an electromagnet for several lifetimes, or some battle armor for a couple hours.

name: Mr. Fusion
description: This portable fusion reactor will allow you to power your computer and time traveling car with garbage alone!

name: Particle Accelerator
description: Using this high tech device, you can create rare atomic isotopes at home!

name: Stabilized Roentgenium
description: Somehow, this is a non-radioactive version of Roentgenium... you guess this might be useful?

name: Enchanted Roentgenium
description: Discovering the effect magic has with copper, silver and gold, you have decided to turn your studies to making something with a bit more of an oomph to it.

name: Spacetime Muncher
description: This fork transcends the limitations of the three corporeal dimensions, allowing you to eat the fabric of reality. Whether you'll survive such comsumption is another matter entirely.

name: Rubber Whip
description: A short whip made of rubber. Makes a red mark on your skin and hurts a bit, but that's all.

name: Dwemer Metal Ingot
description: This creation of this metal is a secret, only known to the Deep Folk.

name: Chione\'s Darkmoon-Chocolate Frosttrident of the Deep Folk
description: This strange, snow-covered metal seems to emit an aura of shadow, and smells faintly of coffee and chocolate.

name: Captain\'s Tactical Hat
description: This hat combines a potent symbol of authority with an impressive integral computer focusing on battlefield calculations. Of course someone unlikely to command troops in battle might find its ability to keep sun and rain out of their face and provide internet access more useful.

name: Double Laser Trigger
description: Two laser pistols with attached under-barrel laser knives.

name: Knife of Bowies
description: Channel the power of two Bowies whether you are cutting with this knife or singing.

name: Glass Bow of Void
description: A hollow glass bow filled with an odd dark blue liquid that doesn't seem entirely there. In case the question of how to draw this wasn't puzzling enough it's also missing a string.

name: Golden Hue Pen
description: A pen that contains exactly 4 different shades of gold, you wonder how this is even possible since gold is a shade in it's self... but somehow it worked

name: Holy Quadrant Pen
description: This pen is known for making everyone around it quite "infatuated" with everyone else, the reason for this is neither here nor there.

name: Big Wooden Pen
description: This pen is quite big. However, it is surprisingly accurate. This may or may not have been dialogue spoken by a female member of your species.

name: UNIFORN PEN
description: This is just horrific to look at...

name: Philosophical Prediction Pen
description: This pen is thought to have power over the future, by taking advantage of causal determinism. Or at least, you THINK that's how it works. It's the thought that counts.

name: Dragonskull Shovel
description: A shovel crafted out of a dragon's skull, a couple bits of its spine, and well-tempered steel.

name: Lamptop
description: Her fingers are the mean lil beaks of furirous woodpeckers. Those digits rain danger on this hapless lamptop.

name: My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic Poster
description: This is a poster of the Popular TV show and internet phenomenon 'My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic'.

name: Holy Hand Grenade
description: And the Lord spake, saying, "First shalt thou take out the Holy Pin. Then shalt thou count to three, no more, no less. Three shall be the number thou shalt count, and the number of the counting shall be three. Four shalt thou not count, neither count thou two, excepting that thou then proceed to three. Five is right out. Once the number three, being the third number, be reached, then lobbest thou thy Holy Hand Grenade of Antioch towards thy foe, who, being naughty in my sight, shall snuff it."

name: 3d(s) Goggles
description: Pros: Your gaming is now even more portable, and the 3D is much clearer and easier to see! Cons: It is MUCH more straining on your eyes than before. You probably won't last 10 minutes playing it.

name: Virus Imprinted CD
description: From what the disk says, This CD is hella harmful to your computer. Why would you even keep something like this around?

name: Unusable Computer
description: Great! You just ruined your computer. What did you go and do that for anyways?

name: Troll Mask
description: Now you can go around trolling not only your friends, But every Imp and Ogre you come across! You're sure to get a kick out of this.

name: Death Punch
description: Small scythe blades extend from this pair of boxing gloves. You might be disqualified for using them in a boxing match, but at least you'd be able to get the ultimate revenge on your opponent first!

name: Hack\'s Hacker
description: An axe used by an incompetent artist. And now it is yours.

name: The Dragon\'s Fire
description: A powerful improvement over the blowtorch. Now you can burn your enemies with the heat of a dragon.

name: Glowing Laser Lizard
description: It's a lizard...with glowing laser pointer eyes. What could be awesomer? Nothing. The answer is, nothing. When it comes to awesomeness, the Glowing Laser Lizard gets all the medals. All of them.

name: Self-powered laptop
description: This laptop comes with a built-in generator. You will never run out of battery!

name: Despair Sword
description: A single cut will leave your enemies in despair. Beware, don't cut yourself...

name: Cyan Paint
description: This is some Cyan colored paint that took forever to make. Take that, subtractive color!

name: Cue Sword
description: Cuts like you would expect a sword made out of pool ball material would. The hardened resin makes it ideal for guarding as well.

name: Electric Dual Knives
description: These dual electricity-channeling knives are sure to give your enemies quite a... surprise.

name: Pile of Snot
description: It's a pile of consort snot. Ick.

name: DS Stylus
description: This is a stylus used on the DS handheld device.

name: 88MPH Pen
description: If this pen were to somehow reach 88MPH, it would travel through time. However, this pen's terminal velocity is 87.999MPH.

name: Tom Nook\'s Online Price Checker
description: This raccoon mask seems to have internet connectability, particularly to many auction sites and online shops. You could probably use it to check up on your competition and price your merchandise accordingly, ensuring that your deals are the absolute best!

name: Ballpoint Pencil
description: On this pencil is a lead sphere near the tip, this is used to make your drawings bigger!

name: Power of Thawt
description: ...icy what you did there.

name: RazorPencil
description: This pencil has very sharp edges. You might think it would make your drawings clearer and crisper, but it's more likely to cut the paper than it is to draw on it...

name: News Writer
description: This pen is used specifically for writing news and NOTHING ELSE. If you plan to use it for STRIFE, remember to write a headline about their demise on their face!

name: Pin-Tip Pen
description: This pen has a RIDICULOUSLY sharp tip...

name: Blood Rosin Blade
description: The musical blade gets a dark wood finish with a slight red tint. Flinging it around produces a slight trail of red petals, filling the area with the scent of roses. The petals dissipate seconds after they fly off the blade.

name: Hidden Pen
description: While this may look like an ordinary fountain pen, flipping the lever reveals several thin and sharp blades in the shape of a shuriken. They'll never see it coming.

name: Jelly Pen
description: This pen shoots jelly instead of ink. Equally annoying, twice as delicious.

name: Perfectly Yellow Pencil
description: You know most #2 pencils tend to be yellow, but you didn't think that the lead should be yellow as well...

name: Slab of Obsidian
description: A massive slab of obsidian. When you're using it, you swear you can hear something whispering to you, but it's so quiet you can't really tell what it's supposed to be saying.

name: Slab of Shale
description: A big ol' chunk of shale rock. It falls apart pretty easily, but it's big enough that you can still reliably hit stuff with it.

name: Goggletop
description: This isn't a computer that can be worn as goggles, as one might expect - it's actually just a laptop with two side by side screens. You feel a little disappointed, until you realize having dual monitors is awesome.

name: Felt Scarf
description: This soft felt scarf is rather very good looking, with its rainbow-ish pattern, and how it keeps changing colours, despite being a bit dizzying to watch.

name: Gleaming Fountain
description: This pen is known as the 'Gleaming Fountain' because its ink comes out much too fast than it needs to, and it's really shiny.

name: Obsidian Tombcaller
description: A large obsidian gravestone, etched with several names and what are probably numbers in an undecipherable script. They seem to change every time you kill something with it, though...

name: Shale Gravestone
description: A large, black gravestone made of shale rock. It falls apart rather easily, but the sheer mass of the thing makes up for it.

name: Big Orange Round Fruit Pen
description: It appears to be nothing more than a pen with a fruit stuck on the end of it. Attempting to write with it will probably make your hands all sticky.

name: Clicker Key
description: At first glance, this is an ordinary ballpoint pen, but clicking it reveals a key instead of a point. The uses for this are very slim, however it is quite entertaining to click for hours!

name: Fancy Pen
description: This pen is VERY fancy, and should be treated as the most important pen in your collection, even if it is not, as it will demand your attention!

name: Time Lord\'s Trench Coat
description: The perfect centerpiece for the wardrobe of an adventurer of space and time. With this trench coat, sentient beings from every corner of the universe will trust you with their lives. Ok, well, maybe not at first, but...

name: Unicorn Mask
description: A mask that is similar to a horse mask, but is pure white and it has a white, pointy horn on top. Each and every time you don it you feel a bit more magical.

name: Radio-Wave Pen
description: This pen has the ability to manipulate radio waves in such a way that you could say you were 'writing' with it...

name: Captain Neckbeard\'s Naval Pick
description: Basically an anchor on a stick with some sharp bits, this tool resembles a pickaxe. Why a ship would need one is questionable, but hey, it kills stuff.

name: One Winged Moustache hammer
description: This Hammer with a moustache on it now also contains on top of it a single wing... because... *shrug*

name: Sleuthing Signature Pen
description: This pen is to only be used by the most sleuthy of sleuths. It is both used for writing Signatures and it's the Signature pen of Sleuths.

name: Squiddle Ink Pen
description: This cheerfully-colored pen contains ink from the Squiddles. Looking at it makes you wonder where the ink comes from...

name: Sulfuric Acid Pen
description: A pen that writes with H2SO4 instead of ink. Clearly designed for writing scathing stories.

name: The Sound Asleep
description: A magnificent sword with the power to produce a magical and soothing sound as you swing it towards your enemies. Its name comes from its effect on your higher-levelled enemies; as you kill their weaker allies, the music you make sounds like a lullaby, so beware of falling giants. (aka: TIMBER!!!)

name: Fancy Stick
description: This pretty little stick with a decorative ribbon is perfect for prancing around in a leotard. Another use you can find for this "Fancy Stick" is to both lasso your enemies and strangle them with the ribbon; you'll find that your enemies cannot escape your ribbon's grip (with all that traction and all).

name: Bottle of Contraband Fury
description: This strange bottle, when opened, starts croaking at incredible volumes, almost as if enraged.

name: Illegal Contraband of Fury
description: This strange purple piece of contraband bears a strange symbol on its back, and occasionally croaks as if enraged.

name: Clockpunk Knives
description: No gentleman would go out without his brass plated, be-geared pair of knives that menace with timepieces.

name: 3+3 Knifedent
description: Three razor-sharp, double-edged blades per knife. This seems unsafe.

name: Whale Teeth Knives
description: These knives were crafted from a white sperm whale's teeth and no small amount of monomania.

name: Whale Music Box
description: A music box that plays a short, haunting whale song.

name: Iron Waistcoat
description: This attractive red and yellow waistcoat is cunningly tailored to resemble Tony Stark's powered armour chestpiece. Onboard weapon systems, flight and power sources not included.

name: Intermission Spellstamp / 5 of Spheres
description: A spellstamp that contains an extremely wide variety of spells ranging from rampant clock destruction to weirdly specific time travel. And let's just pretend that spheres is a completely valid card suit for now, okay?

name: Egg Mangler
description: This is an egg beater that has 8 of the actual beaters that spin while the entire contraption spins as well. It's time to bake a cake and kick ass, and you're all out of cake mix.

name: Chain Beater
description: This chainsaw has razor sharp egg beaters running along the chain, which spin when this thing is revving.

name: Mythical Battlecue
description: You're not sure if there's anything in the legends about billiards. But here it is, none the less, in all its mythical, plasma-spewing glory.

name: 8-Ball Laptop
description: A portable black computer with an 8 in a white circle on the back. It gives questionably truthful answers, but will only respond to yes or no questions. It also works as a regular computer.

name: Triple Anvil-Fanged Diamond Encrusted Pogo Slammer
description: Adds a sparkling shine to the already intimidating weapon. At this point, wearing  sunglasses is an absolute must, not because of how cool you would look, but because you might blind yourself otherwise.

name: TextriFlames
description: These daggers wreathed in blue flame are vicious tools in the hands of any stabhappy pyromaniac worth his salt.

name: Fatal Shank
description: Super sharp moderately radioactive skeletal dagger that can unlock anything - especially the gates of death.

name: 8lue Angel Keyblade
description: After escaping from the bowels of a Monstrous wwhale, the 8lue Fairy granted you this 8oon for saving a compulsive liar. The things heroes do...

name: The Black Colt
description: This black coloured weapon with skulls that have emeralds as their eyes doesn't seem to be a cheap piece of crap. The marks written on the gun imply that its user will become a skeleton in a black robe and wander around killing denizens, but who has time for silly fairy tales like this one?

name: Time Gear
description: A pendant made from a time regulating gear from Temporal Tower, domain of Dialga. This powerful artifact is imbued with the powers that govern the flow of time.

name: Kitty\'s Punishment
description: A Cat-o'-nine-tails with each end having a small, thin beam shooting from it, each one a different color. Makes for epic rave parties, until the laser actually hits someone's eye.

name: Unicorn-Tipped Pen
description: This pen is not only infused with the extremely magical properties of unicorns, but is also very sharp!

name: Nebula-zun Blade
description: This sword-lance has a dying sun giving it power. The sun is of course a black hole, since it is able to be compressed that far.

name: Dragospiral Energized Cosplay
description: You can feel the Fighting Spirit of the LARPer course through your definitely-not-flimsy-body.

name: Looking Glass to All Things
description: Every planet has their beliefs, something they think is true and existing or entirely fake. This magical sphere has the power to show you all to be known as true or false in all the universe, from living creatures to mythic ones, from super machines to magic items. It even shows a few theoretical science expirements or mathematic equations. You now possess all knowledge of the universe, and now it's your responsibility to do what is right with it.

name: Moneyball
description: What are you really worth?

name: Forbidden Planet DVD
description: A classic and highly influential science fiction film from the 50s inspired by The Tempest and Jungian psychology.

name: Red/White Striped Paint
description: No matter how much you stir the paint, the two colors never completely mix. The red and white stripes sit separately in the can, alongside each other.

name: Blue/White Striped Paint
description: No matter how much you stir the paint, the two colors never completely mix. The blue and white stripes sit separately in the can, alongside each other.

name: Sunshine Paint
description: This yellow paint seems to be as bright as the sun! Better not look directly at it...

name: Yellow/White Striped Paint
description: No matter how much you stir the paint, the two colors never completely mix. The yellow and white stripes sit separately in the can, alongside each other.

name: Umbrella of Dryness
description: Ever have an Umbrella that drips rain off the sides, getting your pants and legs wet? Well, with this umbrella that has a double layered cover with a towel on the outside and the usual plastic cover on the inside, the water on the umbrella won't drip down, it'll be absorbed by the towel covering! Is also machine washable.

name: Pen-Stol
description: This pen shoots bullets. Yeah... there isn't much more to say.

name: Chalked Clothing
description: This shirt is covered in chalk... your mother would be so angry if she was still alive!

name: Pokemon Moo Version
description: The only Pokemon in this version are Miltank, Bouffalant, and Tauros. And every trainer is Whitney.

name: Belt of Knives
description: It's a belt made of knives. Why would you wear this? Unless you have some deep-seated grudge against your own waist.

name: Pikachu Panties
description: This is the most adorable pair of panties you've ever seen. And the static field seems to deflect attacks slightly!

name: Chameleon Headset
description: Fool your enemies! Beguile your friends! How are you communicating with them when you're clearly not wearing a microphone? Here's the trick - that uncomfortably stiff and electronic-filled lizard you're wearing on your head IS a microphone!

name: Palkia Cosplay
description: Sadly, wearing this does not seem to give you the ability to rip open spatial tears. Your fantasies of destroying reality will have to wait another day.

name: Heaven-Smasher
description: This formidable warhammer makes you feel as though you could take on the armies of both heaven and earth. You can't, of course, but that doesn't mean you can't dream.

name: Paintball Pistol
description: Do we have a paint gun in this game? If we don't I'm highly disappointed.

name: Philosophical Headset
description: A constant stream of philosophical theories emits from this headset. It'd either drive the wearer mad or help them achieve enlightenment.

name: Afro Pencil
description: This pencil has a large afro on one end of it. Upon closer inspection, it's actually the pencil's eraser. You guess you could use this to... erase the roof?

name: Gr8 Ball Pen
description: This pen is decorated with a blue Pokeball on the top with the number 8 on it. As far as pens go, this is pretty gr8, you guess.

name: Disco Laser Show
