description: This particular laser pointer creates wildly colorful patterns while music plays, enticing everyone who hears it to dance. Especially yourself!

name: Executioner Axe
description: A gruesome, frightening axe, used by the hooded headsmen of the past. With this, you are not only judge and jury, but executioner too.

name: Woodcutting Axe +1
description: Forged by the Gods, this woodcutting axe can do even more damage to the trees and imps you face! Too bad it's only +1.

name: LEGO Brick Chopper
description: An axe made of BIONICLE parts and some random LEGO bricks. How did they get in there? You're afraid to hold it for too long; any sudden movements and it'll fall apart.

name: Thinking Computer
description: This computer has the capability to make decisions with comparable viability to that of a human. It can even hold a conversation without changing the subject randomly every 2 lines. It might even be sentient. And yet, you're still going to use it to look at cats on the internet, aren't you?

name: Supercharged Woodchipper
description: Oh, god, it won't turn off!

name: Mecha Wings
description: A look for ANY occasion! Simply input your desire into the Mecha Wings, and you're set! (Batteries not included)

name: Ruined Shears
description:
Warned you about cutting that bro,
I told you dawg.

name: Majora\'s Bubble Wand
description: The bubbles blown by this wand unsettle all those around it, because they look like angry moons before they crash into the ground.

name: My Little Knives
description: These knives make you want to be friends with everyone. By stabbing them.

name: Permanent Marker Chain
description: A charmed magical object that randomly draws on your chest and face in permanent ink. Your PRANKSTER'S GAMBIT is sure to suffer greatly as a result.

name: Atom Smashers
description: A pair of iron gloves with blue atoms printed on the back. Disclaimer: attempting to actually smash atoms with these is probably a bad idea.

name: Seductive Tarot
description: A rather uncomfortable quantity of sexiness intimates from this promiscuous deck of cards.  Bayonetta seems to have found a place to pose on each card.

name: Steel Yo-yo
description: A slight upgrade from a normal yo-yo, made from cold hard steel. You're not sure why anyone would manufacture a steel yo-yo, though. Someone could get hurt.

name: Assisted Viewer
description: Combined with that magnifying tool on your netbook, this lens can be zoomed to any of your expectations.

name: Clarinetennis Shoes
description: These are a terrible idea! Neither comfortable or playable, they are probably a waste of grist. Or are they?

name: Hammer of the Deep Subterra
description: This hammer cracks the ground as it lands, revealing the prettiest of jewels deep underground. If only you could pick it back up...

name: Cosplay Pikachu Tail
description: This lightning-bolt shaped tail is sure to redden some cheeks!

name: Jewel of Elemental Power
description: When combined with a certain object with an elemental connection, one of five powers of the jewel boosts the element within the object.

name: Ballpoint Pan
description: For those times when you need a pen and a frying pan at the same time, either for cooking and writing or bludgeoning and stabbing.

name: Safety Cubes
description: These cubes are SO safe. So safe, in fact... that they do no damage... But hey, at least you won't poke an eye out... with a... cube...

name: Hellatop
description: This laptop, sporting Hella Jeff's stunning visage, appears to run an incredibly shitty version of Windows 3.1 that seizes up with every button press or mouse click. Attempting to run any program usually pulls up a different program, shuts down the computer entirely, or fills the screen with artifacts and clashing colors. If you can get this piece of shit to do ANYTHING you ask it to, you have achieved a miracle of the highest degree.

name: Midnight Dojo Garb
description: A black and purple martial arts gi, weighted down with metal plates. You feel deliciously pragmatic while wearing this. Kicked dirt, groin-shots, it's all fair game in combat now.

name: Barbed Pixelated Shovel
description: You put barbed wire on a shovel made of pixels. Having realistic looking barbed wire over a pixelated shovel looks weird, but it will work. Not for digging, of course. If you think barbed wire helps with digging, you might need to think about that a bit more.

name: Wrist wraps
description: Bandages designed for use in fighting, so that one does not injure their hand. Typically used in boxing(The sport, not to be confused with Boxing Day).

name: Pizza Cutter
description: A stainless steel pizza cutting wheel.

name: The Legendary Sixth Stamptet
description: Even though there are no other legendary stamptets, you still find this is the sixth one.

name: Dark Re-Imagining
description: This "re-imagined" version of the story is very "dark" and "gritty".

name: Forkwands
description: An essential item for any proper food wizard.

name: Temporal Trenchcoat
description: A scarlet trenchcoat with a gear symbol on the back which unnervingly rotates. It automatically slips the wearer slightly forward or backward in time to evade a close blow. Doing so can, at times, prove deleterious to the wearer's combat efforts though.

name: The Doctor\'s Suit
description: The blue suit worn by the Tenth Doctor. You feel a sense of duty just wearing it.

name: Tactical Scouter
description: A headset with a screen covering your eye. The built-in computer is capable of displaying the stats of the person or underling you're looking at, running advanced tactical analysis in case you find yourself commanding forces and acting as a communicator.

name: Dagger of Time Magic
description: This dagger is surrounded by almost tangible temporal magics that allow it to speed up or slow down the time progression of anything as long as it remains touched by the blade.

name: 4 of Space Frogs / Saber of Vast Croaks
description: This alternately increasingly absurd playing card or surprisingly effective frog themed saber makes you feel like you know exactly where you are at all times.

name: Loaded Octet
description: These magical dice always stop on eight, no matter how fast and hard you roll it.

name: Ebony Bow
description: A long bow made of a dark wood whose limbs curve away from a straight riser with two purple gems set in it. It forms a string of purple light when drawn. Ideally suited to fighting wraiths, but, of course, you will probably not run into any.

name: Soul Force Impactor
description: This railgun fires bullets imbued with dark power leeched off a skull amulet built into the stock. Newton just got a bit badder.

name: Laser Ninjinata
description: An elegant polearm which is jet black except for the activatable red laser blade. Excellent for those requiring both reach and stealth.

name: Electrolaser Rifle
description: This rifle uses far-ultraviolet laser beams to ionize a path through the air allowing a straight line of electrical discharge to the target.

name: Midnight Armor
description: A suit of well tailored pitch black armor to protect you while you aren't missing all the fun.

name: Hand-Held Tumbolia Portal Device
description: Creates one-way portals to Tumbolia, otherwise known as LODHAEL: Land of Dead Hiccups and Extinguished Lightbulbs.

name: Copper, Silver, Gold: An Indestructible Metal Alloy
description: A formidable hodge-podge, turgid and confused -- yet remarkably similar to the present work, by fictional author Egbert B. Gebstadter.

name: Gnarled Stick
description: This item appears to be a botched alchemisation, whatever it was before has been crudely fused with some kind of fiddle, rendering it musically useless. Makes for a stylish cane though.

name: Noise-Cancelling Headphone-Earmuffs
description: The powerful computers in this set of noise-cancelling headphones allow you to instantly escape from the heat of battle with some relaxing music - and look stylish, to boot.

name: Pre-Universe Viewport
description: Huh. This is probably the closest you're going to get to viewing the cosmos before the Big Bang without that annoying infinitesimal speck in the way.

name: High-Flamequency Blade
description: While the name is kind of lame, you can't think of a weapon cooler than a blade vibrating at high frequencies... on fire.

name: SCP-458
description: This never-ending pizza box is both completely indestructible and produces infinite amounts of your favorite pizza. What more could you ask for in life?

name: Buff Banner
description: Provides an offensive buff for nearby teammates. Or would, if this backpack included the horn and wasn't just a replica.

name: Shoujo Blade
description: A sword fused with the power of a cursed eye. By giving up your soul to the blade, you increase its power.

name: Aperture Science Pen for the Uses of Testing
description: This pen can only used for testing, the only question is what this pen does... assumably something sciency.

name: The Pan of the Gods
description: A pan with an odd, ethereal aura about it, simply touching it fills you with an overwhelming sense of power. You cannot help but wonder as to this pan's likely godly roots... and how good bacon is going to taste after you've given it a quick fry. Dang.

name: Dog Tags
description: It's a set of army style 'dog tags'. They all appear to be blank.

name: \'Pokmon: Jirachi Wish Maker\' Movie
description: 'The Millennium Comet is about to make its long-awaited appearance in the sky again, supposedly granting the wishes of all those who see it in the skies above them. Of course, Ash and friends are equally interested in the Millennium Festival, especially when they attend a magic performance by the Great Butler. Even more interesting is the mysterious cocoon in Butlers possessionfrom which Max hears a mysterious voice calling! When Jirachi emerges from its slumber, Max has a new friendsad

name: Jirachi Dog Tag
description: It's one of those army-style 'dog tags'. This one depicts the Pokmon Jirachi. Maybe if you wish hard enough, it'll bring you luck?

name: Wishing Wheel
description: It appears to be a Jirachi themed pizza cutter. The word 'madoka' immediately springs to mind.

name: Catherine Wheel, Shooting Star
description: This thing looks incredibly dangerous. It looks as though someone tried to put an iron ring around a comet tail. If you tried using this to cut pizza, you'd probably burn it. And the table. And the house.

name: Spike Cosplay
description: This costume resembles an adorable purple baby dragon. As you wear this you feel suddenly compelled to do menial labor for your Alicorn Overlords.

name: Luchadore Mask
description: Once you don this mask, the passionate fires of lucha libre will run through your veins and make you feel ready to take on the world. Or at the very least you'll look cool. You had better hope no one unmasks you or you will be shamed forever.

name: Nunchuck Blades
description: Nunchucks that have been fitted with short blades at the tips, making them deadlier in the hands of a ninja... if one can properly handle them without injuring oneself.

name: Swiss army gardening kit
description: A bunch of gardening tools all bundled into a huge swiss army knife case. Its actually really hard to use.

name: Fancy Festive Doctor Who Poster
description: It looks like the Tardis has been decked out in christmas lights. Neat. The image doesn't strike you as odd at all, since the Doctor doesn't seem willing (or able) to miss a Christmas on Earth.

name: Sarashi
description: A long strip of cloth wrapped around your midriff, typically having been worn by samurai and Japanese criminals. This makes you feel exceedingly badass for some reason.

name: Cheap Shots
description: Boxing gloves wrapped in barbed wire. From a time before that sort of thing was frowned upon.

name: Soft Marshmallow Gauze
description: Standard issue gauze at the gingerbread hospital.

name: Welding Mask
description: Protect against sparks and pesky enemies alike! The lack of head coverage does limit its effectiveness, though.

name: The One Harmonica
description: A simple metal harmonica with several rings attached. An inscription glows on its side when it is heated in a fire.

name: Cut Rifle
description: Probably the most versatile item you've seen - a giant pair of scissors with a detachable rifle head mounted on one blade. You wouldn't say this is the most powerful weapon ever - after all, the blades aren't even double-edged - but man, this thing is badass.

name: Pyramid Replica
description: A replica of one of the great Egyptian  pyramids.

name: Popsicle Wizard\'s Gloves of Frostbite
description: The most powerful and ancient of Frost Wizards realized the power inherent in the popsicle. Now, you can channel a fraction of their ancient might to hurl deadly frozen treats at your foes.

name: Plasmatic Musket
description: It glows in a majetic purple color and emits sparky rays everywhere. But watch your fire: those shots still kill.

name: Marty McFly\'s Street Clothes
description: The iconic 1985 style worn by the iconic young time traveler in the iconic film Back to the Icon. I mean Future.

name: Particle Punchers
description: Powerful gloves designed for those brave (or stupid) enough to manually smash atoms. After multiple tests absolutely nothing horrible happened to the gloves.

name: Swiss Army Gunblades
description: A variety of gun/sword combinations lie waiting to unfold from the handles of these slightly unwieldy weapons. Gunblades, sure, but we also got some shotrapiers, a snipeclaymore, and even a machinekhopesh. Go nuts.

name: Rainbow Cake Cannon
description: Your enemies won't stand a chance against your barrage of colorful cakes decorated with frosting and candles. Laugh maniacally as they tremble before your rainbow-y might!

name: Spear Crossbow
description: A high strength crossbow that shoots entire spears at the enemy. You're gonna need some serious mechanical assistance to ready this thing and forget about aiming because it needs to be fired from the hip to allow most of the length of the spear to be behind you. It's also hard to carry much ammunition.

name: Over the Trench Coat
description: Over the top! Up and at them, boys! Field Marshal Haig needs his drinks cabinet six inches closer to Berlin! Perhaps an inauspicious choice of attire.

name: Harry Potter Books 1-7 Boxed Set
description: All of the Harry Potter books in an elegant cardboard box, the cause of all your friends calling you a bookworm. It's their loss; the books are WAY better than the movies...

name: Prismatic Glasses
description: These glasses make the world look like rainbows!

name: Hashslinger\'s Slasher
description: The dreaded spatula of a maddened ghost frycook. The rust on its surface looks disturbingly like dried blood.

name: Smokin\' Hot Heels
description: These heels are some of the hottest things you'll ever wear!

name: Sherlock Poster
description: A poster of your favorite iteration of the Sherlock Holmes story, the BBC series "Sherlock."

name: Dual Wandknives
description: Two wands are firmly grasped within your hands, as you feel the rampaging spirit of magic surge through you. Except magic isn't real, so you just feel kind of stupid ... but at least you can still stab people with the pointy ends.

name: The Spirit of Comedy
description: The handle of a juggling club, capable of sustaining a purple club-shaped construct composed of your own energy without risk to itself. You swear you can hear it laughing sometimes, but that can't be. You'd have to be crazy, right?

name: The American Dream
description: To keep those pesky minorities off your lawn.

name: The Lambda Pen
description: This pen has the Greek letter  on it. For some reason, this makes it seem significantly more awesome than ordinary pens.

name: Semi-Supernatural Pen
description: This white plastic pen comes with four different ink types, each of which has a supernatural ability. Unfortunately, most of them are useless.

name: New Age Book
description: This dense tome is filled with diagrams and instruments on how to heal people's minds, bodies, and souls using gems and liquids. Whatever all of it actually means, this book on "harmony" and "healing" is at least effective at destroying and killing imps.

name: Pokemon X Version
description: This new installment in the Pokemon Franchise includes many new features, including 3D visuals. It also seems to be infused with the concept of life.

name: Pokemon Y Version
description: This new installment in The Pokemon Game Series includes many new features, like a new Fairy type and the concept of Mega-Evolution. This game seems to be infused with the concept of doom.

name: Cosplay Bunny Trench Coat
description: Creeping through the alleyways is made ten times more cute by wearing this fashionable bunny outfit! Now with 15% more fuzz!

name: "Is a Nuke"
description: "Is a nuke" is a nuke.

name: Reaper\'s Judgement
description: A scythe that has the power to take a life, or to spare one.

name: Trusty Umbrella
description: This umbrella was fashioned from an old umbrella frame and the rusty flags of several mailboxes. Shield yourself from rain, sun, and anything/everything that can and will be stabbed.

name: Red Steel Walking Cane
description: Unlike many might believe when looking at the name of this device, this is not a reference to the franchise 'Red Steel' but rather a STEEL cane that happens to be RED.

name: Orange Box
description: All of Valves best games in one box! and it's orange!

name: Paper mushroom computer
description: This computer is so thin that you can only use it on the ground. It's mushroom-shaped

name: Auto Computer gun
description: This gun shoots 0s and 1s, and has a little screen on top of it. It's completly functional.

name: Socketeer\'s Stabbers
description: Show your enemies the joy of sticking metal into sockets by delivering a hundred volts of pain into their stab wounds!

name: iStick
description: The newest apple invention. Glows in the dark, and communicates with people.

name: Remote Controlled Slime
description: This appears to be a mass of programmable slime, which can be controlled via an electronic interface. An intriguing, yet ineffective idea without any set purpose. Maybe you should consider giving it form...

name: Super High School Level Pointer
description: It hates to be in the Hope's Peak Academy, and it's really despaired. But it's the best at being a laser pointer.

name: 0.AD Pistol
description: This Pistol is from the Ye' Olde Days. It seems to be quite effective, disregarding  the fact that, in the time that this pistol is from, gunpowder hadn't been invented yet.

name: Wild Gavel
description: A large, rough-hewn stone mallet mounted upon a wooden haft. Perfect for meting out wild justice!

name: Bristles with Anger
description: Looks like something ruffled up these feathers..er..bristles. Just looking at this broom makes you seethe in anger. With this you will aggressively sweep the dust and your enemies away.

name: Thoughtdriver
description: A screwdriver with the appearance of paper, but the durability of metal. Letters shift and flow all over the object.

name: Noisy Rifle
description: One shot from this gun will temporarily deafen your enemies and give them a massive headache. Just make sure you wear earplugs.

name: iShot
description: Now you can access all the apps and play all the games you want whilst shooting at imps and ogres in a completely bad-ass fashion.

name: Multi-Tool Tonfa
description: These very versatile melee weapons fold out into a variety of blades and tools like scissors, files, knives, screwdrivers, and corkscrews. Oh, they can also be used to knock your enemies senseless.

name: Dear Princess Celestia
description: This pen is used for writing lessons you have learned at the end of your magical adventures. Good thing you have one of these, because if you couldn't record your moral growth for some reason, you might just go insane...

name: Art of the Dress
description: Beautifully laced in while cloth, covered in fabulous purple patterns, and fake diamonds in the corner. This dress is absolutely fabulous, darling!

name: Wizardhair Music Box
description: A music box with an ethereal sound. The insides are strung with glowing silver threads, and the resonating notes haunt your very soul.

name: Thunder Hammer
description: Smite the Enemies of the Emperor...if you can lift this stupid thing.

name: A Hat in Time
description: This hat possess basic time travel abilities, along with the ability to be from an up-coming indie game.

name: Pimp suit
description: Raises your swag levels significantly.

name: Soldering Iron
description: The metal tip of this hand tool produces a low level of heat, typically used to melt solder and join workpieces together.

name: Plush Violet Scythe
description: A scythe plush with a purple blade and a harvester's handle.

name: Dual Kringlereapers
description: If you were likely to cut yourself with these Kamas before, it's practically guaranteed now. You're not sure why the handles are wrapped in tinsel, but it feels marginally more effective.

name: Ghostmetal Jersey
description: Forged with spectral ghostmetals from the Ghost Dimension, this spooky raiment provides both defense and maneuverability.

name: Roadcoat
description: A mid-length, black leather jacket designed for use on the road, on a motorcycle to be specific. It reeks of booze and is a bit tattered, but you feel like you could get away with a lot more wearing this thing than you ever would have been able to without it.

name: Rainbow Sledge Hammer
description: A sledge hammer covered in Rainbows. The best bit about it is it nearly makes you as MANLY as a pink hammer would.

name: Dr. Ball Buster
description: A golf club inscribed with insults from modern English to ancient Sumerian. Just holding this fills you with the need to prove yourself better than those other scrubs.

name: Sonic Rainboom
description: Hitting this hammer to the ground creates a wonderful and destructive rainbow shock wave.

name: Authentic Tron ID Disk
description: This ID Disc is more than just a replica, it's the real deal! And you're pretty sure it will bounce back this time.

name: WWE Championship Belt
description: This golden belt gives you the power of all of the wrestling powerhouses before you that possessed it from Hulk Hogan, to Sergeant Slaughter, to Macho Man Randy Savage, and so on. While wearing this, you involuntarily chokeslam anyone who says wrestling is fake.

name: John Cage\'s Favorite Baton
description: As soon as you take out this baton, the area around you is completely silenced. Which is great for confusing imps before you stab them.

name: My Little Pony TCG Deck
description: My Little Pony now has a Trading Card Game, it's interestingly based around the concept of "puzzle solving" rather then normal brute force fighting.

name: Fly Swatter
description: Used to swat various insects that pass by you, and also arachnids.

name: Gravity Falls Season 1
description: As you watch this show you remember how BLOODY LONG it took for an episode to come out.

name: VVVVVV
description: 2D indie platformer where you constantly flip gravity in order to avoid spikes.

name: Authentic Dragonskin Cooler
description: Nothing better than the skin of a fire-breathing reptile to keep the cold in and the heat out, right? ...right? Ah, well. At least the scales are pretty hard. You could probably beat monsters down with this, if nothing else.

name: Weighted B-Ball
description: This ball doesn't bounce very well. It's pretty good for hitting things with, though.

name: Visor Helmet
description: Combining durability and coverage has given this helmet an edge over its less useful counterparts. It comes with a nifty visor, too!

name: Chain Bomb
description: A chain whose odd links are crafted from C-4. Comes with a detonator. Wrap up your enemies for some explosive fun!

name: Gentleman\'s Clockwork Cap
description: A bronze top hat sporting a few gears and clock hands. The inside is made of comfy black suede.

name: Fushon Rifl
description: If drawn by a competent artist, this would be terrifying. As it is, you're more likely to give yourself artifact radiation poisoning holding this than to do any damage to your enemies.

name: Reactive B-Ball
description: When met with enough force, this ball explodes. Try not to dribble it too hard.

name: Candy Corn Scythesaw
description: A dentist's worst friend, and your best nightmare.

name: Drawing of a Square
description: A simple drawing of a square. You're really approaching geometry from all the right angles.

name: Shitty Drawing of a Square
description: Hella yeah! This Square is SO shitty, you pray to it before you sleep. ...No you dumb homo tool, your PRAYING WRONG.

name: Drawing of a Series of Blocky Squiggly Things
description: You try to make out what this means, but you can't. It's almost as if the creator was trying to make a circle, but was somehow physically incapable of drawing curved lines.

name: Snow Crashtop
description: A Finux running, Metaverse connecting laptop with an unfortunate habit of periodically writing gibberish to the bitmap. Comes with a virtual librarian and the Central Intelligence Corporation's Earth program.

name: Union Jack Moustache
description: A moustache adorned with red, blue and white respectively.

name: Microwave
description: A household tool for quickly heating up food.

name: Left-Handed Remote Ghost Gauntlet
description:
You make a LEFT HANDED REMOTE GHOST GAUNTLET to complete the pair.

BECAUSE YOU DON'T SEE WHY THE HELL NOT.

name: Nanbu 2
description: A pistol that fills you with a vague sense of justice. You feel like shooting shadows, but that would make you look like an idiot.

name: Moon Rock
description: You're not sure that this dull hunk of rock even came from the Moon. It's so light that, for all you know, it could be made of plastic!

name: Selenous Pizza Slicer
description:
The reason behind the blue-ish tint of the metal is questionable... still, it looks cool, and if the imps all get
selenium poisoning, then all the better!

name: Silver Laser Spoon
description: A silver spoon with a laser light in the handle. Useful for highlighting text, eating cereal, and repelling the undead!

name: Freeman\'s Walking Stick
description: This over-sized crowbar is stained with a bit of yellow blood. A serviceable walking aide as well as the perfect tool to stove in alien skulls!

name: Chocolate paintbrush
description: This paintbrush may not do much to your enemy, but it is too good to resist!

name: Apple Hoodie
description: A hoodie in your designated color with a large white Apple print up front. Keeps you comfortable with a built-in temperature system, but the brand makes it incredibly expensive to alchemize.

name: Memorial Scepter of Too Much Cake
description: Someone once said, "Let them eat cake." But let's not be rude. My dear nemesis died that way.

name: A Christmas Miracle
description: A powerful staff that has the ability to shoot flaming  santa heads at the enemy. Defeated enemies explode into a heap of presents, which contains the grist.

name: Swiss Army Wrench
description: A wrench that can be used in a multitude of situations. Also very useful for whacking things.

name: How those Canadians Stole Christmas
description: A movie with the cliche story of Canadians stealing Christmas .

name: Nothing
description: Ask and thou shall recieve.

name: Fancy Pig-Pen
description: This Pig Pen is more fancy then other Pig Pens, and should be treated as such!

name: Akashik Autograth
description: This pen has been 'autographed' by the akashic records itself, giving it some power over the understanding of time-space

name: Lucky Lantern
description: This lantern is of a metallic color. It also radiates a brilliant golden light, brighter rays pointing towards points of interest ranging from hidden artifacts to underlings' weak points.

name: The Power of Fancy-ness
description: With this sword you feel VERY fancy.

name: Rock Candy
description: Hard, delicious rock candy. Yum.

name: Obsidian Rock Candy
description: Pitch-black and filled with shards of obsidian, this candy seems like it would be a good way to break your teeth, cut your gums, or turn your tongue into an unrecognizable bloody mess.

name: Templar Armor
description: Armor worn by the famous Templar Knights in earth's history. You can feel God's protection, as well as the protection of metal plates. Mostly God though.

name: Moomoo Milk
description: This milk is faintly yellow, and smells vaguely like hyper potions.

name: Deus Machina: Nirvana
description: A life size robotic marionette controlled with the mind of the wielder. It resembles a metal gorilla with pointy claws, and a purple dress. Only that gorilla has a human face with completely white eyes, and it walks on two legs.

name: Universal Cosmic Inferno Hammer
description: What was once a really large hammer now became a cosmic hammer. Also an inferno hammer. Imps behold, for it is also universal.

name: Octuple Anvil-Fanged Devil Slammer of Chaos
description: Looks like you could find something else. Congratulations, enemies flee before you. Gods kneel down to you. You are truly powerful.

name: President of the Galaxies Pedestal
description: This Pedestal is reserved specifically for the president of the Galaxy. since you plan to touch it remember that in 4002 when your when the galactic police get here, you great-great-great-great-great-great-great-great-Grandchildren will be in SO much trouble.

name: Fractal Disc Of Raging Miracles
description: Whenever you throw this it explodes into mystical shards of shining rage. Motherfuckin' miracles.

name: Temporal Cloth Frisbee
description: Stretching these amazing socks over a golden frame made this wonderful thing a reality... right before it disappeared into a paradox vortex.

name: Toa Axe
description: An axe of protosteel, this is the perfect tool to channel your Aspect's energy, and for defending yourself!

name: Energy Waster
description: This item requires nuclear energy to make a turbine spin; however, doing so powers a generator. This cycle continues until power source is so diminished the item implodes.

name: Nail Blaster
description: No longer useful for placing nails in wood, since it's powerful enough to shoot straight through a 2x4.

name: Bonk! Atomic Punch
description: Bonk! is fulla radiation, which as we all know is pretty great for givin' people superpowers.

name: Honey Jar
description: This jar is filled with delicious honey that gets all over your fingers.

name: 24kt Shamrock Diamond Ring
description: A gold ring encrusted with a green-tinted, shamrock-shaped diamond, the likes of which could probably grant you an amount of luck befitting an Irishman!

name: Judgement Armor
description: A relic of a bygone age, this golden inquisitorial armor is not the defender aspect of the Paladin you're seeing; it is the commanding, faceless aspect of justice, of judgement. There is more to a Paladin than shining armor.

name: Lightbringer Armor
description: This ornate set of armor is far tougher than it looks - and maybe the glowing shoulderpads will blind someone! Who knows?

name: Eclipsed Blue Sun Disk
description: This once flaming chakram has been shadowed by a blue moon, turning the flames sapphire. This brought forth a lot of latent energy, apparently.

name: Verdant Cake Spear / 5 of Green Cakes
description: A cake spear covered in thorns, vines, and other forms of foliage. And cakes wasn't even a valid card suit to begin with; now we're adding colors?

name: Crag Staff
description: A strong staff made out of rocks and minerals. It is quite hard to use without scratching oneself, but the same properties makes it great in battle.

name: Administrator Microphone
description: A smaller, more compact microphone that was popular in the sports and war announcement business in the 1960's era.

name: Piston Powered Pummelers
description: Mechanized bronze gloves that jut forward forcefully on trigger. Engraved is the familiar face of a green slimer.

name: Lego Axe
description: This child's toy of an axe isn't all that useful, but at least it's fun. Well, fun for anyone who isn't on the receiving end, anyway. An axe made of Legos doesn't exactly scream "safe".

name: Heartseeker
description: You'd think that a cursed skull obscuring the eye of your scope would make this knife even more useless, but when you throw it, it seems to unerringly bury itself into the nearest enemy's chest. Hooray for cursed magic!

name: Blessed Bulwark
description: A silver shield, imbued with the power to resist malicious intent. Handy against the undead and the uncouth.

name: Bladed Steel Shieldarang
description: The manufacturers recommend buying two as a set. One for throwing, one for preventing costly injuries due to ricochet.

name: Midnight Miracle Harshwhimsy Glowsticks
description: The neon glow of these sticks fills you with strangely homicidal urges. You could swear you just heard the reverberating honks of the dreaded EDM Clown in the distance.<iframe width="1" height="1" frameborder=false src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/MUCjAGgiPX4?autoplay=1"></iframe>

name: Lacrosse Pen
description: They laughed at you when you taped this lacrosse net onto your oversized pen - but when you need to create a shopping list during a lacrosse match, you'll be the one laughing at them!

name: Ghost Wallopers
description: A trick set of green boxing gloves that spring forward on trigger.

name: Mobile Trace Bodysuit
description: A skin-tight body suit, emblazoned with your personal symbol. Now if only you had a giant humanoid war machine to control with it...

name: Ski
description: A single ski. Is more or less unusable without a second one.

name: Generic Trope Pyramid
description: Even though you have never seen this pyramid in any piece of media, you still feel a strange sense of deja vu - like it's been in millions.

name: Clockwork Cube
description: This variation on the Rubik's Cube is covered entirely in various cogwheels, springs, and watch hands, interlocking differently depending on how the smaller cubes are aligned. Be careful when trying to solve it (or hitting imps with it), though: getting a finger caught between two sharp gears hurts!

name: Mystical Pyramid
description: Unfortunately, this pyramid is not nearly as mystical as you thought it'd be and has no special powers.

name: Prismatic Pyramid
description: This pyramid reflects light into various colors. You find yourself wondering how this will help in any way, but you soon shrug it off.

name: Exploding Puck-shooter
description: It's still your ordinary hockey stick, but the trick lies in the gasoline-filled pucks! If you suck at hockey, you could always, like, throw them instead...

name: Starstruck Hockey Stick
description: A glowing hockey stick with star-shaped handle. Not much of an improvement, but at least it'll be easier to explore caves.

name: Robokendo armor
description: Tired of always sweating the shit out when you are wearing your Kendo armor? This armor offers all the sweating plus functional computer functions!

name: Bahamut Marionette
description: A tiny replica of the god of metallic dragons. Properly puppeteered, this silver dynamo can fire bolts of searing light from his mouth. It's tough to pull off, though.

name: Good-Night Gloves
description: Yeah, you would not want to be on the receiving end of this.

name: Good-Morning Gloves
description: For when you REALLY need someone to be awake at that exact second. Or to break that annoying imp's ears.

name: Flamin\' Sock Puppet of Steel
description: It looks like a puppet, but it's kind of sharp and... mace-like. Also, it's on fire. That's new. Thankfully, the inside of the puppet is only just hot enough so that it will not burn your hands.

name: Little Shop of Horrors, by Howard Ashman
description: A complete script of the musical Little Shop of Horrors.

name: Club Sandwich
description: This toasted, three-layer sandwich stuffed with turkey, lettuce, bacon, and tomato looks absolutely delicious. Why would you do anything with this other than eat it?

name: Pyramid of Mind
description: This pyramid is infused with the aspect of Mind,; it uses this power to distort the mind of the opponent in such a way that they become unable to think for themselves.

name: Pyramid of Light
description: A pyramid that is infused with the aspect of Light. It shines knowledge onto you, and brings you prosperity.

name: Companion Pyramid
description: For when you want a companion with 5 sides, instead of 6.

name: Spudgun
description: A homemade launcher consisting of a series of tubes and pressure systems, capable of firing projectiles such as potatoes or just about anything else that will fit. It's pretty difficult to set up in a combat situation, but it can be quite potent when used correctly!

name: Noodle Chopsticks
description: Not chopsticks for eating noodles, but rather chopsticks made out of noodles. Good luck trying to pick up and/or stab anything with these.

name: Boo Staff
description: A bo staff made out of stone. For every foe killed, a new name is scribbled into the surface.

name: Ceramic Throwing Darts
description: A handful of leaf-shaped throwing darts made out of lightweight porcelain. Although they look fragile, they hold up surprisingly well when tossed - and besides, the ones that do break provide a little extra damage by shattering into tiny, painful shards.

name: Frying Pan Shaped Meteorite
description: Really, this is pretty useless. It's not even conductive. It's literally a rock with a handle. You guess you could hit some things with it?

name: VVVVVV: Story of Verdigris
description: This alchemized game puts you in control of the minor character Verdigris! While he cannot flip, he can run up the side of walls for a short period of time and jump short heights!

name: Wrist Calculator
description: Rather than displaying the time, this watch-like accessory provides a way to calculate differentials or plot data distributions anywhere you like without having to carry an actual calculator around.

name: Portable Difference Engine
description: A small clockwork calculator, determining the results of arithmetical operations through the turnings of hundreds of tiny gears. It's a fair bit heavier than its modern counterpart, which might be a good thing if you're planning on using it as a weapon.

name: Magnetic Teddy Bear
description: Plush and adorable, and now with magnets inside to cling to things and give teddy bear hugs.

name: Squiddlebear Plush
description: A plush of a Squiddle with the face of a teddy bear. Or maybe it's a teddy bear in the shape of a Squiddle. Oh well, if you can look past the oddness of it, it's actually quite adorable!

name: Energized Textridaggers
description: And you thought these blessed blades were powerful before... But that was before you blessed them with a ton of uranium and the power of science!

name: BIONICLE Puppet
description: A brand new puppet from the LEGO BIONICLES series. What a wonderful world.

name: Klotski Puzzle
description: A wooden puzzle where you need to slide square and rectangular blocks around to get the big square from the top to the bottom.

name: Painting of a Horse Peacefully Standing by a Football Player Wearing a Circus Afro
description: Is the horse wearing the afro or is the football player?

name: Bowling Pyramid
description: Once used by the famously bad bowler Sir McPoopy Pants in the only bowl in the history of ever to get -300 points. Can this thing even roll?

name: Homestuck Book One
description: A familiar note is produced. It's the one Desolation plays to keep its instrument in tune.

name: Desktop Hat
description: A elegant top hat with a heads-up display for computing on the go - in style.

name: Spearwhip
description: A spear at the end of a whip, who even thought of that? Careful not to get into an accident.

name: Ring of Bodacious Black Liquid Sorrow
description: The instructions say not to consume the Bodacious Black Liquid Sorrow Fruit Gushers, but nowhere does it say you can't make an ungodly, all-powerful ring from it. Well, a supposedly ungodly, all-powerful ring.

name: Ancient Plastic Rapier
description: Behold! The nonexistent power of an antique piece of plastic shit!

name: Baseball Gun
description: A rapid-firing gun that shoots baseballs; commonly used to thoroughly hurt genitalia.

name: Knife of Justice
description: With this multiuse knife in hand, you can strike fear in the hearts of your enemies. You'll show them divine justice.

name: Sock Gladiator
description: Your sock puppet is bedecked in tiny Roman gladiator's armor. Comes with a small but razor-sharp gladius and a tiny shield. Javelins sold separately.

name: Spoogles
description: Goggles adorned with... are these human bones? Ew.

name: Yarn Gun
description: Displeased with someone? Why not give them a face-full of yarn-wrapped spuds? Fun for you, pain for them!

name: Audrey II Puppet
description: A puppett of the main antagonist used in the musical Little Shop of Horrors, in its smallest form. Despite not being the real thing, its trap still seems to open up around your wounds. You suppose giving it a few drops of blood wouldn't hurt...

name: Chessboard Cube
description: With 8x8x8 small cubes rather than the 3x3x3 of the original, this variation of the Rubik's Cube is quite a bit too large to be conveniently carried around, but that just makes it all the better to hit things with.

name: Secret Society Cloak
description: A cloak used by a secret society to show off your mystery and your devotedness to the society.

name: Clockwork Calculator Cube
description: Twist the cube to line up the correct numbers and operands, and the clock hands will show the result; this may well be the most needlessly complicated way to calculate the result of an addition ever. And for something supposedly portable, all that metal clockwork sure does add a lot of extra weight.

name: The Second Amendment
description: Fight for what's right. Fight for your life!

name: Bone Bubbles
description: A bubble wand that blows giant, hollow spheres made of bone.

name: Clatter-o\'-Nine-Pans
description: If you thought one pan clanging against things was loud and annoying, try nine of them all clanging against each other! Oh yeah, getting hit with all those pans at once would probably hurt too.

name: Arceus Shrine
description: A small-scale replica of a shrine to the Holy Arceus, covered heavily in carvings of Unown. Each of its three sides represent Dialga, Palkia, and Giratina, respectively.

name: PYRAMID
description: Sharing the same name as one of the episodes of Welcome to Night Vale, this pyramid simply sits there. It is thought to be a publicity stunt for Night Vale's local cereal company, "Flakio's."

name: Community DVD
description: An assortment of episodes from the TV show about a group of community college students.

name: The Mythotyper
description: Everything that this bronze and gold typewriter types somehow comes out as a myth or legend. Too bad it can't do your homework for you.

name: Rubik\'s Wand
description: This wand is made of fifteen varicolored sections and looks glaringly difficult. You hardly want to know how it could be solved.

name: Cardboard Box
description: An item commonly used to hold things inside of it.

name: Meteor Cube
description: A cube-shaped rock that may or may not have fallen from outer space at some point.

name: The Lesser Key of Solomon
description: No one cares if this wasn't written by Solomon and you can tell because of the titles used. What you have here is a (supposedly) bona-fide text on summoning every demon from Amon to Zepar.

name: All-Purpose Carpenter\'s Rifle
description: Whether it be nailing a board in place, sawing lumber the right length, or cutting a piece of twine, this handy gun serves all your needs. It's also pretty good at killing things, if you need it for that.

name: Pillow of [REDACTED]
description: [DATA REDACTED]

name: Candle Claws
description: You aren't quite sure how these could work as a weapon, since it seems to be melting in your hands. But the flames at the tips look really cool in the dark.

name: The Decision Writer
description: This pen is known to have powers over the ways that people act. Those with higher minds are less susceptible to these abilities, however, with this you can write the future.

name: Ski Pole
description: Just an ordinary ski pole, but it could easily be used as a weapon.

name: Blackout
description:
Foolish mortal! You deal with powers beyond your ken! Namely electricity!
This fearsome instrument of Death himself has been given the power of Electricity! It is now even more deadly than before!

name: Lens of Truth
description: "A long time ago... There was a man in this very village who had an eye they said could see the truth!"

name: Swiss Tesla Knife
description: What happens when you combine Serbian and Swiss technology? A zappy little friend. That's what happens.

name: Chained D20
description: A long, metallic chain with a D20 on the end. Roll for initiative, or just strangle your enemies to death. Whichever comes first.

name: Christmas Striped Laser Ninjato
description: A smaller copy of a lightsaber with a striped green and red blade and comfortable green and red felt hilt. What at first appears to be the effects of motion blur turns out to be it trailing laser blade in midair for a fraction of a second after moving away. This makes it even more dangerous than a typical lightsaber but does allow for some neat tricks.

name: Midnight Time Trenchcoat
description: A stylish jet black trenchcoat with a scarlet gear symbol on the back which unnervingly rotates. It lets the wearer move to the previous or future midnight and then back to their previous time plus how much time they spent at the midnight per San Dimas Time Compliance.

name: Scouter of Temporal Tactics
description: A red headset with a dark red tinted screen that covers an eye. The built-in computer is capable of displaying the stats of the person or underling you're looking at, running advanced tactical analysis in case you find yourself commanding forces and acting as a communicator. The last function sadly might end up being the most used.

name: Glass Bow of Void Lasers
description: A deadly and accurate hollow glass bow filled with an odd dark blue liquid that doesn't seem entirely there. Upon making a drawing motion with the nonexistent string invisible and powerful lasers of incredible range shoot forth. Be careful with this thing.

name: Soul Force Laser/Rail Rifle
description: A rather heavy rifle with a skull amulet of dark power built into the stock. It allows the wielder to choose between the path of Newton and fire it as a railgun or the path of Einstein and fire it as a laser. Either way it's pretty bad.

name: The King\'s Laser Rapier
description: An elegant weapon for a more civilized king. Between the Force's Fakeness Attribute making this thing threaten to decapitate you and your presumably low Kingness Attribute making the jeweled hilt just look gaudy, it's an unfortunate combination. It otherwise serves excellently for destroying imps.

name: Unbreakable Frozen Laser Katana
description: An unbreakable sword forged far in the north where lasers freeze for a real elegant dude.

name: Rainbow Laser Rifle
description: Now that you've unlocked the security features on your laser rifle, you can shoot lasers of any visible spectrum light. Better yet, all of them at once.

name: Reason
description: REASON version 1.0B7 Gatling-type 3-mm hypervelocity railgun system Ng Security Industries, Inc. PRERELEASE VERSION - NOT FOR FIELD USE - DO NOT TEST IN A POPULATED AREA -ULTIMA RATIO REGUM-

name: Pc Mask
description: A Black gas mask with a computer built into the eye viewing ports. It automatically directs you to helpful life-saving websites based on the type of gas it's filtering.

name: Lacrosse Tuning Gloves
description: An odd combination of sporting equipment and band equipment, the Lacrosse Tuning Gloves create different tones depending on how hard you hit something. (or someone!)

name: Kanohi Avohkii
description: A golden facemask of an alien culture. You suspect it might contain some kind of great power... for someone else.

name: Headset Chest Pads
description: These chest pads are shaped like a headset. You'd think this would make them awkward to wear... and you're right. They are.

name: Staff of Light
description: Carry the staff used by the Toa of Light, defeat the darkness!

name: Sparkly Prom Thong
description: Only meant to be worn once. But please, for everyone's sake, once is too many.

name: Party Cannon
description: This cannon should be brought anywhere that you want good times to happen, and remember: Smile, Smile, Smile.

name: Swords In The Irons
description: A blacksmithing mishap left what would have been a dissatisfied knight with a pair of formidable hammers.

name: Bucky\'s Curious Two-shot
description: An incredibly odd shotgun used by vampire hunters. Its mechanisms are so odd it's a wonder it fires at all.

name: Rough Stone Statue
description: A statue made up of rocks you could only find underground, and the occasional mineral or two. It looks like it JUST came out of the ground.

name: Fizzing Blade
description: When you hold this sword, you feel energetic, and also like you need to use the bathroom.

name: Sopor Slime Pie
description: A terrific soporific that messes with your mind. Addiction side effects may include horrific hallucinations, chillin' out in general, terrible rap battles, murdering your friends, and just overall nonchalance.

name: Reviving Flame Scythe
description: A scythe with the power of the phoenix! Whenever you kill something it turns into ashes that seem to heal you.

name: Incredibly Smart Know-it-all Fencing Sword
description: This item will tell you everything you are doing wrong while you put up your human house boundary markers... or while you partake in swordsplay. It seems particularly adamant about the fact that fencing is not the same as jousting.

name: Magnetic Wumbo
description: A blue flask shaped like a W, containing a fluid that is said to make the consumer a giant.

name: Sonus Calamo
description: An upgraded version of the Sonic Pen with a lot of different cool upgrades, like the ability to translate things from English to Latin and vice versa.

name: Fabric of Reality
description: On this cape holds the fabric of reality, you were it in full knowledge that touching it could destroy planets, or even universes!

name: Octuple Guardian Hammer
description: That hammer that you couldn't put anything else in? Well, you put something else in it, something rather all-powerful it seems. This hugely alchemized hammer is pure white and crackles with green lightning. Not only that, but it appears the fluorite octets on the thing have lost their marking, and are now pure white and always seem to produce the ideal result.

name: Lagann Helmet
description: It's like you're actually piloting Gurren Lagann! Except you're not in a 50 foot killer robot.

name: Fruit Gushers - Anti-Pollution Powered Hero Flavour
description: Fruit Gushers with 5 different colors: Brown, White, Orange, Blue and Red. Eating them all at once makes you feel like flying around and throwing polluters into things.

name: Imagination Centre
description: A beautiful, magical place filled with everything you so desire. If anyone tells you it's just a box you colored with chalk, they're lying.

name: Gaia\'s Burstheel
description: You can sense the will of the ground beneath your feet, calling to be unleashed in the form of tremors, quakes, and shaping the earth around you into a weapon.

name: Silver Arrow of Justice
description: This sacred arrow was used in order to destroy the Prince of Darkness, but now you are going to use it to destroy some underlings!

name: Space Lawyer\'s Ready Rifle
description: How does the avid lawman of the galaxies defend himself? With a laser firing rifle.

name: Time Shield Suit
description: A black suit with red accents patterned after the Hero of Time godtier outfit. Its true power can only be unlocked by a Hero of Time, and with it, a world of time travel opens up to them!

name: Roadstar Tonfa of the Sleuthgod
description: Twin lipstick tonfas with revolving stars powered by the fires of pure charisma. The purest rims of mythril and wheels of pulchritude combine to bring stylish ruin to your foes.

name: Hyperdark Moon Tonfas
description: Blacker than the blackest night, these cursed weapons lay waste to your foes invisibly. You literally radiate a field of darkness while gripping these. Good luck trying to keep track of them, though.

name: Kris Kringle\'s Kracklin\' Kannon
description: The most festively spiked way to introduce your enemies to superheated globules of death and holiday cheer. The candy cane stock gives added stability, and the fourteen separate elf-built charging batteries mean that you'll be frying your foes 'til Santa comes down the chimney.

name: Captain Sparky\'s Power Musket
description: This weapon emits a strange radiation beam from its core. You better watch out when you click that trigger tough. Its recoil is monstrous.

name: Aperture Science Killer Device
description: The new Aperture Science Handheld Killer Device can shoot bullets in a really fashionable way! It even has those "pew pew" sounds and everything! It shoots the bullets with the casing: that's 65% more bullet per bullet! KIlling monsters is more fun with science!

name: Deathscythe of Metal Memories
description: This curve of this dark blade pulses with the heavy deaths of a hundred thousand lost souls. The percussive symphony of pained moans unleashed when swung can only be described as the most metal thing since the first blacksmith hammered out the first crude sword.

name: Faceless King\'s Crown
description:
A crown made to hide the face of feared kings. When equipped, a sphere of light engulfs the face and hides it.
You can never know if the king is looking at you or sleeping at the throne. It all sounds the same anyway.

name: Nuclear Drill Rocket
description: All of the digging power of a Nuclear Drill, coupled with the mobility of a rocket-powered chair! Rocket through the sky with an unstoppable drill in front of you, ready to pierce through basins and basilisks alike.

name: Blades of Athens
description: These flaming blades once belonged to the legendary Kratos!

name: The Department of Defense
description: In this large armor you feel extremely patriotic, with the oversized pauldrons and gleaming bright surface of red white and blue. For every enemy you slay, knows they were slayed by the power of justice.

name: 4th Dimensional Pyramid
description: This pyramid exists within all points of time. How does it do this? DON'T ASK QUESTIONS!

name: Triangular Stone of Excalibur
description: As many of you might know the stone from which Excalibur was pulled out was, in fact, triangular. How unfortunate that he left it behind, too, because said stone is ironically stronger than the sword it contained.

name: Phony Rolex Pocketwatch
description: It probably wasn't a good idea to purchase this from a shady charatcer in a back alley.

name: Midnight Keeper Gear
description: A constantly spinning jet black gear that, somehow, helps you rise with the moon and go to bed with the sun.

name: nachon rifl
description: hey yo bro wat IF we cold SHOT nachon's,, wed get ALL THE BIPCHES, hel yea

name: Chainsavvvvvv
description: Like chainsaws? Like instant-kill spikes? Then we have the weapon for you, in six deadly colors!

name: 1/2bowchucks
description: Two halves of a bow stave attached by a bow string which are used like nunchucks.

name: Tazglaive
description: The next step in the evolution of the Tazpear. A long, wavy blade mounted at the end of a pole. This massive weapon can be charged with electricity with the press of a button, offering superior voltage and range of attack over its predecessor.

name: Welding Rifle
description: Basically a flamethrower. With a scope. That has an amazing range of 12 centimeters.

name: Top Hat Goggles
description: A top hat that has your goggles strapped around them. It seems that you can't put them on your face, but it still looks like something from your steampunk animus.

name: Heavyweight Rapier
description: A rapier that feels a lot stronger and heavier than before. This feels like it'll pack some more punch, whilst still being able to swing like a Frenchman.

name: Caffeine Patch
description: A square of pure caffeine. The perfect picker-upper for that post-strife feel.

name: Faygo God Pyramid
description: A pyramid used to pray to the holy Juggalo God of Faygo, known as 'blahblah'. You do not plan to really pray to the Faygo God... or at least...you hope you don't...

name: Juggalo Pyramid Shrine
description: This is a sacred shrine for the juggalo religion, it is where they prey to their lord and savior 'gibberish text'. You feel the sudden urge to 'ChUg A fAyGo, MaN' and to 'ChIlL oUt DuDe, HoNk :o)'

name: Heraldric Slammer
description: Thousands of years of history and ultramodern technology combine to form a hammer that's sure to forge its own legend. Crush your enemies with the weight of ancestry! Herald Dynamite!

name: White Mage\'s Cuirass
description: A lightweight fencer's cuirass hemmed in red silk. A soft green glow suffuses it, a few glowing glyphs slowly orbit it.

name: Final Guardian of the Hoop
description: This ball-shaped memorial marker burns with the energy of a green sun gone supernova. Here lies the First Guardian of the Hoop, slamming and jamming to his last breath. Dunking this may detonate your local solar system.

name: Nuclear B-Ball
description: This ball literally radiates energy. Hope you weren't planning on having kids.

name: Fusion B-Ball
description: You're pretty sure this thing breaks every single rule of basketball. Good thing you're just going to hit things with it, I guess.

name: Pimp Daddy Jones\'s Bling-Link Trident
description: Aaaaw snap. This trident's chain links, already golden, now sport diamonds. In addition, a large gold "J" encrusted with rubies swings from the end of the weapon. Don't be mad 'cause Jones stylin' on you.

name: Pushing-Potion
description: Has an exceedingly strange taste, and the more exceedingly strange effect of pushing you onto a lower plane of existence.

name: Popping-Tonic
description: Pops you onto a higher plane of existence. Luckily enough it doesn't quite work in the real world, or who knows what would happen.

name: When The Moon Hits Your Eye Like A Big Pizza Pie
description: That's amore! This silver pizza cutting laser is incredibly powerful by conventional standards. Not strong enough to cut through the moon at all though.

name: Knight of Sunlight Overdrive
description: A true warrior's spirit burns within this whip of crackling sunlight and lightning. With each swing, undead crumble before you. You never need worry about the power to stand your ground again. Praise the sun!

name: Bronze Dragons
description: Nothing says "good old fashioned prank" like shooting ludicrous amounts of fire from the knuckles of two mechanized bronze gloves.

name: Gearbox Ecto-Waveblasters
description: Complicated machinery in these gloves combines microwave radiation with ectoplasmic energy to create a highly volatile substance that is shot out on contact. You may have heard of getting egg on your face, but superheated ghost slime is an entirely different story.

name: Magical Gearbox Ghost Bombarders
description: Enchanted gears turn within these gloves. Punching ghosts causes them to explode. Punching anything else covers it in searing ectoplasm.

name: Monocle
description: A gentleman's preferred eye correction device. It is a mystery precisely what it is that causes gentlemen to require correction of only one eye.

name: Operator\'s Symbol
description: The symbol of The Operator means many things. For some, it could mean a way of summoning Him. For others, it would represent an eye, a way to protect yourself from The Tall Man. Either way, it seems completely useless except for the fact it's spinning in a constant rate.

name: Encyclopedia of Coke Products
description: This book contains a listing of all known Coca-Cola Products. It even smells like a cup of Coke.

name: Sharply Accented Subverticello
description: For the secret virtuosorcerer in everyone, this fine instrument is adorned with literal snake-wood fittings, multiple sharp edges, and a bayonet for an end-pin. Conquer with class.

name: Towering Golden Throne
description: A throne made of solid gold. It's significantly taller than the regular throne, and incredibly uncomfortable.

name: Holy Driver
description: A simple songwriter was once stricken by a prophetic vision of the future in which a Tiger rose to power. Only an edited version of the music was ever released, but the implement of the chosen one was found and kept safe for he who would one day wield it.

name: True Apocrypha
description: This shield is equipped with a pile bunker, inflicts damage on a conceptual level, and carries enough holy energy to protect its owner from being consumed by purified oblivion. Plus, it's shaped like a cello for some reason. Just don't try to play it.

name: 50-foot Solid Gold Statue of Giovan
description: A towering golden statue dedicated to a dedicated moderator. Everyone thought it was a joke until it actually showed up on the alchemiter.

name: Card of the Thunderbird
description: Norse and Greek mythology come together to bring you this electrical powerhouse. Summon and control the mythical Native American Thunderbird, and blast your foes from the face of the earth. Also serves as a convenient ride.

name: Ace of Swords
description: The Ace of Swords is a sign of clear thought and cutting through confusion, a sign of being able to see through deception. It encourages you to make a stand and hold to your decisions no matter how radical. It also turns into a actual sword that's more than capable of being used effectively for mundane purposes. That's probably more pertinent to the situation at hand.

name: Mjolnir Orbital Apocalypse Array
description: This card-shaped control console commands the might of the incredible Mjolnir array, a series of eighty-one fusion cannons in constant orbit around Skaia. With this, utter nuclear annihilation of your entire session is one careless button press away. Aim. Carefully. Trademark Sindri & Brokkr ltd.

name: Scythesaw of Exponential Tooth Decay
description: An upgraded chainsaw/scythe, containing a small candy factory. Every time an imp is killed with this weapon, the candy factory's production rate doubles, and all of the children in a random universe grow a single cavity.

name: John Cage\'s Second Favorite Baton
description: Every time you take out this baton and wave it around, something different happens. With maximum amplification, of course.

name: 5th Dimensional Pyramid
description: This pyramid has the power to show all decisions an opponent will ever make and destroy them all at once.

name: Faygo - Baleful Black Cherry Flavour
description: Judging by the dark color of this swill, you think it contains a lot more black than it does cherry. This is probably marketed to the more edgy consumers.

name: Curator\'s Ascot
description: A flamboyant and bookish looking scarf that looks formal but doesn't get in the way when fighting. Someone who takes care to look this professional will certainly have good fortune in all their endeavors.

name: Barracuda Pike
description: The pikes impaled on your spear have turned into autonomous death machines through the miracle of alchemy! Enjoy nature's finest rendition of a chainsaw at work as you pierce your foes from a comfortable distance.

name: 3D Camera Glasses
description: These red and blue glasses record everything you look at!

name: Low-Quality Rick Moranis
description: feEdnME seyMOU

name: Chalk Blade
description: This sword is made out of chalk, and can be used to draw. However, it does break easily.

name: Ice Dice
description: Well, they're dice. Made of ice. Maybe you can trip some imps or something. Way to go.

name: Gambler\'s Garments
description:
... Haven't you been to Vegas? You probably saw something like these there.

They should have stayed in Vegas, man.

name: Indestructible Alloy Katana
description: A katana forged from an alloy of copper, silver and gold. A real meta sword for a real meta dude.

name: 3D Camera
description: This camera takes pictures and movies in 3D! Except you need to wear special glasses in order to see the 3D...

name: Forks of Oglogoth
description: The forks shiver with the dark hunger from THE DEEP ONE. Any sane adventurer would not eat with these instruments of the occult for fear the flavors of the FURTHEST RING will drive them insane.

name: Soul Force Optical Rail Rifle
description: A rather heavy railgun with a handy attached sight. Of course, technically the sight is just an alternative use for the optics of an attached laser. And either way, the skull amulet built into the stock is imbuing the shots with dark power.

name: Micro-Heaven Macro-Smasher
description: A weapon said to rival the power of heaven and earth, now with a convenient size-changing function. Take the fight to your foe, from cherubs to massive seraphim, with a weapon to match.

name: RaDIOaCTIVE Ticker
description: The most passive-aggressive pocketwatch that ever did exist. Don't trust its irritated muttering.

name: Dr. Seuss\'s Quintiple Funtime Holiday Jamboree
description: It would seem that Dr. Seuss has overpowered, the holidays this keyblade was thusly empowered. But St. Patty, Santa, plus Loving Air, and Halloween do still pack quite a scare. With this keyblade, fearsome and bold, and the rhyming majyks of holidays old, such imps and daemons you will slay, and with their souls the Cat shall Play.

name: Black Arms Greatsword
description: This heavy, two-handed sword was made by the Black Arms Guild and bears its emblem on the hilt.

name: Auto-Radioactive Snack Shotgun
description: Trying to feed imps radioactive fruit snacks will be a hell of a lot easier now that you have a rapid-fire shotgun that does the job for you.

name: Angular Animated Amalgamators of Advantage
description: Holding these hurts. Seriously, just roll them. Who even thought it was a good idea to meld luck and the burgeoning forces of Japan? You, apparently.

name: Bowcaster
description: A crossbow that fires a bolt enveloped in plasma. How exactly was this an upgrade to just using a blaster?

name: Farnsworth
description: A communications device that had wireless video since before color TV. You shouldn't let the government know you have it.

name: Journeyer\'s Cloak
description: A long cloak with a hood and a scarf trailing from the back of the hood. It has a very ornate pattern around the hem.

name: Wind Tome
description: A book containing detailed instructions on how to cast basic wind magic. This ought to knock those pesky flying underlings right out of the sky.

name: Magnetic Squiddlepan
description: Imagine the agonizing squeals of delight your enemies will make when you forcibly introduce this frying pan hydra to their skulls and it promptly makes ultra-powerful magnetic tanglebuddies with their faces! Hooray!

name: Magic Squiddle Octopan
description: Now the cacophony of magnetic frying pans clanging and sticking to each other comes mixed with the satisfying clack of pool balls and inaccurate answers to yes or no questions. It is decidedly good for putting a hurt on foes, but if you wanted to cook with this thing, the outlook is not so good.

name: Checkered Clockwork Calculator Cube
description: More subcubes, more gears, more mathematical operations, and a hell of a lot more weight. Less colours, though.

name: Steampunk Cube
description: The clockwork covering this thing is now powered by steam, eliminating the need for you to wind it every so often. Caution: do not handle without oven mitts.

name: Weighted Steampunk Cube
description: Red-hot, extra-heavy, and covered in pointy gears: this thing is perfect for smashing ogres with. It also has a flat bottom surface, making placing it on any buttons you might find that much easier.

name: Ebonbone Piercer
description: A shaft of glittering crystal, said to be the fossilized marrow of some dark god. All you know is, it sure is sharp!

name: Social Triangle
description: A much more advanced version of a "social circle". The structure is so complex and abnormal that you have no idea how it would work in any human society.

name: Fiduspawner Staff
description: A staff with a pulsating orb on the top, with cards circulating in the air around it. Activating the staff flicks a card at your enemy and spawns a fiduspawn corresponding to the card. Used by the more advanced fiduspawn competitors.

name: Bertie Bott\'s Every Flavour Jellybeans
description: Jellybeans of every flavour imaginable. Just... try not to eat earwax flavour again.

name: Ruberald
description: This is a large cloudy brown gemstone, which supposedly imbues one with the power of the cosmos... now what to combine this with...

name: Rubiphire
description: This is a large cloudy purple gemstone, which supposedly protects one with the power of the cosmos...

name: Emerphire
description: This is a large cloudy teal gemstone, which supposedly enhances travelers well being...

name: Chains of the Noble Circle
description: Chains once used to bind the Lords of the Furthest Ring from entering incipispheres. Now, you can use them to lock down and take out any enemies that stand in your way. Just... try not to listen to the whispering.

name: Puppet of the Excellent Host
description: A fancy green and white puppet, great for puppet shows and the birthday parties of small children.

name: Phthalo Blues
description: A blue wand in shifting dark shades, emitting a strong force that makes you want to clean your room, forever and ever... Although for some reason it is quite easy to bend.

name: The Badass Bat of Nrub\'Tourglith
description: This black bat weeps tears of pure manliness and adrenaline. Each swing causes an explosion of grimdark energy so powerful, it blacks out the light of Skaia for a day. The Elder gods shed tears of pride for the sheer kick-assery of this horrific bat. BOOYEAH.

name: 1920 Proof Nuclear Moonshine
description: You're not actually crazy enough to drink this, right? The Geiger Counter -exploded- when you brought it near this radioactive blue bottle. This may be the hardest alcohol known to man.

name: Knight of the Nile
description: Powerful armour forged millennia ago deep beneath a pyramid. As you wear it, you can feel the power coursing through your veins.

name: Killing Edge
description: A red-hilted blade that somehow seems to make it easier to hit the weak point of an enemy.

name: The Newtonian Yard
description: Bristling with various measurements and smaller orbiting devices, this souped up yard stick is the closest thing to a universal measurement device known to man. Time to get your geek on.

name: The Reality Writer
description: This pen writes on the fabric of reality as if it was paper, allowing it to decide everything about everything.

name: Black Hole Spooktacles
description: You look deep into the black hole, and all you can see are skeletons. How spooky.

name: Smile Paintbrush
description: See? Isn't everything happier now? Aren't your enemies glad you covered them in this lovely paint? Why, it even tastes wonderful!

name: 3 of Spades / Rapier Wit
description: Hate to cut and... Wait, no. Not yet. Wait for it... Hate to... no. Wait... Hate to cut and DAMMIT. Not yet. Hate to cut and run. ... SHIT. Hate to... Hate to... Hate to chop all of your heads off with this sword. Real sorry about that. My bad.

name: Slimy Spectral Springing Spear
description: When it doesn't simply slip out of your hands, this spear is great for fighting baddies. But some simply can't stand springy supernatural sludge-covered spears.

name: Brazing Torch
description: The added power of acetylene gas fuel creates a much hotter flame for melting metal and imps.

name: Welding Torch
description: Now we're talking.  It's time to assault imps and join metal, and you have a plentiful supply of both.

name: Auto-Responder Shades
description: This nifty doodad can now talk to people for you whenever you are taking legendary showers... Or just about anything else!

name: Slytherin Slammer
description: It's... A giant green and silver hammer. Has an aura of dark mischief about it.

name: Laser Cannon Knockoff
description: As awesome as this thing looks, it's a hunk of metal that takes up entirely too much space and, in all honesty, just has a few laser pointers attached to the end of it. 6, to be precise. You counted multiple times in hopes of making that number higher.

name: Fluorite Octopan
description: Eight frying pans, patterned with eight dots each and all connected to a single handle by incredibly strong spider's silk. It may by totally impractical for cooking, but its fully capable of dishing out some seriously 8ad 8r8ks.

name: Gravity Flipping Shoes
description: With these shoes, you are the master of gravity... uh, now you just have to land on something.

name: The Cobra
description: A sniper rifle with explosive bullets?! Sign you up!

name: Subzero Drill Trident
description: This sparkling, icy glove sports three drill heads on its knuckles, each capable of rotating in separate directions and speeds. With each punch, an icy spear erupts from each knuckle, propelling the drills forward. Gives a whole new meaning to knocking an imp out cold.

name: Reactive Broomerang
description: A bladed, curved broom supercharged by an eldritch reactor. This weapon is starting to get pretty complicated. Still, the razor bristles will shred your foes just as well as a blade, and the magical lightning it emits while it flies will fry a basilisk in a second.

name: Dragonbone Whip
description: A whip made with the ancient bones of dragons you excavated from the ground, held together by steel wire.

name: Slacker of Time Suit
description: Jammies made of the same material as god tier outfits. They resemble a popular 80s fashion.

name: Arrowsploder Bow
description: Fires arrows that are stupidly explosive. Now you don't have to go to the tedious effort of deploying a bomb and arrow at the exact same time!

name: Gentleman\'s Clockwork Coat
description: A bronze coat sporting a few gears and clockhands. For the distiguished time-related sir.

name: Isnamidev\'s Captcha Card
description: The actual card used for the 'empty card' in the art submissions. Although you're not sure how you know that, considering it looks no different than an ordinary blank captcha card, and also because that'd be breaking the fourth wall.

name: C\'tri\'s Computer of Code Enhancment
description: Legend tells of a man who, long ago, used a computer like this to optimize the quantum structure of the universe in which you now reside. However, his task having been finished, he mysteriously disappeared one day. Considering you now have his computer, that might explain why...

name: Ben\'s Server Cube
description: A cuboid computer-like device said to run and store all of the data and processes of the universe. There doesn't seem to be any way to interact with that data if it even exists, though. Maybe you can just hit things with it instead. Surely that won't have disastrous consequences.

name: Sylph\'s Healing Salve
description: This salve doesn't do much on actual wounds, but just holding it makes you feel a little calmer.

name: Prince\'s Jeweled Circlet
description: This simple crown fits perfectly on your head and sports a number of tastefully aspect-colored jewels. It's not quite kingly, but it certainly is princely.

name: Page\'s Cluttered Handbag
description: You could carry a jillion things in this huge bag... if you could only find them again. Whoops! At least messages you lose in it seem to end up where they need to go.

name: Rogue\'s Hooded Cloak
description: This cloak is warm and soft and makes you nearly invisible in the shadows. Very good for sneaking around in.

name: Thief\'s Rusty Lockpicks
description: These lockpicks are so rusty you're worried they'll break off in the lock, but they still manage to do the job every time.

name: Knight\'s Training Sword
description: If you train enough with this sword you can become as good as any knight in shining armor!

name: Heir\'s Signet Ring
description: This ring intricately details the heritage of its owner and can be used in place of a signature to prove your identity.

name: Seer\'s Scrying Mirror
description: A classic variety of shewstone to help any budding clairvoyant's abilities.

name: Mage\'s Silver Bell
description: An important tool for an aspiring mage, this silver bell engraved with occult symbols has a number of mystical functions... and can also open a door with a ring for those too lazy to do so themselves.

name: Nonexistent Pyramid
description: This pyramid does not exist. Well, technically a pyramid that's made completely of empty space. You suspect touching it would not be a good idea.

name: Bard\'s Handmade Lute
description: This instrument is far from perfect--in fact, it's more than a little flat--but it's still fun to play. You seem a little better at songwriting when holding it, and the melodies you play seem especially meaningful.

name: Maid\'s Dirty Apron
description: Wow, look at all the stains on this thing. You're not sure you could ever get these out. Oh well, at least it keeps you from getting any dirtier while exploring your land.

name: Witch\'s Pointy Hat
description: This conical hat is imbued with a spark of magic that always makes your nose itch when you put it on.

name: Superpointy Anime Shades
description: These glasses' points are so sharp you could pierce the heavens with the points alone. You're gonna have to be careful while fighting with these things on.

name: Codex of Annihilation
description: A Dungeons & Dragons manual detailing the game's rules on non-existence. Includes answers to such non-questions as, "What happens when I get hit with a sphere of annihilation?", "Does disintegrate work on demi-gods?", and "What, exactly, is under the Lady of Pain's robes?"

name: Sonic Rain-Bow
description: Each arrow breaks the sound barrier and creates a shockwave of rainbow-ness.

name: Burning Ring of Fire
description: Try not to fall into it; you wouldn't want the flames to go any higher.

name: Obsidian Cow Memorial
description: A gigantic statue depicting a recently-slain bovine. Upon closer inspection, it's made entirely out of extremely sharp obsidian.

name: Thunder Tome
description: A spellbook describing how to make your enemies get hit by lightning. Make especially sure to read the chapter on aiming before your first try.

name: x3 Nife Conbo
description: Look at that. A shitty knife. That makes three more shitty knives appear. This is useless.

name: Middle Schooler\'s Whip
description: A long whip that's long and light, with a nice cushioned handle. And it's handle is black... But the whip is white. Where'd you get it? Weenie Pokemart Weaponry? Ha.

name: Persona Dice
description:
A set of oddly shaped 21 sided die.
You feel like there could be some kind of divination use for these, but you aren't too keen on trying with one side missing.
