name: Heat Vision Sniper Bow
description: This bow is built in with the high tech Heat Vision scope to detect enemies! Sadly, all underlings do not give off heat... pretty strong, though.

name: 6th Dimensional Pyramid
description: This pyramid jumps throughout all of all existences, taking a part of one and moving it through the other in less of a time incomprehensible by humanity.

name: Alter Ego
description: An AI that tracks underling movements, designed by a genius programmer while they were still in high school! Doesn't that make you feel inadequate?

name: Grimoire for Summoning the Zoologically Terrifying
description: A large tome which contains details for summoning a variety of truly horrifying creatures. Use with caution.

name: Nevan
description: An electric guitar with a sleek design. It's got plenty of style and rocking out on the strings causes balls of lightning to launch themselves at enemies.

name: Evidence Gun
description: This gun can shoot down arguments as well as underlings as long as you yell 'You've got that wrong!' when you do so.

name: Timetop
description: A red laptop covered in gently turning gears that allows you to chat with your sessionmates at any point on the timeline. Caution: irresponsible use may result in paradoxes, doomed timelines, and the untimely death of everyone in your session.

name: Eggman\'s Belt
description: This belt is strong enough to hold Eggman's enormous girth, and the buckle is harder than steel!

name: Frosted Chained Knives
description: The chain is cold to the touch, and it's got two frozen knives on the ends of it, too. Not exactly amazing at cutting things anymore.

name: Saigyouji Chainswordfan
description: You're not sure how you combined all of these weapons into one, but you've done it. Part chainsaw, part sword, part fan, all awesome.

name: Crystalline Laptop of Light
description: This laptop infused with white magic is sure to be useful in keeping up with your documentation of Skaia's clouds... Or you could use it for playing Surgeon Simulator 2013, that works too.

name: Sixth Day of the Dead Keyblade
description: ...Didn't you already have Halloween represented in this Keyblade? Oh wait Day of the Dead, right. Anyways, this Keyblade now has a focus of ancestors and respecting those that have passed, especially those dead imps. Either way, you think you can hear the voices of the dead whenever you hit something with this thing. That, along with Santa Company.

name: 7th Heaven Keyblade
description: Now fueled by the Holy Majyks of a Non-Denominational Monotheistic Religion, your brand new keyblade will crusade its way through your planet REDEEMING IT WITH YOUR HOLY LIGHT!!!!!! St. Nick would be so proud.

name: Hammer of Thunderbolts
description: This hammer of the gods has gained a shocking aspect... get it? Shocking?

name: Scottydog\'s Stabber
description: Just wielding this knife fills you with the urge to stab something. Anything.

name: The Player\'s Shoes
description: Consider, for a moment, the possibility that what you perceive is not real. Consider the possibility that you are not who you think you are, but in reality, you are but a mere synthetic avatar controlled by a more sophisticated being on a higher plane of existence. Your every action, your every thought, is dictated by this being. ...wearing these shoes seems to bring that possibility to mind.

name: Droidling mask
description: With this hands-free computing device in the form of a bandit mask, looking up the values of loot while thieving things is now easy! If you can deal with the headache of having a screen so close to your eyes, anyway.

name: Whip of Paranormal Punishment
description: This whip is like a combination of an electrical chair and a scarring whip. It grips it's victim and traps them, then lightly electrocutes the victim while the other tendrils lash aggressively against the victim. You have no idea how it does any of this.

name: Prospit\'s Next Hot Marksman
description: This weapon is both fashionable AND functional, not to mention a delightful shade of daffodil! It also shoots flaming bullets, which can do wonders for scaring off those with bad fashion taste!

name: Maple Pines Sweater Gun
description: The Yarn Gun has been "upgraded" with rainbow patterns and Canadian scents. It now smells of pine trees and its ammo smells of maple syrup. Why did you even make this?

name: Edgeless Strawberry "Cube"
description: This red not-an-actual cube smells and tastes like strawberries. But why would you ever taste it? You don't know where it's been! It could have been in contact with deadly neurotoxins for all you know!

name: Dolly Spear
description: Oh god, what the hell. The little doll's face has been stretched and warped into a weapon. Its beady little eyes stare into your soul as you fight, and the head of the weapon... Well, you didn't know doll teeth could be so SHARP.

name: Salamandra
description: This is a really big, really heavy flaming sword. It's hard to swing, but its sharp shooting dragon-shaped flames at things works just as well.

name: 3DLT
description: A 3DS with all the functions of a laptop, and the 3D and touch screen of the 3DS.

name: Blueberry Popcorn Axe
description: An axe with a head made of... is that candy popcorn? Blueberry candy popcorn, at that? You weren't aware that candy corn could even pop! Either way, it's highly sugary and hot to the touch. What more could you ask for in a weapon?

name: Celestial Brush
description: A divine brush used by an ancient sun goddess. For what purpose, though, you're not entirely sure. Painting the sunrise, maybe? Hopefully she won't mind you borrowing it.

name: A Man\'s Burning Heart
description: The Model Heart has ignited with shimmering azure flames. It's cool to the touch, but holding it in your hands fills you with equal parts unstoppable fighting fervor and reckless bravado. This thing seems dangerous, so it's a good thing you now love danger!

name: Mechanical Whiplash
description: You have improved upon the Iron Whip by adding lots of clockworky bits! Why is it better? Wait a tick and you might find out!

name: Paradoxical Whiplash
description: By adding this strange ever-turning gear, it appears that the whip can now affect time, which makes it about 100 times cooler than the other one, though historical records seem to indicate that this whip came before the other one... and before historical records were a thing. Wait they still aren't a thing in this game. Huh.

name: Sonic Pinata
description: This piata is the image of your favorite blue hedgehog... You feel almost guilty beating it up.

name: Mann Co. Uranium Chainsword
description: AND NOW FROM MANN CO, THE MAKERS OF BONK! ATOMIC PUNCH AND SO MANY OTHER WONDERFUL ITEMS, GIVES YOU THE MANN CO URANIUM CHAINSWORD- REND YOUR ENEMIES, REND YOUR FRIENDS, AND BATHE IN THE SOOTHING GREEN GLOW!

name: Creepy Core
description: You combine a dust that makes you think about clowns and knives, and put it in a core that thinks. Now you have a core that thinks about clowns and knives. What did you accomplish?

name: Aperture Science Pizza-Slicers
description: The newest in Aperture Science food technology, this pizza cutter is, in fact, a scissor-like pair of two! Now you can slice your pizza - and whatever gets in the way of you and your food - in half the time. Warning: Aperture Science is not responsible for injury arising from use of this weapon.

name: Death\'s Sun Lantern
description: This lantern makes you shiver a little looking at it, despite the seemingly cheery sun pattern on it. Wait ... did the sun just blink?

name: Bohemian Earspoon
description: Spoon out your opponents' ears. Or their entire heads, while you're at it.

name: Poseidon\'s Ire
description: The blinking Kraken eyeball in the center of this trident focuses the latent power in the fork. Lash out at your foes with rays of super pressurized ocean, or crush them with the weight of the sea's depths.

name: Timekeeper Cube
description: Depending on how the segments of the cube are aligned, the clockwork covering it fits together in different ways, which somehow makes time flow differently for the user.

name: Benediction of Nrub\'yiglith
description: Because the Elder God's view of kindness is to facilitate rampant destruction and chaos - and what better instrument than a chainsaw?

name: Spandex Booty Shorts
description: New, 100% improved booty shorts, with 413% more booty!

name: Kanohi Hau
description: This mask of shielding is not only a symbol of Mata Nui, but also an excellent force-field generator ... if only you could use it.

name: Mummy\'s Grasp
description: No, not your mum. This spectral spear sports ectoplasmic bandages, perfect for wrapping your foes in place to deliver precision strikes. Just be sure to place the bandages BEFORE the wounds.

name: Whammer
description: With a large hammer head at the end of the whip, this weapon makes for a great enemy crusher!

name: Garments of Rushed Gambling
description: Deal faster! I SAID DEAL FASTER.

name: Special Halberd
description: The axehead of this halberd glitters like stars. It makes you feel very unique and special.

name: Special Orbital Halberd
description: This high-tech halberd can float around its owner in a defensive pattern. It would be useful if it was a shield or something, but at least it parries attacks well.

name: Laser Sniper Rifle
description: Even more accurate and long-ranged than a normal laser rifle. Unfortunately it's also single shot.

name: Throwing Laser Ninjato
description: This smaller copy of a lightsabers ability to cut through or parry most weapons makes it an ideal offhand weapon but its true power lies in its perfect balancing for the Kyle Katarn Special.

name: Three-Sectioned Staff
description: A staff with three sections. It's similar to the nunchucks used to make it, but a lot more difficult to use.

name: +1 Athame of Magicness
description: This athame was crafted using formidable magic-science techniques and is dripping in so much raw mana as to defy any possible superlatives.

name: Crystal Axe
description: This shiny, sparkly axe reflects rainbow beams of light into your enemies' eyes. Handy.

name: Whax
description: A whip with an axe blade at the end. Great for long-range head chopping!

name: Spatuspear
description: This spear is pointy on one end and has a spatula on the other end, so you can either fight the imps or make them pancakes.

name: Squiddle Plush
description: A plush version of a friendly squid from the poorly received television series "Squiddles". It seems to be equipped with magnets to draw it towards oth- I mean, they use friendship to cuddle. So much friendship, you're having a friendship aneurysm RIGHT NOW!!!!!

name: The Rapirifle
description: It's like a machine gun ... in the body of a rifle!

name: Nitindo 3Djeff
description: And you thought the 2DS was a bad idea? This conksuck gaming device can't even play TETRIS right. I blame the econony.

name: Broken Mirror
description: Oh no, seven years bad luck. Time to hide in the panic room.

name: Sententia
description: A pen that can be used to alter the views of another person. If used by the wrong hands this could be a very dangerous weapon.

name: Spellbook of the Dark
description: A spellbook containing a large number of generally 'evil' spells, ranging from the merely mischievous to the morosely malevolent. It'd be more useful if someone had thought to put labels in the book, though.

name: Explosive Fantasia Card Slammer
description: The heads of this sparkling weapon are coated with incredibly volatile playing cards. With each swing, an explosion of pixie dust and cinnamon annihilates the point of contact. You never thought subatomic destruction could smell so sweet.

name: The Spirit\'s Breakfast Pole
description: A queer pan; just holding it fills you with a haunting, uncomfortable feeling... And whenever you try to cook anything, you find the familiar crackle of food is replaced with ghastly howling... anyone fancy some eggs?

name: Hidden Pyramid
description: A pyramid hidden in the depths of the time-space continuum, undiscovered by anyone, until you stumbled across it under the rug everyone has been shoving their rubbish under.

name: Poseidon\'s Capital Panishment
description: A terrifying piece of Poseidon's newly implemented capital punishment system, this peculiar pan seems almost ideal for frying fish...

name: Eyes of Sherlock
description: As you wear these glasses, you see the world as the great Sherlock Holmes does. You see every clue, and every action, of every creature.

name: Whale of the Plush Roses
description: An adorable plush whale nestled in a bed of blooming axes. A pair of red and white roses sprout from its blowhole.

name: Amulet of the Evening Phoenix
description: This ancient relic summons the burning heart of a long-forgotten guardian, forming a shield about you and all you hold dearest. Engraved on the back you will find an embellished rune binding the mythical beast to the wearer. Lucky you!

name: Staff of the Oglogoth
description: THE DEEP ONE himself cringes at the sheer power of this APOCALYPTIC MALLET. The cryptic symbols on its grip writhe with the dark energy of the HORRORTERRORS.

name: Illuminati Pyramid
description: A Pyramid used by the Illuminati to see all there is to be seen. Be wary of the all seeing eye.

name: Citizen\'s Cowl
description: What this cowl lacks in stealth it makes up for in patriotism!

name: Fruit Gushers - Chocolate Strawberry Lava flavour
description: It tastes like every chocolate fountain at every fancy party you've ever been to.

name: Texterror
description: A mighty sledgehammer with the ends composed of incredibly dense books. The thing weighs 2 tons and keeps weighing more. Makes it hard to swing, but it packs a hell of a punch. Has some good stories in it, too!

name: Blue Apple Jelly
description: This jar of apple jelly has an odd blue color to it, along with it some healing properties! Tastes pretty good to boot!

name: Aquathyst
description: This is a large cloudy navy blue gemstone, which supposedly boosts your speed.

name: Topamarine
description: This is a large cloudy lime colored gemstone, which supposedly protects you while you move.

name: Topathyst
description: This is a large cloudy orange gemstone, which supposedly enhances your stamina.

name: Night Sky Cloak
description: A fairly stylish black cloak with a few constellations sewn into it. Nothing too fancy.

name: Medi-gel Angel Transformation Brooch
description: The brooch's gem is filled with strange, sloshing jelly. When you believe in it with all your heart, maybe you can transform into the life-giving heroine, Medi-Gel Angel! Or maybe you'll just crack the thing open and apply the gel. Your choice.

name: Incubator\'s Recipes Vol. II: Black Hearts and Broken Minds
description: From the bestselling author of the original Witch's Brew cookbook comes this stunning sequel. The book hums with malevolent yellow light, and each time you crack open its pages one of your deepest nightmares is made manifest in the flesh as a horrifying witch. It's a good thing they seem to hate underlings more than they hate you! For now, at least.

name: Holy Monokuma\'s Punishment Spears
description: These ethereal spears appear from nowhere when you need to punish underlings for breaking the most important school rule. The black/white split of the items is very attractive, if you do say so yourself. Upupupupupu!

name: De Munchees
description: I don't know what glitch tastes like, but I'm sure this item pickles tastebuds sarcophagus butter.

name: Arcane Paintbrush
description: This paintbrush has magical properties that make it especially deadly. Painting on underlings can slice them or poison them or just disintegrate them entirely!

name: SuperSquiddimensional Caesus of Temporal Hyperdemolition
description: Brought about only by years of deep sea research by the looming, tentacled threat; these unholy cutters not only wield the power to cut the fabric of space-time, but also to easily rend your foes incapacitated with one fell swoop of raw destructive force.

name: Candy Cutting Lazer Disk
description: This powerful tool was once used to cut through mountains of rock candy. (It still hurts like hell when you try to eat it but it's so worth it)

name: Volcanic Rock Statue
description: A statue made out of volcanic rock. It has an ashy, grainy texture. It's hard to see when the wind blows the ash into your eyes.

name: Pointy Anime Scouter-Shades of Temporal Tactics
description: A pair of uncomfortably pointy sunglasses with a heads up display capable of showing the stats of the person or underling you're looking at and running advanced tactical analysis with a specialization in temporal shenanigans so you can respond in a coolheaded manner in case you get into an altercation with a more powerful foe. Alternatively you could ignore its advice and rely on sheer hot bloodedness. The built in communicator might end up being used the most.

name: Bucket
description: Whoever has this is a horrible person, and if you use it as a weapon you are disgusting.

name: Ch4a4aA4A4k
description: WhO kn3w ch4444lk cOUld b3 sO gOOd!

name: Book 3
description: The third in a series of mysterious books that seem to be documenting strange occurrences in an Oregon town. The author's name is obscured.

name: Lensman Box Set
description: Holy Klonos Curving Carballoy Claws but to eighteen decimal places there has never been a science fiction series filled with more astoundingly over-the-top arms races or impressively purple prose.

name: Bucket Hat
description: It's a bucket... turned upside-down. Wearing this on your head requires no shame.

name: Troll con air poster
description: A poster that looks very familiar, except the 'title' is extremely long and in some weird-ass alien language. Also, the guy on the front is gray and has bright orange horns on his head. weird.

name: A Digger\'s Best Friend
description: When you combine the shovel and pickaxe you get a weapon with a shovel on one end and a pick axe on the other, this should make work faster

name: Shipping Spear
description: A spear that cycles through the Four suites, mostly cosmetic in effect but the Diamond suite is very sharp indeed.

name: Power Spear
description: Wanna pierce somebody near - pierce it. Wanna pierce somebody distant - pierce it. Pierce everything.

name: Proton Pack
description: One of the high powered backpacks as seen in "Ghostbusters". No matter what Bill Murray tells you, It doesn't need to be charged.

name: Grace of the High Seas
description: You've got a blazer with a British flag on it that belongs in Vegas. Well done, you are truly utilizing the mystical powers of alchemy well.

name: Dark Magic Sais
description: A pair of sai made of what appears to be really shitty laminated cardboard. At least it appears to be.

name: Spandex Stockings
description: Nylon is out, Spandex is in. Be the one everyone is talking about with your new "Spandex Stockings".

name: Rapid fire Baseball gun
description: This ball-blasting weapon emanates some dark intentions and a silly laugh from a bear you obviously don't want around. Whatever! Just don't aim it at red heads!

name: Inert Ball
description: You tried to put just a little more power into this ball, and now it generates none. It's heavy as hell, though, and there's still a ton of latent energy in the core...

name: Teashades
description: Perfectly circular sunglasses, in the style of John Lennon. Or Ozzy. ALL ABOARD!!

name: Bloody Obsidian Rock Candy
description: It seems that someone tried to eat that Obsidian rock candy, and spat it out covered in blood... You quickly put it away to prevent yourself from coming down with a blood-born disease.

description: The garb worn by a Sylph of Time.

name: Scissors of Spades
description: An extra-sharp pair of scissors, colored a fancy blank and red with a spade inlay where the blades join. You can probably seriously hurt something with these. Like stabbing them. In the eyes.

name: Rocket Bow
description: Fires small rockets that ignite after getting far enough away from the wielder's hands. Hopefully.

name: Fey Smasher
description: This little hammer might not look like much, but... no wait, it really isn't much.

name: Seer Scope Bow
description: A bow with an attached scope that taps into a Seers abilities to guide its arrows.

name: Quantum-T
description: A plain white shirt with a picture of an atom on it. Neat.

name: Inherited Silver Knives
description: Obviously the appropriate thing to do with inherited silverware is to stab Imps with them.

name: Felt Hour Hand
description: An enlarged hour hand from a fancy clock covered in green felt. It knocks whoever is stabbed by it backwards or forwards an hour in time. Of course that's just as often a hindrance as a help.

name: Pixie Pulverizer
description: You wouldn't actually hit pixies with this would you?

name: Lightning Storm Vacuum
description: This vacuum shocks enemies as it sucks them into its dust bag.

name: iBrick
description: Heavier than the first phone ever created. Maybe there's some hipster value in it, at least?

name: The Completely Sane Hand Gun
description: You feel the urge to not go on a murderous rampage with this gun.

name: Kenshiro\'s Jacket
description: This jacket once belonged to the messiah of the end of the century, The Fist Of The North Star. Put it on and you will be gifted in the ways of Hokuto Shinken. If you don't know what that means it's essentially exploding people with your fists.

name: Fetch Modus Upgrade: Huge Items
description: A device that can be applied to your fetch modus. This one increases the internal storage capacity, allowing you to captchalogue bigger items.

name: Fetch Modus Upgrade: Immense Items
description: A device that can be applied to your fetch modus. This one resembles a large sliding puzzle and increases your storage capacity further.

name: Fetch Modus Upgrade: Ginormous Items
description: A device that can be applied to your fetch modus. This one resembles a leatherbound wallet, the sort of which no self-respecting father figure would be caught dead without. Except for the fact that it's massive for some reason. Seems counter-productive...

name: Chucksicles
description: The annoyingly sharp sides of a popsicle wrapper, now properly weaponized.

name: Pointy Midnight Shades
description: A pair of pointed, easily recognizable midnight black sunglasses. Perfect for wearing at night.

name: Color Extractor
description: This takes the color out of anything you vacuum with it, leaving you with a dust bag full of pure color.

name: Ear-Splitting Violin
description: This violin plays with enough volume to fill up a football stadium. Other than that, it's a pretty lame weapon.

name: Claymore Claws
description: The claymore's heavyweight drags these claws down, but they're closer to something Wolverine might have now!

name: Chainsaw Claws
description: Chainsaw claws are found only on the most wild of creatures, because of the gore caused when using them.

name: Popping Green Apple Chainsaw
description: A Chainsaw covered in Green Apple Pop Rocks. It makes popping noises when started up.

name: Handbound Particle Cannon
description: The highly advanced code inside this glove aligns nearby particles into a deadly beam that fires from the palm.

name: Galactic Polearm \'Valkyrie\'
description: The sharp end of this polearm leaves a beautiful, slowly fading trail of glimmers in the air wherever it moves. They're not quite as beautiful when enemies stumble into them.

name: Copper Wire
description: A wire used in electrical work.

name: Astartes Power Heliripper
description: Spinning blades and advanced power weapon technology? Only with MORE spinning blades? BRILLIANT!

name: Flux Particle Cannon
description: A glove that focuses electrons through a miniature flux capacitor. It releases 1.21 jigawatt beams of electricity. Caution: All liability for any unintentional time travel falls on the user.

name: Aperture Science Security Saw
description: A lethal hand-held Aperture Science Sentry Turret that utilizes complex tracking algorithms to make every slash of this advanced chainsaw all the more deadly.

name: Trollian Chainblade
description: A daunting combination of spinning candy corn horns and a sharp blade, this weapon shall serve well in mutilating your enemies.

name: Darkened Tome of Sorrows
description: This spellbook contains relatively advanced majyyks, albeit twisted into a darker fashion. Pity the underlings, and their newfound limitless sorrow.

name: Ring of Minor Incindiary Majyyks
description: Oh look, your hand is on fire. Awesome. That's about all this is good for though.

name: Stellar Shooter
description: While you can fire this from your hip, you still aim for the stars!

name: Microwave Gloves
description: Fire microwaves out of the palms of your hands, irradiating enemies and heating them up at the same time!

name: Spiral Broom
description: THIS IS THE BROOM THAT WILL SWEEP THE HEAVENS... no, that's not right...

name: Fencing Mama Instructional Glove
description: This glove teaches you how to fence like Mama does! In other words, badly.

name: Boonvacuum
description: Unfortunately this is a vacuum cleaner painted like a boondollar and not a vacuum that sucks the boondollars out of enemies.

name: Pen Gloves
description: Each fingertip on these gloves has a pen with a seemingly limitless supply of ink.

name: Rock Candy Chopsticks
description: You're not sure that rock candy is a good material for chopsticks to be made out of. But that's not going to stop you from using them.

name: Gauze Armor
description: In addition to providing a thick layer of protection, this armor also ensures you're pre-treated for any major injury.

name: Darkened Eye\'s Thorn
description: A dark red lens framed with a stark black rim, this stylish piece of eyewear occasionally sparks with dark majyyks. You don't know if it's supposed to do that, but it looks cool so that's fine.

name: Zeustop
description: Who's the douchebag? Oh wait, that's just Zeus, great and mighty king of the gods. Wielder of the mighty thunderbolt. And he is now your laptop. Funny how the God of Lightning is now your electrical device.

name: Emerald Anvil-Fanged Pogo Slammer
description: Wow! This hammer is SO ILLEGAL you would be put in the slammer if an Authority Regulator saw you with it! They would call it the slammer because it would be extra heinous!

name: Flufi CAEK Piloa
description: Dude this pillow is totally made of cake now. This if stupidly useless...

name: Polychromite Ingot
description: An ingot of Polychromite. You feel like you shouldn't stare at it for too long.

name: Reflective Shield
description: Wielding this artifact, you feel as if you could take down a basilisk.

name: Shimmerglobe
description: Forged by the protodwarves underneath a volcano, this ball grants increased b-ball power, and notably, perfect accuracy.

name: Miniature SCP-1179
description: A mini statue in the supposed shape of SCP-1179. It is made of volcanic rock, and burns your hand if you hold it for too long. It is holding a whip in one hand, and a sword in another. If you look close, it seems like it has hellfire for eyes. But you often get distracted by its beard and horns.

name: Adelie\'s Pen of Submission Checking
description: A pen used by one of the nicest dev's around 'Adelie' to check if item submissions are able to enter the game.

name: Soul Reaper ID Disc
description: While this may seem like the product of a bizarre cross-over fan-fiction, the power of this weapon is beyond the depths of your soul.

name: Clocktower Keeper\'s Rouge Robe
description: The robe of a wayward keeper of a derelict clocktower, it's rumoured that whomever wears this robe does not abide underneath the constraints of chronology, and exists in their own time.

name: Black Cards of Creation
description: These cards are used by users of a dark, powerful magic. Through their dark energy they are ably to use these cards deadly projectiles, or at times use them to summon dark creatures.

name: Angelic Fantasia Zephyr Slammer
description: The Slammer's head is now enveloped in wind. Its blows now tear at their victim with sparkly strands of air.

name: Subjugglator\'s Femur crusher
description: Nothing more than a basic subjuggulator bone breaking tool. Gotta equip the first sweeps properly or they shan't be moving around in combat much longer!

name: Pyrocitor
description: Usually used for burning hordes of annoying alien blowfish, but it's good for Imps too.

name: Rocket Mask
description: If you don't mind the burns on your neck, and the smell of jet fuel, then you'll probably enjoy this thing.

name: Gilded Heartpins
description: Ornate daggers for the discerning poker.

name: Chione\'s Frosttrident of Echidna
description: This sharp, icy trident is covered with a fine coating of snow, almost as beautiful as Echidna herself. It's also almost as sharp as Echidna's quills themselves, as well.

name: Exalted Demimonde\'s Spear of Royalty
description: The rubies and sapphires adorning the head of this glaive radiate ethereal flames. Once crowned Empress, the Demimonde Semigoddess ironically united the warring kingdoms of Courtesan Heaven and Strumpet Hell with this very weapon. Now, its power is yours to command.

name: Swiss Wiznight Gloves
description: These gloves channel a potent Swiss magic to strike down the wielder's foes. Why Swiss, you say? Well, what better way to make them full of holes?

name: Miracle Wand
description: Forged with the powers of two highbloods, you can strike down any foes in your path while honking with glee.

name: Madoka Dress
description: The Madoka plushie seems to have given this dress magical powers, by ripping out your soul. You made a really shitty contract.

name: Perfect BreezeVisor
description: This cyber-clockwork gasmask's time-altering gears are controlled by the air moving through the pyxis-like filter cartridge on the front of the mask.

name: 7th Dimensional Pyramid
description: This pyramid exists within all universes that follow our laws of physics.

name: Prospitian Handbag
description: This handbag is yellow and covered with little moons. It seems to be capable of carrying quite a sum of heavy change, making it ideal for filling up and hitting potential muggers. Maybe that's why there isn't so much crime on Prospit.

name: Invisible Spellcard Armor
description: This invisible armor creates a rain of magical bullets upon being struck, right in the enemies face. AH YEAH.

name: The Cavitator
description: Whoever's bones these are sure did have a lot of fucking sugary treats.

name: Laser Claymore
description: Be careful where you point this thing, you wouldn't want to put an eye out! Or would you?

name: Ectoplasm Grenadier Gauntlet
description: If you've ever wanted a glove that utilizes both advanced technology and powerful magic in order to grant the ability to create and rapidly fire live grenades comprised of focused energy and ectoplasm, you probably need to re-sort your priorities. Regardless, here it is.

name: Proton Powered Ghost Gauntlet
description: A glove whose inner mechanics utilize highly volatile and shcokingly powerful proton pack technology. Comes with compatible proton pack and an ectoplasm scented candle.

name: Chainsaw of Drunken Mysticism
description: Because wielding a magic chainsaw while sober wasn't dangerous enough!

name: Tome of the Truest Shadows
description: Even looking into this book reveals secrets that no mortal being is ever meant to know - secrets that undermine the very fabric of reality, and their mere presence distorts reality around the arcane tome.

name: Gardener\'s Best Friend
description: A diamond-encrusted saw-blade allows this fashionable chainsaw to chop through even the most hardy underlings with ease and style.

name: Time Stop Throwing Knives
description: For those times when you want to attack someone while time is stopped without getting within range of them.

name: Squiddle Mage\'s Cuirass
description: The platemail of a fallen squiddle battle mage. Imbued is the magic of funtimes and friendship.

name: Quaddent of the Horrorterrors
description: Though this may appear to be a normal quaddent it is in fact a dark and mystical fork staff combo.

name: Galactic Polearm \'Shooting Valkyrie\'
description: The Galactic Polearm 'Valkyrie,' now with extra elementary particles!

name: Jaded Demise
description: While it can no longer tell the time or double as incredibly fashionable lipstick, it CAN chop imps in half incredibly effectively!

name: Burrowing Thunder
description: A nasty little weapon, this spear burrows into its victims before unleashing a massive jolt of electricity right into the victim's innards.

name: Mystic Blade
description: Through a combination of the TRUEST MAJYYKS and WEIRD TIME STUFF (or potentially your own weirdness), alongside the powerful aspects of alchemy, you have crafted a truly magical blade, from who's iridescent blade a faint humming can be heard. Or it could just be a glowing sword. Who knows.

name: Marching Band Uniform
description: Show your school pride! Wear a fancy outfit! Sort of stay warm! Keep secrets about those awkward moments at Band Camp! Do all of these things and more with this amazing uniform--includes a Coat AND Pants!

name: Alto Saxophone
description: The smoothest of grooves can be played on this marvelous horn. Only the saxiest of the saxy play this beauty of an instrument.

name: Mace of Malag Bal
description: This rusty, bloody mace whispers to you to kill and dominate in the name of the Daedric Prince Molag Bal.

name: Kill La Kill DVD
description: The new anime made by the creators of 'Gurren Lagann', where a girl trys to hunt down the killer of her father using half a large pair of scissors.

name: Adelie Penguin Plush
description: An adorable plush of the Adelie penguin species. For some reason, this one holds a tiny fountain pen in its flipper as if preparing to edit out some grammar errors.

name: Dual Laser Lightsticks
description: These two hot pink, lightsaber-esque plasma swords are identifiable as the formidable weapons of Timmy Turner's self-proclaimed arch nemesis, Dark Laser. This is Fairly Odd!

name: Anchor Dropper
description: A bow in the shape of an anchor. Is rather heavy, but shoots smaller anchor-tipped arrows.

name: Sawthorns of Oglogoth
description: Trembling with fell energy and whirring blades, these instruments of destruction seem to beckon their wielder to peer deeply into the whirling depths of their dark gem pommels.

name: Pyramid Hoodie
description: You now have a hoodie with a depiction of Pyramid Head on the front of it. Congratulations.

name: Animal Plush Backpack
description: This backpack is so adorable and fluffy you think you might just die from it.

name: Poseidon and Co\'s Breathtaking Capital Fanishment
description: In a godly union of Poseidon and Typheus, you can now serve HEAVENLY JUSTICE upon your enemies with this massive two handed pan-fan-fan-pan, suspended on a hand carved handle of likes the world has never seen before. This fantastic long length pan-fan-fan-pan grants its user the ability to whip up gale force storms at a moment's notice - you can deal with the consort village property damage later.

name: Hat of Unceasing Eldritch Animosity
description: It is not often that one bears the resemblance of the denizens of the Furthest Ring on themselves- and even fewer are the times where that individual is even slightly sane.

name: The Valkyrie Sings
description: This sparkling polearm seems to imbue its wielder with graceful movements in battle. Snatches of song peal out during particularly intense fights.

name: Faygo - Squiddlescently Explosive Rainbow Influx Revival flavour
description: The Squiddle designs on this bottle are almost as disconcerting as the bright colourfulness of content itself.

name: Time Shenanigans Painting
description: You aren't too sure what you're looking at, but according to temporal artistic experts, it is a depiction of a time travelling horse attacking a time travelling football player. To you it's just a bunch of junk.

name: Green Sun Street Sweeper
description: This automatic weapon is bright green, and imprinted with the image of a white sun on either side, and appears to fire miniature versions of the green sun instead of bullets, but that's arguably more effective at raining death upon your enemies.

name: Digisword
description: This sword doubles as a computer, though you can't quite see how. It just looks like a normal sword, with a keyboard on the blade.

name: The Beginner\'s Guide to Darkness and the Universe
description: It's a terribly long name for a terribly long book. And you'll probably have a terribly long face by the time you're finished, judging by how depressing even the first page is. If you're still willing to look on the bright side, at least it's really heavy and can probably do a lot of damage if you can manage to hit things with it.

name: Marching Band Hat
description: Man look at this hat, so official, so military esque, with that big fluffy stick of a plume sticking out the top. Man it's almost like you're back in school, as opposed to running across planets fighting horrifying monstrosities based off of your friends' personal objects.

name: Chrono Bracer
description: A red bracer with inlays reflecting those of the powerful Time Gears, which allow the manipulation of time- particularly that of freezing it.

name: Dual Sawknives of the Void
description: This couple of dark blue knives seems to flicker in and out of existence, and the teeth of the blades rotate quickly, and silently.

name: Unforseen Expiration
description: It shoots supercharged radioactive crystals at a alarming rate, with a neat little glowy blade at the end. What else could a young lad want?

name: Light Cycle
description: Used in some game using lines and motorcycles. Leaves a wall-like surface of light behind it. Should probably be used on some grid or something. How does this turn on a 90 angle so well?

name: 8th Dimensional Pyramid
description: A pyramid that exists in all possible laws of physics. You're not sure what it's doing or what it looks like... but it's a pyramid. You are positively sure of that.

name: Crystalline Laptop of Darkness
description: This laptop infused with black magic is sure to be useful in keeping up with horror terror communications... Or you could use it for playing Slender, that works too.

name: Anti Spiral Overcoat
description: This overcoat contains the power of the hivemind known as the Anti Spiral.

name: Space Laser Sword
description: The pure white laser sword of a spaceman. Includes compass pommel.

name: Mage\'s Silver Sonic Rifle
description: A silver rifle chased with occult symbols that unleashes a sonic attack when the trigger is pulled.

name: Spirit Staff
description: Now you can summon ghosts to your heart's content.

name: Eiserne Drossel
description: "Iron Thrush" in German. The weapon itself is fairly lightweight, but the blade cuts through steel easily as butter. And your fingers, if you're not careful.

name: Outcast Power Armor
description: Provides massive defensive boosts and low offensive boosts. Sadly, the armor weights so much that it slows you down by an unreasonable amount. It's only a little bit stronger than its normal counterpart, but then again, it looks ten times more badass.

name: Obsidian Candy Shard Medagaburyu
description: The rockets launched from this axe/bazooka contain shards of Obsidian Rock Candy that rip apart your enemies if they are anywhere near the explosion.

name: Amesidian Chain
description: A chain made of a magical amethyst/obsidian alloy, this is sure to be capable of ripping apart your enemies.

name: Shadow Wreath
description: Cloaked in shadows, you radiate an aura of tangible darkness which turns aside the attacks of your foes. Besides, black is slimming.

name: Obsidian Steam Gloves of the Alchemical Wizard
description: These Obsidian gloves are imbued with the power of an arcane master whom once called upon the power of the flames of hell itself.

name: Holo-Bow
description: Shooting arrows and fancy light shows, this bow projects the light arrows directly from the bow itself! As such, you'll never need a quiver again! Sadly, though, being made of light, the arrows don't actually do much by themselves.

name: Shadearang
description: Sharp, pointy, and extremely stylish. No anime hero (or wannabe) should be caught dead without these. Unfortunately, these are way too big to be worn.

name: Dress Piece
description: The dress still looks the same, but it's purple like the cod piece and the straps and belt match the pattern on waist band. Also there's little cods hanging on the hem of the dress. This isn't a fashion statement, it's a fashion question.

name: Legend of The Swiss Army Pride
description: The pride and joy of a Swiss army now mixed with your favorite video game. Courtesy of - ...how accurate is this even?

name: Deadly Strong Annihilator
description: This is an exterminator's dream tool, not only killing bugs, but mankind as well!

name: Fancy Santa Cape
description: Just as luxurious as you'd expect for a blinged out Saint Nick. Not even a bit of coal dust on it.

name: iPhonulet
description: Ever wanted to look at an iPhone at an even smaller size down your neck? No? I don't see how you possibly came to that conclusion!

name: Double Temporal Reacharound Sawstaff
description: With blades powered by the unceasing motion of the clocks inlaid in either end, this powerful artifact of timekeeping and spinning blades is capable of cutting even the fabric of time- although, it seems like that isn't really special with this game.

name: Needles of Further Teleportation
description: A solid, simultaneous hit with these pulsating dark blue and orange needles will send lesser foes straight to the Furthest Ring, where they'll never be able to eat cake again. Truly a fate worse than death.

name: My Little Claymore
description: A greatsword that spreads the magic of friendship through overly aggressive means. Nothing says "let's be friends" quite like a giant pink sword to the neck.

name: 8th Keyblade of Skaia
description: It is said that this keyblade changes depending on its wielder, reflecting their desires, hopes, and fears. Perhaps it can also give you a clue on who you were always meant to be... Oh wait, that's what this whole game was supposed to be for in the first place.

name: Daenathi, Render of Souls
description: This dark artifact siphons the air from the light around it, and every chop echoes with the screams of a million fallen warriors. Neat.

name: Spademore
description: When you combine the two weapons you create a large claymore with the center dug in to make it a shovel mix. Now you can cut down enemies and dig their graves at the same time.

name: Trusty Sawknives
description: Because shards of metal with other shards of metal whirling around them is something to trust.

name: Bach\'s Favorite Baton
description: This baton fills the air with Baroque fugues.

name: The Monomace
description: A stick, attached to a long chain, attached to something that looks remarkably like someone smashed up a laptop into a ball and painted it black and white, with a red decal. Looking at it gives you a vague feeling of despair.

name: Hard-Boiled Fedora
description: This hat may or may not be the same hat that you wore in your childhood. It's still awesome.

name: Veil of the Sun
description: Draped in impenetrable and pure sunlight, watch your enemies cower from your might. Or, maybe they just can't see.

name: UAC Marine Armor
description: This green armor is fit for the finest of the space marines, demons shall bow before your might, however you... Actually... Damn! You move fast in this thing, like REALLY fast, like I can dodge anything fast!

name: Sonic-speed Shoes
description: Wearing these just makes you feel like you've gotta go fast. You're running around at the speed of sound! And, strangely enough... you can stand on ceilings with these...

name: Spaghetti
description: A combination of noodles, sauce, and meatballs, decent food but nothing that can compare to what mom makes.

name: Gasmask of the Father
description: As if you weren't already unstoppable! Rid yourself of those pesky toxic fumes, AND increase your equip load by 15%! Cartwheeling in heavy armor has never been such a breath of fresh air!

name: EMIN3M Poster
description: A poster of the white rapper, EMIN3M, for his single, Lose Yourself.

name: Dimensional Wand
description: Once this wand is poked into that one guy's eye at 88 miles per hour... we'll travel through TIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIIME

name: Laser Pole
description: A ski pole doubling as a laser sword in your designated color. It would be wise to sheath it while riding the ski lift.

name: Inline Skates
description: Shoes. With wheels. Just kick. Go fast. What could possibly go wrong?

name: Chainsaw of the Light Kingdom
description: The black aspects of the chess board have been entirely removed, replaced with the golden colors of prospit. It would relish converting underlings to grist, but it would rather carve topiaries.

name: Unbreakable Ski Pole
description: A real hard ski pole... er, a real solid sports stick... a rigid, uh, bar of... slope-sliding?... dear God, is there any way to describe this thing without making it sound like a boner?

name: Subwoofer Moonboots
description: The classic bounce-around fun shoes, now tricked out with totally sick bass based speakers.

name: Li\'l Wolverines
description: Seel gloves with three miniature chainsaws in a claw fashion. They bear the scribblings of grubby, immature fingers.

name: Hotpocket Hoodie
description: A firey hoodie bearing a dragon print. Twin flamethrowers are mounted on the shoulders. The pocket conceals an electric hand warmer.

name: Guide to the Force
description: Turns out the Force isn't just in movies- and this tome teaches you how to use it to throw imps around with it! No lightning, though.

name: Sherlock\'s Shredder
description: Because nothing cuts like the TRUTH.

name: Shenanigan Slicer
description: The iridescent blades of this chainsaw seem to radiate the sounds of crying, laughter, and rage at the same time- and when they hit anything, peculiar events ensue. Usually involving something getting cut, but still.

name: Skaian Shortcuts
description: With this, you can cut right to the end. No, literally.

name: Temporal Tempest
description: Tearing through those who would trump this tempest of titanium and time 'till the tick-tock stops. (Which it won't.)

name: Venomous Disco Bow
description: Like the 1970's, this bow was created when some wise guy decided to put snake venom on a bow. It is now very good for dancing and gets you all the ladies.

name: Rainbow Staff
description: This technicolor staff appears to have been scribbled on with colored pencils of every hue imaginable. For some reason, this increases its inherent magical abilities sevenfold. Maybe it's because of all the mesmerizing colors...

name: Time-Boy Alpha
description: With all the functionality of a wrist-mounted computer, you can [mostly] seamlessly travel through time! Now with 110% more fresh beats!

name: Ice Pole
description: A cold, transparent ski pole. Remember not to bring it inside, or it will melt.

name: Claws of Pimpeta
description: You're the top... cat... with these gilded claws.

name: Ninja rifle of Rainbowland
description: It's one of the legendary weapons of The Rainbow! No, it's really just a legendary piece of shit. But it's power level... it's... OVER 90! Ok yeah that doesn't change anything.

name: Monster Girl Quest Complete
description: An RPG/hentai visual novel in which you REALLY want to lose sometimes.

name: Majora-Possessed Captain Planet\'s Undefeatable Timey Wimey Air Man-Powered Volcanic Spoon
description: "You might as well keep your distance and wrap it in caution tape." -That one guy who almost died from a spoon

name: Jill-O-Lantern
description:
Hail the pumpkin queen
Soul food and flaming death rays
From her mouth and eyes.

name: Goats: Infinite Typewriters
description: Book one in the Infinite Pendergast Cycle, another story detailing the unending death and rebirth of the simulated multiverse. Despite the plurality of the title it includes only one goat.

name: Book of Matches
description: A small book of matches. Used for making things that aren't on fire stop being not on fire.

name: Wand of Akemi
description: A wand with... A shield on it? And a gear? Youre not really sure what you can do with it, but when you pick it up you feel an uncontrollable urge to smooch a pink haired girl.

name: Shovelken
description: You have no idea what kind of ninja would use shurikens with pointy shovel heads instead of the usual blades. Maybe if you dig really deep, you might find an answer.

name: Woolen Axe of Chained Detonations
description: Spinning blades of explosive wool. Better start counting sheep. And trees. And imps. Won't be many of those left for long.

name: Hatsune Chainsledge
description: With all the danger of hurting yourself, only with more leeks and blue hair!

name: Stachegyouji Chainswordfan
description: A chainsaw/sword/fan mashup with a mustache motif. Truly glorious.

name: Bonehead\'s Mirror
description: Wow, anything you see in this mirror looks like a skeleton of what it once was.

name: Cairo Chainsaw
description: This chainsaw scares you. It seems do to things as soon as the thought crosses your mind- IT'S ALREADY THERE.

name: Rapier Wand
description: This weapon looks like a rapier, but it is smaller and can be used for magical purposes.

name: Wizard\'s Athame
description: As opposed to the kind of athame used by non-wizards obviously.

name: Bear Sticks
description: Have you ever wanted to poke someone's eyes out with Chopsticks that have Bear Claws on the ends? No? Well you probably do now.

name: Explos the Mighty
description: The fabled Axe of legend, capable of slicing through the thickest of hide and blowing up the farthest of meat puppets. It's like an Axe and a Sniper Rifle got married in a Bomb Shelter.

name: Demonic Ring of Ultimate Evil
description: This pitch black ring is covered in strange runes, seems to turn you invisible, and is giving you really bad vibes.

name: Radioactive Cloak
description: This cloak is glowing green and is probably giving you radiation poisoning from wearing it, but uh, its giving some degree of protection so there's that.

name: Cracked Bone Smashing Mirror
description: Weird this isn't glass... You think it's polished bone but then how did it crack.... oh who cares, you just want to kill some imps with it.

name: Eternal Mirror Blade Of Nike
description: So wait does it mean the goddess Nike or the shoe company? Either way it's sure to slice imps.

name: Vacuum Gloves
description: Pull enemies into your grasp using the vacuums held within the palms of these gloves.

name: Journeyer\'s Mirror
description: This magic mirror, once belonging to a Journeyer, has the magic ability to lift enemies into the air so that they can fall to their doom.

name: Icebreakalisaw
description: Half of teeth burning hot, the other frigidly cold, this chainsaw guarantees that the severe differences will cut nearly anything like warm... then cold... then warm again...butter.

name: Newtonian Sorcelacerator
description: A laser-bladed saw. And on top of that, it is shooting fire. This is the best idea you've had in a long time.

name: Dark Night Chainsaw
description: How can a chainsaw even be this cool, this dark, this brooding, you ask yourself. Then you remember that it's just a chainsaw.

name: Sidereal Chainsaw
description: A star covered chainsaw. Pretty.

name: Exploding Clockpunk Card Spewer
description: This thing shoots out cards. Or it's supposed to, at least - instead it spews a mix of cards and rusty, broken gears, practically exploding in your hand whenever it fires. Somehow it never breaks down anyway.

name: Spiked Electric ID Disk
description: This ID disk has been souped up with electric spear heads

name: Shady Garb
description: As they always say, dressing well is the key to winning on the battlefield. Wait, who says that? I'm pretty sure nobody has ever said that.

name: Broken Time
description: The gear-disk is now cracked and reflective it seems to randomly change the flow of time of whatever it reflects, sending things into rewind and fast forward.

name: Oktavia\'s Deadly Composer
description: Not even the power of the gods of luck and fate could repress the sadness of Oktavia von Seckendorff. The haft has violin strings along it, and the scythe's leaden blade cuts a song through the air, a gentle piece heavy with the eventual fate of all Mahou Shoujo.

name: Ivory Six-Shooter
description: The pistol of choice for all knife-loving spies.

name: DiscoSpark
description: This powerful artifact from the planet Cybertron turns anything it touches into a funkbot. It ruminates so much power and groove it can be an orb and a cube at the same time.

name: Sickle of The Green Sun
description: This sickle's blade hums with the power of the green sun all in the palm of your hand!

name: Blue Ecto-Gel
description: A restorative gel made by scientists in the underworld. It glows strangely, which makes you sort of suspicious of it. It's an even bigger bitch to get off of you than the Medi-Gel.

name: Un-Powered Cord Sword
description: Basically just a power cord with a handle. Pretty useless without batteries.

name: Ink Blotter
description: A yo-yo doused in ink. Not much more we can say about it, mostly because the yo-yo stole all of our ink. I'm writing this in my own blood right now.

name: Skull Cap
description: Tight fitting hat with a wicked skull pattern.

name: Acid Quill Cloak
description: A cloack covered in acid-tipped bristles. it provides decent defense at no greater cost than severe chemical burns!

name: Sevith\'s Explorin Duds
description: A set of rugged adventuring clothes belonging to a brave a just man. Wearing them makes you want to start a big project.

name: Electromagnet
description: A magnet buzzing with the power of electricity. Stronger than normal.

name: Thorned Yo-Yo of Past Sacrifice
description: Quivering as though it would break apart at any moment this grimdark Yo-Yo smites your enemies to the furthest ring where it should have been left.

name: Spirits Be Gauntlet
description: Forget magic! Forget science! Face your extra-dimensional foes with the power of RELIGION!

name: Bladed Scarf
description: A scarf made out of razor sharp edges. You aren't really sure how you wear this with out it cutting your head off, but it sure looks cool...

name: Pokemon Alpha Version
description: This special, limited edition (and totally fanmade) version of Pokemon adorns the HOLY DIETY OF THE POKEMON UNIVERSE on its cover. Now that you know the secrets of the universe, your admiration of the god llama monster feels hollow...

name: Returning Non-Stick Frying Pan of Hellfire+2
description: This pan, once wielded by the mighty admin Brashman, is guaranteed to cook your bacon extra-crispy, and bash offenders of site rules mightily with its thwacks.

name: Hand Crossbow
description: On the one hand you aren't sure if you are actually STRONG enough to pull the string back on a crossbow that's actually a threat to an imp and if you use two of these at once it will be really awkward to load but on the other hand, dual wielding crossbows.

name: Solar Time Trenchcoat
description: Harness the power of using the sun's position in the sky to tell time with this blinding trenchcoat.

name: Teatops
description: Circular shades with groovy computing powers, man.

name: Red Mage\'s Solar Hat
description: This stylish hat with a fancy gold rim and a feather allows you to make use of the power of the sun while looking awesome casting spells or dicing monsters with your sword. It looks especially good if you have long hair!

name: Lacrosse Railgun Of The Green Sun
description: A lacrosse stick, it glows green as if it was some type of sportsman's tool that actually played Lacrosse on the green sun. Wait a sec... who plays Lacrosse anyways?

name: Smashing Rhythm-club
description: A stringed club capable of some EXTREME SHREDDING. -Insert guitar solo here-

name: Rocket Bike
description: Now you can look totally fly as you soar across your planet. From the toughest greaser to the sweetest Loli, no one looks bad on a Rocket Bike.

name: Melody Scarf
description: A light scarf weighed down only because it has those revolving cylinders you find in music boxes attached to its ends. Sometimes you imagine a few notes of a haunting tune emanating from it.

name: Crystal Ball Earthtop
description: All the fun of surfing the web and playing your games, but slightly obscured by the blurred continents of the Earth. Darn it Australia, get out of the way.

name: Mann Co. Standard
description: Tried and tested by licensed (crazed) assasins.

name: Manta Ray Plush
description: A plush of one of the best animals in existence......a Manta Ray.

name: Shark Plush
description: This shark has been your best friend since you were little.

name: Operator\'s Final Slam
description: Just looking at this hammer gives you some seriously sinister vibes. Fortunately, it seems to have the same effects on your foes, so if you keep your eyes away from your weapon, you should be fine... in theory.

name: Violin Machine Gun
description: So it's a Violin Rifle with an extended magazine, AND a select-fire knob? Huh. Alright.

name: Heartseeking Timestabbing Horn Thing
description: When thrown, this ridiculous-looking knife becomes displaced in time, emerging where it's most needed in the chest of one of your near-future enemies. You don't know what's worse - being stabbed by a time-traveling knife out of nowhere, or having a weird skull clock thing lodged in your midsection and having to pull it out in front of your peers. How embarrassing.

name: Dream Bubbles
description: "In his dream, he is the prophet. [...] Its him." Oh man, you can't wait to read this amazing book by Charles Dutton, its sure to give you insight about future events in your session!

name: Rainbow Reflecter
description: This blade made of pure shiny opal can reflect all light based attacks back as rainbow blasts.

name: Thermal Trident Of Two Breaths
description: This trident contains the power of the goddess Chione and the dragon Odahviing. It's thermal wrath shall freeze your enemys until they feel burnt and burn them until they die of cold flames.

name: Claws of the Freezing Death
description: A cold poison drips from these claws, reported to leave the victim freezing to death from the inside out. You hope to not have this used against you.

name: Claws of the Burning Disease
description: A mere prick of these claws sends the unfortunate victim into a slow, burning fever that renders their internal organs damaged beyond repair.

name: Dragon Trench Coat
description: A trench coat made from tough dragon hide and covered in dragon scales. It also features a detachable dragon hood with silver horns in case you wanted to look dangerous. Firebreathing powers not included.

name: Anubis\' Time Shieldblade
description: This blade features an oval shield instead of a hilt and gets strapped to your upper arm. You might want to be prepared for some highly unfortunate - yet amusing - mishaps that come with learning to use the odd design.

name: Kid Icarus: Uprising
description: Join Pit once again on his new quest to defeat Hades and the forces of the underworld.

name: Squiddle Beanie
description: It's a beanie that literally looks like a squiddle, complete with little legs that hang down over your head. Wow, how annoying.

name: Mistletoe Scarf
description: It smells like Christmas. And keeps you warm.

name: Blackjack Dog Tags
description: Four dog tags with the Heart, Diamond, Spades, and Clubs shapes. It is very sharp, pretty handy if you need quick defense. Just pull them out and slice someone.

name: Gatling Guitar
description: The neck of this guitar doubles as a high powered machine gun.

name: DOUBLE-BARREL RAPID-FIRE BACKPACK OF EXPLODING ASCENSION
description: It kinda reminds you of that time when you got those random items stuck in that rocket pack, except this time it's fully functional and spewing live grenades out of both orifices.

name: Dancerbane
description: All light that reflects off of this discoball poisons all those that touch it, great for killing those pesky disco-moles that love to dance on your bed.

name: Nokia Mirrorblade
description: This phone has been scientifically changed into a reflective sword that shall never break.... until it does.

name: Piercing Judgment Arspearus
description: Adorned with the "holy" rings of Arceus, this spear is just brimming with the power of the GODS. Or monsters. Or monster gods. Either way be careful with it, numbnuts.

name: Telescopic Laser
description: A handheld device resembling a pen. At the touch of a button, it extends to three times its original length. Extended like this, it fires blasts of concentrated light.

name: Shadow King\'s Chain-Spear
description: Not to be confused with the chain spear, this is a shadow rod with a chainsaw at one end, and instead of teeth, mighty royal spearheads that only the shadow of King Arthur could be mad enough to create.

name: Candy Corn Handgun
description: Never before has justice been this hard-boiled, nor sweet.

name: Avatar: The Last Airbender Complete Boxed Set
description: Everything that changed when the Fire Nation attacked, and what happened after. This thing is enormous! You could probably spend days watching through all of it.

name: Defense\'s Suit
description: Don't you have anything better to do than flash that badge everywhere? You graduated from law school. We get it.

name: Fancy Thief of Breath God Tier Suit
description: Really sharp looking. I almost cut my eyes. Really, that is one fine suit.

name: Ancient Seraphim\'s Divine Strong-Arm
description: This golden shotgun is covered in runes and inscriptions. Emblazoned along the side reads "By the rage of a thousand gods you shall lay the Old Ones down with many a buckshot of great righteousness and furious anger."

name: Magic Mirror
description: This handy mirror can be used to send you back to the beginning of a dungeon!

name: Sunshine Discoball
description: This ball is lighting up the entire area with the intensity of a star! Time to blind your enemies with it!

name: Laser Discodriver
description: Using this weapon, you will shine a light on disco once more!

name: Assassin\'s Hyper Reflective Spine-Chiller
description: The last thing your victim will see before freezing to the core is a blinding ice-cold light. Or you could just hit them.

name: Battletoads Cartridge
description: "Hello, yes, is this GameStop? Yeah, I'd like to preorder the new Battletoads."

name: Sylph of Blood Godly Exoskeleton
description: An outfit truly fit for a God, at least one who's a Sylph of Blood.

name: Reflective Baseball Bat
description: This bat is nice and reflective which makes it great for hitting those pesky projectile attacks right back.

name: M8ro\'s Gr8 Yo-Bola
description: This great yo-yo grants luck to you and spells doom for your enemies.

name: Stellar Strikers
description: OH MY GOD YOUR HANDS ARE METEORS THIS HURTS SO MUCH

name: Tingle Cosplay
description: A bright green spandex outfit, rumored to be what the fairies wear.

name: Giant Novelty Sombrero
description: Where ludicrously wide brimmed hats just weren't ludicrously wide brimmed enough, there exists the Giant Novelty Sombrero. Imps have a hard time attacking through all the Americanization.

name: Kiss of Hate
description: A black umbrella with a 9mm Baretta serving as a handle. The gun is purple and is adorned in black spades. This is incredibly unwieldy but undeniably stylish (and dangerous).

name: Time-Space Chaintinuum
description: As the teeth on this chainsaw approach the speed of light, the slower you move through time!

name: Creative Notepad
description: No satanic ritual is complete without this guy dumping black paint all over everything. Now, LET'S GET CREATIVE!

name: White Hatchflag
description: A simple white flag with the blade of a hatchet on the end. Maybe you haven't given up!

name: Pi Yao Sword
description: Alchemizing this feels like cheating, somehow, but it's way better than actually trying to summon a wealth-loving creature with fake diamond like that weird journal suggested. And you got a cool-looking sword with a winged lion hilt out of it.

name: Prickly Pickaxe
description: This pickaxe has pins all over the iron bit, giving it more points for you to stab enemies with. It does leave a bloody mess after a battle though.

name: Hamlet Visor
description: The very visor a depressed prince would have worn to meet with the ghost of his father. If, you know, there'd been eye-shielding UV-protecting facegear back then.

name: Judgement Aversion Armour
description: Bright red armour decorated with actual, moving gear designs, advertised as skipping you through time to avoid killing shots 99.99% of the time! Unfortunately, with the amount of enemies you fight, the 0.01% can come in pretty often.

name: Prismatic Dragon Armor Trench Coat
description: Shining in colors of black and gold, this once noble armor has been tainted by the blood of the dragons of which the scales were drawn from and molded into a trench coat. This shimmering hide can flow in the wind like a cape and deflect attacks as well as regular armor.

name: Witch\'s Crown
description: Who says a witch cannot be queen?

name: Clockpunk Shieldblade
description: All those cogs and clock hands add about +9999 pure awesome. Sadly this doesn't assist much in battle. The shield portion that fits over your arm has a large gear; it sticks over the edge away from you.

name: Flickering Melody Scarf
description: A long, airy yellow scarf that flickers you in and out of visibility, emanating a cheery tune. Very useful for distracting enemies, who end up aiming at a wisp of music while you dodge aside.

name: Steampunk Alchemic Cleaver of Gloves
description: A steam-powered, gear-covered cleaver made out of gloves decorated with alchemic symbols. You're not sure how you're going to attack with this but at least it has an interesting steampunk atmosphere around it. Somehow.

name: Halloween Scythe
description: This scythe is too spooky.

name: Rapid Rabbit Racer
description: A stuffed bunny wearing a racing helmet. You... guess that's kind of cute?

name: Lightning Nose Hair Ball
description: The user grabs a ball with their nose hair whip, electrifies it, and throws it at the enemy. Don't ask where the ammunition comes from.

name: Jousting Riflance
description: A lance with a trigger on the handle. You're not actually sure how useful this is, but it's pretty awesome.

name: GameBro Protest Sign
description: A sign that reads "Down with GameBro!!!" You're not actually sure why anyone would want to protest GameBro.

name: Pointy Anime Sun-glass Scouters of Temporal Tactics
description: A pair of uncomfortably pointy and luminescent shades that are capable of displaying the stats of the person or underling you're looking at- oh god you can't see anything through these.

name: Spooky Scary Slinkyscythe
description: A deadly scythe attached to the end of a children's spring toy. What could possibly go wrong?

name: Halloween Tombscythe
description: A scythe with a blade made of stone. The blade reads "Here lies Halloween. He was a good man."

name: Steam-Fueled Clockpunk Shieldblade
description: It doesn't look too much different from a non-powered version - except there are two rotating gears on the shield portion's edge. Someone who stumbles into them can be painfully scraped. ...actually, scraped isn't strong enough a word.

name: Proto Visor
description: The ultimate of visors for the mysterious loner. Or for the evil second-in-command, if you happen to be from a cartoon instead.

name: Aversion Armour Z
description: Robotic armour of a bright red hue, it flicks you through time to avoid attacks. You'd think the gear designs on it - somehow moving? - would clash with the futuristic theme, but they blend surprisingly well.

name: Flickering Scarf of the Midnight Melody
description: You don't know why a scarf of MIDNIGHT melody is still bright yellow, but there it is. It retains its limited invisibility-granting powers, anyway, and the music it eminates as a distraction sounds very classy.

name: Rabid Rifle-Raising Rabbit Racer
description: This incredible combo has left you with a rabid rabbit that can rapidly r- er, uh... Ugh. It's a stuffed rabbit with a racing helmet and a rifle, okay?

name: Sparkling Fairyscythe
description: A scythe with a blade that sparkles when you swing it. It is both deadly and adorable.

name: Lumber Light
description: A chainsaw that shines a brilliant red. The beams of light themselves are equally as sharp.

name: Spiked Club
description: A club with some spikes. Just like the time you went to that club and they spiked the punch, only it's a literal club with literal spikes and has nothing to do with that incident so you have no idea why that even had to be brought up.

name: Perforating Raydent of Light
description: You can "zap" AND "pap" your enemies with this new, improved Raydent. By "pap," of course, we mean fill with tiny holes.

name: Chain of Nightmares
description: For your ghosts, ghouls, and generally otherworldly needs.

name: Mach-Daddy 5 Holiday Disco Scepter
description: This ultra-reflective checkered cane lets you boogie at mind-boggling speed. It's time to get down like it's going out of style! Because seriously it is, so you better hurry up!

name: Seizure Spinner
description: This is probably the most powerful Yo-yo you will ever find. Too bad it gives you headaches to look at it. And you need to use your other hand to shield your eyes.

name: Boatmurdered Themed Flash Drive
description: A flash drive containing an old version of dwarf fortress, along with some digital fan works, most notably the Chronicles of Boatmurdered.

name: Biggoron the inside Sword
description: A sword with endless pun potential.

name: Pimpeta\'s Adamantine Action Claws
description: Nobody can question your superiority with the diamond-encrusted golden claws. Nobody. ;33

name: Glowlight
description: Harnesses the power of whatever's in a Glowstick to shine in nifty colors.

name: Knife Time
description: Who the hell designed these things? You read the description on one of the knives: "Ever wanted to kill someone with time? Now you can! Batteries not included". Damn. You really needed some batteries.

name: Aperture Science Blue and Orange Mage\'s Jacket
description: The jacket has been modified, to allow the temporary creation of portals within it's own fabric. The wearer can now transmit their form from one spacial location to another using the jacket to teleport itself, violating many of the laws of physics. In short, blinking!

name: 9th Dimensional Pyramid
description: This pyramid is all possible things, all at once... as long as they're shaped like a pyramid.

name: Eternity\'s Keyed Shotgun of Infinite Probability
description: This beauty seems to radiate time itself ticking and whirring away lke a clock. I'll bet you can make anythings life never even happen anywhere. Literally...

name: Dress of the Green Ocean
description: This dress is imbued with the power of first guardians who happen to be marine mammals.

name: The Blow-Timer
description: Keep your jobs organized, and properly timed.

name: Jumper Oar
description: The plugs on this oar seem to enable it to adjust its shape and length if electrical current is applied.

name: Throwing Amulet
description: This necklace has both an amulet AND knives that come out of it! Unfortunately, the knives are fairly weak and small, making them ineffective in combat. But they look kind of cool!

name: Replica Cleaner Scythe
description: Between cutting things with your scythe, you can sweep the floor, as this replica cleaner scythe has both bristles and a cutting edge.

name: Bonejangles Attire
description: A lovely piece of formal evening wear with a skeletal motif.  Quite popular with the undead.

name: Lorenz Butterfly Attractor
description: This tiny glass ornament, marked with a hypnotic swirl of red and pink, emits an enchanting scent that attracts butterflies to your garden. Just make sure you don't step on them.

name: Scull of the Blood Heirs
description: Using this magical oar, you shall call upon the most ancient bonds to the others and use that power to end your foes!

name: Bleeding Bond Keyblade
description: This Keyblade is supercharged with the Aspect of Blood, with the power of unity drawing forth the Blood from your enemies.

name: Frozen Barracuda
description: These chilling gloves form pike-topped pikes out of ice and launch them from the palm at your foes. The only downside is, you have to refill them with water after every shot. And fish.

name: Space-time Orbiter
description: A mysterious Yo-yo that appears and reappears in different places at different points in time. You find it covered in blood that mysteriously matches your own.

name: Daedric War Axe
description: A war axe of ebony and the blood of daedra, often wielded by those native to the planes of Oblivion- or those who slay them.

name: Rocket Powered Anime Heads-Up Display
description: This gasmask has GOT to defy every law that your bro has ever set for you and more on top of being the most badass thing anyone has the graces of seeing.

name: Blade of SPAAAAAACE
description: This polearm shines with the light of a billion stars, and every so often you think you can hear it whispering excitedly about traveling among them some day. You better keep a tight grip on this one, cause if you let go, it might soar into the atmosphere...

name: Galaxia
description: The weapon of the most meta of knights, you slice down your foes in a rip-off fighting style similar to a certain hero from Hyrule. You have the strangest urge to build a giant ship with your face on it to get your nonspecific revenge.

name: Leek Sword
description: And they said the leekspin was a joke... Maybe if you stabbed them a few times with this extremely sharp leek, you'll knock some sense into them.

name: Shocking Guitar
description: A weap-- instrument that never needs to be tuned. It has used modern science to replace pesky metal strings with PURE ELECTRICITY. (caution, wear gloves while using)

name: Watershades
description: Perfectly round, these glasses somehow have lenses of water.

name: Chaos Emerald (Purple)
description: This is one of the seven Chaos Emeralds... You wonder what happens if you can get all 7?

name: Chaos Emerald (Cyan)
description: This is one of the seven Chaos Emeralds... You wonder what happens if you can get all 7?

name: Chaos Emerald (White)
description: This is one of the seven Chaos Emeralds... You wonder what happens if you can get all 7?

name: Chaos Emerald (Green)
description: This is one of the seven Chaos Emeralds... You wonder what happens if you can get all 7?

name: Chaos Emerald (Red)
description: This is one of the seven Chaos Emeralds... You wonder what happens if you can get all 7?

name: Chaos Emerald (Blue)
description: This is one of the seven Chaos Emeralds... You wonder what happens if you can get all 7?

name: Chaos Emerald (Yellow)
description: This is one of the seven Chaos Emeralds... You wonder what happens if you can get all 7?

name: Poly Mage\'s Hat
description: This is the preferred hat of the wizard of many colours. Psychedelically coluored, it has a feather with a rainbow luster, and a flashing polychromite rim. It will make you look brazenly stylish no matter your strife specibus. Or that's what it says on the inside label, along with washing instructions. YOU think it looks gaudy.

name: Aperture Science Turretbrero
description: Cave Johnson here, introducing our latest breakthrough in personal fashion and self-defense technology: the Aperture Science Sombrero-Mounted Sentry Turret. Not only does it keep the sun out of your eyes, but if one gun on your head isn't enough, it comes with three extra turrets to mount on your sombrero-mounted turret!

name: Ghost of Christmas Future
description: This item is a rather long black trench coat that seemingly has a bit of dark fog rolling off of it along with a feeling of Christmas cheer. A small candy cane is embroidered in the left chest area.

name: Aces Hoodie
description: Not only do you look good, you also look... DANGEROUS.

name: Crow Suit
description: A creepy-looking suit with tattered-looking edges which, upon closer inspection, appear to be made of a large number of crow feathers. Ability to fly and accompanying murder of crows not included.

name: Heavy Metal Chainsaw
description: It's not decorated in Black Sabbath stickers, unfortunately. It weights a lot, and is made of sole metal.

name: Magical Girl Pistol
description: It's frilly. It's pink. It never runs out of ammo, apparently.

name: Ice Skates
description: The wheels of your roller skates have been replaced with blades. You could surely make a few heads turn, or roll, as you (un)gracefully skate across the frozen waters. That is, if you could even find any on your land, although if you can't, now's a good time to put your consorts to proper use and have them build an ice skating rink.

name: iSkate
description: Wow, Apple must be really desperate.

name: Steel-Toe Skates
description: Perfect for charging at your enemies and giving them the boot. (Don't actually give them the boot. You do not have an infinite supply of boots.)

name: Batskates of Nrub\'yiglith
description: Skates with baseball bat-like clubs on their backs and tendrils of grimdark smoke curling from them. Really? Grimdark baseball skates?

name: Bedrock Skates
description: Skates made completely of bedrock. Damn, why the hell did you make these? It's pretty much impossible to move! (But it really fricking hurts to get hit by them.)

name: Amethyst Dancer\'s Skates
description: Translucent stone skates that strangely make one more nimble rather than weigh one down.

name: Skates of the Lost Kingdom
description: An old pair of skates with a complex sigil emblazoned on their sides, now too faded to identify. Perhaps these were passed on from king to king, generation after generation, in an ancient country until they came into your possession through the wonders of alchemy.

name: Bouncy Skates
description: These skates are now propelled by the rolling of bouncy balls. This would be a cute idea, except that bouncy balls don't roll. They bounce. (And now, so do you.)

name: Computerized Skates
description: As you skate the web, this pair of digital footwear leaves streaks of electricity behind you.

name: Hoop Skates
description: You now have hula hoops instead of wheels. Hopefully you didn't expect anything actually useful out of this combination.

name: Melody Skates
description: As you skate on those woodwind-bladed roller blades, a beautiful flute melody follows you around.

name: CD Skates
description: A set of inline skates that glide along on what look to be miniature CDs instead of wheels. They also look really fragile.

name: Death Arcana Scythe
description: With this scythe, you won't need a divination class to predict your enemies' impending dooms.
