name: Not So Hard-Boiled Revolver
description: Your once hard-boiled pistol has become a little... fuzzy.

name: Fortune-Telling Bubble Wand
description: Let those underlings question their future before it happens only seconds later!

name: Glittering Green Ski Pole
description: Everything but the handle and basket of this ski pole is made out of some kind of extremely hard, transparent green crystal. Its lustrous green shine will be the last thing your enemies see.

name: Retractable Skis
description: A pair of skis that can be stored using a simple telescopic cylinder mechanic. They'll be so much easier to carry!

name: Squiddles Headset
description: A squiddle-fied headset, good for computing on the go AND comfortable!

name: Personal Digital Goggles
description: Now you can use obsolete technology on the go!

name: The Ferryman\'s Scythe
description: Makes a good replacement weapon if your chain blades need repairing.

name: Disco Derby Skates
description: These inline skates now have afros perched on their toes. Have fun getting laughed at.

name: Reflective Light-Warping Skates
description: These skates reflect light every which way with the small prisms that decorate their entire length. You're not sure that it will actually have any particular effect, but it's nice to pretend.

name: Angelic Handgun
description: It's more than just holy - what you see is a handgun full of God's power. White as snow, it serves the righteous death to sinners.

name: Musical Skates
description: The wheels of these inline skates have been replaced with music box cylinders. They don't provide much of a tactical advantage, but now you have your own soundtrack when you decide to skate.

name: Spiral Thought Overcoat
description: As you wear this, you can feel all the twists and spirals of the thought patterns of people.

name: Speed of the Hurricane
description: These skates let you move so fast, you leave behind a trail of miniature hurricanes. You could wipe out an entire street just by skating down it... back and forth for several hours.

name: Green Sun Nuclear Splitter
description: A nuclear axe with a blade so vastly large and horrifically sharp you could split that sun up there, the one far, far more vast than your universe. But please, please don't try it.

name: Combpubeanie
description: A computer, within a beanie, wired directly to your brain via a generously large afro comb.

name: Inline Rifles
description: Whoever attached the two rifles on each of these skates must've been some kind of derby mobster.

name: Malpractice Core
description: This core sure does love performing surgery: especially when there isn't any anesthesia around. Also, screaming. Boy does it love the sound of screaming.

name: Swinging 1975
description: It seems you just stuck the discoball onto the whip and made a sort of glowy 70's style ornament. It's time to rewrite the laws of physics into the laws of funky disco groove!

name: Antique Claws
description: These claws, despite being used by generations of skilled hunters, are still great choices for a quick win.

name: Shaded Anime Safety Goggles
description: These goggles will protect your eyes from the sun and any physical threats. Or at least they would, if you started wearing them on your eyes, instead of your forehead where they get fogged up.

name: Temperament of the Void
description: Nothing is the frozen wastes, and yet Nothing is the scorching flames. Nothing is also this chainsaw, which uses both.

name: Cigar
description: Just so that you can entertain your mob-boss styled fantasies.

name: Boatmurdered Elephant Showdown Poster
description: On the item is an image of an elephant, in ink. On the item is an image of a dwarf, in ink. The elephant is badly wounded. The dwarf is dual-wielding swords. They are staring each other down. The artwork relates to the great battle in Boatmurdered.

name: Chain Backscratcher
description: A backscratcher at the end of a long chain. Granted, it's utterly useless for scratching your back now, but you guess it's an okay weapon.

name: Flag of the Doughnut Republic
description: Vive la pastr-... wait, that's rice.

name: CaquotEngdulAgo The Bloody Yo-yo
description: This is a polychromite Yo-yo. All craftsdwarfship is of the highest quality. It is encrusted with malachite, rust, and opal. It is encircled with bands of blood. It menaces with blades of obsidian. On the item is an image of Armok in Malachite. On the item is an image of a Hero in Rust. The Hero is pleading with Armok. The artwork relates to The Choice. On the item is an image of CaquotEngdulAgo, in Opal.

name: Glowing Scalpelscythe
description: A glowing scythe with the blade shaped vaguely like a scalpel. Its true purpose is a riddle wrapped in an enigma.

name: Chessboard Squiddle Beanie
description: It's a squiddle beanie with a chessboard pattern decorating it.

name: Plushy Jacket
description: An extremely comfy jacket that you could wear anytime (please do not wear it in hot or wet weather. We can not guarantee your safety).

name: R.O.C.K. the Robostaff
description: A rock staff with robotic qualities. A pair of robot eyes that occasionally fire laser beams are attached to the top.

name: Shout Stab
description: Never has screaming hurt this much.

name: Extra-Purple Poison Perfume
description: A sweet-smelling perfume fused with fatal acid and the energy of a purple gem. If you had to pick a word to describe the scent of this perfume, it would be "purple."

name: Swiss Omni-Weapon
description: Knives, hammers, guns, swords... why stick to one kind of weapon when you can combine them all into one and fold them together for compact storage?

name: Rubber Band
description: Small and stretchy, it can snap in a variety of slightly painful ways.

name: Bottle cap
description: The light metal cap off the top of a bottle.

name: Heatblade
description: The fastest way to remove wrinkles! Unfortunately, it also tends to remove other things, like the structural integrity of your clothes.

name: Chaos Magician\'s Hat
description: Decorated with color changing stars, this headgear from the cosmos allows the wearer to wield limitless control over entropy itself.

name: Precious Black Magic Skull Ring
description: It's a necromancer's ring of power, capable of some of the most influential black majyyks. Plus, it is some stylish shit.

name: Nintendium Armor of the Green Sun
description: You're not quite sure what goals that game developer had for this... VERY BRIGHT armor, but it's fun to wear anyways. Just don't wear it for too long, okay?
art: Nintendium Armor of the Green Sun.png

name: 10th Dimensional Pyramid
description: This pyramid exists from the last possible dimension that is so far out of our comprehension, NO ONE understands it.

name: First Blade
description: This blade is just one of a new breed of armaments that combine close-quarters combat with ranged proficiency.

name: Ahab\'s Cutterbuss
description: The most unheard of yet legendary piece of shit to ever exist. This Cutterbuss was used by Ahab himself to defend his ship against pirates that would often attempt to raid it. It's still a piece of shit though.

name: Potion Soaked Bandage
description: A Bandage that has been soaked in a Red Potion. You can practically smell the healing power of this thing.

name: Marble Wand
description: It's shiny, slick, and fresh from the magical chest!

name: Hacker\'s ID Disk
description: A darkened ID disk, laced with erratic and glowing red lines.

name: Dersite Pogotar of Law Keeping
description: A weaponized guitar used to keep law while entertaining your subjects!

name: Confectionary Chopper
description: This chainsaw, emblazoned <FONT COLOR="ff0000">[OBEY]</FONT> with the Betty Crocker <FONT COLOR="ff0000">[CONSUME]</FONT> symbol, will certainly let you finely <FONT COLOR="ff0000">[SUBMIT]</FONT> dice your foes!

name: Cogblades
description: The ruby cog teeth that have replaced the blades don't cut quite as well as the saw did - but they quickly turn everything to dust through some time shenanigans.

name: Euphraxia\'s Needle
description: It's not really a needle, but fairies are small enough to use needles for swords, right?

name: Suntanner\'s Shredder
description: For all of your beach-going butchery, this colorful, inflated, and somehow still funtional, chainsaw will serve you well! Probably.

name: Six Shot Skates
description: Metal skates with a six-shot chamber on each shoe. It still claims to be "More than enough to kill anything that moves.", as well as much more mobile!

name: Radio Wave
description: Skates constructed from spare radio parts and speakers, now you can roll in style. Well, if they worked.

name: Squiddles Backpack
description: A large red backpack with two squiddles swimming around printed on it. Its rather fashionable, even if its a bit useless when you have a sylladex.

name: Dungeonmaster\'s Christmas Spirit
description: A prickly staff covered in festive decorations. Perfect for displaying in the house during the holidays, or brutally murdering imps.

name: Modern Shieldblade
description: Alchemizing this made it stronger than the previous, steampunk iteration - but also much less cool. Hopefully it's worth it. You might get attached to the flashy lights eventually.

name: Proto C\'tri-Code Visor
description: This would be the ultimate of visors for the mysterious loner, if it weren't also a computer. The social networking you do on this thing kind of ruins it.

name: Flickering Rocket Scarf of the Midnight Melody
description: Not only can this near-insubstantial yellow scarf grant you invisibility and play music, it can now also allow you to fly. This is absolutely preposterous!

name: Spookier Scarier Jousting Riflescytheaslinky
description: A fearsome and deadly combo between weapons. On a scale of "not spooky" to "very spooky," you would say that this weapon is "pretty spooky."

name: Kusarigama
description: A traditional Japanese weapon that consists of a scythe on a metal chain.

name: ravetastic neckknife
description: When not in use, you can hang this flashing knife around your neck by the length of rope it bears.

name: M-Squeak Hammer
description: The bronze duck topping this hammer seems to squeak out the lyrics to "Can't Touch This" when used to hit things. Adorable, until you realize just how ear-piercingly smug that duck is.

name: Boomiken
description: For when those pesky ninja imps sneak up behind you. Not to be confused with the exploding shuriken.

name: Wooden Skull
description: An intricately carved skull made of wood. At least when this thing lies, there's no immediate indication.

name: Plague Skull
description: A rat skull infused with the essence of the Black Plague.

name: Garbage Club
description: Someone stuck this rotten apple on the end of a bone. It's a little bit disgusting, but at least it makes the bone slightly better for hitting things.

name: Sailor Uniform
description: Sail the seven seas, or emulate a certain duck- either works with this uniform.

name: Universe Destroyer
description: With the touch of this axe you can destroy an universe. Good luck trying to live up to the expectation of a world destroyer kid.

name: White Spacial Chainsaw / Black Temporal Rifle
description: Two weapons, equally dangerous, but entirely opposite- The time-changing rifle is swirled with red, the space-rending chainsaw with green.

name: Life Fiber
description: The fiber that makes up the essential life force of every living being... Oh, the potential.

name: Fluorite Guitar of Shockingly Lucky Strumming
description: This guitar changes shape based on how well you play it. Unfortunately, you have to rely on popup dice to strum to play since you cant reach the strings. The higher the roll, the better it plays.

name: Holy Hunter
description: It seems your logically impossible bow has now been blessed with the ability to shoot light arrows at the speed of, well... light.

name: Elven Petrifying Spellblade
description: This mystical gunblade shoots elvin magic that can change between offensive and defensive on the word, looking into the barrel turns you to--(shouldn't have looked)

name: Powered Chain Gloves
description: Well... At least you don't have to get those rubber gloves now.

name: Black RoBeast
description: These black laser claws are said to belong to a cybertronic wolf, they seem to suck things in like a black hole

name: Radioactive Laser-Guided Cobalt Darts
description: They'll never miss, because even being near these darts after they've been activated is dangerous.

name: Joker Of Pure Corruption
description: A two-sided card, which juxtaposes between a templar's spear and a demonic halberd when the dove on one side tastes tears or the demon tastes blood.

name: Acid Speedsters
description: Time to burn some faces off. If these acid-soaked skates don't burn off your heels first.

name: Soul flames of speed
description: These bladed blades have a soul-wounding byproduct as they're used to tear you apart. Insult to injury, anyone?

name: STRONG Ahab\'s Crosskates
description: A leg-mounted, scoped, and compact Ahab's Crosshairs on a set of tactical kevlar skates. The boot has studded toes for extra power.

name: Ancient Stampskates
description: Skates covered in legendary stamps, with great amounts of resiliance. These were worn by angry postmen in the riots of 1878 when the honorable men and women of the Postal Service stormed the golden archways of Congress to protest their jobs being replaced by magical carrier pigeons.

name: Clarification Flag
description: Freeze those imps in their tracks- not that you know how, but that's exactly what this yellow flag does- at least until they pause, and address their issues. Which should be quite a while, knowing imps.

name: Star Trek: The Next Generation Box Set
description: Ah, Captain Picard and those amazing speeches he always made... You have every episode. Every. Single. One.

name: Smily Hatchflag
description: Oh look, someone painted a smile on this hatchet-flag combo. Guess that puts a new meaning to dying happy.

name: Tarot Deck of the Paranormal
description: If you read the fate of someone with these enchanted cards, they will have to face their paranormal and dramatic readings.

name: The Stiffener
description: Solid as a brick and coursing with electricity, this backscratcher will ease that itch by making you feel nothing at all! For the rest of your life!

name: Blackscratcher
description: It's... a black backscratcher. You have no idea how this is functionally any different than the wooden one, but it looks a little more intimidating, you guess.

name: Midnight Murderer
description: A ten-foot backscratcher with a claw twisted and gnarled into the shape of a lethal blade. It blends in with the stars of the night sky, which makes it perfect for raising over your head before you bring it down on your unsuspecting victim.

name: Gardener\'s Blazing Blazer
description: Seems a bit too fancy and over the top for a gardener, but gardening really is serious business like you wouldn't believe. A fiery uniform like this one is 101% necessary.

name: R.O.C.K. the Rapid Roborabbitstaff
description: A rapid fire laser shooting stone robot staff, now with 100% more adorable rabbit ears!

name: Void Kugelshreiber
description: This deadly sword has a pen embedded in the handle that oozes an Inky darkness that consumes your enemies! It's hard to write with though.

name: Kugelpfanne
description: This legendary pen-pan combination is a razor sharp fountain pen that oozes inky black void that absorbs your enemies. The pan side is pretty cool too you guess.

name: The Lorax (Wild West Edition)
description: In this re-imagining, the Lorax instead challenges the Once-ler to a duel at high noon, and barely escapes with his life.

name: Tarzan Tier
description: The jungle and all of its baked goods are yours to command!

name: Randomized Flag
description: And with this orange flag, may you spread chaos, sporadically joining arbitrary items to form ungodly new monstrosities. Most of the time.

name: Suspended Flag
description: Lock underlings in place with this monochromatic grey flag, until you're ready to deal with them. Go ahead, take your time.

name: Dragon Adhesive Remover
description: In a desperate effort to get some of that Blue Ecto-Gel off of you, you made this thing. Out of the gel. Now you can't even drop it. But on the bright side, your hand is completely invulnerable from injury!

name: Yo Dude Pass Me the Brew
description: Essentially a red metal rod with a string on the end attached to a claw. When you and your bros are sitting around, getting wasted on the wicked elixir, you might need this righteous reacher to pick up some more.

name: Scratch-Sixty-Five
description: This pulsating technicolor backscratcher gives off sparks of various colors from time to time in a rhythm, as if to the beat of some 60's song.

name: Wrath of Pegasus
description: A glistening pink backscratcher that dons the wings and hoof of the mighty Pegasus in all the divine steed's glory, used to trample upon all those who would dare tickle the backs of the gods. Striking any such foe produces a glorious explosion of light that spares only the wielder from harm.

name: Faster Scratcher Blaster
description: For those tough itches that you just can't seem to catch.

name: Void Zapper
description: Bolts of black electricity fire from the clawed tip of this backscratcher that travel outside of conventional space and re-emerge right over your enemies' heads. With this, you can force lighting to strike the same place as many times as you want!

name: Challenge Mode Flag
description: This deep blue flag radiates a sense of difficulty, and seems to make you more important than anyone else.

name: Deletion Flag
description: Anything swatted with this glowing red flag is stopped, and set for death.

name: Ancient Spades
description: Not to be confused with the ancient version of Spades, the Pentacles suit.

name: 11th Dimensional Pyramid
description: If this dimension was to exist it would simply destroy the Laws of Physics. Having this pyramid exist is a danger to Reality itself, and if used incorrectly, could make all dimensions fold onto each other. On the plus side, it will give you a good chance at beating that boss fight.

name: 1 Star Uniform
description: The power of 10% Life Fiber flows through your body and makes your fiercely stronger then a normal human, however, not nearly strong to fight anyone with a higher star.

name: Faygo - Magical Butterbeer Flavour
description: This weirdly colored drink has steam rising off of it, and it smells fairly alcoholic. Are you even allowed to be drinking this?

name: Striped Overcoat
description: A fancy striped overcoat that keeps you warm on breezy days, while upholding your fashion.

name: Crocker\'s Cakemix Stirrer
description: The forefront in cakemix <font color="red">OBEY</font> stirring technology, this Crockercorp endorsed <font color="red">CONSUME</font> spoon is sure to make everything at least 200% more <font color="red">SUBMIT</font> delicious!

name: Crockercorp (TM) Slicer-and-Stirrer
description: Finely <font color="red">[OBEY]</font> dice your enemies, then <font color="red">[CONSUME]</font> mix whatever remains with this state-of-the-art Crockercorp <font color="red">[SUBMIT]</font> product!

name: Greenlight Flag
description: Your victory has been approved, as is evident by this luminescent and powerful green flag.

name: Cuddlebuddy Confection Cake Mix
description: A grand guide to cooking confections themed after the squiddles <font color="red">[AND SUBSERVIENCE]</font>!

name: Pistol of the Jacks
description: This gun doesn't require ammo. Just shoot and a jack lodges itself in your enemy. No bullets, just jacks. Maybe this could be useful?

name: iWho
description: An iPhone with a case designed like the TARDIS on it. Compare it to another iPhone and there really isn't much of a difference, other than the fact that you can call anyone from anywhere in the universe, free of charge.

name: Joker\'s Smiles
description: Show your enemies how you got those scars, and how they'll get theirs!

name: Exploding Shuriken
description: Surprise surprise! Throw and it will explode

name: Ahab\'s Grapple
description: A heavy whip with a small anchor on the end. This thing could take down a whale!

name: Quadrant Claws
description: Claws with a blade for each quadrant, each oozing an ink of its associated color- not too dangerous, but they're cool nonetheless.

name: Wallbuster
description: Block enemies with a dangerous spinning bolt that can be used for fighting as well. This thing is as dangerous to them as it is protective of you!

name: Saw Yo-yo
description: A yo-yo with chainsaw blades on it.  It acts like a normal yo-yo, but it is far more dangerous. Really, this thing probably breaks so many laws.

name: Shadeset
description: A headset with attached flip-up shades. Smooth.

name: Flip-up iShadeset
description: A more compact flip-up set of shades, now with computational capability!

name: Strobe Hoodie
description: This armoured hoodies flashes in neon colors, and should have come with a seizure warning label.

name: Holographic Pencil
description: With this thing, all computer screens work like tablets! Neat.

name: Slashtop
description: You should always carry at least five swords with you at all times.

name: Obsidian Gunblades
description: This obsidian knifegunblade is covered in the blood of all the enemies it has slain, using it for energ. Should it not feed, it will begin to consume its wielder...

name: Field Reaper\'s Scythe
description: Reap wheat, and souls. How convenient!

name: Cocoa Suit
description: All the classy ladies love the chocolate, and this chocolate-brown suit REEKS of it. No, really.

name: Crockercorp (TM) Cocoa-Confection Slicerspoon
description: The optimal tool for cake preparation and underling <FONT COLOR="ff0000">[OBEY]</FONT> extermination! Now in chocolate!

name: Gas-Powered Stick
description: A gift straight from an Emotion Lord, this ultimate weapon can be used in many ways. Recent studies have proved smacking downwards and yelling "GAS-POWERED STICK!"  to be the most effective method of pissing people.

name: Insight Staff
description: A basic staff that shoots simple, long-range lasers. ...What? Of course staves are supposed to shoot lasers. Why use one otherwise?

name: Mega Stone
description: A strange and mysterious stone supposedly used on special Pokemon with some kind of special power. If only they existed. Its kind of pretty, too.

name: Personally Projected Assistant
description: An arm mounted PDA, which is capable of projecting the content of its screen in front of the user, in the form of a convenient heads-up display!

name: PDA-Starnav
description: A PDA with the capability of guiding you through the stars! For whatever that's worth.

name: AllSpark of Slapstick Stupidity
description: Holding this AllSpark makes you want to do something really, really stupid, like attaching military-grade jetpacks to a shopping trolley...

name: Dragon Claws of Athena
description: These legendary blades are enhanced by the fact that they look like a dragon's claws!

name: The Emotional Wreck
description: Attract your opponents! Then break their hearts!

name: Spectrum Slicer
description: A multicolored chainsaw. You're pretty sure that's paint on the blade. But it could be blood. That's what you want to think. Since blood would be cool.

name: Snoop Dog Chainsaw
description: "Well, hip-hop is what makes these teeth go around." Someone said that. Probably.

name: Chain Dog Bust
description: A bust of the greatest horticulturalist turned musician no-ones ever heard of.

name: Yo Dog Bowler
description: "Well, hip-hop is what makes this hat go around." - Said you. You lied, that's your hand. Showing off your new awesome hat.

name: Victorian Dogg Bust
description: Professional, refined, AND cool? What a great man.

name: Sailor Scout Uniform
description: Ability to fascinate watchers with unnecessarily revealing transformation sequence not included.

name: Senketsu Kamui
description: With a name meaning Fresh Blood, this Kamui is probably just a bit different from your average magical girl uniform. As they say, less is more...

name: MLPshades
description: Wow, everything is so bright and colorful and sweet... Is that person a horse?

name: Walking Scythe
description: For when your legs are sore, the fields need reaping, or some imps need maiming.

name: Pillowcane
description: Maybe if you hit something enough with this soft, pillow-cane, it'll fall asleep?

name: Oversized Crochet Needle
description: Impale your enemies with this ridiculously large crochet needle. Or, you know, just ram them with the other side. Either one's cool, you guess.

name: Gold Pressed Latinum Slip
description: These may not be able to be replicated, but it turns out they can be alchemized.

name: Supercomputer
description: This thing is so heavy and bulky that you can't even budge it. But the Internet is amazingly fast! You think it might be its own hotspot.

name: Philosophical Ghost-Busting Headset
description: Now you can bust ghosts in a philosophical style! Or you could listen to music.

name: Fairy Skates
description: D'aww these skates have magical fairy wings on them, how cute, I wonder if you can fly with them....

name: Hatchtorch
description: A flame-spewing hatchet. This is both awesome AND incredibly dangerous! Your parents would be proud.

name: Masked Man\'s Laser
description: A laser used by a Masked Man. Its reportedly very dangerous. Careful.

name: Antique Cleaver
description: This 3 foot cleaver has been passed down from generation to generation to each first-born son when they turn 18. You don't know what species could wield such a weapon, but they must've been large.

name: Cagetop
description: Nicolas Cages' rugged face stares at you with piercing eyes as you surf the web on this laptop. The only true way to watch Con Air. Oh yeah, you can communicate with your teammates with it, too.

name: Shortstopper
description: This metallic, red baseball bat has the word "STOP" printed on it in big, bold letters. This will turn any baseball game around! Or at least... you know... stop it.

name: Beachball Bat
description: A colorfully-striped inflatable bat. This would be perfect for some kind of ocean sport, but it would really only be useful to hit beach balls.

name: Bucketmaid\'s Yoke
description: A pair of buckets dangle attractively from the ends of this long wooden stick.

name: Corpse Cutters
description: A pair of bloodstained shears... you aren't sure, but it seems as though they're whispering to you...

name: Yarnshears
description: Not to be confused with garden shears or lawn shears, but these shears are nonetheless dangerous. In a frilly, yarny kinda way.

name: Feather Glowboa
description: Glowing a hot pink and covered in feathers, this is undisputedly the most fabulous thing you've ever seen.

name: Fur Boa
description: ... You can't wrap this around your neck. You can, however, drape it around your torso. So fabulous, and yet... fur. Yeah, PETA's gonna hate you for this.

name: Chainshears
description: I don't think you're grooming hair with these, and they're too small for horticulture. Perfect for imp-slaying though, and that's what matters. Obviously.

name: Farming Shears
description: Now, the imps are your sheep, and their grist is your wool. That's all you can think of with this oversized conjoined scythe times two thing.

name: Ravenclaw Lantern Smasher
description: This giant hammer appears to have a head made from two magic lanterns that emanate pure rivalry and intelligence that surge you to smarter and better then all your session mates.

name: Duttle
description: The duttle is weirding you out a little. You believe you will keep your distance from the duttle.

name: Wool Shredders
description: This is probably the best idea ever- an over-sized pair of chainsaw-scythes, joined at the handles. Totally safe. Meant entirely for use around the farm. The grist farm.

name: Strikestopper
description: This baseball bat is so heavy, it can hit a guaranteed home run! Assuming you can lift and swing it with the speed of a regular bat.

name: Sharp Quicksilver Shades
description: When you wear these, you can't keep from worrying that the edges will cut your nose, but DAMN are they slick.

name: Whale Tosser\'s Tunic
description: The garb of a practitioner of a unique style of martial arts involving the use of gigantic sea creatures as weapons. Nothing beats taking a whale to the face.

name: Ultimate Dragon Cosplay
description: An advanced version of the dragon cosplay costume, this new bodygear adds defensive bonuses due to its sheer coolness.

name: Chainsickle
description: It's a sickle on a chain. Don't play jump rope with it. And don't lick it. It's also good in long ranged attacks.

name: Antique Shinai
description: A metal-bladed shinai with a golden handle, mildly tarnished with the weight of years.

name: Volatile Bucket Yoke
description: These glass beaker-buckets, attached to a convenient carrying pole, contain a mysterious chemical concoction. You hope it'll kill imps instead of giving them superpowers.

name: Ghoulshredder
description: Post Apocalyptia has NOTHING on these shears - patterned in the dust color of the Capital Wasteland, and more dangerous than any irradiated animal YOU'VE ever seen, this oversized pair of chainscythe-shears is a must-have for anyone who likes dangerous things.

name: Squiddle Lunchshears
description: Brightly colored and patterned with Squiddles, these shears are rather awkward to use, due to the conjoined lunchbox. You always wanted shears you can keep your lunch in, anyways! Oh wait...

name: Bucketbearer\'s Staff
description: A holy weapon of the army of the forces of light. Yeah, they threw this away. Buckets aren't weapons. Even when they shoot magical bursts of energy.

name: Holy on the Go-ly
description: A Holy Hardback that secretly opens to be a laptop! Comes complete with the writings set in picture form, so you can read it AND pester your chums at the same time.

name: Rainbow Flag
description: Some people say the LGBT community shoves it in people's faces too much. You disagree. Shove it in their faces even MORE.

name: Cosbee
description: A frisbee with a Cosby head on it. You can see it having some uses...

name: Spine
description: A vertebral column attached to a skull. This is starting to get creepy...

name: Sheared Spades
description: Black as night and sharp as your tongue, with half-spade shaped blades, this giant pair of shears'll make 'em bleed. Make 'em bleed grist.

name: Apocalypse Butchery
description: Ah, a simple chainsaw spear. Surely that's enough weapon for any sane individual. But wait, there's more! It unfolds, into a deadly pair of chainsaw edged shears! On second thought... this is a bit ludicrous.

name: Aperture Science Broomblade Disc
description: Aperture Labs' newest innovation: A flying disc that unleashes wooden poles tipped with blades when your enemy least expects it. Shareholder boondollars at work, folks.

name: Tactical War Blades
description: Two blades chained together that can switch between the form of a knife and sword during combat, making for excellent combat strategies. Only one with the knowledge and tactical ability of Athena can use them successfully.

name: Sacrificial Planet on a String
description: It looks like a glass bubble on a string.  Are those little people running inside?  More importantly - why do some of them look like you and your friends?!

name: Saw Game Video
description: This video tells you how to get out in the event you stumbled into the nefarious JIGSAW's trap. You're probably not gonna die just by watching it, but the doll on the tape is still creepy.

name: Legend of Zelda Laptop
description: A laptop based on the game Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time, with built-in musical functionality. You really paid your money's worth for this - or you just built it with alchemy.

name: N7 Hoodie
description: This black hoodie with an N7 logo emblazoned on the chest and red and white stripes down the arm looks exactly like the ones from the Mass Effect games. Hey, you may not be saving the galaxy, but you can still look like you are, right?

name: Fountain Fauchard
description: While the pen is mightier than the sword, its might is on par with that of the spear. This weapon combines the best qualities of both, making it DOUBLY mightier than the sword.

name: Beam Blaster
description: A perfectly normal trumpet, except for the part where when you play it, it shoots a blinding beam of light and makes your enemy's ears bleed. You're a true musician.

name: Antique Magnetic Sword
description: A powerful relic imbued with the forces of magnetism. Maybe it does something cool or whatever.

name: Camo Laserneedles
description: Your favorite laser needles, now with stylish black and white camo on them!

name: Jolly Roger
description: Arr, me hearties! Strike fear into the hearts of your enemies with this flag.

name: Sleighander
description: One of Saint Christopher's lesser blades, for smiting the only mildly naughty.

name: Mega Suit
description: Wade into battle cloaked in a bright cyan jumpsuit complete with oversized footwear and boots. Hopefully it's flattering?

name: Bucket of Potatoes
description: Skaian man have many potato. Is glad! End suffering. But is only hallucinate from malnourish.

name: Attorney\'s Badge
description: Proof that you're a lawyer, and license to shout "OBJECTION!" at anything that moves.

name: Static Sock
description: A sock supercharged with a Duracell battery. The lack or protection from the user actually makes it hurt you just as much as it hurts them. Looks like you have to get up close and personal to use it effectively.

name: Dueling Boogaloo
description: Wow, this thing is amazing! It plays classic riffs every time it tastes the blood of an enemy! What sort of legendary swordsman are you if you don't have one of these? You can even flip it upside-down to play air guitar on it in celebration of winning a battle!

name: His Sock Inheritance
description: A slightly shrunk version of the original novel, with all the characters replaced by Sock Puppets. The dialogue is much, much less complex, and could almost be considered a children's book.

name: Caliginous Chaos Shears
description: Black metal ribboned with wasteland colors, the blades on this pair of chainspear-shears cut deep, and is sure to even make underlings bleed. Even though most of them don't have blood, and the ones that do have it in grist form.

name: Lightning Vortex Pikacles
description: A bright, happy yellow, these pikachu-themed spectacles bring back all of the joy and wonder that used to permeate even the smallest of miracles - and they sometimes shoot a few sparks, which are inevitably drawn back into the vortex-lenses. Cool.

name: d24 Kaliber Rifle
description: This solid gold sniper rifle, while heavy, fires a diamond die at your foes at absurd speed.

name: Launcher of Chained Swords
description: This freak of weaponry is a violin-gun that shoots a sword attached to a spiked chain. You might want to take a break from this alchemical nonsense.

name: Eternal Scout Badge
description: Adorned on only the highest ranking of scouts in suspended animation. Only after the mute children pulled you to the burlap tent in the vacant lot could you obtain it. Or maybe you alchemized it.

name: Midnight Channel Glasses
description: Mysterious glasses that allow one to "catch a glimpse of the hollow world," whatever THAT'S supposed to mean.

name: The Final Symphony
description: The very song that lingers throughout your soul, and takes you without notice. Now in control with your fingers.

name: Golden Pocket Dimension Openifier
description: This nifty device opens a portal to a land apparently filled with gold coins. You figure you could use this to bury your enemies, but not much else.

name: Clockfaced Darksiders II Disc
description: This game disc for Darksiders II has the face of a clock on it. You ... guess it could be useful?

name: STRONG Ahab\'s Starskates
description: Super STRONG tactical-looking skates with a mounted Ahab's Crosshairs that is galaxy-fueled, and directly shoots stars at rapid velocity.

name: Pressed Leaf
description: A leaf you preserved between the pages of a book many years ago. It's still kinda pretty.

name: Fall Wreath
description: A wreath made of crunchy leaves to celebrate the coming of autumn.

name: The Hatchet of Coming Winter
description: A hatchet specifically designed to chop down trees to store them as firewood for the winter.

name: The Axe of Frozen Eons
description: This axe levels entire forests with a single swing, and conveniently splits and stacks the wood as some sort of automatic magical lumber-storing tool. You can only wonder what circumstances led to its original design.

name: Hazardous Waste Bucket Yoke
description: You always thought developing poisons would be such a dark, edgy job. It's not that cool when you have to carry out the waste.

name: Frozen Turkey
description: A frozen turkey. Let's hope it doesn't start thawing in your sylladex...

name: Turkeytar
description: A keytar made entirely of frozen fowl. Ew.

name: Turkey Helmet
description: A turkey with a hole cut in it for your head, and another hole or two cut in it so you can see. It's uncomfortably warm and squishy.

name: Frozen Turcake
description: A frozen cake with bits of turkey in it. You think it should probably stay frozen, lest it start to smell.

name: The Sword of Turk Nevargen
description: A legendary blade, wielded by the turkey-slaying hero of yore. It smells slightly like gravy.

name: Frozen Stuffing
description: A package of frozen, prepackaged, Betty Crocker stuffing. Delicious.

name: Frozen Turkey Dinner
description: A turkey and stuffing, combined and frozen.

name: Stuffed Pistol
description: A pistol stuffed with turkey stuffing. It's slightly less effective this way, since the stuffing prevents you from actually shooting things.

name: Fallblade
description: A magical blade with all the powers of summer's end. Turn green to red with but a whisper, breathe frost upon the grass, and send animals into hibernation with a single swing of this sword!

name: Thanksgiving Turkey
description: A well-stuffed and roasted turkey, typically used in the celebration of the American version of Thanksgiving. It smells heavenly.

name: Nuclear Turkeybine
description: You have absolutely no idea what this massive piece of shit does. Uranium goes in, power comes out, and it occasionally makes a very odd gobbling noise.

name: Reinforced Baton
description: Really, all it is is a baton made out of iron.

name: Spookier Bubblier Jousting Riflescytheaslinky
description: A pretty spooky group of haphazardly combined weapons. Now with 50% more bubbles!

name: Stereoscopic Stab Sticks
description:
A set of two spears, one red and one blue.
They are said to appear "Slightly More Three-Dimensional Than Normal Spears."

name: Friendship is Laptops
description: A My Little Pony-themed laptop. Congrats.

name: Polar Sailor Scout Uniform
description: A dashing sailor uniform in red and green, complete with fur trim and obscene amounts of gold embroidery. Fancy, fashionable, and full of holiday cheer.

name: Goose Plush
description: Honk honk honk. The sound of the devil, or  maybe just a hungry bird with teeth. So yeah, the devil.

name: Hanafuda Deck
description: A beautifully-illustrated deck of cards consisting of 12 suits, each depicting a month and a flower.

name: Snuggie
description: A blanket with sleeves, useful for keeping warm. It's a shame it looks so ridiculous.

name: Duracell Puppet
description: Doesn't look very menacing, but then again neither do most cloth puppets. Looks more like an over sized pillow glove rather than a weapon though.

name: Poltergust 3000
description: A mighty vacuum used to suck up the most vile of lost souls. Also dust bunnies.

name: Laser-Proof Glasses
description: Protect your eyes from lasers! A necessary tool for all laser users.

name: Masterfully Crafted Knitting Wands
description: Supposedly magical wands - though you still aren't sure how real the magic is... or how to use it. But the core of the wands seem to resonate with your inner knitter.

name: Bedazzled Hoodie
description: Sparkly AND comfy!

name: The Felt: The Inside Tales
description: Read all about the Felt and their tales of the inside! Fairies not included.

name: Gasworks
description: Self-lighting fireworks that go off in a massive explosion - just make sure you stay far away from them!

name: Fuzzy Pikachu Hoodie
description: A warm, fuzzy yellow hoodie with ears much like a favorite electric mouse from your childhood TV show.

name: Baseball Batana
description: A baseball bat poorly taped to a katana. Nobody will ever know.

name: Candy Corn Themed iPhone
description: For only the true candy lovers on the go.

name: Clubtop
description: The clubtop has the ability to help one ace that golf tournament and help you message your friends back in between holes!

name: Shurichuck
description: Throwable bladed nunchucks.

name: Timey Wimey Scythe
description: You're not completely sure if you're sending souls into the future or the past with this scythe, but either way they're gone.

name: Bloodbeat Spear-Chronochain Shears
description: A blood red spear, whirring with saw-blades seeming kept moving by the turn table inlaid in the center of the shaft - a shaft which splits, transforming the spear into a pair of sharp edged chainsaw shears. Neat.

name: Dark Crystal Ball
description: Using this ball, you can spy on your friends around the session... mostly when they are asleep.

name: Pyrospit Pennant
description: It looks like someone has set this Prospit flag ablaze. I wonder if you could do the same to some enemies.

name: Scythe of the Magic Apocalypse
description: This scythe crackles with an energy blinding to even the most powerful of wizards. Only a truly potent Hero can wield it - and perhaps, only one who bears the power of Hope.

name: Return from Grimdark
description: Your abuse of Grimdark forces allowed you to figure out a way to reverse it.  A child's toy imbued with the power to make peace (though often violently) with anything it comes in contact with! (WARNING: If used on self, may cause immediate death.)

name: Radiant Scythe
description: Despite its dark origins, this scythe glows with the power of the sun, and you feel as if your hits are...luckier, if that makes sense.

name: Hard-light Holopad
description: When a code is inserted into this holopad, it projects a hard-light image of the corresponding item that you can manipulate. You can learn a lot more about an item before you alchemize it with this!

name: Wastelander\'s Jacket
description: Whoa there, Mad Max. Skunk skin might not have been the best choice for a shoulder pad.

name: One Ol\' Barrel a\' Thorny Ducktaped Musical Satellites
description: Y'all can poin' it up and have the uselessest bunch o' satellites anyone 'as ever seen: or yuu can poin' it at 'da critters and set off the most expensiff firework show of tha' dang dur' ever seen! Yeeeee-haaaaaw!~

name: Nuclear Glitch Turbine
description: It's unclear whether this thing runs on glitch or produces glitch-based energy, but either way, having it around can't be healthy for the space-time continuum.

name: Massive Glitched Gate
description: This thing is horribly artifacted and resembles one of the Skaian spirograph gates above your house. If you dare to venture through it, there's no guarantee that you'll like where you appear...
effects: STORAGE:GLITCHGATE.|SHUNT:USELESS.:The pad on top of your Alchemiter has turned into a weird glitched gate, and attempting to alchemize anything causes the new item to fall into it and disappear, never to be seen again.|

name: XVIII - The Moon
description: A card depicting the moon, symbolic of mystery, illusion, and deception. This card's power inspires confusion in your enemies.

name: Bladed Rift Suit
description: A wildcard of an outfit, but nobody can deny that it looks pretty sharp.

name: Marker Bat
description: A metal bat that also functions as a market. Do damage to enemies and make large art at the same time with this weapon!

name: Golden Guitar
description: An acoustic guitar made of pure, solid gold! A sturdy and flashy weapon to be sure.

name: Tarot of Dubious Intent
description: An evil tarot deck consisting of 665 cards. What, there's one missing? You knew you shouldn't have alchemised this.

name: Brusher\'s Pike
description:
Kid grabs the pike. Kid stabs some imps, collects some grist. 
You really did love Bastion.

name: Radioactive Baked Potato Gun
description: In the time it takes to fire, it cooks the potato to perfection, and fills it to the brim with dangerous radiation!

name: Tarot of the Mighty Microchip
description: You've managed to unleash the ultimate combination of science and divinity. Unfortunately, you don't have enough power to use it at full efficiency.

name: Seer\'s Robe
description: You have combined your silly cards with a hoodie, and now you look like a badass seer. Actually, you just look depressed...

name: Mole Claws
description: These gloves were designed off the claws of a giant mole species. With these miniature shovels strapped onto your hands you can tear through dirt and rock with ease.

name: Pumpkin Launcher
description: You fire this large orange launcher and... Nothing!? What a useless item!

name: Red Trench Coat of the Raincoat Killer
description: You feel a large sense of guilt wash over you as you wear this trench coat, yet you feel the need to keep fighting and killing.

name: Captcharoid Camera
description: This camera prints out a ghost image of whatever you snap a picture of with it!

name: Cape of Fighting Spirit
description: It flaps behind you, ends seemingly burning away. You feel like a bad-ass.

name: Miniature Sledgehammer
description: A tiny sledgehammer, which basically amounts to it being a long-handled, poorly balanced gavel. At least it's easier to use in combat than its normal-sized counterpart.

name: Telescoping Laserband
description: A handheld rubberband with a neon green color. It can stretch to three times its original length. Extended like this, it takes on the consistency of a laser. Don't wear it on your wrist.

name: Psi Candy Bracelet
description: An edible rubber brand bracelet that only hurts a bit more than a normal rubber band, due to the hard candies coating the elastic.

name: Glow-in-the-Dark Crayons
description: In a dark room? Need to jot down some notes? Trying to kick your chalk addiction? Why not glow-in-the-dark crayons?

name: Shot-saw
description: It shoots and saws! Only through alchemy could something as glorious as this be made.

name: Pie-glasses
description: Sunglasses with lenses that look like blueberry pies. Unfortunately, they don't also taste like - why are you licking your sunglasses, anyways?

name: Portal Scythe
description: A normal scythe with an orange handle and a blue blade, emblazoned with a white Aperture symbol.

name: Black Market Dice
description: Totally illegal, totally worth it.

name: Lightning Glove
description: Introduce this SHOCKING revelation to your enemies, friends, anyone really.

name: Make Her a Member of the Midnight Crew
description: The perfect LBD for a gorgeous mobster gal to gallivant around in.

name: Sexy Crowbar
description: Oh damn. Someone would look so hot wielding this this baby. It would give me a real goose neck if you know what I mean. I could really pry into them. They could unload my crate with their jimmy any time. Wow.

name: Hefty Girdle
description: Steel reinforced, this foxy garment can lift all the weight you have into a compact and rock-hard shape. Great for high school reunions.

name: Squoose Plush
description: Oh god. What have you done. KILL IT. KILL IT BEFORE IT BREEDS.

name: Psychedelic Walrus Tusks
description: I am here, you are here, you are me and where did these walrus tusk knitting needles come from?

name: Computal Ball
description: Look DEEP into this crystal ball... and pester your chums!

name: CGI Archer\'s Bow
description: Combining the latest portable 3D gaming technology with a weapon has made a barely useful version of a bow.

name: Encyclopedia of Creepypastas
description: A compilation of every creepypasta ever written. Includes pictures of scary gifs to go with each story! Perfect for scaring Imps to death or driving them mad!

name: 4th of July Special
description: A box of fireworks especially formulated for the patriotic man, woman, or child who wishes to blow up a small part of their country.

name: The Reaganator
description: Each rocket fired from this red, white and blue bazooka has a trail of bright white sparks and explodes into the shape of a star. Freedom.

name: Banner of Wishes
description: A luxurious, tasseled red velvet banner hanging from a golden pole, wrapped in a rainbow of ribbon. They say whoever sees this banner in battle can make a wish and have it come true.

name: Slytherin Scarf
description: Display your Slytherin affiliation with pride with this green and silver-striped scarf.

name: iBlow
description: New user friendly blowtorch. 2 pixels thinner than last year's model.

name: Banner of Lost Souls
description: You can now proudly wave the flag of all your lost comrades.

name: Headset of Mythology
description: Now you can instantly look up stats on obscure mythology at any time, even in mid-strife.

name: Never-Dead iPhone
description: You've equipped your iPhone with a proper battery, and now you won't find yourself without that perfect app.

name: Digital Backpack
description: Finally, a something that you can carry on your back and use to track your personal data.

name: Microwave Hosting an MMORPG
description: This microwave is an upgraded version of the model running a certain session. Who has been creating this strange tech, and what is it's purpose?

name: Ohaiotop
description: A nifty little laptop with a sakura theme that types in kana.

name: Deck of the Doom-Seer
description: You listened to the dark gods, and have given them governance over your local star system. In return, you are beginning to feel unstoppable.

name: Mystery CD
description: You are sure that there's something on this CD, and you are quite sure that it is for no good.

name: Respurrator
description: This head-encompassing respirator is vaguely cat-themed, with an orange eye shield, a 'muzzled' shape, and a two-tone brown striped paint job. A faux fur mohawk and two large cat ears at the top complete the look.

name: Electric Tonfa
description: By combining your trusty tonfa and a taser you found you can now shock people while smacking them silly!

name: Spring-Loaded Punch Cannon
description: It's a very cartoonishly designed weapon. With a pull of one trigger, the boxing glove launches out the front on a spring, and then recoils. It's second trigger just makes a 'KA-POW!' sound effect.

name: Lumberjack\'s Wooden Jumpstart
description: So this is just a shitty axe with a fucking battery wired to it...how the fuck does this thing even shock stuff? You'll find out later, it's a bit too fun just shocking your enemies.

name: Hydro Pump
description: Used for firing short, but powerful blasts of water at your enemies. You can't help but think the blue and brown color scheme references something...

name: Alcohol Cards
description: The cards predict that you will get soon become intoxicated.

name: Slinky-Tier Pajamas
description: DO THE STAIRS-Y THING

name: Uranium Power Necklace
description: A necklace with liquidized uranium flowing through the string. This is probably incredibly unsafe to wear.

name: Unevenly-Thawed Fingercakes
description: The candles have not heated this cake very well: parts are burned, parts are left frozen. It is small enough to pick up with two fingers though. You might also try wearing them on your fingers, but they would probably get sticky.

name: Gladius Spatii
description: A black bladed katana that seems to be made from the very fabric of space itself and appears to be able to cut through space as well. It sounds as if there is a humming noise coming from the sword.

name: Golden Ice Claws
description: Boring regular gold claws now has increased powers of freezing death! Besides golden ice is so much better than yellow snow...

name: Spirited Chain
description: A chain that was used in the Spirit World to keep wayward spirits at bay. It also makes a good night light.

name: SCP-361
description: An old Tarot Deck. The cards Ace of Staves, Page of Swords and XIII - Death seem to be missing. The cards can change the way they look and readings done with them are exceedingly accurate. It is unknown if SCP-361 only fortells these events or manipulates them into happening.

name: D-Wheel
description: Also known as Duel Runners, these bikes allow their Driver to participate in so called Turbo Duels. Or in other words CARD GAMES ON MOTORCYCLES!

name: XL Face/Off Shoes
description: A large pair of sleek flats, a rubber John Travolta face adorns the right toe, Nicolas Cage the left. Apparently they were tailor made for an eight foot fanatic.

name: Branding Iron
description: First mark them, then bash their skulls in ...

name: Hee! and Ho! Demon Nunchucks
description: Nunchucks infused with the power of a Jack Frost, a snow demon who likes to chant hee-ho at the end of every sentence. These cold nunchucks will freeze your opponents in the moment you hit them! Hee-ho!

name: PET
description: A futuristic Personal Terminal for use with Net Navigators. Not for use with Netscape Navigator.

name: Ultimate Fix-All Kit
description: Whether it moves and shouldnt, or wont move and should, with this kit youre ready for anything!

name: Rope
description: A coil of rope that was just lying around. Hey, you can never have enough rope when you're adventuring, right?

name: My Immortal
description: HARRY WHAT HAVE THEY DONE TO YOU?!

name: Lingerie
description: Black lace panties and stockings with a garter belt.

name: Power Rake
description: Why gather leaves into a pile when you can electrocute them?

name: The Mirror of Erised
description: An inscription across the top of this gilded mirror reads 'Erised stra ehru oyt ube cafru oyt on wohsi.'

name: Shrek Army Knife
description: Not ogre-ly powerful, but has multiple layers of use.

name: Screwy News
description: It's a screwdriver made of newspaper.

name: Sewing Machine
description: A tool used in the production of clothing.

name: Fuzzy Handcuffs
description: ... Yeah. Don't judge.

name: Yellow Sun Nuclear Splitter
description: A nuclear axe with a blade so large and sharp that you could split a sun that's less large than that giant green one, maybe the yellow one there though. But seriously, don't do it.

name: Vaccacalamus
description: This pen seems to give you the ability to draw an endless amount of cows, forever. And you can't stop.

name: Magic Cue Splitter
description: A large, horrifically sharp, powerful axe with great capabilities, yet not large enough to be unwieldy. Also, it is completely sheet white.

name: Laser-Guided HatchIron
description: Now you can precisely iron your clothes and cut your wood at near the same time!

name: Pogo Hamaxe
description: Boing..Boing...BOING OUCH THAT WAS MY TOE!

name: Programmable Grenade
description: A grenade you can program when to go off and increase damage to your enemies while keeping yourself in the clear.

name: Calamity Cannon
description: An inscription on this reads: "The Mancers not only theorized about the raw forces of the world, they developed blueprints for how to unleash them." Well, that's nice, but who are the Mancers?

name: Straitjacket
description: Useful for restraining the mentally disturbed. Why you have one is nobody's guess.

name: Electric Flamingo
description: You mind think that Randomizer Corp is just throwing a battery on anything it can find, you're right. But you'll alchemize this anyways because c'mon, it's a humming electrified flamingo. There are even sparks coming out of its beak!

name: Red Steel-Toes
description: Exactly the same as the base model, except they're Red.

name: Nuclear Fallout Chainsaw Billiards
description: This powerful weapon creates fission explosions wherever you hit.

name: Elegy of Emptiness Statue
description: A creepy-looking statue of a green-clad warrior. It's useful for solving switch puzzles, but you're just going to beat the tar out of tar imps with it, aren't you?

name: Tarot Extension Deck
description: This set of tarot cards allows you to combine it well with any other tarot deck, making it a good off-hand deck.

name: Tarot of High-End Computing
description: You decided that adding a battery to power your microchip cards would be a good idea, and hey, it is!

name: Chart Cart
description: Not only does this hold your purchased items, but it also leads you to the celestial locations of said items.

name: Pie Coat
description: Tasty and stylish.

name: Plaid Scarf
description: A thick fleece neck wrap. It sure looks Canadian on you.

name: Magnetic Rope
description: For when you need to climb the refrigerator for whatever reason.

name: Example Stampede
description: A stamp that summons a stampede of horses to trample all over your foes. Handy, if you have some method to get out of the way.

name: Tasseled Shades
description: Hipster thick-rimmed glasses with red velvet curtains and golden tassels hanging off the temples. You either have to be too cool to care or too stupid not to know better to wear these.

name: Round Razor
description: A ring blade with two wooden grips on the inside. It's not recommended to try shaving with this thing.

name: Semaphore Shaver
description: A slightly rusty red straight razor with a mailbox-themed handle.

name: Digitized Typewriter
description: This rusty old typewriter has been enhanced to electronically register your keystrokes. It's a great way to fashionably writing digital e-mail to you friends, though reading replies is a slightly more complicated matter. I'm sure you'll get the hang of it though.

name: Anachronistic Computer
description: This computer only displays images in black and white, and the gold lettering on the keys rubs off on your fingers. Additionally, it can only write messages in Cloister Black. But it's pretty damn classy.

name: Typewriter Lite
description: This state-of-the-art machine combines the familiarity of the old with the portability of the new. Perfect for the old-fashioned writer on the go--who maybe can't carry as heavy a typewriter as they used to.

name: Typewritertop
description: The brass and lead keys of an old-timey writing device stop this clunky laptop from shutting all the way and would puncture the screen if you tried. On one hand it can only run Internet Explorer on Windows XP and is quite slow to load, but it looks quirky and eloquent and jingles when you run with it.

name: USB Typewriter
description: This retro-futuristic marvel, this gorgeous vintage typewriter can be used as the computer keyboard for your Mac or PC, or type with ink-on-paper while electronically recording your keystrokes! (It's kind of useless by itself, though.)

name: Demode iPad
description: This first-generation iPad is obsolescent and has a damaged screen.

name: Obsidian Cake Knives
description: A pair of obsidian knives with the sign of an angry cake engraved onto their hilts, seemingly giving it the power of ... dessert.

name: Potatonade
description: You are not sure if this is a cleverly disguised weapon or an useless artifact.

name: Painting of a Blue Beauty
description: This froofy haired, blue 60s glammer queen would look out of place anywhere but on the wall of a depraved old man.

name: Dress of Eclectica
description: This dress is blue, and wavy, and shiny, and has a cozy black body sleeve under it. Absolutely perfect!

name: Irish Man Dress
description: This wavy, flappy, green suit dress is absolutely masculine and pretty and perfect. It has a billiard ball belt buckle that changes colours. Wow.

name: Three in the Morning Dress
description: This dress is so swanky you simply cannot imagine wearing it on anything other than super special occasions, it is that fancy. Plus you'd freeze your ass off in it.

name: Timeless Game
description: Some game maniac thought it's a good idea to mix time hammer with Fluorite Octet. Well, he wasn't wrong. It's powerful. It has great stats too. It's not too big either. And it even has Grist multiplier (or you pretend it has). What more do you want?

name: Insanity Shades
description: Looking at these sends more than just a shiver down your spine. You feel as if you're being... commanded to wear them, and they whisper in your ear of great power.

name: Rocket Armor
description: With rocket thrusters all over this armor, It should both aid in manuvering around large enemies as well as allow you to fly around the medium without a care in the world.

name: Holo-tastic Sugoi Viewer
description: Have you ever wanted to watch the latest amtaeurishly dubbed and written animated shorts on Tumblr or Youtube in THREE DIMENSIONS?! :O Well now you can, with this top-of-the-line video display guaranteed to make everything at least 15x more kawaii desu ne, or your grist back (not guaranteed)!

name: Old Glory Scythe
description: It may be a bit old, but the razor edge decapitates just as well.

name: Ticking German Funeral Frockcoat
description: With the dust of time comes despair, with despair comes pressed funeral attire. The class on this Frockcoat could re-dignify even the sobbingest of old gents.

name: Nylon Collar
description: A human sized dog's collar, granting +10 to ADORABLE. Bell optional.

name: Boxing Knives
description: Throwing knives attached to the knuckles of boxing gloves. Pretty lethal, but not very imaginative.

name: Cue Ball Beanie
description: This beanie seems to be just white cloth, but maybe there's something more to it...? When you wear it, you can vaguely hear the sound of water sloshing, and you are decidedly more decisive.

name: Upcoming Hope
description: These magical cards contain the information of where to find where hope is, and will be.

name: Tommy Chong Wouldn\'t Even Wear These
description: When you close the psychedelic printed curtains on these rose tinted, round framed tortoise shell shades, you feel like you can see FOREVER. Aside from a load of colorful, trippy nonsense, you can see your desktop and pesterchum, anyway.

name: Old Ornament
description: An old Christmas ornament. It's dusty enough to have been sitting in the attic for several generations.

name: Glorious Maple Cleaver
description: This hybrid weapon is great for impaling trees for their syrup, and cleaving them for your log cabin afterwards! Pretty cool eh?

name: Reindeerless Sleigh
description: A small, one-person sleigh with nothing to pull it. It's actually kinda depressing.

name: Deceased Bovine Sleigh
description: ...Who would even hitch up a dead cow to a sleigh? That's disgusting.

name: Swiss Razor
description: A very sharp pocket knife with an integrated set of various tools. If you ever wanted to fight, shave, and open wine bottles with the same item, this is the tool for you.

name: Amutop
description: Its basically a laptop inside an amulet.

name: Sketchbook of Yaoi
description: Sure, this is one of your more embarrassing sketchbooks, but desperate times call for desperate measures, right? Time to blind some imps with your wonderful yaoi!

name: GraveDigger
description: A Shovel made of hard stone with the words R.I.P written at the end.

name: Unicycle
description: All you need is some juggling balls, and you'll be a real performer!

name: Unislicer
description: As long as you can balance on this thing, you'll be cruising!

name: Plasma Dress
description: A fashionable purple and green dress with a somewhat transparent skirt. It also glows faintly. But not ONLY is it sexy as hell on you, it's also got a pretty high defense level. So that's a win-win.

name: Quantumscope
description: This telescope allows you to see even farther into space than before, and a handy HUD tells you all the complicated theories about what you're looking at as well.

name: Homemade Wica\'s Broom
description: You whittled this from a branch using a kitchen knife. It's not pretty, but it's essential for sweeping the negative energy from a room and is uniquely yours.

name: Radioadical Aimbotato Bazooker
description: Sterilized white spud gun with a translucent viewscreen and green laser guidance system.

name: Ubersaw
description: Although called a saw, this sharp, stabby weapon has no teeth. Well, save the giant syringe in the middle.

name: Extreme Retro Netskater
description: This wire dates back to the days of the apple two, and connecting through the phone lines to make it to a BBS.

name: Rocket Powered Anime Bionicle HUD
description: You traversed the land of Mata Nui and climbed the great Mt. Desu Desu and a lot of other vague anime shit to get this helmet. Gog your bro would be proud. "Jet fuel not included."

name: Cueshades
description: Pure white teashades, with no actual lenses, just white. And yet, somehow you can see through them, and beyond them... you can see everything.

name: Frostblue Devil Sword
description: A sword with a blade of an unbreakable cobalt alloy, used by devils of all sorts.

name: Duel Rocket Runner
description: Finally you're able to fly on your bike (while still playing cardgames). This is way more then just +25 badassitude!

name: Skull Breather
description: Sure to provide some badass, morbid moments, while still letting you breathe in toxic air. I'm not sure about the dark purple smoke that leaks from the filters, though.

name: Australium Ingot
description: This golden bar bares the image of a lone figure boxing a kangaroo.

name: The Wooden ID Disk
description: An identity disk from Tron, made of wood from a spectacular redwood tree. The lines and wood grains glow a faint yellow-gold and pulse with power.

name: Toastlauncher
description: A chrome, bazooka shaped toaster that launches super-heated, rock-solid toast at your enemies.

name: You Are My Meat
description: You are an imp, I am a player, you are my meat, turn into grist, you are my meat, so die like the rest, (thanks in part to this gunmetal gray, blood-soaked toaster bazooka.)

name: Sod Buster
description: It's a sword with a sharp shovel at the tip. Not exactly easy to swing, but man could that weight do some damage.

name: Hand Mortar
description: An aged museum piece that still packs one hell of a boom. Dangerous, and hard to set up, but lethal.

name: Ender Dragon Cosplay
description: With piercing purple eyes that glow radiantly against a backdrop of perfect dark, and black scales that seem to shimmer with the void itself, you are truly a fearsome and majestic creature. Or at least, you're dressed as one.

name: The Never Ending Story
description: In a fantastic world being destroyed by a mysterious Nothing, a young warrior is asked by the Empress of Fantastica to set off and find a way to stop it; meanwhile a boy from another world, reading his story, is witness as the story gradually grows more and more realistic.

name: Quantum Rocket Wings
description: Now you can fly and compute complex equations at the same time, just hope you don't stall while the wings are calculating the ten trillionth digit of pi!

name: Slashed-up Samurai\'s Suit
description: A torn and tattered, but stylish old suit. Comes with a thin necktie and a NICE pair of shoes.

name: Festive Octet
description: A set of eight dice that, when rolled, can give you a variety of interesting festive outcomes ranging from putting antlers on your enemy's heads to straight-out dropping a giant sleigh on them.

name: Throwing Scissors
description: This new weapon looks exactly like regular scissors, except sharper on the outside than the inside, and with a better grip. You guess this is an upgrade...?

name: Tricksterlicious Blanky
description: Wow this thing is cozy. And colourful. Wow. You think you'll lie in bed with this cozy sheet, or marry it. Carry it around on your back like a turtle shell.

name: Plush Squoose Babie Blanky
description: This thing is so soft and colours. So soft blanky. Wrap yourself if the beautiful, breathing, cuthulgoose pelts of your childhood and regress.

name: Shooting Star Sword
description: A long, slender sword which has a star-themed decorative hilt, and unusually placed points along the edge. Oddly enough, it might be easy to throw.

name: Revolutionary Spades
description: Ancient technology meets the digital age. Also a sword.

name: Attack On Titan DVD
description: The biggest anime since Death Note, now on DVD.

name: Replica Mech Helmet
description: You think you could probably crash through a concrete wall with this on. Probably. Maybe.

name: Explosive Ornament
description: An ornament that explodes when you throw it. How... festive.

name: Bolting Tome
description: Pick off your enemies from afar with pinpoint-precision lightning magic!

name: Star Spangled Sweater
description: A night-blue turtleneck decorated with bright star shaped patches.

name: Contradictory Cuckoo
description: Although you can't use your biological arms while bound up in this jacket, you do have a handy pair of ghostly ecto-arms that seem to respond to your wriggling.

name: Angled Trisector
description: They all said it was impossible, but this item proves them wrong! ...wait, that was trisecting an angle, not trisecting WITH an angle. Never mind then.

name: Witchdoctor\'s Broom-Wand
description: An miniature besom, up-cycled from an exhausted old wand. It still has some spark in it.

name: Chain of the Fallen Rider
description: Fabled Chain of an undead rider seeking revenge and to purify those in flame. The guilty shall suffer.

name: Hallmark of Spiritual Sanctuary
description: A banner: "Parted per chevron argent and gules, chevron erminois, base sun argent," hung from a brilliantly polished silver pole, it's hilt wrapped in red velvet stitched with golden thread. It is said the souls of dead players find sanctuary near it, and will assist you in battle.

name: Hate
description: It... it almost feels as if this captchalogue card wants to eat you alive.

name: Hellblower
description: A sax that shoots flames of pure, jazzy passion.

name: Pirate Thrasher
description: This weighty guitar not only stops pirates dead in the sea, it's pretty good for stopping other things dead too. If you hold it close to your ear, you can hear it resonating with C Major.

name: Red Whip
description: This whip has obviously seen a lot of use recently, because its coated in fresh bloo- oh wait it's just paint.

name: Haunted Chain of the Forgotten
description: Combine the power of the Horror-terrors, with the puritan goals of the Fallen Rider, and put it all inside a sturdy chain, and you have a weapon to take ownership of the night with.

name: Pirate Hat
description: A nice bicorn with a jolly roger emblazoned on the front.

name: Nightstalker Chainchopper
description: A chain with blades at either end that seem to shimmer with dark energy. When swung, they seem to vanish in a flash of black.

name: Plush Kitty Toy
description: An adorable stuffed cat toy with big, fluffy ears.

name: BlazerMail
description: Similar to a chainmail tunic worn in Ye Old Days, but so much more snazzier. Look at you, champ.

name: Laser-Edged Axe
description: A very heavy axe-shaped implement, edged by a bright red laser. You could probably cut through steel with this! Or maybe even titanium... imps!

name: Objectively Sexy Lingerie
description: This black lace teddy with decorative ribbons, bows, and garter hooks looks objectively sexy on everyone, somehow. Even boys. Huh.

name: Plague Doctor Mask
description: An old mask holding the grim reminder of Europe\'s devastating bubonic plague epidemic. Such a sad memory to hear. For some reason you can smell oranges and clover in this.

name: Bolt Pistol
description: The sidearm of choice for STRONG space fairing soldiers. Fires a 40mm armor piercing high explosive rocket. Basically a rocket launcher in pistol form. Great for finishing off those pitiful Imps.

name: Scythe of Pestilence
description: Made from the forces of armegeddon, as well as poison of death brings forth this weapon! With but a swing, the Earth would fall to its knees! Too bad the meteors destroyed it first. Also the Earth doesn't have knees.

name: Epitaph Sleuth
description: Time to bust out the magic candy corn and put on your hard-boiled coat full of sleuthing mayyjics.

name: Minicrit
description: Glowing yellow dice that do more damage than they should.

name: Vine Whip
description: Tendrils of poison ivy arc in long curves. Actually, you better not touch this thing.

name: Revolutionary Snipping Spades
description: What's more revolutionary than being able to make papercraft while in heavy melee combat? I certainly can't think of anything.

name: Precious Magic Cue Ring
description: It's a pure white ring with a single white orb on it; you think you can maybe hear water sloshing around inside, and maybe also more. Much, much more.

name: Captcha Code Calculator
description: Essentially an economy-sized calculator with a keyboard and two buttons marked "&&" and "||". Inputting two captcha codes and pressing the desired operation button seems to calculate the result!

name: Auto-Scanning Code Calculator
description: The Intellibeam Laserstation has been upgraded with the ability to combine the codes that it scans using a desired operation. This should make alchemy less of a chore!

name: Manual Holopad
description: Instead of a card/totem slot, this Holopad has a keyboard on which you can manually input a code for previewing. Nice!

name: Manual Alchemiter
description: Instead of a totem platform, this Alchemiter has a keyboard on which you can manually input a code to alchemize, allowing you to skip pretty much the entire process of punch card alchemy.

name: Blender
description: A blender, nicked from your kitchen. This should be fun to alchemize with.

name: Encyclopedia of SBURB Device Upgrades
description: Whoa! This book contains a bunch of captcha codes for what appear to be SBURB devices and tools to circumvent most of the tedium of alchemy and inventory management. Simply reading it is enough to populate your session's Atheneum with all the codes inside!

name: String Shot
description: Every strum sends out bullets from the guitar's gun-barrel neck that pierce your enemies. They will feel your art.

name: Slimy Blue Mentos
description: They're gooey, not entirely solid, and leave slime on your fingers when you touch them. Ew.

name: Apollo\'s Lyre
description: Now you can jam out like a God. Without donkey ears. Or with, whatever suits you.

name: Complete Sburb Game Guide
description: This book give the reader access to infinite knowledge of the session they are in, if they can make any sense of it. Also makes an awesome paperweight.

name: Lich\'s Armor of the Dark Sun
description: A breastplate brimming with dark energy. A symbol of a dark sun is seen on the front. Whenever its wearer enters a room everything seems a little darker, a little colder and a little less happy all of a sudden.

name: Karsk
description: It's either way too early for vodka, or way too late for coffee. Either way, you should probably not be drinking it.

name: nachon torky
description: a torky stuffd with nachons. giv thanks.

name: Washington\'s Axe
description: "I cannot tell a lie! It was I who cut down the cherry tree." - Hell yes it was.

name: Homewrecker
description: A normal baseball bat covered in the same kind of clay used to make bricks. This looks like it'll smash some imp skulls.

name: Plasma Splatterer
description: This shotgun splatters accelerated plasma in the general, kind-of, probably, sort-of the direction of your enemies.

name: Phonograph\'s Lament
description:
This record contains incredible tunes somehow created by combining the classics and your favorite songs.
Unfortunately it can only be played using a Phonograph.

name: Beat Mesa Miniature
description: A large record with turning gears under it, said to only be harmed by Echidna\'s quills. This is not your session\'s scratching mechanism, so you can safely use this oversized disc as a shield or weapon, even against echidna! It\'s not like miniature sburb sessions get scratched every time this gets hit, right?

name: Ace of Cups
description: The Ace of Cups indicates a new beginning of an emotional sort, such as the start of a romance. A positive card... But the chalice it turns into holds a potion so potent your enemies will see in reverse.

name: Ace of Pentacles
description: The Ace of Pentacles is a sign of prosperity and wealth to come, and encourages you to introduce something new to your situation... like the powerful magic amulet it turns into!

name: Bad Rap
description: A black spade-tipped cane. Perfect for delivering a vicious drubbing to those in even more flagrant violation of the law than yourself.

name: Razrshades
description: A par of super-cool sunglasses with a Droid Razr heads-up display on the inside. You can be a smartphone hipster without even using your hands!

name: Coca-Cola Dress
description: A short red dress with the Coca-Cola logo running vertically up the front.

name: Bone Knife
description: Ancient knives that glow with a primeval power... nah these just look like some regular old bones that were sharpened.

name: Manic Backpack
description: A rather cute looking white backpack with brown leather straps that hold the front and side pockets shut, and thick, comfortable shoulder straps that cross over the torso in an X shape. Actually makes carrying heavier things in it a lot easier.

name: Formal Panties
description: It's like a tuxedo... for your butt.

name: Viruatop
description: A perfect blending of the Virtual Boy's retinal scarring and a laptop's portability.

name: Rose Cards
description: The Hearts have turned to Rose Blooms and the Spades are now Thorns. Aside from that, you can't shuffle them because there always seem to be some Rose Petals in the way.

name: RotoKiller
description: An upgrade to the Sod Buster, it now features four heads that spin rapidly when you wield it. Great for slicing and dicing, or for quickly plowing a garden.

name: Cat Shirt
description: A fun shirt depicting the image of a cat. :3

name: Glassophone
description: You're not quite sure what the acoustic properties of glass are, or for that matter how all the keyholes, springs, and valves can even work without breaking.

name: Eight Ghost Gauntlets
description: A set of eight ghost gauntlets of varying size and shape, as if this were the reflection of a singular ghost gauntlet in a broken mirror. None of them seem to be particularly strong or useful.

name: Octoectoplasmic BCI
description: A headset that senses your brain waves and interprets instructions for a set of eight ghostly arms to follow. Not as powerful individually as the set of two, but think of all the things you can hold!

name: Playful Fuzzy Thong
description: Well now.

name: White King\'s Crown
description: This crown doesn't really do anything, but it's a symbol of Prospitian values, and the principle of always protecting peace until the very end.

name: Seer\'s Glasses
