description: A pair of glasses that you can use for staring into infinity. A must need for the upcoming seer.

name: Kneehugger Hoodie
description: A hoodie that is extra-long, stopping just above the knees.

name: Hoodset
description: A Hoodie with Headphones on the inside of the hood for maximum convenience of music and warmth

name: Frankenfeller
description: One third gun, one third blade, one third giant syringe. Everything you need to take down the horrible beasts you must be creating in your spare time.

name: Wings of Icarus
description: Be careful around that sun dog...

name: Exploding Marbles
description: Marbles with an explosive core that activate on contact. Seemingly useless one at a time, but lethal in large amounts.

name: Red Scare
description: This top of the line riot helmet has everything from nightvision to a laser rangefinder. The desert rangers used these to augment their lethality.

name: Starflake Cardigan
description: This wool sweater has black buttons and a shooting star inspired pattern. Or are those actually snowflakes? You aren't quite sure.

name: Black King\'s Crown
description: This crown doesn't really do anything, but it's a symbol of the rule of Dersian forces and the ultimate objective the King must strive to fulfill.

name: Oddly Metallic Amulet
description: An amulet made out of an odd metal. It has some minimal defensive properties.

name: Hollowed Metallic Amulet
description: This amulet looks like the inside's been hollowed out with some tiny explosives. The heat has also refined the metal a little bit. Neat.

name: Dual-Metal Amulet
description: An amulet with a Nintendium core inside a shell of an unknown protective metal. It's exceptionally good at taking a beating, but it's a bit too small to be extremely useful.

name: Dual-Metal Hoop
description: A hula hoop made out of Nintendium and a mysterious, unidentified metal. It's pretty good at whacking things.

name: Cards Against Humanity
description: A card game where the objective is to combine two cards to make the most offensive phrases and jokes possible. Perhaps you could tell some of these jokes to Imps?

name: Visionary\'s Teashades
description: With these stylin' babes you can see all the possibilities in front of you. It's  like anything could happen, and that's WILD.

name: Dizzy Lizzie Teashades
description: This plastic red lenses are great for looking hip and unusual, and hide your bloodshot eyes (you know from sleep deprivation. Yeah that's it.)

name: Star Gazer\'s Teashades
description: These lenses are tinted black because black is edgy, but opaque enough that you don't have to remove them to look at the stars. And they're prescription.

name: High Quality Yorkshire Wool
description: This super-strong wool is highly resistant to weapons of all sorts. Especially the Chain Blade.

name: Beatnik Teashades
description: These coal black smooth shades are perfect for a poorly lit cafe. Swing it baby.

name: Waxwinged Hoodie
description: This winged hoodie works well for flying short distances, just stay away from heat sources.

name: Glow in the dark dress
description: A fancy dress that can glow in the dark!

name: Magic Squid Eye
description: If you stare into the gelatinous yuck inside this glossy orb long enough, you get vague premonitions of the unknowable. It might be more useful as a blunt instrument though.

name: AnvilGun
description: What looks like a Light Machine Gun that is actually extremely heavy, made entirely of cast iron, and has a large flat surface at the top. Sure, it can shoot bullets, but it would also make a very effective club.

name: Pointy Anime Hammer
description: This hammer is completely out of proportion and kind of awkward to use, but hey, it makes the enemies go doki doki.

name: Star Spangled Cardigan
description: This thick knit coat might be a little too warm, but is definitely comfy. It's embellished star shaped patches and black wooden buttons give it a playful but mature feel.

name: Black Flame Chainsaw
description: The flames on this act like a blacklight, it's like Texas Chainsaw Rave Party up in here!

name: Plush Tenta-Saw
description: A chainsaw to embarrassingly fondle and hug your enemy into submission, and maybe penetrate a little... as in cut their skin, you pervert.

name: Nevermelt Ice Statue
description: Even though it's made out of ice the statue is in perfect condition. No matter how warm it gets it does not melt, as if it was stuck in time...

name: A Brief History of Time and Space
description: Everything you could possibly need to know about the three dimensions of space, the fourth dimension of time, and how one can be used to warp the other.  Does not cover further dimensions, or eldrich horrors from beyond the edge of the universe.

name: Paint Blaster
description: Paint your enemies black and blue, and a lot of other colors too.

name: iDog Amp\'d
description: A small, robotic toy dog that dances to your music, which is played by a horrible quality speaker on it's back.

name: Old Crowsword
description: A blade that vaguely represents a crow, decorated by black feathers, as well as a talon-shaped handle holding a tiny aluminum can.

name: Miss of Paint God Tier Outfit
description: A dainty little outfit for a dainty little heroine!

name: Alien Power Cell
description: A mysterious power source that doesn't seem to be compatible with any manmade or alternian technology.

name: Jinx Body Pillow
description: A body pillow of the character Jinx from the popular game League of Legends.

name: GirlyTyl\'s Infinite Bag of Kinky Item Submissions
description: A violet-haired, brown furred plush kitten's head sticks out of the top of this light pink canvas backpack, with soft brown leather straps over the pockets and a thick, comfortable harness that crosses the torso in an X shape. On the outside, it appears perfectly innocent, although you can't and don't want to imagine what it might contain.

name: Feather Duster
description: A small black feather duster with a white handle, right out of a french maid's arsenal of cleaning supplies.

name: Kraken Sees Alltop
description: This is... a giant eyeball and a computer in one? You can see a computer screen gazing at you through the cephalapod's pupil, but you don't even want to know how you input keys with this. You'll just leave that an open-ended gaming abstraction.

name: Ratchet
description: A ratcheting socket wrench.

name: Mechanized Garrote
description: Interface technology has come far, producing this lovely garrote - great for interfacing between life and death. It has the side benefit of functioning as a computer, so it's great for strangling imps, while accidentally sending messages to your friends/crush!

name: Toilet Paper Air Cannon
description: A pink and purple plastic tube that launches rolls of toilet paper. Just pull the lever.

name: Vanilla Pod
description: This wiry dried fruit smells amazing.

name: Spike Shield
description: This wooden shield has a bunch of nails sticking out of it.

name: Mythic Knitters
description: Ancient knitting needles once possibly used by an ancient mythological yarn deity.

name: Swaggie
description: The coolest wearable blanket the world has ever seen through tinted lenses.

name: Toothlighter
description: Turn it on and the bristles catch on fire! Well, that's one way to clean your mouth.

name: Father\'s Pipe
description: It gets boring listening to confessions. Jesus was Middle Eastern so a little Marry Joe here and there is OK.

name: Crystal Wand
description: This is a pretty nice-looking wand. It's smoothly crafted and looks a bit on the fragile side, but it sparkles gently when you wave it.

name: Floral Laptop
description: It's a laptop, but with a floral design on it. It also smells a bit like a freshly picked rose...

name: OxiClean
description: OxiClean(tm) tackles household stains - Inside and out!

name: Squiddly Gown
description: A light pink dress with a pastel squiddle pattern and belt.

name: Turkey Armor
description: A suit of armor made entirely from turkey, complete with stuffing... somewhere. It smells delicious.

name: Wand of Minor Incindiary Majyyks
description: This wand emits an orangeish glow and is warm to the touch. However, it can be used to cast raging, powerful fireballs to burn and blister your enemies.

name: Possessed Turkey
description: A turkey that pulses with dark energy, occasionally making some very strange noises.

name: Glass Half Full
description: No matter how much you remove or add to this glass, the level never seems to change. Hmm, not sure what's in it, either.

name: Magic 8-Set
description: This headset is designed to look like a magic 8-ball, with the numbers within it showing the Pesterchum handle of whoever is contacting you.

name: Grand Star-Thorn Fedora
description: Covered in thorns composed of substance from the heart of neutron stars this hat conducts the might of the galaxy safely, separated from you by one whole layer of ordinary fedora.

name: Chalice of Water
description: Cool, refreshing, and stylishly antique.

name: Macrobian Spring Water
description: A small rusted cup fabled to hold water that can heal most wounds and prolong one's life. Don't waste it now.

name: Calling Card of the Noble Circle
description: It's a ominous dark card. Its colour appears to be black but the longer you look at it the more certain you are that it's actually a very dark purple. When you're alone you feel as if you can hear a voice coming from the card, calling out to you.

name: Robes of Silence
description: Because in space, noone can hear you scream.

name: Obsidian Amulet
description: An amulet of jagged obsidian. Wearing it makes you slightly afraid of stabbing yourself, especially since it tends to glow a dark purple whenever it gets close to your heart.

name: Distortion Compass
description: A compass that seems to distort space around you while it\'s worn, deflecting projectiles and occasionally coating your weapon in raw space-shredding power - which would be awesome if raw space-shredding power were at all stable, but as it is it\'s just as likely to explode in your face.

name: Holo-Computer
description: This computer has a built-in projector rather than a screen, making it somewhat portable. The holographic display works on a variety of surfaces, including an ogre\'s face, if you\'re okay with having a raging semi-blind ogre chasing you down.

name: Compu-Gloves
description: These gloves, wirelessly linked, have dual displays on the palms. It\'s operated by hand gestures. You hope you can remember your sign language...

name: Tesla\'s Fury
description: This new electrified hammer hits harder then a 25,000 volt fist in the face. Tesla would be proud.

name: XV - The Devil
description: The fifteenth card of the Major Arcana is the Devil, who symbolizes self-bondage and addiction. Break free from these things, as they hold you back and use this card to turn the faults of your enemies against them.

name: Zeus\' Lightning Rods
description: Used by the God of Thunder to channel the energy of powerful electric storms. Can also be used to make an extra-staticky sweater!

name: Snack of the Virgin Wizard
description: It looks like a bowl of highly radioactive worms, but who cares, you\'re certain that this will make you a wizard.

name: Z-Armor
description: An truly powerful piece of equipment with a red and white color scheme... You just have to be able to handle the booblights.

name: Santa Lucia Crown
description: A symbol of light and perseverance through the dark, this is a festive way to carry candles and sweets when you need both hands free.

name: Rubiphirerald
description: This dark grey gemstone seems to enhance a large amount of your abilities.

name: Inquisitive Plasma Cannon
description: The same old plasma, and the same old bespectacled plaid cannon; With a nack for unraveling the mysterious.

name: Black Queen\'s Crown
description: This spiky headdress doesn\'t have any powers, but it represents the wise and just ruling of Derse.

name: Cleansing Fires
description: You have introduced the power of fire and have created the ultimate cleansing weapon.  So strong that nothing is left in its wake.

name: Dead Turkey Overcoat
description: This thing just smells awful. It keeps enemies away though.

name: Vodkabrella
description: In Soviet Russia, umbrella rain vodka on YOU!

name: Chartreuse-Transparent Transpirationeer
description: A ski pole so cold to the touch it freezes whoever grabs it to absolute zero, stopping the transpiration of time. Better wear gloves!

name: Mazel Tov Cocktailerang
description: Many a drunken brawl has been settled by who is brave enough to catch these bad boys.

name: hellza blendr
description: what a shit blender it hardle blends anything

name: Shitty Blade Blender
description: This gigantic blender specializes in turning shitty blades into shitty blade puree. Unfortunately, it\'s not much use against anything even slightly more durable, and that includes imps. You suppose it\'s still better than whacking them with a toaster, though.

name: Jack of All Spades
description: This is the motherlode of weaponized cards, which emanates pure blackness, somehow, but is also shiny. (It\'s weird, okay.) The edges are so sharp you could cut someone, probably even stab them. You could light someone on fire with the pure energy this thing emits, or darken their vision or something. Et cetera. It\'s also awesome, utilizable and terrifying all at once.

name: Status Testing Item
description: This item is being used to test status effects and stuff.

name: Mysterious Medallion
description: An extremely large medallion with curious markings on it that don\'t really do anything. It makes a pretty good defensive device, but only because it covers most of your chest.

name: Nintendium Medallion
description: A large amulet made out of pure, indestructible Nintendium. It makes up for its lack of magical powers with its significant surface area.

name: Dual-Magnetic Hoop
description: A hoop made up of two magnets which are constantly attracting and repelling each other. If not properly controlled, they can reach an absurd rotational speed, damaging both the wielder and everything around them.

name: Mysterious Hula Hoop
description: A metallic hula hoop covered in strange engravings. It\'s surprisingly heavy.

name: Hula Hoop of Encased Evil
description: A hula hoop with glowing red markings that singe anything that touches them. It takes some practice to get it working well, but professionals can use it to burn through masses of enemies with ease.

name: Dual Grey Doublet
description: This gemstone has two shades of grey in it... perfect for boosting your potential.

name: Fretful Reaper
description: A majestic mix between and old, broken guitar you found in your basement and an old scythe. The strings wrap around the blade at the end, and they\'re probably sharper!

name: Topaz/Sapphire Doublet
description: This gemstone seems to have both a Topaz and Sapphire in it...

name: Ice Queen Crown
description: This sparkly tiara freezes the air around its spiky fractal surface, pouring from it a veil of chilly fog.

name: Queen Quill Besom
description: This diamond-hard twig broom seems more likely to inspire damage in your hardwood than luster, but cut the crap it\'s obviously meant for defending your nest, not tidying it.

name: Hallowe\'en Shrieker
description: This dark, mechanical bird kills with a high pitched sound. It usually only comes out to our plane of existence a few days around Hallowe\'en. But you\'ve \"Tamed\" one as your fighter.

name: Blindman\'s Teashades
description: These distinct and dark lenses will conceal that your eyes are missing or don\'t turn. Everybody will know that you\'re blind at a glance though. That\'s almost the entire point.

name: Green Sun Corneas
description: AND THEY SAID STARING AT THE GREEN SUN WOULD BE HARMFUL FOR YOUR EYES! HA HA HA!

name: Festive Medallion
description: A medallion infused with Christmas spirit. Now you can spread joy and cheer the slightly-less-violent way!

name: 9 of Spades / The Chained Darkness
description: A chain that seems to be tied to the darkness within someone\'s soul and seems to bring it out during battle.

name: Retro-Sci-Fi Goggles
description: For that 80\'s, B-movie, sci-fi feel on your hands-free computer. Also does a pretty good job of protecting your peepers.

name: Radioactive Blender
description: A high-powered blender that\'s emitting all sorts of radiation. Yes, using this is definitely a good idea.

name: hellza nuclear blendz
description: A piece of shit blender that\'s leaking liquid uranium all over the place. oh god its getin to your braincelz man

name: M16 Assault Rifle
description: A 3-round burst fire assault rifle made in the United States of America. Used by police and military forces. Riflekind, build, titanium, jet, Assault bonus +1, Accuse penalty -2

name: Bugged Wand
description: The wand flails violently in your hand. Perhaps it isn\'t the smartest thing to handle a bug while inside of a video game, oh well, you know for sure the underlings won\'t take it well.

name: Australium Wrench
description: This wrench is incredibly rare, and turns the underlings you destroy with it into statues of solid gold.

name: Hard-Light Holographic 3D iGlasses
description: A hands-free computer for people who don\'t mind seeing everything tinted red and blue.

name: MoThErFuCkIn mIrAcLeS, yO
description: You\'re not quite sure how in all hell this motherfuckin yoyo is so powerful, but you\'re sure its some sorta miracle.

name: Quantum Entanglement Dice
description: A pair of dice that is connected through the mysteries of quantum physics so that one always gives the same result as the other. Perfect for the unscrupulous gambler.

name: Fish Stick
description: A processed stick of whitefish, battered.

name: Cup of Tea
description: A good, old fashioned tea.

name: Green Tea
description: A calming steep of tea with possible health benefits.

name: Pepsi Blue
description: Awe man you thought this stuff was great way back in 2003. They still sell it in Indonesia.

name: Keytar
description: A sort of guitar, except instead of strings, it has keys like a keyboard. Or it could be seen as a keyboard on a stick. Either way, it makes a very wieldy bludgeon.

name: The Smoking Gun
description: Do you know what it feels like to have hot lead shot in your face? Would you like to?

name: Disappointing Lump of Butter
description: It\'s a lump of butter. It looks like it half melted at some point. The fact you had to fight your way through a dungeon for this pisses you off. Maybe if you throw it at something it\'ll run away and cry.

name: Prim Reacher
description: An ornate scythe on a fancy ribbon. Perfect for those who want to prance around in a leotard while chopping their enemies into tiny bits.

name: Fanciest Stick
description: The ribbon attached to this stick smoothly pulsates various colors according to the flow and rhythm of the wielder\'s movements: soothing cyan, furious red, and mysterious purple.

name: Rainbow Ribbon Rumba Staff
description: The rainbow ribbon on the end of this brightly-colored staff is much thicker, resembling a whip. Work a few aggressive movements into your routine, and this is sure to make your audience smart... culturally and physically.

name: Legendary Ribboned Staff of Aurora
description: A titanium staff, bearing the most beautiful silken ribbon on its top. The ribbon's silk is so light and so colorful, you feel as if only a goddess could wield it. In fact, you are not mistaken; this weapon belongs to the Roman goddess of sunrise, Aurora. This is the staff she uses to color the heavens.

name: Mystical Sky Ribbon
description: With a ribbon of delicately flowing, transparent rainbow, and a contingent of magical marble-like orbs floating around it, calling this staff "mystical" would be an understatement.

name: Broken Bottle
description: An alcohol bottle you smashed against a surface. Quite deadly, actually.

name: Glow-in-the-Dark Trumpet
description: A trumpet that glows in the dark, perfect for those long night marches.

name: Rolled-Up Poster
description: It\\\'s a glorious poster. Perfect for that blank space on your wall. You haven\\\'t actually seen the inside of the poster yet, but the possibilities are endless!

name: Ebonbonemarrow Grenade
description: This crystallized stone is liable to explode at any moment, sending out shards of painful dark bone marrow.

name: Clockwork Multi-Weapon Time Cube
description: A massive Rubik's Cube that, aside from the inherent time travel abilities, also sports a variety of weapon extensions. Now you don't need to rely on its sheer weight to defeat Underlings anymore!

name: Flyer Sword
description: An old flyer folded up into an origami sword thing. It's kinda sharp.

name: Jawbreaker
description: A little piece of candy that, in the wrong mouth, can put an unsuspecting fool into the ER.

name: Quantum Escape Portal Key
description: This key creates a portal to another dimension when pressed against a wall, offering easy escape from any situation. This does consume the escape key, so the trip is one way.

name: Microscope
description: A device for observing things that are too small to see with the naked eye, although at the moment you might be more interested in its use as a blunt instrument for bashing imps with.

name: Sweet Roll
description: This delicious pastry is spiced and has candied fruit in it. Yum.

name: Saffron Bun
description: A rich sweet bun flavoured with saffron and raisins.

name: Pickhammer
description: It\'s a combination between a sledgehammer and a pickaxe. It\'s got the hammer part on one end, and the pickaxe part on the other, and it\'s all on one wooden pole thing. Beautiful.

name: Telescopic Top Hat
description: It is well known that the stylishness of a top hat is directly proportional to its height.

name: Bottle of Absolute Black Vodka
description: Showcased in a distinctive black bottle, Absolut(e) Black is how vodka should be experienced.

name: Bottle of Denatured Alcohol
description: Strictly for use as fuel or paint solvent, this powerfully concentrated ethanol mix incorporates toxic and foul-smelling ingredients.

name: Rude Elixir
description: You prepare to kick back and motherfuckin\' snap into some rude elixir and maybe get your wicked zone on.

name: Omniscope
description: Despite the lens being completely opaque, this pearly white telescope allows you to see anywhere in the entire Incipisphere! It also crackles with odd green lightning from time to time, and seems to somehow fade in and out of existence.

name: 3D Sickle
description: This sickle is exactly like an ordinary colorfully-painted sickle in every way, except it's 3D! ...no wait, ordinary sickles are 3D as well. But this one has the added bonus of giving you a mild headache if you stare at it too long.

name: Athena\'s Shield
description: Freeze your enemies to stone!  Medusa's head was added to the shield after a little run-in with Perseus.

name: Poisoned Sickle
description: The edge of this sickle's blade is coated with a mildly toxic substance that miiiight poison your targets. If you're lucky.

name: Acoustic Electrifier
description: Caution: Play only with rubber gloves.  Each strum sends out electrical impulses, and unfortunately they are indifferent as to who they harm.

name: Pyramid Texts Transcription
description: This is a transcription of the most ancient texts known to man, telling of Osiris, god of the afterlife, and various spells that allow one to raise the dead, fly, and even threaten the gods into cooperation. It is unlikely any of them work, but wouldn\'t you still like to try?

name: Long Distance Unlocker
description: Nobody understood at first why you attached a key to such a long handle. Then they looked at the mess your server player made of your house.

name: Extra-Weighted Dice
description: Guaranteed to always land sixes up, but since they are way too heavy to actually roll properly, don\'t expect them to stay undetected for long. They make for decent projectiles, though.

name: Iron Fists
description: A pair of gloves you can use to burn your opponents face off! Or butt...or wherever you hit them.  Your steaming hot power will not only impress your allies, but also keep your clothes looking crisp and wrinkle-free!

name: Telescopic Magnifying Glass
description: You pick it up and look down the conveniently attached scope before throwing it. Take THAT, naked lady you totally weren't perving on.

name: Mirrored Chainsaw
description: Just in case your enemies weren't scared enough of chainsaws, now they can watch themselves get chopped in half!  Ideal for the fighting fashionista who needs to fix her make-up in the middle of strifing.

name: Steaming Discoball Thrower
description: Remove wrinkles from your enemies when you steam them flat with hot discoballs. Oooh, sparkly!

name: Super-calibrated Acoustic Electrifier
description: An upgraded version of the Acoustic Electrifier! It now targets only your enemies instead of all living tissue! (Warning: Use of rubber gloves still recommended.)

name: Bomberang
description: Sending timed explosives hurtling back at you is the only viable battle plan.

name: 3-Point Axe
description: An axe with its blade divided in three parts, like a fork. It's not much different from a normal axe. Or is it?

name: Acoustic Electric Rocket Striker
description: All danger to you has been eliminated.  Electrical impulses are now safely dispersed in rocket form! Your strums shoot rockets that explode with pre-calibrated frequencies that create the most beautiful music.

name: Orbital Stamp
description: A stamp coated an odd mix of satellite debris and moon rock. It looks like it's been in space for a long time.

name: Cheap Trick Cane
description: Whenever you threaten a foe with this cane, colorful silk flowers spring from its tip.

name: Guitar of Violent Predictions
description: This guitar TAKES ADVANTAGE of the very fact that OTHER CREATURES EXIST.  If its explosions don't kill your enemies, its nihilistic fortunes for their lives will.

name: PUPE
description: who put SHIT in my PIPE

name: Digital Book of Self Reflection
description: What meaning do words on paper have in this age of digitized information? This tome of smart-fiber pages explores this question with a dash of animation and a hint of surrealism.

name: Compu-Tome of the Anachronistic Heptagram
description: This heavy digitized book is loaded with data on spell cards. Each card is "password-protected" by a thought-provoking incantation, so you'll find your enemies begin engaging in self reflection as the death-dealing elemental beams sends them to the afterlife.

name: Thermal Suit
description: This suit has a metallic sheen to it. It\'s a tad on the heavy side, but it\'ll let you keep your temperature a while longer than you otherwise would in any environment.

name: Poisoned Sickletar of Violent Predictions
description: Your Guitar of Violent Predictions now ... expedites ... its predictions with deadly poison and blades.  And it still fires rockets.

name: Bed
description: It's for sleeping in. Notice: Does not come with sheets or pillows; will not work for ascending to God Tier.

name: -1 - the BIG MAN
description: no dude your reading it wrongg,,. dude... you got to FLIP it . TURN-WAYS

name: Edible Underwear
description: Invented by David Sanderson and Lee Brady in 1975: Candypants, the original 100% edible underwear.

name: Nikola\'s Quantum Spring
description: An electrified spring that exists in the third and fourth dimensions.

name: Box of Automatonic Legos
description: A box of Legos that assemble themselves into things when asked politely. Cool.

name: Stone Cold Unlocking Halberd
description: Cleave your enemy in two while unlocking your potential... and locks.

name: Osiris\' Rave
description: Simply opening this tome summons an image of Osiris, who proceeds to rock out his with new hit single, "I'm taking you to Egyptian Afterlife".

name: Ahab\'s Slicer
description: It is said this pizza cutter's laser precision was used by the great captain himself for preparing food on those long, silent nights.

name: Heaven\'s Light
description: Look at that beautiful(and very dangerous) new shine. NOW THAT'S THE POWER OF OXICLEAN!

name: Rainbow Black Light
description: A cute little black laser pointer with a rainbow adorning its length.  You think the light it casts might actually be rainbows.

name: Text-Eraser
description: A hand-broom that, in addition to sweeping away dust and your enemies, also erases written text. Be careful when cleaning posters.

name: Rainbow Steaming Discoball Thrower
description: Rainbow lights!  Steaming Disco Balls!  Party AND fight AND do household chores, all at the same time!!!!!!!!!!

name: Domino Mask
description: If anyone ever pulls out a shitty bandit mask and calls it a "Domino" mask, you're ready with a counter-argument.

name: Sawn-off shotgun
description:
A pistol's compact, but it doesn't pack much punch, right?
A shotgun kicks ass, but it's large, right?
Well here's your compact, kickass solution: the Sawn Off Shotgun! Does more damage than a basic shotgun, due to ballistics (you don't want to hear about it) but is half as big!

name: Blue T-Shirt
description: Good job, you painted your old shirt blue.

name: Blue Scales Shirt
description: Back on earth, you'd probably have to bring about the extinction of several species of blue reptile to get enough scales for this shirt. Luckily for you, this alchemized shirt carries no such guilt with it.

name: The Bright Idea
description: You always wanted a lightbulb to suddenly turn on over your head when you had an idea, right?

name: Shiny Rifle
description: It's golden, yet somehow lightweight, and fires infinite volleys of sharp amethyst crystal bullets. You're pretty sure that if it somehow does run out of ammo, you're never finding more.

name: Crystal of Radiant Lightning
description: Warning: Do not remove from sylladex if vulnerable to sacred electricity!

name: The Electrifying Gentleman
description: You are now the center of a miniature thunderstorm. This suit's conductive surface delivers stronger electrocutions on impact, and keeps you safely isolated from the lightning, but it doesn't come with a helmet, so you may want to a full head cover made of rubber.

name: Glockomole
description: You may have named your firstborn after avocados, but do your weapons fire them? I didn't think so.

name: Corrupted Mystery Data
description: The abominable, somehow tangible spawn of an innocent video game and an unwanted agent of unpredictable data rearrangement, this stuff should never have come into being. It feels like even the card it's kept on wants to expunge it forever. If freed from its card it finds itself drawn to electronics, which it irreparably damages if left to its devices for very long. Best to keep this stuff safely in your captchalogue.

name: Gold Hoodie
description: This hoodie is so shiny it's hard to look at it.

name: Winged Pastry-Slicer
description: A little bit girly for anyone's tastes, really, but it's light and easy to use.

name: Lunaric Backhand
description: Imbued with the powers of illusion and trickery, this colorful hockey stick is capable of taking over whole galaxies. You are getting delirious just looking at it.

name: When Ra taught Anubis Poetry
description: A collection of angst-filled poetry written by Anubis. When read aloud, the reader's voice becomes deep, and the curses laid within flare to life, starting their own chants. The angry song becomes any unfortunate bystander's self-fulfilling nihilistic prophecy.

name: Torture-master\'s Guitar
description: Your rocket firing, future predicting, deadly guitar now lashes electrified whips covered in poison instead of shooting rockets.  Fortunes are now efficiently "electrified" into your victim's brain before death.

name: Netchair
description: Instead of a seat, its a computer! Which makes sitting useless in it.

name: Scientifically Reconstructed Guitar
description: You have to admit, your last guitar was a bit of a mess.  With this new addition, Aperture science has simplified the weaponizing of your guitar to a molecular level!  The vibrations create micro-rifts in reality tearing at your enemies very being and inserting poison into the cracks via portal technology.

name: Prismatic Dragonbreath Suit
description: This armor reflects light and has dragon heads all over it, which unleash deadly flames - which double as a propellant, allowing you to fly.

name: Dark Soul Reapfractor
description: At some point this scythe started sucking in the souls of those you wielded it against to make its blade, make sure not to cut yourself with it.

name: Formal Amethyst Armored Dress
description: Looks gorgeous and practical against enemies.

name: Shuriken-spewer NRifle
description: You did it. You actually went and made an assault rifle that runs shurikens rather than bullets. Probably a stupid idea if you plan on assassinating anyone.

name: Pyrokinetic Technobookaxe
description: This axe's blade is made of flaming paper pages inscribed with texts detailing various methods to bridge the arcane and the scientific. It's a little hard to read without good sunglasses and flame-proof gloves, though.

name: Asteria\'s Star Scythe
description: Once carried by the goddess of the stars herself, this scythe contains power enough to light up the night skies. It has a long bronze handle and a sleek black blade made out of an unidentifiable metal that glimmers and gives off an unearthly glow.

name: Frost Mage\'s Gloves of White Defense
description: These strange, silvery-white gloves are studded with ever-frozen ice crystals. They seem to be capable of creating a shield whilst healing you.

name: Fiduspawn Chair Cards
description: Wheelchairs the size of cards that are also somehow moving on their own?! Wow, look at them go.

name: Grape
description: A single grape. Pretty tasty.

name: Golden Mech Rifle
description: Golden mechanical rifle that now fires perfected amethyst bullets at a far faster velocity and rate. It has a burst fire setting that you'll probably never use.

name: Reaching Cross-Ripper
description: This oversized lacrosse stick has a long blade on its other end and seems to emit a ghostly aura. There's no way is this legal in any decent sports venue, anywhere.

name: Icicle Bow
description: A frosty bow that shoots ice. It seems to freeze the enemy when hit. A little cold to the touch but a dangerous weapon none the less.

name: Long Island Iced Tea
description: This exotic drink is sure to knock the vacation goers' socks off. And their sobriety.

name: Four In The Mourning Perfume
description: Just the sophisticated aroma you can slap on at four in the morning when you're tired and sore and clutching your underwear in one hand, blood dripping down the left side of your face, so you can sit down and drink your over-priced coffee without onlookers thinking you're some kind of unhygienic wild child. Keep it classy!

name: Dual-Magnetic Pointy Hoop
description: Because the only thing a highly unstable series of magnets in hoop form needed was a variety of pointy bits glued to them.

name: Impact Gel
description: Why am I smashing my hand with this hammer?! The impact absorbing power of Impact Gel!

name: Aquatopathyst
description: This light grey gemstone seems to enhance a large amount of your abilities.

name: Kiki Kiki Cola
description: This sure poppin' elixir has all the eye of frog you need to put a spring in your jump and a curse in your laugh.

name: Ecto Blue Slime Bean
description: A thin membrane is the only thing that's keeping slime from getting all over the place. Also has healing properties. Are these... all... blueberry???

name: Coca-Cola with Slime
description: Normally, you would not be able to drink this, out of fear for copyright infringement. However, this drink is so obviously parodic that Coke just decided to foregoe suing and let this one slide. Now you can drink in peace.

name: Coca-Cola Vanilla
description: Coke already has some vanilla flavor in it, and many patrons of the product have been adding extra themselves since the 40s, but the advertisements for this beverage still emphasized the "new and curious" taste.

name: Alternian Soft Drink
description: Enraged by the Subjugglators' and their monopoly on the soda market, the Empress released a drink said to be more loaded with sugar than even the wicked elixir itself.

name: Automagical Legobot
description: A magical robot made of Legos. When damaged, he can reassemble himself after a short time - useful for taking the occasional hit.

name: Time Jumping Dagger
description: This dagger is capable of not only traveling through time but also performing minor magic tricks; for example cutting an imp in half with an added puff of smoke for that showy magician touch.

name: Hoodie of the Gods
description: This hoodie glows with a shimmering light, as if it where made of the golden fleece itself.

name: Zeushood
description: This godly hoodie grants you instantaneous access to the Olympian Cloud and the ability to communicate with any other being, mortal or otherwise, who is also connected. Which is basically a fancy way of saying it connects to the internet.

name: ButterPlush Dress
description: With this dress, you'll certainly be the cutest, most fluffy person around. Though the wings do look a little obnoxious at times.

name: Dawnbreaking Lightning Machine
description: Not quite Doomsday, but it'll seem to slit the sky itself with a powerful flash of lighting aimed wherever you please.

name: Oya\'s Cackling Broomstick
description: An enchanted relic said to summon wind and lightning to ward your foes. I mean it's not just said to, that's its primary attack. Whatever, you'll see.

name: Automatonic Lego Sleigh
description: A Lego sleigh pulled by eight Lego reindeer. It can fly, too, which is pretty darn cool.

name: Karpophoroi
description: A near-transparent black silk fabric teddy, loosely tied together by ruby red wires of a mysterious material, and decorated with the scales of a powerful dragon. Manages to look good on anyone, but strikes fear into the hearts of others.

name: Gaze of the Horrorterrors
description: Pointing this rifle at anything and pulling the trigger will cause one or more of the horrorterros to begin ogling that point intensely, damaging sanity of creatures struck by the gaze as their feeble minds attempt to grasp what terrible thing is suddenly watching them. Just don't ever look directly into the barrel.

name: Lesser Temporal Cape
description: At first glance, this is an ordinary cape. Closer inspection reveals that time goes all wonky near the outside of it. It could probably provide some defense... if you don't mind the faint ticking noise.

name: Classy Blood Armor
description: Though it looks like a nice, plain red suit, it is strengthened by a quick soak in the blood of your enemies.

name: Physic-al Assault
description: You don't know what quantum physics has to do with it, but this thing sure is heavy. If the weight doesn't damage your opponents enough, you will surely dazzle them with long words and equations they fail to comprehend.

name: Saturday Night Suit
description: A snazzy white suit for when you just gotta dance like it's still the seventies. Why would you even do that?

name: Stealth Shield
description: Your enemies won't even know what they hit.

name: Skullomania
description: It's a Luchadore Mask themed on Day of the Dead. After putting it you feel like you could suplex anything. A N Y T H I N G !

name: Neathglass Goggles
description: These goggles have strange green lenses, unlike anything you've ever seen... at least on the surface.

name: Windows to the Soul
description: In the hands of a powerful Seer, these mirrored cards can...look into people's souls, you guess. They also channel magic well. Assuming magic exists, of course.

name: 00 - Eternity
description: An infinitely powerful tarot card, drawn from a deck used by the gods themselves. The picture on it is constantly changing and gives you a headache if you look at it too long.

name: Fiduspawn Special Edition: Famous Physicists
description: A card game where you summon tiny copies of some of the greatest minds of all times and pit them against each other (or your enemies) in heated debates.

name: Emerald Dual Saw Knives
description: This looks exactly like your old weapon, except now it's just a deep emerald color. Besides looking a little different, you don't think there's anything new to it.

name: Poisoned Kunai
description: This is exactly the same as your current kunai, except now you have to be extra careful about not getting cut by it. Otherwise... Well, just keep some antidote nearby.

name: Sophisticate Tomb-Raider Long-Gun
description: Technologically elite, a direct hit from this electronically-powered beauty could vaporize a zombie's torso. And of course all your hits are direct hits; a gentleman such as yourself never misses.

name: Nuclear Lemonade Holocaust
description: This weapon utilizes the most up-to-date lemon-based technology so that you can be sure that when you launch one of the large, highly-radioactive lemons, all that will be left of the target is ashes and the slight scent of a particularly sour yellow fruit.

name: Sweeple
description: A funny red broom that exalates a faint scent of red apples. Very cheery.

name: The Sand Reckoner
description: This badass laser gun can was made to fire at a range of over half a lightyear away, once thought able to pierce the universe all the way through.

name: Firmament V-Gun
description: Should a solid shell have ever divided the Earth and heavens, you could surely blast the limits to dust.

name: Evadne Armament
description: This harpoongun/cannon/ray gun thing utilizes both hydrolic mechanisms and plasma to fire what's either a lazer that smells like ocean water or incredibly high-velocity steam.

name: Wrinkleshocker
description: A mega ultra electric iron. Shoots arcs of electricity everywhere, but never seems to hit you. The appliancekind abstratus is a joke no more!

name: Apple Glass 3D
description: A completely useless accessory, made of two differently colored apples attached to  the sides of a pair of 3D Glasses.

name: First Aid Kit
description: Hold still and TAKE YOUR MEDICINE LIKE A MAN!

name: Electric Punishment
description: Lighting arcs from the whip, good thing the handle is rubber or you might electrocute yourself!

name: iMachine Gun
description: Texting while driving is dangerous enough, but now you're texting while shooting? You might just kill someo-- oh, right.

name: Bloody Mary Dress
description: A short black dress with red accents. It is designed to be comfortable while you dance in the blood of your enemies.

name: Torch Staff
description: A staff with a lit torch on both ends. It has a comfortable grip in the middle to protect from splinters and burning yourself.

name: Jai Alai Basket
description: Used to catch and throw balls at speeds reaching 188 mph. This sport is totally safe.

name: Gaea\'s Wand
description: The force of life is at your fingertips. A slick marble wand infused with Gaea's power; with it, bend life to your favor, and destroy your enemies.

name: Timekeeper\'s Headset
description: The symphony of eons echoes in this handy mobile computer. You still think that you just could've gotten a laptop.

name: Spacial Lunchtop
description: A black lunchtop with a spiral on its cover. Now you can send messages everywhere. Or so you feel.

name: Armored Dress
description: Ladies & Gentlemen! Ever wanted to look great on the battlefield but didn't want to have to sacrifice the protection from bulky armor? Well now you can have both! Enjoy looking great while not dying!

name: Infermeow
description: A tasteful kitten's tail with a bit of even more tasteful FIRE.

name: Beehive
description: NOT THE BEES!

name: Rifle Pistol
description: A long-ranged pistol with minimal size.

name: Cardboard Fedora
description: A fedora made from folded cardboard. Whoever's idea was this was obviously a master genius.

name: Gas-Fedora
description: When you thought your fedora couldn't be more classy, you were wrong. Putting a gas filter and a mask on it was the best idea you had in your whole life. Now it can protect your head AND your face.

name: 3D-ifier
description: Makes anything drawn with the marker 3-dimensional and/or operational.

name: Taiyaki
description: A fish-shaped cake filled with bean paste. Perfect for post-convention binge eating.

name: The Green Snaplash
description: This thing...is awesome. You have created a wonderful whip, with green and yellow lightning sparks coming off. Anything that touches this is...well, dead. It's awesome. You're awesome. Everything's awesome.

name: Bunnytop
description: A pair of lovely bunny ears that contain a fully functional laptop.

name: Battery-Powered Shotgun
description: A high-powered electricity-based weapon, unfortunately with a very low-powered power source, so it is perpetually set to a lower setting.

name: Rainbow Elixir
description: It's a bottle of Rainbow Faygo. Well, you think that's what it is, but the bottle has no labels. You're not sure if it's chemicals keeping the colors from blending or freaky game magics, but you don't want to know. Probably both.

name: The Burning
description: A large...steel, maybe?...well a large folding chair embroidered with depictions of dragons and other mythical beings. It is hot to the touch near the base, but the handle is only warm. Could probably cut through imps like butter.

name: iDorkhat
description: The ultimate in geekery.

name: Google Goggles
description: Goggles to access Google! Or, you know. Some other useful websites. It's basically a computer but you thought it was a good idea to have them cover your eyes with a fitted strap. Nice.

name: Virtual Laser Goggles
description: Play videogames and shoot lasers at fake monsters to shoot lasers at real monsters with these cool custom Virtual Boy goggles! Cons: everything looks red and also you can't actually see the real world. Pros: it's a Virtual Boy, there are no pros.

name: Cross Stud Dress
description: Damn. Those studs look like they could hurt someone.

name: Buzzshield
description: A shield modified to also serve as a chainsaw. Effective for offense, defense, and cutting down trees.

name: Firelance
description: Now you can stab your enemies and watch them burn at the same time.

name: Flaming Blue Spherehelm of Spectral Spectralness
description: This helmet sure does give you some bad helmet hair, and it has an awesome flaming decor on the sides. I wonder how fast you can go now...

name: Magic Cueball Glasses
description: Absolutely useless for vision, but untold secrets lurk beneath the surface.

name: Bominomerang
description: A chain reaction of wildly unpredictable explosions. Perfect.

name: Bombitonomeiconerang
description: This is just getting ridiculous.

name: Cruxite Wand of the Mystics
description: A wand with the mysterious powers of Sburb itself. Who would've thought of this? The Overseer glares at you as you make this item.

name: Tightey Whiteys
description: A pair of plain white underwear with no manufacturer's mark.

name: bater uop
description: An unbelievably shitty baseball bat. Every hit with this turns out to be a bunt, unless you actually try to bunt with it, in which case the baseball just goes right through it.

name: Elven Grand Wizard\'s Hat
description: Some elves are slightly more magic than others. They wear hats to be easily distinguished, like this one. Some of course say, those Grand Wizards are no more magic than an ordinary hedge elf, they just wear the prettier hats and have decent PR.

name: Autolocking Spacewhale Crosshairs
description: Whether prey from the clouds or from the clear, may your sight point true and  always be on target, no matter how elusive.

name: Studded Vengeance
description: A fragmentation grenade which blasts tiny Legos when exploding.

name: Dal the Billard Bunny
description: A playfully-colored fuzzy knitted bunny with doll-like eyes so complacent and so fuckin' soulless you know it must have eldritch sentience. Dal the Bunny wants to be your and eternity's new best friend!

name: Jelly Fish
description: A would-be umbrella-shaped marine animal, but made entirely of blue gelatin.

name: Crayola-fying Lens
description: The most magical magnifying glass ever. Although you\'re pretty sure a magic marker is the wrong kind of magic...

name: Quantum Crowbar
description: This crowbar is very useful for both solving quantum mechanic equations and beating the snot out of parasitic, head-clinging aliens.

name: Hero of Space Hoodie
description: Hero of Space God Tier Hoodie, as worn by Jade Harley, the Witch of Space. Or so it says on the label.

name: Froggie Hoodie
description: A bright green hoodie apparently styled in honor of the Speaker of the Vast Croak, with ornaments similar to animal parts sewn on.

name: Silly Frog Sweater
description: The shape this garment is fashioned into, though vague, is clearly totally illegal. Don\'t let her malevolent highness catch you wearing this.

name: Wimpy Bean Sprout
description: The slim white stalk of a plant with a few pale, wilted leaves droops here. Now that you think of it, perhaps you shouldn't have doused it in sunblock to protect it from the sun.

name: Fire Poker
description: You're always saying you have a lot of irons in the fire, but now you can have actual irons in the fire!

name: Plasmatic Palmblasters
description: Your typical state-of-the-art plasma destroyer beam, except in glove form.

name: Fedora of the Green Sun
description: Hey dude I love your ha- OH GOD MY EYES IT BURNS!

name: Time-Eraser
description: The ever-spinning cogwheel on this broom's center helps you clean dust and foes very quickly. Also helps if you want to slack off.

name: 220 Magiwatt Wand
description: This seems like your ordinary choice wand, although it specializes in electrical magic, if it even makes sense. Do not recharge.

name: Scatter Multifold Time-Eraser
description: Your best time-sweeping tool now with the splendid Pop-A-Matic technology. If you're lucky, clean the moment when you were beat up. Ages 7+.

name: Really Fast Sickle
description: This extremely aerodynamic sickle can easily reach speeds that normally your hand should not even be able to keep up with.

name: Reflective Nuclear Bomb
description: A nuclear bomb with the surface polished to gleaming perfection so that your enemies can see their own terrified faces before they blow up!

name: Cup of Ecto-Tea
description: A teacup with a blue liquid in it. It looks like blue tea, but slimier.

name: Green Hexafold Polyversal Eraser
description: Cleaning the multiverse, one sweep at a time, fueled by the power of the Green Sun.

name: ScratchingNo.
description: One scratch with this vaguely backscratcher-shaped collection of multicolored pixels and artifacts can spread its corrupted contagion to another entity, causing them to register poorly on the physical plane for the rest of their existence. It goes without saying that you really should not scratch your own back with this.

name: Holy Gunbristler
description: A broom that, in addition to sweeping all possible sins, fires blessed rounds against your foes! Works surprisingly well with undead.

name: Blackest Gem
description: This gemstone is filled with powerful magic, sealed away inside of it.

name: Suit yourself
description: Its either my way or the highway.

name: Fear No Pizza
description: Along with being a master of the forge, Hephaestus is also a master of the oven!

name: Healing Tonic
description: A bottle filled with a slimy, blue substance. The label says it helps with injuries. Only one way to find out!

name: Corrupted Knight of Light Chaos God Tier Armor
description: The garb once worn by a Knight of Light. It has been corrupted through powerful dark magicks and enhanced into armor capable of rendering any mere God Tier's attacks futile.

name: Dev Request Flag
description: This massive, white flag is a signal to the creators of this universe that they are needed. Hold it up high, give it a wave, and maybe they will come to your aid. If they're not busy. Which they usually are.

name: Spectral Rift Tearing Guitar
description: Science has combined the unknown with the absurd to create this weapon.

name: Cerberhu Slenchfirer
description: Congratulations, you can now fire bullets with this stupid wreck... but at least now the name makes sense. Three heads, three specibi.

name: Cursed Golden Gunscythe
description: Gaudy but versatile with both long and mid-range strike capabilities imbued with the power of lost souls.

name: Set is Watching
description: What's this!? This book's cover has a protruding depiction of Set, Egyptian god of Storms and Evil, but the pages are filled with depictions of eerie-looking eyes!

name: Apep Will Eat You While Set Watches
description: This gold-plated tome/rifle shoots the personification of chaos and darkness (which obviously glows green) and then proceed to project a seemingly infinite amount of silently judging eyes from its many pages. Most opponents will die of heart attack before the evil snake even reaches them.

name: Venom Cathedra of the Scorpion Tail
description: A regal purple throne with curving blue decals surrounding it. Curved scythe blades mount the back of the seat, dripping with poison. Hell yeah.

name: Pogo Hammercue
description: This might be good for playing pool, if you ignore the hammer head.

name: Greenflame Meteor Staff / Greenlazer Nebula Eraser
description: This staff/gun duality weapon glows with an immense power that you probably either shouldn't have or don't need.

name: Lovers\' Halberd of Keys
description: A halberd made for lovers with secrets. You're pretty sure it will work just fine with one user, though.

name: Nyx\'s Time-Computing Holographic Shadowspecs
description: These powerful glasses allow the user to see everything, everywhere, everywhen, and wipe it from existence. It also works as a handy-free computer!

name: Lucy in the Sky With Diamonds
description: A really trippy record. If you hold it up to the light just right, you feel like you can see the night sky. Cool!

name: Blue Dragon\'s Talons of Arrows
description: Surely enough, this dragon's talons were made out of arrows. Who knows how that happened?

name: Blood Hammer of the Deep
description: Infused with the blood of your foes and the unborn, this hammer is a crime against life itself.

name: Basher of the Brooding Caverns
description: Whater-logged with the multicolored tribute of natural selection, this massive hammer has crushed thousands of would be grubs and can probable to the same to skulls.

name: Searing Dragonfire Armor
description: Just be careful around your friends with this, they might think you're an actual fireball sent by an angry god.

name: Nintendo-Approved Gunglove
description: It's a glove with a gun built into it. You guess it's pretty cool, although you're more than sure that you could've gotten the same result by taping a shotgun to a glove. It bears the Official Nintendo Seal of Approval.

name: Winged Trenchcoat
description: A combination of cosplay wings and a trench coat.

name: The Pizzsaw
description: This thing can destroy both the thickest trees and the deepest dish pies in the universe. You wonder how frog meat would taste on a pizza.

name: Ullapool Cue
description: The chalked tip of this long badass stick detonates upon contact, indefinitely, apparently without running out of explosive charges.

name: Ullapool Cue Bunny Launcher
description: This tricked out pool cue utilizes powerful contained explosions to fire rabbits at shockingly lethal speeds with the pull of a trigger. It also never runs out of rabbits for some reason.

name: Pocketskulltop Watch
description: For telling time and managing your files, you suppose; with a hip green skull motif. Connect to the internet in an English gentleman's style.

name: Eldritch English Pocket Watchtop
description: This thing... it haunts you. A pocket-watch it seems, of a devilishly hard but light and unknown metal casing, emblazoned with the sickening face of an unknown but horrifying skeletal god which you intuitively know to be the destroyer of all things to come. Its clock face and even numerals flash with such colours, colors, colours. You just hope hope you don't have psychotic break from those flashing lights before your eyes.

name: Omni-Skull Pocket-Watchtop
description: An intricate and eloquent floral skull design marks a slick white casing, smooth as a cue ball and as hard as diamond. The funny thing is you can't actually open this pocket watch without making like that Nazi in Indiana Jones  who got his face melted, but you can check your email with just the outside.

name: Starry Space Cardigan
description: Patterned like the night sky on a dark and star-filled night, this vest seems to bend space around it if even just a little.

name: Spacial Fabric Cardigan
description: This black cardigan seems to bend space around it.

name: Chalk Wand
description: This has to be at least ten times better........nah, it's pretty much just a big piece of chalk.

name: Quick-Stash Rifle
description: This short rifle folds in two so you can conveniently stuff in your trench coat pocket and walk away like nothing happened.

name: Screwrench
description: One end is screwdriver, one end is a wrench, and all in one convenient tool.

name: Lonely Trusty Knives
description: Man, now even your knives feel alone.  If they didn't have you they'd probably slit their wrists, if they had wrists.

name: Princess Jellyfish Dress
description: A snow white tutu with a poofy bell-shaped bottom, pearls and lace trailing off like tendrils. With this you'll feel like the royalty you are.

name: Cup of Bodacious Black Tea Sorrow
description: This looks like a tea cup of tar, but slimier and it smells of rancid seafood.

name: 3D Glasstop
description: With these new glasses you can compute... IN 3D!

name: Dual Flaming Knives
description: Knives. That are on fire. Excalibur, eat your heart out.

name: Boston Baseburner
description: A flaming baseball bat. It allows you to see the baselines better in night games, and makes the umpire FAR more likely to call a ball than a strike.

name: Computerpack
description: Of course, you should never NOT have a computer on you. This handy - actually pretty cumbersome - computer backpack will keep you connected nearly everywhere!

name: Overpowering Star Rod
description: As you wield this weapon, you feel forced to run like a maniac while chanting an annoying tune, the very act of which is likely to set you down a slippery slope of insanity while the rainbow slowly consumes your entire physical, mental, and then spiritual being.

name: Squiddly Chainknives
description:
A pair of small, squiddle-printed chainsaws connected at the handle by what looks like a plush tentacle.
 It's the most adorable yet unnecessarily dangerous thing you have ever seen in your life.

name: Shadowplate Helmet
description: Made from the scales and bones of a being from the void, it resonates with a deep, echoing abyss. At times, one may even hear the distant call of the horrorterrors.

name: SNR SMG
description: At the heart of this carbine lies a collapsed star, a tiny stream of its radiation and starstuff bursting out the barrel at 30000 km/s as you hold the trigger. Somehow the recoil doesn't kill you, probably in a similarly disbelief-suspended way a supernova can be carried around inside a portable rifle.

name: Drilling Gloves
description: You can now drill through baddies with every punch of these gloves!

name: Second Law Rail Gun
description: The ancient electromagnetic cannon sits in rust, it's crude and viscous clockwork exposed and apparently ticking down. Everything is ticking down.

name: Redshift Scythe
description: At first glance this reaping tool seems to have hit rock bottom, bent out of shape and dripping with rust. But made of futuristic alloys, it's still razor sharp and easily maneuverable. You guess nothing can last forever though.

name: Bottle of Carbonated Water
description: This water seems a bit fizzy... oh well, you guess you could use it for the creation of bottled soda.

name: Tome of Madness
description: Some sorry soul attempted to try study the Old Gods these are his notes, it's quite amusing as you can see how his mind deteriorates over time.

name: Dual Miracle Slicing Blades
description: Two blades that literally allow you to cut up natural phenomenon. You have no idea how the hell that works, but hey, you're down with it, as long as it cuts underlings just as well.

name: Cow Skull
description: A skull from an ordinary cow. May be used in satanicow rituals.

name: Mechanized Bow
description: This bow is constructed out of metal and various interlocking parts. It may look fragile, but it is surprisingly effective.

name: Flaming Cow Skull
description: Now that is some real demonic crap. Maybe it is lit by the hell fires, maybe you've set it on fire. Still demonic.

name: Pinkfeather Pummeler
description: Now you've finally got something to deal with those pesky flamingo thieves!

name: Squiddles Lunchscarf
description: Warm, colorful, and convenient! If not a little uncomfortable...

name: Faulty Flamingo Fortuneteller
description: The flamingo lies! Its little pink wings speak nothing but lies!

name: The Complete Compendium of Current Complete and Conceptual Knowledge of the Universe and Beyond
description: Exactly what it says on the packaging, as if this book wasn't heavy enough it's completely made of gold.

name: Doctor Who Screwdriver
description: It's a literal Philips-head screwdriver with a handle patterned like an old-timey blue phone box. There's nothing sonic about it at all...

name: Poster of the Doctor Holding a Regular Screwdriver
description: Okay, now the Alchemiter is just trolling you. This is a poster of the eleventh Doctor holding a regular screwdriver instead of the Sonic Screwdriver. Somehow, he doesn't look as awesome as he used to.

name: iStache
description: Less mainstream than a phone, less user friendly, totally stylin'. The power of a downgraded PC at the bow of your lip!

name: Button
description: It's just a button. Y'know, the kind you get on dress-shirts and coats and stuff.

name: Hip Cane
description: A stylish, hip cane. It has a worn appearance and seems to be made from a pelvic bone!

name: Duttingo Prophet
description: "He is... [the] bird. [It] is him." And very inaccurate too. But don't tell him that, he might get upset.

name: Home Invasion Shot Gun
description: This pump action fires rounds of salt, because a gentleman seeks to disarm before maim. It's also packed with deadly shrapnel, because a man doesn't mess around when protecting his family.

name: Sugar \'N Spice Rifle
description: Some amateurs might play it safe and fire salt rounds, but you know what crystalline substance gets the point across with a sense of style, and it's SWEET.

name: Yardchucks
description: Can be chucked. One whole yard.

name: Loo Roll
description: After combining your toilet paper with your British flag, you got British-style toilet paper. How exciting!

name: Coffee Cake
description: This coffee flavored dessert is crumbly and yummy.

name: Prismapocalyptic Electro-Dragon Armor
description: This light-refracting armor, etched with the forms of ancient and powerful dragons, serves shockingly well in a modern post-apocalyptia.

name: Hellfire Janitor
description: A broom wielded by the most powerful demon janitors. It not only sweeps dust, it burns the floor entirely. Fire extinguisher not included.

name: Hellfire Minotaur Skull-on-a-Chain
description: Transcending punk into a new genre of obscene, you could wear this as a bulky amulet or hit stuff with it you guess, if you're not afraid of burning yourself or demonic possession.

name: Fists of Steel
description: Boxing gloves made out of metal. That's really all there is to say on the matter.

name: Star Piercing Yari
description: A massively over-sized spear with a massive drill on the top of it... However, it is also blessed with the amazing power to shoot drill shaped projectiles, so it's a perfect ranged weapon, up close or far away.

name: Magic Blade-Whip
description: The most ridiculous looking whip ever. It seems to have small blades coming out of this. Who designed this thing? Oh well. It will absolutely hurt whatever comes into contact with it.

name: Unholy Sweeper of the Fire Lord
description: An item whose sole existance is based only on legends, this broom was used by the highest Fire Lord themselves to clean the holy dust setting on their rooms.

name: Shining Psychadelic Flamingo
description: You have no idea why anyone would want something so ridiculous, and yet, you can't stop looking at it.

name: Clawed Green Throne
description: This large green felt-fabric throne has random claw marks on it. It doesn't look mauled, per se. More.. scratched?

name: Daggers of Sophia
description: The shining pink daggers from the Heart Denizen Sophia are so pink it hurts your eyes. At least they're easy to kill things with.

name: Microwave Rifle
description: You didn't think it was a good idea, and it isn't. If anything it's dangerous to even hold the thing. But oh, is it fun!

name: Courier Bag
description: Agile and stylish, this old-timey bag is completely useless compared to your silladex. That's what makes it cool.

name: Die of the Deceased
description: A set of dice that contain weird ghost majyyks.

name: Extra-Dark Coffee
description: Damn you needed this. Unless you're a non-coffee drinker, in which case RUN AWAY KIDS! ONCE YOU START YOUR DAY WITH THIS YOU'LL NEVER BE A MORNING PERSON AGAIN.

name: Extra-Sugar Dark Iced Coffee
description: Dark, sweet, and cold: it taste like the blackest of ashen affairs. Except sweet.

name: Caliginous Motherfuckin Coffee
description: This coffee was fine until someone put some stuff in it and now it motherfucking BURNS with a mad hate on. It burns motherfucking cold, man.

name: German Deatharang
description: A massive curved scythe blade, itching to reap some souls. This thing is so big you need two hand to wield it. Which is honestly kind of obnoxious for a boomerang.

name: Smuggler\'s Baggage
description: Can you look in my bag officer? Nope. It's where I keep my grapes.

name: Black Diamond Shoulder Bag
description: A shadowy messenger bag for... all sorts of things. Has nothing to do with Cheese Stings.

name: Cheese String
description: Kraft: Black Diamond Cheese Strings. Who ever thought you'd be able to take low quality ingredients, mix them with so many fillers and preservatives that they become hard and stringy, and then present it as a positive? Haha, kids are stupid.

name: Fish Finger Phallus
description: Battered and fried fish, but in a very particular shape. Can you say "Freud" three times fast?

name: Scrabble
description: The classic word board game for two to four players.

name: Ouija Board
description: An occult tool used to speak to the souls of the deceased. Users place their hands on the planchette as spirits move it to letters on the board.

name: A Truly Grape Halberd of Keys and Love
description: A lovely halberd with a magnificent grape design and a wonderful and great unlocking capability.

name: Death to Flora
description: With one scythe blade and one axe blade, this weapon is capable of effectively reaping nearly every form of plant life, from crops to trees. Now, if only they had souls...

name: Summoning Board of the Void
description: A summoning board filled to the brim with dark majyyks. It can be used to conjure small creatures from the Furthest Ring.

name: Shadowstaff of Eternal Night
description: This staff grants the wielder power over all that was not, all that is not, and all that will never be. Night will fall, and Nothing will survive.

name: Kingpin
description: The overly fancy pistol of a mobster. Covered with silver and gold it looks cool as hell, though is kind of hard to hide at the same time. Really it's more for looks than power.

name: Bones of Nrub\'yiglith
description: This pair of dice gain their power straight from Nrub'yiglith of the void. Depending on the roll, these dice summon dark spirits from the void of varying power levels.

name: Midnight Needles
description: These strange needlewands radiate strange black aura and the urge to join the midnight crew.

name: Electric Scythe
description: The blade of this scythe pulses with electricity, adding a bit of extra oomph to your slices.

name: Legendary Gun Parts
description: You're pretty sure that no matter what you use with this, it's still going to end up a legendary piece of shit. Heck, not combining it with anything still makes it one.

name: Feel Good Sparkle Noodles
description: These dry noodles, with what looks like chunks of pink sand stuck in it, may or may not be magic. Nope, I checked and instead of magic they're Japanese. Same thing really.

name: Faygo - Grape Flavor
description:
Faygo with a rich and tasty grape flavor,
slight aftertaste of insanity.

name: Rosie Posie Black Scythe
description: A vine of roses grow from and intertwine with this intricate scythe, fashioned from pressed ashes. Its blade is sticky with mild, sweet-smelling poison.

name: Roses Repeater
description: Organic or stylistically carved metal, those thorns are a bummer. But if you're willing to bloody your shoulder with every pull of the trigger, these ashen bullet pack a poisonous punch.

name: Antique Sickle
description: This bronze sickle was used many years ago to cultivate herbs. You just hope it doesn't fall apart.

name: The Gardener\'s Sickle
description: These are perfect for cutting weeds, trimming topiaries, an peering through windows unnoticed as you imagine what else it would be good for slicing.

name: CosmoScope
description: As you hold this telescope up to your eyes the stars seem closer than they ever have been before, and quite unusually, brighter. How does that work?

name: Lime Sun Dotted Cardigan
description: This delightful little jacket is spotted with green mspa-styled suns. The wool is a buzz with static though. What's up with that?

name: Faux First Guardian Coat
description: No actual first guardians were harmed in the making of this coat, that would be impossible. Something about it is... off though.

name: Sekmet Victory Scythe
description: The power of the Godess Sekhmet has joined Tyche and Nemisis to create this tri-bladed scythe guarenteed to bring you to victory in matters of war.

name: Twin Sickles
description: These bright pink sickles are recognizable as the claws of a monster... a Digital Monster.

name: Macabre Festivity
description: Whoever this grave marker was made for, must'nt have been very well-liked...

name: Quantum Entanglescope
description: A very sciency telescope. Something to do with quantum particles maybe?

name: Exoskellington Kolhii Stick
description: A sports necessity from another universe, made from the remains of a previous Kolhii player. It is possibly haunted, or maybe all Kolhii sticks float and rattle like that.

name: Boneyard
description: Face down on the ground, 28 lay. Whose is the name you have lifted today?

name: Pillowrapped Lyregun
description: Unfortunately, the lyre has lost its use as an instrument due to how it's been implemented into the gun. All it does is produce an annoying twang when you pull the trigger.

name: Thorned Amulet of the Earth Goddess
description: The rose amulet is now infused with Life magics, rendering a green glow.

name: Fire Hose
description: Too bad you don't have a hydrant to attach this to.

name: Eyeglasses of Truth
description: The logical next step to corrective eyewear: these glasses, in addition to being a stylish purple, grant you the ability to see through any kind of illusion!

name: All-Seeing Eyes
description: Visible or invisible, right next to you or on the other side of the Incipisphere, with these glasses you can see it all! The privacy of your sessionmates will be a thing of the past!

name: Omniscience Goggles
description: With the ability to both see, analyze and communicate with your entire session right in front of your eyes at all times, you are fairly confident that there are no better eyewear in existence. And if "fairly confident" is not enough for you, you could easily run a quick session-wide search to confirm it!

name: Binary Green Sun Reaper
description: The power of the Green Sun is stored in this mighty weapon not once, but twice! Each side of the double-bladed head pulsates with untold power.

name: Eastern Knight of Heart Armor
description: Some fancy looking heart armor styled in the fashion of the Eastern lands. Protective too!

name: Overseer Figurine
description:
It's a little figurine of the Overseer with credits on the bottom. How cute.
OVERSEER: NO THE GRIST COSTS HAVE NOTHING TO DO WITH VRISKA. GOD.

name: Reaper\'s Cloak
description: The only style for the fashionable reaper on the go!

name: The Nice Guy
description: Boy, do you feel nice wearing this hat. Niceness is just radiating off you, along with the faint smell of sweat and caffeinated drinks. Nice.

name: All-In-One Survival Clothes
description: Need to jump out of a plane? No problem! Going to be stranded at sea afterwards? No problem! This set of clothes will help you survive in any dangerous natural situation!

name: Orange Slices
description: Get it? Orange Slices? Cause they're knives... Made of oranges? You laugh, then die a little on the inside.

name: Screenshot
description: Loading computer chips instead of bullets, pulling the trigger and a holographic screen appears. Unfortunately near useless in battle, other then means of distraction.

name: Seven String Hagia Rifle
description: A very wide golden barrel with a Sutton Hoo styled lyre on the side. Apparently the sound from the lyre is amplified by the barrel or something? Whatever, you hold it to your shoulder with one hand and play with the other and it fires tremendous shortwaves with surprisingly little recoil.

name: Socker Ball
description: There it is. The only soccer ball that matters. The only soccer ball that will ever matter. You are so incredibly glad that you used your grist in the most responsible and effective manner. The Socker Ball will be key to your survival.

name: Two in the Morning Suit-Cardigan
description: The finest and starriest of black fabrics hot pressed and starched, outfitted with two cigar pockets and a sharp white trim.

name: Ashen Star-Patch Cardigan (with magical properties)
description: A midnight black knit of the softest degree forged from the furs of the fairest of mythological beings and spangled with white stars, a pattern traditional of the Pointy Hat Prophets. All that magicky stuff has to be good for something, riiiiight? And check out its massive pockets.

name: Dragonguard\'s Sickle
description: A truly powerful sickle befitting a dragonologist. It has a red-hot edge.

name: Hearts Boxcars\'s Shadow Axe
description: A battleaxe imbued with the very essence of shadows. Retrieved from the wrathtub of Hearts Boxcars.

name: Pom-Pom
description: A large ball made of thin vinyl strips. An absolute must have for any aspiring cheerleader.

name: Ironing Bow
description: Designed to iron clothes at a distance, this bow does an equally good job at tidying up the enemies.

name: Aperture Science Anime-Themed Ocular Heads-Up Scouter Display Device of Temporal Tactics
description: These names are getting downright ridiculous. You don't even remember what this is supposed to do anymore, other than be a lump of miscellaneous gadgetry that just so happens to fit on your face.

name: Windbang Gunblade
description: Your sword-pistol now produces a loud bang upon firing, the sheer sound of the deafening wind blast of which causes enemies to either cringe or bleed from their ears.

name: Moonrobe
description: A glistening robe that feeds on the rays of the moon.

name: Rosaceous Crosbombitonomeiconerangathong
description: This... thing verges on being a heap of junk. That said, it is a beautiful thong that also functions as dominoes, a boomerang, and a satanic tome for summoning explosive demons from beyond the reach of the universe.

name: Crosbombitonomeiconerangathong of the Aquasteel Sun of Life of Hemera\'s Golden Rose
description: You bask in its beauty: the grandfatherly smile of the greatest jazz musician to have ever lived, the revitalizing power of Hemera, and the glint of rose steel, all combined into an incredibly destructive amalgamation of reality. You shed a single tear of glorious golden joy.

name: Chef Noir\'s Hotcake Heaver
description: Flip pancakes and enemies with ease, thanks to this masterfully crafted work of culinary genius. The natural slickness of this breakfast connoisseur's (borderline homicidal) fantasy makes it hard to hold. Let's get cooking.

name: Prismapocalyptic Electro-Dragon Armor Jinba Grape
description: The Prismapocalyptic Electro-Dragon Armor now sports a cool grape design and looks like a samurai raiment!

name: Chisel
description: An instrument used to carve objects such as marble.

name: Electro Hammer
description: A hammer that uses a small electronic motor to boost its speed and power. Conveniently, this makes it easier to wield, but only slightly.

name: Jack Hammer
description: An electro-mechanical tool that combines a hammer directly with a chisel to create a destructive weapon.

name: Sugar Scope Sniper (N)
description: Pretty, pink and brought to you by the makers of your favorite game console, this electrically powered sniper rifle is for the agile, on the go gunman who just wants to have fun.

name: Temporal Gloves
description: Putting them on makes you feel like...like you're old! These are old peoples' gloves!

name: Rapid Feller
description: The soul-reaping tool of the future! Digs holes as fast as it cuts them down, and it's all strictly in line with the Deathdealer's code!

name: Addy Walker Complete Story Collection
description: The tale of a slave girl that escapes to freedom.

name: Rusty Piece of Paper
description: Oh boy! Now you can give your enemies a paper cut AND tetanus! At the same time!

name: Boston Cake Party
description: An unabridged telling of the Boston Cake Party.

name: Color Brick
description: It looks like someone melted down an entire box of crayons, poured them into a mold for a brick, and made some sort of giant coloring block. Oh, wait, that's exactly what it is.

name: Chaotic Shadow Dragon Cloak
description: For all your secret cult of the shadow dragon needs.

name: Battery-Powered Vibrohammer
description: While this spring-loaded hammer is pretty wobbly on its own, just wait until you turn it on! Whoaoaoaoaoaoa.

name: Stuffed Boonbird Slingshot
description: This slingshot fires Stuffed Birds that look like boondollars almost...

name: Steel Vortex
description: By combining the whiplike chain sword and the dangerously fun hula hoop, you get a dangerously fun whip you can hula hoop with. (Don't.)

name: Automated Laser Bow
description: An electronic bow that has tons of buttons and blinking lights. At the click of a button it'll aim and shoot several lasers. You don't know what the rest of the buttons do. You don't want to.

name: Bear Hands
