description: Now you can take on those baddies with your fists! Albeit, hairy and clawed ones.

name: Jack Drill
description: A rideable drill capable of causing uproars due to its loud noise and destructive power.

name: Pain Mask
description: Wearing this mask takes fashion disaster to a whole new level.

name: A Watery Grave
description:
Poseidon's funeral invitation:
"Fish puns prohalibuted."
"Cement shoes required."

name: Mine Spellbook of Time
description: A spellbook containing spells to affect time as well as create vast holes in the ground. The only downside is that the spells are written in orange in blue, rendering it almost unreadable.

name: "S0 M4NY C0W5" Bubble Wand
description: This Wand enables you to summon an unending stream of mutating bubble cows.

name: Divine Lance of Bob Marley the White
description: This holy lance represents the Bob of Spectacles tarot, and fittingly a beautiful elfish inscription on the side reads "Thy name be Marley, thou shall pass it on". It shoots lightning when you rap to it in Dwarfish.

name: Sparkle Wrath Pickaxe
description: This pick of obsidian black rock riddled with glistening crystals beautifully sparkles every color but emanates death. It emanates death like death were cheap cigars.

name: Mjolnir\'s Eastern Cousin
description: Heavy, engraved with Nordic Runes and Japanese Kanji. It probably just reads 'Caught a fish today,' though.

name: Dress of the Green Samsun Galaxy Nexus
description: Green, radiant, and radioactive, this dress somehow allows you to check your email. Praised for it's feel, display, and eternal battery life.

name: Swirling Leprechaun Suit of Luck
description: This green suit looks like it was meant to fit someone that was three feet tall, but as soon as you put it on, it shifts to your exact body type. Also, you feel very lucky while wearing this suit.

name: Omniscient 8-ball glasses
description: Wearing these glasses allow you to see into any point in time, and any point in space. Its really useful for finding you coplayers too.

name: Inflatable Gambit
description: These enchanted dice are massive, and filled with what seems to be... a vacuum. The logic of this perplexes you.

name: Oar of the Ocean\'s Searing Rage
description: It is said that this oar was created the day the entire ocean boiled over, enraged by mankind's constant abuse and disregard of it, and contains an equally potent level of wrath. Perhaps that day hasn't happened yet, but as you gaze upon this for the first time, you can't help but shudder in anticipation.

name: Glowing Skull Scythe of Rock
description: Just like the old model, but with a skull, and 20% more ROCK!!!

name: Gypsie\'s Overcoat
description: A similar overcoat that you might find a gypsy wearing.

name: Crocker Brand Battle Knives
description: Combining Fruit gushers and a pair of knives has left you with... Edible knives.

name: Barrel of Blue Nanopaste
description: This barrel is full of a thick blue paste-like substance. If you manage to drink it all, you may be healed. Either that or you may make yourself sick. Only one way to find out!

name: Tarnished Shard of Amethyst
description: This old, vaguely knife-shaped shard of purple gemstone is sharp enough that it'll make a fair stabbing weapon in a pinch.

name: Bread
description: This household commodity originated around 30,000 years ago and yet it still finds relevance in your strange and chaotic alchemical (or dining) endeavors.

name: Frock of Lunar Gravitation
description: So far a distance, so great a pull...such is the power imbued within the cloth of this robe.

name: Bacchalanian Libations
description: The god of all drunken clowning paid his respects at Poseidon's grave. No amount of scrubbing slaves could make it look the same again.

name: Black Thorn Repeater of Animosity
description: This rifle is tinged with the fabled grimdark energies and consumed in the aura of rising tendrils that accompanies it. Really all those tentathorns are going to make it hard to see, but they offer a mad smoke screen defense.

name: Spacey Spiral-Patch Cardigan
description: This black two-button cardigan is patterned with white, almost Borjgali shaped, patches that look like galaxies floating across the sky. It seems to bend space around it, offering some protection in combat.

name: Malfunctioning Laser Shades
description: While the concept of "laser shades" sounds cool in theory, it just turns out to be a shitty pair of shades that shoots lasers INTO YOUR EYES.

name: Ida Bean
description: The doll belonging to a courageous girl that escaped from slavery during the midst of the American Civil War.

name: The 2nd Amendment
description: Thanks to this new piece of legislation, you finally have the right to bear arms. Nothing could be more American.

name: Lodeodorant Stone
description: You take a whiff of the atrocity youve just created, and it smells just like a locker room. You know lodestones are magnetic, but youre not all that willing to find out if this is...

name: Great Knife of the Void
description: The perfect assasination weapon. The only time your enemies will see it is when their blood is dripping off of it...

name: Sword Flurry
description: This bow appears to be capable of shooting swords rather than arrows. Be careful where you point this thing. You wouldn't want to upset a dev!

name: The Breadstick
description: With this elongated and completely rock-solid breadstick, you will master the not-so-ancient fighting technique developed by mediocre Italian restaurant owners across the globe.

name: Cuestaff of the Dapper Overseer
description: Using Alchemy, you have managed to get the spirits inside this weapon to stop bickering and work together, creating a weapon of mass destruction.

name: Volcanic Cow Rifle
description: This rifle fires cows made out of molten volcanic rock. And man, are they pissed.

name: Rough Skeletal Creepypasta Statue
description: This stone statue is giving you a bad vibe... You think you should get rid of it. Hurry up now.

name: Eighteen Pocket Maelstrom
description: This powerful cuestick can fire bursts of flame that do not obey gravity.

name: South Carolina Zombie Basher
description: Y'all gon' be smashin' in them zombie heads faster than they'll be comin' at ya wif this thing!

name: Baseball Baseball Cap
description: A literal baseball cap? You must be quite the fan of baseball to wear such a thing.

name: XXXVII - The Cosmos
description: Show your enemies how insignificant they are in the grand scheme of things.

name: Fairy Paintbrush
description: It is said that the work of the best painters in the world are so realistic they become real... but that couldn't be true. ...Right?

name: Skaian Hardboiled Staff
description: A grey staff with a skaian globe with a fedora on it. You have never felt so hardboiled in your life.

name: Ding Dong
description: Big Ben isn't all that big anymore.

name: Black Carapace Glove
description: This feels like legitimate Dersite bone-skin. No science or magic could tell the difference. Pretty useless unless you're hand-shaking or painfully karate-chopping something.

name: Steel Wire
description: You could probably use it to strangle a few imps or something

name: Timely Suit
description: With this suit, you will never be late again! Like the true gentleman you are, you command a mystical ability to always arrive just on time, whether you want to or not.

name: Shadow\'s Destruction
description: This hammer is veiled in a dark aura, and seems to hum with power. It radiates desperation and fear, and seems to suck in the light around it.

name: 8lue Fairy Long Colt
description: This enchanted pistol contains the power of a 8lue Fairy, which will blast your enemies away, leaving you victorious!

name: Midnight Obsidian Gunblades
description: These powerful weapons will make your enemies face the darkness of midnight. On a new moon. With a heavy storm cloud cover. Seriously, these things are pretty fucking dark.

name: Volcanic Rock ICP Mask
description: This ICP Mask seems to be made of volcanic rock, with glowing red cracks on the surface... this will be sure to stike fear into your enemies.

name: Fruit Gushers - Godly Cosmos Nectar Flavour
description: Your gushers seem to glow like little tiny stars in your palms. They're almost too much like stars to even want to eat. Almost.

name: Sunglasses of JUSTICE
description: you can just feel the justice pulsing through these red shades, you can't actually see anything out them, but justice is blind, anyway.

name: Dragon Racer
description: A two-wheel device customized to look like you're riding a dragon! ...Shame it still can't fly.

name: Kanaya\'s Choice Panties
description: We all know these weren't made by accident.

name: Shaolin Spade
description: The sturdy shaft has a flat shovel head on one end, and a crescent-shaped blade on the other. It's a little heavy, but it's wicked sharp and can be used for defensive moves as well as beheading things.

name: Pack of Instant Needles
description: Although it appears to be a normal pack of instant noodles, when its plastic packaging is opened, it ejects a barrage of knitting needles at incredibly high speeds. Delicious.

name: Seam Ripper
description: Be careful! You might accidentally stab someone's eyes out with this!

name: x2
description: What... exactly is this? You didn't think you could catalogue the actual NUMBER 2. You feel nervous about using this at all...

name: Black Cleaver
description: An ideal weapon for the king to get his hands dirty.

name: Barbell Hammer
description: An incredibly heavy hammer made of a barbell on the end of a hammer handle.

name: Turn-based Hotbloodedness
description: The simulacrum evolves beyond what it was a minute before! Little by little, it advances a bit further with each turn, until reality and fiction are equal in every respect. That's how a turn-based combat sim works!!

name: Chessknives
description: A pair of knives in the shape of chess pieces. One resembles a Black King, the other a White Queen. The bases are sharpened to points.

name: Extra-Fancy Staff
description: It's just a staff with a rock on it, but at least it's fairly solid and it looks cool!

name: Semeripper
description: All of the Ukes will tremble in fear before your mighty and awesome power.

name: Netforce Extreme Impactor
description: This powerful railgun fires the might of the internet itself, in a large, concentrated burst.

name: Volcanic Blue Dragon Statue
description: This dragon statue made of volcanic rock seems to be sparking... I wouldn't stand too close.

name: Red Scalemate CompuShades
description: While not as plushy as the original scalemate, it still retains the brilliant red and dragon designs on this hands free computing system. Stay in touch in style!

name: Fluthlu\'s Revenge
description: Fluthlu's Bane, twisted and corrupted by the anger of those subservient to the Void, and Lord Fluthlu's humiliation. Re-purposed by the void, and personally warped by a tentacle of Lord Fluthlu himself, this legendary shotgun seems to warp the light around it with just it's mere presence.

name: Grape Purple Twirling Flag
description: A deadly twirling flag in the bright purple color of grapes. Smells like grape juice.

name: Athena the Grape Dragon\'s Halberd of Keys
description: This greek dragon halberd has an obsessive unlocking disorder and is adorned with a godlike grape design.

name: Stapler
description: A simple silver stapler with blue enamel trimmings that you might find on someone's desk. Useful for stapling documents and people's faces.

name: Staple Remover
description: A butterfly-shaped metal device with two pincers that can be used to remove staples. It looks like it's about to bite you.

name: Staple Monster
description: Once this was just your ordinary friendly local staple remover, but after a chance encounter with a mad alchemist who augmented it with blades...

name: Staple Serial Killer
description: Mild-mannered office supply by day, vicious remover of thousands of innocent staples by moonlight.

name: Staple Gun
description: That paperwork will never know what hit it.

name: Tesla Spikes
description: Best used with rubber gloves.

name: Knightly News
description: This edition of the medieval paper is poorly handwritten, and most of the words are spelled wrong. The printing press had not yet been invented, most likely.

name: Barbell Staff
description: A staff that has weighted ends on it, making it a heavy yet well-balanced bludgeon.

name: Scorpion\'s Scorn
description: It blew her arm off, now it was time for her to tear his soul out!

name: iTag
description: A screen on a chain necklace that displays the name of the wearer. Welcome to the future of... tagging?

name: Staples Office Sniper
description: Leo, Thomas, I don't care what you say, we do not need a staple sniper rifle. There are no "paper communists".

name: Sonic Jetpack
description: This item is so fast, one might even say humans wouldn't be able to survive traveling at such speeds. Then again, one might say teens wouldn't be able to survive fighting cosmic beings of near unmatchable power. BUT THAT'S JUST CRAZY, RIGHT?

name: Rubber Band Gun
description: Rubber bands: more painful than any bullet.

name: Harpdent Gun
description: A harpoon gun that shoots a trident instead of a spear.  Besides adding some weight, this really doesn't do anything different...

name: Cupid\'s Bow
description: A bow that was once wielded by the god of love and desire himself Cupid. It comes with a set of magical arrows that are said to help its victims find love in what they desire most, so long as they don't bleed out from being shot...

name: Fairy Dress
description: Wearing this dress makes you feel like a fairy princess.

name: Funtime Forks of the Horrorterrors
description: This is in no way less evil then before.

name: Seer\'s Gown
description: A gown that helps ease the mind, a must-have for all seers!

name: Double Scoped Sweet Sniper
description: This rifle has two scopes: One for taking out baddies from so far away it's insane, and another for a bit closer range that makes things look sparkly and frames them in a heart. The later is so useful it's insane.

name: Folding Polearmchair
description: A folding chair with giant axe blades on the legs which can fold out into a long polearm or a functional chair. When you've just finished lopping off the head of an ogre, feel free to fold it back and take a nice, well-deserved reprieve.

name: Color exterminator
description: You've never liked all that girly "colors and paints" crap, and now you can finally show it! Your raw hatred for colorful things powers this infernal device, which rips through color like a bullet through flesh.

name: Dual Scoped SigarRos Repeater
description: This sniper rifle offers ambient voidy majyyks to keep you hidden from foes, as well as a variety of scopes and booming .308 caliber auto-loading thorned bullets to make your presence known.

name: Jack "The Dungeonmaster" Drill\'s Legendary Staff of Power
description: The drill-staff belonging to the Dungeonmaster himself, Jack Drill. You have no idea who that is, but if he had a weapon like this, he must have been one wicked dude.

name: Faygo - Fountain of Youth Flavor
description: It tastes like... water, carbonation, and some ungodly mixture of infantile pestilence, teenage angst, and those awkward college moments.

name: Copland\'s Revenge
description: The classic sounds of American music resonate whenever you fire this fine instrument!

name: Fairy wings
description: A small set of white fairy wings expressing purity worn for cosplay, or just for fun. Doesn't do much but weight you down, but still looks cool!

name: Panty Sniffing Backpack
description: Finally, a backpack that goes and sniffs people's panties for you, landing you in awkward situations wherever you go! Perfect for convents and feminist rallies!

name: Electric Lacrosse Wand
description: A long wand with a net at the end of it, charged to the brim with electricity to shock opponents!

name: Firestorm Whip
description: Lacerate your foes and cauterize wounds at the same time!

name: Electrified Whipclaws
description: These claws are so long and flexible enough be used as whips! Or as claws, if you REALLY want to. Power surges through them: enemies are in for a brand new haircut.

name: Radiant Electric Kappa Visor 2.4
description: This visor can create an electric pulse to knock out enemies around you. And it won't affect you if you are underwater! Unless you are being affected by grimdarkness.

name: Radiant Lightning Soup
description: This delicious soup will wake you up incredibly quick!

name: Magical Marble Killer Wrench
description: An amazingly enchanted tool. It's also pretty to look at. Too bad the opposition won't get a chance.

name: Ohgodcake Gusher
description: This heavy, artificially-sweetened club creates an infinite fractal of cake upon impact, likely to inflict diabetic death upon anything caught in its blast radius. Which is everything.

name: Rapid Deletion Gauntlets
description: These gauntlets rapidly fire shots that delete holes through whatever they make contact with. Said to be the weapon of choice of this universe's second-in-command when taking down malicious tornadoes full of swords.

name: Telescopic Laser Ring
description: Looks like a regular diamond ring, shoots infrared light from the jewel at the push of a small button. Great for annoying your cat.

name: Glowgo Hammer
description: Now instead of burning your eyes out, you can read in the dark WHILE fighting monsters! Plus you'll never have any problems viewing new pages, because they change at the /slightest touch/.

name: Sun Charged Fancy Santa
description: One thousand suns are concentrated in the shape of a crystal fancy santa. Your enemies will see you coming hours before your arrival.

name: Harp Staff of Foreseen Light
description: Blind your enemies before they even see you coming! Won't stop making that annoying harp sound though. You feel like you're constantly having flashbacks.

name: Curiosity Killed the French
description: A cube of week-old french bread. You really should have thrown this out a long time ago...but something about it is just so...curious...

name: Beaner Hammer
description: You do NOT want to get hit on the head with this.

name: Flaming Bear
description: This was a stupid, stupid idea. What even gave you the SLIGHTEST IDEA that this would go well? You just set a stuffed bear on fire. Great job, loser.

name: Poison Perfume
description: The sweet scent of flowers has been replaced by a horribly chemicalal stench of rat poison. This will probably be better on pesky underlings than on you.

name: Jack "The Dungeonmaster" Drill\'s Lasertastic Sci-fi Staff
description: Apparently, Jack Drill had an entire arsenal of drill-tipped staffs, including one with a hard-light laser drill. The drill doesn't spin, nor does it have to in order to dig into anything, but nothing's stopping you from twisting it a little yourself.

name: Candycorn Battle Axe
description: Straight from the mind of the Pickle Inspector.

name: Cake On The Rocks
description: Your inedible slab of a cake now is also filled to the brim with a potent alcohol.

name: Pharaoh\'s Hair Dryer
description: Now your hair can be weird enough for two people!

name: Adele\'s Thunder Hammer
description: Flaming rain leads electricity surprisingly well.

name: Automatic Canvas Shooter
description: Abstract art is taking a whole new form! Make insta-paintings colored by the blood of your enemies! Just be sure to get some trolls in there, because otherwise those paintings will be kinda dull, though.

name: Thief of Doomed Stars
description: These feel a bit different... well at least you got the cool starry pattern no-oh wait no the stars a going out and the super novas emanate and glow. Bet you could discharge that power somehow...

name: Alto Scratchophone
description: Drop some sick beats as well as play smooth, mellow jazz.

name: Ammonia
description: Its just a regular container of ammonia you found in your garage. Or ammonium hydroxide, to be exact. Because, you know, base ammonia (or NH3) boils at -28 degrees Fahrenheit. But you dont actually know how you know any of that.

name: Cupcake
description: Regular vanilla cupcakes, though it tastes a bit like green tea.

name: Leather Car Seat
description: A good-sized leather seat taken straight out of a sporty vehicle.

name: Quick Escape Wheelchair
description: This wheelchair was optimized for quick movement in any direction, especially backwards. Not that that's really any safer.

name: Sweet-Tooth Dragon Suit
description: If you're the kind of dragon who would hoard candy instead of gold, then this dragon cosplay of pink and other bright colors is just your style.

name: TV Recliner
description: A big comfy chair you'd plop down in front of your TV, climb in, kick back, and promptly fall asleep only to wake up when the show's over.

name: Seated Dress
description: Someone recognized how awkward it was to sit on the floor in a dress, so they designed a dress with a folding chair attached to the back for quick and easy sits on the go. Looks okay on paper, but in reality, it's just plain stupid.

name: Dragon Tamer
description: A combination gilded stool and thorny whip for pacifying even the largest of megabeasts, dragons included. At least, that's the idea. You'd have a hard time confidently using it on something like a hydra or hekatonchire... but who knows?

name: Scorpion\'s Septic Sapphire Sovereignty
description: A truly elegant indigo throne engraved with dark gemstones, it menaces with slender blades of poison-coated sapphire. You feel like such a cunning and sinister monarch sitting in this, as long as you can avoid getting cut and infected.

name: Reinforced Barbed Wire
description: A piece of barbed wire made from thick steel. Itll probably hurt your hands a lot, but it looks like itll hurt your enemies even more.

name: Old Boot
description: You found this grimy old thing on a river bank.  Or maybe you just alchemized it.

name: Fizzy Cola Gushers Extreme
description: The taste of this beautiful combination can only be described as confused.

name: Fruit Gushers - Ultimate Chaos Plutonium Genocide Apeshit Destructopocalype Flavor
description: For when your brain just needs a few more hemorrhages.

name: Fruit Gushers - Ultimate Aquasteel Neptunium Destrucalamitous Chaos Revivalation of the Crosbitonome
description: ...iconerangathongapocalyptic Roseacidal Flavour. The name is so long that it bleeds off of any SBURB device you try to look at it with and glitches up the interface. Anyway, here it is - the greatest clusterfuck ever to grace an Alchemiter. And now it's edible too!<audio controls autoplay><source src="6585134.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">Your browser does not support the audio element.</audio>

name: Thorned Night Cloak of the Steel Stars
description: A rose brooch in the center of the cloak decorated with thorns and constellations sewn with shiny steel thread.

name: Bloody Decimurder Chaos Scissors
description: These sinister, sharpened scissors make you feel... odd. And stabby.

name: Regisickle of Cronus
description: A deadly aura pulsates from this sickle/staff combination. Its short handle resembles an unprototyped Black King's Staff, and it has a blood-red blade that whispers terrible curses in the ancient Greek language.

name: Tiara
description: This makes you feel pretty.

name: Multidimensional Bow
description: No one can describe the shape of this bow for it is always changing its texture, color, and dimensions. However it always stays in the general shape of a bow, so you can still use it as one.

name: Pillow Pen
description: It's a pillow. It's a pen. It's a pillow pen!

name: Eye For An Eye Sunglasses
description: These gallant red cat-eye shades have the word "EYE" scrawled across both lenses, or "3Y3" if you're reading from the inside. They're pretty hard to see out of but you win points for punnery and edgyness.

name: Relativistic Hoodie
description: The symbols of time and space dance across the fabric. Wearing this makes you feel speedy.

name: Plutonic Friends
description: A dress decorated with all the symbols of the quadrants. Said symbols also happen to be glowing radioactively. All those gamma rays can't be very healthy for you...

name: Red Hammurabi-Sees-All CompuShades
description: Your typical pair of red telepathically-controlled pointy computing sunglasses, but with the desktop wallpaper permanently set to a picture of the word "EYE" in big letters. And maybe it fills your thoughts with the desire to punish the horror terrors' enemies. Maybe.

name: Reflecting Telescope
description: A telescope that uses mirrors to magnify images of faraway objects. Newton would be proud.

name: Refracting Telescope
description: If you look carefully through this telescope, you can see the moons of Jupiter. Or could, were you still in the solar system.

name: Razr Bow
description: The phone is built into the bow grip, but the probability of you using these capabilities in battle is low. Unless there's an app to help you aim a bow.

name: Unlucky Mirror Bow
description: The arrows do strange things when fired, including turning away from targets mid flight. Might want to be careful with this, since the arrows could come back at you...

name: Tiaratop
description: A tiara that's also a laptop. Pretty self-explanatory.

name: Crocker-Brand Tiaratop
description: There is no SUBMIT propaganda in OBEY here at all. That CEASE REPRODUCTION would be silly.

name: Wattahbat
description: This bat has bashed one watermelon too many. You suppose the delicious fruity goodness stuck to the end of the bat might dull any blows given or taken, or at least provide emergency rations.

name: Auto Rapping Scratchophone
description: Using its database of poems, this thing almost does all the work for you. Convenient, since playing the saxophone makes rapping impossible.

name: Scratchobow
description: This bow's body is made of two turntables, with saxophones at the two ends. Pulling back an arrow makes the turntables make sick beats as the saxophones lay out a smooth, jazzy, melody. Of course this is only a distraction as the arrow kills its target.

name: Cat Tail of Yendor
description: A cat tail taken from the cat wizard Yendor and made into an amulet. Wearing this makes you feel more agile, and makes you feel a strange urge to purr like a kitten.

name: Skaia War Sledge
description: This seems to be the Black King's Staff gone fallout style. The miniature Skaia seems to be stuck between the massive heads of the hammer. The black king will never know what hit him.

name: Vigilante\'s Tactical CompuShades
description: These totally not self aware sunglasses monitor your surroundings and thoughts to provide on-the-fly information regarding ideal strategies to help you crack down on all that is totally illegal, and provide access to your email and files.

name: Junior Battermaster\'s Bowlbuster Poking Solution 5000
description: It has so many recipes stored in it, and it's great for stabbing things!

name: Squiddlian Forks of Gl\'bgolyb
description: A pair of forks fashioned is the will of Gl'bgolyb in mind. It glows in greyscale colors and whispers to you.

name: Born-Again Staple Serial Apologist
description: After a chance encounter with an unknown deity, it appears this staple murderer has repented its deeds and now goes around helping people to death.

name: The Sceptre of Ik \'ngrechslir
description: Fear trickles down your spine as you hold this staff, you now truly know what it means to be naughty or nice. You don't know who or what Ik 'ngrechslir is, but maybe that's a good thing.

name: Chest
description: Makes for a nice piece of furniture and great for storing items. Too bad those crafty imps will probably find a way inside it.

name: Baking Chest
description: A special Crocker-brand chest for holding all your crocker-branded items the way only Betty Crocker knows how. Submit to the cake. Wait, what?

name: Chest of Whimsy
description: The perfect chest for holding all your refreshing beverages that are totally not made from dismembered trolls.

name: Lewd Magazine
description: O-oh my. Maybe you should keep this under your bed, so the imps don't find it.

name: Cruxite Blender
description: A blender strong enough to quickly convert any number of cruxite dowels and totems into brightly-colored dust. This should prove effective in getting rid of that massive hoard of used totems you no longer need!
effects: STORAGE:CRUXBLEND.|SHUNT:CRUXBLEND.USELESS.:A powerful blender now takes up the area where you would normally place a totem, making the alchemiter itself useless. Unless you really want to destroy all your totems, that is.|

name: Card Shredder
description: A machine with a slot for captchalogue cards, and two bladed rollers that spin dangerously fast. Once you stick in a card, be sure to take your hand away quickly!

name: Blue Witch of Healing
description: Ever felt tired of lugging around slime with your boring spare captchalogue cards? No more! Now in a convenient sandwich form, so you can carry every squishy gooey bite, with your bare hands!

name: Ahab\'s Nightmare
description: Hunt the whitest of whales with the greenest of lasers.

name: Princess Thong of Draconic Might
description: Who says you can't be both graceful and as strong as a truck?

name: Magibow
description: Do you like bows and wands, but cannot use them both? Do not worry anymore. With the Magibow, you can perforate your enemies while you zap than with magic wand arrows! A shame that you cannot decide which spell the wands use, though... Not to be confused with the weeaboo known as Magibon.

name: Chained (to a) Stone Pillow
description: The mafia is so nice these days! Now they even give you a pillow when you're "sleeping with the fishes".

name: Echidna Dress
description: This dress appears to be made out of the fabric of space itself, making you the literal star of the ball. It also seems to be pretty dang strong.

name: The Drunken Scotsman
description: Fires glass bottles filled with liquor so alcoholic that it catches fire when exposed to air. Imbibing may cause burns, spontaneous human combustion, or death.

name: Lime Flavored Turkey Dinner
description: A delicious turkey dinner flavored with lime.

name: His Holy Tears
description: The bottle's label reads "His Holy Tears purge the Sin from the Unclean and make them love Him", and it has a very unnatural smell.

name: Lyre, Lyre, Fists on Fire
description: Your fingers will literally be on fire as you play the built-in lyre on these gloves.

name: Holla Holla Get Boondolla
description: This saxophone is covered in (sadly unusable) boondollars, and raps endlessly about it's considerable "wealth".

name: Drizoo
description: While a drill that makes kazoo noises is somewhat amusing, it is mostly annoying.

name: Green Kashooes
description: These shoes now make kazoo noises every time you take a step. This is probably the second most aggravating thing you can think of involving shoes.

name: Christmas Blizzard Suit
description: While worn, this suit creates an endless snowstorm around you. Hopefully the imps will freeze to death before you do.

name: Portable Delving Assistant
description: A PDA that's red plastic and has a 20 on the back. Uses the latest technology to help in dungeon diving.

name: CH3RRY R3D SC4RF
description: Anyone can wear their heart on their sleeve, but wearing it around your face lets everyone know you're not taking bullshit from anybody and ready to give any jokers what's coming to them.

name: Chrono Bracertop
description: A miniature computer used for playing SBURB and contacting your very few friends has proven to become an armguard.

name: Meteoric God Scythe
description: This scythe is composed of meteoric iron, and is a symbol of the Gods of Time and Beyond.

name: Golden Wand of the Midnight Venus
description: One wave of this, and your opponents will be treated to a harrowing vision of their own future wherein all of their fears and uncertainties manifest. Call now to subscribe to our HD packages.

name: Immaculately Bearded Hollow Mask
description: All the powers of a Hollow and St. Nicholas' trusted barber combined. Actually wearing the thing will probably make you a master with a razor, as well as vaguely homicidal. But that perfect, snow white beard is just begging to be on your face...

name: Time Altering Scratchobow
description: The bow is mostly unchanged, but the arrows it fires now have dials on them that allow you to change when in time they will hit their target.

name: Frozen Turkey Bow
description: Really is completely normal, except for the fact that any arrows fired from it change into frozen turkeys mid flight.

name: Snow Globe
description: A glass globe filled with water and some snow like stuff, it also has a little Santa inside looking particularly fancy.

name: Magic Snow Globe
description: As you look into this globe you see what you presume to be the near future, it's too snowy to be sure.

name: Auto Spearing Flutophone
description: This saxophone... flute... thing stabs you through with spears in time with its rap lyrics.

name: Explosive Stampyrokinesis Pin
description: Stamp the word 'FIRE' onto your enemies from afar using only the power of your mind! And this pin. You should be careful with this, though, as the ink appears to be highly explosive.

name: The Heavy-Headed Monarch
description: This throne seems to carry with it the weight of a million difficult, world-shaping decisions made by the ruler of an ancient land who occupied this very seat long ago. Your enemies are sure to feel the same pressure when you bash them over the head with it.

name: Liquid Luck
description: A glistening golden drink said to make you luckier. You're not entirely sure that luck can be quantified and modified in such a manner, but this drink looks quite enticing. It couldn't hurt to try it, right?

name: Compu-Contacts
description: Now you can "contact" your friends, browse tumblr, read web-comics and basically do anything requiring a laptop, with these compact eye-sized computer lenses. Just don't sleep with them in. Or do, they're your eyes, not mine... yours... uh, someone else's? This second-person narrative is weird.

name: Incendiary Gloves
description: Fashionable white gloves with red pasterns on them, just don't snap your fingers or you might catch something on fire! Unless that's what you're trying to do, in which case, go ahead.

name: Deletion Dragon Axe
description: This axe is imbued with the power of a "dragon" that was said to destroy entire worlds.

name: Miracle of Deletion
description: This computer deletes all of those things you would rather not see before you see them, preventing trauma that would require brain bleach to heal.

name: Shitty Paper Sword
description: A paper sword folded from instructions on the internet. It isn't made very well, though, and it's kinda lumpy. It's less of a sword and more of a disfigured paper airplane, really.

name: Felt Waistcoat
description: A bright green waistcoat. Very stylish if you can ignore the color.

name: Hummingbird
description: Deeply connected to magic, this golden bow constantly undulates with an eerie and captivating light. Its name stems from the strange humming which resonates whenever it fires an arrow.

name: Uranium Speared Flutophone
description: The spears jutting out of this flute are now tipped with glowing green uranium, which hopefully will kill the imps before it kills you.

name: Rapping Skullophone Helmet
description: Speakers mounted on either side of the helmet rap about whatever you are doing. You would destroy this thing for being annoying as all hell, but it's fairly good at keeping your head safe.

name: Spear Tipped Flute Wand
description: Play the song of death as you run through your foes and cast spells of destruction!

name: Broken Mirrored Eyeglasses
description: Even if you could see out of these mirrored glasses, the lenses are cracked. You suppose they can protect your eyes somewhat?

name: Bloodstained Surgical Scissors
description: You're never going to get the dried blood and zombie goo off of these things...

name: Psionic Busted PlayStation 1
description: Forcing that cartridge into a system that takes discs wasn't the best idea. On the bright side, the Playstation now has PSI powers, though how it will use them is anyone's guess.

name: Magic Squid Marker
description: It seems to be a regular marker pen just filled up with squid ink instead of regular ink. However further testing proved that you can only draw squids with it.

name: Maelstrom Lance
description: Just throw it at your enemies and watch them get taken up in a maelstrom. What do you mean that you don't throw lances?

name: Quantum Timestabber
description: This knife not only travels through time, it can cut a hole into the n-th dimension. Presumably, anyway. If it does, you can't see it.

name: Triggered Turkey Bow
description: Frozen turkeys fly quickly from this rapid fire bow, as your trigger finger pulls back on the conveniently easy to see yellow trigger.

name: Horse iPhone
description: An iPhone with the image of a majestic steed on the back of it. Not much else different from a regular iPhone, except its signal strength tends to be STRONG.

name: iPISS
description: An iPad emblazoned all over with shitty kringlefucker santas. All your apps look like a bit more festive and a lot more idiotic.

name: Permafrost Barrier Blazer
description: This blazer shrouds you in cold and freezes all who come near.

name: Pointy Bunny Shades
description: The points of these glasses now make bunny ears, and the frames are knitted from soft yarn.

name: Toilet Pieper Roll
description: A roll of blue toilet paper that tastes exactly like blueberry pie. The only problem is that it's really hard to swallow.

name: LoTRoilet Paper
description: Toilet paper printed with the entirety of The Lord of the Rings Trilogy. Handy for reading in the bathroom.

name: Whinnyphone
description: It's like a normal megaphone, but with way more horses on it, and also a lot more neighing instead of talking.

name: Book of Horrible Mythology
description: History hasn't always been so great. There have been some real bad apples in our history's past. This book will give you the squeeze on what's what.

name: Spiral-Patch Guardian Cardigan
description: A milkshake white cardigan decorated with lime green six-pointed-spirals. Wearing it fills your mind with a blinding green light you can't look away from--in a good way.

name: Roasting Lance
description: It's a lance with flame decals, and a few weird holes near the top. It looks deadly.

name: Tahitian Witch\'s Hat
description: An absolutely scathing staple bonnet adorned with black pearls and contorted (and dead looking) hemlock blooms. Don with caution.

name: TKB-R18817
description: This emerald assault rifle has the charming visage of a frog mounted on it, which is probably a little less useful than a scope would be. Except the frog's eyes are little green suns and the gun fires little green suns. Damn.

name: Pages and Pages of Summoning Rituals
description: A pile of sheets cut out from the Necronomicon. On second thought, making this probably wasn't the best idea.

name: Demonic Pillow of Ultimate Evil
description: I dare you to sleep on it. I dare you.

name: Rubik\'s Duck
description: No matter how much time you spend fussing with this weird duck puzzle, you just can't get the colors to match.

name: PikaShield
description: The Pikachu-decal on the front emits electricity that courses through the shield. Make sure to only touch the grip.

name: Paper Grenade
description: A grenade made of a large piece of printer paper. When it explodes it shoots out razor sharp strips of paper. Papercuts ahoy!

name: Paper Chain
description: A festive chain made up of lots of hoops of paper linked together. Useful for holidays.

name: Festive Pinata Stick
description: Whether it's bashing open a pinata or bashing open the skulls of your enemies, this brightly coloured stick will probably not fail you!

name: Fairy Goggles
description: Frilly and rather useless but somewhat cute. At least they keep the wind and bugs out of your eyes.

name: Telescalpel
description: A large, telescopically extending scalpel used for slightly further and probably less precise operations.

name: Power-Up Leaf
description: This leaf turns you into a raccoon when you eat it. What.

name: Turkey Leaf
description: A leaf that turns you into a turkey when you eat it. This is just silly.

name: Timetraveling Duel Hoverbike
description: Your awesome flying bike now also allows you to travel through time. Here is finally your chance to go back in time to become a forgettable villain in a crossover movie.

name: Rough Stone Palkia Statue
description: This stone statue of the Legendary Pokemon of Space seems to be made from a meteor.

name: Karakasa
description: A rather unattractive umbrella forgotten by its owner long ago. Sometimes it seems to move and weep softly. It's probably your imagination, of course.

name: Fairy Pistol
description: A Pistol infused with the magical fairy powers of the Fairy-Type from Pokemon.

name: Magical Girl Wand
description: Brings out the magical girl in all of us. Just don't sign any magical contracts.

name: Fish Finger and Custard
description: The product of desperate and silly midnight snacking by two children.

name: Black Knight Armor
description: This armor seems to be quite ornate, with etchings everywhere on it. It gives off an aura of power, and the determination to guard the ruler of its previous owner. It seems to be charred black, yet it feels like it provides more defense.

name: Palutena Bow
description: This bow was used to defeat the armies of the Underworld. It can also be split apart into two blades.

name: Togami Conglomerate Wand
description: This wand seems to be made of pure gold and covered in diamonds. It might not have any real magical properties, but you could probably use this to convince people to do whatever you want.

name: Tower Of Gray
description: Listen, I'm gonna give you some invaluable advice; don't put this in your mouth.

name: Elemental Tarot Cards
description: A deck of magical cards infused with the power of Air, Water, Earth, and Fire. Only the Avatar can use all four to their full potential.

name: Murderous Gravy Boat
description: A frying pan patterned with smiley faces and letter 'E's. Whether cooking or fighting, this pan emits a foul purple miasma instead of smoke.

name: Dragonborn Armor
description: As you wield the armor of the mighty Dovahkiin, you feel... YOU FEEL... pretty weighted down, actually.

name: Planet Pack
description: Wow, imagine all the trash you could clean up with this glowing backpack. Too bad you're just going to use it to hold all your bullshit junk.

name: Wooden Ocarina
description: A finely crafted Ocarina made from willow bark by the fairy children in the lost woods. It makes a nice tune, and has strange properties which take effect when you play the right notes.

name: Poe\'s Paradox
description: A suit that somehow manages to be ratty and dirty yet also intensely formal. You often wonder how you could live without it. The joke is Con Air.

name: KFC\'s Fish Donuts
description: Premium fish chops shaped into donuts and "baked" to a golden brown. It's a weird combination but you guess this could be good.

name: Stewed Jellyfish
description: You guess this is a Chinese delicacy. Or at least the Brits think so.

name: Dried Squid
description: A bungle of seasoned tentacles: a dish generally limited to Korea and the Philippines.

name: The Monster Manual
description:
Normally the monster manual is divided into several volumes, since there are so many monsters in DnD, but this appears to a complete compilation of them all.
You're prepared for any monster from any DnD adventure, now! Unfortunately, you're not in a DnD adventure yourself.

name: Jedi Robe
description: You find in your hands a robe, the likes of which was worn by the ancient order of Jedi Knights themselves. Wow! Still just looks like a drab bathrobe though.

name: True Proton Cannon
description: Unblockable and absolutely devastating. If there's any weapon in need of a nerf, it's this one. Just make sure you have a suitable armor to take the recoil.

name: Sendificator
description: The most useful piece of Crocker technology. Just dial up some coordinates and throw in an item, and the device will send the item there.

name: Phazon Corrupted M-Squeak Hammer
description: The bird on top of the hammer now glows a bright blue, and sings in a very distorted manner. You feel nervous about using this.

name: Razr Permafrost Barrier Bow
description: This bow is incredibly cold to the touch, but painless to wield. Enemy attacks are blocked by a cold aura emanated by the bow, as the arrows freeze enemies cold in their tracks.

name: Greg Kringle\'s Hardboiled Sceptre of Unknown Skaian Origin
description: You are dumbfounded at the amount of bullshit coming from this... this thing. It features a jolly yet, frightening decal. It also has a skaian globe with a fedora on it, can't be hardboiled without a fedora. By the way who the hell is Greg?

name: Quantum Clarinet of Space Time
description: Playing a song on this clarinet can send you through dimensions and time, allowing you to dodge attacks and stab imps much more effectively.

name: Bilious Bullpup
description: This nebula-print assault rifle seems to literally be a small universe, or a projection of one? Perhaps it's a sterile universe that's only hope of legacy is that the volatile collapse of its star systems will power your weaponry. Who even knows anymore?

name: Green Sun War Sledge
description: The power of the Green Sun courses through this weapon. This god among suns is right between the heads of the hammer it's self, seemingly doing nothing. Not until you lifted this hammer did you realize how much the Green Sun actually weighed, but what did you expect, it's a frigging sun.

name: Steel Flag of Freedom
description: This hefty version of Old Glory is made of 100% American Steel.

name: Schrodingers Timestabber
description: This knife can stab anyone, anywhere, anytime you need it to.

name: Bloody Raw Steak
description: The man-grit that comes with chowing down on a raw slab of muscle will make any kid grow strong enough to chew off a leg, no matter what your doctor says they "strongly advise against".

name: iPatriot
description: It's an American Flag, but all the stars have been replaced with Apple symbols. Also it plays your music for you.

name: Unlucky Mirrored Scratchophone
description: Songs played by this cursed thing have strange effects, most of which involve the death of the listener. While this is useful for fighting, don't play it for your friends...

name: Santa\'s Got A Knife
description: EVERYONE LOOK OUT! KRINGLE'S ARMED AND DANGEROUS! AND INANIMATE! BUT STILL DEADLY!

name: Grand Cosby Codpiece of Radioactive Thorns
description: This codpiece's aura now shines brightly with the power of the green sun, making you wonder why you wasted all that grist making a codpiece instead of a weapon or something.

name: Wooden Sci-Fi Santa
description: This Santa is not only flammable, but now has snazzy Sci-Fi glasses on as well.

name: Legendary Scraps of Paper
description: The scraps seem to detail the recent crowning of King Arthur, as well as the score for the football game yesterday. Huh.

name: Enveloping Face
description: This mask's ripped straight off one of the show's namesake mecha. It automatically closes at the back when you put it over your face, and makes you feel all protected. It looks pretty creepy to everyone else, however.

name: Burning Knuckler
description: Your hand is now on fire, but you aren't getting burned. Let's hope your land has flammable underlings, because if not, you're not going to do much better using these, though.

name: Santa\'s Jolly Sceptre / Green Sun Fedora
description: He sees you when you're sleeping. He knows when you're awake. He knows if you've been bad or good but either way he'll wreck your shit.

name: Schrodinger\'s Glowing Scalpelsanta
description: Every time you draw this weapon, it changes appearance. Sometimes its a glowing Santa, sometimes a glowing scythe. Schrodinger you are a crazy, crazy man.

name: Really Distracting Shades
description: For some reason you thought making this thing have even more light sources was a good idea.  Goodbye, eyesight!

name: Karpofezoroi
description: This fez, now with bonus scales, silky material and badass red stitching, is more likely to survive the blast of a laser gun. The chances of passing this up? Never gonna happen.

name: Plastic Iron Man Mask
description: While this plastic replica doesn't offer much in the way of head protection, you look just like Iron Man! Minus the rest of the suit, of course.

name: Bassarang
description: A boomerang that exhilarates a large amount of bass upon impact. Be careful not to drop it, though!

name: Icy Cold Black Faygo Claws
description: Frozen Faygo in sharp claw form. Slash at your foes with the wicked elixir!

name: Dragon Fruit Scythe
description: A scythe with a blade made of some fuchsia fruit and twin dragon heads on either side of the pole. Not very powerful, but a very nice ornamental fruit cutter.

name: Flag of Frangleterre
description: This beautiful flag flutters in the sunlight. It looks like it wants to tear itself apart at the seams. Reasonable, considering the current state of geopolitical affairs

name: Prepare to Pillow
description: This pillow is covered with the markings of lost souls giving you vague and mostly useless advice. The real pillow starts here.

name: Super Dangan Ronpa 2: Goodbye Healthcare
description: The same concept as the original game, except it features a new group of students stranded on a series of tropical islands being forced to kill each other by a group of republicans?

name: Sponge Cake-Laden Shopping Cart
description: It's just a shopping cart full of really, really old sponge cake. You'd better be careful not to let this thing get rolling, it could crack skulls.

name: VVVVVVirtual Boy
description: A Virtual Boy console that only plays VVVVVV. You can use it to flip the gravity of the plastic spikes that came in the box! You guess you can... scratch someone with this?

name: Crumpled Pages of Hat Summoning Rituals
description: Crinkling up these pages of the Necronomicap has made the hat demons angry... it's probably best to just leave them alone now.

name: Davy Jones Bio-hazard Witch Hat
description: It's wide brim adorned with a mat of barnacles, pearls, and a variety of unnaturally bleak flora, this bonnet blisters with sea water, hatred, and quite possibly radioactivity.

name: Handheld Tardis
description: A communication device of the timelords.

name: Barrytop
description: A laptop shaped like the handsome bee Barry B. Benson. Oh, Barry...!

name: Cassiopeia
description: Theres something fishy about this perfume Cosmically fishy

name: Hero of Man\'s Helmet
description: I've been here before; I stood where you stand. They called me a hero- the Hero of Man.

name: Mag
description: A simple Mag model. Floating over your shoulder this pet can become an awesome sidekick if well fed... Or you can alchemize your way through.

name: Astleytop
description: A fancy computer featuring the unforgettably handsome Rick Astley. His hit song plays in the background seemingly all the time.

name: Aperture Science Constellation Cleaner
description: Ever wanted to clean up the galaxy? Thanks to Aperture Science, never deal with astronomy class again!

name: Rolled-Up Wizard Poster
description: Gosh do you love wizards. So much so that you've rolled your favourite wizard poster into a snazzy magic wand.

name: Great Ball
description: A good, high-performance Pok Ball that provides a higher Pokmon catch rate than a standard Pok Ball. Too bad it doesn't work on underlings.

name: Black Sorceror Hat
description: This pitch black hat is ornated with dark precious gems... and coated in a spooky aura of pure dark magic. Extended wearing time might drive you mad with megalomania, though. Just because it's insanely powerful.

name: Smoke-Flavored Rock Candy
description: Smoke doesn't taste very good. In fact, nothing about this greyish, smelly mess reminds you of delicious rock candy at all.

name: RobCo Industries RC68 Computer Terminal
description: The cutting edge in electronic computing technology in 2077, the RobCo Industries RC68 provides the most compact and powerful personal computer yet! With it's cutting edge 256kb RAM and an astounding FOUR MEGABYTES of hard disk memory, it's no wonder that every major company that's anyone has this.

name: Orichalcum Bar
description: A bar of solid Orichalcum, straight from the mines of Atlantis. And countless fantasy video games and novels.

name: Staffpopwire
description: This... Gun... staff thing has a lot to it. It's a lot like a shitty makeshift bayonette, except the gun looks kind of toylike with carbonated bullets with a stick pointing out and rusted barbed wire on the end of that. Overall, you guess it could work?

name: Magical Steel-Toe Skates
description:
A small steel-toed pair of skates with hexagrams carved into the sides, capable of emitting immense amounts of magical energy. Among other things, useful for 
giving your enemies the boot and firing giant rainbow-coloured laser like blazing trails fuelled by the power of pure radicality.

name: Magnetic Skates
description: I'm not even sure if this is actually safe to use! On the other hand, it could crash several computers just by skating pass them.

name: Dimensional Drifter
description: These skates are so fast they can tear and bend local space. Guaranteed to bring you to the Nth Dimension of cool.

name: Phork of Physics
description: Ever wonder what a quark tastes like? Spear your food apart particle-by-particle to find out. Remember, one unstable atom can cause far-reaching consequences...

name: Normal Supply Closet Broom
description: Griping the handle would surely cut into your skin, not that this isn't a standard regular broom. It hums lightly, emitting blue sparks as it does so, not that that's unusual for a normal supply closet broom. A mixture of blood and oil have trickled down to the feathery bottom--grin and bear it. No matter what, you must keep in mind, keep thinking, that this is a normal supply closet broom. If your belief fades for even a moment in this thing's presence, they'll know. They'll know!

name: Lucky Honey Shades of the Gods
description: Made by the coolest of gods, high in Asian mountains of something, these cool shades are impossible to break, unless in a heroic or just way.

name: Chocolate Ingot
description: If you need a material that is brittle, melts at room temperature, and is oh so delicious, than this sizable bar of chocolate is worth its weight in gold.

name: Grief Knives
description: These knives are said to draw upon their user's own happiness for power.

name: Final Smash Hoodie
description: A hoodie resembling the form of Yoshi's final smash. Rawr.

name: TARDIS Union Jack Cardigan
description: This police blue sweater jacket has a Union Jack patch sewn onto its breast and... some kind of police box pattern on the back.

name: 2/10 Ball Cardigan
description: A blue long vest, with felt lined buttons, adorned with a round breast patch that oscillates between depictions of the two and ten pool balls. The seasoned reader might postulate there's some sort of weird time shit imbued in it though.

name: Hitchhiker\'s Bathrobe
description: This robe has been places. It's been patched up here and there, and seems ages old. There are some holes in it, and some tea stains that refuse to come off. It may as well have been across the galaxy and back with all this wear!

name: Flame Reductant Mirror Suit
description: This suit has the ability to block fire, and cause anything shot at the wearer to bounce off. Well, as long as it hits the coat.

name: Iron Lass Suit
description: It's quite stylish, but maybe a dress isn't the most practical design for a power armor. It'd need its core accelerated to work efficiently.

name: Pearl Waistcoat
description: A fanciful waistcoat in a lovely shade of pink with stunning pearl buttons. It looks almost too expensive to wear. Almost.

name: Angel Dress
description: Fool people into thinking you're an angel, and when they're least expecting it, bash them over the head with your halo and steal their wallet! How devilish...

name: Anatomically Incorrect Doll
description: This doll would be indistinguishable from any other doll if it didn't have freakishly large arms. What on Earth are you gonna do with this thing?

name: Rubber Chicken
description: One of those random rubber chickens.

name: Lesser Amulet of Light
description: A portable light source worn around the neck. staring into the gem reveals a faint candle flame.

name: Spongebob Squarepants DVD
description: WHO LIVES IN A PINEAPPLE UNDER THE SEA???

name: Commander\'s Spear
description: A spear that belongs to an squad's commander. Inspires other soldiers

name: Claritentacles
description: A soggy clarinet with a faint smell of squid from under the sea. Seems to be clogged with seaweed, but works well enough.

name: Mic Stand Staff
description: It's just a longer microphone stand, apparently. Packs a wallop though!

name: Indescribably Impractical Chained Chainblade Launcher
description: A chainsaw katana attached to a chain shot from a violin, this weapon could do some serious damage; whether that is to your enemies or you is unclear.

name: Nyan Cape
description: This long, flowing cape emanates a constant repetitive, hypnotic sound.  You suddenly have a strange craving for poptarts...

name: Drum Sticks
description: Your tools for rhythm and beating - as in beating imps, perhaps.

name: Cymbals
description: CRASH! Wear them on your hands with straps and hit imps over the head with the side.

name: Breadbat
description: A loaf of bread so hard that it'll take you to the major leagues. Goes great with Ballcheese.

name: Shitty Pneumatic Kunai Gun
description: That's just a reversed vacuum cleaner. Some genius inserted a bunch of kunai.

name: Felt Bunny Ears
description: You haven't made these things from scratch; Alchemization created this striking pair of bunny ears. The tiny little billiard balls on the tips of the ears are weird, but they make them appealingly droopy.

name: Chained Axe
description: An axe on a chain.  Could deal some damage, but be careful where you swing it.

name: Great Dragon\'s Skeleton
description: The skeleton of a great and powerful dragon. You can almost feel the power and grandeur coming from this great beast's bones. But dragons aren't real, you ask? Hogwash! Why, what else could this giant winged assortment of bones be from!

name: Librarian Hand
description: A grotesque hand with long talon-like finger nails. Slightly unsettling. You wonder if this could be of any use to you.

name: Smoky Mountain Pellets
description: Gritty, sharp, and possibly high in lead content, these smoky snacks are sure to put a smile on your face and a dent in whatever you spit them at. Available at the Great Smoky Mountains National Park gift shop.

name: Bow of the Brothian Order
description: Passed down from generation to generation of the Campbell Collective, this mighty bow will deliver swift, chicken noodly death to one's enemies, as well as provide comfort from the mid-winter sniffles.

name: Photographic Pupils
description: Now you can take pictures in the blink of an eye.

name: "No Cake Allowed" Sign
description: This... it makes you cry just looking at it. Unless your name is John Egbert, in which case you are changing your strife specibus to signkind immediately.

name: Half-Life 2 Achievement: Barnacle Bowling
description: 'Kill five barnacles with one barrel.' That's what it says, but... but how did you captchalogue an achievement?

name: Ceramic Vase
description: Is it "vaze", or is it "vahz"?

name: Morphsuit
description: It appears to be a skin-tight suit that encompasses the entire body. Sort of creepy, if you ask me.

name: Ruby Battle Corset
description: Who said this isn't practical for fighting!? It's a combat skirt! This black and red dress not only is very fashionable, but seems highly mobile and provides a bit of armor.

name: Spooky Blue Ghostplate
description: It looks like you just draped a blue sheet over your armour. Good news is that it seems to have retained some rather spooky properties!

name: Burial in the Faygo Sea
description: Freezing cold claws with a small grave on the back. The epitaph reads, "He died as he lived, drowning in Faygo."

name: Hilted Cane
description: It's a cane with a shitty sword hilt instead of a grip. It's not as good for walking, but it's marginally better for bludgeoning.

name: Claw Through Time
description: By turning the gear on the back of the claws, you can control which way these claws affect time. Turning them forward makes them strike the future, and turning them backward makes them hit the past.

name: Green Sun Pork Slicer
description: The power used to slay gods has now been implemented into your trusty cleaver.

name: Gilded Lily
description: On one hand, it's a rather pretty lily covered in a thin layer of pure gold. On the other hand, you can't even wear it properly now.

name: FREEDOM Grater
description: A red, white, and blue kitchen grater that grates food the AMERICAN way.

name: Full-body Spandex
description: A spandex suit that covers your whole body. Good for maintaining a secret identity while super-heroing, but goddamn does it get sweaty.

name: Jacket of the Way
description: The future is bulletproof. Fortunately, so is this stylish leather jacket.

name: Bonerake
description: A rake crafted out of actual, human, bones. This is slightly unsettling. Then again, BONErake, more like BONERake, amirite?

name: Witness Protection
description: Made of oaken wood and bands of gold, the scales of Justice adorn the front of the shield as a golden insignia of Libra's power. Its sole purpose is to dispense justice with the loud BANG it emits when striking an enemy.

name: Frayed Flag of Fortune
description: This slightly tired-looking flag has a large d20 emblazoned on it. Holding it, you notice that it is weighted to make for easier hefting and swinging.

name: Unstable Gay Pride Flag
description: A dizzying array of rainbows that seems like the slightest rip could cause the whole thing to explode into brilliant rainbows and chaos.

name: Patriotic French Pins
description: This set of pins proudly displays national colors and symbols of France.

name: Steel Crayons
description: These crayons are made out of steel.  They can't write anything at all, making them almost completely useless. Good for hitting things with though.

name: Shrekmunity DVD
description: It's a TV show about an ogre attending a community college.  This may be the greatest thing you - nay, the greatest thing the human race has ever created.

name: Fiery Mirrored Sacrificial Athame
description: A black obsidian dagger made for ritual sacrifice. Its surface gleams with the light of a thousand reflected suns.

name: Flag of the Covert Dersite Gambling Ring
description: The flag that Dersite Gamblers use to mark their locales. It's a highly illegal yet lucrative business. As you wave it, you feel as though all those crazy mobsters are at your back. In a good way!

name: Nun-chucks
description: A pair of nunchucks with the sticks formed into the shape of two religious women. Sacrilegious puns have never been so deadly...

name: Tesla powered Shotgun
description: A crazily powered shotgun that's powered by a internal Tesla coil. Nikolai would be so proud!

name: Marrowind Firestorm
description: This incredibly powerful fan made of bones can create a massive fire that is likely to consume a large portion of the area you use it on.

name: Palkia Tiara
description: A pearl-decorated tiara in the shape of a legendary Pokemon.

name: Icy Cold Faygo Whip Claws
description: These claws whip out from your hands, allowing you to scratch at your foes with ice cold Faygo from a distance.

name: Dersite Wizard Statue
description: A statue of a purple-robed wizard with a shiny black carapace.

name: Dragon Lantern
description: The lantern now has light from the flames of the Dragon's Breath, and is brighter and more powerful.

name: Long-Range Lightning Lantern
description: A lantern capable of lighting up far-away objects with lightning flares. Great for singeing enemies, too!

name: Jolly Dimensional Pyramid
description: So that's how Santa does it.. he passes through a dimension of holly, jolly and other things ending in -olly, where the laws of physics don't exist. This pyramid seems to be the very relic that gives him that power.

name: Favorite Time-Traveling Felt Fedora
description: A felt fedora complete with the number of your favorite felt member! And now it even has a version of Sawsbuck's power! Get ready for some time hopping!

name: AURYN
description: This intertwined snake pendant doesn't actually grant wishes, but each snake has red and green eyes! And they symbolize destruction and creation, fantasy and truth, reality and fiction, and how all realities nourish and draw from one another. OK it doesn't do anything, but it's a plot-heavy foreshadowie symbolic thing if you get what I'm saying.

name: Black Jupiter
description: Use the power of your mind to fling bolts of dark lightning at your enemies. The pin says: "When six darklit planets align..."

name: Black Saturn
description: Use the power of your mind to shield you from attacks and damage anything that touches you. The pin says: "When six darklit planets align..."

name: Black Uranus
description: Impale your enemies with icicles of dark energy. The pin says: "When six darklit planets align..."

name: Black Mars
description: Use the power of your mind to immolate anything that tries to approach with dark fire. The pin says: "When six darklit planets align..."

name: Black Mercury
description: Use the power of your mind to keep foes at bay with high-pressure orbs of dark water. The pin says: "When six darklit planets align..."

name: Black Venus
description: Knock enemies away with mental blasts of dark energy. The pin says: "When six darklit planets align..."

name: Pizzamelon
description: See, it's like, it's like a melon, but inside it's pizza. It's like a pizza pocket? But like, in slices... slices of pizza. In a melon.

name: Hyper Iron Lass Suit
description: That's more like it! This suit's super meter is fully charged and ready for action.

name: Eternal Santa Claws of the Sun
description: Ho-ho-holy HELL these are bright. Every swipe of these Santa themed claws hits an enemy throughout their entire timeline, dealing large amounts of damage.

name: Trenchtop
description: A heavy trench coat coat with screens in the lapels and keyboards in the sleeves. For the skulking stranger who needs to keep in touch.

name: Demonic Pillow of Ultimate Love
description: A sweet, lovely pillow. Anyone who sleeps on it will become enamored with the first person they see when they wake up. It also steals your soul, so there is that.

name: Demonic Pillow of Ultimate Greed
description: Sleep on this pillow, and the deal is complete. One soul for one pile of gold. Of course, knocking others unconscious with it and taking the gold they would have received works just as well.

name: Hyper Iron Man Armor
description: This Iron Man armor has been turbo-charged for a maxed out super meter. Unibeams all up in this shit.

name: iFortune Goggles
description: The manufacturer claims these are able to predict the future with 100% accuracy, but you don't believe that garbage for a minute. Instead you use them to browse the net and pester your chums.

name: Angelic Summoning Handgun
description: A gun that shoots scrolls of summoning rituals for angels. It's like a game of whack-a-mole, but more deadly.

name: Flaming Finish Piano Grande
description: A weapon of hot sonic riffs, this keyboard's smooth black exterior glows with a finish of moving flames that don't actually leave its surface until damaging an enemy. Playing refrains or actually hitting the enemies will singe them to dust, leaving a blazing trail in its wake.

name: Brick Plushie
description: Despite being rather soft on the surface, it is quite heavy and sturdy, and hard in the center. It might be useful as a weapon, or you could build a -VERY GREEN- house with it. (Not recommended for use in fireplace construction.)

name: Eternal Medieval Santa Claws of the Sun
description: These bright claws are decorated with Santa themed decorations, except it seems that Santa is in medieval garb.

name: Whelpling Lance
description: Once wielded by a noble sect of warriors who followed the laws of dragons in their quest for justice.

name: Ring of the Outerwinds
description: The eldritch gods have often made use of the wind and its destructive force. Now you can too!

name: Spacial Flip-Phone
description: A black flip-phone with a spiral on it. Send messages to and from anywhere with your connection to Sburb's wireless network.

name: Time Keeper Tags
description: These dog tags seem to be gear shaped and hold some slight time properties. As you wear them you can see battle techniques of wars long past from your old planet...

name: iDog Ski-Mode
description: The iDog Amp'd received an upgrade to become the far superior Ski-Mode. Much more useful for crushing imps with shitty beats than actually skiing.

name: Spicy Chili Mallets
description: Feeling HOT! HOT! HOT! RRRRRRRRR!!!!!

name: Prismatic Rainbow-Sticks Steel Crossbow
description: A steel rainbowy crossbow that materializes and fires glowing colored drumsticks.

name: Holly Jolly Flute
description: A flute covered in red and green stripes, with a curved crown, giving the appearance of a peppermint stick. It tastes delicious, but the downside is it can only play Christmas songs.

name: Sunspawn\'s Eye
description: This huge orb was once used by some eldritch flamedweller. Anything it gazes upon is bathed light so bright that it bursts into flame.

name: Rose Octet
description: These powerful, beautiful set of dice hold the power of the Green Sun itself within them, yet they send chills through you.

name: Alienware Computer
description: A powerful computer said to be the best of the best. The technology is so advanced some people believe it came from the stars.

name: Credit Card
description: Ka-ching!

name: Spook-suckin\' Cane
description: A compact walking cane that doubles as a ghost-suckin' vacuum.

name: Elemental Lightning Trident of Snow and Flame
description: Combined powers of all the gods glow inside this trident, from frosted tips to flaming hilt to static prongs.

name: Demonic Guise
description: Whenever you put this on, you always think about how you end up looking like some video game character or another. Pretty badass, so you aren't complaining.

name: Earl\'s Treasure
description: The condition of this item is absolutely acceptable. You would wear it everyday of your life.

name: Green Solar Flames
description: This yoyo strikes with the power of a green star... which seems impossible to you, but you aren't complaining with the power.

name: The Holy Theological History Textbook
description: A textbook that chronicles the history of the world and what role religion played in those events. It's very much on the side of the Christian god, however.

name: Tarot Warper
description: Warp dimensions through reading the cards.

name: Oglogoth\'s Flintlock
description: A legendary firearm, said to have been forged out of the metallic bones of a fallen horrorterror. Strangely enough, instead of proper gunpowder and lead ammunition, it seems to fire solid balls of pure darkness and rage.

name: Seer\'s Summoning Mirror
description: Not as useful for looking at stuff, but you can always summon a few handy-dandy whatevers to jobs for you. Now with a pretty paper border around the edges.

name: Armored Scouting Uniform
description: It's the usual Scouting Legion uniform except it has a layer of armored coating so a Titachnid won't be able to bite through your limbs as easily.

name: Ink of Diplobelus Pro Quo
description: This seems to be a ammonite shell overflowing with thick, synthetic-smelling black gunk. With leaves stuck in it? Even if it weren't for the foliage and ink you probably wouldn't be able to tell exactly what this is. Weird.

name: Blood-Scythe
description: A scythe with a crimson energy blade that doubles as a sword, used by Ragna the Bloodedge.

name: Veiled Luck
description: A dangerous yet beautiful set of dice that thrum with eldritch power.

name: Hemera\'s Dark Night Chainscarf Shredder
description: A chainscarf? Made from an item of a god and then tainted with the gods opposite element? Count me in! It is a bit dangerous to wear though... Maybe you'll just sling it around? How does this thing even run?

name: Luminescent Mortality Triangle
description: The light you see at the end of the tunnel? Yeah, that's this one. This glowing instrument is made with the bones of the dead.

name: Tome of Electron Punishment
description: This thick tome is so heavy it will scatter the electrons of your enemies. Don't look up if that's possible or not...

name: Neckbeard Frisbee
description: You might not get the tip off, but you'll sure knock their block off.

name: Explosive Swag
description: You're sure to escape the friendzone with this totally pimped out fedora.

name: Holoshades of the Blind Prophets
description: These totally awesome red shades project all your favorite computer funtionalities in a neat hologram. If only you could see through them...

name: Sticky Scarfputer
description: Whatever made you think combining something sticky with warm, cozy neckwear was oddly right in this case. Merely snuggle down into this scarf and it projects a screen infront of you. Also, don't worry about dropping it. It's...really sticky.

name: Twin Tailed Broom
description: The bristles on this sweeper are stiff, slick, and starchy. Probably just like whatever millionaire custom ordered a broom with two golden serpentine statues imbedded in its handle.

name: Highblood\'s Dagger
description: This thing is stained in bright colors. MIRACLES! Nah, it's just because the Highblood who owned this was very stabby. Hey! Don't point that thing at me!

name: Wands of Hope
description: These girly wands have been blessed by Godoka herself. Now go and defeat those witches.

name: Orca-Strength Cymbal Knuckles
description: Uppercut that SOB with these sharp cymbal knuckles empowered with the force of the mighty orca.

name: The Light Fantastic
description: This octagonal lantern can light up enemies at any distance with bolts of magical lightning. The casing is covered in glowing magical runes.

name: Cueing Needles
description: These needles are far too large to do any proper sewing, and far too sharp to be used as any sort of effective pool cue. They're pretty good for stabbing people, though.

name: Murder Sweeper
description: For those times when you just want to sweep something under the rug.

name: Reinforced Dress
description: This dress adds a lot of support. Good armor plating too!

name: High-Frequency Antenna Wands
description: A pair of antenna-shaped wands which transmit a loud and painful voice directly into the eardrums of whatever you point them at. Prolonged exposure may result in your target speaking in really fast run-on sentences.

name: The Power of Gay
description: A gay pride flag, now reinforced and sharpened, with little hearts all over it. It still looks like a rip in the flag could cause a massive explosion

name: Fuzzy Pickle Flashbang
description: Smile and say "fuzzy pickle!"

name: the short GLOWNS IN THE DARK
description: This shirt glows in the dark. Actually, it doesn't glow in the dark. To find out which is true, make the shirt??

name: Book of MiRaClEs
description: HeLlO, dO yOu HaVe TiMe To TaLk AbOuT OuR LoRdS aNd SaViOrS tHe MiRtHfUl MeSsIaHs? HONK

name: Dark Matter Time Cleaver
description: Pulverize the very fabric of space time using this incredibly dangerous Dark Matter Time Cleaver. Just be careful not to open up any black holes. Or paradoxes. Perhaps this weapon is best left to time players.

name: Eldritch Rocketpack
description: This is your normal, everyday rocketpack. Except for the fact that tentacles extend from it in all directions. Strangely, the tentacles don't seem to be affected by the heat from the rockets.

name: Tip Master
description: Never fear the friendzone again! With this puppy on your mop, you'll be sure to turn her onto the "m'lady" bandwagon.

name: Rubber Jackal
description: It's a small rubber jackal, a staple for the ancient Egyptian prankster.

name: HEXagonal Lantern
description: Parts of this lantern are made of... computer parts? And is that ants you see crawling around inside the top bit? You probably shouldn't remove the miniature teddy bear, either...

name: Paper Basket
description: A basket made of paper. What? They can't all be clever.

name: Digital Lunar Glow
description: Not only is this moon-shaped lantern a computer, but it can eradicate even the toughest of, well, the weakest enemies. It apparently gets stronger when there's more light to reflect.

name: Young Light Crown
description: You've got it all, you lost your mind in the sound. There's so much more, you can reclaim your crown.

name: Ender\'s Game series Boxed Set
description: The hit series by Orson Scott Card, all consolidated into one hefty set.

name: Glitched Dimensional Pyramid
description: This pyramid originates from a strange dimension between dimensions. It technically isn't supposed to exist, which is why it's covered in horrible artifacting. Who knows what'll happen if you wield it, let alone hit things with it.

name: Nic Cage Flameboner Suit
description: The hottest and softest fashion choice to showcase a burning desire for love and soft pillows.

name: Cardboard TARDIS
description: Bigger on the inside!

name: Parapparty the Hatter
description: Such swag as this could only be described as, "too cool for school," especially considering you'd probably be beaten up on the playground for wearing it there. Does not increase your rap skills, sadly.

name: Delirious Sweepnasty
description: Yo dawg, ever wanted to clean your house and make sick beats at the same time? Well we put some turn tables in your broom so you can mix tracks while you clean flats.

name: Stitch\'s Backup Needles
description: You feel as if these backup needles were used to sew a backup coat. They're quite large and very green. Very, very, very green.

name: Muscle Wizard\'s Bare Hands
description: Only a truly discerning eye can tell that these are more than just flesh-colored Hulk Hands! In the interest of full disclosure, though, it really helps if said eye is blind.

name: Obsidian Candy Tonfa
description: A delicious obsidian weapon that has a variety of uses, including combat, walking sticks, and rations for when you get hungry.

name: Overseer Death Scepter
description: This scepter is sure to shut up those annoying imps that keep bothering you... forever.

name: The Time Traveler\'s Cardigan - Plus Bow Tie
