description: Your favorite sophiticated-but-cozy nerdwear with an attached bow tie for the sake of novelty.

name: Demonic Stray Sheep Machine gun
description: You feel a demonic aura coming from the gun. The Stray Sheep's logo rests on the side. You seem to recall hearing that name before, but can't remember where. There's also a miniature console, for some reason.

name: White Paper Chain Wand/Gun
description: A wand/pistol that alternately shoots bullets out of its gun form, or surprisingly strong paper chains out of its wand form.

name: Pristine Bow
description: A shiny, shiny bow. While it is rumored to be quite pretty, looking at it is hard. That is why you always bring along sunglasses whenever you decide to use it!

name: Volans\' Vortex Rifle
description: This rifle shoots miniature constellations connected by razor-sharp wires to cut into your enemies that then collapse into black holes to vacuum up the pieces. Isn't science amazing?

name: Suit of The Excellent Game Host
description: This suit radiates the abilities of an excellent game host, making you always able to help people have a good time at a party. However, as a nasty side effect you'll wake up with a sore back, as this suit is made of solid steel.

name: Armored Dress of Cairo Amethysts
description: A tough yet dashing purple dress with flashing rainbow stripes, forged from the finest amethysts straight from Cairo. Specially resistant to temporal tearing, or at least that's what the tag says.

name: Old Maid Outfit
description: You now look like the Maid of Hope, but ancient and hobbled. Hence the cane.

name: Musically Inclined Sociopathic Software
description: GLaDOS will probably still try to kill you, but damn will she have rhythm.

name: Rainbow Razor
description: This is a straight razor, though the varied colors of the blade might make you think otherwise. The blade looks like it might be made out of rainbows, which seems like it'd make it harder to slice things with it. Fortunately solid rainbows seem to be a thing.

name: Paper Ribbon
description: The kind of curly cue you create by running a piece of paper over scissors. Pretty much useless for all but arts and crafts.

name: Laptophat
description: A laptop that you can wear on your head. Pretty self-explanatory.

name: Birthday Invitation
description: Let's throw a party! Whose birthday is it? Who cares! Have a cake!

name: Tonberry Plush
description: This cloaked, dark, yet slightly cute reptilian-turtle-thing holds a plush knife and a lantern only to reveal the fear in your eyes. You feel as if the cleaver in it's cute little hands could either cause your immediate death, or a squeal from it's kawaiitude.

name: Walking Staff
description: Well at least your "YOU SHALL NOT PASS" is much more forceful now.

name: The Nuclear Contraband
description: An upgraded tarot deck featuring many depictions of frogs: including blazing frogs, irradiated frogs, and frogs causing nuclear winters. The deck comes with a nice lead box to store the cards.

name: End to Existence
description: A monstrous axe forged from the power of the Green Sun, and an axe fabled to be capable of splitting universes in twain. Now a weapon made to destroy universes, and fed by their destruction.

name: Thorned Steel Starry Space Cloak
description: A fantastic cloak of thorns complete with a sewn rose centerpiece. Looking into the cloak mesmerizes as it displays changing starry patches of actual space that cycle every waking moment.

name: Tempovoltaic Smackdown
description: This hammer pulses electricity at a heartpounding rhythm, not that the guy you're hitting with it will have a heartbeat anymore! Is that because the hammer stops time, or because now he's dead? Heck if you know.

name: Zippowhip
description: A lazy adventurer's best friend. Forget cracking your wrists to whip-swing over chasms, and kiss heavy, smelly torches goodbye. This little beauty combines an automatically springing whip with all the convenience of a lighter. Comes stored in a flame-patterned leather holster.

name: Dirk\'s Insignia
description: You brandish this flag, feeling the power of the best Homestuck character coursing through you. It is both purple and rainbow at the same time. It is glorious.

name: Chainmail Dress
description: Not only classy, but armored as well! Easy to move around in, although can get pretty hot pretty quickly.

name: Bladed Lance
description: This double-bladed lance has the ability to split into three segments, making it the long range staple of melee fighters and Dragoons alike.

name: Wikipedia Page on Barrels of Fish
description: A page that fell out of your Wikipedia: Text Edition. It highlights the vulnerability of fish in a barrel.

name: Broomstick of Echidna
description: A good host knows there's an ideal tool for every job, but the tool suited for tidying an abode before a dinner party may or may not be the very same tool suited for executing a scratch. Whatever your plans may be, as a host I am sure you're simply the best there is.

name: Cello Conducting Wand
description: A hollow metal wand with holes in it, makes music as you kill stuff. How cool is that?

name: American Snake\'s Wand
description: A wand that shoots out green fireworks. Be careful because this shit goes everywhere!

name: Ancient Insect Pincers
description: Sharp appendages taken from some extinct entomological monstrosity. It must have been pretty large...

name: Silken Wizardhat Yarn
description: A silly hat made out of... some sort of beard hair? Ew.

name: Cutterfwlch
description: That whoever could draw the scissors from the stone would be king by choice of Jesus Christ. Yeah, right. A bunch of nonsense.

name: Bancheese gUITARD.......
description: Hopy shit dude look at those KILLER tunes................................

name: Doctor\'s Sweater Vest
description: Say this thing is pretty snazzy.

name: Eldritch Host\'s Sweater Vest
description: An eternity of living can do a lot to a man's psyche, provided they are 1. living and 2. of man. As the best Host I am neither of those things but that can't stop you from trying on my things.

name: iAstley
description: This phone is never gonna give you up, not even when you're in a tunnel or out of your phone company's service area.

name: Black Claws of Oglogoth
description: Originally imbued with energy from the Green Sun, these claws have been tainted by the Horrorterror's touch. You can sense a powerful evil energy surrounding them.

name: Librarian Talons
description: Wearable claws harvested from one of Night Vale's many fearsome librarians. Ew. But hey. At least they are much sharper than the plastic ones you had prior.

name: Compfoil Cosbycoat
description: This awesome hooded trenchcoat's fully portable computer capabilities would be more impressive if the coat didn't stream The Cosby Show 24/7.

name: Dialga Underwear
description: It's a pair of grey underwear with Dialga printed all over them. Very fetching. Or is it catching? Ha... ha ha....

name: Harry Piano and the Wristwatch of Dreams
description: Look into this tiny wrist mirror, and see your wildest dreams. Provided those dreams are becoming a concert pianist.

name: Cherry
description: Two reddish fruits connected by the stem. Don't eat the pits!

name: Cherry Cupcake
description: Cherry batter with cherry frosting with a cherry on top!

name: Packaged Staraga
description: This burst of concentrated magic has enough juice to patch up some of your more major wounds, as well as prevent you from sustaining any more for a while!

name: SBurb Gaming Computer
description: This computer is made to perfectly run with the game SBurb. It also has many built in bonus features for the game.

name: Gristwidget 12000
description: This Betty Crocker-branded device allows you to recycle items back into their grist components.
effects: STORAGE:RECYCLER.|SHUNT:USELESS.:Attempting to alchemize an item immediately converts it back into grist, making it impossible to get anything done. Good job.|UPGRADE|

name: Nine-Ball Needlewands
description: Great for knitting atomic overcoats and stabbing out eyeballs. Space and time seem to bend around these needles.

name: chilliDog Skis
description: BRR! Those are some cold skis, brother! The robotic dog patterns don't help the lack of warmth either.

name: Armored Derse of Cairo Amethysts
description: An armored dress that is the first choice for any classy dersite who wishes to look fabulous, be protected, and advertise the Kingdom of Darkness.

name: Ki Blast Yo-Yo
description: When you shout the name of an attack, this nifty yo-yo will concentrate your energy!

name: Potted Cactus
description: This small cactus looks cute, if that's possible. You don't seem to see any practical use for it though.

name: Super-luminescent Large Hadron Shredder
description: Every time you strum, the higgs boson appears for a split second and throws up the horns. Radical!

name: Functional Digivice
description: A small gadget which you can use to evo- er, pester a chum or two!

name: Panty And Stocking Merch T-shirt
description: (Un)Official merchandise from the hit series Panty and Stocking with Garterbelt. You have good taste!

name: Sweet Dreams Hard-Light Launcher
description: When you sleep on this, your dreams are projected in beautiful hard light form like a dream come true. Of course, they're then systematically and brutally launched at the nearest moving object.

name: Paper Super Scope
description: The previous version may have been more... wield-able, but this Paper Super Scope can shoot infrared with the best of them. Pro-Tip: For best results, aim for paper ducks.

name: Encyclopedia of Troll Reproduction
description: This is a thick tome extensively detailing the large subject of troll reproduction. It does not, however, relate why someone would want to read it in the first place.

name: Big Daddy Drill
description: The drill arm of a Big Daddy straight out of Rapture. It smells a little fishy and it's covered in seaweed but it'll do.

name: Fiery Gun Cutter
description: A gun that shoots flames mounted on top of a slick pair of red scissors with curved blades. Totally cool.

name: Squiddlepine Back Sheild
description: A backpack filled with wobbly swords. Some occasionally fall out and damage your surroundings.

name: Cape of Attacking Titans
description: Wait, are the titans doing the attacking, or are they being attacked?  All you know is that this is one bloody anim-you mean cape.  Yeah, cape.

name: Indescrib8bly Impract8cal Ch8ned Ch8nbl8de Launcher of Inaccur8 Proph8cies
description: This alchemized horror is so incredibly useless that it has actually somehow become quite effective. A built in tracking system predicts your adversary's next move. Sometimes.

name: Arkham Asylum Armory
description: You're now officially a supervillain. Well done. 8 ghostly arms controlled by wriggling around from within a straitjacket. Why? WHY!?

name: Adult Video Game Disc
description: A game for adults only. Includes nasty scenery.

name: Lagiascythe
description: A scythe that is crackling with electricity. It is surprisingly soft.

name: Orbital Core Obliterator
description: A single control console controlling the mighty Orbital Core Obliterator, a highly powerful satellite energy drill. Not only can you pierce the heavens but also the very earth. Nothing can stop you from digging now.

name: RWBY Poster
description: A Poster for the show RWBY, depicting Ruby, Weiss, Blake, and Yang.

name: Hot Air Belt with Pyramid Buckle
description: Have you ever wanted to blow hot air out of your waist while covering your crotch with the Sphinx? No? Well now you can.

name: Magma-Charred Steak Hammer
description: Pound your enemies with the force of a delicious fiery volcano.

name: Slytherin Wig
description: Want your hair to be big, funky, AND support your House? This obnoxiously show-offy emerald wig is JUST perfect. (Please note that any and all teasing/bullying/names you are called are just because people are so utterly jealous of your amazing new hair.)

name: Smithtop
description: Matt Smith's quirky face, adorned with a glorious mop of hipster hair, gazes up at you from the plastic surface of this laptop. WAIT WHAT'S ALL THIS PORN DOING ON HERE!

name: BEN Statue
description: You shouldn't have done that... <iframe width="1" height="1" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/9u0FKJJclZM&autoplay=1" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Anti-Spiral Aegis
description: Sometimes known as the Death Spiral Field. Blows are absorbed and then converted into raw energy, The more power poured into the blow, the denser the shield becomes.

name: Creeper Hoodie
description: Hissssssss, BOOM!

name: Digimon Crests
description: Representing the qualities of the digidestined like courage, sincerity, light, frie- wait light?

name: Wand of Heat and Clockwork
description: A mystical wand with the power of flame and time. It's decorated with revolving gears.

name: Katamari Damacy
description: A strange Japanese game about rolling up everything on Earth into balls to turn into stars. Don't ask.

name: Inline Lunchabomb Skates
description: Explosive bits of ham and cheese attached to your feet. What could go wrong?

name: Faygo: Psychedelic Rapture Murder Flavor
description: You're not sure if even a clown could survive drinking this holy mess.

name: Tanned Jacket
description: A snazzy suit is what any charismatic salesman might need when they're traveling so very far from home, wherever or whenever that might be.

name: Guy-Manuel\'s Helmet
description: Upon putting on this helmet, you feel a sudden urge to do a ROBOT ROCK, and LOSE YOURSELF TO DANCE.

name: Thomas Bangalter\'s Helmet
description: Upon putting on this helmet, you gain a lot of RANDOM ACCESS MEMORIES, and you want to dance to DA FUNK.

name: Raiden\'s Lament
description: The cyborg ninja's HF blade, now in scythe form! You think Raiden might need some cheering up.

name: Battlestar Galactica: The Complete Series
description: All 4 seasons of Battlestar Galactica on DVD! Comes with collectible cylon.

name: YoshiSet
description: A soft, comfortable headset depicting the color scheme of the beloved dinosaur.

name: Light-up TARDIS Cardigan
description: The prefect novelty Christmas sweater for that special obsessed someone.

name: Cairo Cardigan - Plus Bow Tie
description: This is the perfect cardigan for one who is ALREADY HERE in the worst sense of the phrase, and comes with a trendy bow tie stitched on.

name: Wizard Chess
description: Chess, but with animated pieces that move on your command!

name: Cherubim Chess Set
description: An unique chess set featuring bright red and lime green pieces decorated with lots of spirals and alligator heads.

name: Hollow\'s Shotgun
description: A mysterious gun that seems part medieval and part modern. But even so, it's a rather badass weapon that looks like it was forged with the souls of a thousand angry gamers throwing their controllers on the floor. It also looks incredibly difficult to figure out how to use, but it's alright once you grasp its relatively unforgiving difficulty curve. Prepare to Cry.

name: Pyramidvision Goggles
description: These triangular goggles make your surroundings look like you're in a silent hill game all the time. That is to say, there's so much fog, everything looks 10 times scarier.

name: EFFECT Stamp
description: Wooden stamp that stamps the word EFFECT in burning hot plasma.

name: Complete Guide to the Four Nations and One United Republic
description: Okay, this is just ridiculous. It's basically Wikipedia but if it was applied to the Avatar: the last Airbender world. And its all in Chinese!

name: Hot Wing Freezie
description: It's a freezie that unfortunately tastes like frozen hot wings, leveling it out to a lukewarm temperature.

name: Sendificator Cabinet
description: A larger model of Sendificator, this one can fit bigger items than the last one. It's still not quite big enough to fit yourself into, though. At least not without some dismemberment.

name: Sharp Dress
description: A dress that definitely wasn't meant to be worn to a ball or fancy party. The blades jutting from its fabric could probably intimidate even the rowdiest of foes.

name: Scared Shitless Tattoo Machine
description: The terrifying phantoms you see trying to attack you while using this may or may not be due to ink fumes, previous drug use, latent schizophrenia, or legitimate super natural forces that also killed your cats and edge you towards destruction. Either way you should probably avoid being left alone with this.

name: Insecticide Spray Can
description: On this can is a list of instructions. Spray away from face. Do not use near food, children, pets, or anything living. Anything you spray this with will die. Keep out of reach of idiots.

name: Bug Buster
description: It seems to be an ordinary fly swatter with a can of bug spray strapped to the handle upside down. It comes with an instruction diagram and directions on the can. Flip the device, spray away from face. Flip device once more, strike with precision at paralyzed foe. Enemy Neutralized.

name: Spatial Slinger
description: A pistol with the power to create miniature black holes upon impact that suck the target in. You should probably fire from more than a few feet away.

name: Led Zeppelin: The Song Remains The Same Movie
description: The movie of Led Zeppelin's Madison Square Garden live performance.

name: Pepper Mace
description: Not only a mace that you can fling around, but it also sprays a highly painful irritant that will confound enemies as well! Note: Don't hit yourself in the face with this.

name: Sokkas Boomerang
description: Water? Earth? Fire? Air? Pshh! You have this awesome boomerang! WHACKAPOW!

name: Ch8ned Ch8nbl8s Launcher of Indescribable Horrorterror Hunting
description: This legendary weapon was once used to hunt the darkest, most vile creatures in all of existence.  Or maybe it will be used for that.  Who knows, this is paradox space after all.

name: Infrared Gamegauntlet
description: Line up your shot, pull back, and let that punch fly! ...This is stupid, why would you even need to aim a punch in such a contrived manner?

name: Ecto Knife Chucks
description: Like nunchucks, but with knives. Unfortunately, they heal everything they cut.

name: Symmetric Counterflail
description: A finely balanced flail with a spiked glowing crystal on the end. It deals JUSTICE-FUELED blows to your enemies in a WELL-BALANCED attack.

name: Leeky Top Hat
description: Your top hat looks rather dapper, sir, but, may I ask, why you wear a leek in its fold?

name: Dungeons and Pac Man
description: For how long has man awaited such an epic crossover in this world? Not very long at all, if ever, but you seem to have beaten everyone to the punch, pooplord.

name: Gloves of the Dirkjake Shipper
description: Patterned with green and orange, donning these gloves makes you feel absurdly homosexual. Onwards!

name: Explosive Grape Rock Candy
description: The title of this flavor seems to be quite literal. I wouldn't eat them if I were you.

name: The Hitchhiker\'s Guide to the Galaxy: Pocket Universe Edition
description: The complete compendium of all knowledge in the universe, distilled for the modern-day traveler. Emblazoned on the back is the friendly slogan "DON'T PANIC".

name: Soul Scourge
description: A mace that also happens to summon spirits to aid you in your fight! Good luck un-summoning them, though.

name: Halloween Party Invitation
description: An Invitation to all the Boys and Ghouls out there. Let's get some candy and scare some imps.

name: Bladekind Suspension
description: It was once said that the mighty Overseer looked down upon his creation, and said thus: "fUCK THERE ARE SO MANY BLADES FUCK YOU NO MORE SWORDS." And thus, the holy Bladekind Suspension was born.

name: Greenlit Sub
description: This mouthwatering, neon green sandwich is said to be the meal of choice for the Babby Overseer himself. He usually eats around 25 of them in a day, though he's been know to really pig out when there's nothing else to do.

name: Boot Charm
description: You've carried this boot with you for so long, that you can't quite remember where you got it in the first place. Still, it's kept you out of trouble, so there must be something lucky about keeping it with you!

name: MjolWherever-you-are
description: What? This hammer now has Celine Dion's face on it and is constantly playing "My Heart Will Go On" softly. Quite honestly this may be the most annoying weapon you've ever alchemized.

name: Dragoon Lance
description: This Multi-Pronged is the weapon of choice for all max level Dragoons, and is said to have the ability to increase the strength of your Jump. Whatever that means.

name: Unacceptable Armament
description: This pistol's caliber is.... UNACCEPTABLE!

name: Poseidon\'s Beach Bummin\'  Trident
description: Kick back and relax with your old pal Poseidon and an ice cold glass of lemonade, all in one!  Perfect for a day at the beach.

name: Hatchet Girl Spandex
description: This bright purple and red spandex jumpsuit is a must have for any insane clowns out there. Woop woop on, sister.

name: The Nightmare Before Christmas Collector\'s Edition DVD Set
description: A Collector's Edition DVD set of one of Tim Burton's most known smash hits, The Nightmare Before Christmas! Just the thought of what alchemy can be done with this is both scary and wonderful, just like Halloween and Christmas!

name: Swiss Army Taco
description: Kind of messy, but a survival expert knows to go with what you can take. This taco contains tools for all kinds of situations, and is edible too... if you can get past the metal aftertaste.

name: Twilight Bracelet
description: An interesting bracelet that you can't quite see. It hums with a magical power, and sometimes manifests strange hexagonal shapes around it.

name: The First Grudge
description: Thought to be the first cleaver of the Tonberry King, this cleaver is sharp as all hell, if a little rusted. It's power is moderate, and it reeks of unholiness. It also goes "Doink!" when you stab something!

name: Unstable Green Star Sphere of Doink
description: This thing was already unstable, made of a Miniature Green Sun and pop rocks, but now it's fueled by dark energy. Are you ever going to stop?

name: Book of the Spirit World
description: A thick tome of all the Spirits in the Spirit World compiled by Avatars past.

name: Magic 8-Charge Wand
description: This lucky little weapon provides powerful blasts at command, perfect for fighting Magic 8-Pirates!

name: V.A.T.S. Masktop
description: Just like a V.A.T.S. Mask, but the computing power is boosted significantly, allowing you to process enemy states even quicker. Plus, you get to chat with your buddies and access SBURB on the go.

name: Semi-Supernatural Tome
description: A book containing majyyks of semi-supernatural origin.

name: Keychain
description: A key attached to the end of a chain. It would probably be more effective if you added more keys.

name: Attack on Katamari DVD
description: I'll roll them all up... every last Titan on the face of the Earth!

name: Diamond Time Pillow
description: A pillow that has the texture and colours of Dialga, a dinosaur-like legendary Pokemon with the power of time. Time will be spent when slept on this pillow.

name: Gasoline Wand
description: Don't bring this near fire.

name: Coat of the Green Sun
description: A powerful coat to protect you from sun, rain, wind, and the attacks of your raging enemies. It makes you look and feel quite stylish. Electric sparks occasionally fly from it.

name: Book of Souls
description: Is it a necromancer's manual, or a soul food cookbook? Who knows.

name: BroomGuide to Cleaning the Universe
description: A broomsword that will eradicate all uncleanliness from the cosmos.

name: Cosby Spandex
description: This thing look horrifying...

name: Needleman\'s Needles
description: You can't stop the top, but you can definitely wreck some snakes with these bad boys.

name: Gifdinir, The Bane Of Foliage
description: This gun-axe has been possessed by a Viking Warrior named Gifdinir. He hates plants. Like, a lot.

name: American Pump-Action Pepper Spray
description: Taking care of protestors the only way you know how: the American way.

name: Matriorb
description: This black, spiky orb looks like it's covered in candy corn. What could it possibly be used for?

name: Cruxite Faygo
description: The literal form of miracles in a bottle, this red cruxite flavored soda is out of this world. Sold only in the medium.

name: Air Gear Complete Series DVD
description: This high-flying anime focuses on gang fights on motorized inline skates. What isn't cool about that?!

name: Shitty Space Fury Wand
description: With all the power of space law breaking furies at your wand tip, things get pretty weird. Don't even ask how it works or who made this shit. Just roll with it, and ignore the images of explicit fury exercises that plague your mind while using it.

name: Kanohi Vahi
description: This powerful mask harnesses the power of TIme. Use it carefully.

name: Polar Bear Dog Headdress of Avatar Kuruk
description: A headdress meant to keep you warm while chasing down face-stealing spirit monsters.

name: Electrum-Magnetite Crystal of Atomic Destabilisation
description: This oddly-shaped conglomerate of rocks and minerals generates its own electromagnetic radiation. This is then reflected within itself to amplify the precise frequency required to disintegrate your enemy into its constituent subatomic particles. Be sure to direct the crystalline end away from you when the beam refracts out!

name: Gay Bacon
description: Originally called rainbow belts, this classic candy has now become as trendy as it is tasty.

name: Asexual Bacon
description: A plainly coloured strip of candy that does wonders when you need a pick-me-up and a relaxing snack in one.

name: Ghillie Suit
description: Just the body gear for you if youve ever wanted to become a literal walking plant.

name: The Gothtop 3000
description: The most counter culture emo computing device a rebellious Hot Topic shopper could ask for.

name: Nyx\'s Honeyspecs
description: When wearing these shades, you can see everything in the Incipisphere, wipe anything out of existence in the blink of an eye, and look cool while doing so.

name: Rich Red Velvet Trenchcoat.
description: This extravagant trenchcoat is rich enough to rot your teeth on contact. It is suggested to be worn, not eaten.

name: Skull Stool
description: It's an ordinary bar stool up until the point where it's decorated with human skulls. Skulls for the skull stool, you guess?

name: Fresh Scissors
description: Brand new, almost like they came right out of the box! ... They probably actually would have if you hadn't used alchemy to make them.

name: Sweet Teanade
description: Take out your enemies in a burst of gunpowder and tea leaves, with a hint of peach!

name: Chilling Magi-Steel Spear
description: A blade made of the totally scientific properties of Magi-Steel, and made unbreakable through process of magical freezing. This thing will not only stab an enemy pretty nicely, shoot frozen lasers, but for some reason it can also stop time?

name: The Nightmare of Christmas
description: Santa never really recovered from getting possessed by a demon. The result was a very odd Christmas toy.

name: The Seventh Grudge
description: The seventh blade owned by the Tonberry King, and much more powerful then the first. It has two small holes near the base for some reason.

name: The Last Grudge
description: The deep hunter green blade shines with dark light, a symbol of the Horrorterrors glowing darker as the orichalcum edge glints. Dark energy crackles endlessly around the tall blade, empowering the Tonberry King's Last Grudge. To be wielded by only the darkest and most powerful of heroes.

name: Giant Afro Drill
description: This giant afro sports all the latest in drilling technology. Plus, it looks pretty cool.

name: Stitchers of Fate
description: These needles are so sharp they have the power to penetrate through anything, even fate itself. Okay, maybe that's an exaggeration - they just seem to be just really edgy looking sewing needles.

name: Ogretop
description: Be the envy of all your friends with this absolutely Shrektacular laptop computer.

name: Radio Frequency Band
description: This long, stretchy rubber band pulsates several times per second with an eerie ringing noise. When struck, it releases a torrent of static - and if you listen carefully, you can almost hear voices.

name: Mock Gundam Helmet
description: Though not made of luna titanium, this helmet is still reliably sturdy.

name: Legendary Infinite Fez
description: You can wear a fez now. Fezzes are cool.

name: Despair! Santa Teresa
description: A strange double-headed scythe that looks rather unwieldy, as well as being made of cheap plastic.

name: Sith-Shot Skates
description: Metal skates with a six-shot chamber on each shoe. It appears to be harboring some anomalous evil inside them.

name: Cruxite Turntables
description: No one would guess to alchemize cruxite! Ha! These make godly beats.

name: Ladies\' Luck
description: A meticulously crafted octect of pretty yellow and orange die. It's said their former wielder always rolled high, bringing misfortune to her enemies with a dual-headed scythe, thorny blade, and sweet rosy dress. Now you can, too.

name: Mean Green Host From Outer Space
description: This life-sized puppet resembles the Puppet of the Excellent Host, except now it has long, winding plant tendrils and an insatiable lust for blood. It is, undeniably, mean and green and bad.

name: Skull Wand
description: A wand carved out of a bone with a skull motif. It's not actually magical, but it's certainly pretty sharp.

name: Derse Wand of Skulls
description: A wand carved out of a huge purple bone. The symbol of Derse is stamped upon the skulls that decorate it.

name: Super-Moist Chocolate Cream Cake
description: The aroma wafting from this decadent-looking chocolate cake makes your sweet tooth ache with longing.

name: Vitamin C-4
description: This sticky-sweet device packs a surprisingly violent fruit punch!

name: Toilet Plunger
description: You suppose there is some tactical advantage in using a weapon that your enemies don't even want to touch...

name: Shitfucker
description: Full of spring loaded shitfuckingness, this tool excels at clearing the clogs out of toilets.

name: Ruby Contraband
description: This bright red frog costs a small amount of grist, but for some reason you feel like what you're doing is cheating. The contraband also seems to be imbued with some fire properties.

name: Diamond Contraband
description: This snow white frog costs a small amount of grist, but for some reason you feel like what you're doing is cheating. The contraband also seems to be imbued with some Ice properties.

name: Emerald Contraband
description: This deep green frog costs a small amount of grist, but for some reason you feel like what you're doing is cheating. The contraband also seems to be imbued with some earth properties.

name: Sapphire Contraband
description: This deep blue frog costs a small amount of grist, but for some reason you feel like what you're doing is cheating. The contraband also seems to be imbued with some water properties.

name: Amethyst Contraband
description: This deep purple frog costs a small amount of grist, but for some reason you feel like what you're doing is cheating. The contraband also seems to be imbued with some dark properties.

name: Syringe of Ammonia
description: For external use only.

name: Tarot of Fire and Wind
description: These cards of the Minor Arcana give you control over Fire and Air. Use sharp winds to cut your enemies down or burn them to cinders by shooting fireballs at them.

name: Watermelon-Flavoured Rock Candy
description: A watermelon-flavoured stick of rock candy. Summery!

name: The Cards of Fate
description: After first taking the deck apart and restoring it's power you have finally unlocked the magic that was sealed within the cards. Now you have a deck that not only allows you to predict but to influence and manipulate events in the future. You hold your Fate in your hands now, what will you do with it?

name: Stabby Derse Skull Wand
description: A jet-black wand made of sharpened bone with purple markings. The handle is a single polished skull.

name: Snow Strings
description: With each note played the area becomes colder and colder. A note of desolation my even cause an explosion of cold. Be sure to wear gloves!

name: Tunnel Snakes Overcoat
description: Butch, the Lord of Ruling, and Hero of Vault 101, wore this when fighting the Mighty Villian, Lone Wanderer. He was slain, and the overcoat now comes to you.

name: Maritomb
description: This slab of solid aquamarine would make a great marker for one buried at sea.  Wait, that didn't make any sense...

name: ThunderGun
description: Surprisingly shocking, this gun's electrically-charged bullets shoot through the air with the speed of lightning. Or maybe they're as fast as a regular gun's bullets. It's too fast for you to see either way.

name: Blue Ecto-shot
description: A syringe filled with a blue goop, one shot to a wound delivers direct healing powers to your system. Not for the faint of heart or those with a fear of needles.

name: Cyber Bracelet
description: A golden bracelet which is able to display a holographic computer interface for all your cybering needs! ... Wait a minute...

name: Droid Headtop
description: While leaving a headset plugged into a phone is quite easy, why not just have the headset being an entire computer?

name: Toasted Driver
description: This breaded putter has been toasted to perfection, and will likely do the same to your enemies.

name: Deadly Invitation
description: Let's invite some Imps to their death.

name: Assassination Invitation
description: It looks like a lovely and fancy invitation, though when it is opened, hidden mechanics inside the card spray poisonous gas into the readers face. Make sure to point it at your enemies before you open it.

name: Invitation of the Inevitable
description: When this card is opened, flames spew into the readers face, some demonic laughter can be heard and the scent of brimstone can be smelled. On the inside it reads "Please go to hell. Literally."

name: Sanic Costume
description: This is a horrifyingly bad costume of Sonic. It is glitched out, and does not look good at all. Why someone would want to wear this is beyond me.

name: Electrified Derse Skull Wandstabber
description: Just as stabby and now capable of charging your laptop too. Or electrocuting enemies, if that's your thing.

name: Honey-tov Cocktail
description: Great for hunting bears.

name: Woman-Ray Dress
description: You have no idea why anyone would genderbend Man-Ray from Spongebob, but her outfit seems to be pretty good armor-wise.

name: QuantuMeringue Pie
description: A mad-science spin on an old dessert favorite, this pie glows slightly and you're pretty sure it disappears when you're not looking at it.

name: Spellybeans
description: These jellybeans have been stamped with magic ink.  They're unsuitable for eating now so throw them at enemies!

name: Alchemic Gloves Of Can-Opening
description: The sharpened bits on the ends of the fingers are perfect for opening cans, especially when you apply a burst of ultra-hot steam and change the composition of the metal in the lid. Seems like a lot of trouble just to open a can, but you never know!

name: Castlevania Cartridge
description: The incredible and tough as balls story of the Belmont clan in their quest to keep the world safe from the dreaded Dracula and his army of the undead!

name: Special Starslayer Sparklebow
description: This glittery bow abhors you so much you want to vomit, but it does shoot tiny shooting stars that seem pretty effective, so you aren't complaining that much.

name: Lemonium Explodinator
description: This bow smells of citrus, yet rains destruction and doom of many flavors upon your foes!

name: Stupidly Painful Chalk Ball Lenses
description: Ok, this is just ridiculous how much these make your eyes hurt. I mean, hot-damn this stings! Who in the incipisphere would actually think to make these!?

name: Bio Force Magnetic Accelerator Cannon
description: This weapon is so unspeakably epic you can't believe you haven't thought of it sooner. The magnetic railings at the reciving end of it will no doubt send the devastating plasma blasts much faster. Now you know how it feels to have real power in your hands.

name: Flaming Party Pirate Flag
description: This flag was once carried by ancient, flamingly effeminate, and flamboyant party pirates. It is also just as flaming as those it once heralded.

name: Super-Telescope
description: It was a telescope, but now it's SUPER!!!!

name: Helm of the Pool Lord\'s Eye
description: Not only does wearing this allow you to instinctively calculate the perfect shot while playing pool, but it also allows you to see underwater.

name: Even More Seductive Tarot
description: You'll never see Ms. Paint the same after seeing these cards

name: Infrared Speargauntlet
description: The infrared laser sight has now been given a purpose, providing quick and useful aim for the tethered spear which launches forth from the gauntlet's wrist and pulls the enemy in for a combo! Shouting, "GET OVER HERE," during use of this function is entirely optional, yet completely badass.

name: Battletoad Panties
description: These tight fitting spanks allow for easy access during combat AND have a illustration of all your favorite Battletoads characters on them.

name: Golden Sketchradio
description: Whatever you draw in the book is played in beautiful music via the radio.  Mostly beautiful.  Better used for smashing imps.

name: iPlunger
description:
Want to text your friends while plumbing?
Theres a plunger for that.

name: Tropical Blast Spellybeans
description: Brand new flavors, brand new kinds of mayhem!  Choose between Erratic Orange, Watermelon Whimsy, Risky Raspberry, Critical Kiwi and Megaton Mango!

name: Chaindawg Skiblades
description: These two chainblades have taken on both the shape of skis, as well as a mechanical dog motif. The tag says they run on 5000 AA batteries, but you see nowhere which you would even be able to insert so many, let alone one. They work either way, so go nuts, kiddo.

name: Darkspectrum Lich Rocket Wings
description: These strange cosplay wings now include rockets. It's hard to know why you bother with the actual wings.

name: Lunar Fairy Bow
description: Made from special blue steel found only on the moon with charming fairy wing decor, the bow allows you to shoot harder, better, faster, stronger.

name: Mann Co. Certified Plunger
description: A plunger studded with Australium, it even  has the Mann Co. logo on the stick!

name: Monstro in a Jar
description: You weren't sure what you were expecting to make, but a giant dead whale in a hopefully sturdy jar wasn't it. You don't even know where you are supposed to PUT something this big.

name: PLUNGERE...
description: You are the shit lord, the shit lord is you.

name: Pimp Daddy \'Seidon\'s Beach-Link Trident
description:
Bling'n on the beach, AAHWOO HOO HOO.  Bling'n on the beach, AAHWOO HOO HOO.  
Bling'n on the beach, AAHWOO HOO HOO.

name: Mario\'s Plunger
description: This plunger is surprisingly clean. For an Italian plumber, he doesn't plumb a lot...

name: Ogretacular Plunger
description: Your favorite swamp ogre, now in plunger form. This just got a lot grosser.

name: Toast-A-Matic Ogre-Plunger
description: Because, out of all the things you would want to toast your bread in, it would obviously have to be a Shrek-styled plunger.

name: Festive Toast-A-Matic Ogre-Plunger
description: It's times like these you really have to question the marketing department for the Shrek movies.

name: Luxurious Red Velvet Melt Cake
description: The silky smooth frosting chocolate covering the mouth-watering red cake cloaks the hidden surprise:  a molten fudge center!  Sweet Tooth Heaven!

name: Fusion Assault Sheep
description: Military grade fusion assault sheep, perfect for stealth operations.

name: Paper bag
description: Time to get Eco-friendly up in here. If only it didn't tear so easily...

name: Ringed Watchtop
description: This watch / laptop combo just got a lot more portable and fashionable.

name: Wrist Mounted Jackal Watch
description: WHAT PART OF "Be careful when firing this thing if you want to keep your arm" DO YOU NOT UNDERSTAND

name: Homemade Taser
description: Some uninsulated wires attached to a high-voltage battery. Stab and shock. Just don't touch those wires yourself...

name: Timestamp Pedestal
description: This Pedestal displays the current time in a parallel universe without time travel... which is %DESCVAR_1%.

name: Spaced Out Hammer
description: You feel kind of light holding this thing, almost like you'll float away. You also feel a strange desire to smash everything within three miles.

name: Nine-Ball Laserneedlewands
description: These things are simply ridiculous. Be careful to not shoot your eye out with these needlelaserwands.

name: Cairo Witch Hat
description: From the hit TV series "He Who Is Already Here: A Teenaged Witch!" This hat makes you feel as if you have a grip over time.

name: Magic Infl8-Ball
description: A black inflated ball with an 8 on the front. Inside is a small blue die with multiple ambiguous answers on it. Ask a question, then toss the ball around and whatever the die lands on is your answer! The ball is mostly opaque, though, so the answers are even more useless now.

name: Inflated Naiad Wings
description: You're pretty sure naiads don't have wings, nor do they need the aid of a flotation device to swim, but wearing these in any body of water makes you feel like one anyway.

name: B\'ass Kicker
description: Do you like slapping people around with large fish, but hate it when they inevitably start to smell? Then try the B'ass Kicker, a giant inflatable fish guaranteed to be at least 99% as hilarious as the real thing, or your money back!

name: Gnarly Narwhal Knockout
description: The only thing better than whacking someone with a giant inflatable fish is whacking someone with a giant inflatable NARWHAL! You can also use the horn as a poking implement for even more hilarity!

name: Long-Distance Electrostabber Eight-Skull Wand
description: This black bone wand is capable of stabbing imps at long ranges, thanks to the power of magitech.

name: Mystical Mann Co. Janitor Goggles
description: They protect against radiation and toilet water!

name: Deluxe Size Inspectifying Glass
description: Only the STRONGEST of investigators can carry this giant thing.

name: 1.5D Glasses
description: Um....this looks more like someone just chopped a pair of 3d glasses in half and painted the lens black. How would you even use this?

name: Stereoblind Monochromatic Half-Glass
description: This only sees in 2D, only in old-fashioned black and white, and only covers one eye.  If you were to weaponize it's shittiness this would be surprisingly powerful.

name: Sailor Johnny Sock
description: Johnny Sock, sailor of the hand-seas, at your service!

name: Luchador mask
description: This brightly colored mask is filled with the proud spirit of Mexico. Also sweat from its previous owner's face. Eww.

name: Ceramic Doll
description: It appears to be a pretty generic doll, except it's made of ceramic. Very breakable, and very useless.

name: Skullgirl\'s Best Friend
description: A rifle powered entirely by the Skull Heart. Occasionally grants the dying wishes of imps slain by it.

name: Akashik Drawing Of A Series Of Circles
description: Every time you use this pen it creates a perfect circle in time and space.

name: The Iron Giant DVD
description: A movie about a giant, friendly killer robot pretending he's Superman. Voiced by Vin Diesel.

name: Goat Simulator DVD
description:
Have you ever wanted to be a goat?
Live your dreams with goat simulator.

name: Rose-Spandex Body Suit
description: This deep red spandex suit is tight-fitting and very seductive. Fortunately, it also provides decent defense as well as bringing out all your curves!

name: Double Smoke-Flavoured Rock Candy
description: The overpowering stench created by two kinds of smoke wafting from this rock candy drive you to finish the battle, so you won't have your nose anywhere near it again.

name: Black Electromagic Eight-Skull Stabwand
description: A wand carved out of charred bone that radiates a fearsome aura. The skull-encrusted handle is the only part free of the flashes of magical lightning. Slice apart anything that gets in your way with fearsome power!

name: Recipe Finder
description: A calculating device that scans your entire Sylladex for codes and starts randomly trying combinations until it finds one that results in an existing item. Extremely useful, if it didn't take bloody forever!
effects: STORAGE:COMBOFINDER/inventory/1/1.|SHUNT:USELESS.:The Recipe Finder doesn't seem to interact well with the Alchemiter, resulting in an amalgamation of useless computer parts and machinery.|UPGRADE|

name: Mom\'s Spaghetti
description: There's vomit on your sweater already, Mom's spaghetti. You're nervous, and you keep on forgetting, spaghetti. Mom's Spaghetti. You better lose yourself in Spaghetti.

name: Gaia\'s Lyre
description: Covered in a verdant coat of moss, this lyre emits a pleasant smell of flowers in the spring. However, when played it unleashes nature's uncompromising brutality, thorn-covered vines erupting from the ground to impale and strangle any in its path.

name: Harplunger
description: A harpoon gun with a plunger instead of a harpoon? What are you trying to do, unclog the whale's blowhole?

name: Doctor Park DVD
description: A DVD about a time traveling band, spreading music throughout time and space, but you wouldn't know that because it's supposed to be used as a weapon.

name: Brutal Waistcoat
description: This waistcoat is brutal. And legendary. Brutally legendary. Perfect for a heavy metal hero.

name: Monobear Battery
description: A cartoon bear is printed on the battery. "Disclaimer: Any and all side-effects, including death and overwhelming despair, are completely intentional"

name: Mysterious Hula Horns
description: They appear to be candy-corn colored hula hoops, although they are much harder than your average hula hoop. Perhaps you can whack someone with them. Or just play a game of hula hoop.

name: Chains of the Cherubim
description: This mighty green chain constantly crackles with power in dazzling rainbow colours. Each end is tipped with a gargantuan serpent's head that snaps at enemies. The touch of a just, heroic wielder will cause these heads to turn white, while an unjust, villainous wielder will turn them black: those in conflict with themselves may cause the heads to fight one another for supremacy.

name: Musical Heels
description: Music chimes follow you when you step. Very deadly when you kick.

name: Creepy Voodoo Doll of 3nohj3
description: It's vaguely familiar, also it has bunch of pins in it, all of which are yellow, odd.

name: Danny Rand, Iron Fist Figure
description: The figure didn't come with any accessories, as a kung fu master doesn't need any accessories.

name: Yume Nikki - Game Pack Disc
description: It's a disc with a game called Yume Nikki on it, as well as some fangames, including .flow, yume 2kki, Me, Fleshchild, and Lcd Dem. They all give you an eerie feeling.

name: Soul Of Sanic
description:
GOTTA GO FAST! CUMON, STEP IT UP!
TOO FAST 4 U!

name: Oriental Blades of Double Death
description: Using the power of Math, you made these saw-needles kill foes TWICE. you're not entirely sure how it works, but maybe its for the best.

name: Faygo Helmet
description: A red bicycle helmet with the Faygo logo on it.

name: Shou-Lou the Undying Cosplay
description: You now have the powers, or at least the appearance, of the mightiest dragon in the martial arts world. Hopefully no one tries to rip your heart out for uncontrollable power.

name: Rubber Band Ball
description: You've done it. You've finally organized all the miscellaneous rubber bands littering your office desk by wrapping them around each other and making a ball. Now, if only it would stop rolling away...

name: Citrus Attire
description: This lime-green gives others the impression that you mean business.

name: Phial of Ichor
description: The blood of the Council of Elder Gods (Blah, Overseer, and Mikle).

name: Hickory Smoked Bacon Flavored Rock Candy
description: This candy is packed with the savory flavor of expertly cured and smoked bacon.  Weird but tasty!

name: Meaty Mayhem Spellybeans
description: This new set of flavors includes Staggering Steak, Ballistic Bacon, Chicken Catastrophy, Atomic Turky and Hazardous Ham.  Carnivorous carnage!

name: Inflated Toy Rose Mallet
description: As if the original hammer wasn't loud and annoying enough, this one keeps spouting corny quotes in an ear-searingly irritating and high-pitched voice when it hits things. Here's hoping you have earplugs!

name: Sailor Johnny Thundersuck
description: Sailor Johnny has braved the lightning storms of the hand-seas and came out the other side with shocking new skills.

name: Blazing Sailor Johnny Thundersuck
description: Now Sailor Johnny can suck people in with a shocking gust then blow them away blazing flame.

name: Painting of a Sledgehammer
description: A painting of a sledgehammer on an easel. I guess that's all there really is to say on the matter.

name: Inheritance Collection
description: Basically, four games, each a remake of a book. Games are based off of the books, but have the game mechanics of DMC.

name: Mithril Skateboard
description: Rest easy in the knowledge that you took the skateboard feat back in middle school.

name: Soul-slicing Obsidian Electroskull Octawand
description: The shadowy power of this bone wand can slice directly at your enemies' souls. The eight amethyst skulls on the handle flash with magical energy.

name: Eldritch Skull of the Outerwinds
description: This charred skull has strange eldritch symbols carved into it, and a rather large blue gem set into its forehead. It gives off chilling breezes.

name: Hunk Rump: The Gathering
description: You must tap the ASS CARD to deploy one of your mightiest beefcakes, the legendary COPPER SKINNED BRAWNSTUD.

name: Card-board
description: A deck of playing cards made from... cardboard? Who thought this would be a good idea?

name: Fiery Soul-rending Obsidian Skullectric Bonewand
description: A wand carved out of a single piece of pitch-black bone. The skull decorations glow with heat and flashes of black lightning. It is said that one strike of this wand's power can sever a soul from its body.

name: Jolly Rainbow Flag of Christmas Killing
description: Nothing like celebrating the holidays with homicide.

name: Example Sanic-Stamps
description: Make an example of your enemies with these 2FAST4U stamps.

name: Millenium Puzzle
description: A golden puzzle shaped like a pyramid. Legends say it contains the soul of an ancient Egyptian pharaoh with ridiculous hair.

name: Yggdrasil\'s Leaf
description: A giant leaf radiating with the energy of a mythical universe. Also appears to have safeguarding against majyyks most foul.

name: Prince of Seuss God Tier Outfit
description: On a far-away planet near Skaia Sublime, Theodore Giesel was Prince of the rhyme. A nice little poet. He was skilled. he had beat. The consorts were friendly. They were really quite sweet. The poet had everything a poet might need, And he was quite happy. Quite happy indeed.

name: Mage of Heart Prom Dress
description: A sparkling dress made from some old pajamas. You'll be the most beautiful mage at the prom with this dress!

name: War Hoodie of the Sliced Apples
description: Your battle-hardened Apple Hoodie has seen so many strifes, the apples have been sliced into delicious bite-sized pieces.

name: Magic Cards
description: Every time you draw from this deck, it transforms into a different weapon depending on the card. They're all basic weapons, but you can't help but feel awesome if you draw a halberd or a machine gun.

name: Pimpin\' Gloves
description: May these overly bejeweled gloves keep your hands strong in case you need to smack an imp that you know is holding out on you.

name: Blue Ecto Juice
description: You mixed some slime into your apple juice. Now it tastes gross. Eww!

name: White Broom of Code Enhancment
description: This powerful broom can adjust the fabric of reality, infusing itself with the power of the enemies you defeat.

name: Crouching Serpent Concealed Broom-Gun
description: This classy shmancy broom isn't just for show. Not only is it's compressed oak perfect for bludgeoning, but it has a musket mechanism concealed in it's handle making it a lethal rifle at close range.

name: Soggy & Saggy Sacks of Bear Bear Buttery Buns: Failure Flavour
description: Your dreams are crushed.

name: Green Sun Hardwood Floor Sweeper
description: Good for sweeping floors to a spotless glimmer and for laying down a room full of Charlies with an irradiating array of maintained fire, this closed-quarters automatic broom-gun is a must for any host hoping to tidy up the loose ends that float through one's abode.

name: Mastermind\'s Harp-bow
description: This harp-bow once wielded by a legendary god has ascended and taken on a life of its own.  Luckily enough you are much more intelligent than it and can wield it.

name: Tennis Racket
description: A shiny new tennis racket! Maybe you can serve up some asses with this!

name: Phoenixfire-Smoked Bacon-Flavoured Rock Candy
description: This stick of flaming rock candy can be used to direct the smell of perfectly smoked and cured bacon at your enemies, causing them to immediately die of sheer longing.

name: The King in Yellow
description: This play brings misfortune and insanity to all who read it. Performing it may in fact be a ritual for the summoning of a horrible eldritch abomination.

name: Soul-searing Obsidian-Skull Bonewand of the Thunderbird
description: This wand of ebony bone is said to absorb the souls of everything it is used against. The shaft radiates fierce heat, and flickering lightning sparks at the tip.

name: Terraria: Collector\'s Edition
description:
A nice game about mining, crafting, building, and slaying monsters.
I bet nobody heard of that concept before!

name: Terraria: Sanic Edition
description: Now featuring new exclusive items such as: WAY2FAST HERMES BOOTS and SANIC R.

name: Hat Full of Sky
description: This witch's hat looks like it is decorated with the entire cosmos. Obviously it isn't, since that would be a massive hat.

name: Vegetable Killer
description: These were used by former Fruit-Squad member Limey Mike. The bullets can obliterate veggies.

name: Road Blazer
description: A black leather blazer ensures that you strike fear into the hearts of others, even at the most formal business occasions.

name: Creeper Crochet Needles
description: KEEP THAT AWAY!! THEY COULD EXPLODE!

name: Holy Smitewriter
description: And on the eight day, God said, "Dang, if no one writes any of this down these dumb people will forget all about me." And so He created the Holy Smitewriter, so that the story of His creation would be recorded, and the evildoers who spread other tales would be punished. And God looked upon the manuscript that was written, and saw that it was good.

name: Hatarang
description: Fedora Shmora. Every one knows that razor sharp bendy hats are the way to go.

name: Perfect Party Invitation
description: The Perfect Host is throwing the Perfect Party and YOU are invited. When you point this card towards your enemies they are incinerated by Green Flames. Oddly, this never happens when you try to read it, as if the card knew whether you are trying to read it or use it as a weapon.

name: Sugarcoat
description: A coat coated with sugar.

name: Pumpkin Party in Sea Hitler\'s Water Apocalypse
description: This flag shudders with the life powers granted to a certain Thief, and is decorated with her symbol. Holding it, you feel )(ighly powerful an ready to krill, yo

name: Cat Ear Fedora
description: A fedora with cat ears sticking out of it. Class-waii!

name: Boston Blade Scarf
description: You should probably never actually wear this on your neck. It's pretty sharp.

name: Light Scope
description: It amplifies light to the point where it is hot and blinding, then focuses it through the lens like a giant magnifying glass. Only this one is capable of burning bigger things than just ants.

name: Angry Science
description: With this syringe, you can be a literal mad scientist as you go around angrily stabbing people and injecting them with this aggravating toxin.

name: Fiery Soul-severing Obsidian Scienceskull Electrobonewand
description: A wand carved out of a single piece of pure black bone. Thanks to the power of Modern Science, this wand can immolate your enemies, electrocute them with magical lightning, and sever their souls all at the same time.

name: Stab-Happy Narwhal Float
description: This big inflated narwhal with a sharpened prodding horn is more akin to a torture device than a harmless prank. Doesn't make it any less hilarious, though.

name: Mad Sturgeon\'s Euthanizer
description: The bloated narwhal's horn is now filled with a deadly intoxicant, and the animal has taken on a somewhat maniacal expression. This is the face of someone who has gone off the deep end and is enjoying every minute of it.

name: Dual Uniknives
description: Two knives made of unicorn horns. They should have learned the magic of self-defense instead.

name: Shitty God Tier Shirt-Kit
description: Now all you need is to slap on some color and you can attend conventions looking like your favorite god tier player.

name: Vexitellum Major
description: This axeflag is composed of stars, shining in your hand. The gods themselves once used this to smite their enemies. Probably.

name: Wind Spear
description: Not sure what hurts more, the stabbing point or the gale-force winds coming out of the point.

name: Penguin-Themed PlayStation Controller
description: As the name suggests, it's a PlayStation controller with the color scheme of a penguin. It's a bit fuzzy, too.

name: Beatdown (Strider Style)
description: This flag pulsates with the power of time itself. You feel its sick beats coursing through your veins. When you wave it, ripples in the time-space continuum seem to emanate from its path.

name: Phasmalumen Phlag
description: This flag is composed of stars and has the souls of ancient ghosts coursing through it.

name: Hat Full of Life
description: This hat looks like it is illustrated with the life stories of every single thing that has ever existed in a series of arcane and beautiful symbols in an unknown language. Obviously, it's doesn't have everything's life stories, since that would be a massive hat.

name: Condescension Fabuloso
description: The outfit worn by )(er Imperious Condescension )(----ERS----ELF!! its glubbin fierce

name: Hammer Thrower
description: ...Why would someone make a bow that fires sledgehammers?  This thing is almost impossible to use!

name: Sledgerocket Shot
description: A bow that shoots sledgehammers. Fortunately, said sledgehammers are also propelled by fireworks. Unfortunately, those hammers still weigh a ton.

name: SciFi Tele-Laserrator
description: It looks like something straight out of a SciFi film. Don't ever look straight down the barrel.

name: Golden Bookhammer
description: Because what every successful hammer needs is a book shoved on it.

name: Flags Covered in Blood
description: The blood in question, however, is troll blood: it's an adorable shipping flag made by a certain Rogue!

name: SBurb Gate Starflag
description: This flag is made of stars and is emblazoned with the trademark spirograph gate symbol.

name: Death de Flamingo
description: They all laughed at you when you bought a garden flamingo; now you get to laugh at their corpses.

name: Possessed Journal
description: This is just what you needed. Now you can have haunted nightmares of those who trod in the game of SBuRB before you - wait...! What was that sound!!??

name: Crystal Skull
description: Why do you even have this? Isn't it like, some rare super-valuable treasure or something? Oh well, finders keepers, you guess.

name: The Flashpot
description: For all those times your stage show just needs a bit of pyrotechnics - now conveniently stored in a guitar. Sparklers sizzle with every strum; firecrackers pop with every chord. Shame it always smells like sulfur.

name: Spinning Pin-needles
description: These seem kind of dangerous to hold, but you happen to be a badass that kicks logic to the curb.

name: Skullgirls [TCG] Players Deck
description: Warning: Must be 18 years or older to purchase without a parent's consent. You will be asked to present your completed released-reliability form and ID at the register. Playing this card game is not guaranteed to make any of your dreams actually come true. Skullgirls is not liable for deaths caused by playing this card game.

name: Lacrosse: The Musical
description: Ever wanted to rip some sweet clarinet jams, but play lacrosse at the same time? Fear no more, nerdiest of nerds, for your time for both music and sports has come! (Warning: Actual use of this in lacrosse could cause this item to break.)

name: Wandering Staple Serial Prophet
description: Armed with its trusty map, this staple remover has taken to the planets to spread its gospel of peace and friendship between staplers and staple removers to as many as possible - and it will convert others by force if need be.

name: Menorah
description: Let's be honest, you only really know about this candle holder because you were made to sing songs about the oil or whatever in chorus class... Unless you really do follow the faith, in which case this is now very awkward.

name: Soul-reaving Darktime Skull Bonewand of the Thunderbird
description: A wand carved out of a single piece of bone that crackles with eldritch energies. It is said that one strike can sever souls from bodies and age them to dust.

name: Throwing Star of David
description: A throwing star in the shape of the identity symbol of the Jewish faith. You'd normally be offended by a religious symbol being used as a weapon but you're too distracted by the fact there's a 'Jew-jitsu' joke in there somewhere...

name: Glittering Monochrome Wands
description: An unnatural pair of wands seething with intertwined light and dark enyrjjies. This internal conflict makes them prone to lashing out.

name: Sledgescyther
description: Its a Scythe...but MUCH heavier. If you can lift it, it should deal massive damage.

name: Sharp Squiddly Hula Hoop
description: Each tentacle is a blade of death. Cuddly, hoopy death.

name: Assistant to the Dersite Throne
description: You now take your Royal Dump in peace, for no right-minded defecation will even THINK about clogging your "throne" ever again.

name: Limey Mike Head
description: Limey Mike was once part of the Fruit-Squad, until they disbanded. However, their debt with the Veggie Mafia wasn't over, wear this if you dare.

name: Bedazzled Spear
description: A spear used by a hunter that was drafted into the royal army during war times. This hunter came to be known as "The Hunter" for his ability to pursue the enemy was unparalleled,but alas, he was killed by a bear.

name: Four-Wheeled Pizza Cutter
description: The invention that revolutionized cutting giant pizzas forever.

name: Tripool Axecue
description: Kill your opponents in pool games and strifes with this nifty cue! (Hopefully not literally, but that can be arranged, too.)

name: Flaming Baton
description: Perfect for fire poi.

name: Shadow Truncheon
description: No pep squad, or nosy detectives, can beat you as you swing around the power of the shadows themselves.

name: Amethyst Pillow Sheild
description: A less pretty, more impractical, pretty impractical shield.

name: Torrent Crasher
description: This weapon is liable to destroy the very fabric of your enemies existence, provided it gets the fuel required.

name: Scythe of the Blood Apocalypse
description: This scythe appears to be made of Blood, and it radiates a faint echo of the Life energy that was sacrificed in its conception. Such a weapon could only be wielded by a particular variety of hero. A hero of... void. Yes, you're absolutely positive that Void is the perfect aspect for this weapon.

name: Dual Dragon Scales
description: This pair of knives kind of look like they are made from dragon scales, but on closer inspection, they are only replicas. Dragons aren't real, silly! Doesn't stop them from looking awesome, though.

name: Hammer of Yo-arthica
description: Forged by the metals from Winterhelm's greatest blacksmiths in the heat of Mt. Radicalia, the beauty of this potent one-handed hammer is practically unmatched.

name: Rocket Staff
description: Some would mistake this for a very thin, long rocket. Those people have no imagination. The ROCKET STAFF has all the class of Wizard Buck Rodgers, and half the casual racism!

name: Wallet Chain
description: This simple steel chain is an accessory that is used to keep one's wallet from being stolen, though it has seen some use as a fashion statement.

name: Sour Lime Candy Clobberer
description: This disgusting candy mace is way too many kinds of green. You aren't sure if it's because of the radiation, the flavor or the vomit from the unlucky fellow who tried to taste it.

name: Shit-Fuckinger Of The Void
description: It uses the power of the void to clear out clogs in toilets. It was used by magic plumbers during 1981-1999.

name: Shreck-it Ralph Festive Toast-A-Matic Ogre-Plunger
description: "He's gonna shrek it!"

name: Fuck-Shit Ralph Festive Toast-A-Matic Ogre-Plunger
description: A Wreck it Ralph/Shrek themed plunger-hammer-santa made of iron.  You have created an unholy mishmash of literally unrelated items.  It is beautiful.

name: Faygo - Santa\'s Choice Judgement Eggnog Flavor
description: So apparently carbonated eggnog is a thing. Drinking this makes you feel holy in a festive way, if that makes sense. Sadly does not include nutmeg.

name: Compcueshades
description: Pure white teashades, with no actual lenses, just white. And yet, somehow you can see through them, and beyond them... into a screen, in some omniscient technological sense.

name: Sawflag of the Starry Void Gate
description: This weightless flag shudders with the power of emptiness. The banner ripples with thousands of tiny sawteeth, ready to shred enemies to bits.

name: Fur Plunger
description: A plunger made from a fur rug. For the plumbers with class.

name: Bag of Holding
description: You gaze into the bag. Deeper. Deeper. Ok, that's enough.

name: Knifle
description: Is that a knife? A rifle? A knifle?!

name: Iron Giant Toy
description: A toy replica of a highly advanced and lovable robot. Press a button on his back, and he shoots lasers from his eyes! What's not to love?

name: Automagical Lego Giant
description: A massive automaton made out of magical, self-assembling Legos. It's actually kind of terrifying.

name: Star Claws
description: The heat from the micro-stars contained within these claws is enough to rend many softer materials cleanly apart on contact. Imagine what it could do with some real force applied!

name: Ball Pen Wand of the 8th Dimension
description: It writes with the stars, but for some reason it only writes the number 8. As a weapon, it can travel through time and space!

name: Brolancing Yo-Nuke
description: This weapon seems to be capable of directing a nuclear blast, while balancing it with a giant hat energy shield.

name: Squiddleteir Mage Cosplay
description: A Mage cosplay complete with wings and tentacles, all made out of soft and comfortable recycled Squiddle plushies.

name: amor of the GROEN SHORT
description: ALSO the aurmor,,, GLOWNS IN THE DARK

name: Geno Hoodie
description: This is a hoodie with a blue cape thing with a yellow collar. The hood has a weird yellow symbol on it and...kind of resembles a beanie, actually. This is kind of a weird hoodie.

name: Muse\'s Strings
description: An instrument from the goddesses themselves. The heavenly sounds produced make it a shame to use this as a weapon.

name: Mermaid Angel Cosplay
description: With this on, you'll look just like a mermaid angel! Which, ironically, would probably be unable to swim due to its wings and unable to fly due to its heavy fish tail. You can't deny its majesty, though.

name: Jellybabies
description: Jellybabies. You're sure you've seen a Doctor offer you one, but that doesn't matter. They're good anyway!

name: The Cubed Time Stop Throwing Clocks
description: You know what they say, time flies when you're having fun, except for, you know, the people getting hit by your clocks.

name: The Octocubed Time Stop Throwing Atacamite Clocks
description: Throwing a clock in someone's face and freezing the expression of surprise not enough for you? Now it comes with a new shiny green paint job and a cube with 2 added sides.

name: Love, Chunibyo & Other Delusions Vol.1
description: Volume 1 of the Love, Chunibyo & Other Delusions light novel.

name: Self-powered Computer
description: It's a desktop pc, with a power pack built onto it! Now you can take it wherever you go! Although, it's pretty heavy and bulky..

name: Light Energy Sphere
description: This sphere seems to be made out of an abundance of light energy itself and glows with an intense white light that fills you with courage and hope.

name: Dark Energy Sphere
description: This sphere seems to be made out of an abundance of dark energy itself and has pitch black mist that fills you with anger and jealousy.

name: Orb of Light
description: This smooth but rocky looking diamond ball glows with an intense light and is filled with an exceptional amount of light energy.

name: Orb of Darkness
description: This smooth but rocky looking obsidian ball gives off pitch black mist and is filled with an exceptional amount of dark energy.

name: Orb of Dawn
description: This smooth looking ball made out of some unknown grey gem is filled with an intense grey light and giving off grey mist that is filled with an exceptional amount of both light and dark energy that was somehow combined together. When you hold this sphere you can feel a sense of calmness and peace, as if the balance was restored in you.

name: Sanic-Possessed Fuck-Shit Ralph Festive Toast-A-Matic Ogre-Plunger
description: It was possessed by an evil hege hoooge spirit, use it IF YOU DARE....

name: The Pen is Mightier than the Bladekind
description: And lo, though the blades tried to gain admission with all their strength, the mighty Moderators did thus summon with pen in hand the power of the legendary Suspension Flag. So thus the Pen was declared mightier than the Bladekind.

name: Gotta Go Fast Hatarang
description: A hat-boomerang based on your favourite hege-hooge.

name: Fruit-Squad Poster
description: A poster showing members of the Fruit-Squad. You aspire to be as badass as them.

name: Dress of Wu Ao Shi
description: You now have the dress of the mighty Wu Ao Shi, pirate queen. Now you just need a bow and some mad martial arts skills and you'll be set.

name: SANIC R
description:
Play this amazing racing game featuring your favourite sanic characters, such as:
SANIC, TALS, KNAKLES, AND AME.

name: Unholy Smutwriter
description: And on a lonely night to himself, God said, "LET THERE BE SMUT." He proceeded to create the Unholy Smutwriter. It was a device capable of writing the smuttiest fan fiction imaginable.

name: Rocket Powered Dronkey Wings
description: Now you can pretend you're the freakish offspring of a donkey and a dragon!

name: Ol\' Mary
description: Limey Mike's favourite gun. It uses powerful plutonium bullets that instantly remove vegetables from existence, however some Veggie Mafia members are resistant to its blast.

name: Dawn\'s Octet
description: This legendary octet of eight sided die is now seeping with both combined energies of light and darkness. The moment before you roll these dice is just the calm before the storm, ALL of the storms.

name: Sweetened Green Tea
description: By adding sugar to the point where it's more sugar than tea, you've destroyed all hopes of it ever being healthy again.

name: Your Health Vial
description: This will hurt them more than it will hurt you. Not by much, mind you.

name: Battle Cross
description: A common subweapon used by the Belmont family, a holy cross that can be thrown to tear though the undead monsters in your way and somehow have it fly back to you...you aren't sure how, that shape can't be aerodynamic...

name: Doritos Locos Thanatos
description: Cut your opponents down with the powers of spices, cheese, and Death itself!

name: Piercing Hardlight Ch8ned Ch8nbl8ds Launcher of the Horrorterrors
description: This chainsaw, when shot, fires 8 hardlight chained chainswords, though how they're attached, they aren't exactly usable as swords anymore.

name: Piercing Green Hardlight Ch8ned Ch8nbl8ds Launcher of the Horrorterrors
description: Now you can rip your enemies to shreds, with all the power of the green sun!  Okay, maybe not ALL the power, but it sounds way cooler that way.

name: DeCrapplication.axe
description: A fearsome weapon of the modern era, this axe now comes with a motorized plunger function.

name: Soul Totality
description: An opalescent, dual headed bearded axe, with highlights of the colors of Heart on the weapon. An extremely dangerous and powerful weapon on it's own, capable of keeping souls in check. Yet made even more powerful by the souls of 8 universes in the forms of green die along the base of the blades.

name: Dead Horrorterror in a Jar
description: The fact that this thing is dead, safely tucked within in a jar, AND is one of the alleged "smallest of the small" doesn't make you feel any better, and you won't until it is, say, SEVERAL THOUSAND LIGHTYEARS OF WHEREVER YOU ARE CURRENTLY STANDING AT ANY GIVEN MOMENT

name: Evil Eye Plush
description: A hideous, terrifying creature of many tentacles and a single piercing eye, now in huggable plush form.

name: Rocket Star Skates
description: These powerful stylish skates have rockets and wheels and shoot stars.. that you can, um, fly/skate to?

name: Overseer Moderator Penguinview
description: While wearing this over your face, you perceive everything in black and white. You feel compelled to mark everything you see with colored flags. The ones you mark with green get their color back, the grey ones vanish do nothing, the yellow ones turn green, and the red ones vanish.

name: A Sharp Dragon\'s Breath
description: Question: How does one inflict pain on an enemy in the most gruesome way possible? Answer: Shooting flaming axe heads.

name: Dual Dementias
description: Sickly black wands, seeming to pulse with the power of madness. Once owned by a Demon Queen who went mad with her own power, and killed herself in a fit of hallucinations. These wands can bring their enemies to  hallucinate with the sound of the mad queen's laughter.

name: Deck of Cards / War Chest
description: Perfect for things like 52 pickup or holding maps of your enemies' mansions. Nothing eyebrow-raising, though.

name: Terezi Owns
description: When you attack something with this flag, it seems to go blind. You feel the power of a certain mind player pulsing through your nerves.

name: Hyper Iron Princess Suit of Draconic Might
description: Now crush your foes with the grace of a princess and the might of draconic power armor!

name: Outerwinds Belt with Eldritch Buckle
description: A tentacled Sphinx breaths cursed winds out of your waist. Because that's not at all ominous.

name: Banhammer
description: One strike with this hammer is enough to stop a troublemaker in their tracks, silencing them for good so that the multiverse can continue to function peacefully.

name: Bladekind Banhammer
description: During the tumultuous bladekind submission war of '14, one of the almighty Devs looked down upon the debacle and decided to end it, leaving the forging of a new almighty weapon to a young player. What they made went down in history as the strongest weapon against dumb submissions and enemies alike, and now it's within your grasp.

name: Thunder-Charged Gem
description: This gem is crackling with electrical energy.  Shockingly helpful.

name: Advanced Guide: Dreamshouting
description: Apparently this book teaches you to shout in your dreams. It's kinda useless now though due to Prospit and Derse.

name: Wikidice: The Dice Anyone Can Edit
description: By combining Wikipedia's high editing powers with the Fluorite Octet, perfect rolls are no longer light-player exclusive; all it takes is one click and a poor citation to guarantee a maximum damage roll.

name: The Tri-Cod
description: A trident with the prongs replaced with plush members.

name: Big Ball of Cash
description: A huge wad of cash formed into a ball. Use it to bludgeon your enemies to death, crush their bones, or have a night out to town with the guys. Your treat, of course.

name: Multicolored Ball of Yarn
description: This pretty ball of yarn is much better than that old one. It's got every color of the rainbow, the entire gray scale, and even some weird colors like gamboge and fallow.

name: Thorny Staff
description: Ouch! Prickles everywhere! This is sure to hurt someone.

name: The Time-Nullifier
description: This boomerang has bristled mounted all over it for better cleaning capabilities, and the ever spinning cog wheel mounted to  it seems to make it spin faster through the air. Be careful with it though, when you scrub things with it, they tend to disassemble themselves.

name: Shadowchine Gun
description: A gun with the power to wield darkness. Make your enemies shake in your wake.

name: Expert Guide: Summoning The Bling King
description: A complex and annoying guide to summon The Bling King, it requires a whole load of gold for him to even appear. Since you'd need to be so rich to perform the ritual, it's recommended you just hit imps with this instead.

name: Magnemite Cosplay Ears
description: By the force of magnetism, both of Magnemite's magnets are floating above your head.

name: Kalos Region Gym Badges
description: After training your Pokmon to the best of their ability, you have these 8 badges to show for your commitment!  Each gives you a special boost!

name: Armor of the Ghillie
description: Your Kendo Armor is now upgraded with this stealthy grass shit. HOORAY!

name: Long Trumpet
description: It kinda works as a trumpet. You blow through the long tube thing, you press buttons, sound come out the other side. Only thing now is, it is very long. You could sneak up to someone and blow into their ear very loudly from a distance. Or you could bludgeon them over the head with it.

name: Wizard\'s First Spell
description: It looks just like a wand, but if you try cast a spell, all you'll get is bubbles.

name: Bloody Stamp
description: There are now multiple screws in the bottom of the stamp, so you can now stamp people while causing even bigger damage!

name: Achievement Hunter Poster
description: A poster that makes the AH crew look like a boy band. The poster includes Gavin, Michael, Geoff, Ray, Jack, and Ryan.

name: Danmaku Wand
