description: This fancy new wand is now empowered with the magics of creating danmaku. The fakeness of this item has risen to new levels!

name: Naginata Tetrixspear
description: Some might say that "Naginata Tetrixspear" is redundant. These people have never known the feeling of raw, holy, demonic, Japanese power run through them.

name: Expert Guide: Summoning Sevith
description: It's a book about summoning the mythical codewarrior Sevith. The book is way too complex and hard to read, there's no way you're gonna summon this guy by yourself.

name: Advanced Teaching: Bombs and Evil
description: It's a book about teaching people how to use bombs and be evil. Fun!

name: The Cod-dent
description: It's a cod piece with 3 prongs of a trident on top. Very good penetration, if you know what I mean.

name: Prospit and Derse Globes
description: Did you really stick them together? You absolute idiot. Go sit in the corner and think about the absolute idiocy you just performed.

name: Set of Poisoned Wood Darts
description: These things were really drowned in poison, weren't they? The wood's all damp and they smell kinda funky. You're really going to want to wash your hands each time you use these.

name: Gaming Calculator
description: In your spare time you've programmed your graphing calculator with a few simple games. Look at the pixels move!

name: Senator Lemonsnout
description: This guy seems to reek of deceit...if that's even possible for a stuffed animal. But you can not help but want to hug him! Sometimes you think you're crazy for playing with dolls, especially alien ones.

name: SBuARGH GUIDE ii: the CHEATENING
description: htese COODES... their are a myTSERY... WHOM CAN KNOWN WHAT HTEY DO???////

name: Winged Toothbrush
description: Don't know why you would make this, but this toothbrush has wings now. What now?

name: Einstein M. c2 Solar Gun
description: It may be a single-shot, but one shot is all you should need to wipe out most underlings, summoning up a gigantic explosion supercharged by the green sun itself. Is also useful for lighting up dark outer regions of space. (Warning: Keep out of reach of children.)

name: Pure 100% North Polian Apple Juice
description: You're not sure if you should drink it since it's glowing... do they even have apples in the north pole?

name: Holy LightSpaff
description: This spoon staff shoots silver lasers. You're not sure why but it makes you feel like a benevolent spoon diety is watching over your every move. Comes with a matching pin.

name: A True Magician\'s Top Hat
description: This night blue top hat with silver stars on it is infused with 100% legit magical energy. No fakey illusionism. Just pure, awesome magic.

name: Jar of Breath
description: A blue and yellow jar containing a sweet invigorating breeze. A single whiff will make you feel one with the wind.

name: Breath of Courage
description: A strand of wind, from some place nobody is sure, caught in a jar. When you listen closely you can hear the whispers of a beautiful Sylph.

name: Breath Of Fast
description: It's a white mysterious foggy cloud in a bottle. No, it's not magic cocaine.

name: Snack Time Eraser
description: This item erases snack time? That can't be a good thing can it? At least you'll be a bit leaner while you fight some imps.

name: Quarter-Degree-Burn Piano Organ
description: The refrains of "No Quarter" melt the faces of adversaries.

name: Data Structures for Assholes
description: A book that teaches you total bullshit. Why did you ever grab this book? Wielding it even makes you feel like an asshat.

name: Stack Data for Dummies
description: This book is much better than the previous incarnation (The sticker even claims 99% less assholery) which was a pain to deal with. Though you can't help but feel it's secretly mocking you for all that you don't know.

name: Magical Friendship Knife-Needles
description: A pair of sharp, thin blades in the rough shape of unicorn horns. You suppose this is one way to get the point of friendship across.

name: Expert Guide: Miracle Weapon Handling
description: It will be a miracle if you can understand how to use this damn thing. It also has some lewd comics on the last pages.

name: Armor of the Heart
description: This armor is made of a dark pink-ish metal and has a heart-shaped crystal symbol on the left part of the chestplate, just where one's heart would be. When worn, the crystal glows. Does it mean this armor's strength actually comes from inside of you? Or does it simply react to being worn? Who knows.

name: Advanced Guide: Semi-Supernatural Candy Liquor Mixing
description: It's a guide on how to mix together sorta supernatural candy liquor, only a mad man would make these strange elixirs.

name: Rose Collar
description: It might be uncomfortable to wear because of the thorns, but one must suffer for the sake of beauty.

name: Idiot\'s Guide: Summoning The Cow Demon Lord
description: It's a simple guide on how to summon the Cow Demon Lord, of course nobody even dared to summon him because he would destroy the world. Even though you're kinda iffy on summoning him, the book is quite heavy and could act as a nice weapon.

name: How Those Canadian Cows Stole McDonald\'s
description: A story about a bunch of canadian cows taking over a nearby McDonald's. What kind of maniac thought of this story?!

name: Easter Egg
description: It's an egg that is hidden around places during a holiday named Easter. Looks like nobody found this one until you came along!

name: Nickelnomicon
description: It's a spooky magic book about coins, not really a great read as it can turn your eyes into pennies.

name: Heaven\'s Plumber Coin
description: This coin is said to contain the soul of a red garments wearing plumber who can jump really high. The plumber can unlock the inner good inside a person, by teaching them to jump ridiculously high.

name: SANIC DA GAEM
description: FIGHT OOGMAN IN THIS WAY PAST COOL GAEM, PLAY AS AMAZING CHARACTERS SACH AS, SANIC, TIALS, KNICLES, AND AME. RUN AROUND IN OVER DA TOOP CORSES, BE VERY FAST, AND HAVE FOON!

name: God Blood-Drenched Wool Jumper
description: It's a wool jumper dipped in the blood of the elder gods, it gives you amazing powers of the gods themselves and allows you to edit the world as you please.

name: Skate n\' Spray
description: This skateboard emits a cloud of painful gas as it passes. When using this device, always remember to keep your eyes closed and to avoid inhaling the gas.

name: Quantum Recipe Finder
description: This powerful computer uses qubits in order to calculate every single recipe in your possession at once. However, due to the technology being experemental, its a tad bit slow.

name: SBurb Recipe Supercalculator
description: This insanely powerful supercalculator takes literally every item in your storage and computes possible codes. It generates up to 10 codes but takes quite a while to run calculations.

name: Magical Radioactive Skull
description: This skull... [You stare into it too long.]

name: Space Dictionary
description: Not exactly useful seeing as everyone in the universe apparently speaks English.

name: The Mad King\'s Crown
description: Wear the crown of the mad King! Be careful though, try not to go mad yourself and go on any killing sprees. Actually, that might be good in your case.

name: Red Formal Dress
description: A flaming red dress that will make you look hot as hell, cool as ice, and a walking target.

name: Homestuck Disk One
description: Wait, what's this CD? Well, whatever it is, it does seem valuable, so it may not be in your best interests to scratch it.

name: Flying Cards
description: It's a deck of cards with strings attached so you can fling them out and retract them - just like a yo-yo! Seems it might lead to awful paper cuts, though.

name: Crystal Powered Bow
description: A fragile bow that is most likely the worst option to use, but can be good in a worse scenario.

name: shIT FUCKRE...
description: How dare you alchemize this abomination...

name: Trumpgun
description: Giving you an all-new, deadly feel to playing the trumpet, it's the Trumpgun! When you play, shotgun shells come flying out at your enemy!

name: Steel Feather Duster
description: A feather duster with a steel handle for the more industrially minded.  It's a good thing that the feathers aren't made of steel, too.

name: Glow-in-the-Dark Feather Duster
description: A small, pastel green feather duster, perfect for night-time cleaning.  Just don't forget to charge it first!

name: Drivel
description: A shovel with a spinning head. Good for drilling holes in imps. Alternatively, a synonym for nonsense.

name: French Feather Duster
description: A small black feather duster with a white handle, literally right out of a French maid's arsenal of cleaning supplies.

name: Festive Feather Duster
description: A large feather duster with rainbow feathers and a glittery handle.  What could be more fun to clean with?!

name: Mop
description: Just a regular everyday mop for cleaning tiles and such, though it seems worn from use. Maybe you should get a new one soon...or you would've, if your home planet hadn't been destroyed.

name: Moon Plunger
description: It's a plunger made out of rocks IN SPAAAAAACE.

name: Mail Plunger
description: Used by postal service janitors, these things were quickly got rid of because they didn't plunge as well as other regular plungers. But if you need to receive mail at the same time...

name: Nerf Plunger-shot
description: Why Nerf made this thing is beyond your comprehension. At least you got a thing to put in your Nerf gun collection, right?

name: Old Boot on a Stick
description: Good job. You took your boot and your club and fused them together. With grist and everything, instead of just putting the thing in the other thing.

name: Generator Radio
description: This is still really heavy, and you can't hear any of the music over the sound of the generator. Still, it can play all day.

name: Hunk Rump
description: Let's make some elves cry.

name: Magic the Gathering Cards
description: The oldest of all Trading Card Games. If you focus hard enough on these cards, maybe you can actually cast them. All you'll need is a little Magic.

name: 98.99% Pure Magic
description: Somehow you've managed to capture the essence of not-fake-at-all magic within a captchalogue card. Refining this further could prove dangerous, so the impurities will have to remain for the moment. Now if only this was actually usable...

name: Bloodlust Snakemail
description: This mail is made of red scales, for a kaleidoscope of hues, from crimson to blood red. Wearing it makes you want to see blood very badly.

name: Omnipotent Sendifier
description: The most useful piece of English technology. Using the power of the Green Sun, this Sendifier can send items of any size. Unlike the Crocker knock-off, this Sendifier is a dark green with a flashing Sendifier symbol.

name: Tails Doll
description: It's said that this doll is possessed, evil, and murderous. But that's probably bullshit.

name: Sanic-Possessed New Age Fuck-Shit Ralph Festive Toast-A-Matic Ogre-Plunger
description: A sanic, shrek, and wreck-it ralph endorsed festive toaster plunger-hammer, but people also talk about it being useful in new age healing, what a load of bull.

name: Tomato
description: A semi-edible vegetable, it seems red and ripe, it would be silly to eat it by itself.

name: Aperture Science Quantum Powered Virtual Cleaner
description: Even when the broom it self is completely virtual, it cleans nicely, but it also gives off head-aches as you use it.

name: Fluorite Radioactive Thorned Lucky Cosby Cod-Tar
description: A cod piece shaped guitar based on bill-cosby, it also has radioactive thorns on it, as well as giant pure luck.

name: Blue Ecto-Stimpotionpak
description: Three types of healing going through your veins all at once must feel awesome.

name: Green Claw Spade Blades of the Sun
description: Glowing green claws shaped like spades, drawing from two sources of unimaginable power: The Green Sun, and raw slickness.

name: Holy Hammerizer
description: The glowing fuel cells, now incorporated into the hammer, leak unquantifiable amounts of radiation from the head, that will now, leave your foes shrieking in firey green pain. Also serves as a nice torch.

name: Fairy Godmother\'s Wand
description: Legend has it that this wand has the power to turn mice into horses, pumpkins into carriages, and overall grant miracles. Yeah, the fakeness attribute on this is through the roof. Pretty, though.

name: Colossal Grimdark Scissors of the Squiddle Bishops
description: Those who followed the order of the squiddle a received greater power from them. lost for the ages but rediscovered now. The uncountable years have done little to dull these devilishly sharp shears. They are very large but inexplicably still one handed and darker than black, just like your soul.

name: Censor Bar
description: DISCLAIMER: This is not fit for viewing by the public.

name: Aperture Science Portal Piercing Devices
description: These look just like regular darts, except with an orange/blue theme. What are so special about these things?

name: Firey-Swingy-Axe
description: A staff, with a chain connected to the top and a burning axe head connected to that. Be careful not to hit yourself.

name: 3D Rose-vision
description: Take a look through your new 3D ROSE-VISION GLASSES! They don't actually do anything though, they're just roses shaped like glasses with the 3D lenses in them.

name: Dragon Staff
description: This staff has taken on an elegant and intimidating dragon shape. It can't spit fire or anything, but it can withstand a surprising amount of heat.

name: Tesla\'s Blackcoil Deck
description: Who'da thought Tesla was a gambler? Better yet, he never lost. Turns out he always insisted on using his own deck, and whenever he was about to lose he'd simply give an up close and personal demonstration of alternating flows.

name: Staff of Faith
description: A staff that demands complete faith from its user. Earn your holy knowledge by using this staff!

name: Sweater Vest
description: A close-fitting waist-length garment.

name: Scyfesaber of the Ninja
description: You see a hopeful green crackling as you wield it's felt hilt and cut through practically anything from wheat to weapons. Also, you can hide any part of it by hoping it goes and comes back.

name: Rick Astley Dress
description: Wearing this dress makes you no stranger to love. It lets you know the rules and so do I. Your team-mates will never give you up, never gonna let you down, never gonna tell a lie and hurt you.

name: Inky Spring Water
description: Why did you do this, this was a terrible idea. It's dark and murky. Only an idiot would drink this.

name: Black Rose / Green Sun
description: This flag shudders with the powers of the dark horrorterrors that sit beyond the veil. As you hold it, you hear them whispering, though it seems they are discussing a certain Seer not in your session.

name: Disk Guide to the Furthest Ring
description: This thing is absolutely awful. How can a disk even map a realm that defies the physics of space and time? Besides, when you load the disk, all you get is a black screen and a horrible aura.

name: Turntop
description: These allow for convenient computing on the go! They also probably has weird time powers, too.

name: Super Dragon Plush
description: Hell yes, you are convinced this is what Yoshi was meant to do. By unlocking his true dragon potential, your little plush now spits out fireballs. And it flies.

name: Cellotop
description: Play music and contact players... it'll be awkward to access files though.

name: The Big Bang
description: Said to be the explosion that created the entire multiverse, you now wield it in your hand. You wonder if this thing creates pocket dimension or something since it birthed the multiverse, maybe that's where all the imps go after experiencing the wrath of its explosion.

name: Cymbolism
description: A pair of cymbals that when crashed together produce a voice that screeches different philosophical ideas from the ages that begin to infect any listener's mind rather than a brassy sound. Be sure to wear earplug as conflicting ideals infecting your mind can cause severe mental damage.

name: Cadet Cap
description: It's like a baseball cap, but nice and flat on top. Worn originally in various militaries.

name: Golden Tome of Sketchmagic
description: A magical book that brings your drawings to life.  Infinite possibilities, as long as you have a pencil.

name: Plastic cup
description: Well... Hopefully the you can either throw this really hard or the imps are allergic to plastic...

name: Brush of Dark Matters
description: Wielding this Paintbrush imbued by the dark power from beyond the farthest ring, you feel the tingle of space itself at your fingertips where you hold it, the paint on the tip warping space and matter around it incredibly.

name: iTimeshades
description: Now you have access to all of your apps while having the ability to travel through time with these sleek shades.

name: Skaianet Handheld Defense DeCrapplicator
description: Using this on the orange function opens a vacuum spirograph portal, but it only sucks in human waste. Using it on the blue function opens a spirograph portal that spews an infinite amount of literal shit. There is also an emergency hatchet installed on the side. You have only three options here, but you have a feeling that you will be using all of them. Often.

name: Skaia\'s Hope
description: You feel the luminescence of this weapon flow through you. An unimaginable hope fills you as your hands grip its handle. You feel as if you are holding Skaia itself, packed into 43 inches of cold hard metal. The tips are black and white. the base Blue and the handle Gold. This would be a perfect weapon for a Hero of Hope.

name: Corrupted DiscoSpark
description: This powerful artifact from the planet Cybertron turns anything it touches into a funkbot. It ruminats so muh power and groove  can be an orb and a cube at the sam time.

name: Merc\'s Machine Gun
description: This gun which was once owned by four (insane) mercenaries is now yours to use!

name: Horrorterror Statue
description: A statue of a horrendous cephalopodian creature from beyond the Furthest Ring.  Looking at it for too long makes you feel kind of queasy.

name: Reflective Nuclear Starsweeper
description: A broom of myth that has become reality in this age of technology.  Unfortunately, it doesn't sweep the stars away so much as it explodes them.  Ah, well, at least it leaves glittery dust in its wake.

name: Blood-drenched Magic Mirror and Flag Set
description: The Magic Mirror and Flag set is an essential piece of equipment for any young sailor or wizard.  This one seems to be drenched in blood, however...

name: The Bladekind Wars of 2014
description: This book has pages of text talking about a war in which a man named the Overseer suspended the creation of blades. Blacksmiths made a big deal out of it and started a war.

name: Laser Guided Deletion Darts
description: Used by admi- i mean, THE ELDER GODS, to delete items of annoyance.

name: Broken Unstable Pickaxe of Time
description: The Pickaxe of Time used to be used to remove precious bits of time. Then it became unstable. Then it broke. No one is quite sure what it does any more or even when it is.

name: Hand of Midas
description: Preserved through unknown magical means, the Hand of Midas is a weapon of greed, sacrificing animals to line the owner's pockets.

name: Scratchy Squeakybow
description: You can use this bow to shoot squeeky arrows that can make an opponent bleed! But mostly they just squeak off them harmlessly...

name: Role Playing For Dummies
description: The perfect solution to all things role playing! Now you can learn everything from what those little * mark thingies are, to how to make complicated smilies to denounce your mood.

name: Nepeta\'s Guide to RolePlaying
description: :33 < *ac says this is the purrfected guide to all things role playing. This guide will teach you every technique to purrfect your skills*

name: Nepeta\'s Old Fanfictions
description: You don't know how or why you purrssess this. But it makes you want to claw your eyes out. As will the enemies who suffer the wrath of this collection of horror inducing fictions.

name: Discodrill
description: Built for the party-loving handyman, this drill can turn any workroom into a disco.

name: Fine Leather Kicking Boots
description: These fine compact leather boots make kicking your foes into submission less of a chore!

name: Mickey Manta
description: A baseball bat that resembles a stubby manta ray. It hits hard and fast... like a normal baseball bat. Honestly the only reason why you did this was because it sounded like a cool idea in your head.

name: Ork big choppa
description: Used by the ork clan and some worshipers of the blood god, the ork big choppa is the battlesign for every ork clan.

name: Glitched Health Vial
description: There is no amount of alcohol you could have made to make this seem like a good idea. This even existing is endangering your health.

name: Flaming Blue Vortex Armor of Spectral Spectralness
description: A suit of armor made of a dark blue glass-like material, with spectral blue flames seeming to swirl like vortexes in it. It feels really weird to wear on, but whenever something hits it, a swirl of flames emerges from the armor and vaporizes it.

name: H.E.V. mark V Suit
description: Welcome to the H.E.V. mark V protective system, for use in hazardous environment conditions. High impact reactive armor activated. Atmospheric contaminant sensors activated. Vital sign monitoring activated. Automatic medical systems engaged. Defensive weapon selection system activated. Ammunition level monitoring activated. Communications interface online. Have a very safe day!

name: Capthca-Nailcannon
description: This nail cannon harnesses the surprising power of the Sylladex and its tendency to violently eject items that cannot fit. To reload, simply captchalogue more nails. Be careful, though, because that's also how you fire it.

name: Nailed Fedora
description: A fedora covered in nails, nice brutal fashion wear.

name: Chain Grenade
description: Each rung of the chain is its own grenade! When you whip someone in the face with it, first it'll hurt, then it'll explode! Then it'll hurt some more, but that goes without saying.

name: Curling Yo-Yo
description: It looks like a small curling iron attatched to a yo-yo. Burn the opponents with the power of a hair salon!

name: Speedrunner\'s Friend
description: The clock on the display started counting up when the first player entered your session, and records your fastest time for beating the Black King. Try to beat your friends' best times!

name: Universal Reckoning
description: This shotgun feels strange. Its two barrels are sharp black and white with pawns carved into the metal work. It feels. Like home?

name: Indestructable Hope Armor
description: Sporting the symbol of the Hope aspect, this armor is made out of one of the strongest materials known to man. In fact, this armor is so rigid that you might cause your attackers to lose all hope in inflicting damage to you.

name: Omnipotent\'s Guide: Summoning Drizzle Fo\' Shizzle the Drow Pimp
description: NOTE: Summoning the drow pimp is not a wise choice. He is the spirit of an evil pimp, he possesses his victims, completely taking over their mind, using them as puppets. Oh yeah, did i also mention dangerous purple pimp magic?

name: Dual Ranged Shot Gauntlets
description: A pair of bright gold gauntlets, which happen to have shotguns in them. Each shotgun fires large red explosive rounds. You can also wear them like bracelets when not in use!

name: Hammernade
description: Slamming your enemy is now even more damaging with the new Hammernade! (Warning: we are not responsible for any recoil damage you receive by using this item)

name: Grandmaster\'s Bow of Sledgerockets
description: There's a good chance that sledgehammers, fireworks, and chess pieces will make a powerful weapon. Or not. Which means that this is both a very good and very bad weapon. Won't know until you fire it.

name: Magykk Bow of The Abyss
description: For those who like bows and magic, but prefer a slightly darker outlook. This bow shoots magic wand arrows of pure dark magic, bound to ruin anyone's day if you hit them just right.

name: Stylus of Shredding
description: This thing is useless for drawing with, since it slices everything it touches. Like your tablet. Good job, idiot.

name: Latte
description: The smooth creaminess of the milk takes the bitter edge off of the coffee. The perfect drink for youth who are getting into the coffee scene, and Hipsters. Goddamn Hipsters.

name: Apple Juice Picket Protestor
description: A sign showing how you aren't willing to drink apple juice. Proudly wave this about as you inform and prevent the mischief of Howie Mandel.

name: Problem Sleuth\'s Pizza Slicer
description: Said to be the diplomacy master's own pizza cutter. It's called a Slicer, but that's purely for alliteration purposes.

name: Lily Pattern Gloves
description: These gloves are decorated in a style reminiscent of the exquisite flower. You don't really want to get these dirty, do you?

name: Pumpkin
description: What pumpkin? You have never seen such a squash around here. Though you have the vaguest sense that there was one right here...

name: Mark Nutt\'s Bow
description: The bow belonging to one of the Achievement Hunter's "made up" characters. They're such a great archer and while in possession of his bow, you feel as if you could bullseye an imp from miles away!

name: Air Treks - Basic Edition
description: These motorized inline skates that allow you to perform incredible stunts are also incredibly useful in bashing Imps on their heads. And killing them. While you do your... stunts...

name: Ray\'s Rose Whip
description: The whip of an Achievement Hunter who is quite obsessed with roses. Whenever you crack the whip, you leave rose petals everywhere!

name: Staff of Pimps
description: A smaller and thinner version of the Tower of Pimps. Consisting of a obsidian base, and four lengths of gold above it, you'll definitely be pimp!

name: Gav Core
description: A core which is filled with Gavin Free's personality. Get ready to hear the irritating voice of a Brit all day as you carry him around with you. Is he useful for anything? Well, probably not you muggy lit'le gob.

name: Edgar Plush
description: A plush cow owned by a member of the Achievement Hunters. It's tag reads: You don't understand. EDGAR IS THE PLUSH IN THE HOLE.

name: Space Sign "Danmaku Bounded Field"
description: This spellcard traps Underlings inside a small area where they can do nothing but attempt to dodge waves of bullets until the attack runs out. Almost makes you feel kind of bad for them, really.

name: Mind Sign "Rorschach in Danmaku"
description: You wonder what the Underlings might be seeing in the abstract bullet shapes this spellcard creates. Well, other than their imminent demise.

name: Rage Sign "Seamless Ceiling of Kinkaku-Ji"
description: Literal walls of bullets raining down all around, with a liberal sprinkling of randomly fired shots thrown in for good measure; man, are you glad you're not on the receiving end of this spellcard.

name: Apostrophe Sign "Wrath of the Overseer"
description: This spellcard rains down a deluge of apostrophes of all the colours of the rainbow on your opposition, with side effects of mild reality warping. You get the feeling you probably shouldn't use this unless you absolutely have to.

name: Shrekmunity: Leprechaun Edition DVD
description: A green leprechaun ogre goes to leprechaun college because he lied about having a leprechaun degree. He then finds some other friends such as a golden magic donkey and a rainbow gingerbread man.

name: Amulet Of Power
description:
There is something dark in this amulet.
Probably because it's carrying the fucking ring of Mordor. Throw this in Mount Doom or something.

name: Crown of the Noble-Hearted King
description: This is the crown for a king with a noble heart. Well, it doesn't work like the sword in the rock though: you wear it and it makes you feel gradually kinder and nobler. Extended wearing time may turn you into a new millennium philantropist.

name: Fedorito
description: The attire of choice for any true gentleman. The combination of a classy hat and a delicious snack make it easy to tip more enthusiastically, thus making m'ladies swoon even harder.

name: Doctor Honeytongue
description: An able and skilled physician who is bound by a creed to where he will do no harm unless necessary. He is quite the honorable friend and will likely save you when you are in need. That would be the case at least, if he wasn't a stuffed plush.

name: Dart Machine Gun
description: This... Isn't nearly as effective as a normal machine gun, with actual bullets. But hey! At least the ammo seems unlimited!

name: Mage Armor Hoodie
description: This magic knitted hoodie protects you from all kinds of dangers. It's nice and cozy too!

name: Flame Orb
description: An item supposedly held by a Pokmon. It is a bizarre orb that will afflict the Pokemon with a burn during battle. Doesn't seem to affect SBURB heroes though, so you're safe.

name: Descend
description: As you grasp this flag, the power of four total badasses flows through your body. Harness the power of teamwork and take down the Black King!

name: Hextime Lantern
description: A lantern made out of glowing clockwork. Winding up the gears makes time flow faster for you.

name: Sburb Item Codes
description: This Book contains every code you'll ever need!   Shame you can't god damn well read it.

name: Christmaween Candle
description: A fusion of Christmas and Halloween, all in one candle.

name: Stardust Kolhii Stick
description: A special Kolhii Stick infused with stardust. It's now slightly more shiny.

name: Yin-Yang Energy Sphere
description: An unstable sphere that intermittently flashes with pure white and pitch black energy. You feel both hopeful and hopeless when near this item...

name: Super Telescope of Dubious Prognosticative Competance
description: This telescope, when looked through, shows a blue triangle-based kaleidoscope. On the face of the triangles it shows a really crumby prediction about whatever you're looking at. A near 100% guaranteed false prediction in fact. However, it is perfectly serviceable as a monster bashing instrument.

name: Telescopically Temporal Predicto-Peeper
description: The only thing telescopic about this thing is how quickly the shittiness of its predictions get the further into the future you look, plus that sand gets in your eye more when you look farther. Also, it is a telescope, so that's telescoping, but let's be honest this thing is for bashing skulls.

name: Telescopically Temporal Gazing Apparatus
description: That last function seemed to get rid of the shitty predictions, but keep the seeing into the future, and even lets you turn a section of the telescope to go forward and backwards into some thing's history or future. Neat!

name: Moon Fragment
description: 72 hours remain before you smash this piece of the moon into an imp's head.

name: Zer0\'s Training Knife
description: Before he had a sword, Zer0 had a knife.  To invisibly shank you with.

name: King\'s Royal Crown
description: A crown to show that you ARE the king, and damn is it kingly.

name: Nine-iron from Hell
description: A black and red golf club, with a flaming club head. Sometimes at night you can hear a disturbing demonic laugh emanating from it.

name: Junior Temporal Graphing Kit
description: Map the flow of time with your Junior temporal graphing kit. This new knowledge is sure to come in handy somehow.

name: Flaming Hot Chainsledge
description: Because having a heavy hammer with extremely fast rotating chains on it wasn't enough. No, you needed it to shoot FIRE too. Just don't burn yourself, okay? Be responsible.

name: Top Droid
description: A smartphone for the fancy gentleman, it comes pre-installed with a catalogue of tuxedos and canes. Don't forget those bow-ties either!

name: Prospitian Armour
description: Standard issue for all Prospit Footsoldiers!

name: Sonic Space Gym Badges
description: Oh... Oh My God.   WHAT HAVE YOU DONE? These things are literally glowing.  No i'm serious. Are these safe? You have literally confined Sonic Space into the Gym Badges. THEY WERE POWERFUL ENOUGH, BUT NO. YOU HAD TO DO THIS. Still. could be worse.  You could have used Paradox Space.

name: Spade Shooter
description: A pistol-sized machine gun that shoots knives. Perfect for turning otherwise healthy imps into graveyard stuffers, or it would be if they weren't already.

name: Mug
description: A nice solid ceramic mug, perfect for drinking tea or coffee from.

name: Doritos-Flavoured Mountain Dew
description: Double the neckbeard in liquid form!

name: Mountain Dew-Flavoured Doritos
description: Double the neckbeard in solid form!

name: Sheepy Mascot Head
description: This soft woolly costume head closely resembles the mascot of a famous sports team. Represent!

name: Liaison Pumpkinsnuffle
description: The witness who came close to bringing Senator Lemonsnout to justice. Unfortunately he was slain by the fiend and is now all but alive. God you need a better hobby than this. No wonder you don't have friends.

name: Refraction Throwing Toothbrush
description: Nearly invisible, this cute little brush refracts light, creating little rainbows on your teeth. It also has a sharp end so that you can throw it like a dart because of... reasons.

name: Electromagnetic Bucket of Potatoes
description: The electromagnet within this bucket is powered by all of the potatoes. Finally, one item that can solve both the energy crisis and world hunger.

name: FusRohBAM
description: A shotgun with the explosive force of a Nordic man screaming in your face.

name: WWhite Nautical Hat of Unstoppable Science
description:
this hat is powwered by the powwer of wwhite science.
there are no fakey fake magics invvolved either because wwe all knoww those are fake.

name: Hermes Boots
description: These green boots for some reason give you the ability to sprint at amazing speeds. Maybe someday you'll be like Hermes himself.

name: Gay-Pride iPlunger
description: Made by Apple during a month of pure boredom, and gay-pride parades.

name: Electric Tomahawk
description: A hatchet with an electric blade. Pretty straightforward. Throw it, chop trees with it... hell, you could probably make grilled cheese with it if you really wanted to.

name: Executioner\'s Axe
description: This massive axe is decorated with stone skulls. It seems to pulse with dark fire occasionally.

name: Cascade
description: As you hold this flag, the power of two universes flows through your arms. You feel as though everything is beginning to fall into place for you.

name: Titanic DVD
description: A long movie about the sinking of the famous ship.

name: Set of Barbed Darts
description: The only real difference in these is that the dart now has spikes. You... Guess this is more effective? If you don't stab yourself as you throw?

name: Turnsavvvvvv
description: This chainsaw lets you drop sick beats while killing enemies!

name: Reddest Red Armor
description: This chestpiece is so ridiculously red it's kind of sickening. One glimpse at this and you'll have seen more red than any person has ever seen in their lifetime.

name: Celery
description: A green chunky vegetable, perfect for salads and acting like you're losing weight.

name: Leek
description: This might go well with cooking, or you could spin it around... you guess...

name: Onion
description: This might make you cry... if you're a LITTLE BABY MAN.

name: Artichoke
description: Nice plump green veggie, it can be delicious if served right.

name: Turnip
description: A fresh turnip, ready to be cooked or eaten or thrown or whatever you want to do with it.

name: Asparagus
description: The things your mother begged you to try but ultimately refused, what a fussy kid you were.

name: Cucumber
description: Fine green stick-shaped food. You stifle your temptations to make a crude joke.

name: Ogre-nade
description: KERBLEWY! These ogre shaped grenades will tear you enemies apart! NOTE: Donkey C-4 not included.

name: Hands of Mod
description: It is said that imps die for no apparent reason on occasion. Those who say such things have clearly never witnessed the wrath of Mod. He is our creator. He is our destroyer. It is Him. Fear His fury.

name: Wikipedia\'s Guide to Frog Breeding
description: Wait, isn't this a downgrade? You went from Wikipedia's entirety to just a list of Wikipedia articles on frogs. And it's still more dense. Somehow. At least it's 300% guaranteed to piss off any Dersite you swing it at. And it's easier to sort through for the crap you'll actually need.

name: Glitchy Itchy Remover
description: Removes itches with ease! How? WITH THE POWER OF GLITCH SCIENCE! The downside? It replaces them with glitches.

name: Sanic-Possessed c0w-Sprinkled New Age Fuck-Shit Ralph Festive Toast-A-Matic Ogre-Plunger
description: This holiday season, help Sanic and Shreck-it Ralph heal their souls with the sprinkles of a herd of constantly mutating cows, yeeeah, not the best holiday treat...

name: Key to the Promised LAN
description: Said to unlock the maximum potential of the wifi provided in the medium, this key will guarantee that you are always connected.

name: Spiked Timepiece
description: Keeps the time while also being an excellent flail. Just watch where you grip it.

name: Deadly Neurotoxin Spray
description: Get ready, while I warm up the NEUROTOXIN emitters.

name: Snoop Dog\'s Weed Flavor Mountain Dew
description: Sold in a handful of stores on the date 4/20; miraculously, those stores still haven't been closed down. This oddity's production will probably die out soon, so you should probably drink it now.

name: Yellow Tennis Racket
description: A shiny new BRIGHT YELLOW tennis racket! For some reason, this racket is a bit heavier and tougher than an ordinary racket.

name: Omniscient Recipe Calculator
description: With the addition of the Omniscope, this device can now see farther! It will search your Atheneum for possible recipes, but it may take a while...

name: Uranium Starfish Cocktail
description: A nice cocktail made out of nice cold vodka, nicely cut celery, and pure blended uranium-powered starfish.

name: Fur Plungerang Reaper
description: This is gonna get weird, this is a fur boomerang plunger that is somewhat related to Blue Oyster Cult's "Don't Fear the Reaper". Only the most weirdest plumbers would use these things.

name: Bow-Plunger
description: The stick of this plunger is curved... no, wait, this bow has a plunger suction thingy on the end... okay, you have no idea how this fucking works at all.

name: Dragon Born\'s Dream Job?
description: THEY DON'T EVEN HAVE TOILETS IN SKYRIM.

name: Crown of Greater Luminescence
description: This crown now radiates even more intensely than before. The iridescent glow is gone and is replaced by a blinding white light. You feel slightly better while wearing this. Almost as if you could rule ALL the kingdoms.

name: Map of Russia
description: The map of the motherla- HOLY SHIT ITS COLD HERE!!!

name: Veil of Hope\'s Dawn
description: This radiant veil glows softly like a sunrise; yet nothing will ever pierce the fabric, not eyesight nor blades. With this on, victory is a dream that is coming true. All you have to do is believe.

name: Chainsaw-shaped Cape
description: It's just a cape. Shaped like a large chainsaw. There is really nothing else to say on the matter.

name: Squiddle-dee Paintbrush
description: This is not a mop. It is just a paintbrush with a purple handle, and abnormally long brush strands. At least you can whip the imps with the thing. And make abstract art.

name: Supremely Soft Dice
description: So much soft covering you can barely see the numbers.

name: Cherry Red d20
description: Your d20 now has a beautiful cherry-red color. Like any good roleplayer, you know that the color of your die will greatly affect the outcome on certain rolls.

name: Musical d20
description: This d20 has a musical note rather than a 20. On a critical hit it rings out in perfect B flat concert.

name: Thorn Dice
description: These gaming dice have a unique wireframe design which makes them quite pointy.

name: Glass d20
description: The light shines beautifully through this prismatic d20.

name: i20
description: The 20 on this gaming die is instead a tiny apple logo. This die is worth easily five times the price of the ones produced by microsoft, despite being functionally identical.

name: Demonic Octet of Ultimate Love
description: Die that are said to grant you love with anyone. That is, if you are lucky enough to roll well, otherwise, your soul may very well be consumed by your crushing despair...and also the die.

name: Piercing Bow of Communism
description: A bow said to pierce anyones soul with the power of equality! With this, enemies will be able see the light of how this totally workable and perfect system of goverment is for them! All will unite in the name of Mother Russia!

name: Heart Phylactery
description: This heart-shaped crystal phylactery pulsates and lights up rhythmically. It radiates with a rather eerie, thought not to be malevolent, aura of power and... emotions.

name: Error
description: You have no idea when this got here, or what it is, for that matter. Still, when you throw this at imps it seems to hurt them.

name: Cursed Ring
description: This beautiful gold ring can't be cursed, can it? Sure, you always have an absolutely awful day when you wear it, but cursed stuff only exists in video games! Wait...

name: Red Shirt
description: Wearing this shirt makes you a lot more susceptible to an untimely death. Why did you EVER think wearing it was a good idea?

name: Semaphore Scissors
description: Scissors so red they fleetingly blind enemies, and friends if you're not careful.

name: Arm-Mounted Anti-Metroid Freezer Cannon
description: Not nearly as cool as the Hyper Beam, but knock yourself out.

name: Grandfather Clock
description: A large clock that chimes every hour. It needs to rewound every once in a while to stay on time. Surprisingly light enough to be swung, though it's not recommended.

name: Nick of Time God Tier Outfit
description: With this newfound godly power, you feel like you could take on anyone, do anything. Even steal the Declaration of Independence.

name: Stopwatch
description: Great for timing one's self in a competitive nature - always strive to do better!

name: Robes of the Howling Wind
description: These flowing blue robes are always swept by some kind of wind that seems to be somehow embedded in the fabric itself. The sound they emanate is ominous, like an oncoming storm.

name: Propane-technic Chainsaw
description: The stupidest thing garage gadgetry has ever come up with.

name: Galactic Steel Chair
description: A folding chair forged from incredibly light weight and hard silver alloy harvested from meteors.

name: Flaming Hot Shot
description: A blue toy looking gun with a steel barrel that shoots extremely hot and flaming pellets into the enemy.

name: Steampunk Scythe
description: This scythe is like any other scythe, except much heavier and with several holes on the blade. Whenever it strikes an enemy, it releases jets of hot steam into the enemies' wounds.

name: Abraxas\'s Helm
description: A large, green, bird-like skull, themed after the Denizen of Hope. It has a hollow inside for your head. It's pretty much guaranteed to make your foes start to give up.

name: Vongola Ring
description: This ring was once used by a member of the Vongola Family. It has the power of refining one's lifeforce into a colorful flame with powers based on the color.

name: Klatchian Coffee
description: Drink enough of this, and you will become knurd, making it so you see the world without the rose tinted lenses you have given it, the way nobody ever should.

name: Achievement Hunter Cape
description: A magnificent flowing cape depicting the AH boys as a boy band. Your friends will be so jealous.

name: Flynt Coal\'s Coat
description:
Wear the super spy Flynt Coal's trench coat as you strife!
"Flynt Coal is cool guy extraordinaire, not some loser in a dumb hat!" - Michael Jones

name: Surgeon Simulator 2013 Disc
description: Now you can play the darkly humorous over-the-top operation sim game which is Surgeon Simulator 2013 on disc!

name: Surgeons in Space Poster
description: A poster featuring Gavin Free and Michael Jones as doctors for the game Surgeon Simulator 2013. In surgery, no one can hear you scream.

name: Two-Sided Shitfucker
description: It's a double colored plunger-hammer representing hope and endless despair, some people get the symbolism mixed up with the yin and yang though, which is kinda different due to the fact that the yin and yang are pretty much representing opposites attracting each other. mean while hope and despair are well, hope and despair!

name: Mann Co. Chocolate Plunger
description: This chocolate plunger is property of Mann Co. and probably tastes like melted australium.

name: The Rage of Mogar
description: THE PURE MOTHER FUCKING ESSENCE OF AN ACHIEVEMENT HUNTER WHEN HE IS MAD. MOGAR IS READY!

name: Gamblers Fallacy
description: A deck of cards for the relaxed, simpler gambler. Although it appears to be predictable, it is known to be affected by the strange concept known as "randomness".

name: Demonic Ring of Ultimate Rage
description: This ring shakes furiously when not worn, and once it's on your ring you will feel impossibly angry and aggressive. Please direct your murderous rage on enemies.

name: Luminous Compu-Cat Ear
description: Brightly colored cat ears that radiate light, and somehow function as a computer. Skaia smiles upon the neko.

name: Nayru\'s Love
description: This mystical object that supposedly carries the power of a Golden Goddess raises up a powerful crystal shield to protect you from enemies.

name: Hand-Held Radio Wave-Laser Pistol
description: This fantastic weapon shoots lasers that don't really leave burn marks. They instead shoot extremely high frequency radio waves. If aimed at the head, the extreme overflow of data can blow up the brain in under 20 seconds, but not before an intense, torturing headache.

name: SledgePencil
description: It has the weight, power and durability of a sledgehammer, and the usefulness and pointiness of a pencil! That means the pencil tip won't break. You can also write with this, if you want something with huge ass letters.

name: Turn Table Blazer
description:
Like being in formal AND mixing beats?
Well you're in luck! This turn table blazer will fix your problem. The turn tables can also be used in defense, because they're pretty much portable. One moment you're empty handed, the next you're busting out beats and blocking bullets with the tables.

name: Gushers Pie
description: The new Betty Crocker Gushers Pie is guaranteed to give you diabetes, or your money back!

name: Steel-Feathered Duster
description: A feather duster made entirely out of solid steel. Although it isn't very useful for cleaning anymore, it packs a hefty wallop.

name: Nuclear Handheld Hardon Hurler
description: This nuclear launcher bombards your foes with... phalluses? That's got to be some kind of glitch. There's no way the devs would make such an item on purpose.

name: Professor Pucefoot
description: Held with high regards for his astute nature and high intelligence, Professor Pucefoot occasionally leaves his ivory home to render chalk outlines for high profile cases and crime scenes...You really should stop playing with dolls and get a life, though admittedly he seems to smell like strawberries, so that's kinda cool...You guess...

name: Duke Pinesnort
description: Description: A terrible aristorcrat who betrayed his own people and as such, will pay for it with his life...and the lives of his loved ones... If you keep collecting dolls like this one you're going to end up like one of those old cat ladies, but with scalemates. Though at least you're not like that one person who collects them obsessively and seems to like them for their taste, hers being loving towards sweets. You are totally sure you are not this person.

name: Inspector 8erry8reath
description:
Something seems...off about the Inspector today. His rump is just as ample and absorbent as ever...8ut he seems to 8e more lucky than usual. May8e his luck will ru88 off onto you?
You also have a feeling a certain enthusiast of scalemates may have developed a sudden distaste in 8erry8reath.

name: Felt Dragon Suit
description: A dragon costume with little pool balls as scales, green trim, and a green hood. All the power of the felt; all the fun of dragons.

name: Magic Basketball
description: An all-white basketball imbued with mysterious magical powers. If only you could properly tap into that power.

name: The Black, White and Gray of Magic
description: Not a single one of the pencils in this box are octarine. How disappointing.

name: Deathburn
description: Whenever you hit something with this scythe, it explodes into colourful stars! Ridiculously dangerous, but a big hit at New Year's parties.

name: Spined Universe-Distorting Darts
description: Powerful darts strong enough to scratch the material of space and time. WARNING: Keep out of child's reach.

name: Spiney Christmas Calculator
description: Number crunching for the holidays, this should help you save money.

name: Toxic Boomerang
description: A sharp, high-tech boomerang that seeps poison into the cuts it makes.

name: Dice Pouch
description: Handy for keeping all of your tiny dice in one place.

name: The Constitution Save
description: Roll to save vs. alcohol poisoning.

name: Billiard Brain Deck
description: A deck of cards housing the personalities of a group of leprechauns.

name: Workaround Sign "Escape Sequence"
description: This spellcard creates an ever-shifting maze of colourful apostrophes, each orbited by a razor-sharp backslash. The reality glitches seem to be gone, but you can't really say you mind: those garbled imps and floating error messages were starting to creep you out.

name: Unagi Punchers
description: Strong enough to punch a man eating sea serpent in the face, and still have power for more.

name: Skull Cap of the Really Fast
description: It's an enchanted skullcap that makes you move faster. If only it was true in strife.

name: Power Metal Mixtape
description: A fine mix of the most heroic, uplifting music known to mankind. Its soaring melodies and wailing guitars makes you feel like you could punch a dragon in the face and get away with it.

name: Dynapainter
description: Hell yeah! This ridiculously powerful paintbrush was enchanted with explosive paint witchcraft. You think you can take on this explosive painting beast!? HAH! Well you best be packing another damn Dynapainter!

name: Divination Glasses
description: The way to see the future is not only in what to look at, but in which way you look at it.

name: Plungerbuss
description: Why yes it's a antique shotgun that can clean toilets, and yes, it also looks a bit silly. The fact that this thing existed is a bit silly as well, because you can not imagine a situation where you need a plunger and a shotgun at the same time.

name: Fortune of Dawn
description: This magical deck of cards seemed to be filled with the energies of both light and darkness. While the front is that of a rising dawn the back has a black and white crown. Grey mist also flows from the cards.

name: Nyx\'s Lucky Time-Computing Holographic Honeyspecs
description: When wearing these shades, you can see everything in the Incipisphere, wipe anything out of existence in the blink of an eye, and look cool while doing so. It now also works as a handsfree computer!

name: Robes of Angry Shrieking
description: The Horrorterror's voices emanating from this robe seem to be amplified and are angrier than before.

name: Mind\'s Precious
description: This ring is said to greatly increase your intelligence and wit, and provide you with amazing ideas. Over time, though, you'll notice it will gradually make you more cruel-minded.

name: Defense Against the Dark Hearts
description: Now more of a pun, this powerful paintbrush/shield has been imbued with the power of love! Or just some odd heart. It's hard to tell considering the components. Give a heart-y laugh to this object's ability! It is also shaped like a heart.

name: Astronaut\'s Moon Plunging Fork Device
description: It's a plunger, a fork, and a astronaut's best friend, all in one, however, the fact that it's made out of moon rock makes it less useful as a plunger.

name: Arcane Explosion
description: You've managed to combine high explosives with the energy inherent in pure magic. Time to go blow up some monsters!

name: Cloak of The Forge
description: This cloak seems to stongly flow with Time itself. Even better, all attacks that are inflicted on it seems to get thrown to some other time period.

name: Leaf Kazoo
description: A leaf whistle that makes the sound of a kazoo. You're not really sure how it works, but it's incredibly annoying. You could probably use it to annoy your enemies to death. Or at least into throwing grist at you and running away.

name: Sonic Clock
description: A clock the displays the time and makes super cool noises! Plus, it extends! Oh my!

name: Couch
description: Ahhhh, after a long day of dungeon diving, it's time to sink into this nice, comfortable - wait, this isn't comfortable...

name: Novelty PENguin
description: A pen in the shape of a penguin. It even has a little snow hat. How cute! Not very effective in combat though.

name: Moon Globe
description: Wow, where was this thing when you had to make that paper mache moon? You could have really used it. It's totally useless now since the moon kind of isn't there anymore, but at least it looks pretty cool.

name: Glass Mug
description: Great for putting tea in. Great for smashing over your enemies' heads. Great for putting the blood of your enemies in and drinking a nice hot cup of victory. If you're into that sort of thing...

name: Atom Shirt
description: Display your love of nuclear physics for the world to see!

name: DevilBeast shirt
description: A shirt depicting the silhouette of a rather familiar creature.

name: Gideon\'s Tarot Deck
description: This tarot deck give you power of Gravity Fall's number one Psychic, aka the power of complete bullshit. But it's a little magic too.

name: Titan Dice
description: These gaming dice are much larger than others of their kind. Luckily, you do not need to erect walls around your other dice to keep these from attacking.

name: Blade Sign "Shattering of the Apostrophe Equilibrium"
description: With the backslashes replaced by the vengeful spirits of a thousand blades suspended in moderation limbo, the apostrophe cloud is once again free to wreak havoc on the fabric of reality. Oops. You guess you'd better just try to stay away and hope your enemies succumb to the chaos.

name: Nrub\'yiglith\'s Oriental Blessings
description: Wreathed in writhing darkness, these twin and viciously tapered chainsaws full you with a sense of purity. As pure as the Elder Gods can impart, that is.

name: Cairo Armor of the Dark Sun
description: This armor has a very... depressing aura, along with this feeling that you can't shrug off of it being a certain someone else's...

name: Comfortable Couch
description: Now this is more like it! Ahhhh after a long day of dungeon diving, it's time to sink into this nice, COMFORTABLE COUCH.

name: Prismatic War Scythe
description: Heal blocking, redundant. Colourful curved blade, lethal. Long reach, useful.

name: Shining Maiden of the Sun God Tier Armor
description: The combination of a strongly defensive god tier outfit and a blinding light emanating from it makes for a very difficult battle for Imps when you wear this armor.

name: Fry Pan Chef Hat
description: I'M READY, I'M READY, I'M READY

name: Angel of Double Death\'s Halo
description: A pure black halo with an eerie green outline. It radiates unspeakable dark energy and an aura of pure dread. Any enemy that gets hit with this thing will surely be "double dead."

name: Soul Eater Poster
description: The glory of this poster makes you aspire to be a great meister.

name: Pikacomputerbat
description: A bat, a computer, and a Pikachu face all in one! Now you can run around, pretending to be Volt Tackling your enemies, While listening to some hardcore beats. Fun times are ahead.

name: Arcane ? Block
description: It's a mysterious block with a ? on it, hitting the block can give you random MAGICAL power-ups, such as a magic mushroom, an arcane flower, and a mystical      feather.

name: Prospit Throne
description: Sitting on the White Queen's throne means having power in your hands. Wielding the throne might not be the same, but it still hurts to be hit with.

name: Glowing Oracle
description: A luminescent sphere that can answer any question with precision and clarity- but really, do you WANT to know? It still lacks a portal to view the answer, but you can gather a sense of its responses... somehow. It's not magic, obviously.

name: The Last Breath
description: A Super Spooky gas mask in the shape of a skull. Putting this on makes you want to burn things for some reason.

name: Clever Disguise
description: By combining these Glasses and this Fake Mustache, you've created a Clever Disguise that shall surely leave your aggressors dumbfounded. "Where did the hero go" they'll say "all I see is a bespectacled, mustachioed, and rather attractive individual."

name: Cup O\' Lava
description: It's a mug filled with lava. Much more painful when it shatters on your enemies. Such lava. Very hot. W-ow.

name: Silent Prophet
description: It's... a magic 8-ball. But... there's no little lying triangle to taunt you with inaccurate prophesies. If you look just deep enough into the portal in the side, you can see... nothing.

name: Moplunger
description: Now you can un-clog the toilet and clean it at the same time, it also makes you wonder why these things never got popular on earth, strange.

name: Turing Machine
description: A hypothetical (until now!) computer consisting of nothing but a programmable read/write head and an infinitely long tape to hold ones and zeros. Despite its primitive appearance it runs anything a normal computer would, although reading the output in binary is kind of a pain.

name: Bucket Cake
description: A cake made out of 100% pure steel buckets - it has a delicious, rusty tang in every bite!

name: Astronomer\'s Deck
description: The designs on this tarot deck are made of real - though miniaturized - stars. Be careful not to burn yourself!

name: Vodka Duster
description: It's a feather duster that has a bottle of vodka as a handle, now you can get drunk doing house work, hurrah.

name: Triangle Darts
description: These seem more like ninja stars than darts, but...you guess you'll trust the name? Not like misnomers are a thing or anything.

name: Furry Cup
description: Hopefully you can throw this at imps pretty hard because it's too furry to even be useful as a cup.

name: Robo-beast Necroclaws
description: The talons of a fierce robotic lion defeated in the first half of the episode and brought back to life for a giant robot fight that would take up the second half, these claws combine the badassery of a lion, robot, and giant zombie all in one.

name: iNyx Steedspecs
description: These STRONG shades will fill the void in your heart. They can also work as a computer.

name: Cadet\'s Dream Cap
description: This is a beige cadet cap with a winged design on the front. It fills you with hopefulness, and probably does just the opposite to your foes.
ITEM NOT FOUND

name: Fairy Saw-Saw
description: A beautiful Tutu worn by magical wood-carving Fairies. Spinning around while wearing this makes a loud VRRRRRRRRRRRR sound.

name: Pop-Up Blocker
description: Putting those annoying ads to defensive use, this electronic shield displays an ever-shifting variety of more or less suspect offers. You're fairly certain that most of them would have been invalidated by the destruction of Earth, but hey, the imps don't know that.

name: Makeshift Prospitian Prosthetic Leg
description: This sleek, black-and-gold knife with a rainbow aura functions just as well as a wand. Perfect for replacing legs, stabbing out eyes, and clogging coffins.

name: DOUBLE HOUR-HAND SHOOTING GUN-THING
description: You though one was enough? Nope! Now you can have two!

name: Steel Tennis Racket
description: Using razor-sharp steel wire for this racket causes it to shred any tennis balls it comes into contact with. Fortunately, it does the same to imp heads.

name: Longcat Scarf
description: No 2007 weeaboo's wardrobe would be complete without one of these.

name: Microphone
description: An acoustic-to-electric transducer or sensor that converts sound in air into an electrical signal. Great for barking orders or karaoke nights.

name: x3
description: Third time's the charm, you hope...

name: Thorns of B\'tte Crocklogoth
description: In addition to containing dark magical properties, the wand have the unmistakeable smell of chocolate.

name: Art of the Shrek
description: Finally, you have reached the peak of high-end fashion.

name: Ichorcloth Robes
description: These already-powerful robes have been imbued with the power of the gods. They are as strong as steel and hard as diamond.

name: Robes of the Stratosphere
description: These nigh-impenetrable robes now come with wings! To the heavens!

name: Settlers of Catan
description: Get resources, expand your city, conquer the world, make jokes about how all the other players "want your wood".

name: GOT SPEKE AMLULRET
description: While you still hear yourself normally while wearing this, everyone else around you hears your dialogue as a never-ending stream of shitty SBaHJ references, handily captioned in horribly artifacted comic sans font above your head. It also lets you speak to GOT......or at least it would if you weren't PRAYING WRONG, you dumb homo tool.

name: Flushian Roulette
description: Push your faith in luck to a whole new level. Developed in a far away land, this six-chambered revolver fires sharpened cards - but be careful not to get a Joker!

name: Fabled Wizard\'s Lucky Sweeper
description: Not only did a wizard deserve a kickass fighting stick, but they a also deserve a kickass, magic, and lucky DUST fighting stick. This broom still gives out slot results, but it's now magic! And no longer a hand broom. What did you expect?

name: AEX
description: This thing can barely cut air, god forbid anything worth cutting. BUt i thenk u need,,, a bit of COHPPING done...............

name: Heart Laserglasses
description: The lenses of these glasses glow with dark pink energy. By simply looking at someone with these on, you can drown them in any kind of emotions. Or else, you know, annihilate them in a blast of laser.

name: Death\'s Suit
description: Fitted perfectly for your classy Death needs.

name: Shining Hammer of the Deep
description: WOW! OxiClean really DOES fight stains inside and out! All of the blood and carnage has been washed clean off, and now it shines brilliantly! What's more, it seems to have left a bit of a protective film over the hammer as well! THANKS Milly Bays!

name: Pokemon Emerald Version
description: Welcome to the Hoenn region, where our music consists of trumpets, more trumpets, and even more trumpets.

name: Omniscient Orb
description: Gazing at this sphere too long gives you a headache. You can feel knowledge flowing from it, but so too do dark whispers. Is gazing into it's opaque and glowing portal worth the risk? Shall you bear the gauntlet of eldritch echoes for the sake of the infinite knowledge that it can offer you?

name: 8D Glasses
description: Now if only there were any 8D movies...

name: BFG18000
description: Now with two times the GREEN EXPLOSION.

name: Armor of the Eclipse
description: This armor has a mix of dark and light patterns and embroidery that should clash terribly, but actually seem to come together in an odd sort of harmony.

name: Amulet Coin
description: An item to be held by a person. It increases any prize money received if the person holding it joins in a battle.

name: Despicable Me DVD
description: A movie about a bald evil old guy and a lesson about love.

name: Fart Gun
description: You wanted to alchemize a Dart Gun, not a... UGH! What is that disgusting smell?

name: Robes of Ideas
description: These mint green robes never stop talking with many simultaneous voices, which is pretty confusing (for you and for enemies), but the stuff they say, if you can distinguish it, is pure genius.

name: White-8 Wand
description: This powerful white wand utilizes 8 (yes, 8!!!!!!!!) different types of magic which can deal great damage to your foes.

name: Spiritual Pan
description: It is said that this pan is used to banish others to the spirit world when hit with it.

name: Death-Defying Shield
description: You have always wanted skulls lined around your shield for some interesting BLOOD MAJYYKS. You haven't? Well that's what you've got.

name: Textridaggers of Sophia
description: These daggers flicker with the double blessing of the Demimonde Semigoddess and of Sophia, the Denizen of Heart. They emit all the hues of pink light, and radiate with the godly power of Love. They're unspeakably beautiful and ornate, yet lethal.

name: Hexray Timelantern
description: A glowing green lantern carved out of a single piece of uranium. Being near this has to be TERRIBLE for you. Time near this lantern seems to fluctuate wildly...

name: Small Plastic Cup full of Spare Change
description: Well.. hopefully you can throw this pretty hard because those coins aren't even valid currency here and there's not much else for you to do with it.

name: Badminton Racket
description: A light and shiny badminton racket!

name: Spacial Chainsaw of Obfuscation / Temporal Rifle of Knowledge
description: A white, green-swirled chainsaw that specializes in the returning of things to nothing, paired with a black, red-swirled rifle, that offers knowledge and fortune in combat. You're... kind of awed by this.

name: Intellibeam Laserplunger
description: A big plunger with the power to see hidden captchalogue codes. With LASERS.

name: Mechascythe
description: Google things while collecting souls. Finally, the perfect combo!

name: Shadow Helmet of Bloodlust
description: Wearing this helmet fills you with a cruel desire for blood. It is made of scales and gives off a dark red glint, like a light reflected on dense, fresh blood. For the darkest of souls.

name: Spiral Cape of the Zephyr
description: This beautiful cape looks like a piece of woven sky. It waves continuously, even when there's no wind at all.

name: BFT9000
description: No monster can resist the Big Fucking Trumpet and its barrage of sonic waves.

name: Fear No Norn
description:
A hammer imbued with even more power from the goddesses of fate.
Truely, this hammer will decide your fate, while ending others.

name: Axerill
description: A drill with the head shaped like an axe. Suprisingly easy to dig with this.

name: Shotgun Surgeon
description: On the positive side it is much better at surgery. On the negative side the only surgery it can do is amputations.

name: Anvilscythe
description: Beat down the enemies as ya cut them. Kinda like a hammer and a scythe!

name: Nyx\'s_CRoSS#airs oF GLITC#ed voiD
description: This rifle seems to be highly volatile and dangerous, like if it wasn't supported by reality. It's so glitchy it's surprising that it's even usable, let alone being THIS powerful. It fires a really intense (and really buggy) laser that can glitch anything.

name: Sonic Boombox w/ Detatchable Sneakers
description: The worst boombox to ever be placed on the shelf. Everytime you turn it on, before the music plays you hear "SEGA" and these sneakers are stuck on for seemingly no reason...

name: Time-travelling Metal Umbrella Hat
description: A normal time travelling hat wasn't good enough, eyy? Now you have an umbrella on top to protect you from time-travel rain!

name: Flaming Hot Chainsledge of Poisonous Aromas
description: Description: The flames from this chainsledge are now a dark purple color and the smoke burns your skin too. This thing is even more deadly, and poisonous now...and also very purple.

name: Immoliating Hunter
description: A shotgun that fires a blast of flame strong enough that even the least skilled hunter may hunt the terrors of the void. It leaves the smell of paradox calamari in the wielder's wake.

name: Hateful Pistol Goose
description: Unlike the duck monarchs, the geese are a hell of a lot more likely to attack forcefully. Warning: Their targets may or may not include you.

name: Electronic Map of Time
description: A self-updating map of time in a place where time doesn't actually apply. You guess this could be useful, if you completely ignore the previous issue. It certainly helps keep the time loops in order.

name: Dual CompuShades
description: Now you have a computer in each lens! Great for talking to yourself using two accounts on pesterchum.

name: Omniclub of Felony
description: This club lets you see enemies coming from anywhere in the Incipisphere!...It also can be used to beat them up.

name: Snakemail Knight of Blood Armor
description: Now you're starting to look like a legitimate Knight! It took a while for you to figure out you could customize your God Tier threads. Scale-mail armor over your pajama-like Knight of Blood garb. Don't worry, the cape is still included.

name: Red Scissors of Justice
description: L1K3 4 STR1NG L1F3 PR3C4R1OUSLY H4NGS, 4LL TOO R34DY FOR TH3 CUTT1NG. 4ND SUCH CUTT1NG H4S N3V3R B33N SO 3NJOY4BL3 4S TH4T OF 4 S34SON3D V1LL41N.

name: Right Arm Excavator
description: Through the power of alchemy you create a single massive gauntlet capable of digging tearing through rock and steel. Shame that you could only make a right handed gauntlet.

name: Cookalizer
description: A cubic gizmo with four settings: thaw, cook, irradiate, and a fourth depicting a nuclear blast. You think you'll stay clear of that fourth one because you're not stupid.

name: Refrigerator
description: This is a coommon household "refrigerator" which you guess is a silly thing to call an ordinary refrigifyifator. It keeps food fresh longer in suspended animation and stores it efficiently with some sort of modern witchcraft. Clearly a staple appliance of any first-world kitchen. Clearly.

name: Time-Warping Scissors of the Omnipresent Squiddle Overlord
description: A giant, mechanical Squiddle-themed doll... thing. Each of its tentacles is both a blade and a wand, shooting deadly time beams while rotating around a hinge, crushing anything unlucky enough to get caught between two of them. In reality, the creature's perception of time slows while stuck, allowing it to experience agony for an infinite period of time. All within half a second!

name: Whispering Rock Summer Camp Pamphlet
description: A pamphlet about a camp to train the mentally gifted to be Psychonauts. Unfortunately, you are not one of them.

name: Book of Genetics
description: This book will teach you everything you need to know about genetics!

name: Chunk of Eridium
description: A priceless alien mineral. Don't eat it though; you won't get super powers.

name: "Nice" Fedora
description: A plain fedora. It looks exactly like the hat you made it from, but... for some reason, you're not really sure you can bring yourself to wear this one.

name: Attack on Titanic DVD
description: A movie about a huge boat under siege from even huger ice monsters.  Somehow you doubt it will end happily.

name: Sour Grape Electric Holocaust Fruit Gusher
description: Note: Not actually a fruit gusher. Do not attempt to consume.

name: God Tier Undergarments
description: Oh dear. This was a bad idea. Now you have pajamas that show off all your -ahem- assets. Wear them if you want? I guess you could seduce those imps to death.

name: Pimpin\' Planar Physicist Pitcher
description: This is it, we've reached the pinnacle of the fusion of cards, science and absurdity. It's a gun that fires physicists with infinite mass that yell catchphrases such as "E equals m c squared!" then throw cards that explode into supernovas and then collapse into black holes. Then everything is spaghettified together, scientists and enemies alike. Crazy.

name: Fruit Punch
description: How you even made these artificial fruit-infused gloves is a mystery, but a face full of Gushers is sure to make a smoothie out of your enemies.

name: Bestiary Bomb
description: This grenade contains a multitude of miniature paper monsters, complete with razor-sharp claws and teeth. They can strip a cow to the bone in under two minutes.

name: Dodobaith - Legendary Shield of the Gods
description: This shield has existed for a long, long time and belonged to many heroes. Through the centuries, it has gathered the blessings of many gods. It's best known with its Welsh name, Dodobaith, but the Greeks called it Elpidophora. Both names mean "Bringer of Hope". Behold, o dark ones, and despair!

name: God Tier Cakeridan
description: Okay, maybe alchemizing a powerful confectionary weapon with the pajamas of a god was a bad idea. You begin to think that this cake may be more powerful than you are.

name: Big Ball of Infinite Cash
description: You will become rich in no time from the massive amounts of cash made by this weapon. that is assuming that you survive using it.

name: Ball of Infinite Gold
description: This is too heavy to use in one hand but drops huge amounts of cash per kill.

name: Ball of King Midas
description: Fortunately you are immune to turning into gold from this weapon due to the fact that you are using it.

name: String of the Death God
description: An ethereal floating pitch dark string that once belonged to the Death God. One can either pluck it, as it produces the most ominous sound known to humanity, or draw it like a bow's string and shoot darts of deathly energy. Whichever way you use it, it's intoxicating. Literally.

name: Fear No Scratch
description: A combination of a cue/pen and a hammer of Time, this weapon resembles a pool cue with a flashing stripe running along its side and a gold tip. The hammer head has been replaced by a red pool ball made of garnet with a button on it (which when clicked, allows for the weapon to turn into a smaller, pen version). Small clock hands surround the pool ball, and blows from it seem to stop time...

name: Explosive Black Claws of Oglogoth
description: Claws that draw power from the Green Sun and the Horrorterrors of the furthest ring. If that wasn't already enough, they make things they scratch explode too! Just gotta make sure that you don't accidently cut yourself on them.

name: Sharpened Steel Crayons
description: The only logical thing to do with something made of steel is to sharpen it, right?

name: Universe Wrecker of Universal Wrath
description: This axe is powered by wrath. The fact that it induces rage therefore makes it even more powerful. The field of fury it emits is so strong that even your enemies are influenced by it. With a weapon this powerful, you can pretty literally "hate a hole in paradox space".

name: Chocolate-Scented Flame Darts
description: These darts are just as fiery and pointy, but are now also laced with the delicious scent of chocolate. Now if only you could eat these...

name: Roulette Claws
description: Someone stuck a huge, metal d20 on a pair of gloves and called it claws. It weighs as much as a roulette table. This is just ridiculous.

name: BreathFG65535
description: If you thought you couldn't get a stronger weapon, you didn't make the projectiles create hurricane-force gales and focused blasts of air capable of piercing an anti-bombardment bunker. It also has a mode to shoot fragmentation explosive missiles with the same effect.

name: Rose Cape
description: A cape is good but a rose cape is better. Sure you look like a flower and have thorns on your back but at least you look like one no one wants to touch.

name: Left Arm Mega Drill
description: A large single arm drill covered in spiked rivets for tearing through anything you wish. This nifty left arm drill has the power of a Big Daddy with the capability to pierce the heavens!

name: Wisp of the Ancients
description: This pale green fan adorned in white blossoms feels like it radiates with the life essence of the Planet. One flick of the wrist and you'll feel as if you could speak to your Planet itself. You suddenly feel like you're the last hope of preventing a meteor from hitting your world. (Oh, wait...)

name: Twinklefucker
description: You thought it couldn't get awesomer. You were wrong.

name: Overseer Bladekind Retaliation
description: With the unending rain of bladekind items still continuing the developers needed to take action. With this weapon you fight with the ferocity of a cloud of blades against overused weapons and underlings alike.

name: Grey keychain
description: How is this useful in any way? Maybe you could throw it an an enemy?

name: Ecto Blue Bean Bag Chair
description: A nice squishy bean bag chair to suffocate your enemies in.

name: Legendary Piece of Shit
description: You thought you couldn't make something even shittier, but you were wrong. You've made a literal, steaming pile of badly drawn fecal matter. Good job.

name: Solar Sheep Plush
description: A toy sheep, powered by the same mechanism that makes the sun glow. This gives it the ability to explode with a hell of a ton of energy, releasing several little particles of luck. Unbeknownst to many, however, luck is highly deadly by inhalation to Denizens and their underlings. And imps need to breathe.

name: White Paper Binding Wand / White Hieroglyph Handgun
description: Etched down the side of this ivory wand/gun are indecipherable blood-red runes, along with some strange wing-like symbols. The bullets inside the handgun are pleasingly pleated oblong paper bullets, whereas the wand shoots paper chains with scarlet diamond marks along the sides. You get a feeling that this gun is very old.

name: Dread Wand
description: This weapon has the power of fear, corruption, and malice. It fills you with a sense of dread and emptiness.

name: Silly Paper Hat
description: It's a slightly crumpled paper hat folded from instructions you found once on the internet, then promptly forgot about, and probably sat on once or twice. You kinda wanna do a little dance with it on.

name: The Game Glomper
description:
Now you can beat the shit out of real enemies, and beat the shit out of virtual ones too!
Modern science sure is great!

name: Corpse Party CD
description: Description: A game involving the plight of nine people as they become trapped in a haunted elementary school from the past. Stuck with no way out, they must endure trials and tribulations as they attempt to come together and escape... But will they survive?

name: Amnesia: The Dark Descent
description: The hit survival horror game. For the love of god, don't alchemise it with your SBURB game disk.

name: Tinglefucker
