description: The Wrinklefucker, combined with the fans' sheer haterage towards Tingle, caused them to shit and then have sloppy makeouts with the miles of rage snake that created this monstrosity.

name: Sound of Genesis
description: This sphere is capable of emanating a sound unheard since the creation of this universe: the sound of Genesis itself. It's the sound of the birth of everything, yet no one can hear it without dying. Aside from the wielder, that is.

name: Compu-knives
description: These futuristic computerized knives allow access to all kinds of knowledge - including the best ways to cut things apart.

name: Omni-blades
description: Because if there's anything that small, arm-mounted computers needed, it was knives.

name: Dapper R.O.B. the Robot
description: Still the loveable, slow, noisy, R.O.B., but now with a hat and the personality of a gentlemen!

name: Aperture Science Goggles of Omnipotent Portal Travel
description: These nifty Goggles can make a portal anywhere - even in the air. With these on, you can see all and go there too! Also it's pretty to mess about and trap imps in never ending free falls.

name: Legend of Spyro: Year of Dragon
description: A game involving a purple dragon and a cheetah as they venture through forgotten worlds and save the dragon eggs that were stolen by some wizard or something.

name: Spellcharged Darts
description: These darts hum with various minor spells, and some of them give you shocks when you touch them.

name: Bibidi-Babidi-Aperture Ballgown and Overcoat
description: A metallic white ballgown with a similarly colored overcoat sewn onto it with wires - It'll get you into the company ball for sure!

name: Battery Acid Knife
description: A basic butcher's knife laced with battery acid. Slice someone with this and they're not going to do very well.

name: Syringe of Rat Poison
description: Ah, that's more like it! Now this syringe packs a punch that all rats should fear.

name: Draw-It-Yourself Prophecy Cards
description: Tarot Cards! It looks like you can draw your own designs on them, too. Fun!

name: Time Scepter/Time Rifle
description: This weapon has the ability to morph from a red scepter with a garnet gem on top, to a red rifle that when shot has a small chance to slow down time, giving you a perfect chance to cap those imps!

name: Grandma\'s Favorite Handbag
description: Ah, a simple black leather handbag... on the outside at least. The contents inside are a mystery. Whatever's inside must weigh more than a bowling ball. What the hell is in there?!

name: Kung Dew Staff
description: A weapon that hails from the ancient Mountains of rural Dewia, there is hardly a more culturally myopic weapon.

name: Yoshitop
description: It looks like a laptop themed around your best ridable dinosaur childhood friend!

name: Entrance to a Pocket Dimension
description: This door seems to warp about the edges, and seems to be infinitely large, yet tiny at the same time. Perhaps you should go in?

name: Time Traveler\'s Pocket Digiwatch
description: A pocket watch for only the most pretentious and impractical Time Traveler!

name: Time Traveler\'s Digi-Wristwatch
description: Look absolutely douchey with this application meant for practical Time Travelers! (Of which you meet neither criterion, POOPLORD.)

name: Analogue clock
description:
Just like a digital clock! Except it seems to have a face, two hands and makes a really cool sound-
*ticktockticktockticktockticktockticktock*

name: Oversized Omnipotent Particle Accelerator of the Omnipresent and Omniscient Squiddle Conqueror
description: An obscenely large, mechanical Squiddle doll (you think? That's certainly what it looks like) of demonic power with one new twist: The wands shoot out subatomic particles in addition to time magic. As if this wasn't bad enough in and of itself, some of these particles are capable of messing with time itself. Like tachyons and shit. NOT RECOMMENDED FOR CHILDREN 5 AND UNDER.

name: Paradox Space Gym Badges
description: You have confined Paradox Space into these tiny little Gym badges. They glow with the lives (and deaths) of millions, and you stuck it in some Pokmon badges. Congratulations.

name: Magic Wings
description: Wow! These wings are imbued with the magic power of special stardust! You can't actually use them to fly, though.

name: Computer Knives
description: A pair of knives, that seem to give off an electrical shock when stabbed into something - directed towards whatever it is stabbed into, of course.

name: Crochet Cherry Blossom Beanie
description: Keeps you warm and stylish while you strife. May make you look younger than you are.

name: Yoshi The Dinosaur Thongtop
description: This quirky piece of lingerie is perfecting for keeping things fresh in the bedroom whilst ruining any lover's childhood. It's also a computer because I guarantee you're not going to be doing anything in bed but blogging.

name: Wreck-it Ralph Hands
description: These are just big boxing gloves designed to look like Wreck-It Ralph's massive hands.

name: Friendship Journal
description:
A rather thick tome about the adventures of pastel equines and their conclusions regarding friendship.
Which isn't an emotion.

name: How the Once-Ler stole Christmas
description:
Oh hey your favorite boo-
This is not How The Grinch stole christmas.

name: Perpetual Spinning Top
description: This small toy allows you to tell whether or not you're dreaming, for it will spin infinitely within one. This would be handy, were it not for you always know when you're dreaming nowadays.

name: Screwed-Up News
description: This paper screwdriver has images of black and white Sonic emblazoned across it. The only problem is that sometimes it passes through enemies... and also it reminds you of that god-awful game.

name: Sweet Blues
description: A cool instrument for a very cool artist. It emits a soothing tune of destruction.

name: Godly Cymbals
description: Cymbals representing the gods.  Or maybe cymbals for attacking gods, you're not really sure.

name: Bosscrow
description: You had to do it, you just had to make this pun a reality. You can fire fake crows at your enemies from this crossbow, though.

name: edit nunerr 2
description: ahahahahha now we are changing things

name: Paul Bunyan\'s Woodcutting Axe
description: In theory, this is used for cutting down trees. In practice, it's almost as large as the trees already. Then again, you've been fighting things much larger than trees in your time here...

name: Yoyo of Divine Protection
description: With this yoyo, you possess the reaction time of Mercury himself!

name: Cherenkov Radiation Hammer
description: A hammer that glows like a miniature Chernobyl. You definitely need some lead gloves to handle this.

name: The Binding of Isaac game disk
description: A game about an innocent child suddenly thrown into a morbid world in which horrifying creatures are out to kill him. Thus he uses items to ascend to god-like levels of power.

name: Fresh Steel Hat
description: Now you don't need to worry about your health, appearance, OR your smell.

name: Formal Headlampset
description: Now you can see where you're going, talk with your friends, and look fancy all at the same time!

name: Diabolical Sunglasses
description: This pair of glasses allows you to see into the realm of hell. Plus, because they're sunglasses, the brightness of all of the lava doesn't hurt your eyes!

name: Nuclear Battery
description: A nearly never-ending power source.  Don't drop it too forcefully though; you've already survived one apocalypse but a second one might not be so kind.

name: Mopcoat
description: Now you look like a Wookie or a living haystack or something.

name: Common Sense
description: You would question how common sense is a physical thing you can captchalogue, but you feel that by the end of this ordeal, it'll be one of the more reasonable, sensible, understandable things you'll have encountered.

name: Song of the Lioness Boxed Set
description: Wallop underlings with all the force of Tortall's first lady knight!

name: The Immortals Boxed Set
description: No, using these books won't let you talk to animals.

name: Protector of the Small Boxed Set
description: Channel Kel's strength as you wield this book against your foes.

name: Ecto-Cutters
description: A pair of ghastly, ghostly cutting emplements sure to strike fear into the heart of all, whether phamtasmic or corporeal.

name: Freeze Ray
description: Stop your enemies in their tracks!

name: Electron Ray
description: A pocket ray gun which doubles as a laser pointer. Don't just blind pilots, take their eyes out!

name: Tesla\'s Chain-Coil
description: A lost experiment of Tesla's that combines the rotation of a chainsaw and the power source of tesla coils. Electrifying, burning, and sawing has never been so fun!

name: Halloween Skewer
description: For some reason, you feel like this was never here, yet know it is. It also seems to get some kind glowy aura during Halloween, and you swear that you're seeing ghosts.

name: Mind Laserglasses
description: These glasses' lenses glow with mint green light. They are capable of controlling minds, not to mention firing blasts of mental energy.

name: Witch Queen\'s Crown
description: Does it belong to a witch who is a queen, or a queen who rules over witches? Either way, it's big, pointy, and covered in jewels. Feels vaguely magical, to boot.

name: Robo-Betsy 3.0
description: With your great thinking,you have made... ROBO-BETSY 3.0! The ultimate warriorcrow! Sadly, sticking electronic bits to a dead crow doesn't really do anything, rendering this completely pointless. At least it looks cool.

name: Flame-throwing Trombone
description: A trombone with a flamethrower mechanism. Why would anyone need this?

name: Time Rocket Board
description: Now you can time travel and have fun while doing it. You are thrashing up so many Hellacious stunts it should be illegal! Shit is flying OFF THE HOOK! Its like shit wants nothing to do with that hook! Wooooooooooooooooo.................oooooooooooooooo!

name: Computing Axe
description: An axe that also functions as a computer. The screen is on the blade of the axe, so be careful when you hit things with this!

name: Penwand
description: A blurring of lines between penkind and wandkind. Magical Ink!

name: Star Projector
description: This large sphere projects light through small gaps, making stars appear on the walls of your room.

name: Gamer\'s Jersey
description: Only worn by the most hardcore game-jocks, this jersey grants the user the highest level of nerdiness: UBER-NERD.

name: Soul Wand
description: As you hold the wand, you hear the souls of the deceased crying out around you. Not recommended for Light or Life players.

name: The Ogreseer
description: This is his swamp.

name: A Clockwork Orange
description: Provided your improvised Russian is good enough, reading this novella aloud will cause your enemies to tremble and experience nausea.

name: Ultimate Freezing Ray
description: If you ever wanted a ray capable of freezing enemies to death, here you have it.

name: Pizza Pizza Cutter
description: A cutter made from pizza, for pizza. Hopefully not by pizza though. That'd make things even more bizzarre.

name: Time Traveler\'s Digi-Stopwatch
description: Honestly, how do you suppose you're going to improve when you can stop time-making any attempts at accurately measuring your embetterment null.

name: Megaflame
description: A megaphone that, when shouted into, emits intense heat and flame based on how loud the sound it detected was.

name: Mechaflame
description: A flame-spewing megaphone upgraded with robot parts. Fortunately, the mechanical bits make enough noise that you don't have to shout yourself hoarse.

name: Grist displayer
description: A headset with a screen covering your eye. The display shows the type of grist you can loot from underlings you're looking at. But... didn't you already know that?

name: Spacey As Fuq Unscratchable Cardigan
description: A thick black fabric with blurry white spirals dancing across it, this hooded cardigan manipulates physics to appear diamond hard from the outside and absorb impacts. It's plush lime lining guarantees a warm and cozy fighting experience.

name: Aviator\'s Scarf
description: A white silk scarf that flaps behind pilots dramatically in cartoons.

name: Tombrose
description: A tombstone chiseled to look like a rose.  For flower funerals.

name: Resizer
description: Capable of bending space itself, this gizmo, a puzzling fusion of microscope and compass with the colors of Space, can resize about anything, including enemies!

name: Shrink Ray
description: A laser that'll... take these boys down a notch. Why don't they pick on someone their own size! You're looking a little small, is it cold out?

name: Chicken Noodle Dice
description: Cubes of chicken noodle soup, frozen into the shape of dice.  Should be fine as long as they don't thaw out...

name: Swiss Army Scythe
description: A long stick, with many compact blades on the end. More for brutally impaling things on various pointy bits of metal than cutting wheat now.

name: Skull Trumpet
description: A happy little low-quality skull playing some low-quality doots on a low-quality trumpet. Doot doot.

name: Hand Grenade Launcher
description: ...wait, this thing is firing literal hand grenades, pin and all. They don't blow unless you make them explode yourself. This is almost useless, although the impact of the grenade does sting a bit.

name: Nuclear Mechaflame
description: A nuclear-powered robotic megaphone that shoots flames from the mouth. This is so going to give you radiation poisoning.

name: Hard-Boiled Flutevolver
description: This gun's revolving chamber is filled with six miniature flutes. Whenever you blow into the mouthpiece, one of the flutes shoots an abstraction of a musical note at your target, with lethal effect.

name: Poisonous Clarinet
description: Now the deadliest part about it isn't the horrible sounds it makes! Only trained professionals should play this instrument. Don't breathe in through it, or else...

name: Jump Scare Mirror
description: It seems to be a perfectly generic mirror but every now and then the image of a ghostly lady appears in it for a split second. Perhaps you can scare enemies with it?

name: Golden Whip of Santa\'s Hair
description: Ho ho ho! Look what Santa brought you this year! A whip made of his shining, golden hairs! How did he know this is what you wanted for Christmas this year?

name: Blue Glowing Ghost Paintbrush
description: It's kinda squishy! This is not a paintbrush used by ghosts, rather to paint them. Often as blobs. May contain adverse side effects; please do not consume, taste, touch, or otherwise allow contact with the wet end of this brush.

name: Weaponized Protest Sign
description: With this fancy sign you promote the use of not using weapons. However, if people don't listen it also doubles as a weapon itself!

name: Indestructable Alloy Sai
description: Gold, copper, and silver make up the metal of the weapon. It's both real pretty and real sharp; you should probably watch out so you don't poke yourself.

name: Smoke Weed Everytime
description: A Pocketwatch that not only smells like cannabis, but only displays the time 4:20. You suppose it's right 2 time a day... Everyday...

name: Obsidian Guitar
description: This pitch-black guitar almost looks as if it is the shadow of where a guitar once was or should be.

name: Chained and Bladed Seer\'s Gown
description: It's a seer's gown covered in chains and blades that make it REALLY uncomfortable and REALLY hard to move, but you guess anything that comes near you will get skewered before they can touch you. Probably.

name: Diamond of Abraxas
description: This gem glows with a faint yellow light. You feel hopeful just holding it!

name: Gamer\'s Whip
description: A flexible and fast whip for any gamer! This weapon can be controlled through clunky looking equipment. You'll look like the perfect dork while using this!

name: Heat Rod
description: A model of the OZ-13MS Gundam Epyon's whip-like weapon. It consists of grey segmented chains that form a whip! It's hot to the touch, and you feel as if it could melt anything!

name: Electric Candlestick
description: Because fire is so neanderthal. Or gothic. You're at the very least neo-gothic.

name: Flaming Barb-Whip
description: A hazardous weapon, barbed and on fire! Only an expert can wield this without hurting themselves.

name: Halloween Tombscythe That Is Also A Spear Because Fuck It
description: Just cramming more weapons into your weapons in the hopes that it'll make something better is surely the way to go.

name: Crystal-Powered Candlestick
description: A regular power source was far too dull and short-lasting for this great adventure.

name: Amethyst-Encrusted Gold Nightgown
description: A golden nightgown with pretty purple jewels on it. It's a bit heavy though.

name: Fatherly Suit of the 80s
description: Expect to BUST A MOVE with this RADICAL suit! It's a little flashy, but comfortable.

name: Sham-ROCK
description: This sweet green guitar is only capable of playing songs by Irish groups for some reason.

name: Cherubim Laser Cannon
description: Once you replaced the cannon's focusing crystal, the beam has not only gotten more powerful. The beam now flashes red and green for some reason.

name: Golden Tiara
description: Now you can feel royal AND ostentatious!

name: Green Sun-Glasses
description: Now you can protect yourself from the harmful Green Sun's rays!

name: Tacgnol Scarf
description: A scarf that looks like a black cat run through a taffy puller.

name: Tome of Infinite Recursion
description: A book describing how it describes itself describing how it describes itself describing itself. There are probably even more layers to it, but you kind of got bored and gave up after the first chapter.

name: Magnetic Weasel
description: A fridge magnet in the shape of one of the citizens from a great imaginary kingdom. Prone to flipping the fuck out and falling off whatever surface you attach it to, although you suppose that could just be the magnet not being very strong.

name: Phantom Slicer
description: A scythe with an intangible spirit blade, designed for cleaving souls rather than flesh.

name: Double-Edged Throwing Scythe
description: A scythe with a knife for a handle. Cut your foes with the scythe end and throw the knife end straight into their faces. You can't possibly imagine what could go wrong with using this. Nope, absolutely nothing comes to mind.

name: Radioactive Mechaflame
description: In addition to shooting huge flames from the mouth, this nuclear-powered megaphone now irradiates everything nearby. Lead gloves not included.

name: Police Spectacles
description: Eyewear that flashes red and blue light. Pretty annoying, but maybe you can blind some imps with it?

name: Black Harvest
description: A black-bladed scythe hollowed-out to store more souls. With each swing you can hear them screaming inside.

name: Red Dry-Erase Marker
description: A marker used for writing and drawing on dry-erase boards, drawing boards, and the like. Can also be used to doodle embarrassing things onto the faces of your enemies and friends alike.

name: Seraphic Autohunter
description: A gleaming white weapon, this Seraphic gunbow is made of a bow attached to the barrel of a gun. Just one press of the diamond trigger and dozens of gleaming white and gold arrows are launched towards the forces of darkness.

name: Godly Flute of Restoration
description: This flute has been used during gatherings on Mount Olympus, and has an otherworldly healing effect.

name: Ungodly Woodwind of Leeching
description: This unrecognizable woodwind instrument is known for its leeching songs, which decay the player's enemies, yet rejuvenates the player and their allies.

name: Sparkly Dry-Erase Marker
description: This dry-erase marker leaves behind only sparkly red marks now. Nothing has ever been written so glamorously before.

name: hOPY shIT
description: the SHIT pile doesn't stop form getting TALLEr....

name: Tron Shirt
description: A white T with the futuristic TRON logo pressed on it in glow-in-the-dark ink.

name: Oar Naw
description: This executioner's ax makes you think whether oar not you are making the right choice. also let's you row

name: Fangs of Color
description: There is abundant lore on the power of the rainbow and the hope it brings. This one comes in actual weapon form.

name: Demonic Instrument of Pain
description: This instrument, forged by the ashes of the evil and unholy, has a structure like no other. The sound that floods out of it can only be heard by the most dreadful of beings, as it is the last thing they hear before they perish and are banished to the deep fiery pits of hell.

name: Flame-shredder and Nuclear Loudspeaker
description: This guitar creates such intense solos that the built-in speaker shoots flames whenever you use it!

name: Plague Reaper
description: A loathsome tool of death perpetually coated in toxic gasses and barbs. It can be just as dangerous to its wielder as to its victims.

name: Rainbow Marker
description: This marker is specially designed to release ink that forms the color pattern of a perfect rainbow. It's so complicated that it confuses the heck out of your enemies while you draw all over them!

name: Electr-Ink Light Marker
description: When used to write, the ink left by this marker glows as if powered by microscopic lanterns. Which it is. It leaves a shocking impression on enemies, and even has a nifty light bulb at the end!

name: Mirror of Fear
description: This mirror shows a mutilated image of whoever it's reflecting and then transforms its target into its reflection.

name: Temporal-Ink PenGlove
description: A pair of gloves with pen tips at the ends of the fingers, for writing and drawing with maximum efficiency. The ink is specially made to resist the flow of time, and often causes paradoxes by suddenly appearing in the past after being used!

name: Italy\'s Finest
description: A violin strung with fresh Italian spaghetti- just like-a mama used to make it! Some say when it is played, you can hear the songs of old Italian grandmothers singing to their grandchildren. Others say you hear nothing since spaghetti isn't the best material for strings.

name: Nrub\'yiglith\'s Tongues
description: Crackling with an ominous aura, this once holy bowgun has been tainted by the whispers of the Noble Circle of Horrorterrors. Instead of shooting holy arrows, this black and purple weapon fires small thorns instead.

name: Distortion Mirror
description: A mirror that reflects the spirit world rather than the physical world. Wait, can't ghosts travel through mirrors or something...?

name: Archfiend-Summoning Woodwind of Hell
description: "Music is made one of Satan's most attractive agencies to ensnare souls; but, when turned to a good account, it is a blessing. When abused, it leads the unconsecrated to pride, vanity, and folly."

name: Flaming Knifeboard
description: This looks like a normal musical keyboard, but pushing any key results in a pair of flaming butcher's knives shooting out of the back. Never has Mozart's Fifth been so terrifying.

name: Draghumov CPN
description: A daffodil rifle, themed after Prospit, with a kazoo as the scope for some reason. You guess it can't hurt. Maybe you can use it to alarm your enemies before you shoot them or something?

name: Lash of Piercing Flames
description: Now you can slice your foes into pieces and cauterize the wounds before you faint at the sight of blood.

name: Draconic Guitar with Fire-breathing Loudspeaker
description: This reptilian guitar is strung with steel forged in the fires of dragon's breath and is plucked with a pick carved from a dragon fang. The built-in loudspeaker breathes fire, too!

name: Heavenly Woodwind of Rejuvenating
description: This unrecognizable woodwind instrument is known for its rejuvenating songs, which mellow the player's enemies and heals the player and their allies.

name: Flaming Guitar of Dragons and AI Loudspeaker
description: A bright red guitar with a dragon motif. Whenever you play a chord, the guitar shoots fire everywhere and the artificial intelligence in the loudspeaker calculates the sound most damaging to your foes. Always have a fire extinguisher ready and make sure to wear earbuds while playing, unless you want to deafen and burn yourself for some reason.

name: Space-Time Marker
description: A writing utensil that defies space-time and can be used to write anywhere, any-when. Of course, you can't predict or control the where and when your writing will appear, but at least it's a nice red colored ink.

name: Troll Dragon Guitar with Tyrannical loudspeaker
description: Now you too can play the Alternian Empire's anthem, complete with the explosions, flames, and screams of your dying enemies!

name: Flower Power Leotard
description: You don't think that pinning a flower to your leotard will help against an imp's attacks, but it sure looks pretty.

name: Killer Knife-Shooting Ghoulboard
description: An obscenely weaponised musical keyboard that has an uneasy air to it. It seems to be sentient, somehow? The knives it shoots seem just as alive, somehow homing in on their target(s) and twisting about once inside. It's kind of gruesome, but hard not to watch. And you can't help but feel like things watch you from inside of the keyboard itself from time to time...

name: God\'s Circlet
description: A faint glow shimmers from this royal headpiece. It makes you feels as if someone is protecting you.

name: Mushroom
description: It a toadstool, you can't really see what kind of mushroom this is, but it might be edible?

name: Sylph\'s Killing Salve
description: For when good Sylphs go bad and decide to kill all their friends with death mixed with lotion, ignoring the fact that this mixture typically doesn't permeate the skin.

name: Blue Ecto-Syrup
description: Drinking directly from the bottle is still considered sloppy and rude, but it's not like there's anyone around to reprimand you for that.

name: Cookie
description: Now who left this sitting out?

name: Mushie
description: A mushroom cookie! Who would have thought this would taste just like a regular cookie? You wonder who thought to put mushrooms in baked goods, and why.

name: Fruit Gushers - Spectral Lich Soul flavour
description: Spectral Lich Soul flavoured Fruit Gushers. Consumption can give you immortality, diabetes and tear your soul apart.

name: Heretic Crumple Armor
description: This armor is nigh-useless, shielding you completely from salamanders, contrabands and cruxite. The sheats and hat are adorned with the coat of arms of a large spirograph on the front, and a bubble on the back. What a waste of grist.

name: Cruxite Nectar
description: It's a liquid form of cruxite. You can't be sure it's safe to consume... but when has that ever stopped you?

name: Lady Bow\'s Bow
description: A bow which shoots little ghosts at your enemies. Surprisingly effective, although the green one keeps calling you an urchin for some reason.

name: Mountain Dew: Code Red Flavour
description: The obscenely popular... pop. The spiritual ancestor of the first flavour variation of Mountain Dew. And it tastes pretty good, too. Almost like it's empowering you.

name: Hatcage Nicu
description: A plush of everyones favorite fictional Japanese singer, Nicolas Cage.

name: Oxygen
description: You guess these are all zeros? Or are they capital O's? Zeros would probably make more sense for an empty card, you think.

name: Light\'s Cards of Fortune
description: A truly beautiful tarot deck. Engraved in small, gold letters on the border of each card are those words: "Born and blessed by the Light / We shall win every fight / Destiny in our hands / Power that never ends"

name: Axeshank
description: It's a simple woodcutting axe with a spear sticking out of its hilt for double the stabbing!

name: Blocky Computer
description: This computer looks like...well...a cube. That doesn't stop it from running Sburb, but the graphics are really low-res.

name: Mariner\'s Muffler
description: Once the scarf of a great whaler, this long cotton weave is imbued with the confidence of a traveled navigator and will flap behind you in high winds. Also, if you tense your brow and pout staring at the horizon, will make it look like you know where you're going.

name: Eggheadbeater
description: A skull on a stick with eggbeaters coming out of the eye sockets, so illogical eggheads don't know what to do

name: Hard-light Controller
description: With this you will be able to create objects out of light and then control them with presses of buttons.

name: AV Cables
description: These three cables can send video up to the "crisp" resolution of 480i alongside real stereo audio! Now featuring gold plated connectors. You aren't watching TV until you go AV!

name: Mack-Hammer
description: This Pogo Hammer upgrade resembles the first boss of a certain video game. It still retains it's ability to be pogo-y. Some say that it even contains the very spirit of Mack himself! That's probably bullshit though, because Mack isn't real, he's just in a video game. It does make the weapon sound cooler though.

name: Blood Quill of the Ancient Dwarves
description: Created from the molten flesh of dwarves burning away at themselves to become fire-proof, this quill contains what might be the fully unlocked power of Armok, the Denizen of Blood.

name: x0
description: Oh great, you've captchalogued the concept of nothing. You're not sure whether to be concerned or proud.

name: Hydrophone
description: A microphone designed to be used underwater for recording or listening to underwater sound. Now you can be part of their world by singing with the fishes.

name: Angelic Instrument of Well-being
description: This instrument, forged by the prayers of the good and holy, has a structure like no other. The sound that floods out of it can only be heard by the most dreadful of beings, as it is the last thing they hear before they perish and are forbidden entrance to the holy land of heaven.

name: Auto-Cruxite Blaster
description: A machine gun with a feed for Cruxite Dowel ammo and another feed for soda. The gun crushes up the Dowel and rains the blue chunks onto your enemies with it's Automatic Soda-fire System.

name: Reformed Reaper
description: A scythe once widely-feared and dreaded among the dead, now seeking redemption for its past wrongdoings. It is now the guardian of souls rather than a glutton of souls.

name: Gilded Space-Time Writing Utensil  of the Lily
description: This writing utensil works like a marker, writing in an ink-like substance, but looks and otherwise feels like a pencil. Except that it's covered in gold and radiates energy that permeates Space-Time. The opposite end has an ink-erasing tool shaped like a beautiful lily.

name: Light-Providing-Saber
description: This nifty tool is like a lightsaber... Only with less cutting, and more light-shining. The "blade" glows yellow and feels only slightly warm when you pass your hand through it. Still, staring directly into the light when it's on could put an eye out!

name: Demonic Strings of Cage
description: A terribly unwieldy violin shaped like Nic Cage, complete with a bow also shaped like Nic Cage. Its strings produce hellishly distorted screams of "NOT THE BEES!" and "HOW'D IT GET BURNT?!" Some people would find this impractical. They would be wrong.

name: Twilight Reaver / Soul Shackle
description: The blade frees the soul from the body, whilst the chain binds it eternally to its new master's service.

name: Scarlet Soda-claws
description: NoW ArEn't tHeSe tHiNgS MiRaCuLoUs , lIkE, mOtHeRfUcKiNg cLaWs mAdE Of fAyGo  MeTaL, hAhAhA So mOtHeRfUcKiNg AwEsOmE

name: Megaton Jumping d4 on a Stick
description: This special "hammer" jumps around on it's own. It ends in a spike that it always lands on after jumping, then gravity makes it fall to one of the four possible sides of the "die." It just looks like a cube with a spike on one end attached to a stick, but it certainly is heavy. Now that you think about it, it looks a lot like a dreidel. Albeit one that jumps around on its own and punctures enemies.

name: VR Set
description: A legendary device, capable of putting you into a fake reality. Crafted with utmost care, it is said that it flows with the strongest power in the known universe. Of course that's all shit, the stuff that flows through this is shit, and this thing will probably turn out to be shit too.

name: Crocker-Seas-All Tiaratop
description: The lack [CONSUME] of propaganda in this is quite surprising for this brand! Your mind has access to the [STAY ASLEEP] sights, sounds, and even smells throughout the Incipishere! And none of it is being broadcast to the Betty Crocker Corporation. None of it.

name: d20 Needlewands
description: These wands have d20's as their base. Every time you attack with them, it rolls both of them, and is more powerful based on the roll.

name: Ataraxia Witch Hat
description: A large perfectly white pointed hat. It glows softly and you feel calmer holding it, like you're more aware and in control of your life. Plus it's obviously magic so that's a plus.

name: Katamari Dice
description: This special die has a sticky surface, and can get bigger by rolling around. It does make it harder to see what the result of your roll is though.

name: Fire Hook
description: Despite the cool name, this item is not a hook of fire, but rather a fire poker made into a sickle-like hook! While it might not be as useful for poking fires anymore, but maybe slicing monsters!

name: Marcus Munitions Slingshot
description: This item has a No-Money Back guarantee from Marcus Himself. WARNING: May cause Burning, Shocking and/or Death

name: Gushers-brand Amulet
description: An amulet with a stone shaped exactly like a fruit Gusher. Apparently, the stone actually is a giant fruit Gusher. Don't eat it unless you plan on wearing a plain golden chain.

name: Gold Necklace
description: A necklace made of pure gold. Hopefully it'll at least blunt any attacks aimed at your neck.

name: Staff of Snakes
description: This snake-shaped staff is only for those worthy of the Slytherin house. Contrary to popular belief, even Muggles can wield it if they are worthy.

name: Troll Stamp
description: An American stamp with a troll's face on it. It appears to be a badly-drawn image of Karkat.

name: Rainbow Squiddle
description: This little guy is so cute, with his multicolored tentacles and his.. gaping.. maw.. oh gods please don't kill mE I HAVE A FAMIL-

name: Thousand-Sided Fantastic Die
description: This die has 1,000 sides, each of which is a different color. There don't appear to be any numbers on the faces, but it seems to work on a luck basis just like if it did. It shimmers in the light.

name: Snake\'s Fang
description: A sickle-like weapon shaped like a snake's fang. For some reason you feel like stabbing a book with this will solve some big deadly problem...

name: Hard-light Starcraft Controller
description: Now you have hard-light starcraft units to control. It is a pity that it cannot decide on one so it is just a scrambled form of several at a time.

name: Necronomicon for Summoning the Ontologically Ornery
description: This book is bound in human flesh and reeks of pure, virulent evil. If you want to initiate a zombie apocalypse, say hello to your new best friend.

name: Zombie\'s Flesh Coat
description: Used by zombies during the brain wars.

name: Barber Chisel
description: A chisel that can sculpt hair as if it was stone. A great way to sculpt your beard: a must-have for manscaping.

name: Meaty Meat Hook
description: Used to hold organs and whole animals in butcher's shops, the meat hook is a sharp and possibly dangerous tool normally attached to a chain. This one is just stuck into a slab of meat.

name: Ducky Chemistry Kit
description: Ever wanted to mess around with the element Duckiurm? Probably not...

name: Honey-Tov Murican-Tail
description: Not only is this jar of exploding honey full of 'murican dreams, but it also now fires into a bunch of exploding fireworks that come together to form the 'murican flag.

name: Frost Jack Deck
description: This frozen deck of tarot cards are imprinted with the cute little ice demon from Persona 4.

name: Turned-Up Trumpet
description: A regular trumpet with an amplifier wedge in. Now you can boldly blare your brass beats at an even higher volume than before!

name: Monopoly
description: Everyone's favorite board game! Or bored game, perhaps.  You never were really sure with this one.

name: Ladder
description: A simple ladder, for climbing to high places.

name: Chutes and Ladders
description: Try to move forward, rather than back, so that you can be the first one to reach 100!

name: Candy Land
description: Fight through trials and tribulations to rescue the king of this saccharine world! Or...something like that. You're pretty sure you haven't touched this since you were five.

name: Checkers
description: Capture your opponent's pieces before they take all of yours.

name: Ddraig Tarian Helmed
description: This helmet holds all the power of a dragon, along with the power of unpronounceable welsh words. At least you THINK it's welsh. You never really were a language buff.

name: Essence of Freedom
description: This is literally freedom. If you equip this as a weapon, you will be beating your enemies to death with freedom. Just like America!

name: Pathfinder Players\' Guide
description: An important resource for anyone who wants to play the pathfinder roleplaying game.

name: Swiss Gunblades of Elemental Power
description: A pair of Swiss Army knives, except instead of knives, they have knife/gun combinations. One is frozen, one is almost too hot to handle, and sparks constantly leap from one to the other. You're not entirely sure how safe these are to handle, but they're effective enough at killing enemies.

name: Gasickle
description: A sickle with a constantly burning layer of gasoline on it... don't lick it! It's not that kind of sickle!

name: Very Loud Dark Matter Knife
description: This specific knife is made out of dark matter, which is dangerous in and of itself, but it also can create an extremely loud sound that pierces through time and space, even if there's no matter for the sound to travel through. This thing breaks so many laws of physics.

name: Sentry Gun
description: This marvel of engineering uses advanced motion sensors to detect any nearby enemies and rain down a hail of bullets onto them. Just be careful not to stand in front of it...

name: Nintendium Laptop
description: This laptop is made with Nintendium, making it nigh indestructible. It also has every single Nintendo game ever made on it. Yes, all of the Nintendo games. All of them.

name: Vrisktoria\'s Serket
description: The underwear of choice for a certain troll. If she knew that you had these, she'd br8k your neck.

name: Apostrophe Apocalypse "End of Time and Space"
description: A spellcard that first uses a brightly flashing beam of apostrophes to shatter reality itself around your enemies and then blasts the shards at them. The long-term consequences of this can't possibly be good for your session, but hey, it does a great job at wrecking just about anything you declare it against.

name: The Bacon Monarch
description: This chair was sat on by the ruler of a kingdom of bacon. He claimed it and the crown after killing the previous emperor, who was a huge jerk. How did he kill him? He ate him, of course.

name: Twilight Thug\'s Katana Plush
description: It's a plush pillow in the shape of a Katana, on both sides there is a graphic of a jet black katana. While not capable of slicing, this is a deadly smothering weapon.

name: Invitation of the Unknown
description: This card is coloured in a dark, almost black, purple. If you open it, tentacles come out and grab whatever is in front of them, usually dragging them off to who knows where. But sometimes, they just seem to, well, kind of tickle the enemies. The end result of that isn't much better though...

name: Demonic Cow Voidskull
description: Yeah, because combining those two items was such a great idea. Enjoy freezing your enemies with this even more demonic skull while it lasts. Because, you know, there's pretty much no way a horrorterror isn't on its way to you.

name: Carved Bone Lance
description: A Lance made from an Extremely large bone. Slightly brittle, but it hurts to be pricked by it.

name: Flask of Twilight
description: The liquid inside of this flask seems to be an eerie glow, almost like the crest of dawn.

name: Hat of the Star Magician
description: A black magician hat with constellations drawn in white on it. It emanates a twinkling aura of star-like sparks. Whoever wears it will be given power over the stars.

name: Chekhov\'s Gun
description: Dear lord this rifle looks powerful - you bet it'll come in handy later. It only has a single bullet, though, and there doesn't seem to be any way to reload, so use it wisely.

name: Ahab\'s Octet
description: A set of eight octahedral dice, adorned with various nautical motifs. Said to have been used by the famous whaler himself when dicing in ports, until the constant laser blasts and summoning of miscellaneous aquatic wildlife really started to get on people's nerves.

name: Little Shop of Horrorterrors
description: This book contains a script for an extremely underrated play. It also has details on how to summon the monster in the play - "Audreythulu." Not to mention the fact that it has sheet music for all of the songs. Of course, you're only using it to hit people with, so none of that really matters.

name: 120-Volt Bansweeper
description: This broom-hammer-abomination contains enough raw electricity to silence an entire session, at least temporarily.

name: Teslascopic Laser
description: A small spyglass that shoots blasts of lightning and lasers wherever you look. Very effective as a weapon, but not so useful to look through...

name: LuNyx Crown
description: A crown showing just a modicum of the vast, infinite void. After a few seconds of staring at it, you're transfixed. You get a hold of yourself long enough to put the crown on your head.

name: Faygo - Squiddletastic Candy Corn Ascension flavour
description: This rainbowy drink is the liquified essence of sugary godhood, the nectar of the Imagination-brimming divine creatures. One sip and you'll burst with energy thanks to the godly power of... Squiddles.

name: Chocolate Chip Cookie
description: America's Favorite.

name: Cherry Blood Coca-Cola
description: A can of Coca-Cola with the added flavor of cherry. It also looks like blood! Pretend you're a vampire, just in time for Halloween! Oh wait, it's nowhere near Halloween. Hmm...

name: Club\'n Booty Briefs
description: Spandex form-fitting short shorts generously tossed with glitter.

name: DEEZ
description: NUTZ IN YO MOUTH-I DID IT WHILE YOU WERE NOT LOOKING ...... HENCE THE MYSERTY

name: Half-Eaten Imp Head
description: Ewww. Why'd you pick this up? And what's eating imps? You don't think you want to know.

name: Bi Bacon
description: A half sweet bubblegum and half cool blue raspberry flavored candy belt that tears easily in half, for when you like it both ways. Crocker Corp's Fruit By The Foot did something like this a while ago so be careful they don't sue you.

name: Helvetic Army Gunblades of Alchemical Energy
description: A pair of Swiss Army knives from before the Swiss Army (or Switzerland itself) was a thing yet appear free of aging, as if they leapt through time. Crackling with inexplicably high amounts of temporal energy, some knives have been replaced by guns which shoot bullets made out of a strange material that changes between lead and gold.

name: TY Teddy Hammer
description: This is adorable. You still probably DO NOT want to get hit in the head with this.

name: Maliwan\'s Slingularityshot
description: Maliwan Introduces a new weapon for all those slingshot enthusiasts. Tired of shooting bullets, well this slingshot fires miniature black holes that collapse upon impact! And of course, this Maliwan shooter still includes the elemental properties that make every Maliwan gun special.

name: Bugswatter
description: A flyswatter used to squash bugs. As in actual computer bugs, which have a bad habit of trying to eat your sylladex contents. They look a bit like moths for some reason.

name: UO\'s Shrine
description: A gathering of flowers, pictures, and and letters about someone apparently known as "Optimatum". The letters are praising and thanking him (her? or even it? you have no idea who this being is) for fixing problems with the universe. Whoever this Optimatum is, they must be powerful... and whoever made this shrine is pretty creepy.

name: Optimatum\'s De-bugger
description: A huge flyswatter with a constantly changing computer display at the end. What did it say there? "FTP connection established, uploading dungeons.php"? "UPDATE `Consort_Dialogue` SET `req_base` = 'yes' WHERE `ID` = 125"? Whatever all that means. The handle has the name Optimatum engraved in it.

name: Steel Violin
description: You feel like rocking out! ...however this violin is extremely impractical as an instrument. Oh well, at least you can smash imps with it.

name: Poor Drawing  of a Horse Attacking a Football Player
description: This complicated drawing of a horse jumping upon an athlete is formed of many large triangles, making it look like something out of a retro arcade game.

name: Midas\'s Die
description: A pair of golden dice that gleam splendidly, but also have an air of great danger... They are able to turn an enemy into gold, but it will never affect the user. How convenient.

name: Chocolaty Needlewands of Chance
description: Your trusty d20 Needlewands, except now they seem... substantially stickier... Okay, yeah, the d20s are covered in melted chocolate and this is gross, but you guess it's useful.

name: Silver Rocket Gauntlets of the Enforcer
description: These oversized silver gauntlets fire arrow-shaped enemy-seeking missiles from the palm that release a blast of kinetic force on impact. Guaranteed to annihilate the light, the dark, and anything in between.

name: Reality-Directing Baton
description: Small particles appear in the air around this baton as you swing it, and if you concentrate hard enough, you find you can change small things. Such as the location of imps. Muahahaha....

name: Midas\'s Die-Dropper
description: This heavy and peculiar bow is made of solid gold, and the arrows it fires are tipped with dice made of gold that is equally as solid. These arrows can turn an enemy into gold as well, assuming that the dice roll in your favor.

name: Spectral Grandfather Clock
description: This grandfather clock is a lot heavier than your usual wood clock, but at least it deals more damage now. It also emits a bright, radioactive glow.

name: Spandex-Covered Golden Axe
description: So someone covered your Granddad's prized golden axe in red and black spandex. As awesome as it looks, someones gonna be in trouble when he finds them...

name: Fission Hacker
description: Finally! An all-inclusive scythe, computer, and particle accelerator for all your slicing, surfing, and science needs!

name: Enigmatic Void Armor
description: This armor is nigh-intangible, fazing the swords, fire, and magicks of your enemies about you through some sort of enchantment. The plate and chain-mail is adorned with the symbol of the void aspect on the front, and an outer god on the back.

name: Shitty Fake Headstone
description: For those parsimoniously deceased.

name: Helm of Twilight
description: This armet emits a faint amount of twilight, illuminating a small area around you. It's pretty, but not very useful.

name: Blank Shitty God-Tier Shirt
description: Slowly but surely, piece by piece, your shitty God Tier shirt is coming together...

name: Sandy Cash Slammer
description: Looks like someone's punched out the hourglass and tried to stuff it with ludicrous amounts of money. I hope you like handling sandy wads of cash and broken glass!

name: Bag of Bribery
description: Who needs to fight when you can simply pay them all off.

name: Rubber Gloves
description: Keeps your hands from being dirty and from being electrocuted when handling wires.

name: Bear Bear Bun Buns
description: These strange buns are lightly dusted with flour, and have imprints in the shape of bear buns. Looks scrumptious!

name: How on Earth
description: Your atheneum isn't complete any more >:D

name: Appleture Science Jackniphone
description: You're on the cutting edge of portable communications tech now.

name: James Bonds
description: Named after B. S. James, who specialized in unusual atomic interactions and also pioneered the discovery of specibi tallying.

name: Rare Contraband
description: The rarest of all the contraband types. It can only be found in the deepest depths of the internet. In memory of CC

name: Some science bullshit
description: It's a steaming pile of radioactive waste. Radioactive bull waste.

name: THE OVERSEER PROJECT SYSTEM ALERT CODE
description:
>OBANABANOBANOBANOBANABON

>32vv1\se.itxt
